(108, 'da', 'from the same as (0181)', '\'ed', 'TWOT - 38d', 'ade', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «0181» (in the sense of enveloping); a fog:-- mist, vapor.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mist</OL>'),
(109, 'bda', 'a primitive root', '\'adab', 'TWOT - 24', 'aw-dab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to languish:--grieve.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to grieve, cause grief<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiph) to cause to grieve, to grieve, to cause grief</OL></OL>'),
(110, 'labda', 'probably from (0109) (in the sense of chastisement) and (0410)', '\'Adb\'el', 'None', 'ad-beh-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «0109» (in the sense of chastisement) and «0410»; disciplined of God; Adbeel, a son of Ishmael:--Adbeel.', 'Adbeel = \"chastened of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>third son of Ishmael and grandson of Abraham</OL>'),
(111, 'dda', 'probably an orthographical variation for (02301)', '\'Adad', 'None', 'ad-ad\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably an orthographical variation for «02301»; Adad (or Hadad), an Edomite:--Hadad.', 'Hadad = \"I shall move softly: I shall love\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Edomite enemy God raised up to punish Solomon for his sins</OL>'),
(112, 'wdda', 'of uncertain derivation', '\'Iddow', 'TWOT - 26e, 26f', 'id-do', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; Iddo, an Israelite:--Iddo.', 'Iddo = \"I will praise him\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a chief Israelite during resettlement</OL>'),
(113, '!wda', 'from an unused root (meaning to rule)', '\'adown', 'TWOT - 27b', 'aw-done\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (shortened) adon {aw-done\'}; from an unused root (meaning to rule); sovereign, i.e. controller (human or divine):-- lord, master, owner. Compare also names beginning with \"Adoni-\".', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>firm, strong, lord, master<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>lord, master<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>reference to men 1a</OL><LI>superintendent of household,of affairs 1a<LI>master 1a<LI>king<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>reference to God 1a</OL><LI>the Lord God 1a<LI>Lord of the whole earth<LI>lords, kings<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>reference to men 1b</OL><LI>proprietor of hill of Samaria 1b<LI>master 1b<LI>husband 1b<LI>prophet 1b<LI>governor 1b<LI>prince 1b<LI>king<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>reference to God 1b</OL><LI>Lord of lords (probably = \"thy husband, Yahweh\")<LI>my lord, my master<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>reference to men 1c</OL><LI>master 1c<LI>husband 1c<LI>prophet 1c<LI>prince 1c<LI>king 1c<LI>father 1c<LI>Moses 1c<LI>priest 1c<LI>theophanic angel 1c<LI>captain 1c<LI>general recognition of superiority<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>reference to God 1c</OL><LI>my Lord,my Lord and my God 1c<LI>Adonai (parallel with Yahweh)</OL></OL>'),
(114, '!wdda', 'probably intensive for (0113)', '\'Addown', 'None', 'ad-done\'', 'Adjective', 'probably intensive for «0113»; powerful; Addon, apparently an Israelite:--Addon.', 'Addon = \"powerful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Israelite?</OL>'),
(115, '~yrwda', 'dual from (0142) (in the sense of eminence)', '\'Adowrayim', 'None', 'ad-o-rah\'-yim', 'Proper Name Location', 'dual from «0142» (in the sense of eminence); double mound; Adorajim, a place in Palestine:--Adoraim.', 'Adoraim = \"double glory\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>city in Judah fortified by Rehoboam about 5 miles or 8 km SW of Hebron</OL>'),
(116, '!yda', 'of uncertain derivation', '\'edayin', 'TWOT - 2558', 'ed-ah\'-yin', 'Adverb', '(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; then (of time):--now, that time, then.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>then, afterwards, thereupon, from that time</OL>'),
(117, 'rydda', 'from (0142)', '\'addiyr', 'TWOT - 28b', 'ad-deer\'', 'Adjective', 'from «0142»; wide or (generally) large; figuratively, powerful:--excellent, famous, gallant, glorious, goodly, lordly, mighty(- ier one), noble, principal, worthy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>great, majestic<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of waters of sea<LI>of a tree<LI>of kings, nations, gods</OL><LI>great one, majestic one<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of nobles, chieftains, servants</OL></OL>'),
(118, 'aylda', 'of Persian derivation', '\'Adalya\'', 'None', 'ad-al-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of Persian derivation; Adalja, a son of Haman:--Adalia.', 'Adalia = \"I shall be drawn up of Jah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fifth son of Haman, executed at same time</OL>'),
(119, '~da', 'of unknown derivation', '\'adam', 'TWOT - 26b', 'aw-dam\'', 'Verb', 'to show blood (in the face), i.e. flush or turn rosy:--be (dyed, made) red (ruddy).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be red, red<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) ruddy (of Nazarites)<LI>(Pual)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be rubbed red<LI>dyed red<LI>reddened</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to show red<LI>to glare<LI>to emit (show) redness</OL><LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to redden<LI>to grow red<LI>to look red</OL></OL></OL>'),
(120, '~da', 'from (0119)', '\'adam', 'TWOT - 25a', 'aw-dawm\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «0119»; ruddy i.e. a human being (an individual or the species, mankind, etc.):--X  another, + hypocrite, + common sort, ×  low, man (mean, of low degree), person.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>man, mankind<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>man, human being<LI>man, mankind (much more frequently intended sense in OT)<LI>Adam, first man<LI>city in Jordan valley</OL></OL>'),
(121, '~da', 'the same as (0120)', '\'Adam', 'TWOT - 25a', 'aw-dawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «0120»; Adam the name of the first man, also of a place in Palestine:--Adam.', 'Adam = \"red\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>first man<LI>city in Jordan valley</OL>'),
(122, '~da', 'from (0119)', '\'adom', 'TWOT - 26b', 'aw-dome\'', 'Adjective', 'from «0119»; rosy:--red, ruddy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>red, ruddy (of man, horse, heifer, garment, water, lentils)</OL>'),
(123, '~da', 'from (0122)', '\'Edom', 'TWOT - 26e', 'ed-ome\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or (fully) oEdowm {ed-ome\'}; from «0122»; red (see Gen. 25:25); Edom, the elder twin-brother of Jacob; hence the region (Idumaea) occupied by him:--Edom, Edomites, Idumea.', 'Edom = \"red\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Edom<LI>Edomite, Idumean - descendants of Esau<LI>land of Edom, Idumea - land south and south east of Palestine</OL>'),
(124, '~da', 'from (0119)', '\'odem', 'TWOT - 26c', 'o\'-dem', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «0119»; redness, i.e. the ruby, garnet, or some other red gem:--sardius.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ruby, carnelian (redness)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>precious stone</OL></OL>'),
(125, '~dmda', 'reduplicated from (0119)', '\'adamdam', 'TWOT - 26g', 'ad-am-dawm\'', 'Adjective', 'reduplicated from «0119»; reddish:--(somewhat) reddish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>reddish, be reddish</OL>'),
(126, 'hmda', 'contracted for (0127)', '\'Admah', 'None', 'ad-maw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'contracted for «0127»; earthy; Admah, a place near the Dead Sea:--Admah.', 'Admah = \"red earth\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>city in the Siddim valley</OL>'),
(127, 'hmda', 'from (0119)', '\'adamah', 'TWOT - 25b', 'ad-aw-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «0119»; soil (from its general redness):--country, earth, ground, husband(-man) (-ry), land.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ground, land<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>ground (as general, tilled, yielding sustenance)<LI>piece of ground, a specific plot of land<LI>earth substance (for building or constructing)<LI>ground as earth\'s visible surface<LI>land, territory, country<LI>whole inhabited earth<LI>city in Naphtali</OL></OL>'),
(128, 'hmda', 'the same as (0127)', '\'Adamah', 'None', 'ad-aw-maw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «0127»; Adamah, a place in Palestine:--Adamah.', 'Adamah = \"the earth\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>city in Naphtali</OL>'),
(129, 'ymda', 'from (0127)', '\'Adamiy', 'TWOT - 26f', 'ad-aw-mee\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «0127»; earthy; Adami, a place in Palestine:--Adami.', 'Adami = \"man of Adar\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a pass or fortified place in Naphtali</OL>'),
(130, 'ymda', 'patronymic from (0123)', '\'Edomiy', 'None', 'ed-o-mee\'', 'Adjective', 'or (fully) aEdowmiy {ed-o-mee\'}; patronymic from «0123»; an Edomite, or descendants from (or inhabitants of) Edom:--Edomite. See «0726».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Edomite</OL>'),
