(981, 'atb', 'a primitive root', 'bata\'', 'TWOT - 232', 'baw-taw\'', 'Verb', 'or batah {baw-taw\'}; a primitive root; to babble; hence, to vociferate angrily:--pronounce, speak (unadvisedly).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to speak rashly or angrily, speak thoughtlessly<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) one that babbles, speaks rashly (part.)<LI>(Piel) to speak rashly, unadvisedly</OL></OL>'),
(982, 'xtb', 'a primitive root', 'batach', 'TWOT - 233', 'baw-takh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to hie for refuge (but not so precipitately as «02620»); figuratively, to trust, be confident or sure:--be bold (confident, secure, sure), careless (one, woman), put confidence, (make to) hope, (put, make to) trust.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to trust<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to trust, trust in<LI>to have confidence, be confident<LI>to be bold<LI>to be secure</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to trust, make secure</OL></OL><LI>(TWOT) to feel safe, be careless</OL>'),
(983, 'xtb', 'from (0982)', 'betach', 'TWOT - 233a', 'beh\'takh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «0982»; properly, a place of refuge; abstract, safety, both the fact (security) and the feeling (trust); often (adverb with or without preposition) safely:--assurance, boldly, (without) care(- less), confidence, hope, safe(-ly, -ty), secure, surely.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>security, safety adv<LI>securely</OL>'),
