(990, '!tb', 'from an unused root probably meaning to be hollow', 'beten', 'TWOT - 236a', 'beh\'-ten', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to be hollow; the belly, especially the womb; also the bosom or body of anything:-- belly, body, + as they be born, + within, womb.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>belly, womb, body<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>belly, abdomen<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>as seat of hunger<LI>as seat of mental faculties<LI>of depth of Sheol (fig.)</OL><LI>womb</OL></OL>'),
