(1004, 'tyb', 'probably from (01129) abbreviated', 'bayith', 'TWOT - 241', 'bah\'-yith', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from «01129» abbreviated; a house (in the greatest variation of applications, especially family, etc.):--court, daughter, door, + dungeon, family, + forth of, × great as would contain, hangings, home(born), (winter)house(-hold), inside(-ward), palace, place, + prison, + steward, + tablet, temple, web, + within(-out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>house<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>house, dwelling habitation<LI>shelter or abode of animals<LI>human bodies (fig.)<LI>of Sheol<LI>of abode of light and darkness<LI>of land of Ephraim</OL><LI>place<LI>receptacle<LI>home, house as containing a family<LI>household, family<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>those belonging to the same household<LI>family of descendants, descendants as organized body</OL><LI>household affairs<LI>inwards (metaph.)<LI>(TWOT) temple adv<LI>on the inside prep<LI>within</OL>'),
