(1085, 'ddlb', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Bildad', 'None', 'bil-dad\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; Bildad, one of Job\'s friends:--Bildad.', 'Bildad = \"confusing (by mingling) love\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the second friend of Job</OL>'),
(1086, 'hlb', 'a primitive root', 'balah', 'TWOT - 246', 'baw-law\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to fail; by implication to wear out, decay (causatively, consume, spend):--consume, enjoy long, become (make, wax) old, spend, waste.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wear out, become old<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to wear out<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wear out<LI>to wear out by use, use up completely<LI>to enjoy, use to the full</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1087, 'hlb', 'from (01086)', 'baleh', 'TWOT - 246a', 'baw-leh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «01086»; worn out:--old.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>worn out, old</OL>'),
(1088, 'hlb', 'feminine of (01087)', 'Balah', 'None', 'baw-law\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'feminine of «01087»; failure; Balah, a place in Palestine:--Balah.', 'Balah = \"waxed old\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in Simeon</OL>'),
(1089, 'hhlb', 'a primitive root [rather by transposition for (0926)]', 'balahh', 'TWOT - 247', 'baw-lah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (rather by transposition for «0926»); to palpitate; hence, (causatively) to terrify:--trouble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to trouble</OL>'),
(1090, 'hhlb', 'from (01089)', 'Bilhah', 'None', 'bil-haw\'', '', 'from «01089»; timid; Bilhah, the name of one of Jacob\'s concubines; also of a place in Palestine:--Bilhah.', 'Bilhah = \"troubled\" n pr f<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Rachel\'s handmaid whom she gave to Jacob as a concubine, mother to two of Jacob\'s children, Dan and Naphtali n pr loc<LI>a city in Simeon</OL>'),
(1091, 'hhllb', 'from (01089)', 'ballahah', 'TWOT - 247a', 'bal-law-haw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01089»; alarm; hence, destruction:--terror, trouble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>terror, destruction, calamity, dreadful event</OL>'),
(1092, '!hlb', 'from (01089)', 'Bilhan', 'None', 'bil-hawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01089»; timid; Bilhan, the name of an Edomite and of an Israelite:--Bilhan.', 'Bilhan = \"their decrepitude\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Esau<LI>a Benjamite</OL>'),
(1093, 'wlb', 'from a root corresponding to (01086)', 'blow', 'TWOT - 2632', 'bel-o\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «01086»; excise (on articles consumed):--tribute.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>tribute</OL>'),
(1094, 'awlb', 'from (01086)', 'blow\'', 'TWOT - 246b', 'bel-o\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (fully) blowy {bel-o\'ee}; from «01086»; (only in plural construction) rags:--old.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>worn out things, rags</OL>'),
(1095, 'rccaXtlb', 'of foreign derivation', 'Beltsha\'tstsar', 'None', 'bale-tesh-ats-tsar\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign derivation; Belteshatstsar, the Babylonian name of Daniel:--Belteshazzar.', 'Belteshazzar = \"lord of the straitened\'s treasure\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 4th of the greater prophets, taken as hostage in the first deportation to Babylon; because of the gift of God of the interpretation of dreams, he became the 2nd in command of the Babylon empire and lasted through the end of the Babylonian empire and into the Persian empire. His prophecies are the key to the understanding of end time events. Noted for his purity and holiness by contemporary prophet, Ezekiel<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also, \'Daniel\' (01840 or 01841)</OL></OL>'),
(1096, 'rccaXtlb', 'from a root corresponding to (01095)', 'Beltsha\'tstsar', 'None', 'bale-tesh-ats-tsar\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01095»:--Belteshazzar.', 'Belteshazzar = \"lord of the straitened\'s treasure\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 4th of the greater prophets, taken as hostage in the first deportation to Babylon; because of the gift of God of the interpretation of dreams, he became the 2nd in command of the Babylon empire and lasted through the end of the Babylonian empire and into the Persian empire. His prophecies are the key to the understanding of end time events. Noted for his purity and holiness by contemporary prophet, Ezekiel<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also, \'Daniel\' (01840 or 01841)</OL></OL>'),
(1097, 'ylb', 'from (01086)', 'bliy', 'TWOT - 246e', 'bel-ee\'', '', 'from «01086»; properly, failure, i.e. nothing or destruction; usually (with preposition) without, not yet, because not, as long as, etc.:--corruption, ig(norantly), for lack of, where no...is, so that no, none, not, un(awares), without.', 'subst<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wearing out adv of negation<LI>without, no, not</OL>'),
(1098, 'lylb', 'from (01101)', 'bliyl', 'TWOT - 248a', 'bel-eel\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01101»; mixed, i.e. (specifically) feed (for cattle):--corn, fodder, provender.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fodder</OL>'),
(1099, 'hmylb', 'from (01097) and (04100)', 'bliymah', 'TWOT - 246f', 'bel-ee-mah\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01097» and «04100»; (as indef.) nothing whatever:--nothing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nothingness</OL>'),
(1100, 'l[ylb', 'from (01097) and (03276)', 'bliya`al', 'TWOT - 246g', 'bel-e-yah\'-al', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01097» and «03276»; without profit, worthlessness; by extension, destruction, wickedness (often in connection with «0376», «0802», «01121», etc.):--Belial, evil, naughty, ungodly (men), wicked.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>worthlessness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>worthless, good for nothing, unprofitable, base fellow<LI>wicked<LI>ruin, destruction (construct)</OL></OL>'),
(1101, 'llb', 'a primitive root', 'balal', 'TWOT - 248', 'baw-lal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to overflow (specifically with oil.); by implication, to mix; also (denominatively from «01098») to fodder:--anoint, confound, × fade, mingle, mix (self), give provender, temper.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to mix, mingle, confuse, confound<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to mingle, confuse<LI>to mix<LI>to give provender, feed (animals)</OL><LI>(Hithpoel) to mix oneself (among others)<LI>(Hiphil) to fade away</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(1102, '~lb', 'a primitive root', 'balam', 'TWOT - 249', 'baw-lam\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to muzzle:--be held in.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to curb, hold in, restrain</OL>'),
(1103, 'olb', 'a primitive root', 'balac', 'TWOT - 250', 'baw-las\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pinch sycamore figs (a process necessary to ripen them):--gatherer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to gather figs, tend sycamore trees</OL>'),
(1104, '[lb', 'a primitive root', 'bala`', 'TWOT - 251', 'baw-lah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to make away with (specifically by swallowing); generally, to destroy:--cover, destroy, devour, eat up, be at end, spend up, swallow down (up).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to swallow down, swallow up, engulf, eat up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to swallow down<LI>to swallow up, engulf</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be swallowed up<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to swallow<LI>to swallow up, engulf<LI>squandering (fig.)</OL><LI>(Pual) to be swallowed up<LI>(Hithpael) to be ended</OL></OL>'),
(1105, '[lb', 'from (01104)', 'bela`', 'TWOT - 251a', 'beh\'-lah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01104»; a gulp; figuratively, destruction:--devouring, that which he hath swallowed up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a swallowing, devouring (fig. for ruin)<LI>a thing swallowed</OL>'),
(1106, '[lb', 'the same as (01105)', 'Bela`', 'None', 'beh\'-lah', '', 'the same as «01105»; Bela, the name of a place, also of an Edomite and of two Israelites:--Bela.', 'Bela = \"destruction\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a king of Edom<LI>first son of Benjamin<LI>a son of Ahaz, a Reubenite n pr loc<LI>one of the five cities of the plain which was spared at the intercession of Lot, and received the name of Zoar</OL>'),
(1107, 'yd[lb', 'constructive pl. from (01077) and (05703)', 'bil`adey', 'TWOT - 246h', 'bil-ad-ay\'', '', 'or balmadey {bal-ad-ay\'}; constructive plural from «01077» and «05703», not till, i.e. (as preposition or adverb) except, without, besides:--beside, not (in), save, without.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>apart from, except, without, besides</OL>'),
(1108, 'y[lb', 'patronymically from (01106)', 'Bal`iy', 'None', 'bel-ee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from «01106»: a Belaite (collectively) or descendants of Bela:--Belaites.', 'Belaites = \"swallowing\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Bela</OL>'),
(1109, '~[lb', 'probably from (01077) and (05971)', 'Bil`am', 'TWOT - 251b', 'bil-awm\'', '', 'probably from «01077» and «05971»; not (of the) people, i.e. foreigner; Bilam, a Mesopotamian prophet; also a place in Palestine:--Balaam, Bileam.', 'Balaam = \"not of the people\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of Beor, a man endowed with the gift of prophecy n pr loc<LI>a town in Manasseh</OL>'),
(1110, 'qlb', 'a primitive root', 'balaq', 'TWOT - 252', 'baw-lak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to annihilate:--(make) waste.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to waste, lay waste, devastate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Poel) to make waste<LI>(Pual) devastated (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(1111, 'qlb', 'from (01110)', 'Balaq', 'None', 'baw-lawk\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01110»; waster; Balak, a Moabitish king:--Balak.', 'Balak = \"devastator\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a king of Moab who hired Balaam to curse Israel</OL>'),
(1112, 'rccaXlb', 'of foreign origin (compare (01095))', 'Belsha\'tstsar', 'None', 'bale-shats-tsar\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Belshatstsar {bale-shats-tsar\'}; of foreign origin (compare «01095»); Belshatstsar, a Babylonian king:--Belshazzar.', 'Belshazzar = \"Bel protect the king\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>king of Babylon at the time of its fall; he to whom Daniel interpreted the writing on the wall</OL>'),
(1113, 'rccaXlb', 'corresponding to (01112)', 'Belsha\'tstsar', 'None', 'bale-shats-tsar\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01112»:--Belshazzar.', 'Belshazzar = \"Bel protect the king\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>king of Babylon at the time of its fall; he to whom Daniel interpreted the writing on the wall</OL>'),
(1114, '!Xlb', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Bilshan', 'None', 'bil-shawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; Bilshan, an Israelite:--Bilshan.', 'Bilshan = \"in slander\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an exile who returned with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(1115, 'ytlb', 'constructive fem. of (01086) (equivalent to (01097))', 'biltiy', 'TWOT - 246i', 'bil-tee\'', '', 'constructive feminine of «01086» (equivalent to «01097»); properly, a failure of, i.e. (used only as a negative particle, usually with a prepositional prefix) not, except, without, unless, besides, because not, until, etc.:--because un(satiable), beside, but, + continual, except, from, lest, neither, no more, none, not, nothing, save, that no, without.', 'subst<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>not, except adv<LI>not<LI>except (after preceding negation) conj<LI>except (after an implied or expressed negation) with prep<LI>so as not, in order not<LI>an account of not, because...not<LI>until not</OL>'),
(1116, 'hmb', 'from an unused root (meaning to be high)', 'bamah', 'TWOT - 253', 'bam-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root (meaning to be high); an elevation:--height, high place, wave.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>high place, ridge, height, bamah (technical name for cultic platform)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>high place, mountain<LI>high places, battlefields<LI>high places (as places of worship)<LI>funeral mound?</OL></OL>'),
(1117, 'hmb', 'the same as (01116), See also (01120)', 'Bamah', 'None', 'baw-maw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «01116»; Bamah, a place in Palestine:--Bamah. See also «01120».', 'Bamah = \"high place\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in Palestine (of places of idolatrous worship)</OL>'),
(1118, 'lhmb', 'probably from (04107) with prepositional prefix', 'Bimhal', 'None', 'bim-hawl\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «04107» with prepositional prefix; with pruning; Bimhal, an Israelite:--Bimhal.', 'Bimhal = \"in circumcision: in weakness (by mixture)\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Asher</OL>'),
(1119, 'wmb', 'prolongation for prepositional prefix', 'bmow', 'TWOT - 193', 'bem-o\'', 'Preposition', 'prolongation for prepositional prefix; in, with, by, etc.:--for, in into, through.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in, at, by</OL>'),
(1120, 'twmb', 'plural of (01116)', 'Bamowth', 'None', 'baw-moth\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'plural of «01116»; heights; or (fully) Bamowth Bahal {baw-moth\' bah\'-al}; from the same and «01168»; heights of Baal; Bamoth or Bamoth-Baal, a place East of the Jordan:--Bamoth, Bamoth-baal.', 'Bamoth = \"high places\" or \"great high place\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town on the river Arnon in Moab</OL>'),
(1121, '!b', 'from (01129)', 'ben', 'TWOT - 254', 'bane', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01129»; a son (as a builder of the family name), in the widest sense (of literal and figurative relationship, including grandson, subject, nation, quality or condition, etc., (like «01», «0251», etc.)):--+ afflicted, age, (Ahoh-) (Ammon-) (Hachmon-) (Lev-)ite, (anoint-)ed one, appointed to, (+) arrow, (Assyr-) (Babylon-) (Egypt-) (Grec-)ian, one born, bough, branch, breed, + (young) bullock, + (young) calf, ×  came up in, child, colt, × common, × corn, daughter, × of first, + firstborn, foal, + very fruitful, + postage, × in, + kid, + lamb, (+) man, meet, + mighty, + nephew, old, (+) people, + rebel, + robber, × servant born, × soldier, son, + spark, + steward, + stranger, × surely, them of, + tumultuous one, + valiant(-est), whelp, worthy, young (one), youth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son, grandson, child, member of a group<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>son, male child<LI>grandson<LI>children (pl. - male and female)<LI>youth, young men (pl.)<LI>young (of animals)<LI>sons (as characterisation, i.e. sons of injustice [for un- righteous men] or sons of God [for angels]<LI>people (of a nation) (pl.)<LI>of lifeless things, i.e. sparks, stars, arrows (fig.)<LI>a member of a guild, order, class</OL></OL>'),
(1122, '!b', 'the same as (01121)', 'Ben', 'None', 'bane', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «01121»; Ben, an Israelite:--Ben.', 'Ben = \"son\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite, one of the porters appointed by David for the ark</OL>'),
(1123, '!b', 'corresponding to (01121)', 'ben', 'TWOT - 2639', 'bane', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01121»:--child, son, young.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son, child</OL>'),
(1124, 'anb', 'corresponding to (01129)', 'bna\'', 'TWOT - 2633', 'ben-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) or bnah (Aramaic) {ben-aw\'}; corresponding to «01129»; to build:--build, make.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to build<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to build<LI>(Ithp\'il) to be built</OL></OL>'),
(1125, 'bdnybanb', 'from (01121) and (040)', 'Ben-\'Abiynadab', 'None', 'ben-ab-ee\'\'-naw-dawb\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01121» and «040»; (the) son of Abinadab; Ben-Abinadab, an Israelite:--the son of Abinadab.', 'Ben-Abinadab = \"son of Abinadab\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an officer of Solomon</OL>'),
(1126, 'ynwanb', 'from (01121) and (0205)', 'Ben-\'Owniy', 'None', 'ben-o-nee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01121» and «0205»; son of my sorrow; Ben-Oni, the original name of Benjamin:--Ben-oni.', 'Ben-oni = \"son of my sorrow\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the name given to Benjamin by Rachel</OL>'),
(1127, 'rbgnb', 'from (01121) and (01397)', 'Ben-Geber', 'None', 'ben-gheh\'-ber', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01121» and «01397»; son of (the) hero; Ben- Geber, an Israelite:--the son of Geber.', 'Ben-geber = \"the son of Geber\" or \"the son of a man\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an officer of Solomon</OL>'),
(1128, 'rqdnb', 'from (01121) and a derivative of (01856)', 'Ben-Deqer', 'None', 'ben-deh\'-ker', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01121» and a derivative of «01856»; son of piercing (or of a lance); Ben-Deker, an Israelite:--the son of Dekar.', 'Ben-dekar = \"son of stabbing\" or \"son of Dekar\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an officer of Solomon</OL>'),
(1129, 'hnb', 'a primitive root', 'banah', 'TWOT - 255', 'baw-naw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to build (literally and figuratively):--(begin to) build(-er), obtain children, make, repair, set (up), × surely.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to build, rebuild, establish, cause to continue<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to build, rebuild<LI>to build a house (ie, establish a family)</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be built<LI>to be rebuilt<LI>established (of restored exiles) (fig.)<LI>established (made permanent)<LI>to be built up (of childless wife becoming the mother of a family through the children of a concubine)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1130, 'ddhnb', 'from (01121) and (01908)', 'Ben-Hadad', 'None', 'ben-had-ad\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01121» and «01908»; son of Hadad; Ben-Hadad, the name of several Syrian kings:--Ben-hadad.', 'Ben-hadad = \"son of [the false god] Hadad\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the king of Syria, contemporary with Asa of Judah<LI>the son of Hazael, also king of Syria</OL>'),
(1131, 'ywnnb', 'from (01129)', 'Binnuwy', 'None', 'bin-noo\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01129»; built up; Binnui, an Israelite:--Binnui.', 'Binnui = \"built up\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an exile returnee with Zerubbabel, son of Henadad, who assisted at the reparation of the wall of Jerusalem, under Nehemiah<LI>a Levite in time of Ezra, father of Noadiah<LI>another Levite in time of Ezra, who took a foreign wife<LI>still another Levite in time of Ezra, who took a foreign wife</OL>'),
(1132, 'txwznb', 'from (01121) and (02105)', 'Ben-Zowcheth', 'None', 'ben-zo-khayth\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01121» and «02105»; son of Zocheth; Ben- Zocheth, an Israelite:--Ben-zoketh.', 'Ben-zoheth = \"son of Zoheth\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the tribe of Judah</OL>'),
(1133, 'rwxnb', 'from (01121) and (02354)', 'Ben-Chuwr', 'None', 'ben-khoor\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01121» and «02354»; son of Chur; Ben-Chur, an Israelite:--the son of Hur.', 'Ben-hur = \"son of whiteness\" or \"son of Chur\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a man who was commissariat officer for Solomon in Mount Ephraim</OL>'),
(1134, 'lyxnb', 'from (01121) and (02428)', 'Ben-Chayil', 'None', 'ben-khah\'-yil', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01121» and «02428»; son of might; Ben-Chail, an Israelite:--Ben-hail.', 'Ben-hail = \"son of strength\" or \"son (man) of might\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a ruler (prince) under Jehoshaphat</OL>'),
(1135, '!nxnb', 'from (01121) and (02605)', 'Ben-Chanan', 'None', 'ben-khaw-nawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01121» and «02605»; son of Chanan; Ben- Chanan, an Israelite:--Ben-hanan.', 'Ben-hanan = \"son of favour\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the tribe of Judah</OL>'),
(1136, 'doxnb', 'from (01121) and (02617)', 'Ben-Checed', 'None', 'ben-kheh\'-sed', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01121» and «02617»; son of kindness; Ben- Chesed, an Israelite:--the son of Hesed.', 'Ben-hesed = \"son of mercy\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an officer of Solomon</OL>'),
(1137, 'ynb', 'from (01129)', 'Baniy', 'None', 'baw-nee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01129»; built; Bani, the name of five Israelites:--Bani.', 'Bani = \"built\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Gadite, one of David\'s mighty warriors<LI>a Levite of the line of Merari, and forefather to Ethan<LI>a man of Judah of the line of Pharez<LI>\"children of Bani\" returned from captivity with Zerubbabel<LI>one or up to three Levites in Nehemiah\'s time</OL>'),
(1138, 'ynnb', 'from (01129)', 'Bunniy', 'None', 'boon-nee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or (fuller) Buwniy {boo-nee\'}; from «01129»; built; Bunni or Buni, an Israelite:--Bunni.', 'Bunni = \"built\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite in the time of Nehemiah<LI>another Levite of earlier date</OL>'),
(1139, 'qrbynb', 'from the plural construction of (01121) and (01300)', 'Bney-Braq', 'None', 'ben-ay\'-ber-ak\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the plural construction of «01121» and «01300»; sons of lightning, Bene-berak, a place in Palestine:--Bene-barak.', 'Bene-barak = \"sons of lightning\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in Dan</OL>'),
(1140, 'hynb', 'from (01129)', 'binyah', 'TWOT - 255a', 'bin-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from «01129»; a structure:--building.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>structure, building</OL>'),
(1141, 'hynb', 'from (01129) and (03050)', 'Bnayah', 'None', 'ben-aw-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or (prolonged) Bnayahuw {ben-aw-yaw\'-hoo}; from «01129» and «03050»; Jah has built; Benajah, the name of twelve Israelites:-- Benaiah.', 'Benaiah = \"Jehovah has built\" or \"Yahweh has built up\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of David\'s mighty warriors, son of Jehoiada the chief priest, a Levite, set by David over his bodyguard, later having remained faithful to Solomon during Adonijah\'s attempt on the crown, was raised into the place of Joab as commander-in-chief of the army<LI>the Pirathonite, an Ephraimite, one of David\'s thirty mighty warriors, and the captain of the eleventh monthly course<LI>a Simeonite, a prince of the families of Simeon<LI>a Levite in the time of David who played with a psaltery on Alamoth<LI>a priest in the time of David, appointed to blow the trumpet before the ark<LI>a Levite of the sons of Asaph<LI>a Levite in the time of Hezekiah<LI>Four Israelites in the time of Ezra who had taken strange wives<LI>the father of Pelatiah</OL>'),
(1142, '!q[y ynb', 'from the plural of (01121) and (03292)', 'Bney', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the plural of «01121» and «03292»; sons of Yaakan; Bene-Jaakan, a place in the Desert:--Bene-jaakan.', 'Bene-jaakan = \"sons of twisting\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Israelite place of encampment in the wilderness (same as 0885)</OL>'),
(1143, '~ynb', 'dual of (0996)', 'benayim', 'TWOT - 239a', 'bay-nah\'-yim', '', 'dual of «0996»; a double interval, i.e. the space between two armies:--+ champion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>between, space between two armies<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>man of the space between armies, i.e. champion (of Goliath) (meton)</OL></OL>'),
(1144, '!ymynb', 'from (01121) and (03225)', 'Binyamiyn', 'TWOT - 254a', 'bin-yaw-mene\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01121» and «03225»; son of (the) right hand; Binjamin, youngest son of Jacob; also the tribe descended from him, and its territory:--Benjamin.', 'Benjamin = \"son of the right hand\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Jacob\'s and Rachel\'s youngest son, Joseph\'s full brother<LI>son of Bilhan, great-grandson of Benjamin<LI>a Benjamite, one of the sons of Harim, in the time of Ezra who had taken a strange wife<LI>the tribe descended from Benjamin, the son of Jacob</OL>'),
