(1204, 't[b', 'a primitive root', 'ba`ath', 'TWOT - 265', 'baw-ath\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to fear:--affright, be (make) afraid, terrify, trouble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to terrify, startle, fall upon, dismay, be overtaken by sudden terror<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be terrified<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fall upon, overwhelm<LI>to terrify</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1205, 'ht[b', 'from (01204)', 'b`athah', 'TWOT - 265a', 'beh-aw-thaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01204»; fear:--trouble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>terror, dismay</OL>'),
(1206, '#b', 'probably the same as (0948)', 'bots', 'TWOT - 268a', 'botse', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably the same as «0948»; mud (as whitish clay):--mire.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mire</OL>'),
(1207, 'hccb', 'intensive from (01206)', 'bitstsah', 'TWOT - 268b', 'bits-tsaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'intensive from «01206»; a swamp:--fen, mire(-ry place).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>swamp, marsh</OL>'),
(1208, 'arwcb', 'from (01219)', 'batsowr\'', 'TWOT - 270f', 'baw-tsore\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01219»; inaccessible, i.e. lofty:--vintage (by confusion with «01210»).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vintage<LI>(CLBL) inaccessible</OL>'),
(1209, 'ycb', 'perhaps the same as (01153)', 'Betsay', 'None', 'bay-tsah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'perhaps the same as «01153»; Betsai, the name of two Israelites:--Bezai.', 'Bezai = \"conqueror\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a chief of the returning exiles in the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(1210, 'rycb', 'from (01219)', 'batsiyr', 'TWOT - 270f', 'baw-tseer\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01219»; clipped, i.e. the grape crop:--vintage.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vintage</OL>'),
(1211, 'lcb', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to peel', 'btsel', 'TWOT - 266a', 'beh\'-tsel', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to peel; an onion:--onion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>onion</OL>'),
(1212, 'lalcb', 'probably from (06738) and (0410) with a prepositional prefix', 'Btsal\'el', 'None', 'bets-al-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «06738» and «0410» with a prepositional prefix; in (the) shadow (i.e. protection) of God; Betsalel, the name of two Israelites:--Bezaleel.', 'Bezaleel = \"in the shadow (i.e. protection) of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Uri and grandson of Hur; a skilled Judahite artisan in all works of metal, wood, and stone and one of the architects of the tabernacle<LI>an Israelite, one of the sons of Pahath-moab, in the time of Ezra who had taken a strange wife</OL>'),
(1213, 'twlcb', 'from the same as (01211)', 'Batsluwth', 'None', 'bats-looth\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Batsliyth {bats-leeth\'}; from the same as «01211»; a peeling; Batsluth or Batslith, an Israelite:--Bazlith, Bazluth.', 'Bazlith or Bazluth = \"asking\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a head of a family of exiles returning with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(1214, '[cb', 'a primitive root', 'batsa`', 'TWOT - 267', 'baw-tsah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root to break off, i.e. (usually) plunder; figuratively, to finish, or (intransitively) stop:--(be) covet(- ous), cut (off), finish, fulfill, gain (greedily), get, be given to (covetousness), greedy, perform, be wounded.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut off, break off, gain by unrighteous violence, get, finish, be covetous, be greedy<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut off<LI>to stop<LI>to gain wrongfully or by violence</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut off, sever<LI>to finish, complete, accomplish<LI>to violently make gain of</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1215, '[cb', 'from (01214)', 'betsa`', 'TWOT - 267a', 'beh\'-tsah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01214»; plunder; by extension, gain (usually unjust):--covetousness, (dishonest) gain, lucre, profit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>profit, unjust gain, gain (profit) acquired by violence</OL>'),
(1216, 'qcb', 'a primitive root', 'batseq', 'TWOT - 269', 'baw-tsake\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; perhaps to swell up, i.e. blister:--swell.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to swell, become blistered</OL>'),
(1217, 'qcb', 'from (01216)', 'batseq', 'TWOT - 269a', 'baw-tsake\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01216»; dough (as swelling by fermentation):--dough, flour.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dough (unleavened)</OL>'),
(1218, 'tqcb', 'from (01216)', 'Botsqath', 'None', 'bots-cath\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «01216»; a swell of ground; Botscath, a place in Palestine:--Bozcath, Boskath.', 'Bozkath or Boscath = \"rocky height\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in Judah in the lowlands toward the Philistines, home of Josiah\'s mother</OL>'),
(1219, 'rcb', 'a primitive root', 'batsar', 'TWOT - 270', 'baw-tsar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to clip off; specifically (as denominative from «01210») to gather grapes; also to be isolated (i.e. inaccessible by height or fortification):--cut off, (de-)fenced, fortify, (grape) gather(-er), mighty things, restrain, strong, wall (up), withhold.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to gather, restrain, fence, fortify, make inaccessible, enclose<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut off<LI>fortified, cut off, made inaccessible (pass participle)<LI>secrets, mysteries, inaccessible things (subst)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be withheld<LI>(Piel) to fortify</OL></OL>'),
(1220, 'rcb', 'from (01219)', 'betser', 'TWOT - 270a', 'beh\'-tser', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01219»; strictly a clipping, i.e. gold (as dug out):--gold defence.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gold, precious ore, ring-gold</OL>'),
(1221, 'rcb', 'the same as (01220)', 'Betser', 'None', 'beh\'-tser', '', 'the same as «01220», an inaccessible spot; Betser, a place in Palestine; also an Israelite:--Bezer.', 'Bezer = \"gold ore\" or \"remote fortress\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Zophah, one of the heads of the houses of Asher n pr loc<LI>a city of refuge in Reuben in the downs on the east of the Jordan</OL>'),
(1222, 'rcb', 'another form for (01220)', 'btsar', 'TWOT - 270a', 'bets-ar\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'another form for «01220»; gold:--gold.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>precious ore, gold, ring-gold</OL>'),
(1223, 'hrcb', 'from (01219)', 'botsrah', 'TWOT - 270b', 'bots-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from «01219»; an enclosure, i.e. sheep fold:--Bozrah.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>enclosure, fold, sheepfold (AV - Bozrah)</OL>'),
(1224, 'hrcb', 'the same as (01223)', 'Botsrah', 'None', 'bots-raw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «01223»; Botsrah, a place in Edom:--Bozrah.', 'Bozrah = \"sheepfold\" or \"fortress\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Edom<LI>a town in Moab</OL>'),
(1225, '!wrccb', 'intensive from (01219)', 'bitstsarown', 'TWOT - 270c', 'bits-tsaw-rone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'masculine intensive from «01219»; a fortress:--stronghold.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stronghold</OL>'),
(1226, 'trccb', 'intensive from (01219)', 'batstsoreth', 'TWOT - 270d', 'bats-tso\'-reth', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine intensive from «01219»; restraint (of rain), i.e. drought:--dearth, drought.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dearth, drought, destitution</OL>'),
(1227, 'qwbqb', 'the same as (01228)', 'Baqbuwq', 'None', 'bak-book\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «01228»; Bakbuk, one of the Nethinim:--Bakbuk.', 'Bakbuk = \"bottle\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a head of a family of temple-slaves returning from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(1228, '$bqb', 'from (01238)', 'baqbuk', 'TWOT - 273a', 'bak-book\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01238»; a bottle (from the gurgling in emptying):--bottle, cruse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flask, bottle</OL>'),
(1229, 'hykbqb', 'from (01228) and (03050)', 'Baqbukyah', 'None', 'bak-book-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01228» and «03050»; emptying (i.e. wasting) of Jah; Bakbukjah, an Israelite:--Bakbukiah.', 'Bakbukiah = \"wasting of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite in the time of Nehemiah</OL>'),
(1230, 'rqqbqb', 'reduplicated from (01239)', 'Baqbaqqar', 'None', 'bak-bak-kar\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'reduplicated from «01239»; searcher; Bakbakkar, an Israelite:--Bakbakkar.', 'Bakbakkar = \"searcher\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite, apparently a descendant of Asaph</OL>'),
(1231, 'yqqb', 'from (01238)', 'Buqqiy', 'None', 'book-kee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01238»; wasteful; Bukki, the name of two Israelites:--Bukki.', 'Bukki = \"wasting\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Abishua and father of Uzzi, fifth from Aaron in the line of the high priests<LI>son of Jogli, prince of the tribe of Dan, one of the ten men chosen to apportion the land of Canaan between the tribes</OL>'),
(1232, 'hyqqb', 'from (01238) and (03050)', 'Buqqiyah', 'None', 'book-kee-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01238» and «03050»; wasting of Jah; Bukkijah, an Israelite:--Bukkiah.', 'Bukkiah = \"Jehovah has emptied\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Kohathite Levite, of the sons of Heman, one of the musicians in the temple</OL>'),
(1233, '[yqb', 'from (01234)', 'bqiya`', 'TWOT - 271c', 'bek-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01234»; a fissure:--breach, cleft.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fissure, breach, cleft</OL>'),
(1234, '[qb', 'a primitive root', 'baqa`', 'TWOT - 271', 'baw-kah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to cleave; generally, to rend, break, rip or open:--make a breach, break forth (into, out, in pieces, through, up), be ready to burst, cleave (asunder), cut out, divide, hatch, rend (asunder), rip up, tear, win.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to split, cleave, break open, divide, break through, rip up, break up, tear<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cleave, cleave open<LI>to break through, break into</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be cleft, be rent open, be split open<LI>to be broken into</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cleave, cut to pieces, rend open<LI>to break through, break down</OL><LI>(Pual)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be ripped open, be torn open<LI>to be rent<LI>to be broken into</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to break into<LI>to break through</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be broken into<LI>(Hithpael) to burst (themselves) open, cleave asunder</OL></OL>'),
(1235, '[qb', 'from (01234)', 'beqa`', 'TWOT - 271a', 'beh\'-kah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01234»; a section (half) of a shekel, i.e. a beka (a weight and a coin):--bekah, half a shekel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>half, part also called \"shekel of the sanctuary\" or \"holy shekel\"<LI>half a shekel (meton) There appears to be at least three different shekels, one of silver, gold and copper. See a Bible Dictionary for a complete treatment of the subject.</OL>'),
(1236, 'a[qb', 'corresponding to (01237)', 'biq`a\'', 'TWOT - 2637', 'bik-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01237»:--plain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>plain</OL>'),
(1237, 'h[qb', 'from (01234)', 'biq`ah', 'TWOT - 271b', 'bik-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01234»; properly, a split, i.e. a wide level valley between mountains:--plain, valley.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>valley<LI>plain, level valley</OL>'),
(1238, 'qqb', 'a primitive root', 'baqaq', 'TWOT - 273', 'baw-kah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pour out, i.e. to empty, figuratively, to depopulate; by analogy, to spread out (as a fruitful vine):--(make) empty (out), fail, × utterly, make void.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to empty<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to empty, lay waste<LI>to make void (fig.)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be emptied<LI>(Polel) to empty out, devastate</OL></OL>'),
(1239, 'rqb', 'a primitive root', 'baqar', 'TWOT - 274', 'baw-kar', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to plough, or (generally) break forth, i.e. (figuratively) to inspect, admire, care for, consider:--(make) inquire (-ry), (make) search, seek out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to seek, enquire, consider<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to seek, look for<LI>to consider, reflect</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1240, 'rqb', 'corresponding to (01239)', 'bqar', 'TWOT - 2638', 'bek-ar\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01239»:--inquire, make search.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to seek, enquire<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pael) to enquire<LI>(Ithpael) to let search be made</OL></OL>'),
(1241, 'rqb', 'from (01239)', 'baqar', 'TWOT - 274a', 'baw-kawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01239»; beef cattle or an animal of the ox family of either gender (as used for plowing); collectively, a herd:-- beeve, bull (+ -ock), + calf, + cow, great (cattle), + heifer, herd, kine, ox.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cattle, herd, oxen, ox<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>cattle (generic pl. but sing. in form - coll)<LI>herd (particular one)<LI>head of cattle (individually)</OL></OL>'),
(1242, 'rqb', 'from (01239)', 'boqer', 'TWOT - 274c', 'bo\'-ker', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01239»; properly, dawn (as the break of day); generally, morning:--(+) day, early, morning, morrow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>morning, break of day<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>morning<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of end of night<LI>of coming of daylight<LI>of coming of sunrise<LI>of beginning of day<LI>of bright joy after night of distress (fig.)</OL><LI>morrow, next day, next morning</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(1243, 'hrqqb', 'intensive from (01239)', 'baqqarah', 'TWOT - 274d', 'bak-kaw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'intensive from «01239»; a looking after:--seek out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a seeking, a care, concern</OL>'),
(1244, 'trqqb', 'from (01239)', 'biqqoreth', 'TWOT - 274e', 'bik-ko-reth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01239»; properly, examination, i.e. (by implication) punishment:--scourged.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>punishment (after judicial enquiry), compensation</OL>'),
(1245, 'Xqb', 'a primitive root', 'baqash', 'TWOT - 276', 'baw-kash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to search out (by any method, specifically in worship or prayer); by implication, to strive after:--ask, beg, beseech, desire, enquire, get, make inquisition, procure, (make) request, require, seek (for).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to seek, require, desire, exact, request<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to seek to find<LI>to seek to secure<LI>to seek the face<LI>to desire, demand<LI>to require, exact<LI>to ask, request</OL><LI>(Pual) to be sought</OL></OL>'),
(1246, 'hXqqb', 'from (01245)', 'baqqashah', 'TWOT - 276a', 'bak-kaw-shaw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01245»; a petition:--request.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>request, entreaty, petition</OL>'),
(1247, 'rb', 'corresponding to (01121)', 'bar', 'TWOT - 2639', 'bar', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01121»; a son, grandson, etc.:--X  old, son.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son</OL>'),
(1248, 'rb', 'borrowed (as a title) from (01247)', 'bar', 'TWOT - 277', 'bar', 'Noun Masculine', 'borrowed (as a title) from «01247»; the heir (apparent to the throne):--son.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son, heir</OL>'),
(1249, 'rb', 'from (01305) (in its various senses)', 'bar', 'TWOT - 288a', 'bar', 'Adjective', 'from «01305» (in its various senses); beloved; also pure, empty:--choice, clean, clear, pure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pure, clear, sincere<LI>clean, empty adv<LI>purely</OL>'),
(1250, 'rb', 'from (01305) (in the sense of winnowing)', 'bar', 'TWOT - 288b', 'bawr', 'Noun Masculine', 'or bar {bar}; from «01305» (in the sense of winnowing); grain of any kind (even while standing in the field); by extens. the open country:--corn, wheat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>corn, grain</OL>'),
(1251, 'rb', 'corresponding to (01250)', 'bar', 'TWOT - 2640', 'bar', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01250»; a field:--field.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>field</OL>'),
(1252, 'rb', 'from (01305)', 'bor', 'TWOT - 288d', 'bore', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01305»; purify:--cleanness, pureness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cleanness, pureness</OL>'),
(1253, 'rb', 'the same as (01252)', 'bor', 'TWOT - 288c', 'bore', 'Noun Masculine', 'the same as «01252»; vegetable lye (from its cleansing); used as a soap for washing, or a flux for metals:--X never so, purely.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lye, potash, alkali used in smelting metal</OL>'),
(1254, 'arb', 'a primitive root', 'bara\'', 'TWOT - 278', 'baw-raw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; (absolutely) to create; (qualified) to cut down (a wood), select, feed (as formative processes):-- choose, create (creator), cut down, dispatch, do, make (fat).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to create, shape, form<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to shape, fashion, create (always with God as subject)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of heaven and earth<LI>of individual man<LI>of new conditions and circumstances<LI>of transformations</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be created<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of heaven and earth<LI>of birth<LI>of something new<LI>of miracles</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut down<LI>to cut out</OL></OL><LI>to be fat<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil) to make yourselves fat</OL></OL>'),
(1255, '!dalb $darb', 'a variation of (04757)', 'Bro\'dak', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'a variation of «04757»; Berodak-Baladan, a Babylonian king:--Berodach-baladan.Birliy.', 'Berodach-baladan = \"worshipper of Baal\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>king of Babylon in the days of Hezekiah</OL>'),
(1256, 'hyarb', 'from (01254) and (08050)', 'Bra\'yah', 'None', 'ber-aw-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01254» and «08050»; Jah has created; Berajah, an Israelite:--Beraiah.', 'Beraiah = \"Jehovah has created\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Shimhi, a chief man of Benjamin</OL>'),
(1257, 'rbrb', 'by reduplication from (01250)', 'barbur', 'TWOT - 288g', 'bar-boor\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'by reduplication from «01250»; a fowl (as fattened on grain):--fowl.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(CLBL) fowl, birds<LI>(BDB/TWOT) birds fattened for table of Solomon</OL>'),
(1258, 'drb', 'a primitive root', 'barad', 'TWOT - 280', 'baw-rad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root, to hail:--hail.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to hail</OL>'),
(1259, 'drb', 'from (01258)', 'barad', 'TWOT - 280a', 'baw-rawd\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01258»; hail -hail ((stones)).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hail<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of God\'s judgment (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(1260, 'drb', 'from (01258)', 'Bered', 'None', 'beh\'red', '', 'from «01258»; hail; Bered, the name of a place south of Palestine, also of an Israelite:--Bered.', 'Bered = \"hail\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son or descendant of Ephraim n pr loc<LI>a place in the south of Palestine, near Kadesh, near the well Lahairoi</OL>'),
(1261, 'drb', 'from (01258)', 'barod', 'TWOT - 280b', 'baw-rode\'', 'Adjective', 'from «01258»; spotted (as if with hail):--grisled.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spotted, marked</OL>'),
(1262, 'hrb', 'a primitive root', 'barah', 'TWOT - 281', 'baw-raw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to select; also (as denominative from «01250») to feed; also (as equivalent to «01305») to render clear (Eccl. 3:18):--choose, (cause to) eat, manifest, (give) meat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to eat, consume<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to eat<LI>(Piel) for eating, devouring<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to eat</OL></OL>'),
(1263, '$wrb', 'pass. participle from (01288)', 'Baruwk', 'None', 'baw-rook\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'passive participle from «01288»; blessed; Baruk, the name of three Israelites:--Baruch.', 'Baruch = \"blessed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>friend, amanuensis, and faithful attendant of Jeremiah<LI>a priest, the son of Zabbai who assisted Nehemiah in rebuilding the walls of Jerusalem<LI>a priest, or family of priests, who signed the covenant with Nehemiah<LI>son of Col-hozeh, a descendant of Perez or Pharez, the son of Judah</OL>'),
(1264, '~wrb', 'probably of foreign origin', 'browm', 'TWOT - 286a', 'ber-ome\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably of foreign origin; damask (stuff of variegated thread):--rich apparel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>variegated cloth, damask</OL>'),
(1265, 'Xwrb', 'of uncertain derivation', 'browsh', 'TWOT - 289a', 'ber-osh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; a cypress (?) tree; hence, a lance or a musical instrument (as made of that wood):--fir (tree).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cypress, fir, juniper, pine<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a noble tree (lit.)<LI>of stateliness (fig.)<LI>material for temple</OL></OL>'),
(1266, 'twrb', 'a variation of (01265)', 'browth', 'TWOT - 289a', 'ber-oth\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'a variation of «01265»; the cypress (or some elastic tree):--fir.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cypress, fir, juniper, pine</OL>'),
(1267, 'twrb', 'from (01262)', 'baruwth', 'TWOT - 281b', 'baw-rooth,', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01262»; food:--meat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>food</OL>'),
(1268, 'htwrb', 'probably from (01266)', 'Berowthah', 'None', 'bay-ro-thaw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Berothay {bay-ro-that\'-ee}; probably from «01266»; cypress or cypresslike; Berothah or Berothai, a place north of Palestine:--Berothah, Berothai.', 'Berothah or Berothai = \"cypress grove\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place near Hamath<LI>a city belonging to Hadadezer</OL>'),
(1269, 'twzrb', 'probably fem. pl. from an unused root', 'Birzowth', 'None', 'beer-zoth\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'probably feminine plural from an unused root (apparently mean to pierce); holes; Birzoth, an Israelite:--Birzavith (from the marg.).', 'Birzavith or Birzath = \"in leanness: choice olive\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Asher</OL>'),
(1270, 'lzrb', 'perhaps from the root of (01269)', 'barzel', 'TWOT - 283a', 'bar-zel\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'perhaps from the root of «01269»; iron (as cutting); by extension, an iron implement:--(ax) head, iron.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>iron<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>iron<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>iron ore<LI>as material of furniture, utensils, implements</OL></OL><LI>tool of iron<LI>harshness, strength, oppression (fig.)</OL>'),
(1271, 'yllzrb', 'from (01270)', 'Barzillay', 'None', 'bar-zil-lah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01270»; iron-hearted; Barzillai, the name of three Israelites:--Barzillai.', 'Barzillai = \"my iron\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Gileadite leader who helped David defeat Absalom\'s rebellion<LI>a priest, son-in-law to Barzillai the Gileadite<LI>an Israelite from Mahalath whose son Adriel married Michal, Saul\'s daughter</OL>'),
(1272, 'xrb', 'a primitive root', 'barach', 'TWOT - 284', 'baw-rakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to bolt, i.e. figuratively, to flee suddenly:--chase (away); drive away, fain, flee (away), put to flight, make haste, reach, run away, shoot.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go through, flee, run away, chase, drive away, put to flight, reach, shoot (extend), hurry away<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go, pass through<LI>to flee<LI>to hasten, come quickly</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pass through<LI>to cause to flee, put to flight<LI>to drive away</OL></OL></OL>'),
