(1292, 'lakrb', 'from (01288) and (0410)', 'Barak\'el', 'None', 'baw-rak-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01288» and «0410», God has blessed; Barakel, the father of one of Job\'s friends:--Barachel.', 'Barachel = \"God blesses\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Elihu</OL>'),
(1293, 'hkrb', 'from (01288)', 'Brakah', 'None', 'ber-aw-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01288»; benediction; by implication prosperity:--blessing, liberal, pool, present.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>blessing<LI>(source of) blessing<LI>blessing, prosperity<LI>blessing, praise of God<LI>a gift, present<LI>treaty of peace</OL>'),
(1294, 'hkrb', 'the same as (01293)', 'Brakah', 'None', 'ber-aw-kaw\'', '', 'the same as «01293»; Berakah, the name of an Israelite, and also of a valley in Palestine:--Berachah.', 'n pr m Berachah = \"blessing\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, one of David\'s warriors n pr loc<LI>a valley in the wilderness near Tekoa where Jehoshaphat and his people assembled to bless Jehovah after the overthrow of the hosts of the Moabites</OL>'),
(1295, 'hkrb', 'from (01288)', 'brekah', 'TWOT - 285c', 'ber-ay-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01288»; a reservoir (at which camels kneel as a resting-place):--(fish-)pool.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pool, pond</OL>'),
(1296, 'hykrb', 'from (01290) and (03050)', 'Berekyah', 'None', 'beh-rek-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Berekyahuw {beh-rek-yaw\'-hoo}; from «01290» and «03050»; knee (i.e. blessing) of Jah; Berekjah, the name of six Israelites:--Berachiah, Berechiah.', 'Berachiah or Berechiah = \"Jehovah blesses\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Zerubbabel<LI>a Levite who returned for the exile<LI>father of Meshullam, one of Nehemiah\'s chiefs who assisted in rebuilding the walls of Jerusalem<LI>father of Zechariah<LI>a Gershonite Levite, the father of Asaph, the singer, doorkeeper of the ark<LI>an Ephraimite chief in the time of Ahaz</OL>'),
(1297, '~rb', 'perhaps from (07313) with a prepositional prefix', 'bram', 'TWOT - 2642', 'ber-am\'', 'Adverb', '(Aramaic) perhaps from «07313» with a prepositional prefix; properly, highly, i.e. surely; but used adversatively, however:--but, nevertheless, yet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>only, nevertheless, but</OL>'),
(1298, '[rb', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Bera`', 'None', 'beh\'-rah', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; Bera, a Sodomitish king:--Bera.', 'Bera = \"son of evil\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a king of Sodom</OL>'),
