(1319, 'rXb', 'a primitive root', 'basar', 'TWOT - 291', 'baw-sar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to be fresh, i.e. full (rosy, (figuratively) cheerful); to announce (glad news):--messenger, preach, publish, shew forth, (bear, bring, carry, preach, good, tell good) tidings.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bear news, bear tidings, publish, preach, show forth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to gladden with good news<LI>to bear news<LI>to announce (salvation) as good news, preach</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to receive good news</OL></OL>'),
(1320, 'rXb', 'from (01319)', 'basar', 'TWOT - 291a', 'baw-sawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01319»; flesh (from its freshness); by extension, body, person; also (by euphem.) the pudenda of a man:--body, (fat, lean) flesh(-ed), kin, (man-)kind, + nakedness, self, skin.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flesh<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the body<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of humans<LI>of animals</OL><LI>the body itself<LI>male organ of generation (euphemism)<LI>kindred, blood-relations<LI>flesh as frail or erring (man against God)<LI>all living things<LI>animals<LI>mankind</OL></OL>'),
(1321, 'rXb', 'corresponding to (01320)', 'bsar', 'TWOT - 2643', 'bes-ar\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01320»:--flesh.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flesh</OL>'),
(1322, 'tXb', 'from (0954)', 'bosheth', 'TWOT - 222b', 'bo\'-sheth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «0954»; shame (the feeling and the condition, as well as its cause); by implication (specifically) an idol:--ashamed, confusion, + greatly, (put to) shame(-ful thing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shame<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>shame<LI>shameful thing</OL></OL>'),
(1323, 'tb', 'from (01129) and (01121)', 'bath', 'TWOT - 254b', 'bath', '', 'from «01129» (as feminine of «01121»); a daughter (used in the same wide sense as other terms of relationship, literally and figuratively):--apple (of the eye), branch, company, daughter, × first, × old, + owl, town, village.', 'n f<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>daughter<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>daughter, girl, adopted daughter, daughter-in-law, sister, granddaughters, female child, cousin<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>as polite address n pr f<LI>as designation of women of a particular place</OL></OL><LI>young women, women<OL TYPE=\"a\"><OL TYPE=\"3\"><LI>as personification<LI>daughter-villages<LI>description of character</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1324, 'tb', 'probably from the same as (01327)', 'bath', 'TWOT - 298a', 'bath', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from the same as «01327»; a bath or Hebrew measure (as a means of division) of liquids:--bath.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bath, a unit of liquid measure, equal to dry measure ephah (about 9 imperial gallons or 40 litres, rabbinical writings give sizes of one-half this amount)</OL>'),
