(1328, 'lawtb', 'apparently from the same as (01326) and (0410)', 'Bthuw\'el', 'None', 'beth-oo-ale\'', '', 'apparently from the same as «01326» and «0410»; destroyed of God; Bethuel, the name of a nephew of Abraham, and of a place in Palestine:--Bethuel. Compare «01329».', 'Bethuel = \"God destroys\" or \"man of God\" or \"dweller in God\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nephew of Abraham, son of Nahor by Milcah, father of Rebekah n pr loc<LI>a town of Simeon in the south</OL>'),
(1329, 'lwtb', 'for (01328)', 'Bthuwl', 'None', 'beth-ool\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'for «01328»; Bethul (i.e. Bethuel), a place in Palestine:--Bethuel.', 'Bethul = \"God destroys\" or \"man of God\" or \"dweller in God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town of Simeon in the south (also spelled \'Bethuel\')</OL>'),
(1330, 'hlwtb', 'pass. participle of an unused root meaning to separate', 'bthuwlah', 'TWOT - 295a', 'beth-oo-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine passive participle of an unused root meaning to separate; a virgin (from her privacy); sometimes (by continuation) a bride; also (figuratively) a city or state:--maid, virgin.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>virgin</OL>'),
