(1493, 'ynwzg', 'patrial from the unused name of a place', 'Gizowniy', 'None', 'ghee-zo-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'patrial from the unused name of a place apparently in Palestine; a Gizonite or inhabitant of Gizoh:--Gizonite.', 'Gizonite = \"shearer: quarryman\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant from or inhabitant of Gizon (otherwise unknown)</OL>'),
(1494, 'zzg', 'a primitive root [akin to (01468)]', 'gazaz', 'TWOT - 336', 'gaw-zaz\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (akin to «01468»); to cut off; specifically to shear a flock or shave the hair; figuratively to destroy an enemy:--cut off (down), poll, shave, ((sheep-)) shear(-er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shear, mow<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shear<LI>shearer (participle)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be cut off, be destroyed</OL></OL>'),
(1495, 'zzg', 'from (01494)', 'Gazez', 'None', 'gaw-zaze\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01494»; shearer; Gazez, the name of two Israelites:--Gazez.', 'Gazez = \"shearer\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Caleb by his concubine Ephah<LI>a son of Haran, the son of Caleb by his concubine Ephah (?)</OL>'),
(1496, 'tyzg', 'from (01491)', 'gaziyth', 'TWOT - 335a', 'gaw-zeeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01491»; something cut, i.e. dressed stone:--hewed, hewn stone, wrought.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a cutting, hewing</OL>'),
(1497, 'lzg', 'a primitive root', 'gazal', 'TWOT - 337', 'gaw-zal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pluck off; specifically to flay, strip or rob:--catch, consume, exercise (robbery), pluck (off), rob, spoil, take away (by force, violence), tear.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tear away, seize, plunder, tear off, pull off, rob, take away by force<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tear away, rob<LI>to seize, plunder (with acc cognate)</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be robbed<LI>to be taken away</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1498, 'lzg', 'from (01497)', 'gazel', 'TWOT - 337a', 'gaw-zale\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01497»; robbery, or (concretely) plunder:--robbery, thing taken away by violence.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>robbery, something plundered</OL>'),
(1499, 'lzg', 'from (01497)', 'gezel', 'None', 'ghe\'-zel', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01497»; plunder, i.e. violence:--violence, violent perverting. . gozal. See «01469».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>robbery, plunder</OL>'),
(1500, 'hlzg', 'from (01498)', 'gzelah', 'TWOT - 337b', 'ghez-ay-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «01498» and mean the same:  -that (he had robbed) (which he took violently away), spoil, violence.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>plunder, spoil, robbery</OL>'),
(1501, '~zg', 'from an unused root meaning to devour', 'gazam', 'TWOT - 338a', 'gaw-zawm\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to devour; a kind of locust:--palmer-worm.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>locusts</OL>'),
(1502, '~zzg', 'from the same as (01501)', 'Gazzam', 'None', 'gaz-zawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «01501»; devourer:--Gazzam, one of the Nethinim:--Gazzam.', 'Gazzam = \"devouring\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the head of a family of temple slaves returning from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(1503, '[zg', 'from an unused root meaning to cut down (trees)', 'geza\'', 'TWOT - 339a', 'geh\'-zah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to cut down (trees); the trunk or stump of a tree (as felled or as planted):--stem, stock.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stem, trunk, stock (of trees)</OL>'),
(1504, 'rzg', 'a primitive root', 'gazar', 'TWOT - 340', 'gaw-zar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to cut down or off; (figuratively) to destroy, divide, exclude, or decide:--cut down (off), decree, divide, snatch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut, divide, cut down, cut off, cut in two, snatch, decree<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut in two, divide<LI>to cut down<LI>to cut off, destroy, exterminate<LI>to decree</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be cut off, separated, excluded<LI>to be destroyed, cut off<LI>to be decreed</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1505, 'rzg', 'corresponding to (01504)', 'gzar', 'TWOT - 2654', 'ghez-ar\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01504»; to quarry; determine:--cut out, soothsayer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut, determine<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) determiner (participle)<LI>(Ithp\'al) to be cut out</OL></OL>'),
(1506, 'rzg', 'from (01504)', 'gezer', 'TWOT - 340a', 'gheh\'-zer', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01504»; something cut off; a portion:--part, piece.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>part</OL>'),
