(1511, 'yrzg', 'patrial from (01507)', 'Gizriy', 'None', 'ghiz-ree\'', 'Adjective', '(in the m patrial from «01507»; a Gezerite (collectively) or inhabitants of Gezer; but better (as in the text) by transposition Girziy {gher-zee\'}; patrial of «01630»; a Grizite (collectively) or member of a native tribe in Palestine:--Gezrites.', 'Gezrites = \"a piece: a portion (as cut off)\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>inhabitants of Gezer Gerezites = \"the cutters off\"<LI>inhabitants of Mt Gerizim?</OL>'),
(1512, '!wxg', 'probably from (01518)', 'gachown', 'TWOT - 342a', 'gaw-khone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from «01518»; the external abdomen, belly (as the source of the faetus (compare «01521»)):--belly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>belly (of reptiles)</OL>'),
(1513, 'lxg', 'from an unused root', 'gechel', 'TWOT - 341a', 'geh\'-khel', 'Noun Feminine', 'or (feminine) gacheleth {gah-kheh\'-leth}; from an unused root meaning to glow or kindle; an ember:--(burning) coal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>coal, burning coal, coals of fire, hot coals</OL>'),
(1514, '~xg', 'from an unused root meaning to burn', 'Gacham', 'None', 'gah\'-kham', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to burn; flame; Gacham, a son of Nahor:--Gaham.', 'Gaham = \"burning\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Abraham\'s brother Nahor and his concubine Reumah</OL>'),
(1515, 'rxg', 'from an unused root meaning to hide', 'Gachar', 'None', 'gah\'-khar', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to hide; lurker; Gachar, one of the Nethinim:--Gahar.', 'Gahar = \"hiding place\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the head of a family of temple slaves returning from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(1516, 'ayg', 'probably from the same root as (01466) (abbreviated)', 'gay\'', 'TWOT - 343', 'gah\'-ee', 'Noun', 'or (shortened) gay {gah\'-ee}; probably (by transmutation) from the same root as «01466» (abbreviated); a gorge (from its lofty sides; hence, narrow, but not a gully or winter-torrent):--valley.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>valley, a steep valley, narrow gorge</OL>'),
(1517, 'dyg', 'probably from (01464)', 'giyd', 'TWOT - 344a', 'gheed', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from «01464»; a thong (as compressing); by analogy, a tendon:--sinew.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sinew</OL>'),
(1518, 'xyg', 'a primitive root', 'giyach', 'TWOT - 345', 'ghee\'-akh', 'Verb', 'or (shortened) goach {go\'-akh}; a primitive root; to gush forth (as water), generally to issue:--break forth, labor to bring forth, come forth, draw up, take out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to burst forth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to burst forth<LI>to draw forth<LI>to bring forth</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to break forth</OL></OL>'),
(1519, 'xyg', 'corresponding to (01518)', 'giyach', 'TWOT - 345 v', 'ghee\'-akh', '', '(Aramaic) or (shortened) guwach (Aramaic) {goo\'- akh}; corresponding to «01518»; to rush forth:--strive.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Aphel) to break forth</OL>'),
(1520, 'xyg', 'from (01518)', 'Giyach', 'None', 'ghee\'-akh', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «01518»; a fountain; Giach, a place in Palestine:--Giah.', 'Giah = \"to break forth\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place near Gibeon in Benjamin</OL>'),
(1521, '!wxyg', 'from (01518)', 'Giychown', 'TWOT - 345a', 'ghee-khone\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or (shortened) Gichown {ghee-khone\'}; from «01518»; stream; Gichon, a river of Paradise; also a valley (or pool) near Jerusalem:--Gihon.', 'Gihon = \"bursting forth\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the four rivers of the Garden of Eden<LI>a spring near Jerusalem where the anointing and proclaiming of Solomon as king took place</OL>'),
(1522, 'yzxyg', 'apparently from (01516) and (02372)', 'Geychaziy', 'None', 'gay-khah-zee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Gechaziy {gay-khah-zee\'}; apparently from «01516» and «02372»; valley of a visionary; Gechazi, the servant of Elisha:--Gehazi.', 'Gehazi = \"valley of vision\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the servant of Elisha</OL>'),
(1523, 'lyg', 'a primitive root', 'giyl', 'TWOT - 346', 'gheel', 'Verb', 'or (by permutation) guwl {gool}; a primitive root; properly, to spin round (under the influence of any violent emotion), i.e. usually rejoice, or (as cringing) fear:--be glad, joy, be joyful, rejoice.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rejoice, exult, be glad<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rejoice<LI>to tremble (from fear)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1524, 'lyg', 'from (01523)', 'giyl', 'TWOT - 346a,b', 'gheel', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01523»; a revolution (of time, i.e. an age); also joy:--X  exceedingly, gladness, × greatly, joy, rejoice(-ing), sort.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a rejoicing<LI>a circle, age</OL>'),
(1525, 'hlyg', 'from (01524)', 'giylah', 'TWOT - 346c', 'ghee-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or giylath {ghee-lath\'}; feminine of «01524»; joy:--joy, rejoicing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rejoicing</OL>'),
(1526, 'ynlyg', 'patrial from (01542)', 'Giyloniy', 'None', 'ghee-lo-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'patrial from «01542»; a Gilonite or inhabitant of Giloh:--Gilonite.', 'Gilonite = \"gentilic of preceding\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Giloh</OL>'),
(1527, 'tnyg', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Giynath', 'None', 'ghee-nath\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; Ginath, an Israelite:--Ginath.', 'Ginath = \"protection\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Tibni</OL>'),
(1528, 'ryg', 'corresponding to (01615)', 'giyr', 'TWOT - 2655', 'gheer', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01615»; lime:--plaster.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chalk, plaster</OL>'),
(1529, '!Xyg', 'from the same as (01487)', 'Geyshan', 'None', 'gay-shawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «01487»; lumpish; Geshan, an Israelite:--Geshan.', 'Geshan = \"lump\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the sons of Jahdai, in the genealogy of Judah, in the family of Caleb</OL>'),
(1530, 'lg', 'from (01556)', 'gal', 'TWOT - 353a', 'gal', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01556»; something rolled, i.e. a heap of stone or dung (plural ruins), by analogy, a spring of water (plural waves):--billow, heap, spring, wave.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>heap, spring, wave, billow<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>heap (of stones)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>over dead body<LI>alone<LI>used in ratifying a covenant</OL><LI>waves (fig. of chastisement of Jehovah)<LI>spring</OL></OL>'),
(1531, 'lg', 'from (01556)', 'gol', 'TWOT - 353c', 'gole', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01556»; a cup for oil (as round):--bowl.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bowl, basin<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>basin<LI>bowl<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of a lamp<LI>of bowl shaped portion of capitals of the two pillars in the temple</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1532, 'bllg', 'from an unused root meaning to shave', 'gallab', 'TWOT - 348', 'gal-lawb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to shave; a barber:--barber.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>barber</OL>'),
(1533, '[blg', 'from (01530) and (01158)', 'Gilboa`', 'None', 'ghil-bo\'-ah', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «01530» and «01158»; fountain of ebullition; Gilboa, a mountain of Palestine:--Gilboa.', 'Gilboa = \"swollen heap\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a mountain-ridge at the southeastern end of the plain of Jezreel, site of the death of Saul and Jonathan</OL>'),
(1534, 'lglg', 'by reduplication from (01556)', 'galgal', 'TWOT - 353i', 'gal-gal\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'by reduplication from «01556»; a wheel; by analogy, a whirlwind; also dust (as whirled):--heaven, rolling thing, wheel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wheel, whirl, whirlwind, whirling<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>wheel<LI>whirl (of dust, chaff)</OL></OL>'),
(1535, 'lglg', 'corresponding to (01534)', 'galgal', 'TWOT - 2657a', 'gal-gal\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01534»; a wheel:--wheel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wheel</OL>'),
(1536, 'lglg', 'a variation of (01534)', 'gilgal', 'TWOT - 353j', 'ghil-gawl\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'a variation of «01534»:--wheel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wheel</OL>'),
(1537, 'lglg', 'the same as (01536)', 'Gilgal', 'None', 'ghil-gawl\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «01536» (with the article as a properly, noun); Gilgal, the name of three places in Palestine:--Gilgal. See also «01019».', 'Gilgal = \"a wheel, rolling\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the first site of an Israelite camp west of the Jordan, east of Jericho, here Samuel was judge, and Saul was made king; later used for illicit worship<LI>dwelling place of prophets in northern Israel about four miles (7 km) from Shiloh and Bethel<LI>a region conquered by Joshua, site unsure</OL>'),
(1538, 'tlglg', 'by reduplication from (01556)', 'gulgoleth', 'TWOT - 353l', 'gul-go\'-leth', 'Noun Feminine', 'by reduplication from «01556»; a skull (as round); by implication, a head (in enumeration of persons):--head, every man, poll, skull.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head, poll, skull<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>skull<LI>head, poll (of census)</OL></OL>'),
(1539, 'dlg', 'from an unused root probably meaning to polish', 'geled', 'TWOT - 349', 'ghe\'-led', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to polish; the (human) skin (as smooth):--skin.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>skin (human)</OL>'),
(1540, 'hlg', 'a primitive root', 'galah', 'TWOT - 350', 'gaw-law\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to denude (especially in a disgraceful sense); by implication, to exile (captives being usually stripped); figuratively, to reveal:--+ advertise, appear, bewray, bring, (carry, lead, go) captive (into captivity), depart, disclose, discover, exile, be gone, open, × plainly, publish, remove, reveal, × shamelessly, shew, × surely, tell, uncover.', ''),
(1541, 'hlg', 'corresponding to (01540)', 'glah', 'TWOT - 2656', 'ghel-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) or glat (Aramaic) {ghel-aw\'};  corresponding to «01540»:--bring over, carry away, reveal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to reveal<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to reveal (secrets), be revealed<LI>(Aphel) to take into exile</OL></OL>'),
(1542, 'hlg', 'from (01540)', 'Giloh', 'None', 'ghee-lo\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or (fully) Giyloh {ghee-lo\'}; from «01540»; open; Giloh, a place in Palestine:--Giloh.', 'Giloh = \"exile\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in the mountains of Judah, home town of Ahithophel</OL>'),
(1543, 'hllg', 'from (01556)', 'gullah', 'TWOT - 353c', 'gool-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from «01556»; a fountain, bowl or globe (all as round):--bowl, pommel, spring.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bowl, spring, basin<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>basin<LI>bowl<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of a lamp<LI>of bowl shaped portion of capitals of pillars of the temple</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1544, 'lwllg', 'from (01556)', 'gilluwl', 'TWOT - 353h', 'ghil-lool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (shortened) gillul {ghil-lool\'}; from «01556»; properly, a log (as round); by implication, an idol:--idol.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>idols</OL>'),
(1545, '~wlg', 'from (01563)', 'glowm', 'TWOT - 354a', 'ghel-ome\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01563»; clothing (as wrapped):--clothes.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wrapping, garment</OL>'),
(1546, 'twlg', 'from (01540)', 'galuwth', 'TWOT - 350b', 'gaw-looth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from «01540»; captivity; concretely, exiles (collectively):--(they that are carried away) captives(-ity).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>exile, exiles<LI>(TWOT) captivity</OL>'),
(1547, 'twlg', 'corresponding to (01546)', 'galuwth', 'TWOT - 2656a', 'gaw-looth\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01546»:--captivity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>exile</OL>'),
(1548, 'xlg', 'a primitive root', 'galach', 'TWOT - 351', 'gaw-lakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to be bald, i.e. (causatively) to shave; figuratively to lay waste:--poll, shave (off).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to poll, shave, shave off, be bald<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shave<LI>to shave off<LI>(fig. of devastation)</OL><LI>(Pual) to be shaven<LI>(Hithpael) to shave oneself</OL></OL>'),
(1549, '!wyllg', 'from (01540)', 'gillayown', 'TWOT - 350c', 'ghil-law-yone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or gilyown {ghil-yone\'}; from «01540»; a tablet for writing (as bare); by analogy, a mirror (as a plate):--glass, roll.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>table, tablet, mirror, flat shiny ornament</OL>'),
(1550, 'lylg', 'from (01556)', 'galiyl', 'TWOT - 353f', 'gaw-leel\'', '', 'from «01556»; a valve of a folding door (as turning); also a ring (as round):--folding, ring.', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>turning, folding (of doors) n m<LI>cylinder, rod<LI>circuit, district (on northern border in Naphtali)</OL>'),
(1551, 'lylg', 'the same as (01550)', 'Galiyl', 'None', 'gaw-leel\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or (prolonged) Galiylah {gaw-lee-law\'}; the same as «01550»; a circle (with the article); Galil (as a special circuit) in the North of Palestine:--Galilee.', 'Galilee = \"circuit, district\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a territory in Naphtali largely occupied by heathen; a circuit of towns around Kedesh-Naphtali, in which were situated the 20 towns given by Solomon to Hiram king of Tyre as payment for his work in conveying timber from Lebanon to Jerusalem</OL>'),
(1552, 'hlylg', 'from (01550)', 'gliylah', 'TWOT - 353g', 'ghel-ee-law\'', '', 'feminine of «01550»; a circuit or region:--border, coast, country.', 'n f<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>circuit, boundary, territory n pr loc Galilee = \"circuit, district\"<LI>a territory in Naphtali largely occupied by heathen; a circuit of towns around Kedesh-Naphtali, in which were situated the 20 towns given by Solomon to Hiram king of Tyre as payment for his work in conveying timber from Lebanon to Jerusalem</OL>'),
(1553, 'twlylg', 'plural of (01552)', 'Gliylowth', 'TWOT - 353g', 'ghel-ee-lowth\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'plural of «01552»; circles; Geliloth, a place in Palestine:--Geliloth.', 'Geliloth = \"circuits\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place on Judah and Benjamin\'s border</OL>'),
(1554, '~yllg', 'plural of (01530)', 'Galliym', 'None', 'gal-leem\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'plural of «01530»; springs; Gallim, a place in Palestine:--Gallim.', 'Gallim = \"springs\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place north of Jerusalem, home town of the man to whom Michal, Saul\'s daughter, David\'s wife, was given as wife by Saul even though she was already married to David</OL>'),
(1555, 'tylg', 'perhaps from (01540)', 'Golyath', 'None', 'gol-yath\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'perhaps from «01540»; exile; Goljath, a Philistine:--Goliath.', 'Goliath = \"splendour\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the Philistine giant of Gath slain by David\'s sling</OL>'),
(1556, 'llg', 'a primitive root', 'galal', 'TWOT - 353', 'gaw-lal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to roll (literally or figuratively):--commit, remove, roll (away, down, together), run down, seek occasion, trust, wallow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to roll, roll away, roll down, roll together<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to roll<LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to roll up<LI>to flow down</OL><LI>(Pilpel) to roll<LI>(Poal) to be rolled<LI>(Hithpoel) to roll oneself<LI>(Hithpalpel) to roll oneself<LI>(Hiphil) to roll away</OL></OL>'),
(1557, 'llg', 'from (01556)', 'galal', 'TWOT - 353d', 'gaw-lawl\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01556»; dung (as in balls):--dung.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dung</OL>'),
(1558, 'llg', 'from (01556)', 'galal', 'TWOT - 352', 'gaw-lawl\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01556»; a circumstance (as rolled around); only used adverbially, on account of:--because of, for (sake).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>on account of, for the sake of</OL>'),
(1559, 'llg', 'from (01556)', 'Galal', 'None', 'gaw-lawl\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01556», in the sense of «01560»; great; Galal, the name of two Israelites:--Galal.', 'Galal = \"influential\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite, one of the sons of Asaph<LI>a third Levite, son of Jeduthun</OL>'),
(1560, 'llg', 'from a root corresponding to (01556)', 'glal', 'TWOT - 2657', 'ghel-awl\'', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «01556»; weight or size (as if rolled):--great.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rolling</OL>'),
(1561, 'llg', 'a variation of (01557)', 'gelel', 'TWOT - 353d', 'gay\'-lel', 'Noun Masculine', 'a variation of «01557»; dung (plural balls of dung):--dung.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dung, ball of dung</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(1562, 'yllg', 'from (01561)', 'Gilalay', 'None', 'ghe-lal-ah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01561»; dungy; Gilalai, an Israelite:--Gilalai.', 'Gilalai \"weighty\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levitical musician, one of the priest\'s sons at the consecration of the wall of Jerusalem</OL>'),
(1563, '~lg', 'a primitive root', 'galam', 'TWOT - 354', 'gaw-lam\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to fold:--wrap together.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to wrap up, fold, fold together</OL>'),
(1564, '~lg', 'from (01563)', 'golem', 'TWOT - 354b', 'go\'-lem', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01563»; a wrapped (and unformed mass, i.e. as the embryo):--substance yet being unperfect.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>embryo, fetus</OL>'),
(1565, 'dwmlg', 'probably by prolonged from (01563)', 'galmuwd', 'TWOT - 354c', 'gal-mood\'', 'Adjective', 'probably by prolonged from «01563»; sterile (as wrapped up too hard); figuratively, desolate:--desolate, solitary.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hard, barren, harsh, bleak<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>harsh, bleak (of a company of wicked men)<LI>barren (of women)</OL></OL>'),
(1566, '[lg', 'a primitive root', 'gala`', 'TWOT - 355', 'gaw-lah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be obstinate:--(inter-)meddle (with).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to expose, lay bare<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to disclose oneself, break out<LI>to break out (in contention)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1567, 'd[lg', 'from (01530) and (05707)', 'Gal`ed', 'None', 'gal-ade\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «01530» and «05707»; heap of testimony; Galed, a memorial cairn East of the Jordan:--Galeed.', 'Galeed = \"witness heap\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the pile of stones heaped up between Jacob and Laban to certify their covenant; located on Mt Gilead</OL>'),
(1568, 'd[lg', 'probably from (01567)', 'Gil`ad', 'TWOT - 356', 'ghil-awd\'', '', 'probably from «01567»; Gilad, a region East of the Jordan; also the name of three Israelites:--Gilead, Gileadite.', 'n pr loc Gilead = \"rocky region\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a mountainous region bounded on the west by the Jordan, on the north by Bashan, on the east by the Arabian plateau, and on the south by Moab and Ammon; sometimes called \'Mount Gilead\' or the \'land of Gilead\' or just \'Gilead\'. Divided into north and south Gilead<LI>a city (with prefix \'Jabesh\')<LI>the people of the region n pr m<LI>son of Machir and grandson of Manasseh<LI>father of Jephthah<LI>a Gadite</OL>'),
(1569, 'yd[lg', 'patronymically from (01568)', 'Gil`adiy', 'TWOT - 356a', 'ghil-aw-dee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from «01568»; a Giladite or descendant of Gilad:--Gileadite.', 'Gileadite = \"rocky region\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Gilead<LI>a branch of the tribe of Manasseh, descended of Gilead<LI>of Jephthah as the son of Gilead</OL>'),
(1570, 'Xlg', 'a primitive root', 'galash', 'TWOT - 357', 'gaw-lash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; probably to caper (as a goat):--appear.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sit, sit up, (possibly also) recline<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of flocks of goats<LI>of a woman\'s hair (simile)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1571, '~g', 'by contraction from an unused root', 'gam', 'TWOT - 361a', 'gam', 'Adverb', 'by contraction from an unused root meaning to gather; properly, assemblage; used only adverbially also, even, yea, though; often repeated as correl. both...and:--again, alike, also, (so much) as (soon), both (so)...and , but, either...or, even, for all, (in) likewise (manner), moreover, nay...neither, one, then(-refore), though, what, with, yea.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>also, even, indeed, moreover, yea<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also, moreover (giving emphasis)<LI>neither, neither...nor (with negative)<LI>even (for stress)<LI>indeed, yea (introducing climax)<LI>also (of correspondence or retribution)<LI>but, yet, though (adversative)<LI>even, yea, yea though (with \'when\' in hypothetical case)</OL><LI>(TWOT) again, alike</OL>'),
(1572, 'amg', 'a primitive root', 'gama\'', 'TWOT - 358', 'gaw-maw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (literally or figuratively) to absorb:--swallow, drink.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to swallow (liquids)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to swallow<LI>(Hiphil) to drink</OL></OL>'),
(1573, 'amg', 'from (01572)', 'gome\'', 'TWOT - 358a', 'go\'-meh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01572»; properly, an absorbent, i.e. the bulrush (from its porosity); specifically the papyrus:--(bul-)rush.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rush, reed, papyrus</OL>'),
(1574, 'dmg', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to grasp', 'gomed', 'TWOT - 359a', 'go\'-med', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to grasp; properly, a span:--cubit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cubit<LI>(CLBL) half-cubit - the measure between a cubit and a span - 9 in (20 cm)</OL>'),
(1575, 'dmmg', 'from the same as (01574)', 'gammad', 'None', 'gam-mawd\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «01574»; a warrior (as grasping weapons):--Gammadims.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>brave men, warriors, valorous men</OL>'),
(1576, 'lwmg', 'from (01580)', 'gmuwl', 'TWOT - 360a', 'ghem-ool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01580»; treatment, i.e. an act (of good or ill); by implication, service or requital:--+ as hast served, benefit, desert, deserving, that which he hath given, recompense, reward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dealing, recompense, benefit<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>dealing (of one\'s hand)<LI>recompense<LI>benefit</OL></OL>'),
(1577, 'lwmg', 'pass. participle of (01580)', 'gamuwl', 'None', 'gaw-mool\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'passive participle of «01580»; rewarded; Gamul, an Israelite:--Gamul. See also «01014».', 'Gamul = \"weaned\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest, the leader of the 22nd course in the service of the sanctuary</OL>'),
(1578, 'hlwmg', 'from (01576)', 'gmuwlah', 'TWOT - 360b', 'ghem-oo-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «01576»; meaning the same:--deed, recompense, such a reward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dealing, recompense</OL>'),
(1579, 'wzmg', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Gimzow', 'None', 'ghim-zo\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'of uncertain derivation; Gimzo, a place in Palestine:--Gimzo.', 'Gimzo = \"fertile in sycamores\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Judah south of the road between Jerusalem and Joppa which with its dependant villages was captured by the Philistines in the reign of Ahaz</OL>'),
(1580, 'lmg', 'a primitive root', 'gamal', 'TWOT - 360', 'gaw-mal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to treat a person (well or ill), i.e. benefit or requite; by implication (of toil), to ripen, i.e. (specifically) to wean:--bestow on, deal bountifully, do (good), recompense, requite, reward, ripen, + serve, mean, yield.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to deal fully with, recompense<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to deal out to, do to<LI>to deal bountifully with<LI>to recompense, repay, requite</OL></OL><LI>(Qal) to wean a child (Niphal) to be weaned<LI>(Qal) to ripen, bear ripe (almonds)</OL>'),
(1581, 'lmg', 'apparently from (01580)', 'gamal', 'TWOT - 360d', 'gaw-mawl\'', 'Noun', 'apparently from «01580» (in the sense of labor or burden-bearing); a camel:--camel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>camel<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>as property, as beast of burden, for riding, forbidden for food</OL></OL>'),
(1582, 'yllmg', 'probably from (01581)', 'Gmalliy', 'None', 'ghem-al-lee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «01581»; camel-driver; Gemalli, an Israelite:--Gemalli.', 'Gemalli = \"camel driver\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the father of Ammiel, the Danite spy</OL>'),
(1583, 'laylmg', 'from (01580) and (0410)', 'Gamliy\'el', 'None', 'gam-lee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01580» and «0410»; reward of God; Gamliel, an Israelite:--Gamaliel.', 'Gamaliel = \"reward of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Pedahzur and the leader of the tribe of Manasseh in the wilderness</OL>'),
(1584, 'rmg', 'a primitive root', 'gamar', 'TWOT - 363', 'gaw-mar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to end (in the sense of completion or failure):--cease, come to an end, fail, perfect, perform.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to end, come to an end, complete, cease<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to come to an end, be no more<LI>to bring to an end, complete</OL></OL><LI>(TWOT) to fail, perfect, perform</OL>'),
(1585, 'rmg', 'corresponding to (01584)', 'gmar', 'TWOT - 2658', 'ghem-ar\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01584»:--perfect.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to complete<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) perfect (pass participle)</OL></OL>'),
(1586, 'rmg', 'from (01584)', 'Gomer', 'TWOT - 363a', 'go\'-mer', '', 'from «01584»; completion; Gomer, the name of a son of Japheth and of his descendants; also of a Hebrewess:--Gomer.', 'Gomer = \"complete\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the eldest son of Japheth and grandson of Noah; the progenitor of the early Cimmerians and other branches of the Celtic family n pr f<LI>the unfaithful wife of the prophet Hosea; Hosea\'s relationship with her was symbolic of God\'s relationship with wayward Israel</OL>'),
(1587, 'hyrmg', 'from (01584) and (03050)', 'Gmaryah', 'None', 'ghem-ar-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Gmaryahuw {ghem-ar-yaw\'-hoo}; from «01584» and «03050»; Jah has perfected; Gemarjah, the name of two Israelites:--Gemariah.', 'Gemariah = \"Jehovah has accomplished\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of Shaphan the scribe and father of Michaiah; one of the nobles of Judah who had a chamber in the temple from which Baruch read Jeremiah\'s alarming prophecy to all the people<LI>the son of Hilkiah who bore Jeremiah\'s letter to the captive Jews</OL>'),
(1588, '!g', 'from (01598)', 'gan', 'TWOT - 367a', 'gan', '', 'from «01598»; a garden (as fenced):--garden.', 'n m/f<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>garden, enclosure<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>enclosed garden<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(fig. of a bride)</OL><LI>garden (of plants) n pr loc<LI>Garden of Eden</OL></OL>'),
(1589, 'bng', 'a primitive root', 'ganab', 'TWOT - 364', 'gaw-nab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to thieve (literally or figuratively); by implication, to deceive:--carry away, × indeed, secretly bring, steal (away), get by stealth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to steal, steal away, carry away<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to steal<LI>(Niphal) to be stolen<LI>(Piel) to steal away<LI>(Pual) to be stolen away, be brought by stealth<LI>(Hithpael) to go by stealth, steal away</OL></OL>'),
(1590, 'bnng', 'from (01589)', 'gannab', 'TWOT - 364b', 'gaw-nab\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01589»; a stealer:--thief.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thief</OL>'),
(1591, 'hbng', 'from (01589)', 'gnebah', 'TWOT - 364a', 'ghen-ay-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01589»; stealing, i.e. (concretely) something stolen:--theft.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thing stolen, theft</OL>'),
(1592, 'tbng', 'from (01589)', 'Gnubath', 'None', 'ghen-oo-bath\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01589»; theft; Genubath, an Edomitish prince:--Genubath.', 'Genubath = \"theft\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Hadad, an Edomite of the royal family, by an Egyptian princess, the sister of Tahpenes, the queen of the Pharaoh who governed Egypt in the latter part of the reign of David</OL>'),
(1593, 'hnng', 'from (01588)', 'gannah', 'TWOT - 367b', 'gan-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «01588»; a garden:--garden.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>garden, orchard</OL>'),
(1594, 'hnng', 'another form for (01593)', 'ginnah', 'TWOT - 367b', 'ghin-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'another form for «01593»:--garden.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>garden</OL>'),
(1595, 'zng', 'from an unused root meaning to store', 'genez', 'TWOT - 365a', 'gheh\'-nez', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to store; treasure; by implication, a coffer:--chest, treasury.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>treasury, chests?<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>chests (of variegated cloth) (meaning uncertain)<LI>treasury</OL></OL>'),
(1596, 'zng', 'corresponding to (01595)', 'gnaz', 'TWOT - 2659', 'ghen-az\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01595»; treasure:--treasure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>treasure</OL>'),
(1597, '$zng', 'prolonged from (01595)', 'ginzak', 'TWOT - 366', 'ghin-zak\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'prolonged from «01595»; a treasury:--treasury.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>treasury</OL>'),
(1598, '!ng', 'a primitive root', 'ganan', 'TWOT - 367', 'gaw-nan\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to hedge about, i.e. (generally) protect:--defend.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to defend, cover, surround<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to defend<LI>(Hiphil) to defend</OL></OL>'),
(1599, '!wtnng', 'from (01598)', 'Ginnthown', 'None', 'ghin-neth-one', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Ginnthow {ghin-neth-o\'}; from «01598»; gardener; Ginnethon or Ginnetho, an Israelite:--Ginnetho, Ginnethon.', 'Ginnetho or Ginnethon = \"gardener\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest among the exiles who returned with Zerubbabel and who covenanted with Nehemiah</OL>'),
(1600, 'h[g', 'a primitive root', 'ga`ah', 'TWOT - 368', 'gaw-aw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to bellow (as cattle):--low.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to low, bellow (of cattle)</OL>'),
(1601, 'h[g', 'fem. act. participle of (01600)', 'Go`ah', 'None', 'go-aw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'feminine active participle of «01600»; lowing; Goah, a place near Jerusalem:--Goath.', 'Goath = \"bellowing\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place near Jerusalem, site unknown</OL>'),
(1602, 'l[g', 'a primitive root', 'ga`al', 'TWOT - 369', 'gaw-al\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to detest; by implication, to reject:--abhor, fail, lothe, vilely cast away.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to abhor, loathe, be vilely cast away, fall<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to abhor, loathe<LI>(Niphal) to be defiled<LI>(Hiphil) to reject as loathsome, show aversion</OL></OL>'),
(1603, 'l[g', 'from (01602)', 'Ga`al', 'None', 'gah\'-al', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01602»; loathing; Gaal, an Israelite:--Gaal.', 'Gaal = \"loathing\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Eved who aided the Shechemites in their rebellion against Abimelech</OL>'),
(1604, 'l[g', 'from (01602)', 'go`al', 'TWOT - 369a', 'go\'-al', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01602»; abhorrence:--loathing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>loathing</OL>'),
(1605, 'r[g', 'a primitive root', 'ga`ar', 'TWOT - 370', 'gaw-ar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to chide:--corrupt, rebuke, reprove.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to rebuke, reprove, corrupt</OL>'),
(1606, 'hr[g', 'from (01605)', 'g`arah', 'TWOT - 370a', 'gheh-aw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01605»; a chiding:--rebuke(-ing), reproof.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a rebuke, reproof</OL>'),
(1607, 'X[g', 'a primitive root', 'ga`ash', 'TWOT - 371', 'gaw-ash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root to agitate violently:--move, shake, toss, trouble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shake, quake<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to shake<LI>(Pual) to be shaken up, convulsed<LI>(Hithpael) to shake back and forth, toss or reel to and fro<LI>(Hithpoel) to reel to and fro</OL></OL>'),
(1608, 'X[g', 'from (01607)', 'Ga`ash', 'None', 'ga\'-ash', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «01607»; a quaking; Gaash, a hill in Palestine:--Gaash.', 'Gaash = \"quaking\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a mountain of Ephraim where Joshua was buried</OL>'),
(1609, '~t[g', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Ga`tam', 'None', 'gah-tawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; Gatam, an Edomite:--Gatam.', 'Gatam = \"a burnt valley\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fourth son of Eliphaz and grandson of Esau and one of the dukes of Eliphaz</OL>'),
(1610, '@g', 'from an unused root meaning to arch', 'gaph', 'TWOT - 373a', 'gaf', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to arch; the back; by extensive the body or self:--+ highest places, himself.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>body, self (only in phrase, eg by himself)<LI>height, elevation</OL>'),
(1611, '@g', 'corresponding to (01610)', 'gaph', 'TWOT - 2660', 'gaf', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01610»; a wing:--wing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wing (of bird)</OL>'),
