(1683, 'hrwbd', 'the same as (01682)', 'Dbowrah', 'None', 'deb-o-raw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'or (shortened) Dborah {deb-o-raw\'}; the same as «01682»; Deborah, the name of two Hebrewesses:--Deborah.', 'Deborah = \"bee\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the nurse of Rebekah who accompanied her from the house of Bethuel<LI>a prophetess who judged Israel</OL>'),
(1684, 'xbd', 'corresponding to (02076)', 'dbach', 'TWOT - 2665', 'deb-akh\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02076»; to sacrifice (an animal):--offer (sacrifice).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to sacrifice</OL>'),
(1685, 'xbd', 'from (01684)', 'dbach', 'TWOT - 2665a', 'deb-akh\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «01684»; a sacrifice:--sacrifice.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sacrifice</OL>'),
(1686, '!wybd', 'both (in the pl. only and) of uncertain derivation', 'dibyown', 'TWOT - ?', 'dib-yone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'in the margin for the textual reading, cheryown {kher-yone\'}; both (in the plural only and) of uncertain derivation; probably some cheap vegetable, perhaps a bulbous root:--dove\'s dung.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>doves dung</OL>'),
(1687, 'rybd', 'from (01696) (apparently in the sense of oracle)', 'dbiyr', 'TWOT - 399g', 'deb-eer\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (shortened) dbir {deb-eer\'}; from «01696» (apparently in the sense of oracle); the shrine or innermost part of the sanctuary:--oracle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the holy of holies, the innermost room of the temple or tabernacle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>hindmost chamber, innermost room of the temple of Solomon, most holy place, holy of holies</OL><LI>(TWOT) oracle</OL>'),
(1688, 'rybd', 'the same as (01687)', 'Dbiyr', 'None', 'deb-eer\'', '', 'or (shortened) Dbir (Josh. 13:26 (but see «03810»)) {deb-eer\'}; the same as «01687»; Debir, the name of an Amoritish king and of two places in Palestine:--Debir.', 'Debir = \"sanctuary\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the king of Eglon, one of the five kings hanged by Joshua n pr loc<LI>a town in the mountains of Judah west of Hebron and given to the priests and a city of refuge<LI>a place on the northern boundary of Judah<LI>a town in the territory of Gad</OL>'),
(1689, 'hlbd', 'probably an orthographical error for (07247)', 'Diblah', 'None', 'dib-law\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'probably an orthographical error for «07247»; Diblah, a place in Syria:--Diblath.', 'Diblath = \"place of the fig cake\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place near the wilderness</OL>'),
(1690, 'hlbd', 'from an unused root (akin to (02082))', 'dbelah', 'TWOT - 397a', 'deb-ay-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root (akin to «02082») probably meaning to press together; a cake of pressed figs:--cake (lump) of figs.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fig cake, lump of pressed figs</OL>'),
(1691, '~ylbd', 'dual from (01690)', 'Diblayim', 'None', 'dib-lah\'-yim', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'dual from the masculine of «01690»; two cakes; Diblajim, a symbolic name:--Diblaim.', 'Diblaim = \"two cakes\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the father of Hosea\'s wife Gomer</OL>'),
(1692, 'qbd', 'a primitive root', 'dabaq', 'TWOT - 398', 'daw-bak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to impinge, i.e. cling or adhere; figuratively, to catch by pursuit:--abide fast, cleave (fast together), follow close (hard after), be joined (together), keep (fast), overtake, pursue hard, stick, take.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cling, stick, stay close, cleave, keep close, stick to, stick with, follow closely, join to, overtake, catch<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cling, cleave to<LI>to stay with</OL><LI>(Pual) to be joined together<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to cleave to<LI>to pursue closely<LI>to overtake</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be made to cleave</OL></OL>'),
(1693, 'qbd', 'corresponding to (01692)', 'dbaq', 'TWOT - 2666', 'deb-ak\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01692»; to stick to:--cleave.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to cling</OL>'),
(1694, 'qbd', 'from (01692)', 'debeq', 'TWOT - 398a', 'deh\'-bek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01692»; a joint; by implication, solder:--joint, solder.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>joints, soldering, joining, appendage<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>joining, soldering, riveting<LI>appendage, open joints of a breastplate</OL></OL>'),
(1695, 'qbd', 'from (01692)', 'dabeq', 'TWOT - 398?', 'daw-bake\'', 'Adjective', 'from «01692»; adhering:--cleave, joining, stick closer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>clinging, adhering to</OL>'),
(1696, 'rbd', 'a primitive root', 'dabar', 'TWOT - 399', 'daw-bar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; perhaps properly, to arrange; but used figuratively (of words), to speak; rarely (in a destructive sense) to subdue:--answer, appoint, bid, command, commune, declare, destroy, give, name, promise, pronounce, rehearse, say, speak, be spokesman, subdue, talk, teach, tell, think, use (entreaties), utter, × well, × work.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to speak, declare, converse, command, promise, warn, threaten, sing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to speak<LI>(Niphal) to speak with one another, talk<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to speak<LI>to promise</OL><LI>(Pual) to be spoken<LI>(Hithpael) to speak<LI>(Hiphil) to lead away, put to flight</OL></OL>'),
(1697, 'rbd', 'from (01696)', 'dabar', 'TWOT - 399a', 'daw-baw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01696»; a word; by implication, a matter (as spoken of) or thing; adverbially, a cause:--act, advice, affair, answer, ×  any such (thing), because of, book, business, care, case, cause, certain rate, + chronicles, commandment, ×  commune(-ication), + concern(-ing), + confer, counsel, + dearth, decree, deed, × disease, due, duty, effect, + eloquent, errand, (evil favoured-)ness, + glory, + harm, hurt, + iniquity, + judgment, language, + lying, manner, matter, message, (no) thing, oracle, × ought, × parts, + pertaining, + please, portion, + power, promise, provision, purpose, question, rate, reason, report, request, × (as hast) said, sake, saying, sentence, + sign, + so, some (uncleanness), somewhat to say, + song, speech, × spoken, talk, task, + that, × there done, thing (concerning), thought, + thus, tidings, what(-soever), + wherewith, which, word, work.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>speech, word, speaking, thing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>speech<LI>saying, utterance<LI>word, words<LI>business, occupation, acts, matter, case, something, manner (by extension)</OL></OL>'),
(1698, 'rbd', 'from (01696) (in the sense of destroying)', 'deber', 'TWOT - 399b', 'deh\'-ber', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01696» (in the sense of destroying); a pestilence:--murrain, pestilence, plague.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pestilence, plague<LI>murrain, cattle disease, cattle-plague</OL>'),
(1699, 'rbd', 'from (01696) (in its original sense)', 'dober', 'TWOT - 399c', 'do\'-ber', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01696» (in its original sense); a pasture (from its arrangement of the flock):--fold, manner.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pasture<LI>word, speaking</OL>'),
(1700, 'hrbd', 'fem. of (01697)', 'dibrah', 'TWOT - 399e', 'dib-raw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'feminine of «01697»; a reason, suit or style:--cause, end, estate, order, regard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cause, manner, reason</OL>'),
(1701, 'hrbd', 'corresponding to (01700)', 'dibrah', 'TWOT - 2667', 'dib-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01700»:--intent, sake.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cause, reason</OL>'),
(1702, 'hrbd', 'act. participle of (01696)', 'dobrah', 'TWOT - 399d', 'do-ber-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine active participle of «01696» in the sense of driving (compare «01699»); a raft:--float.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>floats, rafts</OL>'),
(1703, 'hrbbd', 'intensive from (01696)', 'dabbarah', 'TWOT - 399j', 'dab-baw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'intensive from «01696»; a word:--word.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>word, words</OL>'),
(1704, 'yrbd', 'from (01697)', 'Dibriy', 'None', 'dib-ree\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01697»; wordy; Dibri, an Israelite:--Dibri.', 'Dibri = \"my word\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Danite, father of Shelomith in the time of the exodus</OL>'),
(1705, 'trbd', 'from (01697) (perhaps in the sense of (01699))', 'Dabrath', 'None', 'daw-ber-ath\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «01697» (perhaps in the sense of «01699»); Daberath, a place in Palestine:--Dabareh, Daberath.', 'Dabareh or Daberath = \"word\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levitical city, modern \'Debarieh\',situated at the western foot of Tabor</OL>'),
(1706, 'Xbd', 'from an unused root meaning to be gummy', 'dbash', 'TWOT - 400a', 'deb-ash\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to be gummy; honey (from its stickiness); by analogy, syrup:--honey((-comb)).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>honey</OL>'),
(1707, 'tXbbd', 'intensive from the same as (01706)', 'dabbesheth', 'TWOT - 400b', 'dab-beh\'-sheth', 'Noun Feminine', 'intensive from the same as «01706»; a sticky mass, i.e. the hump of a camel:--hunch (of a camel).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hump (of camel)</OL>'),
(1708, 'tXbbd', 'the same as (01707)', 'Dabbesheth', 'None', 'dab-beh\'-sheth', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «01707»; Dabbesheth, a place in Palestine:--Dabbesheth.', 'Dabbasheth = \"a hill-place\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town on the border of Zebulun</OL>'),
(1709, 'gd', 'from (01711)', 'dag', 'TWOT - 401a', 'dawg', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (fully) dag (Nehemiah 13:16) {dawg}; from «01711»; a fish (as prolific); or perhaps rather from «01672» (as timid); but still better from «01672» (in the sense of squirming, i.e. moving by the vibratory action of the tail); a fish (often used collectively):--fish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fish</OL>'),
(1710, 'hgd', 'from (01709)', 'dagah', 'TWOT - 401b', 'daw-gaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «01709», and meaning the same:--fish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fish</OL>'),
(1711, 'hgd', 'a primitive root', 'dagah', 'TWOT - 401', 'daw-gaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to move rapidly; used only as a denominative from «01709»; to spawn, i.e. become numerous:--grow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to multiply, increase</OL>'),
(1712, '!wgd', 'from (01709)', 'Dagown', 'None', 'daw-gohn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01709»; the fish-god; Dagon, a Philistine deity:--Dagon.', 'Dagon = \"a fish\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Philistine deity of fertility; represented with the face and hands of a man and the tail of a fish</OL>'),
(1713, 'lgd', 'a primitive root', 'dagal', 'TWOT - 402b', 'daw-gal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to flaunt, i.e. raise a flag; figuratively, to be conspicuous:--(set up, with) banners, chiefest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to look, behold<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) looked at, conspicuous (participle)</OL><LI>to carry a banner or standard, set up banner or standard<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to set up standard (in battle)<LI>(Niphal) supplied with banners, bannered</OL></OL>'),
(1714, 'lgd', 'from (01713)', 'degel', 'TWOT - 402a', 'deh\'-gel', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01713»; a flag:--banner, standard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>banner, standard</OL>'),
(1715, '!gd', 'from (01711)', 'dagan', 'TWOT - 403a', 'daw-gawn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01711»; properly, increase, i.e. grain:--corn ((floor)), wheat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wheat, cereal, grain, corn</OL>'),
(1716, 'rgd', 'a primitive root', 'dagar', 'TWOT - 404', 'daw-gar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root, to brood over eggs or young:--gather, sit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to gather together as a brood</OL>'),
(1717, 'dd', 'apparently from the same as (01730)', 'dad', 'TWOT - 405', 'dad', 'Noun Masculine', 'apparently from the same as «01730»; the breast (as the seat of love, or from its shape):--breast, teat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>breast, nipple, teat</OL>'),
(1718, 'hdd', 'a doubtful root', 'dadah', 'TWOT - 406', 'daw-daw\'', 'Verb', 'a doubtful root; to walk gently:--go (softly, with).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to move slowly<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hithpael) to walk deliberately</OL></OL>'),
(1719, '!dd', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Ddan', 'None', 'ded-awn\'', '', 'or (prolonged) Ddaneh (Ezek. 25:13) {deh-daw\'- neh}; of uncertain derivation; Dedan, the name of two Cushites and of their territory:--Dedan.', 'Dedan = \"low country\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of Raamah and grandson of Cush. A son of Jokshan and grandson of Keturah n pr loc<LI>a place in south Arabia</OL>'),
(1720, '~yndd', 'plural of (01719) (as patrial)', 'Ddaniym', 'None', 'ded-aw-neem\'', 'Adjective', 'plural of «01719» (as patrial); Dedanites, the descendants or inhabitants of Dedan:--Dedanim.', 'Dedanim = \"low country\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants or inhabitants of Dedan</OL>'),
(1721, '~yndd', 'a plural of uncertain derivation', 'Dodaniym', 'None', 'do-daw-neem\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or (by orthographical error) Rodaniym (1 Chron. 1:7) {ro-daw-neem\'}; a plural of uncertain derivation; Dodanites, or descendants of a son of Javan:--Dodanim.', 'Dodanim or Rodanim = \"leaders\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sons or descendants of Javan</OL>'),
(1722, 'bhd', 'corresponding to (02091)', 'dhab', 'TWOT - 2668', 'deh-hab\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02091»; gold:--gold(- en).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gold</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(1723, '[whd', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Dahava`', 'None', 'dah-hav-aw\'', 'Noun', '(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; Dahava, a people colonized in Samaria:--Dehavites.', 'Dehavites = \"the sickly\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the name of a people or<LI>that is, which is to say (simple particles)</OL>'),
(1724, '~hd', 'a primitive root (compare (01740))', 'daham', 'TWOT - 407', 'daw-ham\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «01740»); to be dumb, i.e. (figuratively) dumbfounded:--astonished.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to astonish, astound<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) astounded (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(1725, 'rhd', 'a primitive root', 'dahar', 'TWOT - 408', 'daw-har\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to curvet or move irregularly:--pause.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rush, dash, gallop (a horse)</OL>'),
(1726, 'rhhd', 'by reduplication from (01725)', 'dahahar', 'TWOT - 408a', 'dah-hah-har\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'by reduplication from «01725»; a gallop:--pransing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dashing, rushing, galloping</OL>'),
(1727, 'bwd', 'a primitive root', 'duwb', 'TWOT - 409', 'doob', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to mope, i.e. (figuratively) pine:-- sorrow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pine away, pass away<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil) to cause to pine away</OL></OL>'),
(1728, 'gwwd', 'an orthographical variation of (01709) as a denominative [(01771)]', 'davvag', 'TWOT - 401d', 'dav-vawg\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'an orthographical variation of «01709» as a denominative («01771»); a fisherman:--fisher.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fisherman, fisher</OL>'),
(1729, 'hgwd', 'from the same as (01728)', 'duwgah', 'TWOT - 401e', 'doo-gaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from the same as «01728»; properly, fishery, i.e. a hook for fishing:--fish (hook).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fishing, fishery</OL>'),
(1730, 'dwd', 'from an unused root meaning properly, to boil', 'dowd', 'TWOT - 410a', 'dode', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (shortened) dod {dode}; from an unused root meaning properly, to boil, i.e. (figuratively) to love; by implication, a love- token, lover, friend; specifically an uncle:--(well-)beloved, father\'s brother, love, uncle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>beloved, love, uncle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>loved one, beloved<LI>uncle<LI>love (pl. abstract)</OL></OL>'),
(1731, 'dwd', 'from the same as (01730)', 'duwd', 'TWOT - 410e', 'dood', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «01730»; a pot (for boiling); also (by resemblance of shape) a basket:--basket, caldron, kettle, (seething) pot.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pot, jar, basket, kettle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>pot, kettle<LI>basket, jar</OL></OL>'),
(1732, 'dwd', 'from the same as (01730)', 'David', 'TWOT - 410c', 'daw-veed\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'rarely (fully); Daviyd {daw-veed\'}; from the same as «01730»; loving; David, the youngest son of Jesse:--David.', 'David = \"beloved\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>youngest son of Jesse and second king of Israel</OL>'),
(1733, 'hdwd', 'from (01730)', 'dowdah', 'TWOT - 410b', 'do-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «01730»; an aunt:--aunt, father\'s sister, uncle\'s wife.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>aunt</OL>'),
(1734, 'wdwd', 'from (01730)', 'Dowdow', 'None', 'do-do\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01730»; loving; Dodo, the name of three Israelites:--Dodo.', 'Dodo = \"his beloved\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a man of the tribe of Issachar<LI>a man of Bethlehem, father of Elhanan who was one of David\'s 30 captains<LI>an Ahohite, father of Eleazar, the second of the 3 mighty men who were over the 30</OL>'),
(1735, 'whwdwd', 'from (01730) and (03050)', 'Dowdavahuw', 'None', 'do-daw-vaw\'-hoo', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01730» and «03050»; love of Jah; Dodavah, an Israelite:--Dodavah.', 'Dodavah = \"beloved of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a man of Mareshah in Judah, the father of Eliezer, who denounced Jehoshaphat\'s alliance with Ahaziah</OL>'),
(1736, 'ydwd', 'from (01731)', 'duwday', 'TWOT - 410d', 'doo-dah\'-ee', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01731»; a boiler or basket; also the mandrake (as an aphrodisiac):--basket, mandrake.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mandrake, love-apple<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>as exciting sexual desire, and favouring procreation</OL></OL>'),
(1737, 'ydwd', 'formed like (01736)', 'Dowday', 'None', 'do-dah\'ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'formed like «01736»; amatory; Dodai, an Israelite:--Dodai.', 'Dodai = \"loving\" or \"amorous\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Ahohite who commanded the course of the second month; probably the same as \'Dodo\'</OL>'),
(1738, 'hwd', 'a primitive root', 'davah', 'TWOT - 411', 'daw-vaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be sick (as if in menstruation):--infirmity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be ill, be unwell<LI>(TWOT)infirmity</OL>'),
(1739, 'hwd', 'from (01738)', 'daveh', 'TWOT - 411b', 'daw-veh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «01738»; sick (especially in menstruation):--faint, menstruous cloth, she that is sick, having sickness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>faint, unwell<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>faint, weak<LI>unwell, menstruous</OL></OL>'),
(1740, 'xwd', 'a primitive root', 'duwach', 'TWOT - 412', 'doo\'-akh', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to thrust away; figuratively, to cleanse:--cast out, purge, wash.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rinse, cleanse away by rinsing, cast out, purge, wash, washing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rinse<LI>to cleanse (by washing) (fig.)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1741, 'ywd', 'from (01739)', 'dvay', 'TWOT - 411a', 'dev-ah\'ee', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01739»; sickness; figuratively, loathing:--languishing, sorrowful.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>illness, languishing</OL>'),
(1742, 'ywwd', 'from (01739)', 'davvay', 'TWOT - 411d', 'dav-voy\'', 'Adjective', 'from «01739»; sick; figuratively, troubled:--faint.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>faint (of heart)</OL>'),
(1743, '$wd', 'a primitive root', 'duwk', 'TWOT - 413', 'dook', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to bruise in a mortar:--beat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to pound, beat (in mortar)</OL>'),
(1744, 'tpykwd', 'of uncertain derivation', 'duwkiyphath', 'TWOT - 414', 'doo-kee-fath\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'of uncertain derivation; the hoopoe or else the grouse:--lapwing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unclean bird (probably hoopoe)</OL>'),
(1745, 'hmwd', 'from an unused root meaning to be dumb (compare (1820))', 'duwmah', 'TWOT - 415a', 'doo-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning to be dumb (compare «01820»); silence; figuratively, death:--silence.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>silence</OL>'),
(1746, 'hmwd', 'the same as (01745)', 'Duwmah', 'None', 'doo-maw\'', '', 'the same as «01745»; Dumah, a tribe and region of Arabia:--Dumah.', 'Dumah = \"silence\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Ishmael and most probably the founder of the Ishmaelite tribe of Arabia n pr loc<LI>a town in the mountainous district of Judah, near Hebron<LI>a mystical name of Edom indicating death and ruin</OL>'),
(1747, 'hymwd', 'from (01820)', 'duwmiyah', 'TWOT - 415b', 'doo-me-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01820»; stillness; adverbially, silently; abstractly quiet, trust:--silence, silent, waiteth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>silence, still, repose, still waiting</OL>'),
(1748, '~mwd', 'from (01826)', 'duwmam', 'TWOT - 415c', 'doo-mawm\'', '', 'from «01826»; still; adverbially, silently:--dumb, silent, quietly wait.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>silence adv<LI>in silence, silently</OL>'),
(1749, 'gnwd', 'of uncertain derivation', 'downag', 'TWOT - 444a', 'do-nag\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; wax; -wax.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wax (always figurative \'of melting\')</OL>'),
(1750, '#wd', 'a primitive root', 'duwts', 'TWOT - 416', 'doots', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to leap:--be turned.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to leap, dance, spring</OL>'),
(1751, 'qwd', 'corresponding to (01854)', 'duwq', 'TWOT - 2681', 'dook', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01854»; to crumble:--be broken to pieces.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be shattered, fall to pieces<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to break in pieces</OL></OL>'),
(1752, 'rwd', 'a primitive root', 'duwr', 'TWOT - 418', 'dure', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to gyrate (or move in a circle), i.e. to remain:--dwell.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to heap up, pile<LI>to dwell<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dwell<LI>heap up (imp.)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1753, 'rwd', 'corresponding to (01752)', 'duwr', 'TWOT - 2669', 'dure', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «01752»; to reside:--dwell.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to dwell</OL>'),
(1754, 'rwd', 'from (01752)', 'duwr', 'TWOT - 418a', 'dure', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01752»; a circle, ball or pile:--ball, turn, round about.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ball, circle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>circle<LI>ball</OL></OL>'),
(1755, 'rwd', 'from (01752)', 'dowr', 'TWOT - 418b', 'dore', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (shortened) dor {dore}; from «01752»; properly, a revolution of time, i.e. an age or generation; also a dwelling:--age, ×  evermore, generation, (n-)ever, posterity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>period, generation, habitation, dwelling<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>period, age, generation (period of time)<LI>generation (those living during a period)<LI>generation (characterised by quality, condition, class of men)<LI>dwelling-place, habitation</OL></OL>'),
