(2226, 'xrz', 'the same as (02225)', 'Zerach', 'None', 'zeh\'-rakh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «02225»; Zerach, the name of three Israelites, also of an Idumaean and an Ethiopian prince:--Zarah, Zerah.', 'Zerah or Zarah = \"rising\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Reuel and grandson of Esau, one of the dukes of the Edomites<LI>twin brother of Pharez, sons of Judah and Tamar; descendants are called Zarhites, Ezrahites, and Izrahites<LI>son of Simeon; also called \'Zohar\'<LI>a Gershonite Levite, son of Iddo of Adaiah<LI>the Ethiopian or Cushite, invader of Judah in the reign of Asa who defeated the invaders; probably the same as the Egyptian king Usarken I, second king of the Egyptian 22nd dynasty or perhaps more probably Usarken II, his 2nd successor<LI>another Edomite leader; possibly same as 1</OL>'),
(2227, 'yxrz', 'patronymically from (02226)', 'Zarchiy', 'None', 'zar-khee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'patronymically from «02226»; a Zarchite or descendant of Zerach:--Zarchite.', 'Zarhites = see Zerah<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Zerah</OL>'),
