(2232, '[rz', 'a primitive root', 'zara`', 'TWOT - 582', 'zaw-rah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to sow; figuratively, to disseminate, plant, fructify:--bear, conceive seed, set with sow(-er), yield.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sow, scatter seed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sow<LI>producing, yielding seed</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be sown<LI>to become pregnant, be made pregnant</OL><LI>(Pual) to be sown<LI>(Hiphil) to produce seed, yield seed</OL></OL>'),
