(2270, 'rbx', 'from (02266)', 'chaber', 'TWOT - 598c', 'khaw-bare\'', '', 'from «02266»; an associate:--companion, fellow, knit together.', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>united n m<LI>associate, fellow, worshippers<LI>companion</OL>'),
(2271, 'rbbx', 'from (02266)', 'chabbar', 'TWOT - 598f', 'khab-bawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02266»; a partner:--companion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>associate, partner (in trade)</OL>'),
(2272, 'hrbrbx', 'by reduplication from (02266)', 'chabarburah', 'TWOT - 598h', 'khab-ar-boo-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'by reduplication from «02266»; a streak (like a line), as on the tiger:--spot.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spots, stripe, mark</OL>'),
(2273, 'hrbx', 'from (02269)', 'chabrah', 'TWOT - 2717b', 'khab-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) feminine of «02269»; an associate:--other.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>associate, fellow, companion</OL>'),
(2274, 'hrbx', 'from (02267)', 'chebrah', 'TWOT - 598b', 'kheb-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02267»; association:--company.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>company, association</OL>'),
(2275, '!wrbx', 'from (02267)', 'Chebrown', 'TWOT - 598i', 'kheb-rone\'', '', 'from «02267»; seat of association; Chebron, a place in Palestine, also the name of two Israelites:--Hebron.', 'Hebron = \"association\" n pr loc<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in south Judah approx 20 south of Jerusalem and approx 20 miles (30 km) north of Beersheba and near where Abraham built an altar n pr m<LI>the 3rd son of Kohath and grandson of Levi<LI>a descendant of Caleb</OL>'),
(2276, 'ynwrbx', 'patronymically from (02275)', 'Chebrowniy', 'None', 'kheb-ro-nee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or Chebroniy {kheb-ro-nee\'}; patronymically from «02275»; Chebronite (collectively), an inhabitant of Chebron:--Hebronites.', 'Hebronites = see Hebron<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the inhabitants of the city of Hebron<LI>the descendants of Hebron, the grandson of Levi</OL>'),
(2277, 'yrbx', 'patronymically from (02268)', 'Chebriy', 'None', 'kheb-ree\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'patronymically from «02268»; a Chebrite (collectively) or descendants of Cheber:--Heberites.', 'Heberites = see Heber<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Heber</OL>'),
(2278, 'trbx', 'from (02270)', 'chabereth', 'TWOT - 598d', 'khab-eh\'-reth', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02270»; a consort:--companion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>companion, wife, consort</OL>'),
(2279, 'trbx', 'act. participle of (02266)', 'chobereth', 'TWOT - 598e', 'kho-beh\'-reth', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine active participle of «02266»; a joint:--which coupleth, coupling.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>junction, a thing joined<LI>curtain pieces of the tabernacle</OL>'),
(2280, 'Xbx', 'a primitive root', 'chabash', 'TWOT - 599', 'khaw-bash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to wrap firmly (especially a turban, compress, or saddle); figuratively, to stop, to rule:--bind (up), gird about, govern, healer, put, saddle, wrap about.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tie, bind, bind on, bind up, saddle, restrain, bandage, govern<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bind, bind on<LI>to bind up</OL><LI>(Piel) to bind, restrain<LI>(Pual) to be bound up</OL></OL>'),
(2281, 'tbx', 'from an unused root probably meaning to cook [compare (04227)]', 'chabeth', 'TWOT - 600a', 'khaw-bayth\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to cook (compare «04227»); something fried, probably a griddle-cake:--pan.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flat cakes, bread wafers</OL>'),
(2282, 'gx', 'from (02287)', 'chag', 'TWOT - 602a', 'khag', 'Noun Masculine', 'or chag {khawg}; from «02287»; a festival, or a victim therefor:--(solemn) feast (day), sacrifice, solemnity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>festival, feast, festival-gathering, pilgrim-feast<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>feast<LI>festival sacrifice</OL></OL>'),
(2283, 'agx', 'from an unused root meaning to revolve [compare (02287)]', 'chagra\'', 'TWOT - 602b', 'khaw-gaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning to revolve (compare «02287»); properly, vertigo, i.e. (figuratively) fear:--terror.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>terror, a reeling (in terror)</OL>'),
(2284, 'bgx', 'of uncertain derivation', 'chagab', 'TWOT - 601a', 'khaw-gawb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; a locust:--locust.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>locust, grasshopper</OL>'),
(2285, 'bgx', 'the same as (02284)', 'Chagab', 'None', 'khaw-gawb\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «02284»; locust; Chagab, one of the Nethinim:--Hagab.', 'Hagab = \"locust\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of a family of exiles who returned with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(2286, 'abgx', 'from (02285)', 'Chagaba\'', 'None', 'khag-aw-baw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Chagabah {khag-aw-baw\'}; feminine of «02285»; locust; Chagaba or Chagabah, one of the Nethinim:--Hagaba, Hagabah.', 'Hagaba or Hagabah = \"locust\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of a family of exiles who returned with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(2287, 'ggx', 'a primitive root [compare (02283), (02328)]', 'chagag', 'TWOT - 602', 'khaw-gag\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «02283», «02328»); properly, to move in a circle, i.e. (specifically) to march in a sacred procession, to observe a festival; by implication, to be giddy:--celebrate, dance, (keep, hold) a (solemn) feast (holiday), reel to and fro.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hold a feast, hold a festival, make pilgrimage, keep a pilgrim-feast, celebrate, dance, stagger<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to keep a pilgrim-feast<LI>to reel</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2288, 'wgx', 'from an unused root meaning to take refuge', 'chagav', 'TWOT - 603a', 'khag-awv\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to take refuge; a rift in rocks:--cleft.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>clefts, places of concealment, retreats</OL>'),
(2289, 'rwgx', 'from (02296)', 'chagowr', 'TWOT - 604b', 'khaw-gore\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02296»; belted:--girded with.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>clothed, girded, girt</OL>'),
(2290, 'rwgx', 'from (02296)', 'chagowr', 'TWOT - 604a,604c', 'khag-ore\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or chagor {khag-ore\'}; and (feminine) chagowrah {khag-o-raw\'}; or chagorah {khag-o-raw\'}; from «02296»; a belt (for the waist):--apron, armour, gird(-le).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>girdle, belt<LI>girdle, loin-covering, belt, loin-cloth, armour</OL>'),
(2291, 'yggx', 'from (02287)', 'Chaggiy', 'None', 'khag-ghee\'', '', 'from «02287»; festive, Chaggi, an Israelite; also (patronymically) a Chaggite, or descendant of the same:--Haggi, Haggites.', 'Haggi = \"festive\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>second son of Gad adj<LI>descendants of Haggi, a Gadite</OL>'),
(2292, 'yggx', 'from (02282)', 'Chaggay', 'None', 'khag-gah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02282»; festive; Chaggai, a Heb. prophet:--Haggai.', 'Haggai = \"festive\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>10th in order of the minor prophets; first prophet to prophecy after the captivity</OL>'),
(2293, 'hyggx', 'from (02282) and (03050)', 'Chaggiyah', 'None', 'khag-ghee-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02282» and «03050»; festival of Jah; Chaggijah, an Israelite:--Haggiah.', 'Haggiah = \"festival of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Shimea and a Merarite Levite</OL>'),
(2294, 'tyggx', 'from (02291)', 'Chaggiyith', 'None', 'khag-gheeth\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'feminine of «02291»; festive; Chaggith, a wife of David:--Haggith.', 'Haggith = \"festive\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a wife of David and mother of Adonijah</OL>'),
(2295, 'hlgx', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Choglah', 'None', 'khog-law\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'of uncertain derivation; probably a partridge; Choglah, an Israelitess:--Hoglah. See also «01031».', 'Hoglah = \"partridge\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>3rd of 5 daughters of Zelophehad, a descendant of Manasseh</OL>'),
(2296, 'rgx', 'a primitive root', 'chagar', 'TWOT - 604', 'khaw-gar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to gird on (as a belt, armor, etc.):--be able to put on, be afraid, appointed, gird, restrain, × on every side.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to gird, gird on, gird oneself, put on a belt<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to gird<LI>to gird on, bind on<LI>to gird oneself</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2297, 'dx', 'abridged from (0259)', 'chad', 'TWOT - 61', 'khad', 'Adjective', 'abridged from «0259»; one:--one.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one (number), same, single, first, each, once</OL>'),
(2298, 'dx', 'corresponding to (02297)', 'chad', 'TWOT - 2718', 'khad', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02297»; as card. one; as article single; as an ordinal, first; adverbially, at once:--a, first, one, together.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one (number)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>one<LI>a (indefinite article)</OL></OL>'),
(2299, 'dx', 'from (02300)', 'chad', 'TWOT - 605a', 'khad', 'Adjective', 'from «02300»; sharp:--sharp.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sharp</OL>'),
(2300, 'ddx', 'a primitive root', 'chadad', 'TWOT - 605', 'khaw-dad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) sharp or (figuratively) severe:--be fierce, sharpen.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be sharp, be alert, be keen<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be sharp, be keen<LI>(Hiphil) to sharpen<LI>(Hophal) to be sharpened</OL></OL>'),
(2301, 'ddx', 'from (02300)', 'Chadad', 'None', 'khad-ad\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02300»; fierce; Chadad, an Ishmaelite:--Hadad.', 'Hadad = \"mighty\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Ishmael</OL>'),
(2302, 'hdx', 'a primitive root', 'chadah', 'TWOT - 607', 'khaw-daw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to rejoice:--make glad, be joined, rejoice.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rejoice<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to rejoice<LI>(Piel) to make glad, gladden</OL></OL>'),
(2303, 'dwddx', 'from (02300)', 'chadduwd', 'TWOT - 605b', 'khad-dood\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02300»; a point:--sharp.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sharp, pointed, sharpened</OL>'),
(2304, 'hwdx', 'from (02302)', 'chedvah', 'TWOT - 607a', 'khed-vaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02302»; rejoicing:--gladness, joy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>joy, gladness</OL>'),
(2305, 'hwdx', 'corresponding to (02304)', 'chedvah', 'TWOT - 2719', 'khed-vaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02304»:--joy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>joy</OL>'),
(2306, 'ydx', 'corresponding to (02373)', 'chadiy', 'TWOT - 2720', 'khad-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02373»; a breast:--breast.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>breast, chest</OL>'),
(2307, 'dydx', 'from (02300)', 'Chadiyd', 'None', 'khaw-deed\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02300»; a peak; Chadid, a place in Palestine:--Hadid.', 'Hadid = \"sharp\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Benjamin</OL>'),
(2308, 'ldx', 'a primitive root', 'chadal', 'TWOT - 609', 'khaw-dal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to be flabby, i.e. (by implication) desist; (figuratively) be lacking or idle:--cease, end, fall, forbear, forsake, leave (off), let alone, rest, be unoccupied, want.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to stop, cease, desist, forego, cease to be, leave undone, forbear<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cease, come to an end<LI>to cease, leave off</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2309, 'ldx', 'from (02308)', 'chedel', 'TWOT - 609a', 'kheh\'-del', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02308»; rest, i.e. the state of the dead:--world.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rest, cessation</OL>'),
(2310, 'ldx', 'from (02308)', 'chadel', 'TWOT - 609b', 'khaw-dale\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02308»; vacant, i.e. ceasing or destitute:--he that forbeareth, frail, rejected.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rejected, forbearing, transient, fleeting, lacking</OL>'),
(2311, 'yldx', 'from (02309)', 'Chadlay', 'None', 'khad-lah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02309»; idle; Chadlai, an Israelite:--Hadlai.', 'Hadlai = \"rest of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Ephraimite</OL>'),
(2312, 'qdx', 'from an unused root meaning to sting', 'chedeq', 'TWOT - 611a', 'khay\'-dek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to sting; a prickly plant:--brier, thorn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>brier, thorn, prick</OL>'),
(2313, 'lqddx', 'probably of foreign origin', 'Chiddeqel', 'None', 'khid-deh\'-kel', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably of foreign origin; the Chiddekel (or Tigris) river:--Hiddekel.', 'Hiddekel = \"rapid\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the rivers of Eden which coursed east toward Assyria; better known as the Tigris (the LXX equivalent)</OL>'),
(2314, 'rdx', 'a primitive root', 'chadar', 'TWOT - 612', 'khaw-dar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to inclose (as a room), i.e. (by analogy,) to beset (as in a siege):--enter a privy chamber.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to encompass, surround, enclose</OL>'),
(2315, 'rdx', 'from (02314)', 'cheder', 'TWOT - 612a', 'kheh\'-der', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02314»; an apartment (usually literal):--((bed) inner)chamber, innermost(-ward) part, parlour, + south, ×  within.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chamber, room, parlour, innermost or inward part, within</OL>'),
(2316, 'rdx', 'another form for (02315)', 'Chadar', 'None', 'khad-ar\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'another form for «02315»; chamber; Chadar, an Ishmaelite:--Hadar.', 'Hadar = \"honour\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Edomite king</OL>'),
(2317, '$rdx', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Chadrak', 'None', 'khad-rawk\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'of uncertain derivation; Chadrak, a Syrian deity:--Hadrach.', 'Hadrach = \"dwelling\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city of Syria (mod Lebanon)</OL>'),
(2318, 'Xdx', 'a primitive root', 'chadash', 'TWOT - 613', 'khaw-dash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be new; causatively, to rebuild:--renew, repair.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be new, renew, repair<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to renew, make anew<LI>to repair</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to renew oneself</OL></OL>'),
(2319, 'Xdx', 'from (02318)', 'chadash', 'TWOT - 613a', 'khaw-dawsh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02318»; new:--fresh, new thing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>new, new thing, fresh</OL>'),
(2320, 'Xdx', 'from (02318)', 'chodesh', 'TWOT - 613b', 'kho\'-desh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02318»; the new moon; by implication, a month:--month(-ly), new moon.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the new moon, month, monthly<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the first day of the month<LI>the lunar month</OL></OL>'),
(2321, 'Xdx', 'the same as (02320)', 'Chodesh', 'None', 'kho\'-desh', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'the same as «02320»; Chodesh, an Israelitess:--Hodesh.', 'Hodesh = \"new moon\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the wife of Shaharaim, a Benjamite</OL>'),
(2322, 'hXdx', 'fem. of (02319)', 'Chadashah', 'None', 'khad-aw-shaw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'feminine of «02319»; new; Chadashah, a place in Palestine:--Hadashah.', 'Hadashah = \"new\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the towns in the low country of Judah</OL>'),
(2323, 'tdx', 'corresponding to (02319)', 'chadath', 'TWOT - 2721', 'khad-ath\'', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02319»; new:--new.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>new</OL>'),
(2324, 'awx', 'corresponding to (02331)', 'chava\'', 'TWOT - 2722', 'khav-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02331»; to show:--shew.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to show, interpret, explain, inform, tell, declare<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pael) to show, interpret<LI>(Aphel) to show</OL></OL>'),
(2325, 'bwx', 'a primitive root', 'chuwb', 'TWOT - 614', 'khoob', 'Verb', 'also chayab {khaw-yab\'}; a primitive root; properly, perhaps to tie, i.e. (figuratively and reflexively) to owe, or (by implication) to forfeit:--make endanger.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be guilty, make guilty<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to endanger</OL></OL>'),
(2326, 'bwx', 'from (02325)', 'chowb', 'TWOT - 614a', 'khobe', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02325»; debt:--debtor.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a debt, debtor</OL>'),
(2327, 'hbwx', 'fem. act. participle of (02247)', 'chowbah', 'None', 'kho-baw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'feminine active participle of «02247»; hiding place; Chobah, a place in Syria:--Hobah.', 'Hobah = \"hiding place\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city north of Damascus to which Abraham pursued the kings who had pillaged Sodom</OL>'),
(2328, 'gwx', 'a primitive root [compare (02287)]', 'chuwg', 'TWOT - 615', 'khoog', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «02287»); to describe a circle:--compass.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to encircle, encompass, describe a circle, draw round, make a circle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to encircle, encompass</OL></OL>'),
(2329, 'gwx', 'from (02328)', 'chuwg', 'TWOT - 615a', 'khoog', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02328»; a circle:--circle, circuit, compass.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>circle, circuit, compass<LI>(BDB) vault (of the heavens)</OL>'),
(2330, 'dwx', 'a primitive root', 'chuwd', 'TWOT - 616', 'khood', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to tie a knot, i.e. (figuratively) to propound a riddle:--put forth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to propose a riddle, propound a riddle</OL>'),
(2331, 'hwx', 'a primitive root [compare (02324), (0242)l]', 'chavah', 'TWOT - 618', 'khaw-vah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; (compare «02324», «02421»); properly, to live; by implication (intensively) to declare or show:--show.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to tell, declare, show, make known<LI>(CLBL) to breath</OL>'),
(2332, 'hwwx', 'causatively from (02331)', 'Chavvah', 'None', 'khav-vaw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'causatively from «02331»; life-giver; Chavvah (or Eve), the first woman:--Eve.', 'Eve = \"life\" or \"living\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the first woman, wife of Adam</OL>'),
(2333, 'hwwx', 'properly, the same as (02332) (life-giving, i.e. living-place)', 'chavvah', 'TWOT - 617a', 'khav-vaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'properly, the same as «02332» (life-giving, i.e. living-place); by implication, an encampment or village:--(small) town.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>village, town, tent village</OL>'),
(2334, 'ry[y twwwx', 'from the plural of (02333) and a modification of (03265)', 'Chavvowth', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the plural of «02333» and a modification of «03265»; hamlets of Jair, a region of Palestine:--(Bashan- )Havoth-jair.', 'Havoth-jair = \"villages of Jair\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>certain villages on the east of Jordan, in Gilead or Bashan, which were taken by Jair, the son of Manasseh, and called after his name; 60 or 23 or 30 cities in total</OL>'),
(2335, 'yzwx', 'from (02374)', 'Chowzay', 'None', 'kho-zah\'-ee', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02374»; visionary; Chozai, an Israelite:--the seers.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>seer<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>seer<LI>vision</OL></OL>'),
(2336, 'xwx', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to pierce', 'chowach', 'TWOT - 620a,620b', 'kho\'-akh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to pierce; a thorn; by analogy, a ring for the nose:--bramble, thistle, thorn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thorn, brier, bramble, thornbush, thicket<LI>hook, ring, fetter</OL>'),
(2337, 'xwx', 'perhaps the same as (02336)', 'chavach', 'TWOT - 620a?', 'khaw-vawkh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'perhaps the same as «02336»; a dell or crevice (as if pierced in the earth):--thicket.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rock, crevice (a hiding place)</OL>'),
(2338, 'twx', 'corresponding to the root of (02339), perhaps as a denominative', 'chuwt', 'TWOT - 2723', 'khoot', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to the root of «02339», perhaps as a denominative; to string together, i.e. (figuratively) to repair:--join.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Aphel) to repair, join</OL>'),
(2339, 'twx', 'from an unused root probably meaning to sew', 'chuwt', 'TWOT - 621a', 'khoot', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to sew; a string; by implication, a measuring tape:--cord, fillet, line, thread.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a thread, cord, line, string</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(2340, 'ywwx', 'perhaps from (02333)', 'Chivviy', 'None', 'khiv-vee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'perhaps from «02333»; a villager; a Chivvite, one of the aboriginal tribes of Palestine:--Hivite.', 'Hivite = \"villagers\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>6th generation of descendants of Canaan, the son of Ham, who were living in northern Canaan near Mount Hermon at the time of the conquest</OL>'),
(2341, 'hlywx', 'probably from (02342)', 'Chaviylah', 'TWOT - 622', 'khav-ee-law\'', '', 'probably from «02342»; circular; Chavilah, the name of two or three eastern regions; also perhaps of two men:--Havilah.', 'Havilah = \"circle\" n pr loc<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a part of Eden through which flowed the river Pison (Araxes); was probably the Grecian Colchis, in the northeast corner of Asia Minor, near the Caspian Sea<LI>a district in Arabia of the Ishmaelites named from the 2nd son of Cush; probably the district of Kualan, in the northwestern part of Yemen n pr m<LI>a son of Cush<LI>a son of Joktan</OL>'),
(2342, 'lwx', 'a primitive root', 'chuwl', 'TWOT - 623', 'khool', 'Verb', 'or chiyl {kheel}; a primitive root; properly, to twist or whirl (in a circular or spiral manner), i.e. (specifically) to dance, to writhe in pain (especially of parturition) or fear; figuratively, to wait, to pervert:--bear, (make to) bring forth, (make to) calve, dance, drive away, fall grievously (with pain), fear, form, great, grieve, (be) grievous, hope, look, make, be in pain, be much (sore) pained, rest, shake, shapen, (be) sorrow(-ful), stay, tarry, travail (with pain), tremble, trust, wait carefully (patiently), be wounded.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to twist, whirl, dance, writhe, fear, tremble, travail, be in anguish, be pained<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dance<LI>to twist, writhe<LI>to whirl, whirl about</OL><LI>(Polel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dance<LI>to writhe (in travail with), bear, bring forth<LI>to wait anxiously</OL><LI>(Pulal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be made to writhe, be made to bear<LI>to be brought forth</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be born<LI>(Hithpolel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>whirling (participle)<LI>writhing, suffering torture (participle)<LI>to wait longingly</OL><LI>(Hithpalpel) to be distressed</OL></OL>'),
(2343, 'lwx', 'from (02342)', 'Chuwl', 'None', 'khool', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02342»; a circle; Chul, a son of Aram; also the region settled by him:--Hul.', 'Hul = \"circle\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the second son of Aram and grandson of Shem</OL>'),
(2344, 'lwx', 'from (02342)', 'chowl', 'TWOT - 623a', 'khole', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02342»; sand (as round or whirling particles):--sand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sand</OL>'),
(2345, '~wx', 'from an unused root meaning to be warm', 'chuwm', 'TWOT - 625a', 'khoom', 'Adjective', 'from an unused root meaning to be warm, i.e. (by implication) sunburnt or swarthy (blackish):--brown.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dark colour, darkened, dark brown or black</OL>'),
(2346, 'hmwx', 'act. participle of an unused root apparently meaning to join', 'chowmah', 'TWOT - 674c', 'kho-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine active participle of an unused root apparently meaning to join; a wall of protection:--wall, walled.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wall</OL>'),
(2347, 'owx', 'a primitive root', 'chuwc', 'TWOT - 626', 'khoos', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to cover, i.e. (figuratively) to compassionate:--pity, regard, spare.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to pity, have compassion, spare, look upon with compassion</OL>'),
(2348, '@wx', 'from an unused root meaning to cover', 'chowph', 'TWOT - 710a', 'khofe', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to cover; a cove (as a sheltered bay):--coast (of the sea), haven, shore, (sea-)side.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>seashore, coast, shore</OL>'),
(2349, '~pwx', 'from the same as (02348)', 'Chuwpham', 'None', 'khoo-fawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «02348»; protection: Chupham, an Israelite:--Hupham.', 'Hupham = \"coast-man\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Benjamin, founder of the family of the Huphamites</OL>'),
(2350, 'ympwx', 'patronymically from (02349)', 'Chuwphamiy', 'None', 'khoo-faw-mee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'patronymically from «02349»; a Chuphamite or descendant of Chupham:--Huphamites.', 'Huphamites = see Hupham<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Hupham of the tribe of Benjamin</OL>'),
(2351, '#wx', '(both forms fem. in the pl.) from an unused root meaning to sever', 'chuwts', 'TWOT - 627a', 'khoots', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (shortened) chuts {khoots}; (both forms feminine in the plural) from an unused root meaning to sever; properly, separate by a wall, i.e. outside, outdoors:--abroad, field, forth, highway, more, out(-side, -ward), street, without.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>outside, outward, street, the outside</OL>'),
(2352, 'rwx', 'from an unused root probably meaning to bore', 'chuwr', 'TWOT - 758b', 'khoor', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (shortened) chur {khoor}; from an unused root probably meaning to bore; the crevice of a serpent; the cell of a prison:--hole.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hole</OL>'),
(2353, 'rwx', 'from (02357)', 'chuwr', 'TWOT - 630a', 'khoor', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02357»; white linen:--white.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>white cloth, white stuff</OL>'),
(2354, 'rwx', 'the same as (02353) or (02352)', 'Chuwr', 'None', 'khoor', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «02353» or «02352»; Chur, the name of four Israelites and one Midianite:--Hur.', 'Hur = \"hole\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a chief assistant to Moses and Aaron<LI>grandfather of Bezaleel, the chief artificer of the tabernacle; possibly the same as 1 above<LI>the 4th of the 5 kings of Midian who were slain with Balaam after Peor<LI>father of Rephaiah in the time of Nehemiah<LI>father of Ben-Hur who was commissariat officer for Solomon in Mount Ephraim</OL>'),
(2355, 'rwx', 'the same as (02353)', 'chowr', 'TWOT - 630a', 'khore', 'Noun Masculine', 'the same as «02353»; white linen:--network. Compare «02715».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>white cloth, white stuff</OL>'),
(2356, 'rwx', 'the same as (02352)', 'chowr', 'TWOT - 758a', 'khore', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (shortened) chor {khore}; the same as «02352»; a cavity, socket, den:--cave, hole.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hole, cave</OL>'),
(2357, 'rwx', 'a primitive root', 'chavar', 'TWOT - 630', 'khaw-var\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to blanch (as with shame):--wax pale.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be white, grow white, grow pale</OL>'),
(2358, 'rwwx', 'from a root corresponding to (02357)', 'chivvar', 'TWOT - 2724', 'khiv-vawr\'', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «02357»; white:--white.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>white</OL>'),
(2359, 'yrwx', 'probably from (02353)', 'Chuwriy', 'None', 'khoo-ree\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «02353»; linen-worker; Churi, an Israelite:--Huri.', 'Huri = \"linen-weaver\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Gadite, father of Abihail</OL>'),
(2360, 'yrwx', 'probably an orthographical variation for (02359)', 'Chuwray', 'None', 'khoo-rah\'ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably an orthographical variation for «02359»; Churai, an Israelite:--Hurai.', 'Hurai = \"linen-weaver\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of David\'s mighty warriors</OL>'),
(2361, '~rwx', 'probably from (02353)', 'Chuwram', 'None', 'khoo-rawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «02353»; whiteness, i.e. noble; Churam, the name of an Israelite and two Syrians:--Huram. Compare «02438».', 'Huram = \"noble born\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Bela and grandson of Benjamin<LI>king of Tyre allied with David and Solomon; alternate spelling for \'Hiram\'<LI>a chief architect of Solomon\'s temple; alternate spelling for \'Hiram\'</OL>'),
(2362, '!rwx', 'apparently from (02357) (in the sense of (02352))', 'Chavran', 'None', 'khav-rawn\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'apparently from «02357» (in the sense of «02352»); cavernous; Chavran, a region East of the Jordan:--Hauran.', 'Hauran = \"caverns\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a province of Palestine east of the Sea of Galilee; exact region uncertain but probably on the borders of the desert in the tetrarchy of Philip</OL>'),
(2363, 'Xwx', 'a primitive root', 'chuwsh', 'TWOT - 631', 'koosh', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to hurry; figuratively, to be eager with excitement or enjoyment:--(make) haste(-n), ready.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to haste, make haste, hurry<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to make haste<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to show haste, act quickly, hasten, come quickly<LI>to enjoy, be excited</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2364, 'hXwx', 'from (02363)', 'Chuwshah', 'None', 'khoo-shaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02363»; haste; Chushah, an Israelite:--Hushah.', 'Hushah = \"haste\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Judah</OL>'),
(2365, 'yXwx', 'from (02363)', 'Chuwshay', 'None', 'khoo-shah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02363»; hasty; Chushai, an Israelite:--Hushai.', 'Hushai = \"hasting\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Archite, a friend of David<LI>the father of Baana, an officer of Solomon; probably the same as 1</OL>'),
(2366, '~yXwx', 'plural from (02363)', 'Chuwshiym', 'None', 'khoo-sheem\'', '', 'or Chushiym {khoo-shem\'}; or Chushim {khoo- sheem\'}; plural from «02363»; hasters; Chushim, the name of three Israelites:--Hushim.', 'Hushim = \"who makes haste\" n pr f<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the two wives of Shaharaim n pr m<LI>the sons of Aher, a Benjamite<LI>descendants of Dan</OL>'),
(2367, '~Xwx', 'from (02363)', 'Chuwsham', 'None', 'khoo-shawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Chusham {khoo-shawm\'}; from «02363»; hastily; Chusham, an Idumaean:--Husham.', 'Husham = \"haste\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the early kings of Edom</OL>'),
(2368, '~twx', 'from (02856)', 'chowtham', 'TWOT - 780a', 'kho-thawm\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or chotham {kho-thawm\'}; from «02856»; a signature-ring:--seal, signet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>seal, signet, signet-ring</OL>'),
(2369, '~twx', 'the same as (02368)', 'Chowtham', 'None', 'kho-thawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «02368»; seal; Chotham, the name of two Israelites:--Hotham, Hothan.', 'Hotham = \"seal\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a man of Asher, son of Heber, of the family of Beriah<LI>father of two of David\'s mighty warriors</OL>'),
(2370, 'azx', 'corresponding to (02372)', 'chaza\'', 'TWOT - 2725', 'khaz-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) or chazah (Aramaic) {khaz-aw\'}; corresponding to «02372»; to gaze upon; mentally to dream, be usual (i.e. seem):--behold, have (a dream), see, be wont.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to see, behold<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to see<LI>to see, behold, witness<LI>to behold (in a dream or vision)<LI>customary, seemly (passive)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2371, 'lazx', 'from (02372) and (0410)', 'Chaza\'el', 'None', 'khaz-aw-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Chazahoel {khaz-aw-ale\'}; from «02372» and «0410»; God has seen; Chazael, a king of Syria:--Hazael.', 'Hazael = \"one who sees God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a king of Syria; sent by his master, Ben-hadad, to the prophet Elisha, to seek a remedy for Ben-hadad\'s leprosy; apparently later killed Ben-hadad, assumed the throne, and soon became engaged in a war with the kings of Judah and Israel for the possession of the city of Ramoth-gilead</OL>'),
(2372, 'hzx', 'a primitive root', 'chazah', 'TWOT - 633', 'khaw-zaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to gaze at; mentally, to perceive, contemplate (with pleasure); specifically, to have a vision of:--behold, look, prophesy, provide, see.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to see, perceive, look, behold, prophesy, provide<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to see, behold<LI>to see as a seer in the ecstatic state<LI>to see, perceive 1a</OL><LI>with the intelligence 1a<LI>to see (by experience) 1a<LI>to provide</OL></OL>'),
(2373, 'hzx', 'from (02372)', 'chazeh', 'TWOT - 634a', 'khaw-zeh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02372»; the breast (as most seen in front):--breast.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>breast (of animals), breast of an animal sacrifice</OL>'),
(2374, 'hzx', 'active participle of (02372)', 'chozeh', 'TWOT - 633b', 'kho-zeh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'active participle of «02372»; a beholder in vision; also a compact (as looked upon with approval):--agreement, prophet, see that, seer, (star-)gazer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>seer<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>seer<LI>vision</OL></OL>'),
(2375, 'wzx', 'from (02372)', 'Chazow', 'None', 'khaz-o\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02372»; seer; Chazo, a nephew of Abraham:--Hazo.', 'Hazo = \"vision\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Nahor by his wife Milcah</OL>'),
(2376, 'wzx', 'from (02370)', 'chezev', 'TWOT - 2725a', 'khay\'-zev', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «02370»; a sight:--look, vision.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vision, appearance<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>vision<LI>appearance</OL></OL>'),
(2377, '!wzx', 'from (02372)', 'chazown', 'TWOT - 633a', 'khaw-zone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02372»; a sight (mentally), i.e. a dream, revelation, or oracle:--vision.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vision<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>vision (in ecstatic state)<LI>vision (in night)<LI>vision, oracle, prophecy (divine communication)<LI>vision (as title of book of prophecy)</OL></OL>'),
(2378, 'twzx', 'from (02372)', 'chazowth', 'TWOT - 633c', 'khaw-zooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02372»; a revelation:--vision.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>visions</OL>'),
(2379, 'twzx', 'from (02370)', 'chazowth', 'TWOT - 2725b', 'khaz-oth\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) from «02370»; a view:--sight.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>view, sight, visibility</OL>'),
(2380, 'twzx', 'from (02372)', 'chazuwth', 'TWOT - 633d', 'khaw-zooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02372»; a look; hence (figuratively) striking appearance, revelation, or (by implication) compact:--agreement, notable (one), vision.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vision, conspicuousness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>vision, oracle of a prophet<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>agreement</OL><LI>conspicuousness in appearance</OL></OL>'),
(2381, 'layzx', 'from (02372) and (0410)', 'Chaziy\'el', 'None', 'khaz-ee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02372» and «0410»; seen of God; Chaziel, a Levite:--Haziel.', 'Haziel = \"vision of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite of the family of Shimei of the Gershonites in the time of David or Solomon</OL>'),
(2382, 'hyzx', 'from (02372) and (03050)', 'Chazayah', 'None', 'khaz-aw-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02372» and «03050»; Jah has seen; Chazajah, an Israelite:--Hazaiah.', 'Hazaiah = \"God has seen\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an exile and descendant of Shelah of the tribe of Judah who returned in the time of Nehemiah</OL>'),
(2383, '!wyzx', 'from (02372)', 'Chezyown', 'None', 'khez-yone\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02372»; vision; Chezjon, a Syrian:--Hezion.', 'Hezion = \"vision\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>king of Syria, father of Tabrimon and grandfather of Ben-hadad; probably identical with \'Rezon\' the contemporary of Solomon</OL>'),
(2384, '!wyzzx', 'from (02372)', 'chizzayown', 'TWOT - 633e', 'khiz-zaw-yone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02372»; a revelation, expectation by dream:--vision.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vision<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>vision (in the ecstatic state)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>valley of vision (perhaps fig. of Jerusalem or Hinnom)</OL><LI>vision (in the night)<LI>vision, oracle, prophecy (in divine communication)</OL></OL>'),
(2385, 'zyzx', 'from an unused root meaning to glare', 'chaziyz', 'TWOT - 635a', 'khaw-zeez\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to glare; a flash of lightning:--bright cloud, lightning.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thunderbolt, lightning flash, lightning, storm, cloud</OL>'),
(2386, 'ryzx', 'from an unused root probably meaning to enclose', 'chaziyr', 'TWOT - 637a', 'khaz-eer\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to enclose; a hog (perhaps as penned):--boar, swine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hog, swine, boar<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>swine (as forbidden food)<LI>wild boar</OL></OL>'),
(2387, 'ryzx', 'from the same as (02386)', 'Cheziyr', 'None', 'khay-zeer\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «02386»; perhaps protected; Chezir, the name of two Israelites:--Hezir.', 'Hezir = \"swine\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest in the time of David, leader of the 17th monthly course<LI>one of the heads of the people who sealed the covenant with Nehemiah</OL>'),
(2388, 'qzx', 'a primitive root', 'chazaq', 'TWOT - 636', 'khaw-zak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to fasten upon; hence, to seize, be strong (figuratively, courageous, causatively strengthen, cure, help, repair, fortify), obstinate; to bind, restrain, conquer:--aid, amend, × calker, catch, cleave, confirm, be constant, constrain, continue, be of good (take) courage(-ous, -ly), encourage (self), be established, fasten, force, fortify, make hard, harden, help, (lay) hold (fast), lean, maintain, play the man, mend, become (wax) mighty, prevail, be recovered, repair, retain, seize, be (wax) sore, strengthen (self), be stout, be (make, shew, wax) strong(-er), be sure, take (hold), be urgent, behave self valiantly, withstand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strengthen, prevail, harden, be strong, become strong, be courageous, be firm, grow firm, be resolute, be sore<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be strong, grow strong 1a</OL><LI>to prevail, prevail upon 1a<LI>to be firm, be caught fast, be secure 1a<LI>to press, be urgent 1a<LI>to grow stout, grow rigid, grow hard (bad sense) 1a<LI>to be severe, be grievous<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to strengthen</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make strong<LI>to restore to strength, give strength<LI>to strengthen, sustain, encourage<LI>to make strong, make bold, encourage<LI>to make firm<LI>to make rigid, make hard</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make strong, strengthen<LI>to make firm<LI>to display strength<LI>to make severe<LI>to support<LI>to repair<LI>to prevail, prevail upon<LI>to have or take or keep hold of, retain, hold up, sustain, support<LI>to hold, contain</OL><LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strengthen oneself<LI>to put forth strength, use one\'s strength<LI>to withstand<LI>to hold strongly with</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2389, 'qzx', 'from (02388)', 'chazaq', 'TWOT - 636a', 'khaw-zawk\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02388»; strong (usu. in a bad sense, hard, bold, violent):--harder, hottest, + impudent, loud, mighty, sore, stiff(-hearted), strong(-er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>strong, stout, mighty<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>strong<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>severe, sharp, hot<LI>firm, hard</OL><LI>a strong one (subst)</OL></OL>'),
(2390, 'qzx', 'from (02388)', 'chazeq', 'TWOT - 636a?', 'khaw-zake\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02388»; powerful:--X wax louder, stronger.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stronger, louder</OL>'),
(2391, 'qzx', 'from (02388)', 'chezeq', 'TWOT - 636b', 'khay\'-zek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02388»; help:--strength.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>strength</OL>'),
(2392, 'qzx', 'from (02388)', 'chozeq', 'TWOT - 636c', 'kho\'-zek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02388»; power:--strength.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>strength</OL>'),
(2393, 'hqzx', 'from (02391)', 'chezqah', 'TWOT - 636b', 'khez-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02391»; prevailing power:--strength(- en self), (was) strong.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>strength, strong, being strong, force</OL>'),
(2394, 'hqzx', 'from (02392)', 'chozqah', 'TWOT - 636d', 'khoz-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02392»; vehemence (usually in a bad sense):--force, mightily, repair, sharply.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>force, might, strength, violence</OL>'),
(2395, 'yqzx', 'from (02388)', 'Chizqiy', 'None', 'khiz-kee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02388»; strong; Chizki, an Israelite:--Hezeki.', 'Hezeki = \"strong\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, descendant of Shaaraim</OL>'),
(2396, 'hyqzx', 'from (02388) and (03050)', 'Chizqiyah', 'None', 'khiz-kee-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Chizqiyahuw {khiz-kee-yaw\'-hoo}; also Ychizqiyah {yekh-iz-kee-yaw\'}; or Ychizqiyahuw {yekh-iz-kee-yaw\'-hoo}; from «02388» and «03050»; strengthened of Jah; Chizkijah, a king of Judah, also the name of two other Israelites:--Hezekiah, Hizkiah, Hizkijah. Compare «03169».', 'Hezekiah or Hizkiah or Hizkijah = \"Jehovah is my strength\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>12th king of Judah, son of Ahaz and Abijah; a good king in that he served Jehovah and did away with idolatrous practices<LI>great-great-grandfather of Zephaniah the prophet<LI>son of Neariah, a descendant of David<LI>head of a family of returning exiles in the time of Nehemiah</OL>'),
(2397, 'xx', 'from the same as (02336)', 'chach', 'TWOT - 620b', 'khawkh', 'Noun Masculine', 'once (Ezek. 29:4) chachiy {khakh-ee\'}; from the same as «02336»; a ring for the nose (or lips):--bracelet, chain, hook.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hook, ring, fetter, brooch<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>hook, ring (in nose of captive)<LI>hook, ring (as jewellery)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nose ring<LI>bracelet</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2398, 'atx', 'a primitive root', 'chata\'', 'TWOT - 638', 'khaw-taw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to miss; hence (figuratively and generally) to sin; by inference, to forfeit, lack, expiate, repent, (causatively) lead astray, condemn:--bear the blame, cleanse, commit (sin), by fault, harm he hath done, loss, miss, (make) offend(-er), offer for sin, purge, purify (self), make reconciliation, (cause, make) sin(-ful, -ness), trespass.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sin, miss, miss the way, go wrong, incur guilt, forfeit, purify from uncleanness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to miss<LI>to sin, miss the goal or path of right and duty<LI>to incur guilt, incur penalty by sin, forfeit</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bear loss<LI>to make a sin-offering<LI>to purify from sin<LI>to purify from uncleanness</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to miss the mark<LI>to induce to sin, cause to sin<LI>to bring into guilt or condemnation or punishment</OL><LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to miss oneself, lose oneself, wander from the way<LI>to purify oneself from uncleanness</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2399, 'atx', 'from (02398)', 'chet\'', 'TWOT - 638a', 'khate', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02398»; a crime or its penalty:--fault, × grievously, offence, (punishment of) sin.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sin<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>sin<LI>guilt for sin<LI>punishment for sin</OL></OL>'),
(2400, 'attx', 'intensively from (02398)', 'chatta\'', 'TWOT - 638b', 'khat-taw\'', '', 'intensively from «02398»; a criminal, or one accounted guilty:--offender, sinful, sinner.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sinners adj<LI>sinful<LI>exposed to condemnation, reckoned as offenders</OL>'),
(2401, 'hatx', 'from (02399)', 'chata\'ah', 'TWOT - 638d', 'khat-aw-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02399»; an offence, or a sacrifice for it:--sin (offering).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sin, sin offering<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>sin<LI>sin offering</OL></OL>'),
(2402, 'hattx', 'corresponding to (02401)', 'chatta\'ah', 'TWOT - 2726b', 'khat-taw-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02401»; an offence, and the penalty or sacrifice for it:--sin (offering).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sin offering</OL>'),
(2403, 'hattx', 'from (02398)', 'chatta\'ah', 'TWOT - 638e', 'khat-taw-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or chattacth {khat-tawth\'}; from «02398»; an offence (sometimes habitual sinfulness), and its penalty, occasion, sacrifice, or expiation; also (concretely) an offender:--punishment (of sin), purifying(-fication for sin), sin(-ner, offering).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sin, sinful<LI>sin, sin offering<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>sin<LI>condition of sin, guilt of sin<LI>punishment for sin<LI>sin-offering<LI>purification from sins of ceremonial uncleanness</OL></OL>'),
(2404, 'btx', 'a primitive root', 'chatab', 'TWOT - 639', 'khaw-tab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to chop or carve wood:--cut down, hew(-er), polish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut, gather<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to cut, gather (wood)<LI>(Pual) to cut, carve</OL></OL>'),
(2405, 'hbtx', 'pass. participle of (02404)', 'chatubah', 'TWOT - 640a', 'khat-oo-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine passive participle of «02404»; properly, a carving; hence, a tapestry (as figured):--carved.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>coloured fabric, dark-hued stuffs</OL>'),
(2406, 'httx', 'of uncertain derivation', 'chittah', 'TWOT - 691b', 'khit-taw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'of uncertain derivation; wheat, whether the grain or the plant:--wheat(-en).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wheat<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>wheat (plant)<LI>wheat flour</OL></OL>'),
(2407, 'Xwttx', 'from an unused root of uncertain signification', 'Chattuwsh', 'None', 'khat-toosh\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root of uncertain signification; Chattush, the name of four or five Israelites:--Hattush.', 'Hattush = \"assembled\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of David, apparently one of the sons of Shechaniah, in the 4th or 5th generation from Zerubbabel<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a man who returned with Ezra; maybe same as 1 above<LI>a man who returned with Zerubbabel; maybe same as 1 above</OL><LI>son of Hashabniah who helped repair the walls of Jerusalem with Nehemiah</OL>'),
(2408, 'ytx', 'from a root corresponding to (02398)', 'chatiy', 'TWOT - 2726a', 'khat-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «02398»; an offence:--sin.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sin</OL>'),
(2409, 'ayttx', 'from the same as (02408)', 'chattaya\'', 'TWOT - 2726b', 'khat-taw-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) from the same as «02408»; an expiation:--sin offering.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sin offering</OL>'),
(2410, 'atytx', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to dig out', 'Chatiyta\'', 'None', 'khat-ee-taw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to dig out; explorer; Chatita, a temple porter:--Hatita.', 'Hatita = \"exploring\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of a family of Levitical porters or gate-keepers who returned from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(2411, 'lyttx', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to wave', 'Chattiyl', 'None', 'khat-teel\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to wave; fluctuating; Chattil, one of \"Solomon\'s servants\":--Hattil.', 'Hattil = \"doubtful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of a family of the children of Solomon\'s slaves who returned from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(2412, 'apytx', 'from (02414)', 'Chatiypha\'', 'None', 'khat-ee-faw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02414»; robber; Chatipha, one of the Nethinim:--Hatipha.', 'Hatipha = \"seized\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of a family of temple slaves who returned from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(2413, '~tx', 'a primitive root', 'chatam', 'TWOT - 641', 'khaw-tam\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to stop:--refrain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hold in, restrain<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to restrain (oneself)</OL></OL>'),
(2414, '@tx', 'a primitive root', 'chataph', 'TWOT - 642', 'khaw-taf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to clutch; hence, to seize as a prisoner:--catch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to catch, seize</OL>'),
(2415, 'rtx', 'from an unused root of uncertain signification', 'choter', 'TWOT - 643a', 'kho\'-ter', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root of uncertain signification; a twig:--rod.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>branch, twig, rod</OL>'),
(2416, 'yx', 'from (02421)', 'chay', 'TWOT - 644a', 'khah\'-ee', '', 'from «02421»; alive; hence, raw (flesh); fresh (plant, water, year), strong; also (as noun, especially in the feminine singular and masculine plural) life (or living thing), whether literally or figuratively:--+ age, alive, appetite, (wild) beast, company, congregation, life(-time), live(-ly), living (creature, thing), maintenance, + merry, multitude, + (be) old, quick, raw, running, springing, troop.', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>living, alive<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>green (of vegetation)<LI>flowing, fresh (of water)<LI>lively, active (of man)<LI>reviving (of the springtime) n m</OL><LI>relatives<LI>life (abstract emphatic)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>life<LI>sustenance, maintenance n f</OL><LI>living thing, animal<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>animal<LI>life<LI>appetite<LI>revival, renewal</OL><LI>community</OL>'),
(2417, 'yx', 'from (02418)', 'chay', 'TWOT - 2727a', 'khah\'-ee', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) from «02418»; alive; also (as noun in plural) life:--life, that liveth, living.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>alive, living, life</OL>'),
(2418, 'ayx', 'corresponding to (02421)', 'chaya\'', 'TWOT - 2727', 'khah-yaw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) or chayah (Aramaic) {khah-yaw\'}; corresponding to «02421»; to live:--live, keep alive.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to live<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to live<LI>(Aphel) to let live, keep alive</OL></OL>'),
(2419, 'layx', 'from (02416) and (0410)', 'Chiy\'el', 'None', 'khee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02416» and «0410»; living of God; Chiel, an Israelite:--Hiel.', 'Hiel = \"God lives\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a native of Bethel who rebuilt Jericho in the reign of Ahab and in whom was fulfilled the curse pronounced by Joshua</OL>'),
(2420, 'hdyx', 'from (02330)', 'chiydah', 'TWOT - 616a', 'khee-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02330»; a puzzle, hence, a trick, conundrum, sententious maxim:--dark saying (sentence, speech), hard question, proverb, riddle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>riddle, difficult question, parable, enigmatic saying or question, perplexing saying or question<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>riddle (dark obscure utterance)<LI>riddle, enigma (to be guessed)<LI>perplexing questions (difficult)<LI>double dealing (with \'havin\')</OL></OL>'),
(2421, 'hyx', 'a primitive root [compare (02331), (02421)]', 'chayah', 'TWOT - 644', 'khaw-yaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «02331», «02421»); to live, whether literally or figuratively; causatively, to revive:--keep (leave, make) alive, × certainly, give (promise) life, (let, suffer to) live, nourish up, preserve (alive), quicken, recover, repair, restore (to life), revive, (X God) save (alive, life, lives), × surely, be whole.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to live, have life, remain alive, sustain life, live prosperously, live for ever, be quickened, be alive, be restored to life or health<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to live 1a</OL><LI>to have life 1a<LI>to continue in life, remain alive 1a<LI>to sustain life, to live on or upon 1a<LI>to live (prosperously)<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to revive, be quickened 1a</OL><LI>from sickness 1a<LI>from discouragement 1a<LI>from faintness 1a<LI>from death<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to preserve alive, let live<LI>to give life<LI>to quicken, revive, refresh 1b</OL><LI>to restore to life 1b<LI>to cause to grow 1b<LI>to restore 1b<LI>to revive<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to preserve alive, let live<LI>to quicken, revive 1c</OL><LI>to restore (to health) 1c<LI>to revive 1c<LI>to restore to life</OL></OL>'),
(2422, 'hyx', 'from (02421)', 'chayeh', 'TWOT - 644e', 'khaw-yeh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02421»; vigorous:--lively.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vigorous, lively, having the vigour of life</OL>'),
(2423, 'awyx', 'from (02418)', 'cheyva\'', 'TWOT - 2727b', 'khay-vaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) from «02418»; an animal:--beast.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>beast, animal</OL>'),
(2424, 'twyx', 'from (02421)', 'chayuwth', 'TWOT - 644g', 'khah-yooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02421»; life:--X living.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>living</OL>'),
(2425, 'yyx', 'a primitive root [compare (02421)]', 'chayay', 'TWOT - 644', 'khaw-yah\'-ee', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «02421»); to live; causatively to revive:--live, save life.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to live, have life, remain alive, sustain life, live prosperously, live for ever, be quickened, be alive, be restored to life or health<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to live 1a</OL><LI>to have life 1a<LI>to continue in life, remain alive 1a<LI>to sustain life, to live on or upon 1a<LI>to live (prosperously)<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to revive, be quickened 1a</OL><LI>from sickness 1a<LI>from discouragement 1a<LI>from faintness 1a<LI>from death<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to preserve alive, let live<LI>to give life<LI>to quicken, revive, refresh 1b</OL><LI>to restore to life 1b<LI>to cause to grow 1b<LI>to restore 1b<LI>to revive<LI>(Hiph)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to preserve alive, let live<LI>to quicken, revive 1c</OL><LI>to restore (to health) 1c<LI>to revive 1c<LI>to restore to life</OL></OL>'),
(2426, 'lyx', 'a collateral form of (02428)', 'cheyl', 'TWOT - 623d', 'khale', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (shortened) chel {khale}; a collateral form of «02428»; an army; also (by analogy,) an intrenchment:--army, bulwark, host, + poor, rampart, trench, wall.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rampart, fortress, wall<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>rampart<LI>fortress</OL></OL>'),
(2427, 'lyx', 'from (02342)', 'chiyl', 'TWOT - 623b', 'kheel', 'Noun Masculine', 'and (feminine) chiylah {khee-law\'}; from «02342»; a throe (expectant of childbirth):--pain, pang, sorrow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pain, agony, sorrow, a writhing, anguish<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>writhing (of fear)<LI>anguish</OL></OL>'),
(2428, 'lyx', 'from (02342)', 'chayil', 'TWOT - 624a', 'khah\'-yil', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02342»; probably a force, whether of men, means or other resources; an army, wealth, virtue, valor, strength:--able, activity, (+) army, band of men (soldiers), company, (great) forces, goods, host, might, power, riches, strength, strong, substance, train, (+)valiant(-ly), valour, virtuous(-ly), war, worthy(-ily).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>strength, might, efficiency, wealth, army<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>strength<LI>ability, efficiency<LI>wealth<LI>force, army</OL></OL>'),
(2429, 'lyx', 'corresponding to (02428)', 'chayil', 'TWOT - 2728', 'khah\'-yil', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02428»; an army, or strength:--aloud, army, × most (mighty), power.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>strength, army, power<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>power<LI>force, army</OL></OL>'),
(2430, 'hlyx', 'from (02428)', 'cheylah', 'TWOT - 623e', 'khay-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02428»; an intrenchment:--bulwark.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bulwark, entrenchment, rampart, fortress</OL>'),
(2431, '~lyx', 'from (02428)', 'Cheylam', 'None', 'khay-lawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Cheleam {khay-lawm\'}; from «02428»; fortress; Chelam, a place East of Palestine:--Helam.', 'Helam = \"stronghold\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place east of the Jordan, west of the Euphrates, in Gilead, at which the Syrians under Hadarezer were defeated by David</OL>'),
(2432, '!lyx', 'from (02428)', 'Chiylen', 'None', 'khee-lane\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02428»; fortress; Chilen, a place in Palestine:--Hilen.', 'Hilen = \"place of caves\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city of Judah allotted to the priests</OL>'),
(2433, '!yx', 'another form for (02580)', 'chiyn', 'TWOT - 694c', 'kheen', 'Noun Masculine', 'another form for «02580»; beauty:--comely.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>beauty, grace</OL>'),
(2434, '#yx', 'another form for (02351)', 'chayits', 'TWOT - 628a', 'khah\'-yits', 'Noun Masculine', 'another form for «02351»; a wall:--wall.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wall, party-wall, thin wall</OL>'),
(2435, '!wcyx', 'from (02434)', 'chiytsown', 'TWOT - 627b', 'khee-tsone\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02434»; properly, the (outer) wall side; hence, exterior; figuratively, secular (as opposed to sacred):--outer, outward, utter, without.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>outer, external, outward</OL>'),
(2436, 'qyx', 'from an unused root, apparently meaning to inclose', 'cheyq', 'TWOT - 629a', 'khake', 'Noun Masculine', 'or cheq {khake}; and chowq {khoke}; from an unused root, apparently meaning to inclose; the bosom (literally or figuratively):--bosom, bottom, lap, midst, within.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bosom, hollow, bottom, midst</OL>'),
(2437, 'hryx', 'from (02357) in the sense of splendour', 'Chiyrah', 'None', 'khee-raw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02357» in the sense of splendor; Chirah, an Adullamite:--Hirah.', 'Hirah = \"a noble family\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Adullamite, the friend of Judah</OL>'),
(2438, '~ryx', 'another form of (02361)', 'Chiyram', 'None', 'khee-rawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Chiyrowm {khee-rome\'}; another form of «02361»; Chiram or Chirom, the name of two Tyrians:--Hiram, Huram.', 'Hiram, Huram = \"noble\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the king of Tyre who sent workmen and materials to Jerusalem to build both the palace for David and the temple for Solomon<LI>the chief architect and engineer of Solomon\'s temple sent by King Hiram to Solomon</OL>'),
(2439, 'Xyx', 'another form of (02363)', 'chiysh', 'TWOT - 631', 'kheesh', 'Verb', 'another form of «02363»; to hurry:--make haste.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to haste, make haste, hurry<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to make haste<LI>(Hiph)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to show haste, act quickly, hasten, come quickly<LI>to enjoy, be excited</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2440, 'Xyx', 'from (02439)', 'chiysh', 'TWOT - 631a', 'kheesh', 'Adverb', 'from «02439»; properly, a hurry; hence (adverb) quickly:--soon.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>quickly</OL>'),
(2441, '$x', 'probably from (02596) in the sense of tasting', 'chek', 'TWOT - 692a', 'khake', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from «02596» in the sense of tasting; properly, the palate or inside of the mouth; hence, the mouth itself (as the organ of speech, taste and kissing):--(roof of the) mouth, taste.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mouth, palate, taste, gums</OL>'),
(2442, 'hkx', 'a primitive root [apparently akin to (02707) through the idea of piercing]', 'chakah', 'TWOT - 645', 'khaw-kaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (apparently akin to «02707» through the idea of piercing); properly, to adhere to; hence, to await:--long, tarry, wait.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wait, wait for, await<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to wait for<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wait, tarry<LI>to wait (in ambush)<LI>to wait for, long for</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2443, 'hkkx', 'probably from (02442)', 'chakkah', 'TWOT - 693c', 'khak-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'probably from «02442»; a hook (as adhering):--angle, hook.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hook, angle, hook fastened in jaw, fish hook</OL>'),
(2444, 'hlykx', 'from the same as (02447)', 'Chakiylah', 'None', 'khak-ee-law\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the same as «02447»; dark; Chakilah, a hill in Palestine:--Hachilah.', 'Hachilah = \"dark\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a hill is southern Judah, on the edge of the wilderness of Ziph</OL>'),
(2445, '~ykkx', 'from a root corresponding to (02449)', 'chakkiym', 'TWOT - 2729a', 'khak-keem\'', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «02449»; wise, i.e. a Magian:--wise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wise man, wise</OL>'),
(2446, 'hylkx', 'from the base of (02447) and (03050)', 'Chakalyah', 'None', 'khak-al-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the base of «02447» and «03050»; darkness of Jah; Chakaljah, an Israelite:--Hachaliah.', 'Hachaliah = \"whom Jehovah enlightens\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the father of Nehemiah</OL>'),
(2447, 'lylkx', 'by reduplication from an unused root apparently meaning to be dark', 'chakliyl', 'TWOT - 646a', 'khak-leel\'', 'Adjective Masculine', 'by reduplication from an unused root apparently meaning to be dark; darkly flashing (only of the eyes); in a good sense, brilliant (as stimulated by wine):--red.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dull<LI>(CLBL) dark-flashing, brilliant</OL>'),
(2448, 'twllkx', 'from (02447)', 'chakliluwth', 'TWOT - 646b', 'khak-lee-looth\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02447»; flash (of the eyes); in a bad sense, blearedness:--redness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>redness, dullness</OL>'),
(2449, '~kx', 'a primitive root', 'chakam', 'TWOT - 647', 'khaw-kam\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root, to be wise (in mind, word or act):--X  exceeding, teach wisdom, be (make self, shew self) wise, deal (never so) wisely, make wiser.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be wise<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be or become wise, act wisely<LI>(Piel) to make wise, teach wisdom, instruct<LI>(Pual) to be made wise<LI>(Hiphil) to make wise<LI>(Hithpael) to show oneself wise, deceive, show one\'s wisdom</OL></OL>'),
(2450, '~kx', 'from (02449)', 'chakam', 'TWOT - 647b', 'khaw-kawm\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02449»; wise, (i.e. intelligent, skilful or artful):--cunning (man), subtil, ((un-)), wise((hearted), man).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wise, wise (man)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>skilful (in technical work)<LI>wise (in administration)<LI>shrewd, crafty, cunning, wily, subtle<LI>learned, shrewd (class of men)<LI>prudent<LI>wise (ethically and religiously)</OL></OL>'),
(2451, 'hmkx', 'from (02449)', 'chokmah', 'TWOT - 647a', 'khok-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02449»; wisdom (in a good sense):--skilful, wisdom, wisely, wit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wisdom<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>skill (in war)<LI>wisdom (in administration)<LI>shrewdness, wisdom<LI>wisdom, prudence (in religious affairs)<LI>wisdom (ethical and religious)</OL></OL>'),
(2452, 'hmkx', 'corresponding to (02451)', 'chokmah', 'TWOT - 2729b', 'khok-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02451»; wisdom:--wisdom.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wisdom</OL>'),
(2453, 'ynwmkx', 'from (02449)', 'Cahkmowniy', 'None', 'khak-mo-nee\'', '', 'from «02449»; skilful; Chakmoni, an Israelite:--Hachmoni, Hachmonite.', 'Hachmoni or Hachmonite = \"wise\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of one of David\'s mighty warriors<LI>father of the tutor of David\'s sons n patr m<LI>the family of one of David\'s servants</OL>'),
(2454, 'twmkx', 'collateral forms of (02451)', 'chokmowth', 'TWOT - 647a', 'khok-moth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or chakmowth {khak-moth\'}; collateral forms of «02451»; wisdom:--wisdom, every wise (woman).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wisdom</OL>'),
(2455, 'lx', 'from (02490)', 'chol', 'TWOT - 623a,661a', 'khole', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02490»; properly, exposed; hence, profane:--common, profane (place), unholy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>profaneness, commonness, unholy, profane, common, sand</OL>'),
(2456, 'alx', 'a primitive root [compare (02470)]', 'chala\'', 'TWOT - 648', 'khaw-law\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «02470»); to be sick:--be diseased.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to suffer, be sick, be diseased</OL>'),
(2457, 'halx', 'from (02456)', 'chel\'ah', 'TWOT - 649a', 'khel-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02456»; properly, disease; hence, rust:--scum.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rust, scum</OL>'),
(2458, 'halx', 'the same as (02457)', 'Chel\'ah', 'None', 'khel-aw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'the same as «02457»; Chelah, an Israelitess:--Helah.', 'Helah = \"rust\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the two wives of Ashur, father of Tekoah</OL>'),
(2459, 'blx', 'from an unused root meaning to be fat', 'cheleb', 'TWOT - 651a', 'kheh\'-leb', 'Noun Masculine', 'or cheleb {khay\'-leb}; from an unused root meaning to be fat; fat, whether literally or figuratively; hence, the richest or choice part:--X best, fat(-ness), × finest, grease, marrow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fat<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>fat (of humans)<LI>fat (of beasts)<LI>choicest, best part, abundance (of products of the land)</OL></OL>'),
(2460, 'blx', 'the same as (02459)', 'Cheleb', 'None', 'khay\'-leb', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «02459»; fatness; Cheleb, an Israelite:--Heleb.', 'Heleb = \"milk\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Baanah, the Netophathite, and one of David\'s mighty warriors; also spelled \'Heled\' (02466)</OL>'),
(2461, 'blx', 'from the same as (02459)', 'chalab', 'TWOT - 650a', 'khaw-lawb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «02459»; milk (as the richness of kine):--+ cheese, milk, sucking.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>milk, sour milk, cheese<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>milk<LI>abundance of the land (metaph.)<LI>white (as milk)</OL></OL>'),
(2462, 'hblx', 'feminine of (02459)', 'Chelbah', 'None', 'khel-baw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'feminine of «02459»; fertility: Chelbah, a place in Palestine:--Helbah.', 'Helbah = \"fertile\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town of Asher, probably on the plain of Phoenicia not far from Sidon</OL>'),
(2463, '!wblx', 'from (02459)', 'Chelbown', 'None', 'khel-bone\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02459»; fruitful; Chelbon, a place in Syria:--Helbah.', 'Helbon = \"fertile\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town a few miles northwest of Damascus, modern \'Helbon\', still noted for its fine grapes</OL>'),
(2464, 'hnblx', 'from (02459)', 'chelbnah', 'TWOT - 652', 'khel-ben-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02459»; galbanam, an odorous gum (as if fatty):--galbanum.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>galbanum<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a kind of resin or gum, ingredient of the holy incense</OL></OL>'),
(2465, 'dlx', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to glide swiftly', 'cheled', 'TWOT - 653a', 'kheh\'-led', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to glide swiftly; life (as a fleeting portion of time); hence, the world (as transient):--age, short time, world.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>age, duration of life, the world</OL>'),
(2466, 'dlx', 'the same as (02465)', 'cheled', 'None', 'khay\'-led', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «02465»; Cheled, an Israelite:--Heled.', 'Heled = \"transient\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Baanah, the Netophathite, and one of David\'s mighty warriors; also spelled \'Heleb\' (02460)</OL>'),
(2467, 'dlx', 'from the same as (02465)', 'choled', 'TWOT - 654a', 'kho\'-led', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «02465»; a weasel (from its gliding motion):--weasel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>weasel, mole<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps an extinct animal, exact meaning unknown</OL></OL>'),
(2468, 'hdlx', 'from (02467)', 'Chuldah', 'None', 'khool-daw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'feminine of «02467»; Chuldah, an Israelitess:--Huldah.', 'Huldah = \"weasel\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a prophetess in the time of Josiah whom Josiah asked for an authoritative opinion on the book of the law which Hilkiah found</OL>'),
(2469, 'ydlx', 'from (02466)', 'Chelday', 'None', 'khel-dah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02466»; worldliness; Cheldai, the name of two Israelites:--Heldai.', 'Heldai = \"worldly\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of David\'s mighty warriors and the 12th captain of the monthly courses for the temple service<LI>a returning exile in the time of Zechariah</OL>'),
(2470, 'hlx', 'a primitive root [compare (02342), (02470), (02490)]', 'chalah', 'TWOT - 655', 'khaw-law\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «02342», «02470», «02490»); properly, to be rubbed or worn; hence (figuratively) to be weak, sick, afflicted; or (causatively) to grieve, make sick; also to stroke (in flattering), entreat:--beseech, (be) diseased, (put to) grief, be grieved, (be) grievous, infirmity, intreat, lay to, put to pain, × pray, make prayer, be (fall, make) sick, sore, be sorry, make suit (X supplication), woman in travail, be (become) weak, be wounded.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or become weak, be or become sick, be or become diseased, be or become grieved, be or become sorry<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be weak, be sick<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or become weak, feel weak<LI>to become sick, become ill<LI>(CLBL) to entreat, pray, beg</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make oneself sick<LI>to be made sick<LI>to be tired</OL><LI>(Pual) to be made weak, become weak<LI>(Hithpael) to make oneself sick<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make sore<LI>to make sick<LI>to show signs of sickness, become sick<LI>to grieve</OL><LI>(Hophal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be made sick<LI>to be wounded</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2471, 'hllx', 'from (02490)', 'challah', 'TWOT - 660b', 'khal-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02490»; a cake (as usually punctured):--cake.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cake, cake (if pierced) (probably perforated)</OL>'),
(2472, '~wlx', 'from (02492)', 'chalowm', 'TWOT - 663a', 'khal-ome\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (shortened) chalom {khal-ome\'}; from «02492»; a dream:--dream(-er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dream<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>dream (ordinary)<LI>dream (with prophetic meaning)</OL></OL>'),
(2473, '!wlx', 'probably from (02344)', 'Cholown', 'None', 'kho-lone\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or (shortened) Cholon {kho-lone\'}; probably from «02344»; sandy; Cholon, the name of two places in Palestine:--Holon.', 'Holon = \"sandy\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in the mountains of Judah given to the priests<LI>a city of Moab; site unknown</OL>'),
(2474, '!wllx', 'unknown derivation', 'challown', 'TWOT - 660c', 'khal-lone\'', 'Noun', 'a window (as perforated):--window.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>window (piercing of the wall)</OL>'),
(2475, '@wlx', 'from (02498)', 'chalowph', 'TWOT - 666b', 'khal-ofe\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02498»; properly, surviving; by implication (collectively) orphans:--X destruction.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>destruction, passing away, vanishing, appointed to destruction</OL>'),
(2476, 'hXwlx', 'pass. participle of (02522)', 'chaluwshah', 'TWOT - 671b', 'khal-oo-shaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine passive participle of «02522»; defeat:--being overcome.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>weakness, defeat, prostration</OL>'),
(2477, 'xlx', 'probably of foreign origin', 'Chalach', 'None', 'khal-akh\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'probably of foreign origin; Chalach, a region of Assyria:--Halah.', 'Halah = \"painful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city or district in Mesopotamia under Assyrian control where the Israelite captives were taken</OL>'),
(2478, 'lwxlx', 'by reduplication from (02342)', 'Chalchuwl', 'None', 'khal-khool\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'by reduplication from «02342»; contorted; Chalchul, a place in Palestine:--Halhul.', 'Halhul = \"trembling\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town on a hill in the mountains of Judah to the left of the road from Jerusalem to Hebron and about 3-4 (5-7 km) miles from Hebron</OL>'),
(2479, 'hlxlx', 'from the same as (02478)', 'chalchalah', 'TWOT - 623f', 'khal-khaw-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from the same as «02478»; writhing (in childbirth); by implication, terror:--(great, much) pain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pain, trembling, terror, writhing, anguish</OL>'),
(2480, 'tlx', 'a primitive root', 'chalat', 'TWOT - 658', 'khaw-lat\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to snatch at:--catch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to take up, catch, pick up (a word)</OL>'),
(2481, 'ylx', 'from (02470)', 'chaliy', 'TWOT - 657a', 'khal-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02470»; a trinket (as polished):--jewel, ornament.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>jewellery, ornament</OL>'),
(2482, 'ylx', 'the same as (02481)', 'Chaliy', 'None', 'khal-ee\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «02481»; Chali, a place in Palestine:--Hali.', 'Hali = \"necklace\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town on the boundary of Asher between Helkath and Beten</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(2483, 'ylx', 'from (02470)', 'choliy', 'TWOT - 655a', 'khol-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02470»; malady, anxiety, calamity:--disease, grief, (is) sick(-ness).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sickness</OL>'),
(2484, 'hylx', 'from (02481)', 'chelyah', 'TWOT - 657b', 'khel-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02481»; a trinket:--jewel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>jewels, jewelry</OL>'),
(2485, 'lylx', 'from (02490)', 'chaliyl', 'TWOT - 660d', 'khaw-leel\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02490»; a flute (as perforated):--pipe.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pipe, flute</OL>'),
(2486, 'hlylx', 'a directive from (02490)', 'chaliylah', 'TWOT - 661c', 'khaw-lee\'-law', 'Interjection', 'or chalilah {khaw-lee\'-law}; a directive from «02490»; literal for a profaned thing; used (interj.) far be it!:--be far, (X  God) forbid.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>far be it (from me), God forbid that, let it not be</OL>'),
(2487, 'hpylx', 'from (02498)', 'chaliyphah', 'TWOT - 666c', 'khal-ee-faw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02498»; alternation:--change, course.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a change, change (of garments), replacement<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>change (of raiment)<LI>relays<LI>relief (from death)<LI>changing, varying (course of life)</OL></OL>'),
(2488, 'hcylx', 'from (02503)', 'chaliytsah', 'TWOT - 667a,668a', 'khal-ee-tsaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02503»; spoil:--armour.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>what is stripped off (a person in war), armour, spoils, belt</OL>'),
(2489, 'aklx', 'apparently from an unused root probably meaning to be dark or (fig.) unhappy', 'chelka\'', 'TWOT - 659a', 'khay-lek-aw\'', 'Adjective', 'or chelkah {khay-lek-aw\'}; apparently from an unused root probably meaning to be dark or (figuratively) unhappy; a wretch, i.e. unfortunate:--poor.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hapless, poor, unfortunate person</OL>'),
(2490, 'llx', 'a primitive root [compare (02470)]', 'chalal', 'TWOT - 660,661', 'khaw-lal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «02470»); properly, to bore, i.e. (by implication) to wound, to dissolve; figuratively, to profane (a person, place or thing), to break (one\'s word), to begin (as if by an \"opening wedge\"); denom. (from «02485») to play (the flute):--begin (X men began), defile, × break, defile, × eat (as common things), × first, × gather the grape thereof, ×  take inheritance, pipe, player on instruments, pollute, (cast as) profane (self), prostitute, slay (slain), sorrow, stain, wound.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to profane, defile, pollute, desecrate, begin<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to profane oneself, defile oneself, pollute oneself 1a</OL><LI>ritually 1a<LI>sexually<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to be polluted, be defiled</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to profane, make common, defile, pollute<LI>to violate the honour of, dishonour<LI>to violate (a covenant)<LI>to treat as common</OL><LI>(Pual) to profane (name of God)<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to let be profaned<LI>to begin</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be begun</OL><LI>to wound (fatally), bore through, pierce, bore<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to pierce<LI>(Pual) to be slain<LI>(Poel) to wound, pierce<LI>(Poal) to be wounded</OL><LI>(Piel) to play the flute or pipe</OL>'),
(2491, 'llx', 'from (02490)', 'chalal', 'TWOT - 660a', 'khaw-lawl\'', '', 'from «02490»; pierced (especially to death); figuratively, polluted:--kill, profane, slain (man), × slew, (deadly) wounded.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>slain, fatally wounded, pierced<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>pierced, fatally wounded<LI>slain adj</OL><LI>(CLBL) profaned<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>defiled, profaned (by divorce)</OL></OL>'),
(2492, '~lx', 'a primitive root', 'chalam', 'TWOT - 662,663', 'khaw-lam\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to bind firmly, i.e. (by implication) to be (causatively to make) plump; also (through the figurative sense of dumbness) to dream:--(cause to) dream(-er), be in good liking, recover.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dream<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dream (ordinary)<LI>to dream (prophetic)<LI>to dream (of false prophets)</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to dream</OL><LI>to be healthy, be strong<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be healthy<LI>(Hiphil) to restore to health</OL></OL>'),
(2493, '~lx', 'from a root corresponding to (02492)', 'chelem', 'TWOT - 2730', 'khay\'-lem', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «02492»; a dream:--dream.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dream</OL>'),
(2494, '~lx', 'from (02492)', 'Chelem', 'None', 'khay\'lem', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02492»; a dream; Chelem, an Israelite:--Helem. Compare «02469».', 'Helem = \"strength\" or \"dream\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a returned exile in the time of Zechariah; also spelled \'Heldai\'</OL>'),
(2495, 'twmllx', 'from (02492) (in the sense of insipidity)', 'challamuwth', 'TWOT - 664', 'khal-law-mooth\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02492» (in the sense of insipidity); probably purslain:--egg.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>purslane, a tasteless plant with thick slimy juice</OL>'),
(2496, 'Xymllx', 'probably from (02492) (in the sense of hardness)', 'challamiysh', 'TWOT - 665', 'klal-law-meesh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from «02492» (in the sense of hardness); flint:--flint(-y), rock.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flint, rock</OL>'),
(2497, '!lx', 'from (02428)', 'Chelon', 'None', 'khay-lone\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02428»; strong; Chelon, an Israelite:--Helon.', 'Helon = \"strength\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Eliab of the tribe of Zebulun</OL>'),
(2498, '@lx', 'a primitive root', 'chalaph', 'TWOT - 666', 'khaw-laf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to slide by, i.e. (by implication) to hasten away, pass on, spring up, pierce or change:--abolish, alter, change, cut off, go on forward, grow up, be over, pass (away, on, through), renew, sprout, strike through.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pass on or away, pass through, pass by, go through, grow up, change, to go on from<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pass on quickly<LI>to pass away (vanish)<LI>to come on anew, sprout again (of grass)<LI>to pass through<LI>to overstep, transgress</OL><LI>(Piel) to cause to pass, change<LI>(Hiph)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to change, substitute, alter, change for better, renew<LI>to show newness (of tree)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2499, '@lx', 'corresponding to (02498)', 'chalaph', 'TWOT - 2731', 'khal-af\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02498»; to pass on (of time):--pass.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pass by, pass over<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pe) to pass by, pass over</OL></OL>'),
(2500, '@lx', 'from (02498)', 'cheleph', 'TWOT - 666a', 'klay\'-lef', '', 'from «02498»; properly, exchange; hence (as preposition) instead of:--X for.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in exchange for (only construct) prep<LI>in return for</OL>'),
(2501, '@lx', 'the same as (02500)', 'Cheleph', 'None', 'kheh\'lef', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «02500»; change; Cheleph, a place in Palestine:--Heleph.', 'Heleph = \"exchange\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the place from which the boundary of Naphtali started, site unknown</OL>'),
(2502, '#lx', 'a primitive root', 'chalats', 'TWOT - 667,668', 'khaw-lats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pull off; hence (intensively) to strip, (reflex.) to depart; by implication, to deliver, equip (for fight); present, strengthen:--arm (self), (go, ready) armed (X  man, soldier), deliver, draw out, make fat, loose, (ready) prepared, put off, take away, withdraw self.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to remove, draw out, draw off, take off, withdraw, equip (for war), arm for war, rescue, be rescued<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) equipped (participle)<LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be equipped<LI>to go equipped<LI>to be armed</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make strong, brace up<LI>to invigorate</OL></OL><LI>to draw off or out, withdraw<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to draw, draw off<LI>to withdraw</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be delivered<LI>to be saved</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pull out, tear out<LI>to rescue, deliver, set free<LI>to take away, plunder</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2503, '#lx', 'from (02502)', 'Chelets', 'None', 'kheh\'-lets', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Chelets {khay\'-lets; from «02502»; perhaps, strength; Chelets, the name of two Israelites:--Helez.', 'Helez = \"he has saved\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Ephraimite, one of the 30 of David\'s mighty warriors, leader of the 7th monthly course<LI>a man of Judah, son of Azariah</OL>'),
(2504, '#lx', 'from (02502) (in the sense of strength)', 'chalats', 'TWOT - 668? (668b)', 'khaw-lawts\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02502» (in the sense of strength); only in the dual; the loins (as the seat of vigor):--loins, reins.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>loins<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>as seat of virility<LI>as girded<LI>as seat of pain (woman\'s travail)</OL></OL>'),
(2505, 'qlx', 'a primitive root', 'chalaq', 'TWOT - 669', 'khaw-lak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be smooth (figuratively); by implication (as smooth stones were used for lots) to apportion or separate:--deal, distribute, divide, flatter, give, (have, im-)part(-ner), take away a portion, receive, separate self, (be) smooth(-er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to divide, share, plunder, allot, apportion, assign<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to divide, apportion<LI>to assign, distribute<LI>to assign, impart<LI>to share<LI>to divide up, plunder</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to divide oneself<LI>to be divided<LI>to assign, distribute</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to divide, apportion<LI>to assign, distribute<LI>to scatter</OL><LI>(Pual) to be divided<LI>(Hiphil) to receive a portion or part<LI>(Hithpael) to divide among themselves</OL><LI>to be smooth, slippery, deceitful<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be smooth, slippery<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be smooth<LI>to flatter</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2506, 'qlx', 'from (02505)', 'cheleq', 'TWOT - 669a', 'khay\'lek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02505»; properly, smoothness (of the tongue); also an allotment:--flattery, inheritance, part, × partake, portion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>portion, share, part, territory<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>portion, share<LI>portion, tract, parcel (of land)<LI>one\'s portion, one\'s possession<LI>(chosen) portion<LI>portion, award (from God)</OL><LI>smoothness, seductiveness, flattery</OL>'),
(2507, 'qlx', 'the same as (02506)', 'Cheleq', 'None', 'khay\'-lek', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «02506»; portion; Chelek, an Israelite:--Helek.', 'Helek = \"portion\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Manasseh, and 2nd son of Gilead</OL>'),
(2508, 'qlx', 'from a root corresponding to (02505)', 'chalaq', 'TWOT - 2732a', 'khal-awk\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «02505»; a part:--portion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>portion, possession, lot</OL>'),
(2509, 'qlx', 'from (02505)', 'chalaq', 'TWOT - 670b', 'khaw-lawk\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02505»; smooth (especially of tongue):--flattering, smooth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flattering, smooth</OL>'),
(2510, 'qlx', 'the same as (02509)', 'Chalaq', 'None', 'khaw-lawk\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «02509»; bare; Chalak, a mountain of Idumaea:--Halak.', 'Halak = \"smooth\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a mountain in southern Judah which is the southern limit of Joshua\'s conquest; site unknown</OL>'),
(2511, 'qllx', 'from (02505)', 'challaq', 'TWOT - 670d', 'khal-lawk\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02505»; smooth:--smooth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>smooth</OL>'),
(2512, 'qllx', 'from (02505)', 'challuq', 'TWOT - 670d', 'khal-look\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02505»; smooth:--smooth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>smooth</OL>'),
(2513, 'hqlx', 'from (02506)', 'chelqah', 'TWOT - 670c', 'khel-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02506»; properly, smoothness; figuratively, flattery; also an allotment:--field, flattering(-ry), ground, parcel, part, piece of land (ground), plat, portion, slippery place, smooth (thing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>portion, parcel<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of ground</OL><LI>smooth part, smoothness, flattery<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>smoothness, smooth part<LI>slippery places<LI>smoothness, flattery</OL></OL>'),
(2514, 'hqqlx', 'from (02505)', 'chalaqqah', 'TWOT - 670e', 'khal-ak-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from «02505»; flattery:--flattery.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flattery, smoothness, fine promises</OL>'),
(2515, 'hqqlx', 'from (02512)', 'chaluqqah', 'TWOT - 669c', 'khal-ook-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02512»; a distribution:--division.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>division, part, portion</OL>'),
(2516, 'yqlx', 'patronymically from (02507)', 'Chelqiy', 'None', 'khel-kee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'patronymically from «02507»; a Chelkite or descendant of Chelek:--Helkites.', 'Helekites = \"flattering\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Helek</OL>'),
(2517, 'yqlx', 'from (02505)', 'Chelqay', 'None', 'khel-kah\'ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02505»; apportioned; Chelkai, an Israelite:--Helkai.', 'Helkai = \"my portion is Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chief of Meremoth\'s priestly family in the time of Joiakim</OL>'),
(2518, 'hyqlx', 'from (02506) and (03050)', 'Chilqiyah', 'None', 'khil-kee-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Chilqiyahuw {khil-kee-yaw\'-hoo}\'from «02506» and «03050»; portion of Jah; {Chilhijah, the name of eight Israelites:-- Hillkiah.', 'Hilkiah = \"my portion is Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Eliakim, an officer of Hezekiah<LI>high priest in the reign of Josiah<LI>a Merarite Levite, son of Amzi<LI>another Merarite Levite, 2nd son of Hosah<LI>one of those who stood on the right of Ezra when he read the law and probably a Levite and a priest<LI>a priest of Anathoth, father of the prophet Jeremiah<LI>father of Gemariah who was one of Zedekiah\'s envoys to Babylon</OL>'),
(2519, 'hqqlqlx', 'by reduplication from (02505)', 'chalaqlaqqah', 'TWOT - 670f', 'khal-ak-lak-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'by reduplication from «02505»; properly, something very smooth; i.e. a treacherous spot; figuratively, blandishment:--flattery, slippery.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flattery, slipperiness, fine promises, smoothness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>slipperiness<LI>fine promises</OL></OL>'),
(2520, 'tqlx', 'a form of (02513)', 'Chelqath', 'None', 'khel-kath\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'a form of «02513»; smoothness; Chelkath, a place in Palestine:--Helkath.', 'Helkath = \"smooth\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the town named as the starting point for the boundary of the tribe of Asher and allotted with its suburbs to the Gershonite Levites</OL>'),
(2521, '~yrcch tqlx', 'from (02520) and the pl. of (06697), with the article inserted', 'Chelqath', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02520» and the plural of «06697», with the article inserted; smoothness of the rocks; Chelkath Hats-tsurim, a place in Palestine:--Helkath-hazzurim.', 'Helkath-hazzurim = \"field of swords\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place near the pool of Gibeon where Ishbosheth\'s men were killed by David\'s men under Joab</OL>'),
(2522, 'Xlx', 'a primitive root', 'chalash', 'TWOT - 671', 'khaw-lash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to prostrate; by implication, to overthrow, decay:--discomfit, waste away, weaken.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be weak, be prostrate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be prostrate</OL><LI>to weaken, disable, prostrate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to disable, prostrate</OL></OL>'),
(2523, 'Xllx', 'from (02522)', 'challash', 'TWOT - 671a', 'khal-lawsh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02522»; frail:--weak.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>weak</OL>'),
(2524, '~x', 'from the same as (02346)', 'cham', 'TWOT - 674a', 'khawm', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «02346»; a father-in-law (as in affinity):--father in law.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father-in-law, husband\'s father</OL>'),
(2525, '~x', 'from (02552)', 'cham', 'TWOT - 677b', 'khawm', 'Adjective', 'from «02552»; hot:--hot, warm.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hot, warm</OL>'),
(2526, '~x', 'the same as (02525)', 'Cham', 'None', 'khawm', '', 'the same as «02525»; hot (from the tropical habitat); Cham, a son of Noah; also (as a patronymic) his descendants or their country:--Ham.', 'n pr m Ham = \"hot\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>2nd son of Noah, father of Canaan and of various peoples which were inhabitants of southern lands<LI>in late usage, a collective name for Egyptians n pr loc<LI>the place where Chedorlaomer smote the Zuzim, probably in the territory of Ammonites (Gilead) east of the Jordan</OL>'),
(2527, '~x', 'from (02552)', 'chom', 'TWOT - 677a', 'khome', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02552»; heat:--heat, to be hot (warm).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>heat, hot</OL>'),
(2528, 'amx', 'corresponding to (02534)', 'chema\'', 'TWOT - 2733', 'khem-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) or chamah (Aramaic) {kham-aw\'}; corresponding to «02534»; anger:--fury.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>anger, rage</OL>'),
