(2598, 'hkknx', 'from (02596)', 'chanukkah', 'TWOT- 693b', 'khan-ook-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02596»; initiation, i.e. consecration:--dedicating(-tion).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dedication, consecration</OL>'),
(2599, 'yknx', 'from (02585)', 'Chanokiy', 'None', 'khan-o-kee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'patronymically from «02585»; a Chanokite (collectively) or descendants of Chanok:--Hanochites.', 'Hanochites = see Hanoch \"dedicated\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Hanoch</OL>'),
(2600, '~nnx', 'from (02580)', 'chinnam', 'TWOT - 694b', 'khin-nawm\'', 'Adverb', 'from «02580»; gratis, i.e. devoid of cost, reason or advantage:--without a cause (cost, wages), causeless, to cost nothing, free(-ly), innocent, for nothing (nought, in vain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>freely, for nothing, without cause<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>gratis, gratuitously, for nothing<LI>for no purpose, in vain<LI>gratuitously, without cause, undeservedly</OL></OL>'),
(2601, 'lamnx', 'probably by orthographical variation for (02606)', 'Chanam\'el', 'None', 'khan-am-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably by orthographical variation for «02606»; Chanamel, an Israelite:--Hanameel.', 'Hanameel = \"God is gracious\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Shallum and cousin of Jeremiah</OL>'),
(2602, 'lmnx', 'of uncertain derivation', 'chanamal', 'TWOT - 693.1', 'khan-aw-mawl\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; perhaps the aphis or plantlouse:--frost.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>frost, flood, sleet (meaning uncertain)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>that which destroyed the sycamore trees</OL></OL>'),
(2603, '!nx', 'a primitive root [compare (02583)]', 'chanan', 'TWOT - 694,695', 'khaw-nan\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «02583»); properly, to bend or stoop in kindness to an inferior; to favor, bestow; causatively to implore (i.e. move to favor by petition):--beseech, × fair, (be, find, shew) favour(-able), be (deal, give, grant (gracious(-ly), intreat, (be) merciful, have (shew) mercy (on, upon), have pity upon, pray, make supplication, × very.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be gracious, show favour, pity<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to show favour, be gracious<LI>(Niphal) to be pitied<LI>(Piel) to make gracious, make favourable, be gracious<LI>(Poel) to direct favour to, have mercy on<LI>(Hophal) to be shown favour, be shown consideration<LI>(Hithpael) to seek favour, implore favour</OL><LI>to be loathsome</OL>'),
(2604, '!nx', 'corresponding to (02603)', 'chanan', 'TWOT - 2737', 'khan-an\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02603»; to favor or (causatively) to entreat:--shew mercy, make supplication.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to show favour<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to show favour<LI>(Ithpael) to implore favour</OL></OL>'),
(2605, '!nx', 'from (02603)', 'Chanan', 'None', 'khaw-nawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02603»; favor; Chanan, the name of seven Israelites:--Canan.', 'Canan or Hanan = \"he is merciful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the chief people of the tribe of Benjamin<LI>last of the 6 sons of Azel, a descendant of Saul<LI>son of Maachah, one of David\'s mighty warriors<LI>father of some sons who returned from exile with Zerubbabel<LI>one of the Levites who assisted Ezra in his public exposition of the law<LI>one of the heads of the people who also sealed the covenant with Nehemiah<LI>another of the chief laymen who also sealed the covenant with Nehemiah<LI>son of Zaccur, grandson of Mattaniah whom Nehemiah made one of the storekeepers of the provisions collected as tithes. Same as 5 ?<LI>son of Igdaliah</OL>'),
(2606, 'lannx', 'from (02603) and (0410)', 'Chanan\'el', 'None', 'khan-an-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02603» and «0410»; God has favored; Chananel, probably an Israelite, from whom a tower of Jerusalem was named:--Hananeel.', 'Hananeel = \"God has favoured\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the name of a tower in Jerusalem</OL>'),
(2607, 'ynnx', 'from (02603)', 'Chananiy', 'None', 'khan-aw-nee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02603»; gracious; Chanani, the name of six Israelites:--Hanani.', 'Hanani = \"gracious\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the sons of Heman, a chief musician of David, and head of the 18th course of the service<LI>a seer who rebuked Asa, king of Judah, and was imprisoned<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>maybe, father of Jehu the seer who testified against Baasha</OL><LI>one of the priests who in the time of Ezra took a foreign wife<LI>brother of Nehemiah whom Nehemiah appointed governor of Jerusalem<LI>another priest who was the chief musician under Nehemiah</OL>'),
(2608, 'hynnx', 'from (02603) and (03050)', 'Chananyah', 'None', 'khan-an-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Chananyahuw {khan-an-yaw\'-hoo}; from «02603» and «03050»; Jah has favored; Chananjah, the name of thirteen Israelites:--Hananiah.', 'Hananiah = \"God has favoured\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the godly friend of Daniel whom Nebuchadnezzar renamed Shadrach; one of the three friends who with Daniel refused to make themselves unclean by eating food from the king\'s table which went against the dietary laws which God had given the Jews; also one of the three who were thrown into the fiery furnace for refusing to bow down to a graven image of Nebuchadnezzar and who were saved by the angel of the Lord. See also, \'Shadrach\' (07714 or 07715)<LI>one of the 14 sons of Heman and chief of the 16th course<LI>a general in the army of King Uzziah<LI>father of Zedekiah in the time of Jehoiakim<LI>son of Azur, a Benjamite of Gibeon and a false prophet in the reign of Zedekiah king of Judah<LI>grandfather of Irijah, the captain of the ward at the gate of Benjamin who arrested Jeremiah on the charge of deserting to the Chaldeans<LI>a head of a Benjamite house<LI>son of Zerubbabel from whom Christ derived His descent also called \'Joanna\' by Luke<LI>one of the sons of Bebai who returned with Ezra from Babylon<LI>a priest, one of the makers of the sacred ointments and incense, who built a portion of the wall of Jerusalem in the days of Nehemiah<LI>head of the priestly course of Jeremiah in the days of Joiakim<LI>ruler of the palace at Jerusalem under Nehemiah and also, along with Hanani, the Tirshatha\'s brother, entrusted with the arrangements of guarding the gates of Jerusalem<LI>Two post exilic Israelites</OL>'),
(2609, 'onx', 'of Egyptian derivation', 'Chanec', 'None', 'khaw-nace\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'of Egyptian derivation; Chanes, a place in Egypt:--Hanes.', 'Hanes = \"grace has fled\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in Egypt, site uncertain but may be either of the following<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>Tahpanhes, a fortified town on the eastern frontier<LI>a place in lower Egypt, on an island in the Nile south of Memphis</OL></OL>'),
(2610, '@nx', 'a primitive root', 'chaneph', 'TWOT - 696', 'khaw-nafe\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to soil, especially in a moral sense:--corrupt, defile, × greatly, pollute, profane.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be profaned, be defiled, be polluted, be corrupt<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be polluted<LI>to be profane, be godless</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pollute<LI>to make profane, make godless, cause to be defiled</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2611, '@nx', 'from (02610)', 'chaneph', 'TWOT - 696b', 'khaw-nafe\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02610»; soiled (i.e. with sin), impious:-- hypocrite(-ical).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hypocritical, godless, profane, hypocrite, irreligious</OL>'),
(2612, '@nx', 'from (02610)', 'choneph', 'TWOT - 696a', 'kho\'-nef', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02610»; moral filth, i.e. wickedness:--hypocrisy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hypocrisy, godlessness, hypocrite, profaneness</OL>'),
(2613, 'hpnx', 'from (02610)', 'chanuphah', 'TWOT - 696c', 'khan-oo-faw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from «02610»; impiety:--profaneness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>profaneness, pollution, hypocrisy, godlessness</OL>'),
(2614, 'qnx', 'a primitive root [compare (02596)]', 'chanaq', 'TWOT - 697', 'khaw-nak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «02596»); to be narrow; by implication, to throttle, or (reflex.) to choke oneself to death (by a rope):--hang self, strangle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strangle, strangle oneself<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to strangle oneself<LI>(Piel) to strangle</OL></OL>'),
(2615, '!tnnx', 'probably from (02603)', 'Channathon', 'None', 'khan-naw-thone\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'probably from «02603»; favored; Channathon, a place in Palestine:--Hannathon.', 'Hannathon = \"gracious\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Zebulun</OL>'),
(2616, 'dox', 'a primitive root', 'chacad', 'TWOT - 698,699', 'khaw-sad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, perhaps to bow (the neck only (compare «02603») in courtesy to an equal), i.e. to be kind; also (by euphem. (compare «0l288»), but rarely) to reprove:--shew self merciful, put to shame.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be good, be kind<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hithpael) to show kindness to oneself</OL><LI>to be reproached, be ashamed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to be put to shame, be reproached</OL></OL>'),
(2617, 'dox', 'from (02616)', 'checed', 'TWOT - 698a,699a', 'kheh\'-sed', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02616»; kindness; by implication (towards God) piety: rarely (by opposition) reproof, or (subject.) beauty:--favour, good deed(-liness, -ness), kindly, (loving-)kindness, merciful (kindness), mercy, pity, reproach, wicked thing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>goodness, kindness, faithfulness<LI>a reproach, shame</OL>'),
(2618, 'dox', 'the same as (02617)', 'Checed', 'None', 'kheh\'-sed', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «02617»: favor; Chesed, an Israelite:--Hesed.', 'Hesed = \"son of faithfulness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of or maybe a commissary officer under Solomon</OL>'),
(2619, 'hydox', 'from (02617) and (03050)', 'Chacadyah', 'None', 'khas-ad-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02617» and «03050»; Jah has favored: Chasadjah, an Israelite:--Hasadiah.', 'Hasadiah = \"Jehovah has been faithful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(2620, 'hox', 'a primitive root', 'chacah', 'TWOT - 700', 'khaw-saw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to flee for protection (compare «0982»); figuratively, to confide in:--have hope, make refuge, (put) trust.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to seek refuge, flee for protection<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to put trust in (God), confide or hope in (God) (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(2621, 'hox', 'from (02620)', 'Chocah', 'None', 'kho-saw\'', '', 'from «02620»; hopeful; Chosah, an Israelite; also a place in Palestine:--Hosah.', 'n pr m Hosah = \"refuge\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levitical doorkeeper of the temple n pr loc<LI>a place in Asher, site unknown</OL>'),
(2622, 'twox', 'from (02620)', 'chacuwth', 'TWOT - 700a', 'khaw-sooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02620»; confidence:--trust.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>refuge, shelter</OL>'),
(2623, 'dyox', 'from (02616)', 'chaciyd', 'TWOT - 698b', 'khaw-seed\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02616»; properly, kind, i.e. (religiously) pious (a saint):--godly (man), good, holy (one), merciful, saint, (un- )godly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>faithful, kind, godly, holy one, saint, pious<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>kind<LI>pious, godly<LI>faithful ones (subst)</OL></OL>'),
(2624, 'hdyox', 'from (02623)', 'chaciydah', 'TWOT - 698c', 'khas-ee-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02623»; the kind (maternal) bird, i.e. a stork:--X  feather, stork.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stork</OL>'),
(2625, 'lyox', 'from (02628)', 'chaciyl', 'TWOT - 701a', 'khaw-seel\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02628»; the ravager, i.e. a locust:--caterpillar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>locust</OL>'),
(2626, '!yox', 'from (02630)', 'chaciyn', 'TWOT - 703c', 'khas-een\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02630»; properly, firm, i.e. (by implication) mighty:--strong.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>strong, mighty</OL>'),
(2627, 'ryoox', 'from a root corresponding to (02637)', 'chacciyr', 'None', 'khas-seer\'', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «02637»; deficient:--wanting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lacking, wanting, deficient</OL>'),
(2628, 'lox', 'a primitive root', 'chacal', 'TWOT - 701', 'khaw-sal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to eat off:--consume.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to consume, finish off, bring to an end</OL>'),
(2629, '~ox', 'a primitive root', 'chacam', 'TWOT - 702', 'khaw-sam\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to muzzle; by analogy, to stop the nose:--muzzle, stop.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to stop up, muzzle</OL>'),
(2630, '!ox', 'a primitive root', 'chacan', 'TWOT - 703', 'khaw-san\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to (be) compact; by implication, to hoard:--lay up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Niphal) to be treasured up, be hoarded, be laid up, be stored</OL>'),
(2631, '!ox', 'corresponding to (02630)', 'chacan', 'TWOT - 2738', 'khas-an\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02630»; to hold in occupancy:--possess.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Aphel) to take possession of</OL>'),
(2632, '!ox', 'from (02631)', 'checen', 'TWOT - 2738a', 'khay\'-sen', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «02631»; strength:--power.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>power, strength, power (of the king), (royal) power</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(2633, '!ox', 'from (02630)', 'chocen', 'TWOT - 703a', 'kho\'-sen', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02630»; wealth:--riches, strength, treasure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>riches, treasure, wealth</OL>'),
(2634, '!ox', 'from (02630)', 'chacon', 'TWOT - 703b', 'khaw-sone\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02630»; powerful:--strong.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>strong</OL>'),
(2635, '@ox', 'from a root corresponding to that of (02636)', 'chacaph', 'TWOT - 2739', 'khas-af\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of «02636»; a clod:--clay.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>clay, potsherd</OL>'),
(2636, 'opox', 'reduplicated from an unused root meaning apparently to peel', 'chacpac', 'TWOT - 704', 'khas-pas\'', 'Verb', 'reduplicated from an unused root meaning apparently to peel; a shred or scale:--round thing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Pual) to peel, flake off (only in the participle)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>scale-like, flake-like, scaled-off</OL></OL>'),
(2637, 'rox', 'a primitive root', 'chacer', 'TWOT - 705', 'khaw-sare\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to lack; by implication, to fail, want, lessen:--be abated, bereave, decrease, (cause to) fail, (have) lack, make lower, want.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lack, be without, decrease, be lacking, have a need<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lack<LI>to be lacking<LI>to diminish, decrease</OL><LI>(Piel) to cause to lack<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to be lacking</OL></OL>'),
(2638, 'rox', 'from (02637)', 'chacer', 'TWOT - 705c', 'khaw-sare\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02637»; lacking; hence, without:--destitute, fail, lack, have need, void, want.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in need of, lacking, needy, in want of</OL>'),
(2639, 'rox', 'from (02637)', 'checer', 'TWOT - 705a', 'kheh\'-ler', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02637»; lack; hence, destitution:--poverty, want.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>poverty, want</OL>'),
(2640, 'rox', 'from (02637)', 'chocer', 'TWOT - 705b', 'kho\'-ser', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02637»; poverty:--in want of.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>want, lack, want of, lack of</OL>'),
(2641, 'hrox', 'from (02637)', 'Chacrah', 'None', 'khas-raw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02637»; want:--Chasrah, an Israelite:--Hasrah.', 'Hasrah = \"lack\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>grandfather of Shallum who was the husband of Huldah, the prophetess; also spelled \'Harhas\'</OL>'),
(2642, '!wrox', 'from (02637)', 'checrown', 'TWOT - 705d', 'khes-rone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02637»; deficiency:--wanting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the thing lacking, defect, deficiency</OL>'),
(2643, '@x', 'from (02653) (in the moral sense of covered from soil)', 'chaph', 'TWOT - 711a', 'khaf', 'Adjective', 'from «02653» (in the moral sense of covered from soil); pure:--innocent.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>innocent, pure, clean</OL>'),
(2644, 'apx', 'an orthographical variation of (02645)', 'chapha\'', 'TWOT - 706', 'khaw-faw\'', 'Verb', 'an orthographical variation of «02645»; properly, to cover, i.e. (in a sinister sense) to act covertly:--do secretly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to cover, do secretly</OL>'),
(2645, 'hpx', 'a primitive root (compare (02644), (02653))', 'chaphah', 'TWOT - 707', 'khaw-faw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «02644», «02653»); to cover; by implication, to veil, to encase, protect:--ceil, cover, overlay.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cover, overlay, wainscotted, covered with boards or panelling<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to cover<LI>(Niphal) to be covered<LI>(Piel) to cover, overlay</OL></OL>'),
(2646, 'hppx', 'from (02645)', 'chuppah', 'TWOT - 710b', 'khoop-paw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02645»; a canopy:--chamber, closet, defence.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chamber, room, canopy, closet<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>canopy<LI>chamber<LI>divine protection (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(2647, 'hppx', 'the same as (02646)', 'Chuppah', 'None', 'khoop-paw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «02646»; Chuppah, an Israelite:--Huppah.', 'Huppah = \"canopy\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest of the 13th course in the time of David</OL>'),
(2648, 'zpx', 'a primitive root', 'chaphaz', 'TWOT - 708', 'khaw-faz\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to start up suddenly, i.e. (by implication) to hasten away, to fear:--(make) haste (away), tremble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hurry, flee, hasten, fear, be terrified<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be in a hurry, be alarmed<LI>(Niphal) to be in a hurry</OL></OL>'),
(2649, '!wzppx', 'from (02468)', 'chippazown', 'TWOT - 708a', 'khip-paw-zone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02468»; hasty flight:--haste.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hurriedly, in haste, trepidation, hurried flight</OL>'),
(2650, '~yppx', 'pl. of (02646) [compare (02349)]', 'Chuppiym', 'None', 'khoop-peem\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'plural of «02646» (compare «02349»); Chuppim, an Israelite:--Huppim.', 'Huppim = \"protected\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the head of a Benjamite family</OL>'),
(2651, '!px', 'from an unused root of uncertain signification', 'chophen', 'TWOT - 709a', 'kho\'-fen', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root of uncertain signification; a fist (only in the dual):--fists, (both) hands, hand(-ful).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>handfuls, hollow of the hand</OL>'),
(2652, 'ynpx', 'from (02651)', 'Chophniy', 'None', 'khof-nee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02651»; perhaps pugilist; Chophni, an Israelite:--Hophni.', 'Hophni = \"pugilist\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the two sons of Eli who were priests at Shiloh and were noted for their brutality and lust; their sinfulness provoked a curse against their father\'s house and were judged by the Lord when they took the ark into battle; the ark was lost and both brothers were killed and Eli died when he heard the news</OL>'),
(2653, '@px', 'a primitive root (compare (02645), (03182))', 'chophaph', 'TWOT - 710', 'khaw-faf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «02645», «03182»); to cover (in protection):--cover.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to cover, enclose, shelter, shield, surround</OL>'),
(2654, '#px', 'a primitive root', 'chaphets', 'TWOT - 712,713', 'khaw-fates\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to incline to; by implication (literally but rarely) to bend; figuratively, to be pleased with, desire:--X any at all, (have, take) delight, desire, favour, like, move, be (well) pleased, have pleasure, will, would.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to delight in, take pleasure in, desire, be pleased with<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of men 1a</OL><LI>to take pleasure in, delight in 1a<LI>to delight, desire, be pleased to do<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>of God 1a</OL><LI>to delight in, have pleasure in 1a<LI>to be pleased to do</OL><LI>to move, bend down<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to bend down</OL></OL>'),
(2655, '#px', 'from (02654)', 'chaphets', 'TWOT - 712a', 'khaw-fates\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02654»; pleased with:--delight in, desire, favour, please, have pleasure, whosoever would, willing, wish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>desiring, delighting in, having pleasure in</OL>'),
(2656, '#px', 'from (02654)', 'chephets', 'TWOT - 712b', 'khay\'-fets', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02654»; pleasure; hence (abstractly) desire; concretely, a valuable thing; hence (by extension) a matter (as something in mind):--acceptable, delight(-some), desire, things desired, matter, pleasant(-ure), purpose, willingly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>delight, pleasure<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>delight<LI>desire, longing<LI>the good pleasure<LI>that in which one takes delight</OL></OL>'),
(2657, 'hhb ycpx', 'from (02656) with suffixes', 'Chephtsiy', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'from «02656» with suffixes; my delight (is) in her; Cheptsi-bah, a fanciful name for Palestine:--Hephzi-bah.', 'Hephzi-bah = \"my delight is in her\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the queen of King Hezekiah and mother of Manasseh<LI>a name for Jesusalem (fig.)</OL>'),
(2658, 'rpx', 'a primitive root', 'chaphar', 'TWOT - 714', 'khaw-far\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to pry into; by implication, to delve, to explore:--dig, paw, search out, seek.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dig, search for<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dig<LI>to search, search out, explore</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2659, 'rpx', 'a primitive root [perhaps rath, the same as (02658) through the idea of detection]', 'chapher', 'TWOT - 715', 'khaw-fare\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (perhaps rath. the same as «02658» through the idea of detection): to blush; figuratively, to be ashamed, disappointed; causatively, to shame, reproach:--be ashamed, be confounded, be brought to confusion (unto shame), come (be put to) shame, bring reproach.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be ashamed, be confounded, be abashed, feel abashed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be ashamed, be abashed<LI>(Hiphil) to display shame, demonstrate shame, cause embarrassment</OL></OL>'),
(2660, 'rpx', 'from (02658) or (02659)', 'Chepher', 'None', 'khay\'-fer', '', 'from «02658» or «02659»; a pit of shame; Chepher, a place in Palestine; also the name of three Israelites:--Hepher.', 'Hepher = \"a well\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>youngest son of Gilead and head of the family of Hepherites<LI>son of Asher, the father of Tekoa<LI>the Mecherathite, one of David\'s mighty warriors n pr loc<LI>a place in ancient Canaan, west of the Jordan, conquered by Joshua site unknown<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a place in Judah, probably the same as 4 above</OL></OL>'),
(2661, 'rpx', 'from (02658)', 'chaphor', 'TWOT - 714a', 'khaf-ore\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02658»; a hole; only in connection with «06512», which ought rather to be joined as one word, thus chapharperah {khaf-ar- pay-raw\'}; by reduplication from «02658»; a burrower, i.e. probably a rat:--+ mole.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mole (as digger)</OL>'),
(2662, 'yrpx', 'patronymically from (02660)', 'Chephriy', 'None', 'khef-ree\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'patronymically from «02660»; a Chephrite (collectively) or descendants of Chepher:--Hepherites.', 'Hepherites = see Hepher \"a pit\" or \"shame\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Hepher, son of Gilead</OL>'),
(2663, '~yrpx', 'dual of (02660)', 'Chapharayim', 'None', 'khaf-aw-rah\'-yim', 'Proper Name Location', 'dual of «02660»; double pit; Chapharajim, a place in Palestine:--Haphraim.', 'Hapharaim = \"two pits\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in Issachar</OL>'),
(2664, 'Xpx', 'a primitive root', 'chaphas', 'TWOT - 716', 'khaw-fas\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to seek; causatively, to conceal oneself (i.e. let be sought), or mask:--change, (make) diligent (search), disquise self, hide, search (for, out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to search, search for, to search out, disguise oneself<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to search for<LI>to think out, devise<LI>to search, test</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be searched out, be exposed<LI>(Piel) to search, search through, search for<LI>(Pual) to be searched for, be sought out<LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to disguise oneself<LI>to let oneself be searched for</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2665, 'Xpx', 'from (02664)', 'chephes', 'TWOT - 716a', 'khay\'-fes', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02664»; something covert, i.e. a trick:--search.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>trick, plot, (shrewd) device</OL>'),
(2666, 'Xpx', 'a primitive root', 'chaphash', 'TWOT - 717', 'khaw-fash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to spread loose; figuratively, to manumit:--be free.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Pual) to be free, be freed</OL>'),
(2667, 'Xpx', 'from (02666)', 'Chophesh', 'TWOT - 717a', 'kho\'-fesh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02666»; something spread loosely, i.e. a carpet:--precious.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>widespread, fabric for horseback riding, saddle-blanket, saddle-cloths; meaning dubious</OL>'),
(2668, 'hXpx', 'from (02666)', 'chuphshah', 'TWOT - 717b', 'khoof-shaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02666»; liberty (from slavery):--freedom.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>freedom</OL>'),
(2669, 'twXpx', 'from (02666)', 'chophshuwth', 'TWOT - 717d', 'khof-shooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'and chophshiyth {khof-sheeth\'}; from «02666»; prostration by sickness (with «01004», a hospital):--several.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>separateness, freedom</OL>'),
(2670, 'yXpx', 'from (02666)', 'chophshiy', 'TWOT - 717c', 'khof-shee\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02666»; exempt (from bondage, tax or care):--free, liberty.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>free<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>free (from slavery)<LI>free (from taxes or obligations)</OL></OL>'),
(2671, '#x', 'from (02686)', 'chets', 'TWOT - 721b', 'khayts', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02686»; properly, a piercer, i.e. an arrow; by implication, a wound; figuratively, (of God) thunder-bolt; (by interchange for «06086») the shaft of a spear:--+ archer, arrow, dart, shaft, staff, wound.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>arrow</OL>'),
(2672, 'bcx', 'a primitive root', 'chatsab', 'TWOT - 718', 'khaw-tsab\'', 'Verb', 'or chatseb {khaw-tsabe\'}; a primitive root ; to cut or carve (wood), stone or other material); by implication, to hew, split, square, quarry, engrave:--cut, dig, divide, grave, hew (out, -er), made, mason.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dig, cleave, divide, hew, make, cut out, dig out, cut down, quarry, hewer, mason<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hew out, dig<LI>to hew 1a</OL><LI>stone 1a<LI>wood<OL TYPE=\"3\"><LI>to hew in pieces (metaph.)<LI>to divide, cleave</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be cut, be hewn, be engraved<LI>(Hiphil) to hew into pieces, cut up into pieces<LI>(Pual) to be cut from, be hewn from</OL></OL>'),
(2673, 'hcx', 'a primitive root [compare (02686)])', 'chatsah', 'TWOT - 719', 'khaw-tsaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «02086»)); to cut or split in two; to halve:--divide, × live out half, reach to the midst, participle', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to divide, cut in two, cut short, live half (of one\'s life)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to divide<LI>to half, cut in two</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be divided</OL></OL>'),
(2674, 'rwcx', 'a collective form of (02691)', 'Chatsowr', 'None', 'khaw-tsore\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'a collective form of «02691»; village; Chatsor, the name (thus simply) of two places in Palestine and of one in Arabia:-- Hazor.', 'Hazor = \"castle\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a royal city of northern Palestine allotted to Naphtali<LI>one of the cities of Judah in the extreme south<LI>a town north of Jerusalem in which the Benjamites resided after the return from exile<LI>a site in Arabia</OL>'),
(2675, 'httdx rwcx', 'from (02674) and a Aramaic form of the fem. of (02319) [compare (02323)]', 'Chatsowr', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02674» and a Aramaizing form of the feminine of 2319 (compare «02323»); new Chatsor, a place in Palestine:--Hazor, Hadattah (as if two places).', 'Hazor-Hadattah = \"new Hazor\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in the south of Judah; Jos 15:25</OL>'),
(2676, 'twcx', 'from (02673)', 'chatsowth', 'TWOT - 719a', 'khaw-tsoth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02673»; the middle (of the night):--mid(-night).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>middle, mid-, half, division</OL>'),
(2677, 'ycx', 'from (02673)', 'chetsiy', 'TWOT - 719b', 'khay-tsee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02673»; the half or middle:--half, middle, mid(-night), midst, part, two parts.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>half<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>half<LI>middle</OL></OL>'),
(2678, 'yccx', 'prolongation from (02671)', 'chitstsiy', 'TWOT - 719c,721b', 'khits-tsee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or chetsiy {chay-tsee\'}; prolongation from «02671»; an arrow:--arrow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>arrow</OL>'),
(2679, 'twxnmmh ycx', 'from (02677) and the plural of (04496), with the article interposed', 'Chatsiy', 'chat-tsee\' ham-men-oo-khoth\'', '', '', 'from «02677» and the plural of «04496», with the article interposed; midst of the resting- places; Chatsi-ham-Menuchoth, an Israelite:--half of the Manahethites.', ''),
(2680, 'txnmmh ycx', 'patronymically from (02679)', 'Chatsiy', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'patronymically from «02679»; a Chatsi-ham-Menachtite or descendant of Chatsi-ham-Menuchoth:--half of the Manahethites.', '(half of the) Manassites = see Manasseh \"causing to forget\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>half of the Manassites; also spelled like 2679</OL>'),
(2681, 'rycx', 'a collateral form of (02691)', 'chatsiyr', 'TWOT - 723b', 'khaw-tseer\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'a collateral form of «02691»; a court or abode:--court.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a dwelling, an abode, settled abode, haunt</OL>'),
(2682, 'rycx', 'perhaps originally the same as (02681), from the greenness of a courtyard', 'chatsiyr', 'TWOT - 724a,725a', 'khaw-tseer\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'perhaps originally the same as «02681», from the greenness of a courtyard; grass; also a leek (collectively):--grass, hay, herb, leek.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>grass, leek, green grass, herbage<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>grass<LI>of the quickly perishing (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(2683, '!cx', 'from an unused root meaning to hold firmly', 'chetsen', 'TWOT - 720a', 'khay\'-tsen', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to hold firmly; the bosom (as comprised between the arms):--bosom.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bosom, bosom of a garment</OL>'),
(2684, '!cx', 'a collateral form of (02683), and meaning the same', 'chotsen', 'TWOT - 720b', 'kho\'tsen', 'Noun Masculine', 'a collateral form of «02683», and meaning the same:--arm, lap.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bosom, lap</OL>'),
(2685, '@cx', 'a primitive root', 'chatsaph', 'TWOT - 2740', 'khats-af\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) a primitive root; properly, to shear or cut close; figuratively, to be severe:--hasty, be urgent.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Aphel) to be urgent, harsh, show insolence</OL>'),
(2686, '#cx', 'a primitive root [compare (02673)]', 'chatsats', 'TWOT - 721,721c', 'khaw-tsats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «02673»); properly, to chop into, pierce or sever; hence, to curtail, to distribute (into ranks); as denom. from «02671», to shoot an arrow:--archer, ×  bands, cut off in the midst.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to divide<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to divide<LI>(Piel) to divide<LI>(Pual) to be cut off, be finished</OL><LI>to shoot arrows<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) archer (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(2687, '#cx', 'from (02686)', 'chatsats', 'TWOT - 721a', 'khaw-tsawts\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02687»; properly, something cutting; hence, gravel (as grit); also (like «02671») an arrow:--arrow, gravel (stone).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gravel</OL>'),
(2688, 'rmt !wccx', 'from (02686) and (08558)', 'Chatstsown', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Chatsatson Tamar {khats-ats-one\' taw-mawr\'}; from «02686» and «08558»; division (i.e. perhaps row) of (the) palm-tree; Chatsetson-tamar, a place in Palestine:--Hazezon- tamar.', 'Hazezon-tamar = \"dividing the date-palm\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Amorite city<LI>a town situated in the desert Judah; probably Engedi<LI>maybe the \'Tamar\' of Solomon\'s day</OL>'),
(2689, 'hrccx', 'by reduplication from (02690)', 'chatsotsrah', 'TWOT - 726a', 'khats-o-tser-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'by reduplication from «02690»; a trumpet (from its sundered or quavering note):--trumpet(-er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>trumpet, clarion</OL>'),
(2690, 'rcx', 'a primitive root', 'chatsar', 'TWOT - 726b', 'khaw-tsar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to surround with a stockade, and thus separate from the open country; but used only in the reduplicated form chatsotser {khast-o-tsare\'}; or (2 Chronicles 5:12) chatsorer {khats-o-rare\'}; as dem. from «02689»; to trumpet, i.e. blow on that instrument:--blow, sound, trumpeter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sound a trumpet<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) players on clarions (participle)<LI>(Hiphil) sound with clarions (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(2691, 'rcx', 'from (02690) in its original sense', 'chatser', 'TWOT - 722a,723a', 'khaw-tsare\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(masculine and feminine); from «02690» in its original sense; a yard (as inclosed by a fence); also a hamlet (as similarly surrounded with walls):--court, tower, village.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>court, enclosure<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>enclosures<LI>court</OL><LI>settled abode, settlement, village, town</OL>'),
(2692, 'rdd rcx', 'from (02691) and (0146)', 'Chatsar', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02691» and «0146»; (the) village of Addar; Chatsar-Addar, a place in Palestine:--Hazar-addar.', 'Hazar-addar = \"enclosure of glory\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place on the southern border of Canaan</OL>'),
(2693, 'hddg rcx', 'from (02691) and a fem. of (01408)', 'Chatsar', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02691» and a feminine of «01408»; (the) village of (female) Fortune; Chatsar-Gaddah, a place in Palestine:--Hazar-gaddah.', 'Hazar-gaddah = \"village of good fortune\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in southern Judah</OL>'),
(2694, '!wkytth rcx', 'from (02691) and (08484) with the article interposed', 'Chatsar', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02691» and «08484» with the article interposed; village of the middle; Chatsar-hat-Tikon, a place in Palestine:--Hazar-hatticon.', 'Hazar-hatticon = \"middle court\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in Palestine, maybe at the east corner of Hermon</OL>'),
(2695, 'wrcx', 'by an orthographical variation for (02696)', 'Chetsrow', 'None', 'khets-ro\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'by an orthographical variation for «02696»; enclosure; Chetsro, an Israelite:--Hezro, Hezrai.', 'Hezro or Hezrai = \"enclosed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the Carmelite, one of David\'s 30 mighty warriors in his guard</OL>'),
(2696, '!wrcx', 'from (02691)', 'Chetsrown', 'None', 'khets-rone\'', '', 'from «02691»; court-yard; Chetsron, the name of a place in Palestine; also of two Israelites:--Hezron.', 'Hezron = \"surrounded by a wall\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Reuben<LI>a son of Pharez and grandson of Judah n pr loc<LI>a place in the extreme south of Judah</OL>'),
(2697, 'ynwrcx', 'patronymically from (02696)', 'Chetsrowniy', 'None', 'khets-ro-nee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'patronymically from «02696»; a Chetsronite or (collectively) descendants of Chetsron:--Hezronites.', 'Hezronites = see Hezron \"enclosed\" or \"division of song\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Hezron</OL>'),
(2698, 'twrcx', 'fem. pl. of (02691)', 'Chatserowth', 'None', 'khats-ay-roth\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'feminine plural of «02691»; yards; Chatseroth, a place in Palestine:--Hazeroth.', 'Hazeroth = \"settlement\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Israelite camp in the wilderness</OL>'),
(2699, '~yrcx', 'pl. masc. of (02691)', 'Chatseriym', 'None', 'khats-ay-reem\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'plural masculine of «02691»; yards; Chatserim, a place in Palestine:--Hazerim.', 'Hazerim = \"villages\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>settlements of Ishmaelites</OL>'),
(2700, 'twmrcx', 'from (02691) and (04194)', 'Chatsarmaveth', 'None', 'khats-ar-maw\'-veth', '', 'from «02691» and «04194»; village of death; Chatsarmaveth, a place in Arabia:--Hazarmaveth.', 'Hazarmaveth = \"village of death\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 3rd in order of the sons of Joktan ++++ He was the founder of an ancient people of southern Arabia which later became a province and important commercial centre</OL>'),
(2701, 'howo rcx', 'from (02691) and (05484)', 'Chatsar', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02691» and «05484»; village of cavalry; Chatsar-Susah, a place in Palestine:--Hazar-susah.', 'Hazar-susah = \"horse village\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the cities allotted to Simeon in the extreme south of Judah and the place where Solomon kept horses</OL>'),
(2702, '~yowo rcx', 'from (02691) and the plural of (05483)', 'Chatsar', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02691» and the plural of «05483»; village of horses; Chatsar-Susim, a place in Palestine:--Hazar- susim.', 'Hazar-susim = \"village of horses\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in Simeon</OL>'),
(2703, '!wny[ rcx', 'from (02691) and a derivative of (05869)', 'Chatsar', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02691» and a derivative of «05869»; village of springs; Chatsar-Enon, a place in Palestine:--Hazar- enon.', 'Hazar-enan = \"village of springs\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city on the northeast border of Canaan; same as 2704</OL>'),
(2704, '!ny[ rcx', 'from (02691) and the same as (05881)', 'Chatsar', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02691» and the same as «05881»; village of springs; Chatsar-Enan, a place in Palestine:--Hazar-enan.', 'Hazar-enan = \"village of fountains\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city on the northeast border of Canaan; same as 2703</OL>'),
(2705, 'l[wX rcx', 'from (02691) and (07776)', 'Chatsar', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02691» and «07776»; village of (the) fox; Chatsar-Shual, a place in Palestine:--Hazar-shual.', 'Hazar-shual = \"jackal village\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in southern Judah<LI>a place in Simeon</OL>'),
(2706, 'qx', 'from (02710)', 'choq', 'TWOT - 728a', 'khoke', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02710»; an enactment; hence, an appointment (of time, space, quantity, labor or usage):--appointed, bound, commandment, convenient, custom, decree(-d), due, law, measure, × necessary, ordinance(- nary), portion, set time, statute, task.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>statute, ordinance, limit, something prescribed, due<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>prescribed task<LI>prescribed portion<LI>action prescribed (for oneself), resolve<LI>prescribed due<LI>prescribed limit, boundary<LI>enactment, decree, ordinance<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>specific decree<LI>law in general</OL><LI>enactments, statutes<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>conditions<LI>enactments<LI>decrees<LI>civil enactments prescribed by God</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2707, 'hqx', 'a primitive root', 'chaqah', 'TWOT - 727', 'khaw-kaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to carve; by implication, to delineate; also to entrench:--carved work, portrayed, set a print.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut, carve, cut in<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pual) carved (participle)<LI>(Hithpael) to engrave, cut a limit</OL></OL>'),
(2708, 'hqqx', 'from (02706)', 'chuqqah', 'TWOT - 728b', 'khook-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02706», and meaning substantially the same:--appointed, custom, manner, ordinance, site, statute.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>statute, ordinance, limit, enactment, something prescribed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>statute</OL></OL>'),
(2709, 'apwqx', 'from an unused root probably meaning to bend', 'Chaquwpha\'', 'None', 'khah-oo-faw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to bend; crooked; Chakupha, one of the Nethinim:--Hakupha.', 'Hakupha = \"bent\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of a family of exiles returning with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(2710, 'qqx', 'a primitive root', 'chaqaq', 'TWOT - 728', 'khaw-kak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to hack, i.e. engrave (Judges 5:14, to be a scribe simply); by implication, to enact (laws being cut in stone or metal tablets in primitive times) or (gen.) prescribe:--appoint, decree, governor, grave, lawgiver, note, pourtray, print, set.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut out, decree, inscribe, set, engrave, portray, govern<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut in<LI>to cut in or on, cut upon, engrave, inscribe<LI>to trace, mark out<LI>to engrave, inscribe (of a law)</OL><LI>(Poel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to inscribe, enact, decree<LI>one who decrees, lawgiver (participle)</OL><LI>(Pual) something decreed, the law (participle)<LI>(Hophal) to be inscribed</OL></OL>'),
(2711, 'qqx', 'from (02710)', 'cheqeq', 'TWOT - 728a', 'khay\'-kek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02710»; an enactment, a resolution:--decree, thought.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>decree, resolve, statute, action prescribed</OL>'),
(2712, 'gqqx', 'from (02710)', 'Chuqqog', 'None', 'Khook-koke\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or (fully) Chuwqoq {khoo-koke\'}; from «02710»; appointed; Chukkok or Chukok, a place in Palestine:--Hukkok, Hukok.', 'Hukkok = \"appointed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town on the boundary of Naphtali</OL>'),
(2713, 'rqx', 'a primitive root', 'chaqar', 'TWOT - 729', 'khaw-kar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to penetrate; hence, to examine intimately:--find out, (make) search (out), seek (out), sound, try.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to search, search for, search out, examine, investigate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to search (for)<LI>to search through, explore<LI>to examine thoroughly</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be searched out, be found out, be ascertained, be examined</OL><LI>(Piel) to search out, seek out</OL></OL>'),
(2714, 'rqx', 'from (02713)', 'cheqer', 'TWOT - 729a', 'khay\'-ker', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02713»; examination, enumeration, deliberation:--finding out, number, (un-)search(-able, -ed, out, -ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a search, investigation, searching, enquiry, thing to be searched out</OL>'),
(2715, 'rx', 'from (02787)', 'chor', 'TWOT - 757a', 'khore', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (fully) chowr {khore}; from «02787»; properly, white or pure (from the cleansing or shining power of fire (compare «02751»); hence (figuratively) noble (in rank):--noble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a noble, freeborn one</OL>'),
(2716, 'arx', 'from an unused (and vulgar) root probably meaning to evacuate the bowels', 'chere\'', 'TWOT - 730a', 'kheh\'-reh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused (and vulgar) root probably meaning to evacuate the bowels: excrement; -dung. Also chariy {khar-ee\'}.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dung, excrement</OL>'),
(2717, 'brx', 'a primitive root', 'charab', 'TWOT - 731,732', 'khaw-rab\'', 'Verb', 'or chareb {khaw-rabe\'}; a primitive root; to parch (through drought) i.e. (by analogy,) to desolate, destroy, kill:-- decay, (be) desolate, destroy(-er), (be) dry (up), slay, ×  surely, (lay, lie, make) waste.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be waste, lay waste, make desolate, be desolate, be in ruins<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be waste, be desolate<LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be made desolate<LI>desolate (participle)</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to lay waste, make desolate<LI>(Hophal) to be laid waste</OL><LI>to be dry, be dried up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be dried, be dried up<LI>(Pual) to be dried<LI>(Hiphil) to dry up<LI>(Hophal) to be dried up</OL><LI>to attack, smite down, slay, fight</OL>'),
(2718, 'brx', 'a root corresponding to (02717)', 'charab', 'TWOT - 2741', 'khar-ab\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) a root corresponding to «02717»; to demolish:--destroy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dry up, be waste<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hophal) to be laid waste</OL></OL>'),
(2719, 'brx', 'from (02717)', 'chereb', 'TWOT - 732a', 'kheh\'-reb', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02717»; drought; also a cutting instrument (from its destructive effect), as a knife, sword, or other sharp implement:--axe, dagger, knife, mattock, sword, tool.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sword, knife<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>sword<LI>knife<LI>tools for cutting stone</OL></OL>'),
(2720, 'brx', 'from (02717)', 'chareb', 'TWOT - 731a', 'khaw-rabe\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02717»; parched or ruined:--desolate, dry, waste.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>waste, desolate, dry</OL>'),
(2721, 'brx', 'a collaterally form of (02719)', 'choreb', 'TWOT - 731b', 'kho\'-reb', 'Noun Masculine', 'a collaterally form of «02719»; drought or desolation:--desolation, drought, dry, heat, × utterly, waste.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dryness, desolation, drought, heat<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>dryness<LI>drought<LI>parching heat</OL></OL>'),
(2722, 'brx', 'from (02717)', 'Choreb', 'TWOT - 731c', 'kho-rabe\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02717»; desolate; Choreb, a (generic) name for the Sinaitic mountains:--Horeb.', 'Horeb = \"desert\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>another name for Mount Sinai from which God gave the law to Moses and the Israelites</OL>'),
(2723, 'hbrx', 'from (02721)', 'chorbah', 'TWOT - 731d', 'khor-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02721»; properly, drought, i.e. (by implication) a desolation:--decayed place, desolate (place, -tion), destruction, (laid) waste (place).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place laid waste, ruin, waste, desolation</OL>'),
(2724, 'hbrx', 'from (02720)', 'charabah', 'TWOT - 731e', 'khaw-raw-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02720»; a desert:--dry (ground, land).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dry land, dry ground</OL>'),
(2725, '!wbrx', 'from (02717)', 'charabown', 'TWOT - 731f', 'khar-aw-bone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02717»; parching heat:--drought.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>drought</OL>'),
(2726, 'anwbrx', 'of Persian origin', 'Charbowna\'', 'None', 'khar-bo-naw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Charbownah {khar-bo-naw\'}; of Persian origin; Charbona or Charbonah, a eunuch of Xerxes:--Harbona, Harbonah.', 'Harbona or Harbonah = \"ass-driver\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 3rd of the seven chamberlains or eunuchs who served Ahasuerus</OL>'),
(2727, 'grx', 'a primitive root', 'charag', 'TWOT - 733', 'khaw-rag\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to leap suddenly, i.e. (by implication) to be dismayed:--be afraid.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to shake from fear, tremble, quake</OL>'),
(2728, 'lgrx', 'from (02727)', 'chargol', 'TWOT - 734a', 'khar-gole\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02727»; the leaping insect, i.e. a locust:--beetle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a kind of locust, a leaping creature</OL>'),
(2729, 'drx', 'a primitive root', 'charad', 'TWOT - 735', 'khaw-rad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to shudder with terror; hence, to fear; also to hasten (with anxiety):--be (make) afraid, be careful, discomfit, fray (away), quake, tremble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tremble, quake, move about, be afraid, be startled, be terrified<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tremble, quake (of a mountain)<LI>to tremble (of people)<LI>to be anxiously careful<LI>to go or come trembling (with prep)</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to tremble<LI>to drive in terror, rout (an army)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2730, 'drx', 'from (02729)', 'chared', 'TWOT - 735a', 'khaw-rade\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02729»; fearful; also reverential:--afraid, trembling.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>trembling, fearful, afraid</OL>'),
(2731, 'hdrx', 'from (02730)', 'charadah', 'TWOT - 735b', 'khar-aw-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02730»; fear, anxiety:--care, × exceedingly, fear, quaking, trembling.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fear, anxiety, quaking, trembling, (extreme) anxiety, anxious care<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>trembling, quaking<LI>anxious care</OL></OL>'),
(2732, 'hdrx', 'the same as (02731)', 'Charadah', 'None', 'khar-aw-daw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «02731»; Charadah, a place in the Desert:--Haradah.', 'Haradah = \"fear\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a desert station of Israel in the wilderness; site unknown</OL>'),
(2733, 'ydrx', 'from a derivative of (02729) [compare (05878)]', 'Charodiy', 'None', 'khar-o-dee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'patrial from a derivative of «02729» (compare «05878»); a Charodite, or inhabitant of Charod:--Harodite.', 'Harodite = see Harod \"trembling\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a resident or descendant of Harod otherwise unknown; two of David\'s 37 guards, Shammah and Elika, called Harodites</OL>'),
(2734, 'hrx', 'a primitive root [compare (02787)]', 'charah', 'TWOT - 736', 'khaw-raw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «02787»); to glow or grow warm; figuratively (usually) to blaze up, of anger, zeal, jealousy:--be angry, burn, be displeased, × earnestly, fret self, grieve, be (wax) hot, be incensed, kindle, × very, be wroth. See «08474».', ''),
(2735, 'dgdggh rx', 'from (02356) and a collateral (masc.) form of (01412), with the article interposed', 'Chor', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02356» and a collateral (masculine) form of «01412», with the article interposed; hole of the cleft: Chor-hag-Gidgad, a place in the Desert:--Hor-hagidgad.', 'Hor-hagidgad = \"cavern of Gidgad\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a desert station of Israel in the wilderness; site unknown</OL>'),
(2736, 'hyhrx', 'from (02734) and (03050)', 'Charhayah', 'None', 'khar-hah-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', '; from «02734» and «03050»; fearing Jah; Charhajah, an Israelite:--Harhaiah.', 'Harhaiah = \"fear of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Uzziel who was one of the builders of the wall in Nehemiah\'s time</OL>'),
(2737, 'zwrx', 'from an unused root meaning to perforate', 'charuwz', 'TWOT - 737a', 'khaw-rooz\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to perforate; properly, pierced, i.e. a bead of pearl, gems or jewels (as strung):--chain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a beaded necklace, string of beads</OL>'),
(2738, 'lwrx', 'apparently, a pass. participle of an unused root probably meaning to be prickly', 'charuwl', 'TWOT - 743a', 'khaw-rool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (shortened) charul {khaw-rool\'}; apparently, a passive participle of an unused root probably meaning to be prickly; properly, pointed, i.e. a bramble or other thorny weed: nettle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nettles, weeds, kind of weed (perhaps chickpea)</OL>'),
(2739, '@mwrx', 'from pass. participle of (02763) and (0639)', 'charuwmaph', 'None', 'khar-oo-maf\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from passive participle of «02763» and «0639»; snub-nosed; Charumaph, an Israelite:--Harumaph.', 'Harumaph = \"split nose\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Jedaiah, one of the builders of the wall in Nehemiah\'s time</OL>'),
(2740, '!wrx', 'from (02734)', 'charown', 'TWOT - 736a', 'khaw-rone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (shortened) charon {khaw-rone\'}; from «02734»; a burning of anger:--sore displeasure, fierce(-ness), fury, (fierce) wrath(-ful).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>anger, heat, burning (of anger)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>always used of God\'s anger</OL></OL>'),
(2741, 'ypwrx', 'from (probably) a collateral form of (02756)', 'Charuwphiy', 'None', 'khar-oo-fee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'a patrial from (probably) a collateral form of «02756»; a Charuphite or inhabitant of Charuph (or Chariph):--Haruphite.', 'Haruphite = \"native of Haruph\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Hariph</OL>'),
(2742, '#wrx', 'pass. participle of (02782)', 'charuwts', 'TWOT - 752a,b,753a', 'khaw-roots\'', '', 'or charuts {khaw-roots\'}; passive participle of «02782»; properly, incised or (active) incisive; hence (as noun masculine or feminine) a trench (as dug), gold (as mined), a threshing-sledge (having sharp teeth); (figuratively) determination; also eager:--decision, diligent, (fine) gold, pointed things, sharp, threshing instrument, wall.', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sharp-pointed, sharp, diligent n m<LI>strict decision, decision<LI>trench, moat, ditch<LI>gold (poetical)</OL>'),
(2743, '#wrx', 'the same as (02742)', 'Charuwts', 'None', 'khaw-roots\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «02742»; earnest; Charuts, an Israelite:--Haruz.', 'Haruz = \"zealous\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a man of Jotbah, father of Meshullemeth, wife of Manasseh and mother of Amon</OL>'),
(2744, 'rwxrx', 'a fuller form of (02746)', 'Charchuwr', 'None', 'khar-khoor\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'a fuller form of «02746»; inflammation; Charchur, one of the Nethinim:--Harhur.', 'Harhur = \"inflammation\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of a family returning from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(2745, 'oxrx', 'from the same as (02775)', 'Charchac', 'None', 'khar-khas\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «02775»; perhaps shining; Charchas, an Israelite:--Harhas.', 'Harhas = \"very poor\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>grandfather of Shallum, the husband of Huldah, the prophetess</OL>'),
(2746, 'rxrx', 'from (02787)', 'charchur', 'TWOT - 756b', 'khar-khoor\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02787»; fever (as hot); -extreme burning.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>extreme heat, inflammation, violent heat, fever</OL>'),
(2747, 'trx', 'from a primitive root meaning to engrave', 'cheret', 'TWOT - 738a', 'kheh\'-ret', 'Noun Masculine', 'from a primitive root meaning to engrave; a chisel or graver; also a style for writing:--graving tool, pen.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an engraving tool, stylus, chisel, graving tool<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>graving tool<LI>stylus</OL></OL>'),
(2748, '~trx', 'from the same as (02747)', 'chartom', 'TWOT - 738b', 'khar-tome\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «02747»; a horoscopist (as drawing magical lines or circles):--magician.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>diviner, magician, astrologer<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>engraver, writer (only in derivative sense of one possessed of occult knowledge)</OL></OL>'),
(2749, '~trx', 'the same as (02748)', 'chartom', 'TWOT - 2742', 'khar-tome\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) the same as «02748»:--magician.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>magician, magician-astrologer</OL>'),
(2750, 'yrx', 'from (02734)', 'choriy', 'TWOT - 736b', 'khor-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02734»; a burning (i.e. intense) anger:--fierce, × great, heat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>heat (of anger), burning (of anger)</OL>'),
(2751, 'yrx', 'from the same as (02353)', 'choriy', 'TWOT - 740', 'kho-ree\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «02353»; white bread:--white.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>white bread, cake<LI>(TWOT) Horite, Hori</OL>'),
(2752, 'yrx', 'from (02356)', 'Choriy', 'None', 'kho-ree\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02356»; cave-dweller or troglodyte; a Chorite or aboriginal Idumaean:--Horims, Horites.', 'Horite = \"cave dweller\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the inhabitants of Mount Seir<LI>the inhabitants of Edom (in later times)</OL>'),
(2753, 'yrx', 'the same as (02752)', 'Choriy', 'None', 'kho-ree\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Chowriy {kho-ree\'}; the same as «02752»; Chori, the name of two men:--Hori.', 'Hori = \"cave dweller\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Horite, son of Lotan, the son of Seir<LI>a Simeonite, father of Shaphat</OL>'),
(2754, 'tyrx', 'from the same as (02747)', 'chariyt', 'TWOT - 739a', 'khaw-reet\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or charit {khaw-reet\'}; from the same as «02747»; properly, cut out (or hollow), i.e. (by implication) a pocket:--bag, crisping pin.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bag, purse</OL>'),
(2755, '~ynwyyrx', 'from the pl. of (02716) and the pl. of (03123)', 'charey-yowniym', 'TWOT - 730a', 'khar-ay\'-yo-neem\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the plural of «02716» and the plural of «03123»; excrements of doves {or perhaps rather the plural of a single word charapyown {khar-aw-yone\'}; of similar or uncertain derivation, probably a kind of vegetable:--doves\' dung.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dung, doves\' dung</OL>'),
(2756, '@yrx', 'from (02778)', 'Chariyph', 'None', 'khaw-reef\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02778»; autumnal; Chariph, the name of two Israelites:--Hariph.', 'Hariph = \"a plucking off\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of a family of exiles returning with Zerubbabel<LI>a head of the people who sealed the covenant with Nehemiah</OL>'),
(2757, '#yrx', 'from (02782)', 'chariyts', 'TWOT - 752c', 'khaw-reets\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or charits {khaw-reets\'}; from «02782»; properly, incisure or (passively) incised (compare «02742»); hence, a threshing-sledge (with sharp teeth): also a slice (as cut):--+ cheese, harrow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a cut, thing cut, sharp instrument, sharp cutting instrument, harrow, hoe</OL>'),
(2758, 'Xyrx', 'from (02790)', 'chariysh', 'TWOT - 760c', 'khaw-reesh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02790»; ploughing or its season:--earing (time), ground.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ploughing, ploughing time</OL>'),
(2759, 'yXyrx', 'from (02790) in the sense of silence', 'chariyshiy', 'TWOT - 760e', 'khar-ee-shee\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02790» in the sense of silence; quiet, i.e. sultry (as feminine noun, the sirocco or hot east wind):--vehement.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>harsh, hot, sultry, silent (meaning uncertain)</OL>'),
(2760, '$rx', 'a primitive root', 'charak', 'TWOT - 741,742', 'khaw-rak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to braid (i.e. to entangle or snare) or catch (game) in a net:--roast.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to set in motion, start<LI>(CLBL) to roast</OL>'),
(2761, '$rx', 'a root probably allied to the equivalent of (02787)', 'charak', 'TWOT - 2743', 'khar-ak\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) a root probably allied to the equivalent of «02787»; to scorch:--singe.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Ithpael) to singe</OL>'),
(2762, '$rx', 'from (02760)', 'cherek', 'TWOT - 742a', 'kheh\'-rek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02760»; properly, a net, i.e. (by analogy) lattice:--lattice.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lattice, other opening through which one may look</OL>'),
(2763, '~rx', 'a primitive root', 'charam', 'TWOT - 744,745', 'khaw-ram\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to seclude; specifically (by a ban) to devote to religious uses (especially destruction); physical and reflexive, to be blunt as to the nose:--make accursed, consecrate, (utterly) destroy, devote, forfeit, have a flat nose, utterly (slay, make away).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to ban, devote, destroy utterly, completely destroy, dedicate for destruction, exterminate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to prohibit (for common use), ban<LI>to consecrate, devote, dedicate for destruction<LI>to exterminate, completely destroy</OL><LI>(Hophal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be put under the ban, be devoted to destruction<LI>to be devoted, be forfeited<LI>to be completely destroyed</OL></OL><LI>to split, slit, mutilate (a part of the body)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to mutilate<LI>(Hiphil) to divide</OL></OL>'),
(2764, '~rx', 'from (02763)', 'cherem', 'TWOT - 744a,745a', 'khay\'-rem', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (Zecheriah 14:11) cherem {kheh\'-rem}; from «02763»; physical (as shutting in) a net (either literally or figuratively); usually a doomed object; abstr. extermination:--(ac-)curse(-d, -d thing), dedicated thing, things which should have been utterly destroyed, (appointed to) utter destruction, devoted (thing), net.', ''),
(2765, '~rx', 'from (02763)', 'Chorem', 'None', 'khor-ame\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02763»; devoted; Chorem, a place in Palestine:--Horem.', 'Horem = \"sacred\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the fortified towns in Naphtali</OL>'),
(2766, '~rx', 'from (02763)', 'Charim', 'None', 'khaw-reem\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02763»; snub-nosed; Charim, an Israelite:--Harim.', 'Harim = \"dedicated\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest in the time of David who had charge of the 3rd course<LI>head of a family of exiles totalling 1017 who returned with Zerubbabel<LI>another head of a family of exiles totalling 320 who returned with Zerubbabel<LI>a priest in the time of Nehemiah<LI>a ruler of the people under Nehemiah</OL>'),
(2767, 'hmrx', 'from (02763)', 'Chormah', 'None', 'khor-maw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02763»; devoted; Chormah, a place in Palestine:--Hormah.', 'Hormah = \"devotion\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town of the Canaanites, conquered by Joshua, allotted to Judah, and located in the south of Judah</OL>'),
(2768, '!wmrx', 'from (02763)', 'Chermown', 'TWOT - 744b', 'kher-mone\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02763»; abrupt; Chermon, a mount of Palestine:--Hermon.', 'Hermon = \"a sanctuary\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a mountain on the northeastern border of Palestine and Lebanon and overlooking the border city of Dan</OL>'),
(2769, '~ynwmrx', 'pl. of (02768)', 'Chermowniym', 'None', 'kher-mo-neem\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'plural of «02768»; Hermons, i.e. its peaks:--the Hermonites.', 'Hermonites = see Hermon \"a sanctuary\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the name for the three summits of Mount Hermon located on the border of Palestine and Lebanon</OL>'),
(2770, 'Xmrx', 'from (02763)', 'chermesh', 'TWOT - 746', 'kher-mashe\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02763»; a sickle (as cutting):--sickle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sickle</OL>'),
(2771, '!rx', 'from (02787)', 'Charan', 'TWOT - 747', 'kaw-rawn\'', '', 'from «02787»; parched; Charan, the name of a man and also of a place:--Haran.', 'Haran = \"mountaineer\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Caleb by his concubine Ephah n pr loc<LI>the city to which Abraham migrated when he left Ur of the Chaldees and where he stayed until his father died before leaving for the promised land; located in Mesopotamia in Padan-aram at the foot of Mount Masius between the Khabour and the Euphrates</OL>'),
(2772, 'ynrx', 'from (02773)', 'Choroniy', 'None', 'kho-ro-nee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'patrial from «02773»; a Choronite or inhabitant of Choronaim:--Horonite.', 'Horonite = \"native of Horonaim\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Horonaim in Moab<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the designation of Sanballat, the opponent of Nehemiah</OL></OL>'),
(2773, '~ynrx', 'dual of a derivative from (02356)', 'Choronayim', 'None', 'kho-ro-nah\'-yim', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'dual of a derivative from «02356»; double cave-town; Choronajim, a place in Moab:--Horonaim.', 'Horonaim = \"two caves\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town of Moab</OL>'),
(2774, 'rpnrx', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Charnepher', 'None', 'khar-neh\'fer', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; Charnepher, an Israelite:--Harnepher.', 'Harnepher = \"panting\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Zophah of the tribe of Asher</OL>'),
(2775, 'orx', 'from an unused root meaning to scrape', 'cherec', 'TWOT - 759b,748a', 'kheh\'-res', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (with a directive enclitic) charcah (khar\'- saw}; from an unused root meaning to scrape; the itch; also (perhaps from the mediating idea of «02777») the sun:--itch, sun.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>itch, an eruptive disease<LI>sun</OL>'),
(2776, 'orx', 'the same as (02775)', 'Cherec', 'None', 'kheh\'-res', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «02775»; shining; Cheres, a mountain in Palestine:--Heres.', 'Heres = \"the sun\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a mountain inhabited by Amorites in Moab; the place where Gideon turned back from chasing the Midianites</OL>'),
(2777, 'tworx', 'from (02775) (apparently in the sense of a red tile used for scraping)', 'charcuwth', 'TWOT - 759c', 'khar-sooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02775» (apparently in the sense of a red tile used for scraping); a potsherd, i.e. (by implication) a pottery; the name of a gate at Jerusalem:--east.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>potsherd</OL>'),
(2778, '@rx', 'a primitive root', 'charaph.', 'TWOT - 749,750,751', 'khaw-raf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pull off, i.e. (by implication) to expose (as by stripping); specifically, to betroth (as if a surrender); figuratively, to carp at, i.e. defame; denominative (from «02779») to spend the winter:--betroth, blaspheme, defy, jeopard, rail, reproach, upbraid.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to reproach, taunt, blaspheme, defy, jeopardise, rail, upbraid<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to reproach<LI>(Piel) to reproach, defy, taunt</OL><LI>(Qal) to winter, spend harvest time, remain in harvest time<LI>(Niphal) to acquire, be betrothed</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(2779, '@rx', 'from (02778)', 'choreph', 'TWOT - 750a', 'kho\'-ref', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02778»; properly, the crop gathered, i.e. (by implication) the autumn (and winter) season; figuratively, ripeness of age:--cold, winter (-house), youth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>harvest time, autumn<LI>(CLBL) winter</OL>'),
(2780, '@rx', 'from (02778)', 'Chareph', 'None', 'khaw-rafe\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02778»; reproachful; Chareph, an Israelite:--Hareph.', 'Hareph = \"a plucking off\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Caleb and father of Bethgader</OL>'),
(2781, 'hprx', 'from (02778)', 'cherpah', 'TWOT - 749a', 'kher-paw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02778»; contumely, disgrace, the pudenda:--rebuke, reproach(-fully), shame.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>reproach, scorn<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>taunt, scorn (upon enemy)<LI>reproach (resting upon condition of shame, disgrace)<LI>a reproach (an object)</OL></OL>'),
(2782, '#rx', 'a primitive root', 'charats', 'TWOT - 752', 'khaw-rats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to point sharply, i.e. (literally) to wound; figuratively, to be alert, to decide:--bestir self, decide, decree, determine, maim, move.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut, sharpen, decide, decree, determine, maim, move, be decisive, be mutilated<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut, mutilate<LI>to sharpen<LI>to decide</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be decisive</OL></OL>'),
(2783, '#rx', 'from a root corresponding to (02782) (sense of vigour)', 'charats', 'TWOT - 2744', 'khar-ats\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «02782» in the sense of vigor; the loin (as the seat of strength):--loin.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>loin, hip, hip joint</OL>'),
(2784, 'hbbcrx', 'of uncertain derivation', 'chartsubbah', 'TWOT - 754a', 'khar-tsoob-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'of uncertain derivation; a fetter; figuratively, a pain:--band.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bond, fetter, pang, hands<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>bonds<LI>pangs</OL></OL>'),
(2785, '!crx', 'from (02782)', 'chartsan', 'TWOT - 752d', 'kchar-tsan\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02782»; a sour grape (as sharp in taste):--kernel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>kernels, seeds, insignificant vine product, grape seeds?</OL>'),
(2786, 'qrx', 'a primitive root', 'charaq', 'TWOT - 755', 'khaw-rak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to grate the teeth:--gnash.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to gnash, grind (the teeth)</OL>'),
(2787, 'rrx', 'a primitive root', 'charar', 'TWOT - 756', 'khaw-rar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to glow, i.e. literally (to melt, burn, dry up) or figuratively (to show or incite passion:--be angry, burn, dry, kindle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to burn, be hot, be scorched, be charred<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be hot, be scorched<LI>to burn, be burned</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be scorched, be burned<LI>to burn<LI>to be dry, be angry</OL><LI>(Pilpel) to cause to burn</OL></OL>'),
(2788, 'rrx', 'from (02787)', 'charer', 'TWOT - 756a', 'khaw-rare\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02787»; arid:--parched place.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dry regions, parched place</OL>'),
(2789, 'Xrx', 'a collateral form mediating between (02775) and (02791)', 'cheres', 'TWOT - 759a', 'kheh\'-res', 'Noun Masculine', 'a collateral form mediating between «02775» and «02791»; a piece of pottery:--earth(-en), (pot-)sherd, + stone.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>earthenware, clay pottery, shard, potsherd, earthen vessel</OL>'),
(2790, 'Xrx', 'a primitive root', 'charash', 'TWOT - 760,761', 'khaw-rash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to scratch, i.e. (by implication) to engrave, plough; hence (from the use of tools) to fabricate (of any material); figuratively, to devise (in a bad sense); hence (from the idea of secrecy) to be silent, to let alone; hence (by implication) to be deaf (as an accompaniment of dumbness):--X altogether, cease, conceal, be deaf, devise, ear, graven, imagine, leave off speaking, hold peace, plow(-er, man), be quiet, rest, practise secretly, keep silence, be silent, speak not a word, be still, hold tongue, worker.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut in, plough, engrave, devise<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut in, engrave<LI>to plough<LI>to devise</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be ploughed<LI>(Hiphil) to plot evil</OL><LI>to be silent, be dumb, be speechless, be deaf<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be silent<LI>to be deaf</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be silent, keep quiet<LI>to make silent<LI>to be deaf, show deafness</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to remain silent</OL></OL>'),
(2791, 'Xrx', 'from (02790)', 'cheresh', 'TWOT - 761b,763a', 'kheh\'-resh', '', 'from «02790»; magical craft; also silence:--cunning, secretly.', 'adv<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>silently, secretly n m<LI>magic art, magician</OL>'),
(2792, 'Xrx', 'the same as (02791)', 'Cheresh', 'None', 'kheh\'-resh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «02791»:--Cheresh, a Levite:--Heresh.', 'Heresh = \"mute\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite attached to the tabernacle</OL>'),
(2793, 'Xrx', 'from (02790)', 'choresh', 'TWOT - 762a', 'kho\'-resh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02790»; a forest (perhaps as furnishing the material for fabric):--bough, forest, shroud, wood.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wood, wooded height, forest, wooded area</OL>'),
(2794, 'Xrx', 'act. participle of (02790)', 'choresh', 'TWOT - 763a?', 'kho-rashe\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'active participle of «02790»; a fabricator or mechanic:--artificer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>metal craftsman</OL>'),
(2795, 'Xrx', 'from (02790)', 'cheresh', 'TWOT - 761a', 'khay-rashe\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02790»; deaf (whether literally or spir.):--deaf.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>deaf</OL>'),
(2796, 'Xrx', 'from (02790)', 'charash', 'TWOT - 760a', 'khaw-rawsh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02790»; a fabricator or any material:--artificer, (+) carpenter, craftsman, engraver, maker, + mason, skilful, (+) smith, worker, workman, such as wrought.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>craftsman, artisan, engraver, graver, artificer<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>graver, artificer<LI>skilful to destroy (warriors) (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(2797, 'aXrx', 'from (02792)', 'Charsha\'', 'None', 'khar-shaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02792»; magician; Charsha, one of the Nethinim:--Harsha.', 'Harsha = \"mute\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of a family of exiles returning with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(2798, '~yXrx', 'pl. of (02796)', 'Charashiym', 'None', 'khar-aw-sheem\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'plural of «02796»; mechanics, the name of a valley in Jerusalem:--Charashim, craftsmen.', 'Charashim or Harashim = \"valley of craftsmen\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a valley near Lydda, a few miles east of Joppa, founded by Joab of Othniel\'s family</OL>'),
(2799, 'tXrx', 'from (02790)', 'charosheth', 'TWOT - 760b', 'khar-o\'-sheth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02790»; mechanical work:--carving, cutting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>carving, skilful working</OL>'),
(2800, 'tXrx', 'the same as (02799)', 'Charosheth', 'None', 'khar-o\'-sheth', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «02799»; Charosheth, a place in Palestine:--Harosheth.', 'Harosheth = \"woodland\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in the north of the land of Canaan on the west coast of the lake Merom</OL>'),
(2801, 'trx', 'a primitive root', 'charath', 'TWOT - 764', 'khaw-rath\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to engrave:--graven.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to engrave, graven</OL>'),
(2802, 'trx', 'from (02801) (but equivalent to (02793))', 'Chereth', 'None', 'kheh\'-reth', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02801» (but equivalent to «02793»); forest; Chereth, a thicket in Palestine:--Hereth.', 'Hareth = \"forest\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a forest whose site is now unknown</OL>'),
(2803, 'bXx', 'a primitive root', 'chashab', 'TWOT - 767', 'khaw-shab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to plait or interpenetrate, i.e. (literally) to weave or (gen.) to fabricate; figuratively, to plot or contrive (usually in a malicious sense); hence (from the mental effort) to think, regard, value, compute:--(make) account (of), conceive, consider, count, cunning (man, work, workman), devise, esteem, find out, forecast, hold, imagine, impute, invent, be like, mean, purpose, reckon(-ing be made), regard, think.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to think, plan, esteem, calculate, invent, make a judgment, imagine, count<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to think, account<LI>to plan, devise, mean<LI>to charge, impute, reckon<LI>to esteem, value, regard<LI>to invent</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be accounted, be thought, be esteemed<LI>to be computed, be reckoned<LI>to be imputed</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to think upon, consider, be mindful of<LI>to think to do, devise, plan<LI>to count, reckon</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to be considered</OL></OL>'),
(2804, 'bXx', 'corresponding to (02803)', 'chashab', 'TWOT - 2745', 'khash-ab\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02803»; to regard:--repute.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to think, account</OL>'),
(2805, 'bXx', 'from (02803)', 'chesheb', 'TWOT - 767a', 'khay\'-sheb', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02803»; a belt or strap (as being interlaced):--curious girdle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>girdle, band, ingenious work<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>ingenious work - the name of the girdle or band of the ephod</OL></OL>'),
(2806, 'hnddbXx', 'from (02803) and (01777)', 'Chashbaddanah', 'None', 'khash-bad-daw\'-naw', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02803» and «01777»; considerate judge; Chasbaddanah, an Israelite:--Hasbadana.', 'Hashbadana = \"considerate judge\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the men who stood on the left of Ezra while he read the law to the people</OL>'),
(2807, 'hbXx', 'from (02803)', 'Chashubah', 'None', 'khash-oo-baw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02803»; estimation; Cashubah, an Israelite:--Hashubah.', 'Hashubah = \"consideration\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(2808, '!wbXx', 'from (02803)', 'cheshbown', 'TWOT - 767b', 'khesh-bone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02803»; properly, contrivance; by implication, intelligence:--account, device, reason.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>account, reasoning, reckoning</OL>'),
(2809, '!wbXx', 'the same as (02808)', 'Cheshbown', 'None', 'khesh-bone\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «02808»; Cheshbon, a place East of the Jordan:--Heshbon.', 'Heshbon = \"stronghold\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the capital city of Sihon, king of the Amorites, located on the western border of the high plain and on the border line between the tribes of Reuben and Gad</OL>'),
(2810, '!wbXXx', 'from (02803)', 'chishshabown', 'TWOT - 767c', 'khish-shaw-bone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02803»; a contrivance, i.e. actual (a warlike machine) or mental (a machination):--engine, invention.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>device, invention</OL>'),
(2811, 'hybXx', 'from (02803) and (03050)', 'Chashabyah', 'None', 'khash-ab-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Chashabyahuw {khash-ab-yaw\'-hoo}; from «02803» and «03050»; Jah has regarded; Chashabjah, the name of nine Israelites:--Hashabiah.', 'Hashabiah = \"Jehovah has considered\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Merarite Levite<LI>the 4th of the 6 sons of Jeduthun who had charge of the 12th course<LI>one of the descendants of Hebron the son of Kohath<LI>the son of Kemuel, who was prince of the tribe of Levi in the time of David<LI>a Levite, one of the chiefs of his tribe who officiated for Josiah at his great passover feast<LI>a Merarite Levite, one of the chief priests who accompanied Ezra from Babylon; ruler of half the circuit of Keilah and one who repaired a portion of the wall of Jerusalem under Nehemiah. He sealed the covenant of reformation after the return from captivity<LI>a Levite, son of Bunni in the time of Nehemiah<LI>a Levite, son of Mattaniah in the time of Nehemiah<LI>a priest of the family of Hilkiah in the days of Joiakim, son of Jeshua</OL>'),
(2812, 'hnbXx', 'fem. of (02808)', 'Chashabnah', 'None', 'khash-ab-naw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'feminine of «02808»; inventiveness; Chashnah, an Israelite:--Hashabnah.', 'Hashabnah = \"Jehovah has considered\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the chiefs of the people who sealed the covenant with Nehemiah</OL>'),
(2813, 'hynbXx', 'from (02808) and (03050)', 'Chashabnyah', 'None', 'khash-ab-neh-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02808» and «03050»; thought of Jah; Chashabnejah, the name of two Israelites:--Hashabniah.', 'Hashabniah = \"whom Jehovah regards\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the father of Hattush, repairer of the wall<LI>a Levite who was among those who officiated at the great fast under Ezra and Nehemiah when the covenant was sealed</OL>'),
(2814, 'hXx', 'a primitive root', 'chashah', 'TWOT - 768', 'khaw-shaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to hush or keep quiet:--hold peace, keep silence, be silent, (be) still.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be silent, quiet, still, inactive<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be silent, be still<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be silent, exhibit silence<LI>to show inactivity, be inactive<LI>to make silent, make quiet, cause to be still</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2815, 'bwXXx', 'from (02803)', 'Chashshuwb', 'None', 'khash-shoob\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02803»; intelligent; Chashshub, the name of two or three Israelites:--Hashub, Hasshub.', 'Hashub = \"considerate\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Merarite Levite chief, son of Azrikam<LI>a son of Pahath-moab who assisted in the repair of the wall of Jerusalem<LI>a man who assisted in the repair of the wall of Jerusalem; may be same as 2 above<LI>one of the heads of the people who sealed the covenant with Nehemiah</OL>'),
(2816, '$wXx', 'from a root corresponding to (02821)', 'chashowk', 'TWOT - 2747', 'khash-oke\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «02821»; the dark:--darkness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>darkness</OL>'),
(2817, 'apwXx', 'from (02834)', 'Chasuwpha\'', 'None', 'khas-oo-faw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Chasuphao {khas-oo-faw\'}; from «02834»; nakedness; Chasupha, one of the Nethinim:--Hashupha, Hasupha.', 'Hasupha or Hashupha = \"stripped\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of the family of temple slaves returning from exile in the 1st caravan</OL>'),
(2818, 'xXx', 'a collateral root to one corresponding to (02363) in the sense of readiness', 'chashach', 'TWOT - 2746', 'khash-akh\'', '', '(Aramaic) a collateral root to one corresponding to «02363» in the sense of readiness; to be necessary (from the idea of convenience) or (transitively) to need:--careful, have need of.', 'v<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to need, have need n<LI>(P\'al) the thing needed</OL>'),
(2819, 'twxXx', 'from a root corresponding to (02818)', 'chashchuwth', 'TWOT - 2746b', 'khash-khooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a root corresponding to «02818»; necessity:--be needful.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>things needed, requirements, that which is required</OL>'),
(2820, '$Xx', 'a primitive root', 'chasak', 'TWOT - 765', 'khaw-sak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to restrain or (reflex.) refrain; by implication, to refuse, spare, preserve; also (by interch. with «02821») to observe:--assuage, × darken, forbear, hinder, hold back, keep (back), punish, refrain, reserve, spare, withhold.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to withhold, restrain, hold back, keep in check, refrain<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to withhold, keep back, keep for oneself, keep from, hold in check, refrain, spare, reserve<LI>to restrain, check</OL><LI>(Niphal) to assuage, be spared</OL></OL>'),
(2821, '$Xx', 'a primitive root', 'chashak', 'TWOT - 769', 'khaw-shak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be dark (as withholding light); transitively, to darken:--be black, be (make) dark, darken, cause darkness, be dim, hide.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or become dark, grow dim, be darkened, be black, be hidden<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or grow dark<LI>to have a dark colour<LI>to grow dim</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make dark, cause to be dark<LI>to hide, conceal<LI>to obscure, confuse (fig.)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2822, '$Xx', 'from (02821)', 'choshek', 'TWOT - 769a', 'kho-shek\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02821»; the dark; hence (literally) darkness; figuratively, misery, destruction, death, ignorance, sorrow, wickedness:--dark(-ness), night, obscurity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>darkness, obscurity<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>darkness<LI>secret place</OL></OL>'),
(2823, '$Xx', 'from (02821)', 'chashok', 'TWOT - 769b', 'khaw-shoke\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02821»; dark (figuratively, i.e. obscure):--meaning', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>obscure, insignificant, low</OL>'),
(2824, 'hkXx', 'from (02821)', 'cheshkah', 'None', 'khesh-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02821»; darkness:--dark.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>darkness, obscure, low</OL>'),
(2825, 'hkXx', 'from (02821)', 'chashekah', 'TWOT - 769c', 'khash-ay-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or chashekah {khash-ay-kaw\'}; from «02821»; darkness; figuratively, misery:--darkness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>darkness</OL>'),
(2826, 'lXx', 'a primitive root', 'chashal', 'TWOT - 770', 'khaw-shal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to make (intrans. be) unsteady, i.e. weak:--feeble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shatter<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be feeble</OL></OL>'),
(2827, 'lXx', 'a root corresponding to (02826)', 'chashal', 'TWOT - 2748', 'khash-al\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) a root corresponding to «02826»; to weaken, i.e. crush:--subdue.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to subdue, crush, shatter</OL>'),
(2828, '~Xx', 'from the same as (02831)', 'Chashum', 'None', 'khaw-shoom\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «02831»; enriched; Chashum, the name of two or three Israelites:--Hashum.', 'Hashum = \"rich\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of a family of 223 exiles returning with Zerubbabel<LI>one of the priests or Levites who stood on Ezra\'s left while he read the law</OL>'),
(2829, '!wmXx', 'the same as (02831)', 'Cheshmown', 'None', 'klesh-mone\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «02831»; opulent; Cheshmon, a place in Palestine:--Heshmon.', 'Heshmon = \"rich soil\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in the extreme south of Judah; site uncertain</OL>'),
(2830, 'lmXx', 'of uncertain derivation', 'chashmal', 'TWOT - 770.1', 'khash-mal\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; probably bronze or polished spectrum metal:--amber.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a shining substance, amber or electrum or bronze (uncertain)</OL>'),
(2831, '!mXx', 'from an unused root (probably meaning firm or capacious in resources)', 'chashman', 'TWOT - 771', 'khash-man\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root (probably meaning firm or capacious in resources); apparently wealthy:--princes.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ambassadors, bronze (meaning uncertain)</OL>'),
(2832, 'hnmXx', 'fem. of (02831)', 'Chashmonah', 'None', 'khash-mo-naw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'feminine of «02831»; fertile; Chasmonah, a place in the Desert:--Hashmonah.', 'Hashmonah = \"fatness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a station of Israel in the wilderness</OL>'),
(2833, '!Xx', 'from an unused root probably meaning to contain or sparkle', 'choshen', 'TWOT - 772a', 'kho\'-shen', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to contain or sparkle; perhaps a pocket (as holding the Urim and Thummim), or rich (as containing gems), used only of the gorget of the highpriest:--breastplate.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>breastplate, breastpiece<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>sacred pouch of the high priest designed to hold the Urim and Thummim</OL></OL>'),
(2834, '@Xx', 'a primitive root', 'chasaph', 'TWOT - 766', 'khaw-saf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to strip off, i.e. generally to make naked (for exertion or in disgrace), to drain away or bail up (a liquid):--make bare, clean, discover, draw out, take, uncover.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strip, strip off, lay bare, make bare, draw out<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strip off<LI>to strip, lay bare<LI>to draw (water), skim, take from the surface</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2835, '@Xx', 'from (02834)', 'chasiph', 'TWOT - 766a', 'khaw-seef\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02834»; properly, drawn off, i.e. separated; hence, a small company (as divided from the rest):--little flock.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>small flocks, little flocks</OL>'),
(2836, 'qXx', 'a primitive root', 'chashaq', 'TWOT - 773', 'khaw-shak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to cling, i.e. join, (figuratively) to love, delight in; elliptically (or by interchangeable for «02820») to deliver:--have a delight, (have a ) desire, fillet, long, set (in) love.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to love, be attached to, long for<LI>(Piel) fillet<LI>(Pual) fillet</OL>'),
(2837, 'qXx', 'from (02836)', 'chesheq', 'TWOT - 773a', 'khay\'-shek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02836»; delight:--desire, pleasure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>desire, thing desired</OL>'),
(2838, 'qXx', 'past participle of (02836)', 'chashuq', 'TWOT - 773b', 'khaw-shook\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or chashuwq {khaw-shook\'}; past participle of «02836»; attached, i.e. a fence-rail or rod connecting the posts or pillars:--fillet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fillets, binders<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>rings clasping a pillar of the tabernacle or silver rods between the pillars</OL></OL>'),
(2839, 'qXXx', 'from (02836)', 'chishshuq', 'TWOT - 773d', 'khish-shook\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02836»; conjoined, i.e. a wheel-spoke or rod connecting the hub with the rim:--felloe.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spoke, spoke of a wheel</OL>'),
(2840, 'rXXx', 'from an unused root meaning to bind together', 'chishshur', 'TWOT - 774b', 'khish-shoor\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to bind together; combined, i.e. the nave or hub of a wheel (as holding the spokes together):--spoke.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hub, hub of a wheel, nave</OL>'),
(2841, 'hrXx', 'from the same as (02840)', 'chashrah', 'TWOT - 774a', 'khash-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «02840»; properly, a combination or gathering, i.e. of watery clouds:--dark.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>collection, mass, an accumulation of water</OL>'),
(2842, 'XXx', 'by variation for (07179)', 'chashash', 'TWOT - 775a', 'khaw-shash\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'by variation for «07179»; dry grass:--chaff.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chaff, dry grass</OL>'),
(2843, 'ytXx', 'from (02364)', 'Chushathiy', 'None', 'khoo-shaw-thee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'patronymically from «02364»; a Chushathite or descendant of Chushah:--Hushathite.', 'Hushathite = \"inhabitant of Hushah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Hushah or a descendant of Hushah; the designation given to two of David\'s mighty warriors</OL>'),
(2844, 'tx', 'from (02865)', 'chath', 'TWOT - 784a', 'khath', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02865»; concretely, crushed; also afraid; abstractly, terror:--broken, dismayed, dread, fear.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fear, terror<LI>shattered, dismayed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>shattered<LI>dismayed</OL></OL>'),
(2845, 'tx', 'from (02865)', 'Cheth', 'TWOT - 776', 'khayth', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02865»; terror; Cheth, an aboriginal Canaanite:--Heth.', 'Heth = \"terror\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Canaan and the progenitor of the Hittites</OL>'),
(2846, 'htx', 'a primitive root', 'chathah', 'TWOT - 777', 'khaw-thaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to lay hold of; especially to pick up fire:--heap, take (away).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to take hold of, seize, take away, pile up, snatch up (coals)</OL>'),
(2847, 'httx', 'from (02865)', 'chittah', 'TWOT - 784d', 'khit-taw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02865»; fear:--terror.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>terror, fear</OL>'),
(2848, 'lwttx', 'from (02853)', 'chittuwl', 'TWOT - 779b', 'khit-tool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02853»; swathed, i.e. a bandage:--roller.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bandage</OL>'),
(2849, 'txtx', 'from (02844)', 'chathchath', 'TWOT - 784e', 'khath-khath\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02844»; terror:--fear.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>terror</OL>'),
(2850, 'yttx', 'from (02845)', 'Chittiy', 'TWOT - 776a', 'khit-tee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'patronymically from «02845»; a Chittite, or descendant of Cheth:--Hittite, Hittities.', 'Hittite = \"descendant of Heth\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the nation descended from Heth, the 2nd son of Canaan; once inhabitants of central Anatolia (modern Turkey), later in north Lebanon</OL>'),
(2851, 'tyttx', 'from (02865)', 'chittiyth', 'TWOT - 784f', 'khit-teeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02865»; fear:--terror.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>terror</OL>'),
(2852, '$tx', 'a primitive root', 'chathak', 'TWOT - 778', 'khaw-thak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to cut off, i.e. (figuratively) to decree:--determine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to divide, determine<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be determined, be decreed, be settled, be marked out</OL></OL>'),
(2853, 'ltx', 'a primitive root', 'chathal', 'TWOT - 779', 'khaw-thal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to swathe:--X at all, swaddle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to entwine, enwrap, be swaddled<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pual) to be swathed, be enwraped<LI>(Hophal) to be swathed, be swaddled</OL></OL>'),
(2854, 'hlltx', 'from (02853)', 'chathullah', 'TWOT - 779a', 'khath-ool-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02853»; a swathing cloth (figuratively):--swaddling band.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>swaddling-band, navel-band</OL>'),
(2855, '!ltx', 'from (02853)', 'Chethlon', 'None', 'kheth-lone\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02853»; enswathed; Chethlon, a place in Palestine:--Hethlon.', 'Hethlon = \"hiding place\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place on the northern border of Palestine; site unknown</OL>'),
(2856, '~tx', 'a primitive root', 'chatham', 'TWOT - 780', 'khaw-tham\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to close up; especially to seal:--make an end, mark, seal (up), stop.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to seal, seal up, affix a seal<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to seal, affix one\'s seal<LI>to seal up, fasten up by sealing</OL><LI>(Niphal) to seal<LI>(Piel) to lock up<LI>(Hiphil) to be stopped</OL></OL>'),
(2857, '~tx', 'a root corresponding to (02856)', 'chatham', 'TWOT - 2749', 'khath-am\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) a root corresponding to «02856»; to seal:--seal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) seal.</OL>'),
(2858, 'tmtx', 'act. participle of (02856)', 'chothemeth', 'TWOT - 780b', 'kho-the-meth', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine active participle of «02856»; a seal:--signet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>signet ring, signet seal</OL>'),
(2859, '!tx', 'a primitive root', 'chathan', 'TWOT - 781b', 'khaw-than\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to give (a daughter) away in marriage; hence (generally) to contract affinity by marriage:--join in affinity, father in law, make marriages, mother in law, son in law.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to become a son-in-law, make oneself a daughter\'s husband<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) wife\'s father, wife\'s mother, father-in-law, mother-in- law (participle)<LI>(Hithpael) to make oneself a daughter\'s husband</OL></OL>'),
(2860, '!tx', 'from (02859)', 'chathan', 'TWOT - 781c', 'khaw-thawn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02859»; a relative by marriage (especially through the bride); figuratively, a circumcised child (as a species of religious espousal):--bridegroom, husband, son in law.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son-in-law, daughter\'s husband, bridegroom, husband</OL>'),
(2861, 'hnntx', 'from (02859)', 'chathunnah', 'TWOT - 781d', 'khath-oon-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02859»; a wedding:--espousal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wedding, marriage</OL>'),
(2862, '@tx', 'a primitive root', 'chathaph', 'TWOT - 782', 'khaw-thaf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to clutch:--take away.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to seize, take away, snatch away</OL>'),
(2863, '@tx', 'from (02862)', 'chetheph', 'TWOT - 782a', 'kheh\'-thef', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02862»; properly, rapine; figuratively, robbery:--prey.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>prey<LI>(CLBL) robber</OL>'),
(2864, 'rtx', 'a primitive root', 'chathar', 'TWOT - 783', 'khaw-thar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to force a passage, as by burglary; figuratively, with oars:--dig (through), row.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dig, row<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dig (into houses - of burglary)<LI>to row (in water)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2865, 'ttx', 'a primitive root', 'chathath', 'TWOT - 784', 'khaw-thath\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to prostrate; hence, to break down, either (literally) by violence, or (figuratively) by confusion and fear:--abolish, affright, be (make) afraid, amaze, beat down, discourage, (cause to) dismay, go down, scare, terrify.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be shattered, be dismayed, be broken, be abolished, be afraid<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be shattered, be broken<LI>to be dismayed</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be broken, be dismayed<LI>(Piel) to be shattered, be dismayed, be scared<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to be dismayed<LI>to dismay, terrify<LI>to shatter</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2866, 'ttx', 'from (02865)', 'chathath', 'TWOT - 784c', 'khath-ath\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02865»; dismay:--casting down.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>terror</OL>'),
(2867, 'ttx', 'the same as (02866)', 'Chathath', 'None', 'khath-ath\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «02866»; Chathath, an Israelite:--cathath.', 'Hathath = \"fearful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Othniel and grandson of Kenaz, the brother of Caleb</OL>'),
(2868, 'baj', 'a primitive root', 't\'eb', 'TWOT - 2750', 'teh-abe\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) a primitive root; to rejoice:--be glad.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to be glad, be good</OL>'),
(2869, 'bj', 'from (02868)', 'tab', 'TWOT - 2750a', '', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «02868»; the same as «02896»; good:--fine, good.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>good</OL>'),
(2870, 'labj', 'from (02895) and (0410)', 'tab\'el', 'None', 'taw-beh-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02895» and «0410»; pleasing (to) God; Tabeel, the name of a Syrian and of a Persian:--Tabeal, Tabeel.', 'Tabeal = \"God is good\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a man whose son was either in the army of Pekah or the army of Rezin and whom Pekah and Rezin proposed to make king of Israel Tabeel = \"God is good\"<LI>an officer of the Persian government in Samaria in the reign of Artaxerxes</OL>'),
(2871, 'lwbj', 'pass. participle of (02881)', 'tabuwl', 'TWOT - 788a', 'taw-bool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'passive participle of «02881»; properly, dyed, i.e. a turban (probably as of colored stuff):--dyed attire.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>turban</OL>'),
(2872, 'rwbbj', 'from an unused root meaning to pile up; properly, accumulated', 'tabbuwr', 'TWOT - 790a', 'tab-boor\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to pile up; properly, accumulated; i.e. (by implication) a summit:--middle, midst.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>centre, midst, navel, highest part</OL>'),
(2873, 'xbj', 'a primitive root', 'tabach', 'TWOT - 786', 'taw-bakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to slaughter (animals or men):--kill, (make) slaughter, slay.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to slaughter, slay, butcher, kill ruthlessly<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to slaughter, butcher<LI>to slay, kill ruthlessly (fig.)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2874, 'xbj', 'from (02873)', 'tebach', 'TWOT - 786a', 'teh\'-bakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02873»; properly, something slaughtered; hence, a beast (or meat, as butchered); abstr. butchery (or concretely, a place of slaughter):--X beast, slaughter, × slay, × sore.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>slaughter, slaughtering, animal<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>slaughtering, slaughter (of animals)<LI>slaughter (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(2875, 'xbj', 'the same as (02874)', 'Tebach', 'None', 'teh\'-bakh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «02874»; massacre; Tebach, the name of a Mesopotamian and of an Israelite:--Tebah.', 'Tebah = \"a slaughter\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Nahor by his concubine Reumah</OL>'),
(2876, 'xbbj', 'from (02873)', 'tabbach', 'TWOT - 786c', 'tab-bawkh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02873»; properly, a butcher; hence, a lifeguardsman (because he was acting as an executioner); also a cook (usually slaughtering the animal for food):--cook, guard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>executioner, cook, bodyguard, guardsman<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>cook (who also killed the animal for food)<LI>guardsmen, bodyguard</OL></OL>'),
(2877, 'xbbj', 'the same as (02876)', 'tabbach', 'TWOT - 2751', 'tab-bawkh\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) the same as «02876»; a lifeguardsman:--guard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bodyguard, executioner, guardsmen</OL>'),
(2878, 'hxbj', 'from (02874)', 'tibehah', 'TWOT - 786b', 'tib-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02874» and meaning the same:--flesh, slaughter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>slaughtered meat, a slaughter, flesh, meat, thing slaughtered</OL>'),
(2879, 'hxbbj', 'from (02876)', 'tabbachah', 'TWOT - 786d', 'tab-baw-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02876»; a female cook:--cook.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>female cook, cook</OL>'),
(2880, 'txbj', 'from (02878)', 'Tibchath', 'None', 'tib-khath\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «02878»; slaughter; Tibchath, a place in Syria:--Tibhath.', 'Tibhath = \"extension\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Syrian city of Hadadezer, king of Zobah; also \'Betah\'</OL>'),
(2881, 'lbj', 'a primitive root', 'tabal', 'TWOT - 787,788', 'taw-bal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to dip, to immerse:--dip, plunge.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dip, dip into, plunge<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dip in or into<LI>to dip oneself</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be dipped</OL></OL>'),
(2882, 'whylbj', 'from (02881) and (03050)', 'Tbalyahuw', 'None', 'teb-al-yaw\'-hoo', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02881» and «03050»; Jah has dipped; Tebaljah, an Israelite:--Tebaliah.', 'Tebaliah = \"purified\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 3rd son of Hosah of the children of Merari and temple gatekeeper</OL>'),
(2883, '[bj', 'a primitive root', 'taba`', 'TWOT - 789', 'taw-bah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to sink:--drown, fasten, settle, sink.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sink, sink into, sink down, pierce, settle down, drown, be settled, be planted<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to sink, sink down<LI>(Pual) to be sunk<LI>(Hophal) to cause to sink</OL></OL>'),
(2884, 'tw[bbj', 'plural of (02885)', 'Tabba`owth', 'None', 'tab-baw-othe\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'plural of «02885»; rings; Tabbaoth, one of the Nethinim:--Tabaoth.', 'Tabbaoth = \"rings\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a family of temple slaves who returned from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(2885, 't[bbj', 'from (02883)', 'tabba`ath', 'TWOT - 789a', 'tab-bah\'-ath', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02883»; properly, a seal (as sunk into the wax), i.e. signet (for sealing); hence (generally) a ring of any kind:--ring.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ring, signet, signet ring<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>signet ring (as symbol of authority)<LI>ring (as ornament)</OL></OL>'),
(2886, '!wmmrbj', 'from (02895) and (07417)', 'Tabrimmown', 'None', 'tab-rim-mone\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02895» and «07417»; pleasing (to) Rimmon; Tabrimmon, a Syrian:--Tabrimmon.', 'Tabrimon = \"good is Rimmon\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the father of Ben-hadad I, king of Syria</OL>'),
(2887, 'tbj', 'probably of foreign derivation', 'Tebeth', 'None', 'tay\'-beth', 'Noun', 'probably of foreign derivation; Tebeth, the tenth Heb. month:--Tebeth.', 'Tebeth = \"goodness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 10th month of the Jewish calendar corresponding to modern Dec-Jan</OL>'),
(2888, 'tbbj', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Tabbath', 'None', 'tab-bath\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'of uncertain derivation; Tabbath, a place East of the Jordan:--Tabbath.', 'Tabbath = \"celebrated\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>site near which Gideon\'s pursuit of the Midianites stopped; site unknown</OL>'),
(2889, 'rwhj', 'from (02891)', 'tahowr', 'TWOT - 792d', 'taw-hore\'', 'Adjective', 'or tahor {taw-hore\'}; from «02891»; pure (in a physical, chemical, ceremonial or moral sense):--clean, fair, pure(-ness).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pure, clean<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>clean (ceremonially - of animals)<LI>pure (physically)<LI>pure, clean (morally, ethically)</OL></OL>'),
(2890, 'rwhj', 'from (02891)', 'thowr', 'TWOT - 792b', 'teh-hore\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02891»; purity:--pureness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pureness, cleanness, clean, pure<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>clean (ceremonially - of animals)<LI>pure (physically)<LI>pure, clean (morally, ethically)</OL></OL>'),
(2891, 'rhj', 'a primitive root', 'taher', 'TWOT - 792', 'taw-hare\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to be bright; i.e. (by implication) to be pure (physical sound, clear, unadulterated; Levitically, uncontaminated; morally, innocent or holy):--be (make, make self, pronounce) clean, cleanse (self), purge, purify(-ier, self).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be clean, be pure<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be clean (physically - of disease)<LI>to be clean ceremonially<LI>to purify, be clean morally, made clean</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cleanse, purify 1b</OL><LI>physically 1b<LI>ceremonially 1b<LI>morally<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to pronounce clean<LI>to perform the ceremony of cleansing</OL><LI>(Pual) to be cleansed, be pronounced clean<LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to purify oneself 1d</OL><LI>ceremonially 1d<LI>morally<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to present oneself for purification</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2892, 'rhj', 'from (02891)', 'tohar', 'TWOT - 792a', 'to\'-har', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02891»; literally brightness; ceremonially purification:--clearness, glory, purifying.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>purity, purification, purifying<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>purity<LI>purifying</OL><LI>clearness, lustre</OL>'),
(2893, 'hrhj', 'from (02892)', 'tohorah', 'TWOT - 792c', 'toh-or-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «02892»; ceremonial purification; moral purity:--X  is cleansed, cleansing, purification(-fying).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>purifying, cleansing, purification, purity, cleanness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>purifying, menstruation<LI>cleansing, purification</OL></OL>'),
(2894, 'awj', 'a primitive root', 'tuw\'', 'TWOT - 785', 'too', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to sweep away:--sweep.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Pilpel) to sweep, sweep away</OL>'),
(2895, 'bwj', 'a primitive root', 'towb', 'TWOT - 793', 'tobe', 'Verb', 'a primitive root, to be (transitively, do or make) good (or well) in the widest sense:--be (do) better, cheer, be (do, seem) good, (make) goodly, × please, (be, do, go, play) well.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be good, be pleasing, be joyful, be beneficial, be pleasant, be favourable, be happy, be right<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be pleasant, be delightful<LI>to be glad, be joyful<LI>to be better<LI>to be well with, be good for<LI>to be pleasing</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to do well, do good, act right, act rightly</OL></OL>'),
(2896, 'bwj', 'from (02895)', 'towb', 'TWOT - 793a', 'tobe', '', 'from «02895»; good (as an adjective) in the widest sense; used likewise as a noun, both in the masculine and the feminine, the singular and the plural (good, a good or good thing, a good man or woman; the good, goods or good things, good men or women), also as an adverb (well):--beautiful, best, better, bountiful, cheerful, at ease, × fair (word), (be in) favour, fine, glad, good (deed, -lier, -liest, -ly, -ness, -s), graciously, joyful, kindly, kindness, liketh (best), loving, merry, × most, pleasant, + pleaseth, pleasure, precious, prosperity, ready, sweet, wealth, welfare, (be) well ((-favoured)).', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>good, pleasant, agreeable<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>pleasant, agreeable (to the senses)<LI>pleasant (to the higher nature)<LI>good, excellent (of its kind)<LI>good, rich, valuable in estimation<LI>good, appropriate, becoming<LI>better (comparative)<LI>glad, happy, prosperous (of man\'s sensuous nature)<LI>good understanding (of man\'s intellectual nature)<LI>good, kind, benign<LI>good, right (ethical) n m</OL><LI>a good thing, benefit, welfare<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>welfare, prosperity, happiness<LI>good things (collective)<LI>good, benefit<LI>moral good n f</OL><LI>welfare, benefit, good things<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>welfare, prosperity, happiness<LI>good things (collective)<LI>bounty</OL></OL>'),
(2897, 'bwj', 'the same as (02896)', 'Towb', 'None', 'tobe', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «02896»; good; Tob, a region apparently East of the Jordan:--Tob.', 'Tob = \"good\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a region east of the Jordan, north or northeast of Gilead, probably Aramean, location uncertain</OL>'),
(2898, 'bwj', 'from (02895)', 'tuwb', 'TWOT - 793b', 'toob', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02895»; good (as a noun), in the widest sense, especially goodness (superlative concretely, the best), beauty, gladness, welfare:--fair, gladness, good(-ness, thing, -s), joy, go well with.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>goods, good things, goodness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>good things<LI>goods, property<LI>fairness, beauty, joy, prosperity, goodness (abstract)<LI>goodness (of taste, discernment)<LI>goodness (of God) (abstract)</OL></OL>'),
(2899, 'whynd bwj', 'from (02896) and (0138)', 'Towb', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02896» and «0138»; pleasing (to) Adonijah; Tob-Adonijah, an Israelite:--Tob-adonijah.', 'Tob-adonijah = \"my Lord is good\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the Levites sent by Jehoshaphat through the cities of Judah to teach the law to the people</OL>'),
(2900, 'hybwj', 'from (02896) and (03050)', 'Towbiyah', 'None', 'to-bee-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Towbiyahuw {to-bee-yaw\'-hoo}; from «02896» and «03050»; goodness of Jehovah; Tobijah, the name of three Israelites and of one Samaritan:--Tobiah, Tobijah.', 'Tobiah = \"Jehovah is good\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of a family who returned from exile with Zerubbabel but who were unable to prove their connection with Israel<LI>the Ammonite who with Sanballat opposed the rebuilding of Jerusalem<LI>a Levite in the reign of Jehoshaphat<LI>a chief of the returning exiles</OL>'),
(2901, 'hwj', 'a primitive root', 'tavah', 'TWOT - 794', 'taw-vaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to spin:--spin.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to spin</OL>'),
(2902, 'xwj', 'a primitive root', 'tuwach', 'TWOT - 795', 'too\'-akh', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to smear, especially with lime:--daub, overlay, plaister, smut.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to spread over, overlay, plaster, cover over, coat, besmear<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to overspread, coat, overlay<LI>(Niphal) to be coated, be plastered</OL><LI>(Qal) to be besmeared</OL>'),
(2903, 'hppwj', 'from an unused root meaning to go around or bind', 'towphaphah', 'TWOT - 804a', 'to-faw-faw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unusued root meaning to go around or bind; a fillet for the forehead:--frontlet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bands, phylacteries, frontlets, marks</OL>'),
(2904, 'lwj', 'a primitive root', 'tuwl', 'TWOT - 797', 'tool', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pitch over or reel; hence (transitively) to cast down or out:--carry away, (utterly) cast (down, forth, out), send out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hurl, cast<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pilpel) to throw away, carry away, hurl<LI>(Hiphil) to throw, cast, cast out<LI>(Hophal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be hurled, hurled down<LI>to be cast, be thrown, be cast out, be thrown down</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2905, 'rwj', 'from an unused root meaning to range in a regular manner', 'tuwr', 'TWOT - 798a', 'toor', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to range in a regular manner; a row; hence, a wall:--row.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>row<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>row, course (of building)<LI>row (of jewels)</OL></OL>'),
(2906, 'rwj', 'corresponding to (06697)', 'tuwr', 'TWOT - 2752', 'toor', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06697»; a rock or hill:--mountain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mountain</OL>'),
(2907, 'Xwj', 'a primitive root', 'tuws', 'TWOT - 799', 'toos', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pounce as a bird of prey:--haste.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to dart, flutter, rush</OL>'),
(2908, 'twj', 'from a root corresponding to (02901)', 'tvath', 'TWOT - 2753', 'tev-awth\'', 'Adverb', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «02901»; hunger (as twisting):--fasting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fasting, fastingly, hungrily</OL>'),
(2909, 'hxj', 'a primitive root', 'tachah', 'TWOT - 800', 'taw-khaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to stretch a bow, as an archer:--(bow-)shot.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hurl, shoot<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) a bowshot (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(2910, 'hxwj', 'from (02909) (or (02902)) in the sense of overlaying', 'tuwchah', 'TWOT - 795b', 'too-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02909» (or «02902») in the sense of overlaying; (in the plural only) the kidneys (as being covered); hence (figuratively) the inmost thought:--inward parts.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>inner regions, hidden recesses, inward parts</OL>'),
(2911, '!wxj', 'from (02912)', 'tchown', 'TWOT - 802a', 'tekh-one\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02912»; a hand mill; hence, a millstone:--to grind.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mill, grinding mill, hand mill</OL>'),
(2912, '!xj', 'a primitive root', 'tachan', 'TWOT - 802', 'taw-khan\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to grind meal; hence, to be a concubine (that being their employment):--grind(-er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to grind, crush</OL>'),
(2913, 'hnxj', 'from (02912)', 'tachanah', 'TWOT - 802b', 'takh-an-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02912»; a hand mill; hence (figuratively) chewing:--grinding.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mill</OL>'),
(2914, 'rxj', 'from an unused root meaning to burn', 'tchor', 'TWOT - 803a', 'tekh-ore\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to burn; a boil or ulcer (from the inflammation), especially a tumor in the anus or pudenda (the piles):--emerod.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>tumours, haemorrhoids</OL>'),
(2915, 'xyj', 'from (the equiv. of) (02902)', 'tiyach', 'TWOT - 795a', 'tee\'akh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from (the equiv. of) «02902»; mortar or plaster:--daubing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a coating, plaster</OL>'),
(2916, 'tyj', 'from an unused root meaning apparently to be sticky [rath perb. a demon. From (02894), through the idea of dirt to be swept away]', 'tiyt', 'TWOT - 796a', 'teet', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning apparently to be sticky (rath. perb. a demon. from «02894», through the idea of dirt to be swept away); mud or clay; figuratively, calamity:--clay, dirt, mire.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mud, clay, mire, damp dirt<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>mud, mire<LI>clay (poetical)</OL></OL>'),
(2917, '!yj', 'perhaps, by interchange, for a word corresponding to (02916)', 'tiyn', 'TWOT - 2754', 'teen', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) perhaps, by interchange, for a word corresponding to «02916»; clay:--miry.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>clay</OL>'),
(2918, 'hryj', 'from (an equivalent to) (02905)', 'tiyrah', 'TWOT - 798b', 'tee-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of (an equivalent to) «02905»; a wall; hence, a fortress or a hamlet:--(goodly) castle, habitation, palace, row.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>encampment, battlement<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>encampment, tent camp<LI>walled dwelling places, battlement (metaph.)<LI>row (of stones)</OL></OL>'),
(2919, 'lj', 'from (02926)', 'tal', 'TWOT - 807a', 'tal', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02926»; dew (as covering vegetation):--dew.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dew, night mist</OL>'),
(2920, 'lj', 'the same as (02919)', 'tal', 'TWOT - 2755', 'tal', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) the same as «02919»:--dew.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dew</OL>'),
(2921, 'alj', 'a primitive root', 'tala\'', 'TWOT - 805', 'taw-law\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to cover with pieces; i.e. (by implication) to spot or variegate (as tapestry):--clouted, with divers colours, spotted.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to patch, spot, be spotted, be coloured<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to spot<LI>spotted (participle)</OL><LI>(Pual) to be patched</OL></OL>'),
(2922, 'alj', 'apparently from (02921) in the (orig.) sense of covering (for protection)', 'tla\'', 'TWOT - 806a', 'tel-aw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'apparently from «02921» in the (orig.) sense of covering (for protection); a lamb (compare «02924»):--lamb.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lamb</OL>'),
(2923, '~yalj', 'from the pl. of (02922)', 'Tla\'iym', 'None', 'tel-aw-eem\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the plural of «02922»; lambs; Telaim, a place in Palestine:--Telaim.', 'Telaim = \"lambs\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in Judah where Saul mustered his forces before attacking Amalek; site unknown</OL>'),
(2924, 'hlj', 'by variation for (02922)', 'taleh', 'TWOT - 806a', 'taw-leh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'by variation for «02922»; a lamb:--lamb.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lamb</OL>'),
(2925, 'hltlj', 'from (02904)', 'taltelah', 'TWOT - 797a', 'tal-tay-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02904»; overthrow or rejection:--captivity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a hurling, captivity</OL>'),
(2926, 'llj', 'a primitive root', 'talal', 'TWOT - 808', 'taw-lal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to strew over, i.e. (by implication) to cover in or plate (with beams):--cover.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to cover with a roof, cover over, roof</OL>'),
(2927, 'llj', 'corresponding to (02926)', 'tlal', 'TWOT - 2756', 'tel-al\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02926»; to cover with shade:--have a shadow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Aphel) to seek shade, have shade</OL>'),
(2928, '~lj', 'from an unused root meaning to break up or treat violently', 'Telem', 'None', 'teh\'-lem', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to break up or treat violently; oppression; Telem, the name of a place in Idumaea, also of a temple doorkeeper:--Telem.', 'Telem = \"oppression\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a gatekeeper among the returning exiles in the time of Ezra n pr loc<LI>one of the cities in the extreme south of Judah in the Negeb</OL>'),
(2929, '!wmlj', 'from the same as (02728)', 'Talmown', 'None', 'tal-mone\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «02728»; oppressive; Talmon, a temple doorkeeper:--Talmon.', 'Talmon = \"oppressor\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the head of a family of doorkeepers in the temple; some of his descendants returned from exile with Zerubbabel and were employed in their hereditary office in the days of Nehemiah and Ezra<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>possibly two other doorkeepers in the time of Nehemiah</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(2930, 'amj', 'a primitive root', 'tame\'', 'TWOT - 809', 'taw-may\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be foul, especially in a ceremial or moral sense (contaminated):--defile (self), pollute (self), be (make, make self, pronounce) unclean, × utterly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be unclean, become unclean, become impure<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be or become unclean<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sexually<LI>religiously<LI>ceremonially</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to defile oneself, be defiled 1b</OL><LI>sexually 1b<LI>by idolatry 1b<LI>ceremonially<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to be regarded as unclean</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to defile 1c</OL><LI>sexually 1c<LI>religiously 1c<LI>ceremonially<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to pronounce unclean, declare unclean (ceremonially)<LI>to profane (God\'s name)</OL><LI>(Pual) to be defiled<LI>(Hithpael) to be unclean<LI>(Hothpael) to be defiled</OL></OL>'),
(2931, 'amj', 'from (02930)', 'tame\'', 'TWOT - 809a', 'taw-may\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02930»; foul in a relig. sense:--defiled, + infamous, polluted(-tion), unclean.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unclean, impure<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>ethically and religiously<LI>ritually<LI>of places</OL></OL>'),
(2932, 'hamj', 'from (02930)', 'tum\'ah', 'TWOT - 809b', 'toom-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02930»; religious impurity:--filthiness, unclean(-ness).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>uncleanness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>sexual<LI>of filthy mass<LI>ethical and religious<LI>ritual<LI>local (of nations)</OL></OL>'),
(2933, 'hmj', 'a collateral form of (02930)', 'tamah', 'TWOT - 810', 'taw-maw\'', 'Verb', 'a collateral form of «02930»; to be impure in a religious sense:--be defiled, be reputed vile.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Niphal) to be stopped up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be regarded as unclean (metaplastic)</OL></OL>'),
(2934, '!mj', 'a primitive root', 'taman', 'TWOT - 811', 'taw-man\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to hide (by covering over):--hide, lay privily, in secret.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hide, conceal, bury<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hide<LI>hiding, concealing, secretly laying (participle)<LI>darkness (participle)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to hide oneself<LI>(Hiphil) to hide</OL></OL>'),
(2935, 'anj', 'from an unused root probably meaning to weave', 'tene\'', 'TWOT - 812a', 'teh\'-neh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to weave; a basket (of interlaced osiers):--basket.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>basket</OL>'),
(2936, '@nj', 'a primitive root', 'tanaph', 'TWOT - 813', 'taw-naf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to soil:--defile.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to defile, soil</OL>'),
(2937, 'h[j', 'a primitive root', 'ta`ah', 'TWOT - 814', 'taw-aw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to wander; ,causatively to lead astray:--seduce.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wander, stray, wander astray, err<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to seduce<LI>to cause to go astray</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2938, '~[j', 'a primitive root', 'ta`am', 'TWOT - 815', 'taw-am\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to taste; figuratively, to perceive:--X  but, perceive, taste.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to taste, perceive, eat<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to taste</OL></OL>'),
(2939, '~[j', 'corresponding to (02938)', 't`am', 'TWOT - 2757', 'teh-am\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02938»; to taste; causatively to feed:--make to eat, feed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to feed, cause to eat</OL>'),
(2940, '~[j', 'from (02938)', 'ta`am', 'TWOT - 815a', 'tah\'-am', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02938»; properly, a taste, i.e. (figuratively) perception; by implication, intelligence; transitively, a mandate:-- advice, behaviour, decree, discretion, judgment, reason, taste, understanding.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>taste, judgment<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>taste<LI>judgment (fig.)<LI>decision, decree</OL></OL>'),
(2941, '~[j', 'from (02939)', 'ta`am', 'TWOT - 2757a', 'tah\'-am', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «02939»; properly, a taste, i.e. (as in «02940») a judicial sentence:--account, × to be commanded, commandment, matter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>taste, judgment, command<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>taste<LI>judgment, discretion<LI>report<LI>command</OL></OL>'),
(2942, '~[j', 'from (02939), and equivalent to (02941)', 't`em', 'TWOT - 2757a', 'teh-ame\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «02939», and equivalent to «02941»; properly, flavor; figuratively, judgment (both subjective and objective); hence, account (both subj. and obj.):--+ chancellor, + command, commandment, decree, + regard, taste, wisdom.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>decree, taste, judgment, command<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>taste<LI>judgment, discretion<LI>report<LI>command</OL></OL>'),
(2943, '![j', 'a primitive root', 'ta`an', 'TWOT - 816', 'taw-an\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to load a beast:--lade.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to load</OL>'),
(2944, '![j', 'a primitive root', 'ta`an', 'TWOT - 817', 'taw-an\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to stab:--thrust through.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Pual) to pierce</OL>'),
(2945, '@j', 'from (02952) (perhaps referring to the tripping gait of children)', 'taph', 'TWOT - 821a', 'taf', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02952» (perhaps referring to the tripping gait of children); a family (mostly used collectively in the singular):--(little) children (ones), families.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>children, little children, little ones</OL>'),
(2946, 'xpj', 'a primitive root', 'taphach', 'TWOT - 821', 'taw-fakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to flatten out or extend (as a tent); figuratively, to nurse a child (as promotive of growth); or perhaps a denom. from «02947», from dandling on the palms:--span, swaddle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to extend, spread, trip, take quick little steps<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to spread out<LI>to carry on the palms, dandle<LI>to rear children</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2947, 'xpj', 'from (02946)', 'tephach', 'TWOT - 818b', 'tay\'-fakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02946»; a spread of the hand, i.e. a palm- breadth (not \"span\" of the fingers); architecturally, a corbel (as a supporting palm):--coping, hand-breadth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>span, width of the hand, hand breadth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a unit of measurement, measurement of length</OL><LI>coping (an architectural term)</OL>'),
(2948, 'xpj', 'from (02946) (the same as (02947))', 'tophach', 'TWOT - 818c', 'to\'-fakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02946» (the same as «02947»):--hand-breadth (broad).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>span, hand breadth</OL>'),
(2949, 'xppj', 'from (02946)', 'tippuch', 'TWOT - 818a', 'tip-pookh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02946»; nursing:--span long.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>tender care, dandling</OL>'),
(2950, 'lpj', 'a primitive root', 'taphal', 'TWOT - 819', 'taw-fal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to stick on as a patch; figuratively, to impute falsely:--forge(-r), sew up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to smear, plaster over, stick, glue</OL>'),
(2951, 'ropj', 'of foreign derivation', 'tiphcar', 'TWOT - 820', 'tif-sar\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of foreign derivation; a military governor:--captain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>scribe, official, marshal</OL>'),
(2952, '@pj', 'a primitive root', 'taphaph', 'TWOT - 821', 'taw-faf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; apparently to trip (with short steps) coquettishly:--mince.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to skip, trip, take quick little steps</OL>'),
(2953, 'rpj', 'from a root corresponding to (06852), and meaning the same as (06856)', 'tphar', 'TWOT - 2758', 'tef-ar\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «06852», and meaning the same as «06856»; a finger-nail; also a hoof or claw:--nail.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fingernail, nail, claw</OL>'),
(2954, 'Xpj', 'a primitive root', 'taphash', 'TWOT - 822', 'taw-fash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, apparently to be thick; figuratively, to be stupid:--be fat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be gross, be insensitive, be fat</OL>'),
(2955, 'tpj', 'probably from (05197)', 'Taphath', 'None', 'taw-fath\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'probably from «05197»; a dropping (of ointment); Taphath, an Israelitess:--Taphath.', 'Taphath = \"ornament\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the daughter of Solomon who was married to Ben-Abinadab</OL>'),
(2956, 'drj', 'a primitive root', 'tarad', 'TWOT - 823', 'taw-rad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to drive on; figuratively, to follow close:--continual.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pursue, chase, be continuous<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) dripping (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(2957, 'drj', 'corresponding to (02956)', 'trad', 'TWOT - 2759', 'ter-ad\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02956»; to expel:--drive.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to drive away, drive from, chase away</OL>'),
(2958, '~wrj', 'a variation of (02962)', 'trowm', 'TWOT - 826', 'ter-ome\'', 'Conjunction', 'a variation of «02962»; not yet:--before.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>before, not yet, before that, ere (of time)</OL>'),
(2959, 'xrj', 'a primitive root', 'tarach', 'TWOT - 825', 'taw-rakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to overburden:--weary.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to burden, toil, be burdened</OL>'),
(2960, 'xrj', 'from (02959)', 'torach', 'TWOT - 825a', 'to\'-rakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02959»; a burden:--cumbrance, trouble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>burden</OL>'),
(2961, 'yrj', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to be moist', 'tariy', 'TWOT - 824a', 'taw-ree\'', 'Adjective Feminine', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to be moist; properly, dripping; hence, fresh (i.e. recently made such):--new, putrefying.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fresh, new</OL>'),
(2962, '~rj', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to interrupt or suspend', 'terem', 'TWOT - 826', 'teh\'-rem', 'Preposition', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to interrupt or suspend; properly, non-occurrence; used adverbially, not yet or before:--before, ere, not yet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>before, not yet, before that</OL>'),
(2963, '@rj', 'a primitive root', 'taraph', 'TWOT - 827', 'taw-raf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pluck off or pull to pieces; causatively to supply with food (as in morsels):--catch, × without doubt, feed, ravin, rend in pieces, × surely, tear (in pieces).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tear, rend, pluck<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to tear, rend<LI>(Niphal) to be torn in pieces<LI>(Poal) to be torn in pieces<LI>(Hiphil) to provide food</OL></OL>'),
(2964, '@rj', 'from (02963)', 'tereph', 'TWOT - 827b', 'teh\'-ref', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02963»; something torn, i.e. a fragment, e.g. a fresh leaf, prey, food:--leaf, meat, prey, spoil.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>prey, food, leaf<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>prey<LI>food<LI>leaf</OL></OL>'),
(2965, '@rj', 'from (02963)', 'taraph', 'TWOT - 827a', 'taw-rawf\'', 'Adjective', 'from «02963»; recently torn off, i.e. fresh:--pluckt off.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>freshly picked, freshly plucked, fresh-plucked</OL>'),
(2966, 'hprj', 'from (collectively) (02964)', 'trephah', 'TWOT - 827c', 'ter-ay-faw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine (collectively) of «02964»; prey, i.e. flocks devoured by animals:--ravin, (that which was) torn (of beasts, in pieces).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that which is torn, animal torn (by beasts)</OL>'),
(2967, 'ylprj', 'from a name of foreign derivation', 'Tarplay', 'None', 'tar-pel-ah\'-ee', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a name of foreign derivation; a Tarpelite (collectively) or inhabitants of Tarpel, a place in Assyria:--Tarpelites.', 'Tarpelites = \"they of the fallen (or wondrous) mountain\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the group of Assyrian colonists who were planted in the cities of Samaria after the captivity of the northern kingdom of Israel; identity uncertain</OL>'),
(2968, 'bay', 'a primitive root', 'ya\'ab', 'TWOT - 828', 'yaw-ab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to desire:--long.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to long, long for, desire</OL>'),
(2969, 'hay', 'a primitive root', 'ya\'ah', 'TWOT - 829', 'yaw-aw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be suitable:--appertain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to pertain to, befit, be befitting</OL>'),
(2970, 'hynzay', 'from (0238) and (03050)', 'Ya\'azanyah', 'None', 'yah-az-an-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Ya.azanyahuw {yah-az-an-yaw\'-hoo}; from «0238» and «03050»; heard of Jah; Jaazanjah, the name of four Israelites:-- Jaazaniah. Compare «03153».', 'Jaazaniah = \"Jehovah hears\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Judean, son of the Maachathite, a captain of the Judean forces who visited Gedaliah at Mizpah after Gedaliah had been appointed governor of Judah by Nebuchadnezzar</OL>'),
(2971, 'ryay', 'from (0215)', 'Ya\'iyr', 'None', 'yaw-ere\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «0215»; enlightener; Jair, the name of four Israelites:--Jair.', 'Jair = \"he enlightens\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Manasseh who conquered many towns during the time of the conquest<LI>the Gileadite, a judge of Israel for 22 years during the time of the judges; father of 30 sons<LI>a Benjamite, son of Kish, and father of Mordecai<LI>father of Elhanan, one of David\'s mighty warriors</OL>'),
(2972, 'yray', 'from (02971)', 'Ya\'iriy', 'None', 'yaw-ee-ree\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'patronymically from «02971»; a Jairite or descendant of Jair:--Jairite.', 'Jairite = \"descendant of Jair\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Jair<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>Ira the Jairite was a priest to David</OL></OL>'),
(2973, 'lay', 'a primitive root', 'ya\'al', 'TWOT - 830', 'yaw-al\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to be slack, i.e. (figuratively) to be foolish:--dote, be (become, do) foolish(-ly).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be foolish, become fools, act foolishly, show wicked folly<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to show wicked folly<LI>to become fools</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2974, 'lay', 'a primitive root [probably rather the same as (02973) through the idea of mental weakness]', 'ya\'al', 'TWOT - 831', 'yaw-al\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (probably rather the same as «02973» through the idea of mental weakness); properly, to yield, especially assent; hence (pos.) to undertake as an act of volition:--assay, begin, be content, please, take upon, ×  willingly, would.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to begin, make a beginning, show willingness, undertake to do, be pleased, be determined<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to agree to, show willingness, acquiesce, accept an invitation, be willing<LI>to undertake<LI>to resolve, be pleased, be determined</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2975, 'r[y', 'of Egyptian origin', 'y`or', 'TWOT - 832', 'yeh-ore\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Egyptian origin; a channel, e.g. a fosse, canal, shaft; specifically the Nile, as the one river of Egypt, including its collateral trenches; also the Tigris, as the main river of Assyria:--brook, flood, river, stream.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>river, stream, canal, Nile, Nile-canal<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>stream, river (Nile)<LI>Nile-arms, Nile-canals<LI>watercourses<LI>shafts (mining)<LI>river (in general)</OL></OL>'),
(2976, 'Xay', 'a primitive root', 'ya\'ash', 'TWOT - 833', 'yaw-ash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to desist, i.e. (figuratively) to despond:--(cause to) despair, one that is desperate, be no hope.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to despair<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be despaired, be desperate<LI>(Piel) to cause to despair interj</OL><LI>it is hopeless!</OL>'),
(2977, 'hyXay', 'from the same root as (0803) and (03050)', 'Yo\'shiyah', 'None', 'yo-shee-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or {yo-she-yaw\'-hoo}; from the same root as «0803» and «03050»; founded of Jah; Joshijah, the name of two Israelites:-- Josiah.', 'Josiah = \"whom Jehovah heals\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Amon by Jedidah who succeeded his father to the throne of Judah and reigned for 31 years; his reign is noteworthy for the great revivals back to the worship of Jehovah which he led<LI>a returned exile and son of Zephaniah at whose house took place the solemn and symbolical crowning of Joshua the high priest in the time of Zechariah the prophet</OL>'),
(2978, '!wtay', 'from (0857)', 'y\'ithown', 'TWOT - 188a', 'yeh-ee-thone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «0857»; an entry:--entrance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>entrance</OL>'),
(2979, 'yrtay', 'from the same as (0871)', 'y\'athray', 'None', 'yeh-aw-ther-ah\'ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «0871»; stepping; Jeatherai, an Israelite:--Jeaterai.', 'Jeaterai = \"whom Jehovah leads\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Gershonite Levite, son of Zerah</OL>'),
(2980, 'bby', 'a primitive root', 'yabab', 'TWOT - 834', 'yaw-bab', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to bawl:--cry out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to cry, cry shrilly</OL>'),
(2981, 'lwby', 'from (02986)', 'ybuwl', 'TWOT - 835c', 'yeb-ool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02986»; produce, i.e. a crop or (figuratively) wealth:--fruit, increase.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>produce, fruit, produce (of the soil)</OL>'),
(2982, 'owby', 'from (0947)', 'Ybuwc', 'None', 'yeb-oos\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «0947»; trodden, i.e. threshing-place; Jebus, the aboriginal name of Jerusalem:--Jebus.', 'Jebus = \"threshing place\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an early name for Jerusalem, the city of the Jebusites; also \'Jebusi\'</OL>'),
(2983, 'yowby', 'from (02982)', 'Yebuwciy', 'None', 'yeb-oo-see\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'patrial from «02982»; a Jebusite or inhabitant of Jebus:--Jebusite(-s).', 'Jebusite = \"descendants of Jebus\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of the 3rd son of Canaan who lived in or around the site of Jebus, the early name for Jerusalem</OL>'),
(2984, 'rxby', 'from (0977)', 'Yibchar', 'None', 'yib-khar\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «0977»; choice; Jibchar, an Israelite:--Ibhar.', 'Ibhar = \"Jehovah chooses\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the sons of David, born in Jerusalem</OL>'),
(2985, '!yby', 'from (0995)', 'Yabiyn', 'None', 'yaw-bene\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «0995»; intelligent; Jabin, the name of two Canaanitish kings:--Jabin.', 'Jabin = \"whom God observes\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a king of Hazor who organised a confederacy of the northern princes against Joshua; confederacy routed by the waters of Merom<LI>another king of Hazor whose general, Sisera, was defeated by Barak</OL>'),
(2986, 'lby', 'a primitive root', 'yabal', 'TWOT - 835', 'yaw-bal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to flow; causatively, to bring (especially with pomp):--bring (forth), carry, lead (forth).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bring, lead, carry, conduct, bear along<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bear along, bring<LI>to carry away, lead away<LI>to lead, conduct</OL><LI>(Hophal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be borne along<LI>to be borne (to the grave)<LI>to be brought, be led, be conducted</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2987, 'lby', 'corresponding to (02986)', 'ybal', 'TWOT - 2760', 'yeb-al\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «02986»; to bring:--bring, carry.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Aphel) to bring, carry, bear along</OL>'),
(2988, 'lby', 'from (02986)', 'yabal', 'TWOT - 835a', 'yaw-bawl\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02986»; a stream:--(water-)course, stream.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a stream, watercourse<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>as irrigating</OL></OL>'),
