(3006, 'tXbby', 'a variation of (03004)', 'yabbesheth', 'TWOT - 837c', 'yab-beh\'-sheth', 'Noun Feminine', 'a variation of «03004»; dry ground:--dry land.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dry land</OL>'),
(3007, 'tXbby', 'corresponding to (03006)', 'yabbesheth', 'TWOT - 2761', 'yab-beh\'-sheth', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «03006»; dry land:--earth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the earth (as a planet)<LI>dry land</OL>'),
(3008, 'lagy', 'from (01350)', 'Yig\'al', 'None', 'yig-awl\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01350»; avenger; Jigal, the name of three Israelites:--Igal, Igeal.', 'Igal or Igeal = \"He redeems\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Joseph and a spy from the tribe of Issachar<LI>son of Nathan of Zobah, one of David\'s mighty warriors<LI>a son of Shemaiah and descendant of Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(3009, 'bgy', 'a primitive root', 'yagab', 'TWOT - 838', 'yaw-gab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to dig or plow:--husbandman.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to till, be a husbandman</OL>'),
(3010, 'bgy', 'from (03009)', 'yageb', 'TWOT - 838a', 'yaw-gabe\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03009»; a plowed field:--field.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>field, ploughed field</OL>'),
(3011, 'hhbgy', 'from (01361)', 'Yogbhah', 'None', 'yog-beh-haw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from «01361»; hillock; Jogbehah, a place East of the Jordan:--Jogbehah.', 'Jogbehah = \"lofty\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the cities east of the Jordan which was built and fortified by the tribe of Gad</OL>'),
(3012, 'whyldgy', 'from (01431) and (03050)', 'Yigdalyahuw', 'None', 'yig-dal-yaw\'-hoo', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01431» and «03050»; magnified of Jah; Jigdaljah, an Israelite:--Igdaliah.', 'Igdaliah = \"Jehovah is great\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a prophet or holy man and father of Hanan in the time of Josiah</OL>'),
(3013, 'hgy', 'a primitive root', 'yagah', 'TWOT - 839', 'yaw-gaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to grieve:--afflict, cause grief, grieve, sorrowful, vex.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to afflict, grieve, suffer, cause grief<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) grieved, grieving (participle)<LI>(Piel) to grieve<LI>(Hiphil) to cause grief, cause sorrow</OL></OL>'),
(3014, 'hgy', 'a primitive root [probably rather the same as (03013) through thecommon idea of dissatisfaction]', 'yagah', 'TWOT - 840', 'yaw-gaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (probably rather the same as «03013» through the common idea of dissatisfaction); to push away; -be removed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to repel, thrust away, push away</OL>'),
(3015, '!wgy', 'from (03013)', 'yagown', 'TWOT - 839a', 'yaw-gohn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03013»; affliction:--grief, sorrow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>grief, sorrow, anguish</OL>'),
(3016, 'rwgy', 'from (03025)', 'yagowr', 'TWOT - 843a', 'yaw-gore\'', 'Adjective', 'from «03025»; fearful:--afraid, fearest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) fearful, fearing</OL>'),
(3017, 'rwgy', 'probably from (01481)', 'Yaguwr', 'None', 'yaw-goor\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'probably from «01481»; a lodging; Jagur, a place in Palestine:--Jagur.', 'Jagur = \"he sojourns\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town of Judah, one of those farthest to the south, on the frontier of Edom</OL>'),
(3018, '[ygy', 'from (03021)', 'ygiya`', 'TWOT - 842e', 'yeg-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03021»; toil; hence, a work, produce, property (as the result of labor):--labour, work.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>toil, work<LI>product, produce, acquired property (as a result of work)</OL>'),
(3019, '[ygy', 'from (03021)', 'yagiya`', 'TWOT - 842d', 'yaw-ghee\'-ah', 'Adjective', 'from «03021»; tired:--weary.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>weary, tired</OL>'),
(3020, 'ylgy', 'from (01540)', 'Yogliy', 'None', 'yog-lee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01540»; exiled; Jogli, an Israelite:--Jogli.', 'Jogli = \"he is exiled\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Danite and father of Bukki who was one of the 12 rulers charged with the conquest of Canaan</OL>'),
(3021, '[gy', 'a primitive root', 'yaga`', 'TWOT - 842', 'yaw-gah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to gasp; hence, to be exhausted, to tire, to toil:--faint, (make to) labour, (be) weary.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to toil, labour, grow weary, be weary<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to toil, labour<LI>to grow weary, be weary</OL><LI>(Piel) to weary, make weary, cause to go toilsomely<LI>(Hiphil) to make to toil, make weary, cause to be weary</OL></OL>'),
(3022, '[gy', 'from (03021)', 'yaga`', 'TWOT - 842a', 'yaw-gaw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03021»; earnings (as the product of toil); -that which he laboured for.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>earnings, gain (product of labour)</OL>'),
(3023, '[gy', 'from (03021)', 'yagea`', 'TWOT - 842b', 'yaw-gay\'-ah', 'Adjective', 'from «03021»; tired; hence (transitive) tiresome:--full of labour, weary.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>weary, wearisome</OL>'),
(3024, 'h[gy', 'from (03019)', 'ygi`ah', 'TWOT - 842c', 'yeg-ee-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «03019»; fatigue:--weariness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a wearing, a tiring</OL>'),
(3025, 'rgy', 'a primitive root', 'yagor', 'TWOT - 843', 'yaw-gore\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to fear:--be afraid, fear.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to fear, dread, be afraid</OL>'),
(3026, 'atwdhX rgy', 'from a word derived from an unused root (meaning to gather) and a derivation of a root corresponding to (07717)', 'Ygar', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', '(Aramaic) from a word derived from an unused root (meaning to gather) and a derivation of a root corresponding to «07717»; heap of the testimony; Jegar-Sahadutha, a cairn East of the Jordan:--Jegar-Sahadutha.', 'Jegar-sahadutha = \"witness heap\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the mound of stones raised as witness between Jacob and Laban, called by Jacob in Hebrew \'Galeed\'</OL>'),
(3027, 'dy', 'a primitive word', 'yad', 'TWOT - 844', 'yawd', 'Noun Feminine', 'a primitive word; a hand (the open one (indicating power, means, direction, etc.), in distinction from «03709», the closed one); used (as noun, adverb, etc.) in a great variety of applications, both literally and figuratively, both proximate and remote (as follows):--(+ be) able, × about, + armholes, at, axletree, because of, beside, border, × bounty, + broad, (broken-)handed, × by, charge, coast, + consecrate, + creditor, custody, debt, dominion, × enough, + fellowship, force, × from,  hand(-staves, -y work), × he, himself, × in, labour, + large, ledge, (left-)handed, means, × mine, ministry, near, × of, × order, ordinance, × our, parts, pain, power, × presumptuously, service, side, sore, state, stay, draw with strength, stroke, + swear, terror, × thee, × by them, × themselves, × thine own, × thou, through, × throwing, + thumb, times, × to, × under, × us, × wait on, (way-)side, where, + wide, × with (him, me, you), work, + yield, ×  yourselves.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hand<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>hand (of man)<LI>strength, power (fig.)<LI>side (of land), part, portion (metaph.) (fig.)<LI>(various special, technical senses)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sign, monument<LI>part, fractional part, share<LI>time, repetition<LI>axle-trees, axle<LI>stays, support (for laver)<LI>tenons (in tabernacle)<LI>a phallus, a hand (meaning unsure)<LI>wrists</OL></OL></OL>'),
(3028, 'dy', 'corresponding to (03027)', 'yad', 'TWOT - 2763', 'yad', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «03027»:--hand, power.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hand<LI>power (fig.)</OL>'),
(3029, 'ady', 'corresponding to (03034)', 'yda\'', 'TWOT - 2764', 'yed-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «03034»; to praise:--(give) thank(-s).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Aphel) to praise, give thanks</OL>'),
(3030, 'hldy', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Yidalah', 'None', 'yid-al-aw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'of uncertain derivation; Jidalah, a place in Palestine:--Idalah.', 'Idalah = \"memorial of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Zebulun between Shimron and Bethlehem, site unknown</OL>'),
(3031, 'Xbdy', 'from the same as (01706)', 'Yidbash', 'None', 'yid-bawsh\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «01706»; perhaps honeyed; Jidbash, an Israelite:--Idbash.', 'Idbash = \"stout\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 3 sons of Abi-etam, a descendant of Judah</OL>'),
(3032, 'ddy', 'a primitive root', 'yadad', 'TWOT - 845,846', 'yaw-dad\'', '', 'a primitive root; properly, to handle (compare «03034»), i.e. to throw, e.g. lots:--cast.', 'v<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to throw lots, cast lots n<LI>love, loving-one, friend</OL>'),
(3033, 'twddy', 'from (03039)', 'ydiduwth', 'TWOT - 846c', 'yed-ee-dooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03039»; properly, affection; concretely, a darling object:--dearly beloved.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one dearly loved, beloved one, object of love</OL>'),
(3034, 'hdy', 'a primitive root; used only as denominative from (03027)', 'yadah', 'TWOT - 847', 'yaw-daw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; used only as denominative from «03027»; literally, to use (i.e. hold out) the hand; physically, to throw (a stone, an arrow) at or away; especially to revere or worship (with extended hands); intensively, to bemoan (by wringing the hands):--cast (out), (make) confess(-ion), praise, shoot, (give) thank(-ful, -s, -sgiving).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to throw, shoot, cast<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to shoot (arrows)<LI>(Piel) to cast, cast down, throw down<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give thanks,, laud, praise<LI>to confess, confess (the name of God)</OL><LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to confess (sin)<LI>to give thanks</OL></OL></OL>'),
(3035, 'wddy', 'from (03034)', 'Yiddow', 'None', 'yid-do\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03034»; praised; Jiddo, an Israelite:--Iddo.', 'Iddo = \"timely\" or \"lovely\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Zechariah, ruler of the tribe of Manasseh east of the Jordan in the time of David<LI>a man who took a foreign wife in the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(3036, '!wdy', 'from (03034)', 'Yadown', 'None', 'yaw-done\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03034»; thankful; Jadon, an Israelite:--Jadon.', 'Jadon = \"thankful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Meronothite and one of the builders of the walls of Jerusalem</OL>'),
(3037, '[wddy', 'from (03045)', 'Yadduwa`', 'None', 'yad-doo\'-ah', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03045»; knowing; Jaddua, the name of two Israelites:--Jaddua.', 'Jaddua = \"knowing\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the chiefs of the people who sealed the covenant with Nehemiah<LI>son and successor in the high priesthood of Jonathan, Jeshua, or Johanan; the last of the high priests mentioned in the OT, probably living in the time of Alexander the Great</OL>'),
(3038, '!wtwdy', 'probably from (03034)', 'Yduwthuwn', 'None', 'yed-oo-thoon\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Yduthuwn {yed-oo-thoon\'}; or Ydiythuwn {yed-ee-thoon\'}; probably from «03034»; laudatory; Jeduthun, an Israelite:--Jeduthun.', 'Jeduthun = \"praising\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite of the family of Merari and the chief of one of the 3 choirs of the temple whose descendants also formed one of the perpetual temple choirs; he is named at the beginning of 3 Psalms (39, 62,<LI>either as the composer or the recipient of those Psalms but most likely as the leader of the choir by which those Psalms were to be sung</OL>'),
(3039, 'dydy', 'from the same as (01730)', 'ydiyd', 'TWOT - 846a', 'yed-eed\'', '', 'from the same as «01730»; loved:--amiable,  (well-)beloved, loves.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one beloved, beloved adj<LI>lovely</OL>'),
(3040, 'hdydy', 'from (03039)', 'Ydiydah', 'None', 'yed-ee-daw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'feminine of «03039»; beloved; Jedidah, an Israelitess:--Jedidah.', 'Jedidah = \"beloved\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the wife of king Amon and mother of king Josiah</OL>'),
(3041, 'hydydy', 'from (03039) and (03050)', 'Ydiydyah', 'None', 'yed-ee-deh-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03039» and «03050»; beloved of Jah; Jedidejah, a name of Solomon:--Jedidiah.', 'Jedidiah = \"beloved of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the name given to Solomon through Nathan the prophet</OL>'),
(3042, 'hydy', 'from (03034) and (03050)', 'Ydayah', 'None', 'yed-aw-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03034» and «03050»; praised of Jah; Jedajah, the name of two Israelites:--Jedaiah.', 'Jedaiah = \"praised of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Simeonite, forefather of Ziza<LI>son of Harumaph and one who took part in rebuilding the walls of Jerusalem</OL>'),
(3043, 'la[ydy', 'from (03045) and (0410)', 'Ydiy`a\'el', 'None', 'yed-ee-ah-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03045» and «0410»; knowing God; Jediael, the name of three Israelites:--Jediael.', 'Jediael = \"God makes known\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a chief patriarch of the tribe of Benjamin; maybe the same as \'Ashbel\'<LI>the 2nd son of Meshelemiah and a Korahite gatekeeper<LI>son of Shimri and one of David\'s mighty warriors<LI>one of the chiefs of the thousands of Manasseh who joined David on his march to Ziklag; maybe the same man as 3 above</OL>'),
(3044, '@ldy', 'from (01811)', 'Yidlaph', 'None', 'yid-lawf\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01811»; tearful; Jidlaph, a Mesopotamian:--Jidlaph.', 'Jidlaph = \"weeping\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Nahor</OL>'),
(3045, '[dy', 'a primitive root', 'yada`', 'TWOT - 848', 'yaw-dah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to know (properly, to ascertain by seeing); used in a great variety of senses, figuratively, literally, euphemistically and inferentially (including observation, care, recognition; and causatively, instruction, designation, punishment, etc.) (as follow):--acknowledge, acquaintance(-ted with), advise, answer, appoint, assuredly, be aware, (un-)awares, can(-not), certainly, comprehend, consider, ×  could they, cunning, declare, be diligent, (can, cause to) discern, discover, endued with, familiar friend, famous, feel, can have, be (ig-)norant, instruct, kinsfolk, kinsman, (cause to let, make) know, (come to give, have, take) knowledge, have (knowledge), (be, make, make to be, make self) known, + be learned, + lie by man, mark, perceive, privy to, ×  prognosticator, regard, have respect, skilful, shew, can (man of) skill, be sure, of a surety, teach, (can) tell, understand, have (understanding), × will be, wist, wit, wot.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to know<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to know 1a</OL><LI>to know, learn to know 1a<LI>to perceive 1a<LI>to perceive and see, find out and discern 1a<LI>to discriminate, distinguish 1a<LI>to know by experience 1a<LI>to recognise, admit, acknowledge, confess 1a<LI>to consider<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to know, be acquainted with<LI>to know (a person carnally)<LI>to know how, be skilful in<LI>to have knowledge, be wise</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be made known, be or become known, be revealed<LI>to make oneself known<LI>to be perceived<LI>to be instructed</OL><LI>(Piel) to cause to know<LI>(Poal) to cause to know<LI>(Pual)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be known<LI>known, one known, acquaintance (participle)</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to make known, declare<LI>(Hophal) to be made known<LI>(Hithpael) to make oneself known, reveal oneself</OL></OL>'),
(3046, '[dy', 'corresponding to (03045)', 'yda`', 'TWOT - 2765', 'yed-ah\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «03045»:--certify, know, make known, teach.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to know<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to know<LI>(Aphel) to let someone know, communicate, inform, cause to know</OL></OL>'),
(3047, '[dy', 'from (03045)', 'Yada`', 'None', 'yaw-daw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03045»; knowing; Jada, an Israelite:--Jada.', 'Jada = \"He knows\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Judahite, son of Onam and brother of Shammai, in the genealogy of the sons of Jerahmeel by his wife Atarah</OL>'),
(3048, 'hy[dky', 'from (03045) and (03050)', 'Ykda`yah', 'None', 'yed-ah-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03045» and «03050»; Jah has known; Jedajah, the name of two Israelites:--Jedaiah.', 'Jedaiah = \"Jehovah has known\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest in Jerusalem<LI>a man who returned with Zerubbabel<LI>a ruler of the priests in the days of Jeshua<LI>a post exilic priest<LI>one honoured by Jehovah, perhaps one of the above</OL>'),
(3049, 'yn[ddy', 'from (03045)', 'yidd`oniy', 'TWOT - 848d', 'yid-deh-o-nee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03045»; properly, a knowing one; specifically, a conjurer; (by impl) a ghost:--wizard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a knower, one who has a familiar spirit<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a familiar spirit, soothsayer, necromancer (meton)</OL></OL>'),
(3050, 'hhy', 'contraction for (03068), and meaning the same', 'Yahh', 'TWOT - 484b', 'yaw', 'Proper Name', 'contraction for «03068», and meaning the same; Jah, the sacred name:--Jah, the Lord, most vehement. Compare names in \"-iah,\" \"- jah.\"', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Jah (Jehovah in the shortened form)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the proper name of the one true God<LI>used in many compounds<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>names beginning with the letters \'Je\'<LI>names ending with \'iah\' or \'jah\'</OL></OL></OL>'),
(3051, 'bhy', 'a primitive root', 'yahab', 'TWOT - 849', 'yaw-hab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to give (whether literal or figurative); generally, to put; imperatively (reflexive) come:--ascribe, bring, come on, give, go, set, take.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give, provide, ascribe, come<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give<LI>to set, place<LI>to provide (with reflexive)<LI>to ascribe (glory)<LI>to grant, permit, come now</OL></OL></OL>'),
(3052, 'bhy', 'corresponding to (03051)', 'yhab', 'TWOT - 2766', 'yeh-hab\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «03051»; -deliver, give, lay, + prolong, pay, yield.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give, provide<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give<LI>to place, lay (foundations)</OL><LI>(Hithp\'al)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be given<LI>to be paid</OL></OL></OL>'),
(3053, 'bhy', 'from (03051)', 'yhab', 'TWOT - 849a', 'ye-hawb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03051»; properly, what is given (by Providence), i.e. a lot:--burden.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>burden, lot (that which is given)</OL>'),
(3054, 'dhy', 'denominative from a form corresponding to (03061)', 'yahad', 'TWOT - 850', 'yaw-had\'', 'Verb', 'denominative from a form corresponding to «03061»; to Judaize, i.e. become Jewish:--become Jews.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hithpael) to become a Jew (in fact or in fraud), become Judaised</OL>'),
(3055, 'dhy', 'a briefer form of one corresponding to (03061)', 'Yhud', 'None', 'yeh-hood\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'a briefer form of one corresponding to «03061»; Jehud, a place in Palestine:--Jehud.', 'Jehud = \"beauty\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Dan, located between Baalath and Bene-berak and 8 miles east of Joppa</OL>'),
(3056, 'ydhy', 'perhaps from a form corresponding to (03061)', 'Yehday', 'None', 'yeh-dah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'perhaps from a form corresponding to «03061»; Judaistic; Jehdai, an Israelite:--Jehdai.', 'Jahdai \"whom he will place\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the family of Caleb</OL>'),
(3057, 'hydhy', 'from (03064)', 'Yhudiyah', 'None', 'yeh-hoo-dee-yaw\'', '', 'feminine of «03064»; Jehudijah, a Jewess:  -Jehudijah.', 'adj f<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the Jewess or n pr f (CLBL) Jehudijah = \"Jewess\"<LI>a Calebite, the wife of one named Ezra</OL>'),
(3058, 'awhy', 'from (03068) and (01931)', 'Yehuw\'', 'None', 'yay-hoo\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «01931»; Jehovah (is) He; Jehu, the name of five Israelites:--Jehu.', 'Jehu = \"Jehovah is He\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the king of the northern kingdom Israel who overthrew the dynasty of Omri<LI>son of Hanani and an Israelite prophet in the time of Baasha and Jehoshaphat<LI>the Antothite, a Benjamite, one of David\'s mighty warriors<LI>a descendant of Judah of the house of Hezron<LI>son of Josibiah and a chief of the tribe of Simeon</OL>'),
(3059, 'zxawhy', 'from (03068) and (0270)', 'Yhow\'achaz', 'None', 'yeh-ho-aw-khawz\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «0270»; Jehovah-seized; Jehoachaz, the name of three Israelites:--Jehoahaz. Compare «03099».', 'Jehoahaz = \"Jehovah has seized\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a king of Judah and son of Josiah<LI>a king of the northern kingdom of Israel and son of Jehu<LI>a king of Judah and son of Jehoram (Ahaziah)</OL>'),
(3060, 'Xawhy', 'from (03068) and (perhaps) (0784)', 'Yhow\'ash', 'None', 'yeh-ho-awsh\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and (perhaps) «0784»; Jehovah-fired; Jehoash, the name of two Israelite kings:--Jehoash. Compare «03101».', 'Jehoash = \"given by the Lord\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of king Ahaziah and the 8th king of Judah<LI>son of king Jehoahaz and the 12th king of the northern kingdom of Israel</OL>'),
(3061, 'dwhy', 'contracted from a form corresponding to (03063)', 'Yhuwd', 'None', 'yeh-hood\'', 'Proper Name', '(Aramaic) contracted from a form corresponding to «03063»; properly, Judah, hence, Judaea:--Jewry, Judah, Judea.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Judah - the territory of the tribe of Judah</OL>'),
(3062, 'yadwhy', 'patrial from (03061)', 'Yhuwda\'iy', 'None', 'yeh-hoo-daw-ee\'', 'Proper Name', '(Aramaic) patrial from «03061»; a Jehudaite (or Judaite), i.e. Jew:--Jew.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Jew</OL>'),
(3063, 'hdwhy', 'from (03034)', 'Yhuwdah', 'TWOT - 850c', 'yeh-hoo-daw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03034»; celebrated; Jehudah (or Judah), the name of five Israelites; also of the tribe descended from the first, and of its territory:--Judah.', 'Judah = \"praised\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of Jacob by Leah<LI>the tribe descended from Judah the son of Jacob<LI>the territory occupied by the tribe of Judah<LI>the kingdom comprised of the tribes of Judah and Benjamin which occupied the southern part of Canaan after the nation split upon the death of Solomon<LI>a Levite in Ezra\'s time<LI>an overseer of Jerusalem in the time of Nehemiah<LI>a Levite musician in the time of Nehemiah<LI>a priest in the time of Nehemiah</OL>'),
(3064, 'ydwhy', 'patronymically from (03063)', 'Yhuwdiy', 'TWOT - 850a', 'yeh-hoo-dee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'patronymically from «03063»; a Jehudite (i.e. Judaite or Jew), or descendant of Jehudah (i.e. Judah):--Jew.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Jew</OL>'),
(3065, 'ydwhy', 'the same as (03064)', 'Yhuwdiy', 'None', 'yeh-hoo-dee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «03064»; Jehudi, an Israelite:--Jehudi.', 'Jehudi = \"Jew\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Nethaniah and servant of king Jehoiakim</OL>'),
(3066, 'tydwhy', 'from (03064)', 'Yhuwdiyth', 'TWOT - 850b', 'yeh-hoo-deeth\'', 'Adjective Feminine', 'feminine of «03064»; the Jewish (used adverbially) language:--in the Jews\' language.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in the Jewish language, in Hebrew</OL>'),
(3067, 'tydwhy', 'the same as (03066)', 'Yhuwdiyth', 'None', 'yeh-ho-deeth\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'the same as «03066»; Jewess; Jehudith, a Canaanitess:--Judith.', 'Judith = \"Jewess\" or \"praised\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the daughter of Beeri the Hittite and wife of Esau</OL>'),
(3068, 'hwhy', 'from (01961)', 'Yhovah', 'TWOT - 484a', 'yeh-ho-vaw\'', 'Proper Name', 'from «01961»; (the) self-Existent or Eternal; Jehovah, Jewish national name of God:--Jehovah, the Lord. Compare «03050», «03069».', 'Jehovah = \"the existing One\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the proper name of the one true God<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>unpronounced except with the vowel pointings of 0136</OL></OL>'),
(3069, 'hwhy', 'a variation of ((03068)) [used after ((0136)), and pronounced by Jews as (0430), in order to prevent the repetition of the same sound, since they elsewhere pronounce 03068 as 0136]', 'Yhovih', 'None', 'yeh-ho-vee\'', 'Proper Name', 'a variation of «03068» (used after «0136», and pronounced by Jews as «0430», in order to prevent the repetition of the same sound, since they elsewhere pronounce «03068» as «0136»):--God.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Jehovah - used primarily in the combination \'Lord Jehovah\'<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>equal to 03068 but pointed with the vowels of 0430</OL></OL>'),
(3070, 'hry hwhy', 'from (03068) and (07200)', 'Yhovah', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «03068» and «07200»; Jehovah will see (to it); Jehovah-Jireh, a symbolical name for Mount Moriah:--Jehovah- jireh.', 'Jehovah-jireh = \"Jehovah sees\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>symbolic name given by Abraham to Mount Moriah in commemoration of the interposition of the angel of Jehovah who prevented the sacrifice of Isaac and provided a substitute</OL>'),
(3071, 'yoon hwhy', 'from (03068) and (05251) with the prononimal suffix', 'Yhovah', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «03068» and «05251» with the prononimal suffix; Jehovah (is) my banner; Jehovah-Nissi, a symbolical name of an altar in the Desert:--Jehovah-nissi.', 'Jehovah-nissi = \"Jehovah is my banner\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the name given by Moses to the altar which he built in commemoration of the discomfiture of the Amalekites</OL>'),
(3072, 'wnqdc hwhy', 'from (03068) and (06664) with pronominal suffix', 'Yhovah', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «06664» with pronominal suffix; Jehovah (is) our right; Jehovah-Tsidkenu, a symbolical epithet of the Messiah and of Jerusalem:--the Lord our righteousness.', 'Jehovah is our righteousness<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a sacred name symbolically applied to Jerusalem and the Messiah</OL>'),
(3073, '~wlX hwhy', 'from (03068) and (07965)', 'Yhavah', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «03068» and «07965»; Jehovah (is) peace; Jehovah-Shalom, a symbolical name of an altar in Palestine:  -Jehovah-shalom.', 'Jehovah-shalom = \"Jehovah is peace\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the name of a sacred altar built by Gideon in Ophrah</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(3074, 'hmmX hwhy', 'from (03068) and (08033) with directive enclitic', 'Yhovah', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «03068» and «08033» with directive enclitic; Jehovah (is) thither; Jehovah-Shammah, a symbolic title of Jerusalem:--Jehovah-shammah.', 'Jehovah-shammah = \"Jehovah is there\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a symbolic name for Jerusalem</OL>'),
(3075, 'dbzwhy', 'from (03068) and (02064)', 'Yhowzabad', 'None', 'yeh-ho-zaw-bawd\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «02064»; Jehovah-endowed; Jehozabad, the name of three Israelites:--Jehozabad. Compare «03107».', 'Jehozabad = \"Jehovah has endowed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Shomer, a Moabitish woman, who murdered Joash, king of Judah<LI>a Benjamite, captain of 180,000 armed men, in the days of Jehoshaphat<LI>a Korhite Levite, 2nd son of Obededom, and one of the porters of the temple and of the storehouse there in the time of David</OL>'),
(3076, '!nxwhy', 'from (03068) and (02603)', 'Yhowchanan', 'None', 'yeh-ho-khaw-nawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «02603»; Jehovah-favored; Jehochanan, the name of eight Israelites:--Jehohanan, Johanan. Compare «03110».', 'Jehohanan = \"Jehovah has graced\"<OL TYPE=\"5\"><LI>a Korhite Levite and one of the doorkeepers to the tabernacle in the time of David<LI>a captain of Judah under king Jehoshaphat</OL>'),
(3077, '[dywhy', 'from (03068) and (03045)', 'Yhowyada`', 'None', 'yeh-ho-yaw-daw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «03045»; Jehovah-known; Jehojada, the name of three Israelites:--Jehoiada. Compare «03111».', 'Jehoiada = \"Jehovah knows\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Benaiah, David\'s mighty warrior<LI>leader of the priests who joined David at Hebron<LI>high priest at the time of Athaliah\'s usurpation of the throne of Judah; hid Joash, the king\'s son, for six years and eventually replaced him on the throne of Judah<LI>second priest, or sagan, to Seraiah the high priest</OL>'),
(3078, '!ykywhy', 'from (03068) and (03559)', 'Yhowyakiyn', 'None', 'yeh-ho-yaw-keen\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «03559»; Jehovah will establish; Jehojakin, a Jewish king:--Jehoiachin. Compare «03112».', 'Jehoiachin = \"Jehovah establishes\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>king of Judah, son of Jehoiakim, and the next to last king of Judah before the Babylonian captivity; kingship lasted for 3 months and 10 days before he surrendered to Nebuchadnezzar who took him to Babylon and imprisoned him for 36 years when he was finally released</OL>'),
(3079, '~yqywhy', 'from (03068) abbreviated and (06965), cf. (3113)', 'Yhowyaqiym', 'None', 'yeh-ho-yaw-keem\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» abbreviated and «06965»; Jehovah will raise; Jehojakim, a Jewish king:--Jehoiakim. Compare «03113».', 'Jehoiakim = \"Jehovah raises up\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Josiah and the third from the last king of Judah; subject vassel of Nebuchadnezzar who reigned for 11 years before he died a violent death either in combat or by the hands of his own subjects</OL>'),
(3080, 'byrywhy', 'from (03068) and (07378)', 'Yhowyariyb', 'None', 'yeh-ho-yaw-reeb\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «07378»; Jehovah will contend; Jehojarib, the name of two Israelites:--Jehoiarib. Compare «03114».', 'Jehoiarib = \"Jehovah contends\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>A priest in Jerusalem<LI>the head of the 1st of the 24 courses of priests in David\'s time</OL>'),
(3081, 'lkwhy', 'from (03201)', 'Yhuwkal', 'None', 'yeh-hoo-kal\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03201»; potent; Jehukal, an Israelite:  -Jehucal. Compare «03116».', 'Jehucal = \"Jehovah is able\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Shelemiah and a servant of king Zedekiah whom he sent to Jeremiah to entreat his prayers and advice</OL>'),
(3082, 'bdnwhy', 'from (03068) and (05068)', 'Yhownadab', 'None', 'yeh-ho-naw-dawb\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «05068»; Jehovah-largessed; Jehonadab, the name of an Israelite and of an Arab:--Jehonadab, Jonadab. Compare «03122».', 'Jehonadab = \"Jehovah is willing\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Rechab, chief of the Rechabites, in the time of Jehu and Ahab<LI>a nephew of David</OL>'),
(3083, '!tnwhy', 'from (03068) and (05414)', 'Yhownathan', 'None', 'yeh-ho-naw-thawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «05414»; Jehovah-given; Jehonathan, the name of four Israelites:--Jonathan. Compare «03129».', 'Jonathan or Jehonathan = \"Jehovah has given\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of king Saul and a friend of David<LI>a son of the high priest Abiathar and the last descendant of Eli of whom we hear<LI>a nephew of David who like David slew a giant of Gath<LI>an uncle of David<LI>one of David\'s mighty warriors<LI>one of David\'s treasurers<LI>a scribe in the time of Jeremiah<LI>a Levite and father of Zechariah, a priest who blew the trumpet at the dedication of the wall<LI>a son or descendant of Gershom, the son of Moses, and a priest to the tribe of Dan<LI>a son of Kareah and a brother of Johanan; a Judaite captain after the fall of Jerusalem<LI>another Judaite father of Peleth<LI>father of Ebed in the time of Ezra<LI>son of Asahel in the time of Ezra<LI>a priest of the family of Melicu in the time of Nehemiah<LI>son of Joiada and his successor to the high priesthood in the time of Nehemiah</OL>'),
(3084, '@owhy', 'a fuller form of (03130)', 'Yhowceph', 'None', 'yeh-ho-safe\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'a fuller form of «03130»; Jehoseph (i.e. Joseph), a son of Jacob:--Joseph.', 'Joseph = \"Jehovah has added\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the eldest son of Jacob by Rachel</OL>'),
(3085, 'hdd[why', 'from (03068) and (05710)', 'Yhow`addah', 'None', 'yeh-ho-ad-daw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «05710»; Jehovah-adorned; Jehoaddah, an Israelite:--Jehoada.', 'Jehoadah = \"Jehovah has adorned\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Saul through Jonathan</OL>'),
(3086, '!ydd[why', 'from (03068) and (05727)', 'Yhow`addiyn', 'None', 'yeh-ho-ad-deen\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'or Yhowaddan {yeh-ho-ad-dawn\'}; from «03068» and «05727»; Jehovah-pleased; Jehoaddin or Jehoaddan, an Israelitess:--Jehoaddan.', 'Jehoaddan = \"Jehovah delights\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wife of king Joash and mother of king Amaziah of Judah</OL>'),
(3087, 'qdcwhy', 'from (03068) and (06663)', 'Yhowtsadaq', 'None', 'yeh-ho-tsaw-dawk\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «06663»; Jehovah-righted; Jehotsadak, an Israelite:--Jehozadek, Josedech. Compare «03136».', 'Jehozadak or Josedech = \"Jehovah is righteous\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>grandson of the high priest Hilkiah; son of the high priest Seraiah; and father of the high priest Joshua; he never attained the office of high priest himself because he was carried captive to Babylon by Nebuchadnezzar</OL>'),
(3088, '~rwhy', 'from (03068) and (07311)', 'Yhowram', 'None', 'yeh-ho-rawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «07311»; Jehovah-raised; Jehoram, the name of a Syrian and of three Israelites:--Jehoram, Joram. Compare «03141».', 'Jehoram or Joram = \"Jehovah is exalted\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of king Jehoshaphat of Judah and himself king of Judah for 8 years; his wife was the wicked Athaliah who was probably the instigator for his returning the nation of Judah to the worship of Baal<LI>son of king Ahab of the northern kingdom of Israel and king of Israel himself for 12 years; he was murdered by Jehu on the plot of land for which his father had murdered Naboth thus fulfilling the prophecy of Elijah to the very letter<LI>a priest in the reign of Jehoshaphat</OL>'),
(3089, '[bXwhy', 'from (03068) and (07650)', 'Yhowsheba`', 'None', 'yeh-ho-sheh\'-bah', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'from «03068» and «07650»; Jehovah-sworn; Jehosheba, an Israelitess:--Jehosheba. Compare «03090».', 'Jehosheba = \"Jehovah has sworn\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>daughter of king Joram of Judah and wife of the high priest Jehoiada<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>alternate spelling \'Jehoshabeath\' - 03090</OL></OL>'),
(3090, 't[bXwhy', 'a form of (03089)', 'Yhowshab`ath', 'None', 'yeh-ho-shab-ath\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'a form of «03089»; Jehoshabath, an Israelitess:--Jehoshabeath.', 'Jehoshabeath = \"Jehovah is an oath\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>daughter of king Joram of Judah and wife of the high priest Jehoiada<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>alternate spelling \'Jehosheba - 03089</OL></OL>'),
(3091, '[wXwhy', 'from (03068) and (03467)', 'Yhowshuwa`', 'None', 'yeh-ho-shoo\'-ah', '', 'or Yhowshua {yeh-ho-shoo\'-ah}; from «03068» and «03467»; Jehovah-saved; Jehoshua (i.e. Joshua), the Jewish leader:--Jehoshua, Jehoshuah, Joshua. Compare «01954», «03442».', 'Joshua or Jehoshua = \"Jehovah is salvation\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Nun of the tribe of Ephraim and successor to Moses as the leader of the children of Israel; led the conquest of Canaan<LI>a resident of Beth-shemesh on whose land the Ark of the Covenant came to a stop after the Philistines returned it<LI>son of Jehozadak and high priest after the restoration<LI>governor of Jerusalem under king Josiah who gave his name to a gate of the city of Jerusalem</OL>'),
(3092, 'tpXwhy', 'from (03068) and (08199)', 'Yhowshaphat', 'None', 'yeh-ho-shaw-fawt\'', '', 'from «03068» and «08199»; Jehovah-judged; Jehoshaphat, the name of six Israelites; also of a valley near Jerusalem:--Jehoshaphat. Compare «03146».', 'Jehoshaphat = \"Jehovah has judged\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of king Asa and himself king of Judah for 25 years; one of the best, most pious, and prosperous kings of Judah<LI>son of Nimshi and father of king Jehu of the northern kingdom of Israel<LI>son of Ahilud and chronicler under David and Solomon<LI>son of Paruah and one of the 12 commissary officers under Solomon<LI>a priest and trumpeter in the time of David n pr loc<LI>symbolical name of a valley near Jerusalem which is the place of ultimate judgment; maybe the deep ravine which separates Jerusalem from the Mount of Olives through which the Kidron flowed</OL>'),
(3093, 'ryhy', 'probably from the same as (02022)', 'yahiyr', 'TWOT - 851a', 'yaw-here\'', 'Adjective', 'probably from the same as «02022»; elated; hence, arrogant:--haughty, proud.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>proud, arrogant, haughty</OL>'),
(3094, 'lalllhy', 'from (01984) and (0410)', 'Yhallel\'el', 'None', 'yeh-hal-lel-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «01984» and «0410»; praising God; Jehallelel, the name of two Israelites:--Jehalellel, Jehalelel.', 'Jehaleleel or Jehalelel = \"God is praised\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Calebite descendant of Judah<LI>father of Azariah and a Merarite Levite in the time of Hezekiah</OL>'),
(3095, '~lhy', 'from (01986) (in the sense of hardness)', 'yahalom', 'TWOT - 502b', 'yah-hal-ome\'', '', 'from «01986» (in the sense of hardness); a precious stone, probably onyx:--diamond.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a precious stone (known for its hardness)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps the jasper, onyx, or diamond</OL></OL>'),
(3096, '#hy', 'from an unused root meaning to stamp', 'Yahats', 'None', 'yah\'-hats', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Yahtsah {yah\'-tsaw}; or (feminine) Yahtsah  {yah-tsaw\'}; from an unused root meaning to stamp; perhaps threshing-floor; Jahats or Jahtsah, a place East of the Jordan:--Jahaz, Jahazah, Jahzah.', 'Jahaz or Jahazah or Jahzah = \"trodden down\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in Reuben east of the Dead Sea where Israel defeated Sihon king of the Amorites; site uncertain</OL>'),
(3097, 'bawy', 'from (03068) and (1)', 'Yow\'ab', 'None', 'yo-awb\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «01»; Jehovah-fathered; Joab, the name of three Israelites:--Joab.', 'Joab = \"Jehovah is father\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of David\'s sister Zeruiah and general of David\'s army<LI>a Judaite descendant of Kenaz<LI>a post exilic family</OL>'),
(3098, 'xawy', 'from (03068) and (0251)', 'Yow\'ach', 'None', 'yo-awkh\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03068» and «0251»; Jehovah-brothered; Joach, the name of four Israelites:--Joah.', 'Joah = \"Jehovah is brother\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Asaph and chronicler to Hezekiah<LI>a Gershonite son or grandson of Zimmah<LI>a Korhite, 3rd son of Obed-edom and doorkeeper in the time of David<LI>son of Joahaz and chronicler to king Josiah</OL>'),
(3099, 'zxawy', 'a form of (03059)', 'Yow\'achaz', 'None', 'yo-aw-khawz\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'a form of «03059»; Joachaz, the name of two Israelites:--Jehoahaz, Joahaz.', 'Joahaz or Jehoahaz = \"Jehovah has grasped\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the father of Joah, Josiah\'s chronicler</OL>'),
