(3153, 'hynzy', 'probably for (02970)', 'Yzanyah', 'None', 'yez-an-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Yzanyahuw {yez-an-yaw\'-hoo}; probably for «02970»; Jezanjah, an Israelite:--Jezaniah.', 'Jezaniah = \"Jehovah has listened\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Hoshaiah the Maachathite and one of the captains who escaped from Jerusalem during the last siege of the Babylonians; one of the first to return to Gedaliah at Mizpah where he took a prominent part after the assassination of Gedaliah</OL>'),
(3154, '[zy', 'from an unused root mean to ooze', 'yeza`', 'TWOT - 857a', 'yeh\'-zah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root mean to ooze; sweat, i.e. (by implication) a sweating dress:--any thing that causeth sweat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sweat, perspiration</OL>'),
(3155, 'xrzy', 'a variation for (0250)', 'Yizrach', 'None', 'yiz-rawkh\'', 'Adjective', 'a variation for «0250»; a Jizrach (i.e. Ezrachite or Zarchite) or descendant of Zerach:--Izrahite.', 'Izrahite = \"descendant of Zerah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Zerah of Judah</OL>'),
(3156, 'hyxrzy', 'from (02224) and (03050)', 'Yizrachyah', 'None', 'yiz-rakh-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02224» and «03050»; Jah will shine; Jizrachjah, the name of two Israelites:--Izrahiah, Jezrahiah.', 'Izrahiah or Jezrahiah = \"Jehovah will shine\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a chieftain of Issachar<LI>a Levite and leader of the chorus at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem under Nehemiah</OL>'),
(3157, 'la[rzy', 'from (02232) and (0410)', 'Yizr`e\'l', 'None', 'yiz-reh-ale\'', '', 'from «02232» and «0410»; God will sow; Jizreel, the name of two places in Palestine and of two Israelites:--Jezreel.', 'Jezreel = \"God sows\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of the father or founder of Etam of Judah<LI>first son of Hosea the prophet n pr loc<LI>a city in the Nekeb of Judah<LI>a city in Issachar on the northwest spur of Mount Gilboa</OL>'),
(3158, 'yla[rzy', 'patronymically from (03157)', 'Yizr`e\'liy', 'None', 'yiz-reh-ay-lee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from «03157»; a Jizreelite or native of Jizreel:--Jezreelite.', 'Jezreelite = see Jezreel \"sown of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Jezreel</OL>'),
(3159, 'tyla[rzy', 'from (03158)', 'Yizr`e\'liyth', 'None', 'yiz-reh-ay-leeth\'', 'Adjective Feminine', 'feminine of «03158»; a Jezreelitess:--Jezreelitess.', 'Jezreelitess = see Jezreel \"sown of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a female inhabitant of Jezreel<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used only of Ahinoam, a wife of David</OL></OL>'),
(3160, 'hbbxy', 'from (02247)', 'Ychubbah', 'hidden', 'yekh-oob-baw\'', 'Neuter', 'from «02247»; hidden; Jechubbah, an Israelite:--Jehubbah.', 'Jehubbah = \"hidden\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a man of Asher, son of Shomer or Shamer of the house of Beriah</OL>'),
(3161, 'dxy', 'a primitive root', 'yachad', 'TWOT - 858', 'yaw-khad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be (or become) one:--join, unite.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to join, unite, be joined, be united<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be united<LI>(Piel) to unite</OL></OL>'),
(3162, 'dxy', 'from (03161)', 'yachad', 'TWOT - 858b', 'yakh\'-ad', '', 'from «03161»; properly, a unit, i.e. (adverb) unitedly:--alike, at all (once), both, likewise, only, (al-)together, withal.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>union, unitedness adv<LI>together, altogether, all together, alike</OL>'),
(3163, 'wdxy', 'from (03162) with pronominal suffix', 'Yachdow', 'None', 'yakh-doe\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03162» with pronominal suffix; his unity, i.e. (adverb) together; Jachdo, an Israelite:--Jahdo.', 'Jahdo = \"His unity\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Gileadite, son of Buz and father of Jeshishai</OL>'),
(3164, 'laydxy', 'from (03162) and (0410)', 'Yachdiy\'el', 'None', 'yakh-dee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03162» and «0410»; unity of God; Jachdiel, an Israelite:--Jahdiel.', 'Jahdiel = \"my unity is God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a chief of Manasseh on the east of the Jordan</OL>'),
(3165, 'whydxy', 'from (03162) and (03050)', 'Yechdiyahuw', 'None', 'yekh-dee-yaw\'-hoo', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03162» and «03050»; unity of Jah; Jechdijah, the name of two Israelites:--Jehdeiah.', 'Jehdeiah = \"Jehovah is unity\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite in the time of David<LI>a Meronothite, officer of David in charge of the she-asses</OL>'),
(3166, 'layzxy', 'from (02372) and (0410)', 'Yachaziy\'el', 'None', 'yakh-az-ee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02372» and «0410»; beheld of God; Jachaziel, the name of five Israelites:--Jahaziel, Jahziel.', 'Jahaziel = \"beheld of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite warrior who joined David at Ziklag<LI>a priest in the reign of David who helped move the ark<LI>a Kohathite Levite, 3rd son of Hebron<LI>a Levite, son of Zechariah, of the sons of Asaph, in the reign of Jehoshaphat<LI>an ancestor of one of the families who returned from exile with Ezra</OL>'),
(3167, 'hyzxy', 'from (02372) and (03050)', 'Yachzyah', 'None', 'yakh-zeh-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02372» and «03050»; Jah will behold; Jachzejah, an Israelite:--Jahaziah.', 'Jahaziah = \"Jehovah views\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Tikvah, apparently a priest and leader during the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(3168, 'laqzxy', 'from (02388) and (0410)', 'Ychezqe\'l', 'None', 'yekh-ez-kale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02388» and «0410»; God will strengthen; Jechezkel, the name of two Israelites:--Ezekiel, Jehezekel.', 'Ezekiel or Jehezekel = \"God strengthens\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Buzi and a priest and prophet; author of the book by his name; taken captive with Jehoiachin and exiled in Babylon where he prophesied for the next 22 years<LI>a priest in charge of the 20th course in the time of David</OL>'),
(3169, 'hyqzxy', 'from (03388) and (03050)', 'Ychizqiyah', 'None', 'yekh-iz-kee-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Ychizqiyahuw {yekh-iz-kee-yaw\'- hoo}; from «03388» and «03050»; strengthened of Jah; Jechizkijah, the name of five Israelites:--Hezekiah, Jehizkiah. Compare «02396».', 'Hezekiah or Jehizkiah = \"Jehovah has made strong\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of king Ahaz by Abi or Abijah and the 12th king of Judah; his reign was characterised by his godly conduct; reigned for 29 years<LI>head of a family of returning exiles in the time of Nehemiah<LI>an Ephraimite in the time of Ahaz</OL>'),
(3170, 'hrzxy', 'from the same as (02386)', 'Yachzerah', 'None', 'yakh-zay-raw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «02386»; perhaps protection; Jachzerah, an Israelite:--Jahzerah.', 'Jahzerah = \"whom God leads back\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest of the house of Immer</OL>'),
(3171, 'layxy', 'from (02421) and (0410)', 'Ychiy\'el', 'None', 'yekh-ee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or (2 Chron. 29:14) Ychavrel  {yekh-av-ale\'}; from «02421» and «0410»; God will live; Jechiel (or Jechavel), the name of eight Israelites:--Jehiel.', 'Jehiel = \"God lives\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite and one of the chief musicians in the time of David<LI>a Gershonite Levite who had charge of the treasures in the time of David<LI>son of Hachmoni and an officer of David and tutor of David\'s sons<LI>a son of king Jehoshaphat of Judah put to death by his brother Jehoram<LI>Hemanite who took part in the restoration of king Hezekiah<LI>a Levite and overseer in the time of Hezekiah<LI>a ruler of the temple during the reforms of Josiah<LI>father of Obadiah of the sons of Joab in the time of Ezra<LI>father of Shechaniah of the sons of Elam in the time of Ezra<LI>a son of Elam who put away his foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>a priest of the sons of Harim who also had to put away his foreign wife in the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(3172, 'ylayxy', 'patronymically from (03171)', 'Ychiy\'eliy', 'None', 'yekh-ee-ay-lee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'patronymically from «03171»; a Jechielite or descendant of Jechiel:--Jehieli.', 'Jehieli = \"God shall save alive\" or \"swept away of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Gershonite Levite of the family of Laadan</OL>'),
(3173, 'dyxy', 'from (03161)', 'yachiyd', 'TWOT - 858a', 'yaw-kheed\'', '', 'from «03161»; properly, united, i.e. sole; by implication, beloved; also lonely; (feminine) the life (as not to be replaced):--darling, desolate, only (child, son), solitary.', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>only, only one, solitary, one<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>only, unique, one<LI>solitary<LI>(TWOT) only begotten son subst</OL><LI>one</OL>'),
(3174, 'hyxy', 'from (02421) and (03050)', 'Ychiyah', 'None', 'yekh-ee-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02421» and «03050»; Jah will live; Jechijah, an Israelite:--Jehiah.', 'Jehiah = \"Jehovah lives\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>doorkeeper of the ark at the time of its establishment in Jerusalem</OL>'),
(3175, 'lyxy', 'from (03176)', 'yachiyl', 'TWOT - 859a', 'yaw-kheel\'', 'Adjective', 'from «03176»; expectant:--should hope.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>waiting, hoping</OL>'),
(3176, 'lxy', 'a primitive root', 'yachal', 'TWOT - 859', 'yaw-chal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to wait; by implication, to be patient, hope:--(cause to, have, make to) hope, be pained, stay, tarry, trust, wait.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wait, hope, expect<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to wait<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wait, await, tarry<LI>to wait for, hope for</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to wait, tarry, wait for, hope for</OL></OL>'),
(3177, 'lalxy', 'from (03176) and (0410)', 'Yachl\'el', 'None', 'yakh-leh-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03176» and «0410»; expectant of God; Jachleel, an Israelite:--Jahleel.', 'Jahleel = \"God waits\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 3rd of the 3 sons of Zebulun; founder of the family of the Jahleelites</OL>'),
(3178, 'ylalxy', 'patronymically from (03177)', 'Yachl\'eliy', 'None', 'yakh-leh-ay-lee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from «03177»; a Jachleelite or descendant of Jachleel:--Jahleelites.', 'Jahleelites = \"the hope of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Jahleel of the tribe of Zebulun</OL>'),
(3179, '~xy', 'a primitive root', 'yacham', 'TWOT - 860', 'yaw-kham\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; probably to be hot; figuratively, to conceive:--get heat, be hot, conceive, be warm.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be hot, conceive<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be hot, become hot<LI>to mate (of animals)<LI>to be or become hot (fig. of anger)</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to conceive (sexually)<LI>to be in heat (of animals)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(3180, 'rwmxy', 'from (02560)', 'yachmuwr', 'TWOT - 685b', 'yakh-moor\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02560»; a kind of deer (from the color; compare «02543»):--fallow deer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>roebuck<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a kind of deer, reddish in colour<LI>perhaps an extinct animal, exact meaning unknown</OL></OL>'),
(3181, 'ymxy', 'probably from (03179)', 'Yachmay', 'None', 'yakh-mah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «03179»; hot; Jachmai, an Israelite:--Jahmai.', 'Jahmai = \"whom Jehovah guards\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a man of Issachar and one of the heads of the family of Tola</OL>'),
(3182, '@xy', 'from an unused root meaning to take off the shoes', 'yacheph', 'TWOT - 861a', 'yaw-khafe\'', 'Adjective', 'from an unused root meaning to take off the shoes; unsandalled:--barefoot, being unshod.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>barefoot<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>bareness, being unshod (subst)</OL></OL>'),
(3183, 'lacxy', 'from (02673) and (0410)', 'Yachts\'el', 'None', 'yakh-tseh-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02673» and «0410»; God will allot; Jachtseel, an Israelite:--Jahzeel. Compare «03185».', 'Jahzeel = \"God divides\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 1st of the 4 sons of Naphtali and founder of the family of Jahzeelites</OL>'),
(3184, 'ylacxy', 'patronymically from (03183)', 'Yachts\'eliy', 'None', 'yakh-tseh-ay-lee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from «03183»; a Jachtseelite (collectively) or descendants of Jachtseel:--Jahzeelites.', 'Jahzeelites = see Jahzeel \"God divides\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the descendants of Jahzeel, the 1st son of Naphtali</OL>'),
(3185, 'laycxy', 'from (02673) and (0410)', 'Yachtsiy\'el', 'None', 'yakh-tsee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02673» and «0410»; allotted of God; Jachtsiel, an Israelite:--Jahziel. Compare «03183».', 'Jahziel = \"God divides\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 1st of the 4 sons of Naphtali and founder of the family of Jahzeelites</OL>'),
(3186, 'rxy', 'a primitive root', 'yachar', 'TWOT - 68', 'yaw-khar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to delay:--tarry longer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to delay, tarry, defer</OL>'),
(3187, 'Xxy', 'a primitive root', 'yachas', 'TWOT - 862', 'yaw-khas\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to sprout; used only as denominative from «03188»; to enroll by pedigree:--(number after, number throughout the) genealogy (to be reckoned), be reckoned by genealogies.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hithpael) to reckon genealogically, enrol on a genealogy, enrol, be enrolled</OL>'),
(3188, 'Xxy', 'from (03187)', 'yachas', 'TWOT - 862a', 'yakh\'-as', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03187»; a pedigree or family list (as growing spontaneously):--genealogy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>genealogy</OL>'),
(3189, 'txy', 'from (03161)', 'Yachath', 'None', 'yakh\'-ath', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03161»; unity; Jachath, the name of four Israelites:--Jahath.', 'Jahath = \"He will snatch up\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Reaiah and grandson of Shobal of the tribe of Judah<LI>a son of Libni and grandson of Gershom and great grandson of Levi<LI>a Gershonite Levite; the eldest son of Shimei and the grandson of Laadan; founder of the house of Jahath<LI>a Levite and son of Shelomoth<LI>a Merarite Levite in the reign of Josiah</OL>'),
(3190, 'bty', 'a primitive root', 'yatab', 'TWOT - 863', 'yaw-tab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be (causative) make well, literally (sound, beautiful) or figuratively (happy, successful, right):--be accepted, amend, use aright, benefit, be (make) better, seem best, make cheerful, be comely, + be content, diligent(-ly), dress, earnestly, find favour, give, be glad, do (be, make) good((-ness)), be (make) merry, please (+ well), shew more (kindness), skilfully, × very small, surely, make sweet, thoroughly, tire, trim, very, be (can, deal, entreat, go, have) well (said, seen).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be good, be pleasing, be well, be glad<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be glad, be joyful<LI>to be well placed<LI>to be well for, be well with, go well with<LI>to be pleasing, be pleasing to</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make glad, rejoice<LI>to do good to, deal well with<LI>to do well, do thoroughly<LI>to make a thing good or right or beautiful<LI>to do well, do right</OL></OL></OL>'),
(3191, 'bty', 'corresponding to (03190)', 'ytab', 'TWOT - 2768', 'yet-ab\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «03190»:--seem good.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to be good, do good, be pleasing</OL>'),
(3192, 'hbty', 'from (03190)', 'Yotbah', 'None', 'yot-baw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «03190»; pleasantness; Jotbah, a place in Palestine:--Jotbah.', 'Jotbah = \"pleasing\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in Judah, hometown of Meshullemeth, wife of king Manasseh<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>site unknown</OL></OL>'),
(3193, 'htbty', 'from (03192)', 'Yotbathah', 'None', 'yot-baw\'-thaw', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «03192»; Jotbathah, a place in the Desert:--Jotbath, Jotbathah.', 'Jotbath or Jotbathah = \"pleasantness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a stopping place in the wilderness; site unknown</OL>'),
(3194, 'htty', 'from (05186)', 'Yuttah', 'None', 'yoo-taw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Yuwtah {yoo-taw\'}; from «05186»; extended; Juttah (or Jutah), a place in Palestine:--Juttah.', 'Juttah = \"stretched out\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in the mountains of Judah, in the neighbourhood of Maon and Carmel; modern \'Yutta\'</OL>'),
(3195, 'rwty', 'probably from the same as (02905)', 'Ytuwr', 'None', 'yet-oor\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from the same as «02905»; encircled (i.e. inclosed); Jetur, a son of Ishmael:--Jetur.', 'Jetur = \"enclosed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Ishmael whose descendants warred with Israel east of the Jordan<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also called \'Ituraea\'</OL></OL>'),
(3196, '!yy', 'from an unused root meaning to effervesce', 'yayin', 'TWOT - 864', 'yah\'-yin', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to effervesce; wine (as fermented); by implication, intoxication:--banqueting, wine, wine(-bibber).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wine</OL>'),
(3197, '$y', 'by erroneous transcription for (03027)', 'yak', 'TWOT - 844', 'yak', 'Noun Masculine', 'by erroneous transcription for «03027»; a hand or side:-- (way-)side.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hand, (way)side</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(3198, 'xky', 'a primitive root', 'yakach', 'TWOT - 865', 'yaw-kahh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be right (i.e. correct); reciprocal, to argue; causatively, to decide, justify or convict:--appoint, argue, chasten, convince, correct(-ion), daysman, dispute, judge, maintain, plead, reason (together), rebuke, reprove(-r), surely, in any wise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to prove, decide, judge, rebuke, reprove, correct, be right<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to decide, judge<LI>to adjudge, appoint<LI>to show to be right, prove<LI>to convince, convict<LI>to reprove, chide<LI>to correct, rebuke</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be chastened<LI>(Niphal) to reason, reason together<LI>(Hithp) to argue</OL></OL>'),
(3199, '!yky', 'from (03559)', 'Yakiyn', 'None', 'yaw-keen\'', '', 'from «03559»; he (or it) will establish; Jakin, the name of three Israelites and of a temple pillar:--Jachin.', 'Jachin = \"He will establish\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 4th son of Simeon and founder of the family of Jachinites<LI>a priest and the head of the 21st course in the time of David<LI>a post-exilic priest in the time of Nehemiah n pr<LI>name of the right-hand pillar before the temple</OL>'),
(3200, 'ynyky', 'patronymically from (03199)', 'Yakiyniy', 'None', 'yaw-kee-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from «03199»; a Jakinite (collectively) or descendants of Jakin:--Jachinites.', 'Jachinites = see Jachin \"he will establish\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the descendants of Jachin</OL>'),
(3201, 'lky', 'a primitive root', 'yakol', 'TWOT - 866', 'yaw-kole\'', 'Verb', 'or (fuller) yakowl {yaw-kole\'}; a primitive root; to be able, literally (can, could) or morally (may, might):--be able, any at all (ways), attain, can (away with, (-not)), could, endure, might, overcome, have power, prevail, still, suffer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to prevail, overcome, endure, have power, be able<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be able, be able to gain or accomplish, be able to endure, be able to reach<LI>to prevail, prevail over or against, overcome, be victor<LI>to have ability, have strength</OL></OL></OL>'),
(3202, 'lky', 'to (03201)', 'ykel', 'TWOT - 2769', 'yek-ale\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) or ykiyl (Aramaic) {yek-eel\'}; to «03201»:--be able, can, couldest, prevail.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be able<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be able<LI>to prevail</OL></OL></OL>'),
(3203, 'hylky', 'from (03201) and (03050)', 'Ykolyah', 'None', 'yek-ol-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'and Ykolyahuw {yek-ol-yaw\'-hoo}; or (2 Chronicles 26:3) Ykiylyah {yek-ee-leh-yaw\'}; from «03201» and «03050»; Jah will enable; Jekoljah or Jekiljah, an Israelitess:--Jecholiah, Jecoliah.', 'Jecoliah or Jecholiah = \"Jehovah is able\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wife of king Amaziah of Judah and mother of king Uzziah (Azariah)</OL>'),
(3204, 'hynky', 'from (03559) and (03050)', 'Ykonyah', 'None', 'yek-on-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'and Ykonyahuw {yek-on-yaw\'-hoo}; or (Jereremiah 27:20) Ykownyah {yek-o-neh-yaw\'}; from «03559» and «03050»; Jah will establish; Jekonjah, a Jewish king:--Jeconiah. Compare «03659».', 'Jeconiah = \"Jehovah will establish\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of king Jehoiakim of Judah and king of Judah for 3 months and 10 days before he surrendered to Nebuchadnezzar and was taken captive to Babylon where he was imprisoned for the next 36 years; released at the death of Nebuchadnezzar and lived in Babylon until his death<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>primary spelling \'Jehoiachin\'</OL></OL>'),
(3205, 'dly', 'a primitive root', 'yalad', 'TWOT - 867', 'yaw-lad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to bear young; causatively, to beget; medically, to act as midwife; specifically, to show lineage:--bear, beget, birth((-day)), born, (make to) bring forth (children, young), bring up, calve, child, come, be delivered (of a child), time of delivery, gender, hatch, labour, (do the office of a) midwife, declare pedigrees, be the son of, (woman in, woman that) travail(-eth, -ing woman).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bear, bring forth, beget, gender, travail<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bear, bring forth 1a</OL><LI>of child birth 1a<LI>of distress (simile) 1a<LI>of wicked (behaviour)<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to beget</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be born<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause or help to bring forth<LI>to assist or tend as a midwife<LI>midwife (participle)</OL><LI>(Pual) to be born<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to beget (a child)<LI>to bear (fig. - of wicked bringing forth iniquity)</OL><LI>(Hophal) day of birth, birthday (infinitive)<LI>(Hithpael) to declare one\'s birth (pedigree)</OL></OL>'),
(3206, 'dly', 'from (03205)', 'yeled', 'TWOT - 867b', 'yeh\'-led', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03205»; something born, i.e. a lad or offspring:--boy, child, fruit, son, young man (one).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>child, son, boy, offspring, youth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>child, son, boy<LI>child, children<LI>descendants<LI>youth<LI>apostate Israelites (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(3207, 'hdly', 'from (03206)', 'yaldah', 'TWOT - 867b', 'yal-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «03206»; a lass:--damsel, girl.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>girl, damsel, marriageable girl</OL>'),
