(3251, '$oy', 'a primitive root', 'yacak', 'TWOT - 1474', 'yaw-sak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pour (intransitive):--be poured.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to anoint, be poured,</OL>'),
(3252, 'hkoy', 'from an unused root meaning to watch', 'Yickah', 'None', 'yis-kaw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning to watch; observant; Jiskah, sister of Lot:--Iscah.', 'Iscah = \"one who looks forth\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>daughter of Haran, niece of Abraham, sister of Lot and Milcah</OL>'),
(3253, 'whykmoy', 'from (05564) and (03050)', 'Yicmakyahuw,', 'None', 'yis-mak-yaw-hoo\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05564» and «03050»; Jah will sustain; Jismakjah, an Israelite:--Ismachiah.', 'Ismachiah = \"Jehovah sustains\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite and overseer of the offerings during the revival in the time of king Hezekiah</OL>'),
(3254, '@oy', 'a primitive root', 'yacaph', 'TWOT - 876', 'yaw-saf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to add or augment (often adverbial, to continue to do a thing):--add, × again, × any more, × cease, ×  come more, + conceive again, continue, exceed, × further, ×  gather together, get more, give more-over, × henceforth, increase (more and more), join, × longer (bring, do, make, much, put), × (the, much, yet) more (and more), proceed (further), prolong, put, be (strong-) er, × yet, yield.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to add, increase, do again<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to add, increase, do again<LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to join, join oneself to<LI>to be joined, be added to</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to add, increase<LI>to do more, do again</OL></OL></OL>'),
