(3258, '#b[y', 'from an unused root probably meaning to grieve', 'Ya`bets', 'None', 'yah-bates\'', '', 'from an unused root probably meaning to grieve; sorrowful; Jabets, the name of an Israelite, and also of a place in Palestine:  -Jabez.', 'Jabez = \"sorrow\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the head of a Calebite family n pr loc<LI>a town in Judah apparently near Bethlehem</OL>'),
(3259, 'd[y', 'a primitive root', 'ya`ad', 'TWOT - 878', 'yaw-ad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to fix upon (by agreement or appointment); by implication, to meet (at a stated time), to summon (to trial), to direct (in a certain quarter or position), to engage (for marriage):  -agree,(maxke an) appoint(-ment,a time), assemble (selves), betroth, gather (selves, together), meet (together), set (a time).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fix, appoint, assemble, meet, set, betroth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to appoint, assign, designate<LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to meet<LI>to meet by appointment<LI>to gather, assemble by appointment</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to cause to meet<LI>(Hophal) to be set, be placed before, be fixed</OL></OL>'),
(3260, 'yd[y', 'from (03259)', 'Y`diy', 'None', 'yed-ee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03259»; appointed; Jedi, an Israelite:--Iddo (from the margin) See «03035».', 'Iddo = \"appointed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the seer who proclaimed to king Jeroboam of Israel</OL>'),
(3261, 'h[y', 'a primitive root', 'ya`ah', 'TWOT - 879', 'yaw-aw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; apparently to brush aside:--sweep away.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to sweep, sweep away, sweep together</OL>'),
(3262, 'law[y', 'from (03261) and (0410)', 'Y`uw\'el', 'None', 'yeh-oo-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03261» and «0410»; carried away of God; Jeuel, the name of four Israelites; -Jehiel, Jeiel, Jeuel. Compare «03273».', 'Jeuel = \"God sweeps away\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Zerah and a chief man of Judah</OL>'),
(3263, '#w[y', 'from (05779)', 'Y`uwts', 'None', 'yeh-oots\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05779»; counsellor; Jeuts, an Israelite:  -Jeuz.(gl', 'Jeuz = \"counsellor\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of a house of Benjamin</OL>'),
