(3273, 'lay[y', 'from (03261) and (0410)', 'Y`iy\'el', 'None', 'yeh-ee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03261» and «0410»; carried away of God; Jeiel, the name of six Israelites:--Jeiel, Jehiel. Compare «03262».', 'Jeiel or Jehiel = \"God sweeps away\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the sons of Adonikam who returned from exile with Ezra<LI>a chief Reubenite of the house of Joel<LI>a Merarite Levite and a gatekeeper to the tabernacle who also played the harp and psaltery in the service before the ark<LI>one of the chiefs of the Levites in the time of king Josiah<LI>one of the sons of Nebo who took a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>a man of Gibeon and ancestor of king Saul<LI>one of the sons of Hotham the Aroerite and one of David\'s mighty warriors<LI>the scribe of king Uzziah who kept the account of the king\'s irregular predatory warriors<LI>a Gershonite Levite of the sons of Elizaphan<LI>a Gershonite Levite of the sons of Asaph and forefather of Jahaziel in the time of king Jehoshaphat</OL>'),
(3274, 'Xy[y', 'from (05789)', 'Y`iysh', 'None', 'yeh-eesh\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05789»; hasty; Jeish, the name of an Edomite and of a an Israelite:--Jeush (from the margin). Compare «03266».', 'Jeush = \"assembler\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Esau by Aholibamah the daughter of Anah, son of Zibeon the Hivite<LI>a Benjamite, son of Bilhan</OL>'),
(3275, '!k[y', 'from the same as (05912)', 'Ya`kan', 'None', 'yah-kawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «05912»; troublesome; Jakan, an Israelite:--Jachan.', 'Jachan = \"troublesome\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of seven chief men of the tribe of Gad</OL>'),
(3276, 'l[y', 'a primitive root', 'ya`al', 'TWOT - 882', 'yaw-al\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to ascend; figuratively, to be valuable (objectively: useful, subjectively: benefited):--X at all, set forward, can do good, (be, have) profit, (able).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to gain, profit, benefit, avail</OL>'),
(3277, 'l[y', 'from (03276)', 'ya`el', 'TWOT - 883a', 'yaw-ale\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03276»; an ibex (as climbing):--wild goat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mountain goat</OL>'),
(3278, 'l[y', 'the same as (03277)', 'Ya`el', 'None', 'yaw-ale\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'the same as «03277»; Jael, a Canaanite:--Jael.', 'Jael = \"mountain goat\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the wife of Heber the Kenite who killed the general Sisera as he slept by driving a peg through his temples into the ground</OL>'),
(3279, 'al[y', 'the same as (03280) or direct from (03276)', 'Ya`ala\'', 'None', 'yah-al-aw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Yaaalah {yah-al-aw\'}; the same as «03280» or direct from «03276»; Jaala or Jaalah, one of the Nethinim:--Jaala, Jaalah.', 'Jaala or Jaalah = \"ascending\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the head of a family of the descendants of Solomon\'s slaves who returned from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(3280, 'hl[y', 'from (03277)', 'ya`alah', 'TWOT - 883b', 'yah-al-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «03277»:--roe.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>female mountain goat</OL>'),
(3281, '~l[y', 'from (05956)', 'Ya`lam', 'None', 'yah-lawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05956»; occult; Jalam, an Edomite:--Jalam.', 'Jaalam = \"concealed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Edomite, descendant of Esau</OL>'),
(3282, '![y', 'from an unused root meaning to pay attention', 'ya`an', 'TWOT - 1650e', 'yah\'-an', '', 'from an unused root meaning to pay attention; properly, heed; by implication, purpose (sake or account); used adverbially to indicate the reason or cause:--because (that), forasmuch (+ as), seeing then, + that, + wheras, + why.', 'conj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>because, therefore, because that, on account of prep<LI>because of, on account of<LI>why (with interrogative pron)</OL>'),
(3283, '![y', 'from the same as (03282)', 'ya`en', 'TWOT - 884a', 'yaw-ane\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «03282»; the ostrich (probably from its answering cry:--ostrich.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ostrich<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>ceremonially unclean animal</OL></OL>'),
(3284, 'hn[y', 'from (03283)', 'ya`anah', 'TWOT - 884b', 'yah-an-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «03283», and meaning the same:--+ owl.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an unclean bird<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>owl, ostrich, literally translated as \"daughters of the owl\"<LI>perhaps an extinct bird, exact meaning unknown</OL></OL>'),
(3285, 'yn[y', 'from the same as (03283)', 'Ya`anay', 'None', 'yah-an-ah\'ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «03283»; responsive; Jaanai, an Israelite:--Jaanai.', 'Jaanai = \"whom Jehovah answers\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a chief man in the tribe of Gad</OL>'),
(3286, '@[y', 'a primitive root', 'ya`aph', 'TWOT - 885', 'yaw-af\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to tire (as if from wearisome flight):--faint, cause to fly, (be) weary (self).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or grow weary, be fatigued, be faint<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be or grow weary, be fatigued, be faint<LI>(Hophal) wearied (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(3287, '@[y', 'from (03286)', 'ya`ph', 'TWOT - 885a', 'yaw-afe\';', 'Adjective', 'from «03286»; fatigued; figuratively, exhausted:--faint, weary.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>faint, weary, fatigued</OL>'),
(3288, '@y', 'from (03286)', 'yaph', 'TWOT - 885b', 'yeh-awf\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03286»; fatigue (adverb, utterly exhausted):  -swiftly.e', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>weariness, fatigue, faintness</OL>'),
(3289, '#[y', 'a primitive root', 'ya`ats', 'TWOT - 887', 'yaw-ats\'', 'Verb', ' a primitive root;  to  advise; reflexively, to deliberate or resolve:--advertise, take advise, advise (well), consult, (give, take) counsel(-lor), determine, devise, guide, purpose.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to advise, consult, give counsel, counsel, purpose, devise, plan<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to advise, counsel, give counsel, consult<LI>counsellor (participle)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to consult together, exchange counsel, deliberate, counsel together<LI>(Hithpael) to conspire</OL></OL>'),
(3290, 'bq[y', 'from (06117)', 'Ya`aqob', 'None', 'yah-ak-obe\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06117»; heel-catcher (i.e. supplanter); Jaakob, the Israelitish patriarch:--Jacob.', 'Jacob = \"heel holder\" or \"supplanter\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Isaac, grandson of Abraham, and father of the 12 patriarchs of the tribes of Israel</OL>'),
(3291, 'hbq[y', 'from (03290)', 'Ya`aqobah', 'None', 'yah-ak-o\'-baw', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03290»; Jaakobah, an Israelite:  -Jaakobah.', 'Jaakobah = \"toward Jacob\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Simeon and grandson of Jacob</OL>'),
(3292, '!q[y', 'from the same as (06130)', 'Ya`aqan', 'None', 'yah-ak-awn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «06130»; Jaakan, an Idumaean:  -Jaakan. Compare «01142».', 'Jakan = \"let him oppress them\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Edomite</OL>'),
(3293, 'r[y', 'from an unused root probably meaning to thicken with verdure', 'ya`ar', 'TWOT - 888,889', 'yah\'-ar', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to thicken with verdure; a copse of bushes; hence, a forest; hence, honey in the comb (as hived in trees):--(honey-)comb, forest, wood.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>forest, wood, thicket, wooded height</OL>'),
(3294, 'hr[y', 'a form of (03295)', 'Ya`rah', 'None', 'yah-raw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'a form of «03295»; Jarah, an Israelite:--Jarah.', 'Jarah = \"forested\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Saul, son of Micah, great grandson of Mephibosheth</OL>'),
(3295, 'hr[y', 'from (03293)', 'ya`arah', 'TWOT - 889b', 'yah-ar-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «03293», and meaning the same:--(honey-) comb, forest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>forest<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>honeycomb (meton)</OL></OL>'),
(3296, '~ygra yr[y', 'from the pl. of (03293) and the masc. pl. act. participle of (707)', 'Ya`arey', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the plural of «03293» and the masculine plural active participle of «0707»; woods of weavers; Jaare-Oregim, an Israelite:--Jaare-oregim.', 'Jaare-oregim = \"forests of weaver\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a man of Bethlehem, father of Elhanan the giant slayer and one of David\'s mighty warriors; also called \'Jair\'</OL>'),
(3297, '~yr[y', 'pl. of (03293)', 'Y`ariym', 'None', 'yeh-aw-reem\'', 'Location', 'plural of «03293»; forests; Jearim, a place in Palestine:--Jearim. Compare «07157».', 'Jearim = \"forests\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a hill on the northern boundary of Judah</OL>'),
(3298, 'hyXr[y', 'from an unused root of uncertain signification and (03050)', 'Ya`areshyah', 'None', 'yah-ar-esh-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root of uncertain signification and «03050»; Jaareshjah, an Israelite:--Jaresiah.', 'Jaresiah = \"whom Jehovah nourishes\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, one of the descendants of Jehoram</OL>'),
(3299, 'wX[y', 'from (06213)', 'Ya`asuw', 'None', 'yah-as-oo\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06213»; they will do; Jaasu, an Israelite:  -Jaasau.', 'Jaasau = \"they will do\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the descendants of Bani who took a foreign wife during the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(3300, 'layX[y', 'from (06213) and (0410)', 'Ya`asiy\'el', 'None', 'yah-as-ee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06213» and «0410»; made of God; Jaasiel, an Israelite:--Jaasiel, Jasiel.', 'Jasiel or Jaasiel = \"God is maker\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of David\'s mighty warriors<LI>a son of Abner and a chief of Benjamin</OL>'),
(3301, 'hydpy', 'from (06299) and (03050)', 'Yiphdyah', 'None', 'yif-deh-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06299» and «03050»; Jah will liberate; Jiphdejah, an Israelite:--Iphedeiah.', 'Iphedeiah = \"Jehovah will redeem\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Benjamin and of the family of Shashak</OL>'),
(3302, 'hpy', 'a primitive root', 'yaphah', 'TWOT - 890', 'yaw-faw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to be bright, i.e. (by implication) beautiful:--be beautiful, be (make self) fair(-r), deck.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be bright, be beautiful, be handsome, be fair<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be beautiful<LI>(Piel) to beautify<LI>(Pual) to be beautiful<LI>(Hithpael) to beautify oneself</OL></OL>'),
(3303, 'hpy', 'from (03302)', 'yapheh', 'TWOT - 890a', 'yaw-feh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «03302»; beautiful (literally or figuratively):--+ beautiful, beauty, comely, fair(-est, one), + goodly, pleasant, well.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fair, beautiful, handsome</OL>'),
(3304, 'hyphpy', 'from (03302) by reduplication', 'ypheh-phiyah', 'TWOT - 890b', 'yef-eh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «03302» by reduplication; very beautiful:--very fair.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pretty (reduplication with the force of the diminutive)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>fair of mouth (lit.)</OL><LI>(CLBL) very beautiful</OL>'),
(3305, '@y', 'from (03302)', 'Yapho', 'None', 'yaw-fo\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Yaphow  (Ezra 3:7) {yaw-fo\'}; from «03302»; beautiful; Japho, a place in Palestine:--Japha, Joppa.', 'Joppa or Japho = \"beautiful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town on the southwest coast of Palestine in the territory of Dan; became primary port of Jerusalem during reign of Solomon</OL>'),
(3306, 'xpy', 'a primitive root', 'yaphach', 'TWOT - 891', 'yaw-fakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to breathe hard, i.e. (by implication) to sigh:--bewail self.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to breathe, breathe hard, puff<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hithpael) to gasp for breath</OL></OL>'),
(3307, 'xpy', 'from (03306)', 'yapheach', 'TWOT - 891a', 'yaw-fay\'-akh', 'Adjective', 'from «03306»; properly, puffing, i.e. (figuratively) meditating:--such as breathe out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a breathing out, exhaling, puffing out (subst)</OL>'),
(3308, 'ypy', 'from (03302)', 'yophiy', 'TWOT - 890c', 'yof-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03302»; beauty:--beauty.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>beauty</OL>'),
(3309, '[ypy', 'from (03313)', 'Yaphiya`', 'None', 'yaw-fee\'-ah', '', 'from «03313»; bright; Japhia, the name of a Canaanite, an Israelite, and a place in Palestine:--Japhia.', 'Japhia = \"shining\" n pr loc<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town on the border of Zebulun and Issachar<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps modern \'Yafa\' n pr m</OL><LI>the king of Lachish at the time of the conquest of Canaan by Joshua<LI>a son of David by a concubine</OL>'),
(3310, 'tlpy', 'from (06403)', 'Yaphlet', 'None', 'yaf-late\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06403»; he will deliver; Japhlet, an Israelite:--Japhlet.', 'Japhlet = \"he will deliver\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Asher through Beriah</OL>'),
(3311, 'ytlpy', 'patronymically from (03310)', 'Yaphletiy', 'None', 'yaf-lay-tee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from «03310»; a Japhletite or descendant of Japhlet:--Japhleti.', 'Japhleti see Japhlet = \"let him escape\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Asher of the family of Japhlet who lived on the southwest border of Ephraim. Used as location</OL>'),
(3312, 'hnnpy', 'from (06437)', 'Yphunneh', 'None', 'yef-oon-neh\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06437»; he will be prepared; Jephunneh, the name of two Israelites:--Jephunneh.', 'Jephunneh = \"He will be facing\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Kenezite and father of Caleb the spy from the tribe of Judah<LI>son of Jether and descendant of Asher</OL>'),
(3313, '[py', 'a primitive root', 'yapha`', 'TWOT - 892', 'yaw-fah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to shine:--be light, shew self, (cause to) shine (forth).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shine, shine forth or out, cause to shine, send out beams<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shine out, shine forth, send out beams<LI>to cause to shine</OL></OL></OL>'),
(3314, 'h[py', 'from (03313)', 'yiph`ah', 'TWOT - 892a', 'yif-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03313»; splendor or (figuratively) beauty:  -brightness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>splendour, brightness, shining</OL>'),
(3315, 'tpy', 'from (06601)', 'Yepheth', 'None', 'yeh\'-feth', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06601»; expansion; Jepheth, a son of Noah; also his posterity:--Japheth.', 'Japheth = \"opened\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 3rd son of Noah whose descendants after the flood settled on the coastal lands of the Mediterranean spreading north into Europe and parts of Asia</OL>'),
(3316, 'xtpy', 'from (06605)', 'Yiphtach', 'None', 'yif-tawkh\'', '', 'from «06605»; he will open; Jiphtach, an Israelite; also a place in Palestine:--Jephthah, Jiphtah.', 'Jephthah or Jiphtah = \"he opens\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Gilead and a concubine and the judge who defeated the Ammonites; after the victory because of a vow taken before the battle he sacrificed his daughter as a burnt offering n pr loc<LI>a city in Judah</OL>'),
(3317, 'laxtpy', 'from (06605) and (0410)', 'Yiphtach-\'el', 'None', 'yif-tach-ale\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06605» and «0410»; God will open; Jiphtach-el, a place in Palestine:--Jiphthah-el.', 'Jiphthah-el = \"God opens\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a valley between Zebulun and Asher; location uncertain</OL>'),
(3318, 'acy', 'a primitive root', 'yatsa\'', 'TWOT - 893', 'yaw-tsaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to go (causatively, bring) out, in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively, direct and proxim.:--X after, appear, × assuredly, bear out, ×  begotten, break out, bring forth (out, up), carry out, come (abroad, out, thereat, without), + be condemned, depart(-ing, -ure), draw forth, in the end, escape, exact, fail, fall (out), fetch forth (out), get away (forth, hence, out), (able to, cause to, let) go abroad (forth, on, out), going out, grow, have forth (out), issue out, lay (lie) out, lead out, pluck out, proceed, pull out, put away, be risen, ×  scarce, send with commandment, shoot forth, spread, spring out, stand out, × still, × surely, take forth (out), at any time, × to (and fro), utter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go out, come out, exit, go forth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go or come out or forth, depart<LI>to go forth (to a place)<LI>to go forward, proceed to (to or toward something)<LI>to come or go forth (with purpose or for result)<LI>to come out of</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to go or come out, bring out, lead out<LI>to bring out of<LI>to lead out<LI>to deliver</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be brought out or forth</OL></OL>'),
(3319, 'acy', 'corresponding to (03318)', 'ytsa\'', 'TWOT - 3028', 'yets-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «03318»:--finish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Shaphel) to bring to an end, finish, bring out to an end</OL>'),
(3320, 'bcy', 'a primitive root', 'yatsab', 'TWOT - 894', 'yaw-tsab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to place (any thing so as to stay); reflexively, to station, offer, continue:--present selves, remaining, resort, set (selves), (be able to, can, with-) stand (fast, forth, -ing, still, up).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to place, set, stand, set or station oneself, present oneself<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hithpael) to station oneself, take one\'s stand, stand, present oneself, stand with someone</OL></OL>'),
(3321, 'bcy', 'corresponding to (03320)', 'ytseb', 'TWOT - 2773', 'yets-abe\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «03320»; to be firm; hence, to speak surely:--truth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Pael) to make stand, make certain, gain certainty, know the truth, be certain</OL>'),
(3322, 'gcy', 'a primitive root', 'yatsag', 'TWOT - 895', 'yaw-tsag\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to place permanently:--establish, leave, make, present, put, set, stay.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to place, set, establish<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to set, place<LI>to present<LI>to exhibit</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be stopped, be stayed, be detained</OL></OL>'),
(3323, 'rhcy', 'from (06671)', 'yitshar', 'TWOT - 1883c', 'yits-hawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06671»; oil (as producing light); figuratively, anointing:--+ anointed oil.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fresh oil, shining (pure) oil</OL>'),
(3324, 'rhcy', 'the same as (03323)', 'Yitshar', 'None', 'yits-hawr\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «03323»; Jitshar, an Israelite:--Izhar.', 'Izhar = \"shining oil\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Kohath, grandson of Levi, uncle of Moses and Aaron, and father of Korah; progenitor of the Izharites</OL>'),
(3325, 'yrhcy', 'patronymically from (03324)', 'Yitshariy', 'None', 'yits-haw-ree\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from «03324»; a Jitsharite or descendant of Jitshar:--Izeharites, Izharites.', 'Izharites or Izeharites = \"oil\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Izhar son of Kohath and grandson of Levi</OL>'),
(3326, '[wcy', 'passive participle of (03331)', 'yatsuwa`', 'TWOT - 896a', 'yaw-tsoo\'-ah', 'Noun Masculine', 'passive participle of «03331»; spread, i.e. a bed; (architecture) an extension, i.e. wing or lean-to (a single story or collectively):  -bed, chamber, couch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>couch, bed</OL>'),
(3327, 'qxcy', 'from (06711)', 'Yitschaq', 'TWOT - 1905b', 'yits-khawk\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06711»; laughter (i.e. mochery); Jitschak (or Isaac), son of Abraham:--Isaac. Compare «03446».', 'Isaac = \"he laughs\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Abraham by Sarah his wife and father of Jacob and Esau</OL>'),
