(4114, 'hkphm', 'from (02015)', 'mahpekah', 'TWOT - 512d', 'mah-pay-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02015»; a destruction:  --when...overthrew, overthrow(-n).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>overthrow, destruction<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>always of Sodom and Gomorrah</OL></OL>'),
(4115, 'tkphm', 'from (02015)', 'mahpeketh', 'TWOT - 512e', 'mah-peh\'-keth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02015»; a wrench, i.e. the stocks:--prison, stocks.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stocks<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>similar instrument of punishment (compelling crooked posture or distorting)<LI>house of stocks, prison-house</OL></OL>'),
(4116, 'rhm', 'a primitive root', 'mahar', 'TWOT - 1152', 'maw-har\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to be liquid or flow easily, i.e. (by implication); to hurry (in a good or a bad sense); often used (with another verb) adverbially, promptly:--be carried headlong, fearful, (cause to make, in, make) haste(-n, -ily), (be) hasty, (fetch, make ready) × quickly, rash, × shortly, (be so) × soon, make speed, × speedily, × straightway, ×  suddenly, swift.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to hasten<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be hurried, be anxious<LI>hasty, precipitate, impetuous<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hasten, make haste<LI>hasten (used as adverb with another verb)<LI>to hasten, prepare quickly, do quickly, bring quickly</OL></OL></OL>'),
(4117, 'rhm', 'a primitive root (perhaps rather the same as (4116) through the idea of readiness in assent)', 'mahar', 'TWOT - 1153', 'maw-har\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (perhaps rather the same as «04116» through the idea of readiness in assent); to bargain (for a wife), i.e. to wed:--endow, × surely.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to obtain or acquire by paying purchase price, give a dowry<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to obtain in exchange</OL></OL>'),
(4118, 'rhm', 'from (04116)', 'maher', 'TWOT - 1152a, 1152b', 'mah-hare\'', '', 'from «04116»; properly, hurrying; hence (adverbially) in a hurry:--hasteth, hastily, at once, quickly, soon, speedily, suddenly.', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hurrying, speedy, swift, hastening adv<LI>quickly, speedily</OL>'),
(4119, 'rhm', 'from (04117)', 'mohar', 'TWOT - 1153a', 'mo\'-har', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04117»; a price (for a wife):--dowry.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>purchase price for wife, wedding money</OL>'),
(4120, 'hrhm', 'from (04118)', 'mherah', 'TWOT - 1152d', 'meh-hay-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «04118»; properly, a hurry; hence (adverbially) promptly:--hastily, quickly, shortly, soon, make (with) speed(-ily), swiftly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>haste, speed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>hastily, speedily (as adverb)<LI>in haste (with prep)</OL></OL>'),
(4121, 'yrhm', 'from (04116)', 'Maharay', 'None', 'mah-har-ah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04116»; hasty; Maharai, an Israelite:--Maharai.', 'Maharai = \"impetuous\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Netophah in the tribe of Judah and one of David\'s mighty warriors</OL>'),
(4122, 'zb Xx llX rhm', 'from (04118) and (07998) and (02363) and (0957)', 'Maher', 'None', 'Chash', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04118» and «07998» and «02363» and «0957»; hasting (is he (the enemy) to the) booty, swift (to the) prey; Maher-Shalal-Chash-Baz; the symbolical name of the son of Isaiah:--Maher-sha-lal-bash-baz.', '= Maher-shalal-hash-baz \"swift is booty, speedy is prey\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>symbolic name given by Isaiah by the Lord\'s direction to Isaiah\'s son; prophetic indication that Damascus and Samaria were soon to be plundered by the king of Assyria</OL>'),
(4123, 'hllthm', 'from (02048)', 'mahathallah', 'TWOT - 2514a', 'mah-hath-al-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02048»; a delusion:--deceit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>deceptions, illusions</OL>'),
(4124, 'bawm', 'from a prolonged form of the prepositional prefix m- and (01)', 'Mow\'ab', 'from (her [the mother\'s]) father', 'mo-awb', '', 'from a prolonged form of the prepositional prefix m- and «01»; from (her (the mother\'s)) father; Moab, an incestuous son of Lot; also his territory and descendants:--Moab.', 'Moab = \"of his father\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Lot by his eldest daughter<LI>the nation descended from the son of Lot n pr loc<LI>the land inhabited by the descendants of the son of Lot</OL>'),
(4125, 'ybawm', 'patronymical from (04124)', 'Mow\'abiy', 'TWOT - 1155a', 'mo-aw-bee\'', 'Adjective', 'feminine Mownabiyah {mo-aw-bee-yaw\'}; or Mowabiyth {mo-aw-beeth\'}; patronymical from «04124»; a Moabite or Moabitess, i.e. a descendant from Moab:--(woman) of Moab, Moabite(-ish, -ss).', 'Moabite = \"from father: what father?\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an citizen of Moab<LI>an inhabitant of the land of Moab</OL>'),
(4126, 'abwm', 'by transp. for (03996)', 'mowba\'', 'TWOT - 212b', 'mo-baw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'by transp. for «03996»; an entrance:--coming.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>entrance, entering, in-coming</OL>'),
(4127, 'gwm', 'a primitive root', 'muwg', 'TWOT - 1156', 'moog', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to melt, i.e. literally (to soften, flow down, disappear), or figuratively (to fear, faint):--consume, dissolve, (be) faint(-hearted), melt (away), make soft.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to melt, cause to melt<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to melt, faint<LI>to cause to melt</OL><LI>(Niphal) to melt away<LI>(Polel) to soften, dissolve, dissipate<LI>(Hithpolel) to melt, flow</OL></OL>'),
