(4131, 'twm', 'a primitive root', 'mowt', 'TWOT - 1158', 'mote', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to waver; by implication , to slip, shake, fall:--be carried, cast, be out of course, be fallen in decay, × exceedingly, fall(-ing down), be (re-)moved, be ready, shake, slide, slip.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to totter, shake, slip<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to totter, shake, slip<LI>(Niphal) to be shaken, be moved, be overthrown<LI>(Hiphil) to dislodge, let fall, drop<LI>(Hithpael) to be greatly shaken</OL></OL>'),
(4132, 'twm', 'from (04131)', 'mowt', 'TWOT - 1158a', 'mote', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04131»; a wavering, i.e. fall; by implication, a pole (as shaking); hence, a yoke (as essentially a bent pole):--bar, be moved, staff, yoke.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a shaking, wavering, pole, bar of yoke<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a shaking, tottering<LI>pole, bar (for carrying)<LI>bar of yoke</OL></OL>'),
(4133, 'htwm', 'from (04132)', 'mowtah', 'TWOT - 1158b', 'mo-taw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «04132»; a pole; by implication, an  ox-bow; hence, a yoke (either literal or figurative):--bands, heavy, staves, yoke.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pole, bar of yoke<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>pole<LI>bar of yoke<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of oppression (fig.)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(4134, '$wm', 'a primitive root', 'muwk', 'TWOT - 1159', 'mook', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to become thin, i.e. (figuratively) be impoverished:--be (waxen) poor(-er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be low, grow poor, be depressed, be poor</OL>'),
(4135, 'lwm', 'a primitive root', 'muwl', 'TWOT - 1161', 'mool', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to cut short, i.e. curtail (specifically the prepuce, i.e. to circumcise); by implication, to blunt; figuratively, to destroy:--circumcise(-ing), selves), cut down (in pieces), destroy, × must needs.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to circumcise, let oneself be circumcised, cut, be cut off<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to circumcise<LI>(Niphal) to be circumcised, circumcise oneself<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to be circumcised<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of destruction (fig.)</OL><LI>(Hithpolel) to be cut off<LI>(Polel) cut down</OL></OL>'),
(4136, 'lwm', 'from (04135)', 'muwl', 'TWOT - 1160', 'mool', '', 'or mowl (Deuteronomy 1:1) {mole}; or mowtl (Nehemiah 12:38) {mole}; or mul (Numbers 22:5) {mool}; from «04135»; properly, abrupt, i.e. a precipice; by implication, the front; used only adverbially (with prepositional prefix) opposite:--(over) against, before, (fore-)front, from, (God-)ward, toward, with.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>front<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>front<LI>in the opposite direction prep</OL><LI>in front of<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>in front of<LI>(with prefix)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>towards the front of, to the front of, on the front of<LI>from the front of, off the front of, close in front of, on the forefront of</OL></OL></OL>'),
(4137, 'hdlwm', 'from (03205)', 'Mowladah', 'None', 'mo-law-daw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «03205»; birth; Moladah, a place in Palestine:--Moladah.', 'Moladah = \"birth\" or \"race\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in the south of Canaan allocated to Judah then reallocated to Simeon</OL>'),
(4138, 'tdlwm', 'from (03205)', 'mowledeth', 'TWOT - 867f', 'mo-leh\'-deth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03205»; nativity (plural birth-place); by implication, lineage, native country; also offspring, family:--begotten, born, issue, kindred, native(-ity).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>kindred, birth, offspring, relatives<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>kindred<LI>birth, circumstances of birth<LI>one born, begotten, issue, offspring, female offspring</OL></OL>'),
(4139, 'hlwm', 'from (04135)', 'muwlah', 'TWOT - 1161a', 'moo-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04135»; circumcision:--circumcision.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>circumcision</OL>'),
(4140, 'dylwm', 'from (03205)', 'Mowliyd', 'None', 'mo-leed\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03205»; genitor; Molid, an Israelite:--Molid.', 'Molid = \"begetter\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a man of Judah, son of Abishur by Abihail and a descendant of Jerahmeel</OL>'),
(4141, 'bowm', 'from (05437)', 'muwcab', 'TWOT - 1456b', 'moo-sawb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05437»; a turn, i.e. circuit (of a building):--winding about.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>encompassing, surrounding, round about</OL>'),
(4142, 'hbbowm', 'from (04141)', 'muwcabbah', 'TWOT - 1456b', 'moo-sab-baw\'', 'Verb Feminine', 'or mucabbah {moo-sab-baw\'}; feminine of «04141»; a reversal, i.e. the backside (of a gem), fold (of a double-leaved door), transmutation (of a name):--being changed, inclosed, be set, turning.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hophal)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be turned<LI>surrounded, set (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(4143, 'dowm', 'from (03245)', 'muwcad', 'TWOT - 875d', 'moo-sawd\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03245»; a foundation:--foundation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>foundation, laying of foundation, foundation-laying</OL>'),
(4144, 'dowm', 'from (03245)', 'mowcad', 'TWOT - 875f', 'mo-sawd\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03245»; a foundation:--foundation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>foundation</OL>'),
(4145, 'hdowm', 'from (04143)', 'muwcadah', 'TWOT - 875e', 'moo-saw-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «04143»; a foundation; figuratively, an appointment:--foundation, grounded. Compare «04328».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>foundation, appointment</OL>'),
