(4212, 'hrmmzm', 'from (02168)', 'mzammrah', 'TWOT - 559d', 'mez-am-mer-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02168»; a tweezer (only in the plural):--snuffers.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>snuffers (temple utensil)</OL>'),
(4213, 'r[zm', 'from the same as (02191)', 'miz`ar', 'TWOT - 571b', 'miz-awr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «02191»; fewness; by implication, as superl. diminutiveness:--few, × very.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a little, a trifle, a few<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a trifle, a little (of time)<LI>a remnant, a very few (of number)</OL></OL>'),
(4214, 'hrzm', 'from (02219)', 'mizreh', 'TWOT - 579a', 'miz-reh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02219»; a winnowing shovel (as scattering the chaff):--fan.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pitchfork</OL>'),
(4215, 'hrzm', 'apparently from (02219)', 'mzareh', 'TWOT - 579', 'mez-aw-reh\'', '', 'apparently from «02219»; properly, a scatterer, i.e. the north wind (as dispersing clouds; only in plural):--north.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>scatterer</OL>'),
(4216, 'hrzzm', 'apparently from (05144) in the sense of distinction', 'mazzarah', 'TWOT - 1176', 'maz-zaw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'apparently from «05144» in the sense of distinction; some noted constellation (only in the plural), perhaps collectively, the zodiac:--Mazzoroth. Compare «04208».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Mazzaroth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the 12 signs of the Zodiac and their 36 associated constellations</OL></OL>'),
