(4310, 'ym', 'an interrogative pronoun of persons, as (04100) is of things, who? (occasionally, by a peculiar idiom, of things', 'miy', 'TWOT - 1189', 'me', '', 'an interrogative pronoun of persons, as «04100» is of things, who? (occasionally, by a peculiar idiom, of things); also (indefinitely) whoever; often used in oblique construction with prefix or suffix:--any (man), × he, × him, + O that! what, which, who(-m, -se, -soever), + would to God.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>who?, whose?, whom?, would that, whoever, whosoever</OL>'),
