(4349, '!wkm', 'from (03559)', 'makown', 'TWOT - 964c', 'maw-kone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03559»; properly, a fixture, i.e. a basis; generally a place, especially as an abode:--foundation, habitation, (dwelling-, settled) place.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fixed or established place, foundation<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>fixed place<LI>foundation</OL></OL>'),
(4350, 'hnwkm', 'from (04349)', 'mkownah', 'TWOT - 964d', 'mek-o-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or mkonah {mek-o-naw\'}; feminine of «04349»; a pedestal, also a spot:--base.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fixed resting place, base, pedestal</OL>'),
(4351, 'hrwkm', 'from the same as (03564) in the sense of dipping', 'mkuwrah', 'TWOT - 1033c', 'mek-oo-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or mkorah {mek-o-raw\'}; from the same as «03564» in the sense of dipping; origin (as if a mine):--birth, habitation, nativity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>origin</OL>'),
(4352, 'ykm', 'probably from (04134)', 'Makiy', 'None', 'maw-kee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «04134»; pining; Maki, an Israelite:--Machi.', 'Machi = \"decrease\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Geuel the Gadite who was one of the 12 spies of Israel</OL>'),
(4353, 'rykm', 'from (04376)', 'Makiyr', 'None', 'maw-keer\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04376»; salesman; Makir, an Israelite:--Machir.', 'Machir = \"sold\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>eldest son of Manasseh by an Aramite or Syrian concubine and progenitor of a large family<LI>son of Ammiel, a powerful chief of one of the Transjordanic tribes who rendered essential services to Saul and to David</OL>'),
(4354, 'yrykm', 'patronymical from (04353)', 'Makiyriy', 'None', 'maw-kee-ree\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymical from «04353»; a Makirite or descend. of Makir:--of Machir.', 'Machirites = \"a salesman\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the descendants of Machir the father of Gilead</OL>'),
(4355, '$km', 'a primitive root', 'makak', 'TWOT - 1193', 'maw-kak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to tumble (in ruins); figuratively, to perish:--be brought low, decay.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be low, be humiliated<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be low, be humiliated<LI>(Niphal) to sink<LI>(Hophal) to be brought low</OL></OL>'),
(4356, 'halkm', 'from (03607)', 'mikla\'ah', 'TWOT - 980c', 'mik-law-aw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or miklah {mik-law\'}; from «03607»; a pen (for flocks):--((sheep-))fold. Compare «04357».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fold, enclosure</OL>'),
(4357, 'hlkm', 'from (03615)', 'miklah', 'TWOT - 982d', 'mik-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03615»; completion (in plural concrete adverbial, wholly):--perfect. Compare «04356».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>completeness, perfection</OL>'),
(4358, 'lwlkm', 'from (03634)', 'miklowl', 'TWOT - 985c', 'mik-lole\'', '', 'from «03634»; perfection (i.e. concrete adverbial, splendidly):--most gorgeously, all sorts.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>perfection, gorgeous attire adv<LI>perfectly, most gorgeously</OL>'),
(4359, 'llkm', 'from (03634)', 'miklal', 'TWOT - 985e', 'mik-lawl\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03634»; perfection (of beauty):--perfection.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>completeness, perfection</OL>'),
(4360, 'llkm', 'from (03634)', 'miklul', 'TWOT - 985d', 'mik-lool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03634»; something perfect, i.e. a splendid garment:--all sorts.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a thing made perfect, perfect thing, gorgeous garment or stuff<LI>(TWOT) all sorts of things</OL>'),
(4361, 'tlkkm', 'from (0398)', 'makkoleth', 'TWOT - 85g', 'mak-ko\'-leth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «0398»; nourishment:--food.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>food, food stuff</OL>'),
(4362, '!mkm', 'from the same as (03646) in the sense of hiding', 'mikman', 'TWOT - 991a', 'mik-man\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «03646» in the sense of hiding; treasure (as hidden):--treasure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hidden stores, hidden treasure</OL>'),
(4363, 'omkm', 'from (03647)', 'Mikmac', 'None', 'mik-maws\'', 'Proper Name Location', '(Ezra 2:2 or Mikmash {mik-mawsh\'}; or Mikmash (Neh. 11:31) {mik-mash\'}; from «03647»; hidden; Mikmas or Mikmash, a place in Palestine:--Mikmas, Mikmash.', 'Michmas or Michmash = \"hidden\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in Benjamin lying near Ramah and approximately 10 miles (16 km) north of Jerusalem; probably modern \'Mukhmas\'</OL>'),
(4364, 'rmkm', 'from (03648) in the sense of blackening by heat', 'makmar', 'TWOT - 995b', 'mak-mawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or mikmor {mik-more\'}; from «03648» in the sense of blackening by heat; a (hunter\'s) net (as dark from concealment):--net.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>net, snare</OL>'),
(4365, 'trmkm', 'from (04364)', 'mikmereth', 'TWOT - 995c', 'mik-meh\'-reth', 'Noun Feminine', 'or mikmoreth {mik-mo\'-reth}; feminine of «04364»; a (fisher\'s) net:--drag, net.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>net, fishing net</OL>'),
(4366, 'ttmkm', 'apparently from an unused root meaning to hide', 'Mikmthath', 'None', 'mik-meth-awth\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'apparently from an unused root meaning to hide; concealment; Mikmethath, a place in Palestine:--Michmethath.', 'Michmethah = \"hiding place\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in northeast Ephraim near the border of Manasseh between Shechem and Taanath-shilo</OL>'),
(4367, 'ybdnkm', 'from (04100) and (05068) with a particle interposed', 'Maknadbay', 'None', 'mak-nad-bah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04100» and «05068» with a particle interposed; what (is) like (a) liberal (man)?; Maknadbai, an Israelite:--Machnadebai.', 'Machnadebai = \"he brought low my willing ones\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the sons of Bani who put away his foreign wife at Ezra\'s command</OL>'),
(4368, 'hnkm', 'the same as (04350)', 'Mkonah', 'None', 'mek-o-naw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «04350»; a base; Mekonah, a place in Palestine:--Mekonah.', 'Mekonah = \"foundation\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the towns which were reinhabited after the return from exile</OL>'),
(4369, 'hnkm', 'the same as (04350)', 'mkunah', 'TWOT - 964d', 'mek-oo-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'the same as «04350»; a spot:--base.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>resting place, base</OL>'),
(4370, 'onkm', 'from (03647) in the sense of hiding', 'miknac', 'TWOT - 1000a', 'mik-nawce\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03647» in the sense of hiding; (only in dual) drawers (from concealing the private parts):--breeches.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>underwear, drawers, trousers<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a priestly undergarment of linen</OL></OL>'),
(4371, 'okm', 'probably from an unused root meaning to enumerate', 'mekec', 'TWOT - 1014a', 'meh\'-kes', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from an unused root meaning to enumerate; an assessment (as based upon a census):--tribute.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>computation, proportion to be paid, tribute, tax</OL>'),
(4372, 'hokm', 'from (03680)', 'mikceh', 'TWOT - 1008c', 'mik-seh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03680»; a covering, i.e. weather-boarding:--covering.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a covering<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>covering (of the ark)<LI>covering (of the skins of the tabernacle)</OL></OL>'),
(4373, 'hokm', 'from (04371)', 'mikcah', 'TWOT - 1014b', 'mik-saw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «04371»; an enumeration; by implication, a valuation:--number, worth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>computation<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>number<LI>worth, valuation</OL></OL>'),
(4374, 'hookm', 'from (03680)', 'mkacceh', 'TWOT - 1008d', 'mek-as-seh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03680»; a covering, i.e. garment; specifically, a coverlet (for a bed), an awning (from the sun); also the omentum (as covering the intestines):--clothing, to cover, that which covereth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>covering, that which covers</OL>'),
(4375, 'hlpkm', 'from (03717)', 'Makpelah', 'TWOT - 1019b', 'mak-pay-law\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «03717»; a fold; Makpelah, a place in Palestine:--Machpelah.', 'Machpelah = \"double\" or \"portion\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the location of a burial cave for the patriarchs, near Hebron</OL>'),
(4376, 'rkm', 'a primitive root', 'makar', 'TWOT - 1194', 'maw-kar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to sell, literally (as merchandise, a daughter in marriage, into slavery), or figuratively (to surrender):--X at all, sell (away, -er, self).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sell<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sell<LI>seller (participle)</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be sold<LI>to sell oneself<LI>to be given over to death</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to sell oneself</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(4377, 'rkm', 'from (04376)', 'meker', 'TWOT - 1194a', 'meh\'-ker', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04376»; merchandise; also value:--pay, price, ware.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>merchandise, value, price</OL>'),
(4378, 'rkkm', 'from (05234)', 'makkar', 'TWOT - 1368f', 'mak-kawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05234»; an acquaintance:--acquaintance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>acquaintance, friend</OL>'),
(4379, 'hrkm', 'from (03738)', 'mikreh', 'TWOT - 1033b', 'mik-reh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03738»; a pit (for salt):--(salt-)pit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pit, salt pit<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning uncertain</OL></OL>'),
(4380, 'hrkm', 'probably from the same as (03564) in the sense of stabbing', 'mkerah', 'TWOT - 1194d', 'mek-ay-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'probably from the same as «03564» in the sense of stabbing; a sword:--habitation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>swords, weapons, devices<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(4381, 'yrkm', 'from (04376)', 'Mikriy', 'None', 'mik-ree\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04376»; salesman; Mikri, an Israelite:--Michri.', 'Michri = \"worthy of price\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ancestor of Elah, one of the heads of Benjamin</OL>'),
(4382, 'ytrkm', 'patrial from an unused name (the same as (04380)) of a place in Palestine', 'Mkerathiy', 'None', 'mek-ay-raw-thee\'', 'Adjective', 'patrial from an unused name (the same as «04380») of a place in Palestine: a Mekerathite, or inhabitant of Mekerah:-- Mecherathite.', 'Mecherathite = \"he of the dug-out\" or \"he of the digging tool\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a native or inhabitant of Mecherah</OL>'),
(4383, 'lwXkm', 'from (03782)', 'mikshowl', 'TWOT - 1050c', 'mik-shole\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or mikshol {mik-shole\'}; masculine from «03782»; a stumbling-block, literally or figuratively (obstacle, enticement (specifically an idol), scruple):--caused to fall, offence, × (no-)thing offered, ruin, stumbling-block.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a stumbling, means or occasion of stumbling, stumbling block<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>stumbling, fall<LI>means or occasion of stumbling, stumbling block</OL></OL>'),
(4384, 'hlXkm', 'from (03782)', 'makshelah', 'TWOT - 1050d', 'mak-shay-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from «03782»; a stumbling-block, but only figuratively (fall, enticement (idol)):--ruin, stumbling-block.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>overthrown mass, stumbling-block, something overthrown, decay, ruin<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>thing overthrown (figurative of kingdom)<LI>stumbling-block (of idols)</OL></OL>'),
(4385, 'btkm', 'from (03789)', 'miktab', 'TWOT - 1053c', 'mik-tawb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03789»; a thing written, the characters, or a document (letter, copy, edict, poem):--writing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>writing, thing written<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>handwriting<LI>thing written<LI>writing</OL></OL>'),
(4386, 'httkm', 'from (03807)', 'mkittah', 'TWOT - 1062b', 'mek-it-taw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03807»; a fracture:--bursting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>crushed or pulverised fragments</OL>'),
(4387, '~tkm', 'from (03799)', 'miktam', 'TWOT - 1056a', 'mik-tawm\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03799»; an engraving, i.e. (techn.) a poem:--Michtam.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>michtam<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a technical term found in psalm titles<LI>meaning uncertain</OL></OL>'),
(4388, 'Xtkm', 'from (03806)', 'maktesh', 'TWOT - 1061a', 'mak-taysh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03806»; a mortar; by analogy, a socket (of a tooth):--hollow place, mortar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mortar</OL>'),
(4389, 'Xtkm', 'the same as (04388)', 'Maktesh', 'None', 'mak-taysh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'the same as «04388»; dell; the Maktesh, a place in Jerusalem:--Maktesh.', 'Maktesh = \"a mortar\" or \"deep hollow\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a hollow or valley evidently in the greater Jerusalem area</OL>'),
(4390, 'alm', 'a primitive root', 'male\'', 'TWOT - 1195', 'maw-lay\'', 'Verb', 'or malae (Esth. 7:5) {maw-law\'}; a primitive root, to fill or (intransitively) be full of, in a wide application (literally and figuratively):--accomplish, confirm, + consecrate, be at an end, be expired, be fenced, fill, fulfil, (be, become, ×  draw, give in, go)  full(-ly, -ly set, tale), (over-)flow, fulness, furnish, gather (selves, together), presume, replenish, satisfy, set, space, take a (hand-)full, + have wholly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fill, be full<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be full 1a</OL><LI>fulness, abundance (participle) 1a<LI>to be full, be accomplished, be ended<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to consecrate, fill the hand</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be filled, be armed, be satisfied<LI>to be accomplished, be ended</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fill<LI>to satisfy<LI>to fulfil, accomplish, complete<LI>to confirm</OL><LI>(Pual) to be filled<LI>(Hithpael) to mass themselves against</OL></OL>'),
(4391, 'alm', 'corresponding to (04390)', 'mla\'', 'TWOT - 2826', 'mel-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «04390»; to fill:--fill, be full.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fill<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to fill<LI>(Ithp\'al) to be filled</OL></OL>'),
(4392, 'alm', 'from (04390)', 'male\'', 'TWOT - 1195a', 'maw-lay\'', 'Adjective', 'from «04390»; full (literally or figuratively) or filling (literally); also (concretely) fulness; adverbially, fully:--X she that was with child, fill(-ed, -ed with), full(-ly), multitude, as is worth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>full, fulness, that which fills<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>fully (adv)</OL></OL>'),
(4393, 'alm', 'from (04390)', 'mlo\'', 'TWOT - 1195b', 'mel-o\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'rarely mlowf {mel-o\'}; or mlow (Ezekiel 41:8), {mel-o\'}; from «04390»; fulness (literally or figuratively):--X all along, ×  all that is (there-)in, fill, (X that whereof...was) full, fulness, (hand- )full, multitude.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fulness, that which fills<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>fulness, handful<LI>mass, multitude<LI>fulness, that which fills, entire contents<LI>full length, full line</OL></OL>'),
(4394, 'allm', 'from (04390)', 'millu\'', 'TWOT - 1195e', 'mil-loo\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04390»; a fulfilling (only in plural), i.e. (literally) a setting (of gems), or (technically) consecration (also concretely, a dedicatory sacrifice):--consecration, be set.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>setting, installation<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>setting, stones for setting<LI>installation (of priests)</OL></OL>'),
(4395, 'halm', 'from (04392)', 'mle\'ah', 'TWOT - 1195c', 'mel-ay-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «04392»; something fulfilled, i.e. abundance (of produce):--(first of ripe) fruit, fulness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fulness, full produce</OL>'),
(4396, 'hallm', 'from (04394)', 'millu\'ah', 'TWOT - 1195d', 'mil-loo-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «04394»; a filling, i.e. setting (of gems):--inclosing, setting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>setting (of jewel)</OL>'),
(4397, '$alm', 'from an unused root meaning to despatch as a deputy', 'mal\'ak', 'TWOT - 1068a', 'mal-awk\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to despatch as a deputy; a messenger; specifically, of God, i.e. an angel (also a prophet, priest or teacher):--ambassador, angel, king, messenger.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>messenger, representative<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>messenger<LI>angel<LI>the theophanic angel</OL></OL>'),
(4398, '$alm', 'corresponding to (04397)', 'mal\'ak', 'TWOT - 2827', 'mal-ak\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «04397»; an angel:--angel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>angel</OL>'),
(4399, 'hkalm', 'from the same as (04397)', 'mla\'kah', 'TWOT - 1068b', 'mel-aw-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «04397»; properly, deputyship, i.e. ministry; generally, employment (never servile) or work (abstractly or concretely); also property (as the result of labor):--business, + cattle, + industrious, occupation, (+ -pied), + officer, thing (made), use, (manner of) work((-man), -manship).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>occupation, work, business<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>occupation, business<LI>property<LI>work (something done or made)<LI>workmanship<LI>service, use<LI>public business<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>political<LI>religious</OL></OL></OL>'),
(4400, 'twkalm', 'from the same as (04397)', 'mal\'akuwth', 'TWOT - 1068c', 'mal-ak-ooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «04397»; a message:--message.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>message</OL>'),
(4401, 'yk[lm', 'from the same as (04397)', 'Mal`akiy', 'None', 'mal-aw-kee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «04397»; ministrative; Malaki, a prophet:--Malachi.', 'Malachi = \"My messenger\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the prophet who wrote the last book of the Old Testament; nothing else is known</OL>'),
(4402, 'tallm', 'from (04390)', 'mille\'th', 'TWOT - 1195f', 'mil-layth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04390»; fulness, i.e. (concretely) a plump socket (of the eye):--X fitly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fulness, setting, border, rim<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(4403, 'Xwblm', 'from (03847)', 'malbuwsh', 'TWOT - 1075b', 'mal-boosh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or malbush {mal-boosh\'}; from «03847»; a garment, or (collectively) clothing:--apparel, raiment, vestment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>clothing, apparel, vestments, raiment, attire</OL>'),
(4404, '!blm', 'from (03835) (denominative)', 'malben', 'TWOT - 1074i', 'mal-bane\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03835» (denominative); a brick-kiln:--brickkiln.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>brick mold, brick kiln, quadrangle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>brick mould, brick kiln<LI>quadrangle</OL></OL>'),
(4405, 'hllm', 'from (04448) (as if from milleh) {mil-leh\'}', 'millah', 'TWOT - 1201a', 'mil-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04448» (plural masculine as if from milleh {mil-leh\'}; a word; collectively, a discourse; figuratively, a topic:--+ answer, by-word, matter, any thing (what) to say, to speak(-ing), speak, talking, word.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>word, speech, utterance</OL>'),
(4406, 'hllm', 'corresponding to (04405)', 'millah', 'TWOT - 2831a', 'mil-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «04405»; a word, command, discourse, or subject:--commandment, matter, thing. word.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>word, thing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>word, utterance, command<LI>thing, affair, matter</OL></OL>'),
(4407, 'awllm', 'from (04390)', 'millow\'', 'None', 'mil-lo\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or mil-loe (2 Kings 12:20) {mil-lo\'}; from «04390»; a rampart (as filled in), i.e. the citadel:--Millo. See also «01037».', 'Millo = \"rampart\" or \"mound\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place near Shechem; site unknown<LI>a part of the fortifications of Jerusalem</OL>'),
(4408, 'xwllm', 'from (04414)', 'malluwach', 'TWOT - 1197c', 'mal-loo\'-akh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04414»; sea-purslain (from its saltness):--mallows.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mallow<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a plant that grows in salt marshes</OL></OL>'),
(4409, '$wllm', 'from (04427)', 'Malluwk', 'None', 'mal-luke\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Malluwkiy (Neh. 12:14) {mal-loo-kee\'}; from «04427»; remnant; Malluk, the name of five Israelites:--Malluch, Melichu (from the margin).', 'Malluch or Melicu = \"counsellor\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Merarite Levite, son of Hashabiah<LI>a descendant of Bani who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>a descendant of Harim who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>a priest who signed the covenant with Nehemiah<LI>one of the leaders of the people who signed the covenant with Nehemiah<LI>a priest who returned from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(4410, 'hkwlm', 'pass. participle of (04427)', 'mluwkah', 'TWOT - 1199d', 'mel-oo-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine passive participle of «04427»; something ruled, i.e. a realm:--kingsom, king\'s, × royal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>kingship, royalty, kingly office</OL>'),
(4411, '!wlm', 'from (03885)', 'malown', 'TWOT - 1096a', 'maw-lone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03885»; a lodgment, i.e. caravanserai or encampment:--inn, place where...lodge, lodging (place).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>place of lodging, inn, khan</OL>'),
(4412, 'hnwlm', 'from (03885)', 'mluwnah', 'TWOT - 1096b', 'mel-oo-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from «03885»; a hut, a hammock:--cottage, lodge.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lodge, hut</OL>'),
(4413, 'ytwllm', 'apparently from (04448)', 'Mallowthiy', 'None', 'mal-lo\'-thee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'apparently from «04448»; I have talked (i.e. loquacious):--Mallothi, an Israelite:--Mallothi.', 'Mallothi = \"I have uttered\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 14 sons of Heman, the singer in the time of David</OL>'),
(4414, 'xlm', 'a primitive root', 'malach', 'TWOT - 1196,1197', 'maw-lakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to rub to pieces or pulverize; intransitively, to disappear as dust; also (as denominative from «04417») to salt whether internally (to season with salt) or externally (to rub with salt):--X at all, salt, season, temper together, vanish away.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tear away, dissipate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be dispersed, be dissipated</OL><LI>to salt, season<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to salt, season<LI>(Pual) to be salted<LI>(Hophal) to be rubbed or washed with salt</OL></OL>'),
(4415, 'xlm', 'corresponding to (04414)', 'mlach', 'TWOT - 2828', 'mel-akh\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «04414»; to eat salt, i.e. (generally) subsist:--+ have maintenance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to eat salt</OL>'),
(4416, 'xlm', 'from (04415)', 'mlach', 'TWOT - 2828a', 'mel-akh\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «04415»; salt:--+ maintenance, salt.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>salt</OL>'),
(4417, 'xlm', 'from (04414)', 'melach', 'TWOT - 1197a', 'meh\'-lakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04414»; properly, powder, i.e. (specifically) salt (as easily pulverized and dissolved:--salt((-pit)).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>salt</OL>'),
(4418, 'xlm', 'from (04414) in its original sense', 'malach', 'TWOT - 1196a', 'maw-lawkh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04414» in its original sense; a rag or old garment:--rotten rag.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rag</OL>'),
(4419, 'xllm', 'from (04414) in its second. sense', 'mallach', 'TWOT - 1197d', 'mal-lawkh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04414» in its second. sense; a sailor (as following \"the salt\"):--mariner.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mariner, sailor, seaman</OL>'),
(4420, 'hxlm', 'from (04414) (in its denominative sense)', 'mlechah', 'TWOT - 1197b', 'mel-ay-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04414» (in its denominative sense); properly, salted (i.e. land (776 being understood)), i.e. a desert:--barren land(-ness), salt (land).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>saltness, barrenness, saltiness</OL>'),
(4421, 'hmxlm', 'from (03898) (in the sense of fighting)', 'milchamah', 'TWOT - 1104c', 'mil-khaw-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03898» (in the sense of fighting); a battle (i.e. the engagement); generally, war (i.e. warfare):--battle, fight(-ing), war((-rior)).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>battle, war</OL>'),
(4422, 'tlm', 'a primitive root', 'malat', 'TWOT - 1198', 'maw-lat\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to be smooth, i.e. (by implication) to escape (as if by slipperiness); causatively, to release or rescue; specifically, to bring forth young, emit sparks:--deliver (self), escape, lay, leap out, let alone, let go, preserve, save, × speedily, × surely.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to slip away, escape, deliver, save, be delivered<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to slip away<LI>to escape<LI>to be delivered</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lay, let slip out (of eggs)<LI>to let escape<LI>to deliver, save (life)</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give birth to<LI>to deliver</OL><LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to slip forth, slip out, escape<LI>to escape</OL></OL></OL>'),
(4423, 'tlm', 'from (04422)', 'melet', 'TWOT - 1198a', 'meh\'-let', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04422», cement (from its plastic smoothness):--clay.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mortar, cement, clay (flooring)</OL>'),
(4424, 'hytlm', 'from (04423) and (03050)', 'Mlatyah', 'None', 'mel-at-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04423» and «03050»; (whom) Jah has delivered; Melatjah, a Gibeonite:--Melatiah.', 'Melatiah = \"Jehovah delivered\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Gibeonite who assisted in rebuilding the wall of Jerusalem</OL>'),
(4425, 'hlylm', 'from (04449) (in the sense of cropping [compare (04135)])', 'mliylah', 'TWOT - 1202a', 'mel-ee-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04449» (in the sense of cropping (compare «04135»)); a head of grain (as cut off):--ear.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ear (of wheat), head (of wheat)</OL>'),
(4426, 'hcylm', 'from (03887)', 'mliytsah', 'TWOT - 1113b', 'mel-ee-tsaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03887»; an aphorism; also a satire:--interpretation, taunting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>satire, mocking poem, mocking song, taunting, figure, enigma</OL>'),
(4427, '$lm', 'a primitive root', 'malak', 'TWOT - 1199,1200', 'maw-lak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to reign; inceptively, to ascend the throne; causatively, to induct into royalty; hence (by implication) to take counsel:--consult, × indeed, be (make, set a, set up) king, be (make) queen, (begin to, make to) reign(-ing), rule, × surely.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or become king or queen, reign<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be or become king or queen, reign<LI>(Hiphil) to make one king or queen, cause to reign<LI>(Hophal) to be made king or queen</OL><LI>to counsel, advise<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to consider</OL></OL>'),
(4428, '$lm', 'from (04427)', 'melek', 'TWOT - 1199a', 'meh\'-lek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04427»; a king:--king, royal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>king</OL>'),
(4429, '$lm', 'the same as (04428)', 'Melek', 'None', 'meh\'-lek', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «04428»; king; Melek, the name of two Israelites:--Melech, Hammelech (by including the article).', 'Melech = \"king\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, the 2nd son of Micah and grandson of Mephibosheth</OL>'),
(4430, '$lm', 'corresponding to (04428)', 'melek', 'TWOT - 2829a', 'meh\'-lek', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «04428»; a king:--king, royal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>king</OL>'),
(4431, '$lm', 'from a root corresponding to (04427) in the sense of consultation', 'mlak', 'TWOT - 2830a', 'mel-ak\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «04427» in the sense of consultation: advice:--counsel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>counsel, advice</OL>'),
(4432, '$lm', 'from (04427)', 'Molek', 'TWOT - 1199h', 'mo\'-lek', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04427»; Molek (i.e. king), the chief deity of the Ammonites:--Molech. Compare «04445».', 'Molech = \"king\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the god of the Ammonites and Phoenicians to whom some Israelites sacrificed their infants in the valley of Hinnom</OL>'),
(4433, 'aklm', 'corresponding to (04436)', 'malka\'', 'TWOT - 2829b', 'mal-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «04436»; a queen:--queen.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>queen</OL>'),
(4434, 'tdklm', 'from (03920)', 'malkodeth', 'TWOT - 1115b', 'mal-ko\'-deth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03920»; a snare:--trap.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a catching instrument, snare, trap</OL>'),
(4435, 'hklm', 'a form of (04436)', 'Milkah', 'None', 'mil-kaw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'a form of «04436»; queen; Milcah, the name of a Hebrewess and of an Israelite:--Milcah.', 'Milcah = \"queen\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>daughter of Haran and wife of Nahor, her uncle and Abraham\'s brother, to whom she bore 8 children<LI>a daughter of Zelophehad and granddaughter of Manasseh</OL>'),
(4436, 'hklm', 'from (04428)', 'malkah', 'TWOT - 1199b', 'mal-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «04428»; a queen:--queen.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>queen</OL>'),
(4437, 'wklm', 'corresponding to (04438)', 'malkuw', 'TWOT - 2829c', 'mal-koo\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «04438»; dominion (abstractly or concretely):--kingdom, kingly, realm, reign.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>royalty, reign, kingdom<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>royalty, kingship, kingly authority<LI>kingdom<LI>realm (of territory)<LI>reign (of time)</OL></OL>'),
(4438, 'twklm', 'from (04427)', 'malkuwth', 'TWOT - 1199e', 'mal-kooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or malkuth {mal-kooth\'}; or (in plural) malkuyah {mal-koo-yah\'}; from «04427»; a rule; concretely, a dominion:--empire, kingdom, realm, reign, royal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>royalty, royal power, reign, kingdom, sovereign power<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>royal power, dominion<LI>reign<LI>kingdom, realm</OL></OL>'),
(4439, 'layklm', 'from (04428) and (0410)', 'Malkiy\'el', 'None', 'mal-kee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04428» and «0410»; king of (i.e. appointed by) God; Malkiel, an Israelite:--Malchiel.', 'Malchiel = \"my king is God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of Beriah and grandson of Asher</OL>'),
(4440, 'ylayklm', 'patronymical from (04439)', 'Malkiy\'eliy', 'None', 'mal-kee-ay-lee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymical from «04439»; a Malkielite or descendant of Malkiel:--Malchielite.', 'Malchielites = Malchiel \"my king is God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Asherite and a descendant of Malchiel, the grandson of Asher</OL>'),
(4441, 'hyklm', 'from (04428) and (03050)', 'Malkiyah', 'None', 'mal-kee-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Malkiyahuw (Jer. 38:6),  {mal-kee-yaw\'-hoo}; from «04428» and «03050»; king of (i.e. appointed by) Jah; Malkijah, the name of ten Israelites:--Malchiah, Malchijah.', 'Malchijah or Malchiah = \"my king is Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the father of Pashur in the time of Jeremiah<LI>the son of Hammelech into whose dungeon Jeremiah was cast<LI>the head of the 5th course of priests in the time of David<LI>one of the priests who was at the reading of the law by Ezra, sealed the covenant with Nehemiah, and was at the dedication of the wall with Nehemiah<LI>a Levite ancestor of Asaph and descendant of Levi through Gershon<LI>son of Parosh who put away a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>son of Harim who put away a foreign wife and helped repair the wall and the Tower of Ovens in the time of Ezra and Nehemiah<LI>son of Rechab, leader of the district of Beth Haccerem, who helped repair the Refuse Gate in the time of Nehemiah<LI>a goldsmith who helped repair the wall in the time of Nehemiah</OL>'),
(4442, 'qdcyklm', 'from (04428) and (06664)', 'Malkiy-Tsedeq', 'TWOT - 1199i', 'mal-kee-tseh\'-dek', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04428» and «06664»; king of right; Malki-Tsedek, an early king in Palestine:--Melchizedek.', 'Melchizedek = \"my king is Sedek\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>king of Salem and priest of the Most High God to whom Abram paid tithe after the battle he fought to free Lot; \'the order of Melchizedek\' the order of the priesthood to which Christ belongs</OL>'),
(4443, '~ryklm', 'from (04428) and (07311)', 'Malkiyram', 'None', 'mal-kee-rawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04428» and «07311»; king of a high one (i.e. of exaltation); Malkiram, an Israelite:--Malchiram.', 'Malchiram = \"my king is high\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of king Jehoiachin of Judah</OL>'),
(4444, '[wXyklm', 'from (04428) and (07769)', 'Malkiyshuwa`', 'None', 'mal-kee-shoo\'-ah', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04428» and «07769»; king of wealth; Malkishua, an Israelite:--Malchishua.', 'Malchishua = \"my king is wealth\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of king Saul of Israel</OL>'),
(4445, '~klm', 'from (04428) for (04432)', 'Malkam', 'None', 'mal-kawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Milkowm {mil-kome\'}; from «04428» for «04432»; Malcam or Milcom, the national idol of the Ammonites:--Malcham, Milcom.', 'Milcom = \"great king\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the god of the Ammonites and Phoenicians to whom some Israelites sacrificed their infants in the valley of Hinnom<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Molech\'</OL><LI>a Benjamite, son of Shaharaim by his wife Hodesh</OL>'),
(4446, 'tklm', 'from (04427)', 'mleketh', 'TWOT - 1199c', 'mel-eh\'-keth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04427»; a queen:--queen.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>queen</OL>'),
(4447, 'tklm', 'act. participle of (04427)', 'Moleketh', 'None', 'mo-leh\'-keth', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'feminine active participle of «04427»; queen; Moleketh, an Israelitess:--Hammoleketh (including the article).', 'Hammoleketh = \"the queen\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>daughter of Machir and sister of Gilead</OL>'),
(4448, 'llm', 'a primitive root', 'malal', 'TWOT - 1201', 'maw-lal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to speak (mostly poetical) or say:--say, speak, utter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to speak, utter, say<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to speak<LI>(Piel) to say, utter</OL></OL>'),
(4449, 'llm', 'corresponding to (04448)', 'mlal', 'TWOT - 2831', 'mel-al\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «04448»; to speak:--say, speak(-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Pael) to speak, say</OL>'),
(4450, 'yllm', 'from (04448)', 'Milalay', 'None', 'mee-lal-ah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04448»; talkative; Milalai, an Israelite:--Milalai.', 'Milalai = \"eloquent\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of the priest Jonathan and a descendant of Asaph</OL>'),
(4451, 'dmlm', 'from (03925)', 'malmad', 'TWOT - 1116b', 'mal-mawd\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03925»; a goad for oxen:--goad.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ox goad</OL>'),
(4452, '#lm', 'a primitive root', 'malats', 'TWOT - 1205', 'maw-lats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be smooth, i.e. (figuratively) pleasant:--be sweet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be smooth, be slippery<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be smooth (agreeable, pleasant)</OL></OL>'),
(4453, 'rclm', 'of Persian derivation', 'meltsar', 'TWOT - 1206', 'mel-tsawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Persian derivation; the butler or other officer in the Babylonian court:--Melzar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>guardian, an officer of the court<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(4454, 'qlm', 'a primitive root', 'malaq', 'TWOT - 1207', 'maw-lak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to crack a joint; by implication, to wring the neck of a fowl (without separating it):--wring off.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to nip, nip off (head of a bird)</OL>'),
(4455, 'xwqlm', 'from (03947)', 'malqowach', 'TWOT - 1124b,1124c', 'mal-ko\'-akh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03947»; transitively (in dual) the jaws (as taking food); intransitively, spoil (and captives) (as taken):--booty, jaws, prey.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>booty, prey<LI>jaw</OL>'),
(4456, 'Xwqlm', 'from (03953)', 'malqowsh', 'TWOT - 1127b', 'mal-koshe\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03953»; the spring rain (compare «03954»); figuratively, eloquence:--latter rain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>latter rain, spring rain<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the March and April rains which mature the crops of Palestine</OL></OL>'),
(4457, 'xqlm', 'from (03947)', 'melqach', 'TWOT - 1124d', 'mel-kawkh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or malqach {mal-kawkh\'}; from «03947»; (only in dual) tweezers:--snuffers, tongs.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>snuffers, tongs<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>tongs (for altar use)<LI>snuffers (for lamps in temple or tabernacle)</OL></OL>'),
(4458, 'hxtlm', 'from an unused root meaning to spread out', 'meltachah', 'TWOT - 1132a', 'mel-taw-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning to spread out; a wardrobe (i.e. room where clothing is spread):--vestry.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wardrobe, wearing apparel, vestment</OL>'),
(4459, 'h[tlm', 'transp. for (04973)', 'malta`ah', 'TWOT - 2516d', 'mal-taw-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'transp. for «04973»; a grinder, i.e. back tooth:--great tooth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>tooth, great tooth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>teeth, incisors</OL></OL>'),
(4460, 'hrgmmm', 'from (04048) (in the sense of depositing)', 'mammgurah', 'TWOT - 330e', 'mam-meg-oo-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04048» (in the sense of depositing); a granary:--barn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>granary, storehouse</OL>'),
(4461, 'dmm', 'from (04058)', 'memad', 'TWOT - 1146c', 'may-mad\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04058»; a measure:--measure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>measurement</OL>'),
(4462, '!kwmm', 'of Persian derivation', 'Mmuwkan', 'None', 'mem-oo-kawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or (transp.) Mowmukan (Esth. 1:16)  {mo-moo-kawn\'}; of Persian derivation; Memucan or Momucan, a Persian satrap:--Memucan.', 'Memucan = \"dignified\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 7 princes of Persia in the reign of Ahasuerus</OL>'),
(4463, 'twmm', 'from (04191)', 'mamowth', 'TWOT - 1169b', 'maw-mothe\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04191»; a mortal disease; concretely, a corpse:--death.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>death</OL>'),
(4464, 'rzmm', 'from an unused root meaning to alienate', 'mamzer', 'TWOT - 1174a', 'mam-zare\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to alienate; a mongrel, i.e. born of a Jewish father and a heathen mother:--bastard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bastard, child of incest, illegitimate child<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>bastard<LI>mixed population (fig.)<LI>born of a Jewish father and a heathen mother or visa versa</OL></OL>'),
(4465, 'rkmm', 'from (04376)', 'mimkar', 'TWOT - 1194b', 'mim-kawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04376»; merchandise; abstractly, a selling:--X ought, (that which cometh of) sale, that which...sold, ware.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sale, ware, thing sold</OL>'),
(4466, 'trkmm', 'from (04465)', 'mimkereth', 'TWOT - 1194c', 'mim-keh\'-reth', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «04465»; a sale:--+ sold as.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sale</OL>'),
(4467, 'hklmm', 'from (04427)', 'mamlakah', 'TWOT - 1199f', 'mam-law-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04427»; dominion, i.e. (abstractly) the estate (rule) or (concretely) the country (realm):--kingdom, king\'s, reign, royal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>kingdom, dominion, reign, sovereignty<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>kingdom, realm<LI>sovereignty, dominion<LI>reign</OL></OL>'),
(4468, 'twklmm', 'a form of (04467) and equiv. to it', 'mamlakuwth', 'TWOT - 1199g', 'mam-law-kooth\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'a form of «04467» and equiv. to it:--kingdom, reign.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>kingdom, dominion, reign, sovereignty<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>kingdom<LI>dominion, royal power<LI>reign</OL></OL>'),
(4469, '$omm', 'from (04537)', 'mamcak', 'TWOT - 1220b', 'mam-sawk\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04537»; mixture, i.e. (specifically) wine mixed (with water or spices):--drink-offering, mixed wine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mixed drink, mixed wine, drink-offering</OL>'),
(4470, 'rmm', 'from an unused root meaning to grieve', 'memer', 'TWOT - 1248j', 'meh\'-mer', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to grieve; sorrow:--bitterness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bitterness</OL>'),
(4471, 'armm', 'from (04754)(in the sense of vigour)', 'Mamre\'', 'TWOT - 1208', 'mam-ray\'', '', 'from 4754(in the sense of vigor); lusty; Mamre, an Amorite:--Mamre.', 'Mamre = \"strength\" or \"fatness\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Amorite who allied himself with Abram n pr loc<LI>an oak grove on Mamre\'s land in Palestine where Abraham dwelt<LI>a place near Abraham\'s burial place, apparently identified with Hebron</OL>'),
(4472, 'rrmm', 'from (04843)', 'mamror', 'TWOT - 1248k', 'mam-rore\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04843»; a bitterness, i.e. (figuratively) calamity:--bitterness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bitter thing, bitterness</OL>'),
(4473, 'xXmm', 'from (04886), in the sense of expansion', 'mimshach', 'TWOT - 1255d', 'mim-shakh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04886», in the sense of expansion; outspread (i.e. with outstretched wings):--anointed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>anointed, expansion<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning uncertain</OL></OL>'),
(4474, 'lXmm', 'from (04910)', 'mimshal', 'TWOT - 1259b', 'mim-shawl\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04910»; a ruler or (abstractly) rule:--dominion, that ruled.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dominion, ruler<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>dominion<LI>ruler</OL></OL>'),
(4475, 'hlXmm', 'from (04474)', 'memshalah', 'TWOT - 1259c', 'mem-shaw-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «04474»; rule; also (concretely in plural) a realm or a ruler:--dominion, government, power, to rule.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rule, dominion, realm<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>rule, dominion, realm, domain<LI>rule<LI>rule, dominion (of God)</OL></OL>'),
(4476, 'qXmm', 'from the same as (04943)', 'mimshaq', 'TWOT - 1261b', 'mim-shawk\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «04943»; a possession:--breeding.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>possession, place possessed</OL>'),
(4477, 'qtmm', 'from (04985)', 'mamtaq', 'TWOT - 1268d', 'mam-tak\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04985»; something sweet (literally or figuratively):--(most) sweet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sweetness, sweet thing</OL>'),
(4478, '!m', 'from (04100)', 'man', 'TWOT - 1208,1209', 'mawn', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04100»; literally, a whatness (so to speak), i.e. manna (so called from the question about it):--manna.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>manna<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the bread from Heaven that fed the Israelites for 40 years of wilderness wanderings<LI>means \'What is it?\'</OL></OL>'),
(4479, '!m', 'from (04101)', 'man', 'TWOT - 2832', 'mawn', '', '(Aramaic) from «04101»; who or what (properly, interrogatively, hence, also indefinitely and relatively):--what, who(-msoever, + -so).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>who?, what?, whoever, whosoever</OL>'),
(4480, '!m', 'from (04482)', 'min', 'TWOT - 1212,1213e', 'min', '', 'or minniy {min-nee\'}; or minney (constructive plural) {min-nay\'}; (Isaiah 30:11); for «04482»; properly, a part of; hence (prepositionally), from or out of in many senses (as follows):--above, after, among, at, because of, by (reason of), from (among), in, × neither, × nor, (out) of, over, since, × then, through, × whether, with.', 'prep<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>from, out of, on account of, off, on the side of, since, above, than, so that not, more than<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>from (expressing separation), off, on the side of<LI>out of<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(with verbs of proceeding, removing, expelling)<LI>(of material from which something is made)<LI>(of source or origin)</OL><LI>out of, some of, from (partitively)<LI>from, since, after (of time)<LI>than, more than (in comparison)<LI>from...even to, both...and, either...or<LI>than, more than, too much for (in comparisons)<LI>from, on account of, through, because (with infinitive) conj</OL><LI>that</OL>'),
(4481, '!m', 'corresponding to (04480)', 'min', 'TWOT - 2833', 'min', 'Preposition', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «04480»:--according, after, + because, + before, by, for, from, × him, × more than, (out) of, part, since, × these, to, upon, + when.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>from, out of, by, by reason of, at, more than<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>from, out of (of place)<LI>from, by, as a result of, by reason of, at, according to, (of source)<LI>from (of time)<LI>beyond, more than (in comparisons)</OL></OL>'),
(4482, '!m', 'from an unused root meaning to apportion', 'men', 'TWOT - 1211', 'mane', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to apportion; a part; hence, a musical chord (as parted into strings):--in (the same) (Psalm 68:23), stringed instrument (Psalm 150:4), whereby (Psalm 45:8 (defective plural)).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>string (of harp)<LI>(BDB) portion</OL>'),
(4483, 'anm', 'corresponding to (04487)', 'mna\'', 'TWOT - 2835', 'men-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) or mnah (Aramaic) {men-aw\'}; corresponding to «04487»; to count, appoint:--number, ordain, set.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to number, reckon<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to number<LI>(Pael) to appoint</OL></OL>'),
(4484, 'anm', 'pass. participle of (04483)', 'mene\'', 'TWOT - 2835a', 'men-ay\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) passive participle of «04483»; numbered:--Mene.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) mina, maneh<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a weight or measurement; usually 50 shekels but maybe 60 shekels</OL></OL>'),
(4485, 'hnygnm', 'from (05059)', 'mangiynah', 'TWOT - 1291.1b', 'man-ghee-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05059»; a satire:--music.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mocking or derisive song</OL>'),
(4486, '[dnm', 'corresponding to (04093)', 'manda`', 'TWOT - 2765a,2834', 'man-dah\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «04093»; wisdom or intelligence:--knowledge, reason, understanding.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>knowledge, power of knowing</OL>'),
(4487, 'hnm', 'a primitive root', 'manah', 'TWOT - 1213', 'maw-naw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to weigh out; by implication, to allot or constitute officially; also to enumerate or enroll:--appoint, count, number, prepare, set, tell.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to count, reckon, number, assign, tell, appoint, prepare<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to count, number<LI>reckon, assign, appoint</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be counted, be numbered<LI>to be reckoned, be assigned</OL><LI>(Piel) to appoint, ordain<LI>(Pual) appointed (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(4488, 'hnm', 'from (04487)', 'maneh', 'TWOT - 1213b', 'maw-neh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04487»; properly, a fixed weight or measured amount, i.e. (techn.) a maneh or mina:--maneh, pound.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>maneh, mina, pound<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>60 shekels and 1/50 talent (of silver)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>1/60 talent in early Babylonian standard</OL><LI>100 shekels and 1/100 talent (of gold)</OL></OL>'),
(4489, 'hnm', 'from (04487)', 'moneh', 'TWOT - 1213c', 'mo-neh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04487»; properly, something weighed out, i.e. (figuratively) a portion of time, i.e. an instance:--time.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>something weighed out, counted number, time</OL>'),
(4490, 'hnm', 'from (04487)', 'manah', 'TWOT - 1213a', 'maw-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04487»; properly, something weighed out, i.e. (generally) a division; specifically (of food) a ration; also a lot:--such things as belonged, part, portion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>part, portion</OL>'),
(4491, 'ghnm', 'from (05090)', 'minhag', 'TWOT - 1309a', 'min-hawg\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05090»; the driving (of a chariot):--driving.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>driving, charioteering</OL>'),
(4492, 'hrhnm', 'from (05102)', 'minharah', 'TWOT - 1316b', 'min-haw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05102»; properly, a channel or fissure, i.e. (by implication) a cavern:--den.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>crevices, ravines, mountain clefts, den, dugout holes<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(4493, 'dwnm', 'from (05110) a nodding or toss (of the head in derision)', 'manowd', 'TWOT - 1319c', 'maw-node\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05110» a nodding or toss (of the head in derision):--shaking.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shaking, wagging</OL>'),
(4494, 'xwnm', 'from (05117)', 'manowach', 'TWOT - 1323e', 'maw-no\'-akh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05117»; quiet, i.e. (concretely) a settled spot, or (figuratively) a home:--(place of) rest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>resting place, state or condition of rest, place<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>resting place<LI>rest, repose, condition of rest<LI>coming to rest</OL></OL>'),
(4495, 'xwnm', 'the same as (04494)', 'Manowach', 'None', 'maw-no\'-akh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «04494»; rest; Manoach, an Israelite:--Manoah.', 'Manoah = \"rest\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Danite, father of the judge Samson and inhabitant of Zorah</OL>'),
(4496, 'hxwnm', 'from (04495)', 'mnuwchah', 'TWOT - 1323f', 'men-oo-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or mnuchah {men-oo-khaw\'}; feminine of «04495»; repose or (adverbially) peacefully; figuratively, consolation (specifically, matrimony); hence (concretely) an abode:--comfortable, ease, quiet, rest(-ing place), still.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>resting place, rest<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>resting place<LI>rest, quietness</OL></OL>'),
(4497, '!wnm', 'from (05125)', 'manown', 'TWOT - 1213f', 'maw-nohn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05125»; a continuator, i.e. heir:--son.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>grief, progeny, thankless one<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning uncertain</OL></OL>'),
(4498, 'ownm', 'from (05127)', 'manowc', 'TWOT - 1327a', 'maw-noce\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05127»; a retreat (literally or figuratively); abstractly, a fleeing:--X apace, escape, way to flee, flight, refuge.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flight, refuge, place of escape<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>flight<LI>refuge, place of escape</OL></OL>'),
(4499, 'hownm', 'from (04498)', 'mnuwcah', 'TWOT - 1327b', 'men-oo-saw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or mnucah {men-oo-saw\'}; feminine of «04498»; retreat:--fleeing, flight.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flight, retreat</OL>'),
(4500, 'rwnm', 'from (05214)', 'manowr', 'TWOT - 1361a', 'maw-nore\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05214»; a yoke (properly, for plowing), i.e. the frame of a loom:--beam.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>beam<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>beam (carrying the heddles in a loom)</OL></OL>'),
(4501, 'hrwnm', 'from (04500) (in the original sense of (5216))', 'mnowrah', 'TWOT - 1333c', 'men-o-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or mnorah {men-o-raw\'}; feminine of «04500» (in the original sense of «05216»); a chandelier:--candlestick.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lamp stand</OL>'),
(4502, 'rznnm', 'from (05144)', 'minnzar', 'TWOT - 1340d', 'min-ez-awr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05144»; a prince:--crowned.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>princes, anointed ones, consecrated ones<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(4503, 'hxnm', 'from an unused root meaning to apportion, i.e. bestow', 'minchah', 'TWOT - 1214a', 'min-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning to apportion, i.e. bestow; a donation; euphemistically, tribute; specifically a sacrificial offering (usually bloodless and voluntary):--gift, oblation, (meat) offering, present, sacrifice.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gift, tribute, offering, present, oblation, sacrifice, meat offering<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>gift, present<LI>tribute<LI>offering (to God)<LI>grain offering</OL></OL>'),
(4504, 'hxnm', 'corresponding to (04503)', 'minchah', 'TWOT - 2836', 'min-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «04503»; a sacrificial offering:--oblation, meat offering.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gift, offering<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>oblation, offering (to God through representative)<LI>meal offering</OL></OL>'),
(4505, '~xnm', 'from (05162)', 'Mnachem', 'None', 'men-akh-ame\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05162»; comforter; Menachem, an Israelite:--Menahem.', 'Menahem = \"comforter\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Gadi and king of the northern kingdom of Israel; slew the usurper Shallum to ascend the throne and reigned for ten years; contemporary with prophets Hosea and Amos</OL>'),
(4506, 'txnm', 'from (05117)', 'Manachath', 'None', 'maw-nakh\'-ath', '', 'from «05117»; rest; Manachath, the name of an Edomite and of a place in Moab:--Manahath.', 'Manahath = \"rest\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Shobal and a descendant of Seir the Horite n pr loc<LI>a place in Benjamin; site unknown</OL>'),
(4507, 'ynm', 'from (04487)', 'Mniy', 'None', 'men-ee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04487»; the Apportioner, i.e. Fate (as an idol):--number.', 'Meni = \"fate\" or \"fortune\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>god of fate who the Jews worshipped in Babylonia</OL>'),
(4508, 'ynnm', 'of foreign derivation', 'Minniy', 'None', 'min-nee\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'of foreign derivation; Minni, an Armenian province:--Minni.', 'Minni = \"division\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a region in Armenia</OL>'),
(4509, '!ymynm', 'from (04480) and (03225)', 'Minyamiyn', 'None', 'min-yaw-meen\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04480» and «03225»; from (the) right hand; Minjamin, the name of two Israelites:--Miniamin. Compare «04326».', 'Miniamin = \"from the right hand\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite in the time of Hezekiah<LI>a priest who was present at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem in the time of Nehemiah</OL>'),
(4510, '!ynm', 'from (04483)', 'minyan', 'TWOT - 2835b', 'min-yawn\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «04483»; enumeration:--number.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>number</OL>'),
(4511, 'tynnm', 'from the same as (04482)', 'Minniyth', 'None', 'min-neeth\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the same as «04482»; enumeration; Minnith, a place East of the Jordan:--Minnith.', 'Minnith = \"distribution\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place east of the Jordan in Ammonite territory; site unknown</OL>'),
(4512, 'hlnm', 'from (05239)', 'minleh', 'TWOT - 1370a', 'min-leh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05239»; completion, i.e. (in produce) wealth:--perfection.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gain, wealth, acquisition<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(4513, '[nm', 'a primitive root', 'mana`', 'TWOT - 1216', 'maw-nah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to debar (negatively or positively) from benefit or injury:--deny, keep (back), refrain, restrain, withhold.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to withhold, hold back, keep back, refrain, deny, keep restrain, hinder<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to withhold<LI>(Niphal) to be withheld</OL></OL>'),
(4514, 'lw[nm', 'from (05274)', 'man`uwl', 'TWOT - 1383c', 'man-ool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or maniul {man-ool\'}; from «05274»; a bolt:--lock.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bolt</OL>'),
(4515, 'l[nm', 'from (05274)', 'man`al', 'TWOT - 1383d', 'man-awl\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05274»; a bolt:--shoe.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shoe</OL>'),
(4516, '~[nm', 'from (05276)', 'man`am', 'TWOT - 1384d', 'man-am\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05276»; a delicacy:--dainty.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>delicacies, dainties</OL>'),
(4517, '[n[nm', 'from (05128)', 'mna`na`', 'TWOT - 1328a', 'men-ah-ah\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05128»; a sistrum (so called from its rattling sound):--cornet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a kind of rattle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a kind of rattle used as a musical instrument</OL></OL>'),
(4518, 'tyqqnm', 'from (05352)', 'mnaqqiyth', 'TWOT - 1412d', 'men-ak-keeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05352»; a sacrificial basin (for holding blood):--bowl.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sacrificial bowl or cup</OL>'),
(4519, 'hXXnm', 'from (05382)', 'Mnashsheh', 'TWOT - 1217', 'men-ash-sheh\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05382»; causing to forget; Menashsheh, a grandson of Jacob, also the tribe descended from him, and its territory:--Manasseh.', 'Manasseh = \"causing to forget\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the eldest son of Joseph and progenitor of the tribe of Manasseh<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the tribe descended from Manasseh<LI>the territory occupied by the tribe of Manasseh</OL><LI>son of king Hezekiah of Judah and himself king of Judah; he was the immediate and direct cause for the exile<LI>a descendant of Pahath-moab who put away a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>a descendant of Hashum who put away a foreign wife in the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(4520, 'yXXnm', 'from (04519)', 'Mnashshiy', 'None', 'men-ash-shee\'', 'Adjective', 'from «04519»; a Menashshite or descendant of Menashsheh:--of Manasseh, Manassites.', 'Manassites = Manasseh \"causing to forget\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Manasseh, son of Joseph and grandson of Jacob<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>specifically used only of that half that lived east of the Jordan</OL></OL>'),
(4521, 'tnm', 'from (04487)', 'mnath', 'TWOT - 1213d', 'men-awth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04487»; an allotment (by courtesy, law or providence):--portion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>portion</OL>'),
(4522, 'om', 'from (04549)', 'mac', 'TWOT - 1218', 'mas', 'Noun Masculine', 'or mic {mees}; from «04549»; properly, a burden (as causing to faint), i.e. a tax in the form of forced labor:--discomfited, levy, task(-master), tribute(-tary).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gang or body of forced labourers, task-workers, labour band or gang, forced service, task-work, serfdom, tributary, tribute, levy, taskmasters, discomfited<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>labour-band, labour-gang, slave gang<LI>gang-overseers<LI>forced service, serfdom, tribute, enforced payment</OL></OL>'),
(4523, 'om', 'from (04549)', 'mac', 'TWOT - 1223a', 'mawce', 'Adjective', 'from «04549»; fainting, i.e. (figuratively) disconsolate:--is afflicted.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>despairing</OL>'),
(4524, 'bom', 'from (05437)', 'mecab', 'TWOT - 1456c', 'may-sab\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'plural masculine mcibbiym {mes-ib-beem\'}; or feminine mcibbowth {mes-ib-bohth\'}; from «05437»; a divan (as enclosing the room); abstractly (adverbial) around:--that compass about, (place) round about, at table.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>round thing, surroundings, round about, that which surrounds, that which is round<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>environs<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>surrounding places<LI>round about (adv)</OL><LI>round table</OL></OL>'),
(4525, 'rgom', 'from (05462)', 'macger', 'TWOT - 1462c', 'mas-gare\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05462»; a fastener, i.e. (of a person) a smith, (of a thing) a prison:--prison, smith.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a shutting up, locksmith, smith, dungeon, enclosure, builder of bulwarks<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>locksmith, smith<LI>dungeon</OL></OL>'),
(4526, 'trgom', 'from (05462)', 'micgereth', 'TWOT - 1462d', 'mis-gheh\'-reth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05462»; something enclosing, i.e. a margin (of a region, of a panel); concretely, a stronghold:--border, close place, hole.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>border, fastness, rim<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>border, rim<LI>fastness</OL></OL>'),
(4527, 'doom', 'from (03245)', 'maccad', 'TWOT - 875g', 'mas-sad\'', '', 'from «03245»; a foundation:--foundation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>foundation</OL>'),
(4528, '!wrdom', 'from the same as (05468)', 'micdrown', 'TWOT - 1467c', 'mis-der-ohn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «05468»; a colonnade or internal portico (from its rows of pillars):--porch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>porch, colonnade<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(4529, 'hom', 'a primitive root', 'macah', 'TWOT - 1219', 'maw-saw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to dissolve:--make to consume away, (make to) melt, water.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to melt, dissolve, be liquefied<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to melt, cause to dissolve, consume, cause to vanish<LI>to intimidate (fig)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(4530, 'hoom', 'from (04549) (in the sense of flowing)', 'miccah', 'TWOT - 1225', 'mis-saw\'', 'Noun', 'from «04549» (in the sense of flowing); abundance, i.e. (adverbially) liberally: tribute.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sufficient, sufficiency<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>sufficiency, enough<LI>full amount or proportion (affordable)</OL></OL>'),
(4531, 'hoom', 'from (05254)', 'maccah', 'TWOT - 1223b', 'mas-saw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05254»; a testing, of men (judicial) or of God (querulous):--temptation, trial.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>despair, test<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>despair<LI>testing, proving, trial</OL></OL>'),
(4532, 'hoom', 'the same as (04531)', 'Maccah', 'None', 'mas-saw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «04531»; Massah, a place in the Desert:--Massah.', 'Massah = \"temptation\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the place in the wilderness where the Israelites tested Jehovah<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Meribah\'</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(4533, 'hwom', 'apparently from an unused root meaning to cover', 'macveh', 'TWOT - 1472b', 'mas-veh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'apparently from an unused root meaning to cover; a veil:--vail.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>veil</OL>'),
(4534, 'hkwom', 'for (04881)', 'mcuwkah', 'TWOT - 1475a', 'mes-oo-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'for «04881»; a hedge:--thorn hedge.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hedge</OL>'),
(4535, 'xoom', 'from (05255) in the sense of staving off', 'maccach', 'TWOT - 1374a', 'mas-sawkh\'', '', 'from «05255» in the sense of staving off; a cordon, (adverbially) or (as a) military barrier:--broken down.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>meaning uncertain - perhaps n<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>guard adv<LI>alternately, by turns</OL></OL>'),
(4536, 'rxom', 'from (05503)', 'micchar', 'TWOT - 1486d', 'mis-khawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05503»; trade:--traffic.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>merchandise<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(BDB) merchandise; meaning doubtful</OL></OL>'),
(4537, '$om', 'a primary root', 'macak', '1220', 'maw-sak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to mix, especially wine (with spices):--mingle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to mix, mingle, produce by mixing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to pour, mix</OL></OL>'),
(4538, '$om', 'from (04537)', 'mecek', 'TWOT - 1220a', 'meh\'-sek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04537»; a mixture, i.e. of wine with spices:--mixture.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mixture</OL>'),
(4539, '$om', 'from (05526)', 'macak', 'TWOT - 1492a', 'maw-sawk\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05526»; a cover, i.e. veil:--covering, curtain, hanging.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>covering, rag, screen<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>covering<LI>screen (of the tabernacle)</OL></OL>'),
(4540, 'hkkom', 'a covering, i.e. garniture', 'mcukkah', 'TWOT - 1492a', 'mes-ook-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05526»; a covering, i.e. garniture:--covering.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>covering</OL>'),
(4541, 'hkoom', 'from (05258)', 'maccekah', 'TWOT - 1375c,1376a', 'mas-say-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05258»; properly, a pouring over, i.e. fusion of metal (especially a cast image); by implication, a libation, i.e. league; concretely a coverlet (as if poured out):--covering, molten (image), vail.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a pouring, libation, molten metal, cast image, drink offering<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>libation (with covenant sacrifice)<LI>molten metal, molten image, molten gods</OL><LI>web, covering, veil, woven stuff</OL>'),
(4542, '!kom', 'from (05531)', 'micken', 'TWOT - 1221', 'mis-kane\'', 'Adjective', 'from «05531»; indigent:--poor (man).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>poor, poor man</OL>'),
(4543, 'hnkom', 'by transp. from (03664)', 'micknah', 'TWOT - 1494a', 'mis-ken-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'by transp. from «03664»; a magazine:  --store(-house), treasure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>supply, storage, storage house, magazine</OL>'),
(4544, 'tnkom', 'from (04542)', 'mickenuth', 'TWOT - 1222', 'mis-kay-nooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04542»; indigence:--scarceness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>poverty, scarcity</OL>'),
(4545, 'tkoom', 'from (05259) in the sense of spreading out', 'macceketh', 'TWOT - 1376b', 'mas-seh\'-keth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05259» in the sense of spreading out; something expanded, i.e. the warp in a loom (as stretched out to receive the woof):--web.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>web<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>web of unfinished stuff on a loom</OL></OL>'),
(4546, 'hllom', 'from (05549)', 'mcillah', 'TWOT - 1506d', 'mes-il-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05549»; a thoroughfare (as turnpiked), literally or figuratively; specifically a viaduct, a staircase:--causeway, course, highway, path, terrace.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>highway, raised way, public road</OL>'),
(4547, 'lwlom', 'from (05549)', 'macluwl', 'TWOT - 1506d', 'mas-lool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05549»; a thoroughfare (as turnpiked):--highway.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>highway</OL>'),
(4548, 'rmom', 'from (05568)', 'macmer', 'TWOT - 1518b', 'mas-mare\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or micmer {mis-mare\'}; also (feminine) macmrah {mas-mer-aw\'}; or micmrah {mis-mer-aw\'}; or even masmrah (Eccles. 12:11) {mas-mer-aw\'}; from «05568»; a peg (as bristling from the surface):--nail.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nail</OL>'),
(4549, 'oom', 'a primitive root', 'macac', 'TWOT - 1223', 'maw-sas\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to liquefy; figuratively, to waste (with disease), to faint (with fatigue, fear or grief):--discourage, faint, be loosed, melt (away), refuse, ×  utterly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dissolve, melt<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to waste away<LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to melt, vanish, drop off, melt away<LI>to faint, grow fearful (fig.)<LI>wasted, worthless (participle)</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to cause to melt</OL></OL>'),
(4550, '[oom', 'from (05265)', 'macca`', 'TWOT - 1380a', 'mas-sah\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05265»; a departure (from striking the tents), i.e. march (not necessarily a single day\'s travel); by implication, a station (or point of departure):--journey(-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a pulling up (of stakes), breaking camp, setting out, journey<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>pulling up, breaking camp<LI>setting out<LI>station, stage, journey</OL></OL>'),
(4551, '[oom', 'from (05265) in the sense of projecting', 'macca`', 'TWOT - 1380b,1381a', 'mas-saw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05265» in the sense of projecting; a missile (spear or arrow); also a quarry (whence stones are, as it were, ejected):--before it was brought, dart.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>quarry, quarrying, breaking out (of stones)<LI>missile, dart</OL>'),
