(4820, 'hmrm', 'from (07411) in the sense of deceiving', 'mirmah', 'TWOT - 2169b', 'meer-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07411» in the sense of deceiving; fraud:--craft, deceit(-ful, -fully), false, feigned, guile, subtilly, treachery.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>deceit, treachery</OL>'),
(4821, 'hmrm', 'the same as (04820)', 'Mirmah', 'None', 'meer-maw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «04820»; Mirmah, an Israelite:--Mirma.', 'Mirma = \"fraud\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite born in the land of Moab</OL>'),
(4822, 'twmrm', 'from (07311)', 'Mremowth', 'None', 'mer-ay-mohth\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'plural from «07311»; heights; Meremoth, the name of two Israelites:--Meremoth.', 'Meremoth = \"elevations\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest, son of Uriah of the family of Koz active in rebuilding the wall of Jerusalem and in the 7th course of temple service in the time of Ezra and Nehemiah<LI>a priest in the time of Zerubbabel<LI>a returning exile of the family of Bani who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(4823, 'omrm', 'from (07429)', 'mirmac', 'TWOT - 2176a', 'meer-mawce\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07429»; abasement (the act or the thing):--tread (down)-ing, (to be) trodden (down) under foot.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>trampling place, trampling<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>trampling place<LI>trampling</OL></OL>'),
(4824, 'ytnrm', 'patrial from an unused noun', 'Meronothiy', 'None', 'may-ro-no-thee\'', 'Adjective', 'patrial from an unused noun; a Meronothite, or inhabitant of some (otherwise unknown) Meronoth.:--Meronothite.', 'Meronothite = \"joyful shouter\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a native of a place probably called \'Meronoth\'<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>Jehdeiah<LI>Jadon</OL></OL>'),
(4825, 'orm', 'of foreign derivation', 'Merec', 'None', 'meh\'-res', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign derivation; Meres, a Persian:--Meres.', 'Meres = \"lofty\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 7 counsellors of Ahasuerus</OL>'),
(4826, 'anorm', 'of foreign derivation', 'Marcna\'', 'None', 'mar-sen-aw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign derivation; Marsena, a Persian:--Marsena.', 'Marsena = \"worthy\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 7 counsellors of Ahasuerus</OL>'),
(4827, '[rm', 'from (07489)', 'mera`', 'TWOT - 2186f', 'may-rah\'', '', 'from «07489»; used as (abstract) noun, wickedness:--do mischief.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) mischief<LI>(TWOT) confidential friend</OL>'),
(4828, '[rm', 'from (07462) in the sense of companionship', 'merea`', 'TWOT - 2186f', 'may-ray\'-ah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07462» in the sense of companionship; a friend:--companion, friend.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>companion, friend, confidential friend</OL>'),
(4829, 'h[rm', 'from (07462) in the sense of feeding', 'mir`eh', 'TWOT - 2185b', 'meer-eh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07462» in the sense of feeding; pasture (the place or the act); also the haunt of wild animals:--feeding place, pasture.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pasture, pasturage</OL>'),
(4830, 'ty[rm', 'from (07462) in the sense of feeding', 'mir`iyth', 'TWOT - 2185c', 'meer-eeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07462» in the sense of feeding; pasturage; concretely, a flock:--flock, pasture.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pasturing, pasturage, shepherding<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>pasturing, shepherding<LI>pasturage<LI>flock (meton)</OL></OL>'),
(4831, 'hl[rm', 'from (07477)', 'Mar`alah', 'None', 'mar-al-aw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «07477»; perhaps, earthquake; Maralah, a place in Palestine:--Maralah.', 'Maralah = \"trembling\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town or landmark on the border of Zebulun</OL>'),
(4832, 'aprm', 'from (07495)', 'marpe\'', 'TWOT - 2196c', 'mar-pay\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07495»; properly, curative, i.e. literally (concretely) a medicine, or (abstractly) a cure; figuratively (concretely) deliverance, or (abstractly) placidity:--((in-))cure(-able), healing(-lth), remedy, sound, wholesome, yielding.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>health, healing, cure<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>healing, cure<LI>health, profit, sound (of mind)<LI>healing<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>incurable (with negative)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(4833, 'Xprm', 'from (07515)', 'mirpas', 'TWOT - 2199a', 'meer-paws\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07515»; muddled water:--that which...have fouled.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>befouled, thing befouled</OL>'),
(4834, '#rm', 'a primitive root', 'marats', 'TWOT - 1245', 'maw-rats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to press, i.e. (figuratively) to be pungent or vehement; to irritate:--embolden, be forcible, grievous, sore.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or make sick<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be grievous or painful<LI>(Hiphil) to make sick</OL></OL>'),
(4835, 'hcrm', 'from (07533)', 'mrutsah', 'TWOT - 2212b', 'mer-oo-tsaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07533»; oppression:--violence. See also «04794».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>crushing, oppression</OL>'),
(4836, '[crm', 'from (07527)', 'martsea`', 'TWOT - 2209a', 'mar-tsay\'-ah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07527»; an awl:--aul.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>awl, boring-instrument</OL>'),
(4837, 'tpcrm', 'from (07528)', 'martsepheth', 'TWOT - 2210b', 'mar-tseh\'-feth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07528»; a pavement:--pavement.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pavement</OL>'),
(4838, 'qrm', 'a primitive root', 'maraq', 'TWOT - 1246', 'maw-rak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to polish; by implication, to sharpen; also to rinse:--bright, furbish, scour.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to scour, polish<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to scour, polish<LI>(Pual) to be scoured</OL></OL>'),
(4839, 'qrm', 'from (04838)', 'maraq', 'TWOT - 1247a', 'maw-rawk\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04838»; soup (as if a rinsing):--broth. See also «06564».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>broth, juice cooked from meat</OL>'),
(4840, 'xqrm', 'from (07543)', 'merqach', 'TWOT - 2215f', 'mer-kawkh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07543»; a spicy herb:--X sweet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spice, perfume, aromatic spices</OL>'),
(4841, 'hxqrm', 'from (04840)', 'merqachah', 'TWOT - 2215g', 'mer-kaw-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «04840»; abstractly, a seasoning (with spicery); concretely, an unguent-kettle (for preparing spiced oil):--pot of ointment, × well.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a seasoning, compounding, spice-seasoning<LI>ointment pot</OL>'),
(4842, 'txqrm', 'from (07543)', 'mirqachath', 'TWOT - 2215h', 'meer-kakh\'-ath', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07543»; an aromatic unguent; also an unguent-pot:--prepared by the apothecaries\' art, compound, ointment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ointment, mixture of ointment<LI>ointment-pot</OL>'),
(4843, 'rrm', 'a primitive root', 'marar', 'TWOT - 1248', 'maw-rar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to trickle (see «04752»); but used only as a denominative from «04751»; to be (causatively, make) bitter (literally or figuratively):--(be, be in, deal, have, make) bitter(-ly, - ness), be moved with choler, (be, have sorely, it) grieved(-eth), provoke, vex.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be bitter<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be bitter<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to show bitterness<LI>to make bitter</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to make bitter, embitter<LI>(Hithpalpel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to embitter oneself<LI>to be enraged</OL></OL><LI>(TWOT) to be strong, strengthen</OL>'),
(4844, 'rrm', 'from (04843)', 'mror', 'TWOT - 1248e', 'mer-ore\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or mrowr {mer-ore\'}; from «04843»; a bitter herb:-- bitter(-ness).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bitter thing, bitter herb, bitterness</OL>'),
(4845, 'hrrm', 'from (04843)', 'mrerah', 'TWOT - 1248g', 'mer-ay-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04843»; bile (from its bitterness):--gall.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gall</OL>'),
(4846, 'hrrm', 'from (04843)', 'mrorah', 'TWOT - 1248f', 'mer-o-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or mrowrah {mer-o-raw\'}; from «04843»; properly, bitterness; concretely, a bitter thing; specifically bile; also venom (of a serpent):--bitter (thing), gall.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bitter thing, gall, poison<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>gall, gall-bladder (seat of gall)<LI>poison, venom<LI>bitter thing<LI>bitterness</OL></OL>'),
(4847, 'yrrm', 'from (04843)', 'Mrariy', 'None', 'mer-aw-ree\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04843»; bitter; Merari, an Israelite:--Merari. See also «04848».', 'Merari = \"bitter\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 3rd son of Levi and head of a Levitical family</OL>'),
(4848, 'yrrm', 'from (04847)', 'Mrariy', 'None', 'mer-aw-ree\'', 'Adjective', 'from «04847»; a Merarite (collectively), or decendants of Merari:--Merarites.', 'Merarites = see Marari \"bitter\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Merari, the son of Levi, and members of a Levitical family</OL>'),
(4849, 't[Xrm', 'from (07561)', 'mirsha`ath', 'TWOT - 2222d', 'meer-shah\'-ath', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07561»; a female wicked doer:--wicked woman.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wickedness</OL>'),
(4850, '~ytrm', 'dual of (04751)', 'Mrathayim', 'None', 'mer-aw-thah\'-yim', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'dual of «04751» feminine; double bitterness; Merathajim, an epithet of Babylon:--Merathaim.', 'Merathaim = \"double rebellion\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>another name for \'Babylon\'</OL>'),
(4851, 'Xm', 'of foreign derivation', 'Mash', 'None', 'mash', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign derivation; Mash, a son of Aram, and the people descended from him:--Mash.', 'Mash = \"drawn out\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the sons of Aram; also \'Meshech\'</OL>'),
(4852, 'aXm', 'of foreign derivation', 'Mesha\'', 'None', 'may-shaw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'of foreign derivation; Mesha, a place in Arabia:--Mesha.', 'Mesha = \"freedom\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a region marking one of the limits of the territory of the Joktanites when they first settled in Arabia</OL>'),
(4853, 'aXXm', 'from (05375)', 'massa\'', 'TWOT - 1421d,1421e', 'mas-saw\'', '', 'from «05375»; a burden; specifically, tribute, or (abstractly) porterage; figuratively, an utterance, chiefly a doom, especially singing; mental, desire:--burden, carry away, prophecy, × they set, song, tribute.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>load, bearing, tribute, burden, lifting<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>load, burden<LI>lifting, uplifting, that to which the soul lifts itself up<LI>bearing, carrying<LI>tribute, that which is carried or brought or borne</OL><LI>utterance, oracle, burden n pr m (BDB) Massa = \"burden\"<LI>a son of Ishmael</OL>'),
(4854, 'aXXm', 'the same as (04853)', 'Massa\'', 'None', 'mas-saw\'', '', 'the same as «04853»; burden; Massa, a son of Ishmael:--Massa.', 'Massa = \"burden\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Ishmael</OL>'),
(4855, 'aXXm', 'from (05383)', 'mashsha\'', 'TWOT - 1424a', 'mash-shaw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05383»; a loan; by implication, interest on a debt:--exaction, usury.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lending on interest, usury<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>in Neh. 5:11, the rate of \"usury\" was only one per cent</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(4856, 'aXXm', 'from (05375)', 'masso\'', 'TWOT - 1421f', 'mas-so\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05375»; partiality (as a lifting up):--respect.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a lifting up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>partiality (in construct)</OL></OL>'),
(4857, 'baXm', 'from (07579)', 'mash\'ab', 'TWOT - 2299.1a', 'mash-awb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07579»; a trough for cattle to drink from:--place of drawing water.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>drawing place of water, place to draw water</OL>'),
(4858, 'haXXm', 'from (05375)', 'massa\'ah', 'TWOT - 1421g', 'mas-saw-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05375»; a conflagration (from the rising of smoke):--burden.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the uplifted, uplifting</OL>'),
(4859, 'haXXm', 'from (04855)', 'mashsha\'ah', 'TWOT - 1424b', 'mash-shaw-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «04855»; a loan:--X any(- thing), debt.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>loan</OL>'),
(4860, '!waXXm', 'from (05377)', 'mashsha\'own', 'TWOT - 1425a', 'mash-shaw-ohn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05377»; dissimulation:--deceit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>guile, dissimulation, deceit</OL>'),
(4861, 'laXm', 'from (07592)', 'Mish\'al', 'None', 'mish-awl\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «07592»; request; Mishal, a place in Palestine:--Mishal, Misheal. Compare «04913».', 'Misheal = \"entreaty\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in the territory of Asher allotted to the Gershonite Levites</OL>'),
(4862, 'hlaXm', 'from (07592)', 'mish\'alah', 'TWOT - 2303b', 'mish-aw-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07592»; a request:--desire, petition.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>request, petition, desire</OL>'),
(4863, 'traXm', 'from (07604) in the original sense of swelling', 'mish\'ereth', 'TWOT - 1252', 'mish-eh\'-reth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07604» in the original sense of swelling; a kneading-trough (in which the dough rises):--kneading trough, store.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>kneading trough or bowl</OL>'),
(4864, 'taXm', 'from \\\\(05375)\\\\', 'mas\'eth', 'TWOT - 1421h', 'mas-ayth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05375»; properly, (abstractly) a raising (as of the hands in prayer), or rising (of flame); figuratively, an utterance; concretely, a beacon (as raised); a present (as taken), mess, or tribute; figuratively, a reproach (as a burden):--burden, collection, sign of fire, (great) flame, gift, lifting up, mess, oblation, reward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>uprising, utterance, burden, portion, uplifting<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>that which rises, uprising, uplifting, signal, rising<LI>utterance, oracle<LI>burden<LI>portion, present, largesse, gift, contribution, offering, tribute</OL></OL>'),
(4865, 'hcbXm', 'from (07660)', 'mishbtsah', 'TWOT - 2320b', 'mish-bets-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07660»; a brocade; by analogy, a (reticulated) setting of a gem:--ouch, wrought.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>plaited or filigree or chequered work (of settings for gems)</OL>'),
(4866, 'rbXm', 'from (07665)', 'mishber', 'TWOT - 2321c', 'mish-bare\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07665»; the orifice of the womb (from which the fetus breaks forth):--birth, breaking forth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>place of breaking forth, place of breach, opening<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of womb</OL></OL>'),
(4867, 'rbXm', 'from (07665)', 'mishbar', 'TWOT - 2321d', 'mish-bawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07665»; a breaker (of the sea):--billow, wave.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>breaker, breaking (of sea)</OL>'),
(4868, 'tbXm', 'from (07673)', 'mishbath', 'TWOT - 2323e', 'mish-bawth\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07673»; cessation, i.e. destruction:--sabbath.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cessation, annihilation</OL>'),
(4869, 'bgXm', 'from (07682)', 'misgab', 'TWOT - 2234a', 'mis-gawb\'', '', 'from «07682»; properly, a cliff (or other lofty or inaccessible place); abstractly, altitude; figuratively, a refuge:-- defence, high fort (tower), refuge, Misgab, a place in Moab:--Misgab.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>high place, refuge, secure height, retreat<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>stronghold<LI>refuge (of God) n pr loc Misgab = \"height\"</OL><LI>a place in Moab</OL>'),
(4870, 'hgXm', 'from (07686)', 'mishgeh', 'TWOT - 2325b', 'mish-gay\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07686»; an error:--oversight.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mistake</OL>'),
(4871, 'hXm', 'a primitive root', 'mashah', 'TWOT - 1253', 'maw-shaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pull out (literally or figuratively):--draw(out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to draw<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to draw<LI>(Hiphil) to draw</OL></OL>'),
(4872, 'hXm', 'from (04871)', 'Mosheh', 'TWOT - 1254', 'mo-sheh\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04871»; drawing out (of the water), i.e. rescued; Mosheh, the Israelite lawgiver:--Moses.', 'Moses = \"drawn\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the prophet and lawgiver, leader of the exodus</OL>'),
(4873, 'hXm', 'corresponding to (04872)', 'Mosheh', 'None', 'mo-sheh\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «04872»:--Moses.', 'Moses = \"drawn\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the prophet and lawgiver, leader of the exodus</OL>'),
(4874, 'hXXm', 'from (05383)', 'mashsheh', 'TWOT - 1427b', 'mash-sheh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05383»; a debt:--+ creditor.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>loan<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of loan released in the 7th year</OL></OL>'),
(4875, 'hawXm', 'from the same as (07722)', 'mshow\'ah', 'TWOT - 2339b', 'meh-o-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or mshoah {mesh-o-aw\'}; from the same as «07722»; (a) ruin, abstractly (the act) or concretely (the wreck):--desolation, waste.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>desolation, ruin</OL>'),
(4876, 'hawXXm', 'for (04875)', 'masshuw\'ah', 'TWOT - 2339b', 'mash-shoo-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or mashshu ah {mash-shoo-aw\'}; for «04875»; ruin:--desolation, destruction.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>desolation, ruin</OL>'),
(4877, 'bbwXm', 'from (07725)', 'Mshowbab', 'None', 'mesh-o-bawb\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07725»; returned; Meshobab, an Israelite:--Meshobab.', 'Meshobab = \"restored\" or \"backsliding\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Simeon</OL>'),
(4878, 'hbwXm', 'from (07725)', 'mshuwbah', 'TWOT - 2340c', 'mesh-oo-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or mshubah {mesh-oo-baw\'}; from «07725»; apostasy:--backsliding, turning away.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>turning away, turning back, apostasy, backsliding</OL>'),
(4879, 'hgwXm', 'from an unused root meaning to stray', 'mshuwgah', 'TWOT - 2341a', 'mesh-oo-gaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning to stray; mistake:--error.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>error</OL>'),
(4880, 'twXm', 'from (07751)', 'mashowt', 'TWOT - 2344e', 'maw-shote\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or mishshowt {mish-shote\'}; from «07751»; an oar:--oar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>oar</OL>'),
(4881, 'hkwXm', 'from (07753)', 'msuwkah', 'TWOT - 2241a', 'mes-oo-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or msukah {mes-oo-kaw\'}; from «07753»; a hedge:--hedge.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hedge</OL>'),
(4882, 'howXm', 'from an unused root meaning to plunder', 'mshuwcah', 'TWOT - 2426a', 'mesh-oo-saw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning to plunder; spoilation:--spoil.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>booty, spoil, plunder</OL>'),
(4883, 'rwXXm', 'from an unused root meaning to rasp', 'massowr', 'TWOT - 1423a', 'mas-sore\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to rasp; a saw:--saw.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>saw</OL>'),
(4884, 'hrwXm', 'from an unused root meaning apparently to divide', 'msuwrah', 'TWOT - 1250', 'mes-oo-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning apparently to divide; a measure (for liquids):--measure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>measure</OL>'),
(4885, 'XwXm', 'from (07797)', 'masows', 'TWOT - 2246b', 'maw-soce\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07797»; delight, concretely (the cause or object) or abstractly (the feeling):--joy, mirth, rejoice.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>exultation, joy, rejoicing</OL>'),
(4886, 'xXm', 'a primitive root', 'mashach', 'TWOT - 1255', 'maw-shakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to rub with oil, i.e. to anoint; by implication, to consecrate; also to paint:--anoint, paint.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to smear, anoint, spread a liquid<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to smear<LI>to anoint (as consecration)<LI>to anoint, consecrate</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be anointed</OL></OL>'),
(4887, 'xXm', 'from a root corresponding to (04886)', 'mshach', 'TWOT - 2842', 'mesh-akh\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «04886»; oil:--oil.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>oil</OL>'),
(4888, 'hxXm', 'from (04886)', 'mishchah', 'TWOT - 1255a,1255b', 'meesh-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or moshchah {mosh-khaw\'}; from «04886»; unction (the act); by implication, a consecratory gift:--(to be) anointed(-ing), ointment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>consecrated portion, anointing oil, portion, ointment, anointing portion<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>ointment (used to consecrate by anointing)<LI>anointing portion</OL></OL>'),
(4889, 'tyxXm', 'from (07843)', 'mashchiyth', 'TWOT - 2370a', 'mash-kheeth\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07843»; destructive, i.e. (as noun) destruction, literally (specifically a snare) or figuratively (corruption):--corruption, (to) destroy(-ing), destruction, trap, × utterly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ruin, destruction</OL>'),
(4890, 'qxXm', 'from (07831)', 'mischaq', 'TWOT - 1905f', 'mis-khawk\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07831»; a laughing-stock:--scorn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>object of derision</OL>'),
(4891, 'rxXm', 'from (07836) in the sense of day breaking', 'mishchar', 'TWOT - 2369b', 'mish-khawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07836» in the sense of day breaking; dawn:--morning.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dawn</OL>'),
(4892, 'txXm', 'for (04889)', 'mashcheth', 'TWOT - 2370b', 'mash-khayth\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'for «04889»; destruction:--destroying.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ruin, destruction</OL>'),
