(4949, 'tlqXm', 'from (04948) or (04947)', 'mishqeleth', 'TWOT - 2454d', 'mish-keh\'-leth', 'Noun Feminine', 'or mishqoleth {mish-ko\'-leth}; feminine of «04948» or «04947»; a weight, i.e. a plummet (with line attached):--plummet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>level, levelling tool or instrument, plummet</OL>'),
(4950, '[qXm', 'from (08257)', 'mishqa`', 'TWOT - 2456a', 'mish-kaw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08257»; a settling place (of water), i.e. a pond:--deep.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>what is settled or clarified, clear</OL>'),
(4951, 'hrXm', 'from (08280)', 'misrah', 'TWOT - 2288a', 'mis-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08280»; empire:--government.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rule, dominion, government</OL>'),
(4952, 'hrXm', 'from (08281) in the sense of loosening', 'mishrah', 'TWOT - 2464a', 'mish-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08281» in the sense of loosening; maceration, i.e. steeped juice:--liquor.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>juice</OL>'),
(4953, 'yqwrXm', 'from a root corresponding to (08319)', 'mashrowqiy', 'TWOT - 3049a', 'mash-ro-kee\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «08319»; a (musical) pipe (from its whistling sound):--flute.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pipe</OL>'),
(4954, 'y[rXm', 'patrial from an unused noun from an unused root', 'Mishra`iy', 'None', 'mish-raw-ee\'', 'Adjective', 'patrial from an unused noun from an unused root; probably meaning to stretch out; extension; a Mishraite, or inhabitant (collectively) of Mishra:--Mishraites.', 'Mishraites = \"touching evil\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 4th of the 4 families of Kirjath-jearim</OL>'),
(4955, 'hprXm', 'from (08313)', 'misraphah', 'TWOT - 2292d', 'mis-raw-faw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08313»; combustion, i.e. cremation (of a corpse), or calcination (of lime):--burning.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a burning</OL>'),
(4956, '~ym twprXm', 'from pl of (04955) and (04325)', 'Misrphowth', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the plural of «04955» and «04325»; burnings of water; Misrephoth-Majim, a place in Palestine:--Misrephoth-mayim.', 'Misrephoth-maim = \"burnings of water\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in northern Palestine near Sidon</OL>'),
(4957, 'hqrXm', 'a form for (07796) used denominatively', 'Masreqah', 'None', 'mas-ray-kaw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'a form for «07796» used denominatively; vineyard; Masrekah, a place in Idumaea:--Masrekah.', 'Masrekah = \"vineyard of noble vines\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an ancient place, the native spot of Samlah, one of the old kings of the Edomites</OL>'),
(4958, 'trXm', 'apparently from an unused root meaning to perforate, i.e. hollow out', 'masreth', 'TWOT - 1251', 'mas-rayth\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'apparently from an unused root meaning to perforate, i.e. hollow out; a pan:--pan.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pan, dish</OL>'),
(4959, 'XXm', 'a primitive root', 'mashash', 'TWOT - 1262', 'maw-shash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to feel of; by implication, to grope:--feel, grope, search.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to feel, grope<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to feel, grope<LI>(Piel) to feel over or through, grope<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to feel through<LI>to grope</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to feel</OL></OL>'),
(4960, 'htXm', 'from (08354)', 'mishteh', 'TWOT - 2477c', 'mish-teh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08354»; drink, by implication, drinking (the act); also (by implication) a banquet or (generally) feast:--banquet, drank, drink, feast((-ed), -ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>feast, drink, banquet<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>feast, banquet<LI>drink</OL></OL>'),
(4961, 'htXm', 'corresponding to (04960)', 'mishteh', 'TWOT - 3051a', 'mish-teh\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «04960»; a banquet:--banquet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>feast, banquet</OL>'),
(4962, 'tm', 'from the same as (04970)', 'math', 'TWOT - 1263', 'math', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «04970»; properly, an adult (as of full length); by implication, a man (only in the plural):--+ few, × friends, men, persons, × small.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>male, man<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>males, men<LI>few men (in prose)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>less emphasis on sex</OL><LI>men (poetic)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>less emphasis on sex</OL></OL></OL>'),
(4963, '!btm', 'denominative from (08401)', 'mathben', 'TWOT - 2493a', 'math-bane\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'denominative from «08401»; straw in the heap:--straw.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>straw heap</OL>'),
(4964, 'gtm', 'from an unused root meaning to curb', 'metheg', 'TWOT - 1264a', 'meh-theg', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to curb; a bit:--bit, bridle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bridle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>bridle (for animals)<LI>control, authority (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(4965, 'hmmah gtm', 'from (04964) and (0520) with the art. interposed', 'Metheg', 'None', '', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04964» and «0520» with the art. interposed; bit of the metropolis; Metheg-ha-Ammah, an epithet of Gath:--Metheg-ammah.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mother city<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>bridle of the mother city (ie control or authority of)</OL></OL>'),
(4966, 'qwtm', 'from (04985)', 'mathowq', 'TWOT - 1268c', 'maw-thoke\'', '', 'or mathuwq {maw-thook\'}; from «04985»; sweet:-- sweet(-er, -ness).', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sweet n m<LI>sweetness, pleasant (thing)</OL>'),
(4967, 'laXwtm', 'from (04962) and (0410), with the relative interposed', 'Mthuwsha\'el', 'None', 'meth-oo-shaw-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04962» and «0410», with the relative interposed; man who (is) of God; Methusael, an antediluvian patriarch:--Methusael.', 'Methusael = \"who is of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Mehujael, 4th in descent from Cain, and father of Lamech</OL>'),
(4968, 'xlXwtm', 'from (04962) and (07973)', 'Mthuwshelach', 'None', 'meth-oo-sheh\'-lakh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04962» and «07973»; man of a dart; Methushelach, an antediluvian patriarch:--Methuselah.', 'Methuselah = \"man of the dart\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Enoch, 6th in descent from Seth, and father of Lamech</OL>'),
(4969, 'xtm', 'a primitive root', 'mathach', 'TWOT - 1265', 'maw-thakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to stretch out:--spread out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to spread out</OL>'),
(4970, 'ytm', 'from an unused root meaning to extend', 'mathay', 'TWOT - 1266', 'maw-thah\'ee', '', 'from an unused root meaning to extend; properly, extent (of time); but used only adverbially (especially with other particle prefixes), when (either relative or interrogative):--long, when.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>when?<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>with prep<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>against when?, until when?, how long?, after how long?</OL></OL></OL>'),
(4971, 'tnktm', 'from (08505) in the transferred sense of measuring', 'mathkoneth', 'TWOT - 2511c', 'math-ko\'-neth', 'Noun Feminine', 'or mathkuneth {math-koo\'-neth}; from «08505» in the transferred sense of measuring; proportion (in size, number or ingredients):--composition, measure, state, tale.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>measurement, proportion, tale<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>tale, tally (of bricks)<LI>measurement, proportion</OL></OL>'),
(4972, 'halttm', 'from (04100) and (08513)', 'mattla\'ah', 'TWOT - 1066a', 'mat-tel-aw-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04100» and «08513»; what a trouble!:--what a weariness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>what a weariness, toil, hardship, weariness</OL>'),
(4973, 'h[lltm', 'contr. from (03216)', 'mthall`ah', 'TWOT - 2516d', 'meth-al-leh-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'contr. from «03216»; properly, a biter, i.e. a tooth:--cheek (jaw) tooth, jaw.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>teeth, fangs, incisors</OL>'),
(4974, '~tm', 'from (08552)', 'mthom', 'TWOT - 2522e', 'meth-ohm\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08552»; wholesomeness; also (adverb) completely:--men (by reading «04962»), soundness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>soundness, entirety, entire</OL>'),
(4975, '!tm', 'from an unused root meaning to be slender', 'mothen', 'TWOT - 1267a', 'mo\'-then', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to be slender; properly, the waist or small of the back; only in plural the loins:--+ greyhound, loins, side.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>loins, hips<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used with 02223 in Pr. 30:31; perhaps an extinct animal, exact meaning unknown</OL></OL>'),
(4976, '!ttm', 'from (05414)', 'mattan', 'TWOT - 1443b', 'mat-tawn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05414»; a present:--gift, to give, reward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gifts, offerings, presents</OL>'),
(4977, '!ttm', 'the same as (04976)', 'Mattan', 'None', 'mat-tawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «04976»; Mattan, the name of a priest of Baal, and of an Israelite:--Mattan.', 'Mattan = \"a gift\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest of Baal in Jerusalem in the time of Athaliah<LI>father of Shephatiah in the time of Jeremiah</OL>'),
(4978, 'anttm', 'corresponding to (04979)', 'mattna\'', 'TWOT - 2880a', 'mat-ten-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «04979»:--gift.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gift</OL>'),
(4979, 'hnttm', 'from (04976)', 'mattanah', 'TWOT - 1443c', 'mat-taw-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «04976»; a present; specifically (in a good sense), a sacrificial offering, (in a bad sense) a bribe:--gift.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gift</OL>'),
(4980, 'hnttm', 'the same as (04979)', 'Mattanah', 'None', 'mat-taw-naw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «04979»; Mattanah, a place in the Desert:--Mattanah.', 'Mattanah = \"gift of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a station of the Israelites in the latter part of their wanderings located east of the Jordan and probably to the southeast of the Dead Sea</OL>'),
(4981, 'yntm', 'probably patrial from an unused noun meaning slenderness', 'Mithniy', 'None', 'mith-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'probably patrial from an unused noun meaning slenderness; a Mithnite, or inhabitant of Methen:--Mithnite.', 'Mithnite = \"athlete\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unknown derivation<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used in description of Joshaphat, one of David\'s guards</OL></OL>'),
(4982, 'ynttm', 'from (04976)', 'Mattnay', 'None', 'mat-ten-ah\'ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «04976»; liberal; Mattenai, the name of three Israelites:--Mattenai.', 'Mattenai = \"gift of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest, son of Joiarib, in the time of Joiakim<LI>an Israelite who had and put away his foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>another Israelite who had and put away his foreign wife in the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(4983, 'hynttm', 'from (04976) and (03050)', 'Mattanyah', 'None', 'mat-tan-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Mattanyahuw {mat-tan-yaw\'-hoo}; from «04976» and «03050»; gift of Jah; Mattanjah, the name of ten Israelites:--Mattaniah.', 'Mattaniah = \"gift of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the original name of the last king of Judah before the captivity; also known as \'Zedekiah\'<LI>a Levite, son of Heman, whose office was to blow the horns in the temple service as appointed by David<LI>a Levite of the family of Asaph<LI>a Levite of the family of Asaph who assisted in the purification of the temple in the reign of Hezekiah<LI>a Levite of the family of Asaph who took part in the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem; leader of the temple choir<LI>a Levite, descendant of Asaph and ancestor of Jahaziel in the time of Jehoshaphat<LI>another Levite in the time of Nehemiah<LI>a Levite, father of Zaccur and ancestor of Hanan the under-treasurer who had charge of the offerings in the time of Nehemiah<LI>a man of the sons of Elam who had and put away a strange wife in the time of Ezra<LI>a man of the sons of Zattu who had and put away a strange wife in the time of Ezra<LI>a man descended from Pahath-moab who had and put away a strange wife in the time of Ezra<LI>a man of the sons of Bani who had and put away a strange wife in the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(4984, 'aXXntm', 'from (05375)', 'mithnasse\'', 'TWOT - 1421?', 'mith-nas-say\'', '', 'from «05375»; (used as abstractly) supreme exaltation:--exalted.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hithpael) one who exalts himself</OL>'),
(4985, 'qtm', 'a primitive root', 'mathaq', 'TWOT - 1268', 'maw-thak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to suck, by implication, to relish, or (intransitively) be sweet:--be (made, × take) sweet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or become sweet or pleasing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or become sweet<LI>to be or become pleasant<LI>to suck</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to give sweet taste</OL></OL>'),
(4986, 'qtm', 'from (04985)', 'metheq', 'TWOT - 1268a', 'meh\'-thek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04985»; figuratively, pleasantness (of discourse):--sweetness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sweetness</OL>'),
(4987, 'qtm', 'from (04985)', 'motheq', 'TWOT - 1268b', 'mo\'-thek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04985»; sweetness:--sweetness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sweetness</OL>'),
(4988, 'qtm', 'from (04985)', 'mathaq', 'TWOT - 1268c?', 'maw-thawk\'', 'Verb', 'from «04985»; a dainty, i.e. (generally) food:--feed sweetly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to feed sweetly</OL>'),
(4989, 'hqtm', 'from (04987)', 'Mithqah', 'None', 'mith-kaw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'feminine of «04987»; sweetness; Mithkah, a place in the Desert:--Mithcah.', 'Mithcah = \"sweetness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a station of Israel in the wilderness; site unknown</OL>'),
(4990, 'tdrtm', 'of Persian origin', 'Mithrdath', 'None', 'mith-red-awth\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of Persian origin; Mithredath, the name of two Persians:--Mithredath.', 'Mithredath = \"given by Mithra\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>treasurer of king Cyrus of Persia<LI>a Persian officer stationed at Samaria in the time of Artaxerxes</OL>'),
(4991, 'tttm', 'from (04976) abbrev. form', 'mattath', 'TWOT - 1443d', 'mat-tawth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «04976» abbreviated form; a present:--gift.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gift, reward</OL>'),
(4992, 'httttm', 'for (04993)', 'Mattattah', 'None', 'mat-tat-taw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'for «04993»; gift of Jah; Mattattah, an Israelite:--Mattathah.', 'Mattathah = \"gift of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Hashum who took and put away his foreign wife in the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(4993, 'hytttm', 'from (04991) and (03050)', 'Mattithyah', 'None', 'mat-tith-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Mattithyahuw {mat-tith-yaw\'-hoo}; from «04991» and «03050»; gift of Jah; Mattithjah, the name of four Israelites:-- Mattithiah.', 'Mattithiah = \"gift of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite who presided over the offerings<LI>a Levite appointed by David to minister in the musical service before the ark<LI>one of the family of Nebo who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>one of the men who stood at the right hand of Ezra when he read the law to the people</OL>'),
(4994, 'an', 'a primitive particle of incitement and entreaty, which may usually be rendered: \"I pray,\" \"now,\" or \"then\"', 'na\'', 'TWOT - 1269', 'naw', '', 'a primitive particle of incitement and entreaty, which may usually be rendered: \"I pray,\" \"now,\" or \"then\"; added mostly to verbs (in the Imperative or Future), or to interjections, occasionally to an adverb or conjunction:--I beseech (pray) thee (you), go to, now, oh.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>I (we) pray, now, please<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used in entreaty or exhortation</OL></OL>'),
(4995, 'an', 'apparently from (05106) in the sense of harshness from refusal', 'na\'', 'TWOT - 1358a', 'naw', 'Adjective', 'apparently from «05106» in the sense of harshness from refusal; properly, tough, i.e. uncooked (flesh):--raw.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>raw</OL>'),
(4996, 'an', 'of Egyptian origin', 'No\'', 'None', 'no', 'Proper Name Location', 'of Egyptian origin; No (i.e. Thebes), the capital of Upper Egypt:--No. Compare «0528».', 'No = \"disrupting\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the ancient capital of Egypt; also \'Thebes\'</OL>'),
(4997, 'dan', 'from an unused root of uncertain signification', 'no\'d', 'TWOT - 1270', 'node', 'Noun Masculine', 'or noywd {node}; also (feminine) no)dah {no-daw\'}; from an unused root of uncertain signification; a (skin or leather) bag (for fluids):--bottle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>skin, bottle, skin-bottle</OL>'),
(4998, 'han', 'a primitive root', 'na\'ah', 'TWOT - 1271', 'naw-aw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to be at home, i.e. (by implication) to be pleasant (or suitable), i.e. beautiful:--be beautiful, become, be comely.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be comely, be beautiful, be befitting<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pilpel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be comely<LI>to be befitting</OL></OL></OL>'),
(4999, 'han', 'from (04998)', 'na\'ah', 'TWOT - 1322a', 'naw-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04998»; a home; figuratively, a pasture:--habitation, house, pasture, pleasant place.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pasture, abode, abode of shepherd, habitation, meadow<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>pasture, meadow<LI>abode</OL></OL>'),
(5000, 'hwan', 'from (04998) or (05116)', 'na\'veh', 'TWOT - 1271a', 'naw-veh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «04998» or «05116»; suitable, or beautiful:--becometh, comely, seemly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>comely, beautiful, seemly<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>comely, beautiful<LI>seemly</OL></OL>'),
(5001, '~an', 'a primitive root', 'na\'am', 'TWOT - 1272', 'naw-am\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to whisper, i.e. (by implication) to utter as a oracle:--say.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to prophesy, utter a prophecy, speak as prophet, say<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to utter a prophecy, speak as prophet</OL></OL>'),
(5002, '~an', 'from (05001)', 'n\'um', 'TWOT - 1272a', 'neh-oom\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05001»; an oracle:--(hath) said, saith.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) utterance, declaration (of prophet)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>utterance, declaration, revelation (of prophet in ecstatic state)<LI>utterance, declaration (elsewhere always preceding divine name)</OL></OL>'),
(5003, '@an', 'a primitive root', 'na\'aph', 'TWOT - 1273', 'naw-af\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to commit adultery; figuratively, to apostatize:--adulterer(-ess), commit(-ing) adultery, woman that breaketh wedlock.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to commit adultery<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to commit adultery 1a</OL><LI>usually of man 1a<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>always with wife of another 1a</OL><LI>adultery (of women) (participle)<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>idolatrous worship (fig.)</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to commit adultery 1b</OL><LI>of man 1b<LI>adultery (of women) (participle)<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>idolatrous worship (fig.)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5004, '@an', 'from (05003)', 'ni\'uph', 'TWOT - 1273a', 'nee-oof\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05003»; adultery:--adultery.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>adultery<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>idolatrous worship (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(5005, '@wpan', 'from (05003)', 'na\'aphuwph', 'TWOT - 1273b', 'nah-af-oof\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05003»; adultery:--adultery.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>adultery</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(5006, '#an', 'a primitive root', 'na\'ats', 'TWOT - 1274', 'naw-ats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to scorn; or (Ecclesiastes 12:5) by interchange for «05132», to bloom:--abhor, (give occasion to) blaspheme, contemn, despise, flourish, × great, provoke.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to spurn, contemn, despise, abhor<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to spurn, contemn<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to spurn<LI>to cause to contemn</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to spurn<LI>(Hithpolel) to be contemned</OL></OL>'),
(5007, 'hcan', 'from (05006)', 'n\'atsah', 'TWOT - 1274a,1274b', 'neh-aw-tsaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or nematsah {neh-aw-tsaw\'}; from «05006»; scorn:--blasphemy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>contempt, contumely<LI>contempt, blasphemy</OL>'),
(5008, 'qan', 'a primitive root', 'na\'aq', 'TWOT - 1275', 'naw-ak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to groan:--groan.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to groan</OL>'),
(5009, 'hqan', 'from (05008);', 'n\'aqah', 'TWOT - 1275a', 'neh-aw-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05008»; a groan:--groaning.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>groan, groaning</OL>'),
(5010, 'ran', 'a primitive root', 'na\'ar', 'TWOT - 1276', 'naw-ar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to reject:--abhor, make void.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to abhor, spurn</OL>'),
(5011, 'bn', 'the same as (05108)', 'Nob', 'None', 'nobe', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «05108»; fruit; Nob, a place in Palestine:--Nob.', 'Nob = \"high place\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priestly city in the Benjamin situated on some eminence north but near Jerusalem</OL>'),
(5012, 'abn', 'a primitive root', 'naba\'', 'TWOT - 1277', 'naw-baw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to prophesy, i.e. speak (or sing) by inspiration (in prediction or simple discourse):--prophesy(-ing), make self a prophet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to prophesy<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to prophesy 1a</OL><LI>under influence of divine spirit 1a<LI>of false prophets<LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to prophesy 1b</OL><LI>under influence of divine spirit 1b<LI>of false prophets</OL></OL>'),
(5013, 'abn', 'corresponding to (05012)', 'nba\'', 'TWOT - 2843a', 'neb-aw\'', '', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05012»:--prophesy.', 'v (CLBL)<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>(Ithpael) to prophesy</OL>'),
(5014, 'bbn', 'a primitive root', 'nabab', 'TWOT - 1278', 'naw-bab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pierce; to be hollow, or (figuratively) foolish:--hollow, vain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to hollow out<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>hollowed (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(5015, 'wbn', 'probably of foreign derivation', 'Nbow', 'TWOT - 1279,1280', 'neb-o\'', '', 'probably of foreign derivation; Nebo, the name of a Babylonian deity, also of a mountain in Moab, and of a place in Palestine:--Nebo.', 'Nebo = \"prophet\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Babylonian deity who presided over learning and letters; corresponds to Greek Hermes, Latin Mercury, and Egyptian Thoth n pr loc<LI>a city in Moab and at one time assigned to Reuben; probably located on or near Mount Nebo<LI>a city in Judah (maybe Benjamin) from which the families of some exiles, who returned from Babylon with Zerubbabel, originally came<LI>the mountain where Moses died; located east of the Jordan opposite Jericho; site uncertain</OL>'),
(5016, 'hawbn', 'from (05012)', 'nbuw\'ah', 'TWOT - 1277b', 'neb-oo-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05012»; a prediction (spoken or written):--prophecy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>prophecy<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>prophecy<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>specific and genuine<LI>false</OL><LI>prophetic writing</OL></OL>'),
(5017, 'hawbn', 'corresponding to (05016)', 'nbuw\'ah', 'TWOT - 2843b', 'neb-oo-aw', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05016»; inspired teaching:--prophesying.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>prophesying</OL>'),
(5018, '!drzwbn', 'of foreign origin', 'Nbuwzaradan', 'None', 'neb-oo-zar-ad-awn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign origin; Nebuzaradan, a Babylonian general:--Nebuzaradan.', 'Nebuzaradan = \"Nebo has given seed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a general of Nebuchadnezzar\'s army at the capture of Jerusalem</OL>'),
(5019, 'rccandkwbn', 'of foreign derivation', 'Nbuwkadne\'tstsar', 'None', 'neb-oo-kad-nets-tsar\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Nbukadneotstsar (2 Kings 24:1, «010») {neb-oo-kad-nets-tsar\'}; or Nbuwkadnetstsar (Esther 2:6; Daniel 1:18) {neb-oo-kad-nets-tsar\'}; or Nbuwkadreotstsar {neb-oo-kad-rets-tsar\'}; or Nbuwkadreltstsowr (Ezra 2:1; Jeremiah 49:28) {neb-oo-kad-rets-tsore\'}; or foreign derivation; Nebukadnetstsar (or -retstsar, or -retstsor), king of Babylon:--Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuchadrezzar.', 'Nebuchadnezzar or Nebuchadrezzar = \"may Nebo protect the crown\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the great king of Babylon who captured Jerusalem and carried Judah captive</OL>'),
(5020, 'rccndkwbn', 'corresponding to (05019)', 'Nbuwkadnetstsar', 'None', 'neb-oo-kad-nets-tsar\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05019»:--Nebuchadnezzar.', 'Nebuchadnezzar = \"may Nebo protect the crown\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the great king of Babylon who captured Jerusalem and carried Judah captive</OL>'),
(5021, '!bzXwbn', 'of foreign derivation', 'Nbuwshazban', 'None', 'neb-oo-shaz-bawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign derivation; Nebushazban, Nebuchadnezzar\'s chief eunuch:--Nebushazban.', 'Nebushasban = \"Nebo delivers me\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the officers of Nebuchadnezzar at the capture of Jerusalem</OL>'),
(5022, 'twbn', 'from the same as (05011)', 'Nabowth', 'None', 'naw-both\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'feminine plural from the same as «05011»; fruits; Naboth, an Israelite:--Naboth.', 'Naboth = \"fruits\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the vineyard owner of Jezreel who Ahab and Jezebel had killed so that they could have his vineyard</OL>'),
(5023, 'hbzbn', 'of uncertain derivation', 'nbizbah', 'TWOT - 2844', 'neb-iz-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; a largess:--reward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>reward</OL>'),
(5024, 'xbn', 'a primitive root', 'nabach', 'TWOT - 1281', 'naw-bakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to bark (as a dog):--bark.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to bark</OL>'),
(5025, 'xbn', 'from (05024)', 'Nobach', 'None', 'no\'-bach', '', 'from «05024»; a bark; Nobach, the name of an Israelite, and of a place East of the Jordan:--Nobah.', 'Nobah = \"barking\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a warrior of Manasseh who during the conquest of the territory on the east of the Jordan possessed himself of the town of Kenath and surrounding villages n pr loc<LI>a place in Gilead which comprised the towns of Kenath and its surrounding villages captured by 1 above and renamed after himself; area eventually regained its original identity</OL>'),
(5026, 'zxbn', 'of foreign origin', 'Nibchaz', 'None', 'nib-khaz\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign origin; Nibchaz, a deity of the Avites:--Nibhaz.', 'Nibhaz = \"the barker\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a deity of the Avites introduced by them into Samaria in the time of Shalmaneser; idol had the figure of a dog</OL>'),
(5027, 'tbn', 'Nabat', 'nabat', 'naw-bat\'', 'naw-bat\'', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to look, regard<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to look<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to look<LI>to regard, show regard to, pay attention to, consider<LI>to look upon, regard, show regard to</OL></OL></OL>', 'a primitive root; to scan, i.e. look intently at; by implication, to regard with pleasure, favor or care:--(cause to) behold, consider, look (down), regard, have respect, see.', ''),
(5028, 'tbn', 'from (05027)', 'Nbat', 'None', 'neb-awt\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05027»; regard; Nebat, the father of Jeroboam I:--Nebat.', 'Nebat = \"aspect\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Ephraimite of Zereda, father of king Jeroboam I of the northern kingdom of Israel</OL>'),
(5029, 'aybn', 'corresponding to (05030)', 'nbiy\'', 'TWOT - 2843a', 'neb-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05030»; a prophet:--prophet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>prophet</OL>'),
(5030, 'aybn', 'from (05012)', 'nabiy\'', 'TWOT - 1277a', 'naw-bee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05012»; a prophet or (generally) inspired man:--prophecy, that prophesy, prophet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spokesman, speaker, prophet<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>prophet<LI>false prophet<LI>heathen prophet</OL></OL>'),
(5031, 'haybn', 'from (05030)', 'nbiy\'ah', 'TWOT - 1277c', 'neb-ee-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «05030»; a prophetess or (generally) inspired woman; by implication, a poetess; by association a prophet\'s wife:--prophetess.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>prophetess<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>ancient type endowed with gift of song (Miriam)<LI>later type consulted for a word (Huldah)<LI>false prophetess (Noadiah)<LI>wife of Isaiah the prophet</OL></OL>'),
(5032, 'twybn', 'from (05107)', 'Nbayowth', 'None', 'neb-aw-yoth\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'or Nbayoth {neb-aw-yoth\'}; feminine plural from «05107»; fruitfulnesses; Nebajoth, a son of Ismael, and the country settled by him:--Nebaioth, Nebajoth.', 'Nebaioth or Nebajoth = \"heights\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Ishmael<LI>people descended from 1 called the Nabateans with their capital at Petra</OL>'),
(5033, '$bn', 'from an unused root meaning to burst forth', 'nebek', 'TWOT - 1283', 'nay\'-bek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to burst forth; a fountain:--spring.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spring, springs</OL>'),
(5034, 'lbn', 'a primitive root', 'nabel', 'TWOT - 1286', 'naw-bale\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to wilt; generally, to fall away, fail, faint; figuratively, to be foolish or (morally) wicked; causatively, to despise, disgrace:--disgrace, dishounour, lightly esteem, fade (away, - ing), fall (down, -ling, off), do foolishly, come to nought, × surely, make vile, wither.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be senseless, be foolish<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be foolish<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to regard or treat as foolish<LI>to treat with contempt</OL></OL><LI>to sink or drop down, languish, wither and fall, fade<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sink or drop down<LI>to fall, wither and fall, fade<LI>to droop</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5035, 'lbn', 'from (05034)', 'nebel', 'TWOT - 1284a,1284b', 'neh\'-bel', 'Noun Masculine', 'or nebel {nay\'-bel}; from «05034»; a skin-bag for liquids (from collapsing when empty); hence, a vase (as similar in shape when full); also a lyre (as having a body of like form):--bottle, pitcher, psaltery, vessel, viol.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a skin-bag, jar, pitcher<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>skin-bottle, skin<LI>jar, pitcher (earthen)</OL><LI>harp, lute, guitar, musical instrument</OL>'),
(5036, 'lbn', 'from (05034)', 'nabal', 'TWOT - 1285a', 'naw-bawl\'', 'Adjective', 'from «05034»; stupid; wicked (especially impious):-- fool(-ish, -ish man, -ish woman), vile person.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>foolish, senseless, fool</OL>'),
(5037, 'lbn', 'the same as (05036)', 'Nabal', 'None', 'naw-bawl\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «05036»; dolt; Nabal, an Israelite:--Nabal.', 'Nabhal or Nabal = \"fool\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a man of Carmel who spurned David\'s messengers, then died of shock when he realised it might cause his death; his case was pleaded by his wife Abigail who became David\'s wife after his death</OL>'),
(5038, 'hlbn', 'from (05034)', 'nbelah', 'TWOT - 1286a', 'neb-ay-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05034»; a flabby thing, i.e. a carcase or carrion (human or bestial, often collectively); figuratively, an idol:-- (dead) body, (dead) carcase, dead of itself, which died, (beast) that (which) dieth of itself.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>carcass, corpse<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of humans, idols, animals</OL></OL>'),
(5039, 'hlbn', 'from (05036)', 'nbalah', 'TWOT - 1285b', 'neb-aw-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «05036»; foolishness, i.e. (morally) wickedness; concretely, a crime; by extension, punishment:--folly, vile, villany.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>senselessness, folly<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>disgraceful folly<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of immorality, profane actions</OL><LI>disgrace, contumely disgrace</OL></OL>'),
(5040, 'twlbn', 'from (05036)', 'nabluwth', 'TWOT - 1285c', 'nab-looth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05036»; properly, disgrace, i.e. the (female) pudenda:--lewdness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>immodesty, shamelessness, lewdness, pudenda (of female)</OL>'),
(5041, 'tllbn', 'apparently from (05036) and (03909)', 'Nballat', 'None', 'neb-al-lawt\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'apparently from «05036» and «03909»; foolish secrecy; Neballat, a place in Palestine:--Neballat.', 'Neballat = \"hidden folly\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town of Benjamin reoccupied after the captivity</OL>'),
(5042, '[bn', 'a primitive root', 'naba`', 'TWOT - 1287', 'naw-bah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to gush forth; figuratively, to utter (good or bad words); specifically, to emit (a foul odor):--belch out, flowing, pour out, send forth, utter (abundantly).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to flow, pour out, pour, gush forth, spring, bubble up, ferment<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to flow<LI>(Hiphil) to pour out, emit, cause to bubble, belch forth<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pour out<LI>to cause to bubble, ferment<LI>to pour forth, emit, belch forth</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5043, 'aXrbn', 'from an unused root meaning to shine', 'nebrsha\'', 'TWOT - 2845', 'neb-reh-shaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) from an unused root meaning to shine; a light; plural (collectively) a chandelier:--candlestick.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lamp stand, candlestick<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>not the 7 branch candlestick of the temple</OL></OL>'),
(5044, '!Xbn', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Nibshan', 'None', 'nib-shawn\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'of uncertain derivation; Nibshan, a place in Palestine:--Nibshan.', 'Nibshan = \"soft soil\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 6 cities of Judah which were in the wilderness</OL>'),
(5045, 'bgn', 'from an unused root meaning to be parched', 'negeb', 'TWOT - 1288a', 'neh\'-gheb', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to be parched; the south (from its drought); specifically, the Negeb or southern district of Judah, occasionally, Egypt (as south to Palestine):--south (country, side, -ward).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>south-country, Nekeb, south<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>south-country<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>region of southern Judah, boundaries not specific</OL><LI>south</OL></OL>'),
(5046, 'dgn', 'a primitive root', 'nagad', 'TWOT - 1289', 'naw-gad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to front, i.e. stand boldly out opposite; by implication (causatively), to manifest; figuratively, to announce (always by word of mouth to one present); specifically, to expose, predict, explain, praise:--bewray, × certainly, certify, declare(-ing), denounce, expound, × fully, messenger, plainly, profess, rehearse, report, shew (forth), speak, × surely, tell, utter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be conspicuous, tell, make known<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil) to tell, declare<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tell, announce, report<LI>to declare, make known, expound<LI>to inform of<LI>to publish, declare, proclaim<LI>to avow, acknowledge, confess 1a</OL><LI>messenger (participle)<LI>(Hophal) to be told, be announced, be reported</OL></OL>'),
(5047, 'dgn', 'corresponding to (05046)', 'ngad', 'TWOT - 2846', 'neg-ad\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05046»; to flow (through the idea of clearing the way):--issue.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Pael) to stream, flow</OL>'),
(5048, 'dgn', 'from (05046)', 'neged', 'TWOT - 1289a', 'neh\'-ghed', '', 'from «05046»; a front, i.e. part opposite; specifically a counterpart, or mate; usually (adverbial, especially with preposition) over against or before:--about, (over) against, × aloof, × far (off), × from, over, presence, × other side, sight, × to view.', 'subst<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>what is conspicuous, what is in front of adv<LI>in front of, straight forward, before, in sight of<LI>in front of oneself, straightforward<LI>before your face, in your view or purpose with prep<LI>what is in front of, corresponding to<LI>in front of, before<LI>in the sight or presence of<LI>parallel to<LI>over, for<LI>in front, opposite<LI>at a distance prep<LI>from the front of, away from<LI>from before the eyes of, opposite to, at a distance from<LI>from before, in front of<LI>as far as the front of</OL>'),
(5049, 'dgn', 'corresponding to (05048);', 'neged', 'TWOT - 2846a', 'neh\'-ghed', 'Preposition', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05048»; opposite:--toward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in front of, facing</OL>'),
(5050, 'hhgn', 'a primitive root', 'nagahh', 'TWOT - 1290', 'naw-gah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to glitter; causatively, to illuminate:--(en-)lighten, (cause to) shine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shine<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to shine<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to enlighten<LI>to cause to shine</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5051, 'hhgn', 'from (05050)', 'nogahh', 'TWOT - 1290a', 'no\'-gah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05050»; brilliancy (literally or figuratively):--bright(-ness), light, (clear) shining.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>brightness</OL>'),
(5052, 'hhgn', 'the same as (05051)', 'Nogahh', 'None', 'no\'-gah', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «05051»; Nogah, a son of David:--Nogah.', 'Nogah = \"brightness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 13 sons of David born to him in Jerusalem</OL>'),
(5053, 'hhgn', 'corresponding to (05051)', 'nogahh', 'TWOT - 2847', 'no\'-gah', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05051»; dawn:--morning.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>brightness, daylight</OL>'),
(5054, 'hhgn', 'from (05051)', 'ngohah', 'TWOT - 1290b', 'neg-o-haw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «05051»; splendor:--brightness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>brightness</OL>'),
(5055, 'xgn', 'a primitive root', 'nagach', 'TWOT - 1291', 'naw-gakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to but with the horns; figuratively, to war against:--gore, push (down, -ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to push, thrust, gore<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to gore<LI>(Piel) to push or thrust at<LI>(Hithpael) to engage in thrusting, wage war</OL></OL>'),
(5056, 'xggn', 'from (05055)', 'naggach', 'TWOT - 1291a', 'nag-gawkh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «05055»; butting, i.e. vicious:--used (wont) to push.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>addicted to goring, apt to gore</OL>'),
(5057, 'dygn', 'from (05046)', 'nagiyd', 'TWOT - 1289b', 'naw-gheed\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or nagid {naw-gheed\'}; from «05046»; a commander (as occupying the front), civil, military or religious; generally (abstractly, plural), honorable themes:--captain, chief, excellent thing, (chief) governor, leader, noble, prince, (chief) ruler.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>leader, ruler, captain, prince<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>ruler, prince<LI>prince-overseer<LI>ruler (in other capacities)<LI>princely things</OL></OL>'),
(5058, 'hnygn', 'from (05059)', 'ngiynah', 'TWOT - 1292.1a', 'neg-ee-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or ngiynath (Psa. 61:title) {neg-ee-nath\'}; from «05059»; properly, instrumental music; by implication, a stringed instrument; by extension, a poem set to music; specifically, an epigram:--stringed instrument, musick, Neginoth (plural), song.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>music, song, taunt song<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>music (of stringed instrument)<LI>song<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>taunting or mocking song</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5059, '!gn', 'a primitive root', 'nagan', 'TWOT - 1292.1', 'naw-gan\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to thrum, i.e. beat a tune with the fingers; expec. to play on a stringed instrument; hence (generally), to make music:--player on instruments, sing to the stringed instruments, melody, ministrel, play(-er, -ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to play or strike strings, play a stringed instrument<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>player (participle)</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to play 1b</OL><LI>player, minstrel (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(5060, '[gn', 'a primitive root', 'naga`', 'TWOT - 1293', 'naw-gah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to touch, i.e. lay the hand upon (for any purpose; euphem., to lie with a woman); by implication, to reach (figuratively, to arrive, acquire); violently, to strike (punish, defeat, destroy, etc.):--beat, (X be able to) bring (down), cast, come (nigh), draw near (nigh), get up, happen, join, near, plague, reach (up), smite, strike, touch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to touch, reach, strike<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to touch<LI>to strike<LI>to reach, extend to<LI>to be stricken 1a</OL><LI>stricken (participle)<LI>(Niphal) to be stricken, be defeated<LI>(Piel) to strike<LI>(Pual) to be stricken (by disease)<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to touch, reach, approach, arrive<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to touch, apply<LI>to reach, extend, attain, arrive, come<LI>to approach (of time)<LI>to befall (of fate)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5061, '[gn', 'from (05060)', 'nega`', 'TWOT - 1293a', 'neh\'-gah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05060»; a blow (figuratively, infliction); also (by implication) a spot (concretely, a leprous person or dress):--plague, sore, stricken, stripe, stroke, wound.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stroke, plague, disease, mark, plague spot<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>stroke, wound<LI>stroke (metaphorical of disease)<LI>mark (of leprosy)</OL></OL>'),
(5062, '@gn', 'a primitive root', 'nagaph', 'TWOT - 1294', 'naw-gaf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to push, gore, defeat, stub (the toe), inflict (a disease):--beat, dash, hurt, plague, slay, smite (down), strike, stumble, × surely, put to the worse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strike, smite<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to strike, smite<LI>(Niphal) to be stricken, be smitten<LI>(Hithpael) to stumble</OL></OL>'),
(5063, '@gn', 'from (05062)', 'negeph', 'TWOT - 1294a', 'neh\'-ghef', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05062»; a trip (of the foot); figuratively, an infliction (of disease):--plague, stumbling.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>blow, striking, plague<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>blow, plague (fatal)<LI>striking</OL></OL>'),
(5064, 'rgn', 'a primitive root', 'nagar', 'TWOT - 1295', 'naw-gar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to flow; figuratively, to stretch out; causatively, to pour out or down; figuratively, to deliver over:--fall, flow away, pour down (out), run, shed, spilt, trickle down.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pour, run, flow, pour down<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be poured, be spilt<LI>to pour oneself, flow, trickle<LI>to vanish (fig.)<LI>to be stretched out</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to pour down<LI>(Hophal) to melt</OL></OL>'),
(5065, 'Xgn', 'a primitive root', 'nagas', 'TWOT - 1296', 'naw-gas\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to drive (an animal, a workman, a debtor, an army); by implication, to tax, harass, tyrannize:--distress, driver, exact(-or), oppress(-or), ×  raiser of taxes, taskmaster.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to press, drive, oppress, exact, exert demanding pressure<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to press, drive<LI>to exact<LI>driver, taskmaster, ruler, oppressor, tyrant, lord, exactor of tribute (participle)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be hard pressed</OL></OL>'),
(5066, 'Xgn', 'a primitive root', 'nagash', 'TWOT - 1297', 'naw-gash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be or come (causatively, bring) near (for any purpose); euphemistically, to lie with a woman; as an enemy, to attack; relig. to worship; causatively, to present; figuratively, to adduce an argument; by reversal, to stand back:--(make to) approach (nigh), bring (forth, hither, near), (cause to) come (hither, near, nigh), give place, go hard (up), (be, draw, go) near (nigh), offer, overtake, present, put, stand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to draw near, approach<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to draw or come near<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of humans 1a</OL><LI>of sexual intercourse<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>of inanimate subject 1a</OL><LI>to approach one another<LI>(Niphal) to draw near<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to approach, bring near, bring<LI>(Hophal) to be brought near<LI>(Hithpael) to draw near</OL></OL>'),
(5067, 'dn', 'from (05110) in the sense of piling up', 'ned', 'TWOT - 1301a', 'nade', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05110» in the sense of piling up; a mound, i.e. wave:--heap.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>heap</OL>'),
(5068, 'bdn', 'a primitive root', 'nadab', 'TWOT - 1299', 'naw-dab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to impel; hence, to volunteer (as a soldier), to present spontaneously:--offer freely, be (give, make, offer self) willing(-ly).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to incite, impel, make willing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to incite, impel<LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to volunteer<LI>to offer free-will offerings</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5069, 'bdn', 'corresponding to (05068)', 'ndab', 'TWOT - 2848', 'ned-ab\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05068»; be (or give) liberal(-ly):--(be minded of...own) freewill (offering), offer freely (willingly).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to volunteer, offer freely<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Ithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to volunteer<LI>to give freely, offer freely</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5070, 'bdn', 'from (05068)', 'Nadab', 'None', 'naw-dawb\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05068»; liberal; Nadab, the name of four Israelites:--Nadab.', 'Nadab = \"generous\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>eldest son of Aaron by Elisheba; struck dead before the sanctuary in the wilderness for kindling the censers with strange fire<LI>son of king Jeroboam I of the northern kingdom of Israel and king of Israel for 2 years before being slain by Baasha<LI>a Jerahmeelite, son of Shammai, of the tribe of Judah<LI>a son of Gibeon of the tribe of Benjamin</OL>'),
(5071, 'hbdn', 'from (05068)', 'ndabah', 'TWOT - 1299a', 'ned-aw-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05068»; properly (abstractly) spontaneity, or (adjectively) spontaneous; also (concretely) a spontaneous or (by inference, in plural) abundant gift:--free(-will) offering, freely, plentiful, voluntary(-ily, offering), willing(-ly), offering).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>voluntariness, free-will offering<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>voluntariness<LI>freewill, voluntary, offering</OL></OL>'),
(5072, 'hybdn', 'from (05068) and (03050)', 'Ndabyah', 'None', 'ned-ab-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05068» and «03050»; largess of Jah; Nedabjah, an Israelite:--Nedabiah.', 'Nedabiah = \"whom Jehovah impels\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the sons of king Jehoiachin (Jeconiah) of Judah</OL>'),
(5073, '$bdn', 'from a root meaning to stick', 'nidbak', 'TWOT - 2849', 'nid-bawk\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a root meaning to stick; a layer (of building materials):--row.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>row, layer, course (of stones)</OL>'),
(5074, 'ddn', 'a primitive root', 'nadad', 'TWOT - 1300', 'naw-dad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to wave to and fro (rarely to flap up and down); figuratively, to rove, flee, or (causatively) to drive away:--chase (away), × could not, depart, flee (X apace, away), (re-)move, thrust away, wander (abroad, -er, -ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to retreat, flee, depart, move, wander abroad, stray, flutter<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to retreat, flee<LI>to flee, depart<LI>to wander, stray<LI>to flutter (of birds)</OL><LI>(Poal) to flee away, be chased<LI>(Hiphil) to chase away<LI>(Hophal) to be chased away<LI>(Hithpolel) to flee away</OL></OL>'),
(5075, 'ddn', 'corresponding to (05074)', 'ndad', 'TWOT - 2850', 'ned-ad\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05074»; to depart:--go from.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to flee</OL>'),
(5076, 'ddn', 'pass participle of (05074)', 'nadud', 'TWOT - 1300a', 'naw-dood\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'passive participle of «05074»; properly, tossed; abstractly, a rolling (on the bed):--tossing to and fro.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>tossing (of sleeplessness)</OL>'),
(5077, 'hdn', 'a primitive root', 'nadah', 'TWOT - 1302', 'naw-daw\'', 'Verb', 'or nada  (2 Kings 17:21) {naw-daw\'}; a primitive root; properly, to toss; figuratively, to exclude, i.e. banish, postpone, prohibit:--cast out, drive, put far away.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) exclude, drive away, thrust aside<LI>(Piel) cast out, put away</OL>'),
(5078, 'hdn', 'from (05077) in the sense of freely flinging money', 'nedeh', 'TWOT - 1303a', 'nay\'-deh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05077» in the sense of freely flinging money; a bounty (for prostitution):--gifts.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gift</OL>'),
(5079, 'hddn', 'from (05074)', 'niddah', 'TWOT - 1302a', 'nid-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05074»; properly, rejection; by implication, impurity, especially personal (menstruation) or moral (idolatry, incest):--X far, filthiness, × flowers, menstruous (woman), put apart, × removed (woman), separation, set apart, unclean(-ness, thing, with filthiness).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>impurity, filthiness, menstruous, set apart<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>impurity<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of ceremonial impurity<LI>of menstruation</OL><LI>impure thing (fig.)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of idolatry, immorality</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5080, 'xdn', 'a primitive root', 'nadach', 'TWOT - 1304', 'naw-dakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to push off; used in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively (to expel, mislead, strike, inflict, etc.):--banish, bring, cast down (out), chase, compel, draw away, drive (away, out, quite), fetch a stroke, force, go away, outcast, thrust away (out), withdraw.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to impel, thrust, drive away, banish<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to impel<LI>to thrust away, banish</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be impelled<LI>to be thrust out, be banished 1b</OL><LI>banished, outcast (participle)<OL TYPE=\"3\"><LI>to be driven away<LI>to be thrust away, thrust aside</OL><LI>(Pual) to be thrust into<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thrust (participle)</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to thrust, move, impel<LI>to thrust out, banish<LI>to thrust away, thrust aside</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be chased, be hunted<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chased, hunted (participle)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5081, 'bydn', 'from (05068)', 'nadiyb', 'TWOT - 1299b', 'naw-deeb\'', '', 'from «05068»; properly, voluntary, i.e. generous; hence, magnanimous; as noun, a grandee (sometimes a tyrant):--free, liberal (things), noble, prince, willing ((hearted)).', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>inclined, willing, noble, generous<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>incited, inclined, willing<LI>noble, princely (in rank)<LI>noble (in mind and character) n m</OL><LI>noble one</OL>'),
(5082, 'hbydn', 'from (05081)', 'ndiybah', 'TWOT - 1299c', 'ned-ee-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «05081»; properly, nobility, i.e. reputation:--soul.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nobility, nobleness, noble deeds<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>nobility (of rank), honour<LI>noble things</OL></OL>'),
(5083, '!dn', 'probably from an unused root meaning to give', 'nadan', 'TWOT - 1305', 'naw-dawn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from an unused root meaning to give; a present (for prostitution):--gift.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gift<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of a harlot\'s bribe</OL></OL>'),
(5084, '!dn', 'of uncertain derivation', 'nadan', 'TWOT - 1306', 'naw-dawn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; a sheath (of a sword):--sheath.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sheath</OL>'),
(5085, 'hndn', 'from the same as (05084)', 'nidneh', 'TWOT - 2851', 'nid-neh\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from the same as «05084»; a sheath; figuratively, the body (as the receptacle of the soul):--body.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sheath<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning uncertain</OL></OL>'),
(5086, '@dn', 'a primitive root', 'nadaph', 'TWOT - 1307', 'naw-daf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to shove asunder, i.e. disperse:--drive (away, to and fro), thrust down, shaken, tossed to and fro.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to drive, drive away, drive asunder<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to drive about<LI>(Niphal) to be driven, be driven about</OL></OL>'),
(5087, 'rdn', 'a primitive root', 'nadar', 'TWOT - 1308', 'naw-dar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to promise (pos., to do or give something to God):--(make a) vow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to vow, make a vow<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to vow a vow</OL></OL>'),
(5088, 'rdn', 'from (05087)', 'neder', 'TWOT - 1308a', 'neh\'-der', 'Noun Masculine', 'or neder {nay\'-der}; from «05087»; a promise (to God); also (concretely) a thing promised:--vow((-ed)).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vow, votive offering</OL>'),
(5089, 'hhn', 'from an unused root meaning to lament', 'noahh', 'TWOT - 1320a', 'no\'-ah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to lament; lamentation:--wailing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>eminency, distinction</OL>'),
(5090, 'ghn', 'a primitive root', 'nahag', 'TWOT - 1309,1310', 'naw-hag\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to drive forth (a person, an animal or chariot), i.e. lead, carry away; reflexively, to proceed (i.e. impel or guide oneself); also (from the panting induced by effort), to sigh:--acquaint, bring (away), carry away, drive (away), lead (away, forth), (be) guide, lead (away, forth).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to drive, lead, guide, conduct<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to drive, lead on, drive away, drive off<LI>to behave itself (fig.) (of heart)</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to drive away, lead off<LI>to lead on, guide, guide on<LI>to cause to drive</OL></OL><LI>(Piel) to moan, lament</OL>'),
(5091, 'hhn', 'a primitive root', 'nahah', 'TWOT - 1311', 'naw-haw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to groan, i.e. bewail; hence (through the idea of crying aloud), to assemble (as if on proclamation):-- lament, wail.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wail, lament<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to wail, lament<LI>(Niphal) to go mourning after</OL></OL>'),
(5092, 'yhn', 'from (05091)', 'nhiy', 'TWOT - 1311a', 'neh-hee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05091»; an elegy:--lamentation, wailing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wailing, lamentation, mourning song<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>wailing<LI>mourning song</OL></OL>'),
(5093, 'hyhn', 'from (05092)', 'nihyah', 'TWOT - 1311b', 'nih-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «05092»; lamentation:--doleful.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wailing, lament, lamentation, mourning song</OL>'),
(5094, 'ryhn', 'from the same as (05105)', 'nhiyr', 'TWOT - 2853a,2853b', 'neh-heere\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) or nehiyruw (Aramaic) {neh-hee-roo\'}; from the same as «05105»; illumination, i.e. (figuratively) wisdom:--light.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>light</OL>'),
(5095, 'lhn', 'a primitive root', 'nahal', 'TWOT - 1312', 'naw-hal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to run with a sparkle, i.e. flow; hence (transitively), to conduct, and (by inference) to protect, sustain:--carry, feed, guide, lead (gently, on).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lead, give rest, lead with care, guide to a watering place or station, cause to rest, bring to a station or place of rest, guide, refresh<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lead to a watering-place or station and cause to rest there<LI>to lead or bring to a station or goal<LI>to lead, guide<LI>to give rest to<LI>to refresh (with food)</OL><LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lead on<LI>to journey by stations or stages</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5096, 'llhn', 'the same as (05097)', 'Nahalal', 'None', 'nah-hal-awl\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Nahalol {nah-hal-ole\'}; the same as «05097»; Nahalal or Nahalol, a place in Palestine:--Nahalal, Nahallal, Nahalol.', 'Nahalal or Nahallal or Nahalol = \"pasture\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the cities of Zebulun given to the Merarite Levites<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>site uncertain<LI>maybe modern \'Malul\', a village in the plain of Esdraelon</OL></OL>'),
(5097, 'llhn', 'from (05095)', 'nahalol', 'TWOT - 1312a', 'nah-hal-ole\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05095»; pasture:--bush.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pasture, watering-place</OL>'),
(5098, '~hn', 'a primitive root', 'naham', 'TWOT - 1313', 'naw-ham\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to growl:--mourn, roar(-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to growl, groan<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to growl (of lion)<LI>to groan (of sufferer)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5099, '~hn', 'from (05098)', 'naham', 'TWOT - 1313a', 'nah\'-ham', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05098»; a snarl:--roaring.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>growling, roaring<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of lion<LI>of king\'s wrath (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(5100, 'hmhn', 'from (05099)', 'nhamah', 'TWOT - 1313b', 'neh-haw-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «05099»; snarling:--disquietness, roaring.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>growling, groaning</OL>'),
(5101, 'qhn', 'a primitive root', 'nahaq', 'TWOT - 1314', 'naw-hak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to bray (as an ass), scream (from hunger:--bray.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to bray, cry, cry out</OL>'),
(5102, 'rhn', 'a primitive root', 'nahar', 'TWOT - 1316,1315', 'naw-har\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to sparkle, i.e. (figuratively) be cheerful; hence (from the sheen of a running stream) to flow, i.e. (figuratively) assemble:--flow (together), be lightened.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shine, beam, light, burn<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to beam, be radiant</OL><LI>to flow, stream<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to flow, stream</OL></OL>'),
(5103, 'rhn', 'from a root corresponding to (05102)', 'nhar', 'TWOT - 2852', 'neh-har\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «05102»; a river, especially the Euphrates:--river, stream.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>river</OL>'),
(5104, 'rhn', 'from (05102)', 'nahar', 'TWOT - 1315a', 'naw-hawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05102»; a stream (including the sea; expec. the Nile, Euphrates, etc.); figuratively, prosperity:--flood, river.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stream, river<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>stream, river<LI>(underground) streams</OL></OL>'),
(5105, 'hrhn', 'from (05102) in its original sense', 'nharah', 'TWOT - 1316a', 'neh-haw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05102» in its original sense; daylight:--light.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>light, daylight</OL>'),
(5106, 'awn', 'a primitive root', 'nuw\'', 'TWOT - 1317', 'noo', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to refuse, forbid, dissuade, or neutralize:--break, disallow, discourage, make of none effect.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hinder, hold back, forbid, disallow, restrain, frustrate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to hinder, hold back<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to restrain, forbid, frustrate<LI>to restrain, make averse, discourage</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5107, 'bwn', 'a primitive root', 'nuwb', 'TWOT - 1318', 'noob', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to germinate, i.e. (figuratively) to (causatively, make) flourish; also (of words), to utter:--bring forth (fruit), make cheerful, increase.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bear fruit<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to bear fruit<LI>(Pilel) to make to flourish (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(5108, 'bwn', 'from (05107)', 'nowb', 'TWOT - 1318a,1318b', 'nobe', 'Noun Masculine', 'or neyb {nabe}; from «05107»; produce, literally or figuratively:--fruit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fruit</OL>'),
(5109, 'ybwn', 'from (05108)', 'Nowbay', 'None', 'no-bah\'ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05108»; fruitful; Nobai, an Israelite:--Nebai (from the margin).', 'Nebai = \"fruitful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a family of the heads of the people who signed the covenant with Nehemiah</OL>'),
(5110, 'dwn', 'a primitive root', 'nuwd', 'TWOT - 1319', 'nood', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to nod, i.e. waver; figuratively, to wander, flee, disappear; also (from shaking the head in sympathy), to console, deplore, or (from tossing the head in scorn) taunt:--bemoan, flee, get, mourn, make to move, take pity, remove, shake, skip for joy, be sorry, vagabond, way, wandering.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shake, waver, wander, move to and fro, flutter, show grief, have compassion on<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to move to and fro, wander (aimlessly), take flight<LI>to flutter<LI>to waver, wave, shake<LI>to show grief 1a</OL><LI>to lament, condole, show sympathy<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to wander (aimlessly)<LI>to make a wagging, wag (with the head)</OL><LI>(Hithpolel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to move oneself to and fro, sway, totter<LI>to shake oneself<LI>to bemoan oneself</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5111, 'dwn', 'corresponding to (05116)', 'nuwd', 'TWOT - 2854', 'nood', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05116»; to flee:--get away.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to flee</OL>'),
(5112, 'dwn', 'from (05110)', 'nowd', 'TWOT - 1319a', 'node', 'Noun Masculine', '(only defect. nod {node}); from «05110»; exile:--wandering.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wandering (of aimless fugitive)</OL>'),
(5113, 'dwn', 'the same as (05112)', 'Nowd', 'None', 'node', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «05112»; vagrancy; Nod, the land of Cain:--Nod.', 'Nod = \"\"wandering\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>land to which Cain fled or wandered after the murder of Abel</OL>'),
(5114, 'bdwn', 'from (05068)', 'Nowdab', 'None', 'no-dawb\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05068»; noble; Nodab, an Arab tribe:--Nodab.', 'Nodab = \"nobility\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Arab tribe probably descended from Nodab, son of Ishmael and grandson of Abraham</OL>'),
(5115, 'hwn', 'a primitive root', 'navah', 'TWOT - 1321,1322', 'naw-vaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to rest (as at home); causatively (through the implied idea of beauty (compare «05116»)), to celebrate (with praises):--keept at home, prepare an habitation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to beautify<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil) to beautify, adorn</OL><LI>to dwell<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to dwell, abide, keep at home</OL><LI>(Hophal) rest</OL>'),
(5116, 'hwn', 'from (05115)', 'naveh', 'TWOT - 1322a,1322b,1322c', 'naw-veh\'', '', 'or (feminine) navah {naw-vaw\'}; from «05115»; (adjectively) at home; hence (by implication of satisfaction) lovely; also (noun) a home, of God (temple), men (residence), flocks (pasture), or wild animals (den):--comely, dwelling (place), fold, habitation, pleasant place, sheepcote, stable, tarried.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>abode, habitation, abode of shepherds or flocks, pasture<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>abode (of sheep)<LI>abode (of shepherds)<LI>meadow<LI>habitation adj</OL><LI>dwelling, abiding</OL>'),
(5117, 'xwn', 'a primitive root', 'nuwach', 'TWOT - 1323', 'noo\'-akh', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to rest, i.e. settle down; used in a great variety of applications, literal and figurative, intransitive, transitive and causative (to dwell, stay, let fall, place, let alone, withdraw, give comfort, etc.):--cease, be confederate, lay, let down, (be) quiet, remain, (cause to, be at, give, have, make to) rest, set down. Compare «03241».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rest<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rest, settle down and remain<LI>to repose, have rest, be quiet</OL><LI>(Hiph)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to rest, give rest to, make quiet<LI>to cause to rest, cause to alight, set down<LI>to lay or set down, deposit, let lie, place<LI>to let remain, leave<LI>to leave, depart from<LI>to abandon<LI>to permit</OL><LI>(Hoph)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to obtain rest, be granted rest<LI>to be left, be placed<LI>open space (subst)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5118, 'xwn', 'from (05117)', 'nuwach', 'TWOT - 1323?', 'noo\'-akh', 'Noun Masculine', 'or nowach {no\'-akh}; from «05117»; quiet:--rest(-ed, -ing place).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>resting place</OL>'),
(5119, 'hxwn', 'from (05118)', 'Nowchah', 'None', 'no-chaw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'feminine of «05118»; quietude; Nochah, an Israelite:--Nohah.', 'Nohah = \"rest\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 4th son of Benjamin</OL>'),
(5120, 'twn', 'to quake', 'nuwt', 'TWOT - 1324', 'noot', 'Verb', 'to quake:--be moved.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to quake, shake, dangle</OL>'),
(5121, 'tywn', 'from (05115)', 'Naviyth', 'None', 'naw-veeth\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «05115»; residence; Navith, a place in Palestine:--Naioth (from the margin).', 'Naioth = \"habitations\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a dwelling place of prophets in the time of Samuel</OL>'),
(5122, 'wlwn', 'from an unused root probably meaning to be foul', 'nvaluw', 'TWOT - 2855', 'nev-aw-loo\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) or nvaliy (Aramaic) {nev-aw-lee\'}; from an unused root probably meaning to be foul; a sink:--dunghill.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>refuse-heap, dunghill, outhouse</OL>'),
(5123, '~wn', 'a primitive root', 'nuwm', 'TWOT - 1325', 'noom', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to slumber (from drowsiness):--sleep, slumber.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be drowsy, slumber, sleep<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to slumber, be drowsy</OL></OL>'),
(5124, 'hmwn', 'from (05123)', 'nuwmah', 'TWOT - 1325a', 'noo-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05123»; sleepiness:--drowsiness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>drowsiness, somnolence, indolence (fig.)</OL>'),
(5125, '!wn', 'a primitive root', 'nuwn', 'TWOT - 1326', 'noon', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to resprout, i.e. propagate by shoots; figuratively, to be perpetual:--be continued.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Niphal) continue, to increase, propagate<LI>(Hiphil) continue, to increase, propagate</OL>'),
(5126, '!wn', 'from (05125)', 'Nuwn', 'None', 'noon', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Nown (1 Chron. 7:27) {nohn}; from «05125»; perpetuity, Nun or Non, the father of Joshua:--Non, Nun.', 'Nun = \"fish\" or \"posterity\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Joshua the successor of Moses</OL>'),
(5127, 'own', 'a primitive root', 'nuwc', 'TWOT - 1327', 'noos', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to flit, i.e. vanish away (subside, escape; causatively, chase, impel, deliver):--X abate, away, be displayed, (make to) flee (away, -ing), put to flight, × hide, lift up a standard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to flee, escape<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to flee<LI>to escape<LI>to take flight,m depart, disappear<LI>to fly (to the attack) on horseback</OL><LI>(Polel) to drive at<LI>(Hithpolel) to take flight<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to put to flight<LI>to drive hastily<LI>to cause to disappear, hide</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5128, '[wn', 'a primitive root', 'nuwa`', 'TWOT - 1328', 'noo\'-ah', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to waver, in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively (as subjoined):--continually, fugitive, × make, to (go) up and down, be gone away, (be) move(-able, -d), be promoted, reel, remove, scatter, set, shake, sift, stagger, to and fro, be vagabond, wag, (make) wander (up and down).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to quiver, totter, shake, reel, stagger, wander, move, sift, make move, wave, waver, tremble<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wave, quiver, vibrate, swing, stagger, tremble, be unstable<LI>to totter, go tottering 1a</OL><LI>vagabond (participle)<LI>(Niphal) to be tossed about or around<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to toss about<LI>to shake, cause to totter<LI>to shake, disturb<LI>to cause to wander</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5129, 'hyd[wn', 'from (03259) and (03050)', 'Now`adyah', 'None', 'no-ad-yaw\'', '', 'from «03259» and «03050»; convened of Jah; Noadjah, the name of an Israelite, and a false prophetess:--Noadiah.', 'Noadiah = \"meeting with Jehovah\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite, son of Binnui, who weighed the vessels of gold and silver belonging to the temple which were brought back from Babylon n pr f<LI>a prophetess who joined Sanballat and Tobiah in their attempt to intimidate Nehemiah</OL>'),
(5130, '@wn', 'a primitive root', 'nuwph', 'TWOT - 1329,1330', 'noof', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to quiver (i.e. vibrate up and down, or rock to and fro); used in a great variety of applications (including sprinkling, beckoning, rubbing, bastinadoing, sawing, waving, etc.):--lift up, move, offer, perfume, send, shake, sift, strike, wave.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to move to and fro, wave, besprinkle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to besprinkle, sprinkle<LI>(Polel) to wave, brandish (in threat)<LI>(Hiphil) to swing, wield, wave<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wield<LI>to wave or shake (the hand) 1c</OL><LI>to wave (hand) 1c<LI>to shake or brandish against 1c<LI>to swing to and fro<OL TYPE=\"3\"><LI>to wave (an offering), offer<LI>to shed abroad</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be waved</OL></OL>'),
(5131, '@wn', 'from (05130)', 'nowph', 'TWOT - 1331a', 'nofe', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05130»; elevation:--situation. Compare «05297».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>elevation, height</OL>'),
(5132, '#wn', 'a primitive root', 'nuwts', 'TWOT - 1399', 'noots', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to flash; hence, to blossom (from the brilliancy of color); also, to fly away (from the quickness of motion):--flee away, bud (forth).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to fly, flee<LI>(Hiphil) to bloom, blossom</OL>'),
(5133, 'hcwn', 'from (005327) in the sense of flying', 'nowtsah', 'TWOT - 1399a', 'no-tsaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or notsah {no-tsaw\'}; feminine active participle of «05327» in the sense of flying; a pinion (or wing feather); often (collectively) plumage:--feather(-s), ostrich.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>plumage, feathers</OL>'),
(5134, 'qwn', 'a primitive root', 'nuwq', 'TWOT - 1332', 'nook', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to suckle:--nurse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to suckle, nurse</OL>'),
(5135, 'rwn', 'from an unused root (corresponding to that of (05216)) meaning to shine', 'nuwr', 'TWOT - 2856', 'noor', 'Noun', '(Aramaic) from an unused root (corresponding to that of «05216») meaning to shine; fire:--fiery, fire.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fire</OL>'),
(5136, 'Xwn', 'a primitive root', 'nuwsh', 'TWOT - 1334', 'noosh', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be sick, i.e. (figuratively) distressed:--be full of heaviness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be sick</OL>'),
(5137, 'hzn', 'a primitive root', 'nazah', 'TWOT - 1335,1336', 'naw-zaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to spirt, i.e. besprinkle (especially in expiation):--sprinkle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to spurt, spatter, sprinkle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to spurt, spatter<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to spurt, sprinkle upon</OL><LI>to spring, leap<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil) to cause to leap, startle</OL></OL>'),
(5138, 'dyzn', 'from (02102)', 'naziyd', 'TWOT - 547d', 'naw-zeed\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «02102»; something boiled, i.e. soup:--pottage.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>boiled food, soup, pottage, thing sodden or boiled</OL>'),
(5139, 'ryzn', 'from (05144)', 'naziyr', 'TWOT - 1340b', 'naw-zeer\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or nazir {naw-zeer\'}; from «05144»; separate, i.e. consecrated (as prince, a Nazirite); hence (figuratively from the latter) an unpruned vine (like an unshorn Nazirite):--Nazarite (by a false alliteration with Nazareth), separate(-d), vine undressed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>consecrated or devoted one, Nazarite<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>consecrated one<LI>devotee, Nazarite<LI>untrimmed (vine)</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(5140, 'lzn', 'a primitive root', 'nazal', 'TWOT - 1337', 'naw-zal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to drip, or shed by trickling:--distil, drop, flood, (cause to) flow(-ing), gush out, melt, pour (down), running water, stream.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to flow, distil, flow forth or down, trickle, drop<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to flow 1a</OL><LI>streams, floods (participle)<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to distil</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to cause to flow</OL></OL>'),
(5141, '~n', 'from an unused root of uncertain meaning', 'nexem', 'TWOT - 1338a', 'neh\'-zem', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root of uncertain meaning;  a nose-ring:--earring, jewel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ring, nose ring, earring<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>nose ring (woman\'s ornament)<LI>earring (ornament of men or women)</OL></OL>'),
(5142, 'qzn', 'corresponding to the root of (05143)', 'nzaq', 'TWOT - 2857', 'nez-ak\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to the root of «05143»; to suffer (causatively, inflict) loss:--have (en-)damage, hurt(-ful).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to suffer injury<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to suffer injury<LI>(Aphel) to injure</OL></OL>'),
(5143, 'qzn', 'from an unused root meaning to injure', 'nezeq', 'TWOT - 1339', 'nay\'zek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to injure; loss:--damage.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>injury, damage</OL>'),
(5144, 'rzn', 'a primitive root', 'nazar', 'TWOT - 1340', 'naw-zar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to hold aloof, i.e. (intransitivey) abstain (from food and drink, from impurity, and even from divine worship (i.e. apostatize)); specifically, to set apart (to sacred purposes), i.e. devote:--consecrate, separate(-ing, self).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dedicate, consecrate, separate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to dedicate oneself, devote oneself<LI>(Hiphil) to keep sacredly separate</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to be a Nazarite, live as a Nazarite</OL>'),
(5145, 'rzn', 'from (05144)', 'nezer', 'TWOT - 1340a', 'neh\'-zer', 'Noun Masculine', 'or nezer {nay\'-zer}; from «05144»; properly, something set apart, i.e. (abstractly) dedication (of a priet or Nazirite); hence (concretely) unshorn locks; also (by implication) a chaplet (especially of royalty):--consecration, crown, hair, separation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>consecration, crown, separation, Nazariteship<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>crown (as sign of consecration), earring<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stones of a crown, diadem, stones of charming</OL><LI>woman\'s hair<LI>consecration<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of high priest<LI>of Nazarite</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5146, 'xn', 'the same as (05118)', 'Noach', 'TWOT - 1323b', 'no\'-akh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «05118»; rest; Noach, the patriarch of the flood:--Noah.', 'Noah = \"rest\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Lamech, father of Shem, Ham, and Japheth; builder of the ark which saved his family from the destruction of the world which God sent on the world by the flood; became the new seminal head of mankind because his family were the only survivors of the flood</OL>'),
(5147, 'ybxn', 'from (02247)', 'Nachbiy', 'None', 'nakh-bee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «02247»; occult; Nachbi, an Israelite:--Nakbi.', 'Nahbi = \"hidden\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Vophsi, a Naphtalite, and one of the 12 spies sent to spy out the promised land</OL>'),
(5148, 'hxn', 'a primitive root', 'nachah', 'TWOT - 1341', 'naw-khaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to guide; by implication, to transport (into exile, or as colonists):--bestow, bring, govern, guide, lead (forth), put, straiten.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lead, guide<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to lead, bring<LI>(Hiphil) to lead, guide</OL></OL>'),
(5149, '~wxn', 'from (05162)', 'Nchuwm', 'None', 'neh-khoom\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05162»; comforted; Nechum, an Israelite:--Nehum.', 'Nehum = \"comfort\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the exiles who returned from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(5150, '~wxn', 'from (05162)', 'nichuwm', 'TWOT - 1344b', 'nee-khoom\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or nichum {nee-khoom\'}; from «05162»; properly, consoled; abstractly, solace:--comfort(-able), repenting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>comfort, compassion<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>comfort<LI>compassion</OL></OL>'),
(5151, '~wxn', 'from (05162)', 'Nachuwm', 'None', 'nakh-oom\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05162»; comfortable; Nachum, an Israelite prophet:--Nahum.', 'Nahum = \"comfort\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the Elkoshite, prophet who predicted the fall and destruction of Nineveh; writer of the book by his name; personal history and situation unknown</OL>'),
(5152, 'rwxn', 'from the same as (05170)', 'Nachowr', 'None', 'naw-khore\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «05170»; snorer; Nochor, the name of the grandfather and a brother of Abraham:--Nahor.', 'Nahor = \"snorting\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Serug, father of Terah, and grandfather of Abraham<LI>son of Terah and brother of Abraham</OL>'),
(5153, 'Xwxn', 'apparently pass participle of (05172) (perhaps in the sense of ringing, i.e. bell-metal', 'nachuwsh', 'TWOT - 1349b', 'naw-khoosh\'', 'Adjective', 'apparently passive participle of «05172» (perhaps in the sense of ringing, i.e. bell-metal; or from the red color of the throat of a serpent (5175, as denominative) when hissing); coppery, i.e. (figuratively) hard:--of brass.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bronze</OL>'),
(5154, 'hXwxn', 'from (05153)', 'nchuwshah', 'TWOT - 1349b', 'nekh-oo-shaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or nchushah {nekh-oo-shaw\'}; feminine of «05153»; copper:--brass, steel. Compare «05176».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>copper, bronze<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>copper (made from melting copper ore)<LI>bronze (made from copper and alloy)</OL></OL>'),
(5155, 'hlyxn', 'probably denominative from (02485)', 'nchiylah', 'TWOT - 1342b', 'nekh-ee-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'probably denominative from «02485»; a flute:--(plural) Nehiloth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>meaning uncertain<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>may be name of melody<LI>may be a musical instrument<LI>found only in title of PS 5</OL></OL>'),
(5156, 'ryxn', 'from the same as (05170)', 'nchiyr', 'TWOT - 1346c', 'nekh-eer\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «05170»; a nostril:--(dual) nostrils.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nostril</OL>'),
(5157, 'lxn', 'a primitive root', 'nachal', 'TWOT - 1342', 'naw-khal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to inherit (as a (figurative) mode of descent), or (generally) to occupy; causatively, to bequeath, or (generally) distribute, instate:--divide, have ((inheritance)), take as a heritage, (cause to, give to, make to) inherit, (distribute for, divide (for, for an, by), give for, have, leave for, take (for)) inheritance, (have in, cause to, be made to) possess(-ion).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to get as a possession, acquire, inherit, possess<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to take possession, inherit<LI>to have or get as a possession or property (fig.)<LI>to divide the land for a possession<LI>to acquire (testimonies) (fig.)</OL><LI>(Piel) to divide for a possession<LI>(Hithpael) to possess oneself of<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give as a possession<LI>to cause to inherit, give as an inheritance</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be allotted, be made to possess</OL></OL>'),
(5158, 'lxn', 'from (05157) in its original sense', 'nachal', 'TWOT - 1343a,1343b', 'nakh\'-al', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (feminine) nachlah (Psalm 124:4) {nakh\'-law}; or nachalah (Ezekiel 47:19; 48:28) {nakh-al-aw\'}; from «05157» in its original sense; a stream, especially a winter torrent; (by implication) a (narrow) valley (in which a brook runs); also a shaft (of a mine):--brook, flood, river, stream, valley.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>torrent, valley, wadi, torrent-valley<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>torrent<LI>torrent-valley, wadi (as stream bed)<LI>shaft (of mine)</OL><LI>palm-tree<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(5159, 'hlxn', 'from (05157) (in its usual sense)', 'nachalah', 'TWOT - 1342a', 'nakh-al-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05157» (in its usual sense); properly, something inherited, i.e. (abstractly) occupancy, or (concretely) an heirloom; generally an estate, patrimony or portion:--heritage, to inherit, inheritance, possession. Compare «05158».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>possession, property, inheritance, heritage<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>property<LI>portion, share<LI>inheritance, portion</OL></OL>'),
(5160, 'laylxn', 'from (05158) and (0410)', 'Nachaliy\'el', 'None', 'nakh-al-ee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «05158» and «0410»; valley of God; Nachaliel, a place in the Desert:--Nahaliel.', 'Nahaliel = \"torrents of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a station of Israel in the wilderness; located north of the Arnon</OL>'),
(5161, 'ymlxn', 'apparently a patronymic from an unused name (apparently pass. participle of (02492))', 'Nechelamiy', 'None', 'nekh-el-aw-mee\'', 'Adjective', 'apparently a patronymic from an unused name (apparently passive participle of «02492»); dreamed; a Nechelamite, or descendant of Nechlam:--Nehelamite.', 'Nehelamite = \"he of the dream\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the designation of a false prophet Shemaiah taken into captivity to Babylon; name is formed from his native place or his progenitor</OL>'),
(5162, '~xn', 'a primitive root', 'nacham', 'TWOT - 1344', 'naw-kham\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to sigh, i.e. breathe strongly; by implication, to be sorry, i.e. (in a favorable sense) to pity, console or (reflexively) rue; or (unfavorably) to avenge (oneself):--comfort (self), ease (one\'s self), repent(-er,-ing, self).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be sorry, console oneself, repent, regret, comfort, be comforted<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be sorry, be moved to pity, have compassion<LI>to be sorry, rue, suffer grief, repent<LI>to comfort oneself, be comforted<LI>to comfort oneself, ease oneself</OL><LI>(Piel) to comfort, console<LI>(Pual) to be comforted, be consoled<LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be sorry, have compassion<LI>to rue, repent of<LI>to comfort oneself, be comforted<LI>to ease oneself</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5163, '~xn', 'from (05162)', 'Nacham', 'None', 'nakh\'-am', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05162»; consolation; Nacham, an Israelite:--Naham.', 'Naham = \"comfort\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the brother of IIodiah or Jehudijah, wife of Ezra</OL>'),
(5164, '~xn', 'from (05162)', 'nocham', 'TWOT - 1344a', 'no\'-kham', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05162»; ruefulness, i.e. desistance:--repentance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>repentance, sorrow</OL>'),
(5165, 'hmxn', 'from (05162)', 'nechamah', 'TWOT - 1344c', 'nekh-aw-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05162»; consolation:--comfort.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>comfort</OL>'),
(5166, 'hymxn', 'from (05162) and (03050)', 'Nchemyah', 'None', 'nekh-em-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05162» and «03050»; consolation of Jah; Nechemjah, the name of three Israelites:--Nehemiah.', 'Nehemiah = \"Jehovah comforts\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of Hachaliah, cupbearer to king Artaxerxes, who became governor of Judah after the return from exile<LI>one of the 12 heads of the people who returned from exile with Zerubbabel<LI>son of Azbuk and ruler of the half part of Beth-zur, who helped to repair the wall of Jerusalem</OL>'),
(5167, 'ynmxn', 'from (05162)', 'Nachamaniy', 'None', 'nakh-am-aw-nee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05162»; consolatory; Nachamani, an Israelite:--Nahamani.', 'Nahamani = \"merciful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a chief man among the exiles who returned from Babylon with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(5168, 'wnxn', 'for (0587)', 'nachnuw', 'TWOT - 128a', 'nakh-noo\'', '', 'for «0587»; we:--we.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>we</OL>'),
(5169, '#xn', 'a primitive root', 'nachats', 'TWOT - 1345', 'naw-khats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be urgent:--require haste.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to urge<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be urgent (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(5170, 'rxn', 'from an unused root meaning to snort or snore', 'nachar', 'TWOT - 1346,1346a,1346b', 'nakh\'-ar', 'Noun', 'and (feminine) nacharah {nakh-ar-aw\'}; from an unused root meaning to snort or snore; a snorting:--nostrils, snorting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>snorting</OL>'),
(5171, 'yrxn', 'from the same as (05170)', 'Nacharay', 'None', 'nakh-ar-ah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Nachray {nakh-rah\'-ee}; from the same as «05170»; snorer; Nacharai or Nachrai, an Israelite:--Naharai, Nahari.', 'Naharai = \"snorter\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of David\'s mighty warriors and the armour bearer of Joab</OL>'),
(5172, 'Xxn', 'a primitive root', 'nachash', 'TWOT - 1348', 'naw-khash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to hiss, i.e. whisper a (magic) spell; generally, to prognosticate:--X certainly, divine, enchanter, (use) × enchantment, learn by experience, × indeed, diligently observe.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to practice divination, divine, observe signs, learn by experience, diligently observe, practice fortunetelling, take as an omen<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to practice divination<LI>to observe the signs or omens</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5173, 'Xxn', 'from (05172)', 'nachash', 'TWOT - 1348a', 'nakh\'-ash', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05172»; an incantation or augury:--enchantment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>divination, enchantment</OL>'),
(5174, 'Xxn', 'corresponding to (05154)', 'nchash', 'TWOT - 2858', 'nekh-awsh\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05154»; copper:--brass.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>copper, bronze</OL>'),
(5175, 'Xxn', 'from (05172)', 'nachash', 'TWOT - 1347a', 'naw-khawsh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05172»; a snake (from its hiss):--serpent.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>serpent, snake<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>serpent<LI>image (of serpent)<LI>fleeing serpent (mythological)</OL></OL>'),
(5176, 'Xxn', 'the same as (05175)', 'Nachash', 'None', 'naw-khawsh\'', '', 'the same as «05175»; Nachash, the name of two persons apparently non-Israelite:--Nahash.', 'Nahash = \"serpent\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a king of the Ammonites during the time of king Saul<LI>the father of Abigail, the mother of Amasa, the commander of Absalom\'s army</OL>'),
(5177, '!wXxn', 'from (05172)', 'Nachshown', 'None', 'nakh-shone\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05172»; enchanter; Nachshon, an Israelite:--Naashon, Nahshon.', 'Nahshon = \"enchanter\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Amminadab and prince of the Judah at the first numbering in the wilderness; 5th in descent from Judah in the genealogy of Christ</OL>'),
(5178, 'tXxn', 'for (05154)', 'nchosheth', 'TWOT - 1349a,1350a', 'nekh-o\'-sheth', 'Noun Masculine', 'for «05154»; copper, hence, something made of that metal, i.e. coin, a fetter; figuratively, base (as compared with gold or silver):--brasen, brass, chain, copper, fetter (of brass), filthiness, steel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>copper, bronze<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>copper (ore), bronze (as copper alloy)<LI>fetters (of copper or bronze)<LI>copper (as value)</OL><LI>lust, harlotry<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(5179, 'atXxn', 'from (05178)', 'Nchushta\'', 'None', 'nekh-oosh-taw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'from «05178»; copper; Nechushta, an Israelitess:--Nehushta.', 'Nehushta = \"brass\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>daughter of Elnathan, wife of king Jehoiakim of Judah and mother of king Jehoiachin of Judah</OL>'),
(5180, '!tXxn', 'from (05178)', 'Nchushtan', 'TWOT - 1347b', 'nekh-oosh-tawn\'', 'Noun', 'from «05178»; something made of copper, i.e. the copper serpent of the Desert:--Nehushtan.', 'Nehushtan = \"a thing of brass\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>name by which the brazen serpent made by Moses in the wilderness was worshipped in the time of king Hezekiah of Judah before he destroyed it</OL>'),
(5181, 'txn', 'a primitive root', 'nachath', 'TWOT - 1351', 'naw-khath\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to sink, i.e. descend; causatively, to press or lead down:--be broken, (cause to) come down, enter, go down, press sore, settle, stick fast.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go down, descend<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go down, descend<LI>to descend, descend into (chastisement) (fig.)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to come down into, penetrate<LI>(Piel) to cause to descend, press down, stretch (a bow)<LI>(Hiphil) to bring down</OL></OL>'),
(5182, 'txn', 'corresponding to (05181)', 'nchath', 'TWOT - 2859', 'nekh-ath\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05181»; to descend; causatively, to bring away, deposit, depose:--carry, come down, depose, lay up, place.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to descend<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to descend<LI>(Aphel) to deposit<LI>(Hophal) to be deposed, be cast down</OL></OL>'),
(5183, 'txn', 'from (05182)', 'Nachath', 'TWOT - 1323a,1351a', 'nakh\'-ath', 'Noun', 'from «05182»; a descent, i.e. imposition, unfavorable (punishment) or favorable (food); also (intransitively; perhaps from «05117»), restfulness:--lighting down, quiet(-ness), to rest, be set on.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rest, quietness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>quietness, quiet attitude<LI>rest (of death)</OL><LI>descent (of judgment)</OL>'),
(5184, 'txn', 'the same as (05183)', 'Nachath', 'None', 'nakh\'-ath', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «05183»; quiet; Nachath, the name of an Edomite and of two Israelites:--Nahath.', 'Nahath = \"rest\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the dukes of Edom, son of Reuel and grandson of Esau<LI>a Kohathite Levite, son of Zophai and grandson of Elkanah<LI>an Levite overseer in the time of Hezekiah</OL>'),
(5185, 'txn', 'from (05181)', 'nacheth', 'TWOT - 1351b', 'naw-khayth\'', 'Adjective', 'from «05181»; descending:--come down.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descending</OL>'),
(5186, 'htn', 'a primitive root', 'natah', 'TWOT - 1352', 'naw-taw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to stretch or spread out; by implication, to bend away (including moral deflection); used in a great variety of application (as follows):--+ afternoon, apply, bow (down, - ing), carry aside, decline, deliver, extend, go down, be gone, incline, intend, lay, let down, offer, outstretched, overthrown, pervert, pitch, prolong, put away, shew, spread (out), stretch (forth, out), take (aside), turn (aside, away), wrest, cause to yield.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to stretch out, extend, spread out, pitch, turn, pervert, incline, bend, bow<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to stretch out, extend, stretch, offer<LI>to spread out, pitch (tent)<LI>to bend, turn, incline 1a</OL><LI>to turn aside, incline, decline, bend down 1a<LI>to bend, bow 1a<LI>to hold out, extend (fig.)<LI>(Niphal) to be stretched out<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to stretch out<LI>to spread out<LI>to turn, incline, influence, bend down, hold out, extend, thrust aside, thrust away</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5187, 'lytn', 'from (05190)', 'ntiyl', 'TWOT - 1353b', 'net-eel\'', 'Adjective', 'from «05190»; laden:--that bear.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>laden</OL>'),
(5188, 'hpytn', 'from (05197)', 'ntiyphah', 'TWOT - 1355c', 'net-ee-faw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05197»; a pendant for the ears (especially of pearls):--chain, collar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>drop<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>pendant, ornament</OL></OL>'),
(5189, 'hXytn', 'from (05203)', 'ntiyshah', 'TWOT - 1357a', 'net-ee-shaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05203»; a tendril (as an offshoot):--battlement, branch, plant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>twig, tendril, tendrils of a vine (as spread out)</OL>'),
(5190, 'ltn', 'a primary root', 'natal', 'TWOT - 1353', 'naw-tal\'', 'Verb', 'a prim root; to lift; by implication, to impose:--bear, offer, take up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lift, bear, bear up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to lift, lift over, lift upon, set up<LI>(Piel) to bear up</OL></OL>'),
(5191, 'ltn', 'corresponding to (05190)', 'ntal', 'TWOT - 2860', 'net-al\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05190»; to raise:--take up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lift<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to lift, lift up<LI>(P\'il) to be lifted</OL></OL>'),
(5192, 'ltn', 'a burden', 'netel', 'TWOT - 1353a', 'nay\'-tel', 'Noun Masculine', ': from «05190»; a burden:--weighty.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>burden, weight</OL>'),
(5193, '[tn', 'a primitive root', 'nata`', 'TWOT - 1354', 'naw-tah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to strike in, i.e. fix; specifically, to plant (literally or figuratively):--fastened, plant(- er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to plant, fasten, fix, establish<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to plant<LI>to plant, establish (fig.)</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be planted<LI>to be established (fig.)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5194, '[tn', 'from (05193)', 'neta`', 'TWOT - 1354a', 'neh\'-tah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05193»; a plant; collectively, a plantation; abstractly, a planting:--plant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>plantation, plant, planting<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>plantation<LI>planting (act of)<LI>plant</OL></OL>'),
(5195, '[tn', 'from (05193)', 'natia`', 'TWOT - 1354b', 'naw-tee\'-ah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05193»; a plant:--plant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>plant (fig. of vigorous sons)</OL>'),
(5196, '~y[tn', 'from (05194)', 'Nta`iym', 'None', 'net-aw-eem\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'plural of «05194»; Netaim, a place in Palestine:--plants.', 'Netaim = \"among plants\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in Palestine</OL>'),
(5197, '@tn', 'a primitive root', 'nataph', 'TWOT - 1355', 'naw-taf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to ooze, i.e. distil gradually; by implication, to fall in drops; figuratively, to speak by inspiration:--drop(-ping), prophesy(-et).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to drop, drip, distil, prophesy, preach, discourse<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to drop, drip<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to drip<LI>to drop (prophecy)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5198, '@tn', 'from (05197)', 'nataph', 'TWOT - 1355a,1355b', 'naw-tawf\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05197»; a drop; specifically, an aromatic gum (probably stacte):--drop, stacte.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>drop<LI>gum, drops of stacte<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>an aromatic gum resin of a shrub used in incense</OL></OL>'),
(5199, 'hptn', 'from (05197)', 'Ntophah', 'None', 'net-o-faw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «05197»; distillation; Netophah, a place in Palestine:--Netophah.', 'Netophah = \"dropping\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Judah resettled by the exiles returning from Babylon with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(5200, 'ytptn', 'from (05199)', 'Ntophathiy', 'None', 'net-o-faw-thee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymic from «05199»; a Netophathite, or inhabitant of Netophah:--Netophathite.', 'Netophathite = see Netophath \"dropping\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Netophah</OL>'),
(5201, 'rtn', 'a primitive root', 'natar', 'TWOT - 1356', 'naw-tar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to guard; figuratively, to cherish (anger):--bear grudge, keep(-er), reserve.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to keep, keep guard, reserve, maintain<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to keep, maintain<LI>to keep, guard</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5202, 'rtn', 'corresponding to (05201)', 'ntar', 'TWOT - 2861', 'net-ar\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05201»; to retain:--keep.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to keep</OL>'),
(5203, 'Xtn', 'a primitive root', 'natash', 'TWOT - 1357', 'naw-tash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to pound, i.e. smite; by implication (as if beating out, and thus expanding) to disperse; also, to thrust off, down, out or upon (inclusively, reject, let alone, permit, remit, etc.):--cast off, drawn, let fall, forsake, join (battle), leave (off), lie still, loose, spread (self) abroad, stretch out, suffer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to leave, permit, forsake, cast off or away, reject, suffer, join, spread out or abroad, be loosed, cease, abandon, quit, hang loose, cast down, make a raid, lie fallow, let fall, forgo, draw<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to leave, let alone, lie fallow, entrust to<LI>to forsake, abandon<LI>to permit</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be forsaken<LI>to be loosened, be loose<LI>to be let go, spread abroad</OL><LI>(Pual) to be abandoned, be deserted</OL></OL>'),
(5204, 'yn', 'a doubtful word', 'niy', 'TWOT - 1311c', 'nee', 'Noun Masculine', 'a doubtful word; apparently from «05091»; lamentation:-- wailing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wailing</OL>'),
(5205, 'dyn', 'from (05110)', 'niyd', 'TWOT - 1319b', 'need', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05110»; motion (of the lips in speech):--moving.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>quivering (motion) of lips</OL>'),
(5206, 'hdyn', 'from (05205)', 'niydah', 'TWOT - 1302b', 'nee-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «05205»; removal, i.e. exile:--removed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>impure, filthiness, impurity</OL>'),
(5207, 'xwxn', 'from (05117)', 'nichowach', 'TWOT - 1323c', 'nee-kho\'-akh', 'Noun Masculine', 'or niychoach {nee-kho\'-akh}; from «05117»; properly, restful, i.e. pleasant; abstractly, delight:--sweet (odour).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>soothing, quieting, tranquillising</OL>'),
(5208, 'xwxyn', 'corresponding to (05207)', 'niychowach', 'TWOT - 2862', 'nee-kho\'-akh', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) or (shorter) niychoach (Aramaic) {nee-kho\'-akh}; corresponding to «05207»; pleasure:--sweet odour (savour).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>soothing, tranquillising</OL>'),
(5209, '!yn', 'from (05125)', 'niyn', 'TWOT - 1326a', 'neen', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05125»; progeny:--son.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>offspring, posterity</OL>'),
(5210, 'hwnyn', 'of foreign origin', 'Niynveh', 'None', 'nee-nev-ay\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'of foreign origin; Nineveh, the capital of Assyria:--Nineveh.', 'Nineveh = \"abode of Ninus\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>capital of the ancient kingdom of Assyria; located on the east bank of the Tigris river, 550 miles (880 km) from its mouth and 250 miles (400 km) north of Babylon</OL>'),
(5211, 'oyn', 'from (05127)', 'niyc', 'TWOT - 1327', 'neece', '', 'from «05127»; fugitive:--that fleeth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>refuge, a fleeing one</OL>'),
(5212, '!oyn', 'probably of foreign origin', 'Niycan', 'TWOT - 1359', 'nee-sawn\'', 'Noun', 'probably of foreign origin; Nisan, the first month of the Jewish sacred year:--Nisan.', 'Nisan = \"their flight\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 1st month of the Jewish calendar corresponding to Mar or Apr</OL>'),
(5213, '#wcyn', 'from (05340)', 'niytsowts', 'TWOT - 1405a', 'nee-tsotes\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05340»; a spark:--spark.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spark</OL>'),
(5214, 'ryn', 'a root probably identical with that of (05216), through the idea of the gleam of a fresh furrow', 'niyr', 'TWOT - 1360', 'neer', 'Verb', 'a root probably identical with that of «05216», through the idea of the gleam of a fresh furrow; to till the soil:--break up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to break up, freshly plough or till</OL>'),
(5215, 'ryn', 'from (05214)', 'niyr', 'TWOT - 1360a', 'neer', 'Noun Masculine', 'or nir {neer}; from «05214»; properly, plowing, i.e. (concretely) freshly plowed land:--fallow ground, plowing, tillage.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>tillable or untilled or fallow ground</OL>'),
(5216, 'ryn', 'from a primitive root [see (05214); (05135)] properly, meaning to glisten', 'niyr', 'TWOT - 1333b', 'neer', 'Noun Masculine', 'or nir {neer}; also neyr {nare}; or ner {nare}; or (feminine) nerah {nay-raw\'}; from a primitive root (see «05214»; «05135») properly, meaning to glisten; a lamp (i.e. the burner) or light (literally or figuratively):--candle, lamp, light.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lamp</OL>'),
(5217, 'akn', 'a primitive root', 'naka\'', 'TWOT - 1362', 'naw-kaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to smite, i.e. drive away:--be viler.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Niph) to strike, scourge, smite</OL>'),
(5218, 'akn', 'from (05217)', 'nake\'', 'TWOT - 1362a,1362b', 'naw-kay\'', 'Adjective', 'or nakat {naw-kaw\'}; from «05217»; smitten, i.e. (figuratively) afflicted:--broken, stricken, wounded.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stricken</OL>'),
(5219, 'takn', 'from (05218)', 'nko\'th', 'TWOT - 1362c', 'nek-ohth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05218»; properly, a smiting, i.e. (concretely) an aromatic gum (perhaps styrax) (as powdered):--spicery(-ces).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a spice<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps tragacanth gum</OL></OL>'),
(5220, 'dkn', 'from an unused root meaning to propagate', 'neked', 'TWOT - 1363a', 'neh\'-ked', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to propagate; offspring:--nephew, son\'s son.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>progeny, posterity</OL>'),
(5221, 'hkn', 'a primitive root', 'nakah', 'TWOT - 1364', 'naw-kaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to strike (lightly or severely, literally or figuratively):--beat, cast forth, clap, give (wounds), ×  go forward, × indeed, kill, make (slaughter), murderer, punish, slaughter, slay(-er, -ing), smite(-r, -ing), strike, be stricken, (give) stripes, × surely, wound.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strike, smite, hit, beat, slay, kill<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be stricken or smitten<LI>(Pual) to be stricken or smitten<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to smite, strike, beat, scourge, clap, applaud, give a thrust<LI>to smite, kill, slay (man or beast)<LI>to smite, attack, attack and destroy, conquer, subjugate, ravage<LI>to smite, chastise, send judgment upon, punish, destroy</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be smitten<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to receive a blow<LI>to be wounded<LI>to be beaten<LI>to be (fatally) smitten, be killed, be slain<LI>to be attacked and captured<LI>to be smitten (with disease)<LI>to be blighted (of plants)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5222, 'hkn', 'from (05221)', 'nekeh', 'TWOT - 1364b', 'nay-keh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «05221»; a smiter, i.e. (figuratively) traducer:--abject.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stricken, smitten</OL>'),
(5223, 'hkn', 'TWOT - (1364)a', 'nakeh', 'adj', 'naw-keh\'', '', 'smitten, i.e. (literally) maimed, or (figuratively) dejected:--contrite, lame.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stricken, smitten</OL>'),
(5224, 'wkn', 'probably of Egyptian origin', 'Nkow', 'None', 'nek-o\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably of Egyptian origin; Neko, an Egyptian king:--Necho. Compare «06549».', 'Necho = \"lame\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the Pharaoh of Egypt in the time of king Josiah of Judah</OL>'),
(5225, '!wkn', 'from (03559)', 'Nakown', 'None', 'naw-kone\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «03559»; prepared; Nakon, probably an Israelite:--Nachon.', 'Nachon = \"prepared\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the owner of the threshing floor which the ark was passing on the trip to Jerusalem when it started to fall off the cart, Uzzah steadied it, and God smote him dead for touching it</OL>'),
(5226, 'xkn', 'from an unused root meaning to be straightforward', 'nekach', 'TWOT - 1365a', 'nay\'-kakh', '', 'from an unused root meaning to be straightforward; properly, the fore part; used adverbially, opposite:--before, over against.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>be in front of adv<LI>in front of, opposite to, in the sight of, before, to the front, right on prep<LI>towards the front of, in front of, on behalf of, as far as in front of</OL>'),
(5227, 'xkn', 'from the same as (05226)', 'nokach', 'TWOT - 1365a', 'no\'-kakh', '', 'from the same as «05226»; properly, the front part; used adverbially (especially with preposition), opposite, in front of, forward, in behalf of:--(over) against, before, direct(-ly), for, right (on).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>be in front of adv<LI>in front of, opposite to, in the sight of, before, to the front, right on prep<LI>towards the front of, in front of, on behalf of, as far as in front of</OL>'),
(5228, 'xkn', 'from the same as (05226)', 'nakoach', 'TWOT - 1365a', 'naw-ko\'-akh', '', 'from the same as «05226»; straightforward, i.e. (figuratively), equitable, correct, or (abstractly), integrity:--plain, right, uprightness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>straight, right, straightness, be in front of</OL>'),
(5229, 'hxkn', 'from (05228)', 'nkochah', 'TWOT - 1365a', 'nek-o-khaw\'', 'Adjective Feminine', 'feminine of «05228»; properly, straightforwardness, i.e. (figuratively) integrity, or (concretely) a truth:--equity, right (thing), uprightness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>straight in front, be in front of, straight, right, straightness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>true things (of prophecy)<LI>rectitude (subst)</OL></OL>'),
(5230, 'lkn', 'a primary root', 'nakal', 'TWOT - 1366', 'naw-kal\'', 'Verb', 'a prim root; to defraud, i.e. act treacherously:--beguile, conspire, deceiver, deal subtilly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be deceitful, be crafty, be knavish<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be knavish<LI>deceiver (participle)</OL><LI>(Piel) to beguile<LI>(Hithpael) to act craftily, act knavishly, deal knavishly</OL></OL>'),
(5231, 'lkn', 'from (05230)', 'nekel', 'TWOT - 1366a', 'nay\'-kel', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05230»; deceit:--wile.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cunning, wiliness, craft, knavery</OL>'),
(5232, 'okn', 'corresponding to (05233)', 'nkac', 'TWOT - 2863', 'nek-as\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05233»:--goods.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>riches, property</OL>'),
(5233, 'okn', 'from an unused root meaning to accumulate', 'nekec', 'TWOT - 1367', 'neh\'-kes', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to accumulate; treasure:--riches, wealth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>riches, treasures</OL>'),
(5234, 'rkn', 'a primitive root', 'nakar', 'TWOT - 1368', 'naw-kar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to scrutinize, i.e. look intently at; hence (with recognition implied), to acknowledge, be acquainted with, care for, respect, revere, or (with suspicion implied), to disregard, ignore, be strange toward, reject, resign, dissimulate (as if ignorant or disowning):--acknowledge, × could, deliver, discern, dissemble, estrange, feign self to be another, know, take knowledge (notice), perceive, regard, (have) respect, behave (make) self strange(-ly).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to recognise, acknowledge, know, respect, discern, regard<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be recognised<LI>(Piel) to regard<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to regard, observe, pay attention to, pay regard to, notice<LI>to recognise (as formerly known), perceive<LI>to be willing to recognise or acknowledge, acknowledge with honour<LI>to be acquainted with<LI>to distinguish, understand</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to make oneself known</OL><LI>to act or treat as foreign or strange, disguise, misconstrue<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to disguise oneself<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to treat as foreign (profane)<LI>to misconstrue</OL><LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to act as alien<LI>to disguise oneself</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5235, 'rkn', 'from (05234)', 'neker', 'TWOT - 1368a', 'neh\'-ker', 'Noun Masculine', 'or noker {no\'-ker}; from «05234»; something strange, i.e. unexpected calamity:--strange.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>calamity, disaster, misfortune</OL>'),
(5236, 'rkn', 'from (05234)', 'nekar', 'TWOT - 1368b', 'nay-kawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', '\' from «05234»; foreign, or (concretely) a foreigner, or (abstractly) heathendom:--alien, strange (+ -er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>foreign, alien, foreignness, that which is foreign<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>foreignness, foreign gods<LI>alien, foreigner<LI>foreign (vanities)</OL></OL>'),
(5237, 'yrkn', 'from (05235) (second form)', 'nokriy', 'TWOT - 1368c', 'nok-ree\'', 'Adjective', 'from «05235» (second form); strange, in a variety of degrees and applications (foreign, non-relative, adulterous, different, wonderful):--alien, foreigner, outlandish, strange(-r, woman).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>foreign, alien<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>foreign<LI>foreigner (subst)<LI>foreign woman, harlot<LI>unknown, unfamiliar (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(5238, 'tkn', 'probably for (05219)', 'nkoth', 'TWOT - 1369', 'nek-oth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'probably for «05219»; spicery, i.e. (generally) valuables:--precious things.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>treasure</OL>'),
(5239, 'hln', 'apparently a primitive root', 'nalah', 'TWOT - 1370', 'naw-law\'', 'Verb', 'apparently a primitive root; to complete:--make an end.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to complete, bring to an end<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning doubtful</OL></OL>'),
(5240, 'hzbmn', 'from (0959)', 'nmibzeh', 'TWOT - 224', 'nem-ib-zeh\'', '', 'from «0959», despised:--vile.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vile, despised, disdained, held in contempt</OL>'),
(5241, 'lawmn', 'apparently for (03223)', 'Nmuw\'el', 'None', 'nem-oo-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'apparently for «03223»; Nemuel, the name of two Israelites:--Nemuel.', 'Nemuel = \"day of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the eldest son of Simeon<LI>a Reubenite, son of Eliab and brother of Dathan and Abiram in the time of the exodus</OL>'),
(5242, 'ylawmn', 'from (05241)', 'Nmuw\'eliy', 'None', 'nem-oo-ay-lee\'', 'Adjective', 'from «05241»; a Nemuelite, or descendant of Nemuel:--Nemuelite.', 'Nemuelites = see Nemuel \"day of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Nemuel</OL>'),
(5243, 'lmn', 'a primitive root', 'namal', 'TWOT - 1161', 'naw-mal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to become clipped or (specifically) circumcised:--(branch to) be cut down (off), circumcise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to circumcise, become clipped, be circumcised, be cut off</OL>'),
(5244, 'hlmn', 'from (05243)', 'nmalah', 'TWOT - 1371a', 'nem-aw-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from «05243»; an ant (probably from its almost bisected form):--ant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ant</OL>'),
(5245, 'rmn', 'corresponding to (05246)', 'nmar', 'TWOT - 2864', 'nem-ar\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05246»:--leopard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>leopard</OL>'),
(5246, 'rmn', 'from an unused root meaning properly, to filtrate, i.e. be limpid [comp (05247) and (05249)]', 'namer', 'TWOT - 1372a', 'naw-mare\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning properly, to filtrate, i.e. be limpid (comp «05247» and «05249»); and thus to spot or stain as if by dripping; a leopard (from its stripes):--leopard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>leopard</OL>'),
(5247, 'hrmn', 'from the same as (05246)', 'Nimrah', 'None', 'nim-raw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the same as «05246»; clear water; Nimrah, a place East of the Jordan:--Nimrah. See also «01039», «05249».', 'Nimrah = \"limpid\" or \"pure\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place on the east of the Jordan, 10 miles (16 km) north of the Dead Sea and 3 miles (5 km) east of the Jordan</OL>'),
(5248, 'dwrmn', 'probably of foreign origin', 'Nimrowd', 'None', 'nim-rode\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Nimrod {nim-rode\'}; probably of foreign origin; Nimrod, a son of Cush:--Nimrod.', 'Nimrod = \"rebellion\" or \"the valiant\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of Cush, grandson of Ham, and great grandson of Noah; a mighty hunter, he established an empire in the area of Babylon and Assyria</OL>'),
(5249, '~yrmn', 'corresponding to (05247)', 'Nimriym', 'None', 'nim-reem\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'plural of a masculine corresponding to «05247»; clear waters; Nimrim, a place East of the Jordan:--Nimrim. Compare «01039».', 'Nimrim = \"limpid\" or \"pure\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a stream or brook in the territory of Moab</OL>'),
(5250, 'yXmn', 'probably from (04871)', 'Nimshiy', 'None', 'nim-shee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «04871»; extricated; Nimshi, the (grand-)father of Jehu:--Nimshi.', 'Nimshi = \"rescued\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>grandfather of Jehu</OL>'),
(5251, 'on', 'from (05264)', 'nec', 'TWOT - 1379a', 'nace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05264»; a flag; also a sail; by implication, a flagstaff; generally a signal; figuratively, a token:--banner, pole, sail, (en-)sign, standard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>something lifted up, standard, signal, signal pole, ensign, banner, sign, sail<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>standard (as rallying point), signal<LI>standard (pole)<LI>ensign, signal</OL></OL>'),
(5252, 'hbbon', 'participle pass. of (05437)', 'ncibbah', 'TWOT - 1456a', 'nes-ib-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine participle passive of «05437»; properly, an environment, i.e. circumstance or turn of affairs:--cause.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>turn of affairs, a bringing about</OL>'),
(5253, 'gon', 'a primitive root', 'nacag', 'TWOT - 1469', 'naw-sag\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to retreat:--departing away, remove, take (hold), turn away.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to move away, backslide, move, go, turn back<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to backslide, prove recreant to<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to displace, move back<LI>to remove, carry away</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be driven back, be moved back</OL></OL>'),
(5254, 'hon', 'a primitive root', 'nacah', 'TWOT - 1373', 'naw-saw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to test; by implication, to attempt:--adventure, assay, prove, tempt, try.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to test, try, prove, tempt, assay, put to the proof or test<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to test, try<LI>to attempt, assay, try<LI>to test, try, prove, tempt</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5255, 'xon', 'a primitive root', 'nacach', 'TWOT - 1374', 'naw-sakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to tear away:--destroy, pluck, root.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pull or tear away<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to tear away, tear down<LI>(Niphal) to be torn away</OL></OL>'),
(5256, 'xon', 'corresponding to (05255)', 'ncach', 'TWOT - 2865', 'nes-akh\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05255»:--pull down.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pull or tear away<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Ithp\'al) to be torn away</OL></OL>'),
(5257, '$yon', 'from (05258)', 'nciyk', 'TWOT - 1375b,1377a', 'nes-eek\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05258»; properly, something poured out, i.e. a libation; also a molten image; by implication, a prince (as anointed):--drink offering, duke, prince(-ipal).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>poured out, libation, molten image, one anointed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>libation, drink-offering<LI>molten image</OL><LI>prince, anointed one</OL>'),
(5258, '$on', 'a primitive root', 'nacak', 'TWOT - 1375,1377', 'naw-sak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pour out, especially a libation, or to cast (metal); by analogy, to anoint a king:--cover, melt, offer, (cause to) pour (out), set (up).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pour out, pour, offer, cast<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pour out<LI>to cast metal images<LI>to anoint (a king)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be anointed<LI>(Piel) to pour out (as a libation)<LI>(Hiphil) to pour out libations<LI>(Hophal) to be poured out</OL><LI>to set, install<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to install<LI>(Niphal) to be installed</OL></OL>'),
(5259, '$on', 'a primitive root [probably identical with (05258) through the idea fusion]', 'nacak', 'TWOT - 1376', 'naw-sak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (probably identical with «05258» through the idea of fusion); to interweave, i.e. (figuratively) to overspread:--that is spread.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to weave</OL>'),
(5260, '$on', 'corresponding to (05258)', 'ncak', 'TWOT - 2866', 'nes-ak\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05258»; to pour out a libation:--offer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pour out, offer sacrifice<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pael) to pour out, offer (a sacrifice)</OL></OL>'),
(5261, '$on', 'corresponding to (05262)', 'ncak', 'TWOT - 2866a', 'nes-ak\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05262»; a libation:--drink offering.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>something poured out, libation, drink offering, libation offering</OL>'),
(5262, '$on', 'from (05258)', 'necek', 'TWOT - 1375a', 'neh\'-sek', 'Noun Masculine', 'or necek {nay\'-sek}; from «05258»; a libation; also a cast idol:--cover, drink offering, molten image.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>drink offering, libation, molten image, something poured out<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>drink offering<LI>molten images</OL></OL>'),
(5263, 'oon', 'a primitive root', 'nacac', 'TWOT - 1378', 'naw-sas\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to wane, i.e. be sick:--faint.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be sick</OL>'),
(5264, 'oon', 'a primitive root', 'nacac', 'TWOT - 1379', 'naw-sas\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to gleam from afar, i.e. to be conspicuous as a signal; or rather perhaps a denominative from «05251» (and identical with «05263», through the idea of a flag as fluttering in the wind); to raise a beacon:--lift up as an ensign.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be lifted up (meaning dubious)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hithpoel) to be lifted up, be displayed</OL></OL>'),
(5265, '[on', 'a primitive root', 'naca`', 'TWOT - 1380', 'naw-sah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to pull up, especially the tent-pins, i.e. start on a journey:--cause to blow, bring, get, (make to) go (away, forth, forward, onward, out), (take) journey, march, remove, set aside (forward), × still, be on his (go their) way.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pull out, pull up, set out, journey, remove, set forward, depart<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pull out or up<LI>to set out, depart<LI>to journey, march<LI>to set forth (of wind)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be pulled up, be removed, be plucked up<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to set out, lead out, cause to spring up<LI>to remove, quarry</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5266, 'qon', 'a primitive root', 'nacaq', 'TWOT - 1511', 'naw-sak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to go up:--ascend.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to ascend</OL>'),
(5267, 'qon', 'corresponding to (05266)', 'ncaq', 'TWOT - 2889', 'nes-ak\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05266»:--take up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to ascend, come up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Aphel) to lift, take up<LI>(Hophal) to be taken up</OL></OL>'),
(5268, '$ron', 'of foreign origin', 'Nicrok', 'TWOT - 1382', 'nis-roke\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign origin; Nisrok, a Babylonian idol:--Nisroch.', 'Nisroch = \"the great eagle\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an idol of Nineveh worshipped by Sennacherib; symbolised by the eagle-headed human figure</OL>'),
(5269, 'h[n', 'from (05128)', 'Ne`ah', 'None', 'nay-aw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «05128»; motion; Neah, a place in Palestine:--Neah.', 'Neah = \"shaking\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a boundary mark of the territory of Zebulun; site unknown</OL>'),
(5270, 'h[n', 'from (05128)', 'No`ah', 'None', 'no-aw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'from «05128»; movement; Noah, an Israelitess:--Noah.', 'Noah = \"motion\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 5 daughters of Zelophehad in the time of the exodus</OL>'),
(5271, 'rw[n', 'properly, pass. participle from (05288) as denominative', 'na`uwr', 'TWOT - 1389d,1389e', 'naw-oor\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or naur {naw-oor\'}; and (feminine) nturah {neh- oo-raw\'}; properly, passive participle from «05288» as denominative; (only in plural collectively or emphatic form) youth, the state (juvenility) or the persons (young people):--childhood, youth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>youth, early life</OL>'),
(5272, 'lay[n', 'from (05128) and (0410)', 'N`iy\'el', 'None', 'neh-ee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «05128» and «0410»; moved of God; Neiel, a place in Palestine:--Neiel.', 'Neiel = \"moved by God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place on the border of the territory of Asher</OL>'),
(5273, '~y[n', 'from (05276)', 'na`iym', 'TWOT - 1384b,1385a', 'naw-eem\'', 'Adjective', 'from «05276»; delightful (objective or subjective, literal or figurative):--pleasant(-ure), sweet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pleasant, delightful, sweet, lovely, agreeable<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>delightful<LI>lovely, beautiful (physical)</OL><LI>singing, sweetly sounding, musical</OL>'),
(5274, 'l[n', 'a primitive root', 'na`al', 'TWOT - 1383,1383b', 'naw-al\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to fasten up, i.e. with a bar or cord; hence (denominative from «05275»), to sandal, i.e. furnish with slippers:--bolt, inclose, lock, shoe, shut up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bar, lock, bolt<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to bar, lock, bolt</OL><LI>to furnish with sandals, shoe<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to shoe<LI>(Hiphil) to give sandals</OL></OL>'),
(5275, 'l[n', 'from (05274)', 'na`al', 'TWOT - 1383a', 'nah\'-al', 'Noun Feminine', 'or (feminine) na;alah {nah-al-aw\'}; from «05274»; properly, a sandal tongue; by extens. a sandal or slipper (sometimes as a symbol of occupancy, a refusal to marry, or of something valueless):--dryshod, (pair of) shoe((-latchet), -s).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sandal, shoe</OL>'),
(5276, '~[n', 'a primitive root', 'na`em', 'TWOT - 1384', 'naw-ame\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be agreeable (literally or figuratively):--pass in beauty, be delight, be pleasant, be sweet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be pleasant, be beautiful, be sweet, be delightful, be lovely</OL>'),
(5277, '~[n', 'from (05276)', 'Na`am', 'None', 'nah\'-am', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05276»; pleasure; Naam, an Israelite:--Naam.', 'Naam = \"pleasantness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the sons of Caleb and grandson of Jephunneh</OL>'),
(5278, '~[n', 'from (05276)', 'no`am', 'TWOT - 1384a', 'no\'-am', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05276»; agreeableness, i.e. delight, suitableness, splendor or grace:--beauty, pleasant(-ness).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>kindness, pleasantness, delightfulness, beauty, favour<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>delightfulness<LI>symbolic name of one of two staves<LI>pleasantness</OL></OL>'),
(5279, 'hm[n', 'from (05277)', 'Na`amah', 'None', 'nah-am-aw\'', '', 'feminine of «05277»; pleasantness; Naamah, the name of an antediluvian woman, of an Ammonitess, and of a place in Palestine:--Naamah.', 'Naamah = \"loveliness\" n pr f<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>daughter of Lamech by his wife Zillah and sister of Tubal-cain in the days before the flood<LI>the Ammonite wife of Solomon and mother of king Rehoboam of Judah n pr f loc<LI>a town in the lowlands of Judah in Philistia</OL>'),
(5280, 'ym[n', 'patronymic from (05283)', 'Na`amiy', 'None', 'nah-am-ee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymic from «05283»; a Naamanite, or descendant of Naaman (collectively):--Naamites.', 'Naamites = see Naamah \"loveliness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the descendants of Naaman, the grandson of Benjamin</OL>'),
(5281, 'ym[n', 'from (05278)', 'No`omiy', 'None', 'no-om-ee\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'from «05278»; pleasant; Noomi, an Israelitess:--Naomi.', 'Naomi = \"my delight\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wife of Elimelech, mother of Mahlon and Chilion, and mother-in-law of Ruth and Orpah</OL>'),
(5282, '!m[n', 'from (05276)', 'na`aman', 'TWOT - 1384c', 'nah-am-awn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05276»; pleasantness (plural as concrete):--pleasant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pleasantness</OL>'),
(5283, '!m[n', 'the same as (05282)', 'Na`aman', 'None', 'nah-am-awn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «05282»; Naaman, the name of an Israelite and of a Damascene:--Naaman.', 'Naaman = \"pleasantness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Bela of the family of Benjamin; he was among the family of Jacob that went down to Egypt<LI>commander-in-chief of the army of Syria; stricken with leprosy he went to Elisha, eventually followed his instructions, and was cured</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(5284, 'ytm[n', 'patrial from a place corresponding in name (but not identical) with (05279)', 'Na`amathiy', 'None', 'nah-am-aw-thee\'', 'Adjective', 'patrial from a place corresponding in name (but not identical) with «05279»; a Naamathite, or inhabitant of Naamah:--Naamathite.', 'Naamathite = see Naamah \"pleasantness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Naamah (site unknown); describes Zophar the friend of Job</OL>'),
(5285, '#wc[n', 'from an unused root meaning to prick', 'na`atsuwts', 'TWOT - 1386a', 'nah-ats-oots\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to prick; probably a brier; by implication, a thicket of thorny bushes:--thorn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thornbush</OL>'),
(5286, 'r[n', 'a primitive root', 'na`ar', 'TWOT - 1387', 'naw-ar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to growl:--yell.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to growl</OL>'),
(5287, 'r[n', 'a primitive root [probably identical with (05286), through the idea of the rustling of mane, which usually accompanies the lion\'s roar]', 'na`ar', 'TWOT - 1388', 'naw-ar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (probably identical with «05286», through the idea of the rustling of mane, which usually accompanies the lion\'s roar); to tumble about:--shake (off, out, self), overthrow, toss up and down.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shake, shake out or off<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to shake out, show emptiness<LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be shaken<LI>to shake oneself</OL><LI>(Piel) to shake off or out<LI>(Hithpael) to shake oneself</OL></OL>'),
(5288, 'r[n', 'from (05287)', 'na`ar', 'TWOT - 1389a', 'nah\'-ar', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05287»; (concretely) a boy (as active), from the age of infancy to adolescence; by implication, a servant; also (by interch. of sex), a girl (of similar latitude in age):--babe, boy, child, damsel (from the margin), lad, servant, young (man).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a boy, lad, servant, youth, retainer<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>boy, lad, youth<LI>servant, retainer</OL></OL>'),
(5289, 'r[n', 'from (05287) in its derivative sense of tossing about', 'na`ar', 'TWOT - 1388a', 'nah\'-ar', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05287» in its derivative sense of tossing about; a wanderer:--young one.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a shaking, scattering</OL>'),
(5290, 'r[n', 'from (05287)', 'no`ar', 'TWOT - 1389b', 'no\'-ar', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05287»; (abstractly) boyhood (compare «05288»):--child, youth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>youth, boyhood, early life</OL>'),
(5291, 'hr[n', 'from (05288)', 'na`arah', 'TWOT - 1389c', 'nah-ar-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «05288»; a girl (from infancy to adolescence):--damsel, maid(-en), young (woman).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>girl, damsel, female servant<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>girl, damsel, little girl<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of young woman, marriageable young woman, concubine, prostitute</OL><LI>maid, female attendant, female servant</OL></OL>'),
(5292, 'hr[n', 'the same as (05291)', 'Na`arah', 'None', 'nah-ar-aw\'', '', 'the same as «05291»; Naarah, the name of an Israelitess, and of a place in Palestine:--Naarah, Naarath.', 'Naarah or Naarath = \"maiden\" n pr f<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 2nd wife of Ashur of the tribe of Judah n pr loc<LI>one of the landmarks on the southern boundary of the territory of Ephraim</OL>'),
(5293, 'yr[n', 'from (05288)', 'Na`aray', 'None', 'nah-ar-ah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05288»; youthful; Naarai, an Israelite:--Naarai.', 'Naarai = \"handmaid\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the Arbite, son of Ezbai and one of David\'s mighty warriors</OL>'),
(5294, 'hyr[n', 'from (05288) and (03050)', 'Ne`aryah', 'None', 'neh-ar-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05288» and «03050»; servant of Jah; Nearjah, the name of two Israelites:--Neariah.', 'Neariah = \"servant of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 6 sons of Shemaiah in the line of the royal family of David of the tribe of Judah in the time after the captivity<LI>son of Ishi and one of the captains of the 500 Simeonites who, in the days of king Hezekiah of Judah, drove out the Amalekites from Mount Seir</OL>'),
(5295, '!r[n', 'from (05288)', 'Na`aran', 'None', 'nah-ar-awn\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «05288»; juvenile; Naaran, a place in Palestine:--Naaran.', 'Naaran = \"juvenile\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town on the eastern limit of the territory of Ephraim</OL>'),
(5296, 'tr[n', 'from (05287)', 'n`oreth', 'TWOT - 1388b', 'neh-o\'-reth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05287»; something shaken out, i.e. tow (as the refuse of flax):--tow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a strand of flax, tow (as shaken from flax when beaten)</OL>'),
(5297, '@n', 'a variation of (04644)', 'Noph', 'None', 'nofe', 'Proper Name Location', 'a variation of «04644»; Noph, the capital of Upper Egypt:--Noph.', 'Noph = \"presentability\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>another name for \'Memphis\' the capital city of Egypt</OL>'),
(5298, 'gpn', 'from an unused root probably meaning to spring forth', 'Nepheg', 'None', 'neh\'-feg', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to spring forth; a sprout; Nepheg, the name of two Israelites:--Nepheg.', 'Nepheg = \"sprout\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of sons of Izhar and grandson of Kohath of the tribe of Levi in the time of the exodus<LI>one of the sons of David born to him at Jerusalem</OL>'),
(5299, 'hpn', 'from (05130) in the sense of lifting', 'naphah', 'TWOT - 1331b,1330a', 'naw-faw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05130» in the sense of lifting; a height; also a sieve:--border, coast, region, sieve.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a lofty place, height<LI>sieve, winnowing implement</OL>'),
(5300, '~yoXwpn', 'for (05304)', 'Nphuwshciym', 'None', 'nef-oo-shes-eem\'', 'Noun', 'for «05304»; Nephushesim, a Temple- servant:--Nephisesim (from the margin).', 'Nephishesim or Nephusim = \"refreshed of spices\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a family of exiles who returned with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(5301, 'xpn', 'a primitive root', 'naphach', 'TWOT - 1390', 'naw-fakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to puff, in various applications (literally, to inflate, blow hard, scatter, kindle, expire; figuratively, to disesteem):--blow, breath, give up, cause to lose (life), seething, snuff.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to breathe, blow, sniff at, seethe, give up or lose (life)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to breathe, blow<LI>(Pual) to be blown<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to breathe out</OL></OL>'),
(5302, 'xpn', 'from (05301)', 'Nophach', 'None', 'no\'-fakh', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «05301»; a gust; Nophach, a place in Moab:--Nophah.', 'Nophah = \"blast\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in Moab</OL>'),
(5303, 'lypn', 'from (05307)', 'nphiyl', 'TWOT - 1393a', 'nef-eel\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or nphil {nef-eel\'}; from «05307»; properly, a feller, i.e. a bully or tyrant:--giant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>giants, the Nephilim</OL>'),
(5304, '~yoypn', 'from an unused root meaning to scatter', 'Nphiyciym', 'None', 'nef-ee-seem\'', 'Proper Name', 'plural from an unused root meaning to scatter; expansions; Nephisim, a Temple-servant:--Nephusim (from the margin).', 'Nephusim = \"scattered spices\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a family of exiles who returned with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(5305, 'Xypn', 'from (05314)', 'Naphiysh', 'None', 'naw-feesh\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05314»; refreshed; Naphish, a son of Ishmael, and his posterity:--Naphish.', 'Naphish = \"refreshment\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the next to last son of Ishmael<LI>an Arabian tribe</OL>'),
(5306, '$pn', 'from an unused root meaning to glisten', 'nophek', 'TWOT - 1391', 'no\'-fek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to glisten; shining; a gem, probably the garnet:--emerald.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a precious stone in the high priest\'s breastplate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps an emerald, turquoise, ruby, or carbuncle</OL><LI>jewels imported from Tyre</OL>'),
(5307, 'lpn', 'a primitive root', 'naphal', 'TWOT - 1392', 'naw-fal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to fall, in a great variety of applications (intransitive or causative, literal or figurative):--be accepted, cast (down, self, (lots), out), cease, die, divide (by lot), (let) fail, (cause to, let, make, ready to) fall (away, down, -en, -ing), fell(-ing), fugitive, have (inheritance), inferior, be judged (by mistake for «06419»), lay (along), (cause to) lie down, light (down), be (X hast) lost, lying, overthrow, overwhelm, perish, present(-ed, -ing), (make to) rot, slay, smite out, × surely, throw down.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fall, lie, be cast down, fail<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fall<LI>to fall (of violent death)<LI>to fall prostrate, prostrate oneself before<LI>to fall upon, attack, desert, fall away to , go away to, fall into the hand of<LI>to fall short, fail, fall out, turn out, result<LI>to settle, waste away, be offered, be inferior to<LI>to lie, lie prostrate</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to fall, fell, throw down, knock out, lay prostrate<LI>to overthrow<LI>to make the lot fall, assign by lot, apportion by lot<LI>to let drop, cause to fail (fig.)<LI>to cause to fall</OL><LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to throw or prostrate oneself, throw oneself upon<LI>to lie prostrate, prostrate oneself</OL><LI>(Pilel) to fall</OL></OL>'),
(5308, 'lpn', 'corresponding to (05307)', 'nphal', 'TWOT - 2867', 'nef-al\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05307»:--fall (down), have occasion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fall<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fall<LI>to fall down</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5309, 'lpn', 'from (05307)', 'nephel', 'TWOT - 1392a', 'neh\'-fel', 'Noun Masculine', 'or nephel {nay\'-fel}; from «05307»; something fallen, i.e. an abortion:--untimely birth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>untimely birth, abortion, miscarriage</OL>'),
(5310, '#pn', 'a primitive root', 'naphats', 'TWOT - 1394', 'naw-fats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to dash to pieces, or scatter:--be beaten in sunder, break (in pieces), broken, dash (in pieces), cause to be discharged, dispersed, be overspread, scatter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shatter, break, dash, beat in pieces<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shatter<LI>shattering (infinitive)</OL><LI>(Piel) to dash to pieces<LI>(Pual) to pulverise</OL><LI>to scatter, disperse, overspread, be scattered<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be scattered<LI>dispersed (participle)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5311, '#pn', 'from (05310)', 'nephets', 'TWOT - 1394a', 'neh\'-fets', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05310»; a storm (as dispersing):--scattering.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>driving storm</OL>'),
(5312, 'qpn', 'a primitive root', 'nphaq', 'TWOT - 2868', 'nef-ak\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) a primitive root; to issue; causatively, to bring out:--come (go, take) forth (out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go or come out, bring or come forth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to go out or forth<LI>(Aphel) to bring forth</OL></OL>'),
(5313, 'aqpn', 'from (05312)', 'niphqa\'', 'TWOT - 2868a', 'nif-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) from «05312»; an outgo, i.e. expense:--expense.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>outlay, expense</OL>'),
(5314, 'Xpn', 'a primitive root', 'naphash', 'TWOT - 1395', 'naw-fash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to breathe; passively, to be breathed upon, i.e. (figuratively) refreshed (as if by a current of air):--(be) refresh selves (-ed).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Niphal) to take breath, refresh oneself</OL>'),
(5315, 'Xpn', 'from (05314)', 'nephesh', 'TWOT - 1395a', 'neh\'-fesh', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05314»; properly, a breathing creature, i.e. animal of (abstractly) vitality; used very widely in a literal, accommodated or figurative sense (bodily or mental):--any, appetite, beast, body, breath, creature, × dead(-ly), desire, × (dis-)contented, × fish, ghost, + greedy, he, heart(-y), (hath, × jeopardy of) life (X in jeopardy), lust, man, me, mind, mortally, one, own, person, pleasure,  (her-, him-, my-, thy-)self, them (your)-selves, + slay, soul, + tablet, they, thing, (X she) will, × would have it.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>soul, self, life, creature, person, appetite, mind, living being, desire, emotion, passion<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>that which breathes, the breathing substance or being, soul, the inner being of man<LI>living being<LI>living being (with life in the blood)<LI>the man himself, self, person or individual<LI>seat of the appetites<LI>seat of emotions and passions<LI>activity of mind<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dubious</OL><LI>activity of the will<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dubious</OL><LI>activity of the character<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dubious</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5316, 'tpn', 'for (05299)', 'nepheth', 'TWOT - 1331c', 'neh\'-feth', 'Noun Feminine', 'for «05299»; a height:--country.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>height</OL>'),
(5317, 'tpn', 'from (05130) in the sense of shaking to pieces', 'nopheth', 'TWOT - 1396', 'no\'-feth', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05130» in the sense of shaking to pieces; a dripping i.e. of honey (from the comb):--honeycomb.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flowing honey, honey from the comb, a dropping down, honey, honeycomb</OL>'),
(5318, 'xwtpn', 'from (06605)', 'Nephtowach', 'None', 'nef-to\'-akh', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06605»; opened, i.e. a spring; Nephtoach, a place in Palestine:--Neptoah.', 'Nephtoah = \"opening\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a spring or source of water on the boundary of the territories of Judah and Benjamin; located northwest of Jerusalem</OL>'),
(5319, 'lwtpn', 'from (06617)', 'naphtuwl', 'TWOT - 1857c', 'naf-tool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06617»; properly, wrestled; but ued (in the plural) transitively, a struggle:--wrestling.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wrestlings</OL>'),
(5320, '~yxtpn', 'of foreign origin, Naphtuhim, an Egyptian tribe', 'Naphtuchiym', 'None', 'naf-too-kheem', 'Proper Name', 'plural of foreign origin, Naphtuchim, an Egyptian tribe:--Naptuhim.', 'Naphtuhim = \"openings\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an unclear reference to Egypt; perhaps Lower Egypt</OL>'),
(5321, 'yltpn', 'from (06617)', 'Naphtaliy', 'None', 'naf-taw-lee\'', '', 'from «06617»; my wrestling; Naphtali, a son of Jacob, with the tribe descended from him, and its territory:--Naphtali.', 'Naphtali = \"wrestling\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 5th son of Jacob and the 2nd by Bilhah the handmaid of Rachel<LI>the tribe descended from Naphtali the son of Jacob n pr loc<LI>the territory assigned to the tribe of Naphtali</OL>'),
(5322, '#n', 'from (05340)', 'nets', 'TWOT - 1405b,1406a', 'nayts', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05340»; a flower (from its brilliancy); also a hawk (from it flashing speed); --blossom, hawk.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>blossom<LI>a unclean bird of prey<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>hawk, falcon<LI>perhaps an extinct bird, exact meaning unknown</OL></OL>'),
(5323, 'acn', 'a primitive root', 'natsa\'', 'TWOT - 1397', 'naw-tsaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to go away; --flee.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to fly</OL>'),
(5324, 'bcn', 'a primitive root', 'natsab', 'TWOT - 1398', 'naw-tsab\'', 'Verb', 'a prim root; to station, in various applications (literally or figuratively):--appointed, deputy, erect, establish, ×  Huzzah (by mistake for a proper name), lay, officer, pillar, present, rear up, set (over, up), settle, sharpen, establish, (make to) stand(-ing, still, up, upright), best state.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to stand, take one\'s stand, stand upright, be set (over), establish<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to station oneself, take one\'s stand<LI>to stand, be stationed<LI>to stand, take an upright position<LI>to be stationed, be appointed<LI>deputy, prefect, appointed, deputed (subst)<LI>to stand firm</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to station, set<LI>to set up, erect<LI>to cause to stand erect<LI>to fix, establish</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be fixed, be determined, be stationary</OL></OL>'),
(5325, 'bccn', 'passive participle of (05324)', 'nitstsab', 'TWOT - 1398a', 'nits-twawb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'passive participle of «05324»; fixed, i.e. a handle:--haft.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>haft, hilt (of sword)</OL>'),
(5326, 'hbcn', 'from a root corresponding to (05324)', 'nitsbah', 'TWOT - 2869', 'nits-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «05324»; fixedness, i.e. firmness:--strength.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>firmness</OL>'),
(5327, 'hcn', 'a primitive root', 'natsah', 'TWOT - 1399,1400,1401', 'naw-tsaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to go forth, i.e. (by implication) to be expelled, and (consequently) desolate; causatively, to lay waste; also (specifically), to quarrel:--be laid waste, runinous, strive (together).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to fly<LI>to struggle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to struggle<LI>(Hiphil) to struggle</OL><LI>to strip off, make desolate, fall in ruins<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to fall in ruins<LI>(Niphal) desolated, ruined heaps (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(5328, 'hccn', 'from (05322)', 'nitstsah', 'TWOT - 1405c', 'nits-tsaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «05322»; a blossom; --flower.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>blossom</OL>'),
(5329, 'xcn', 'a primitive root', 'natsach', 'TWOT - 1402', 'naw-tsakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to glitter from afar, i.e. to be eminent (as a superintendent, especially of the Temple services and its music); also (as denominative from «05331»), to be permanent:--excel, chief musician (singer), oversee(-r), set forward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to excel, be bright, be preeminent, be perpetual, be overseer, be enduring<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) enduring (participle)<LI>(Piel) to act as overseer or superintendent or director or chief</OL></OL>'),
(5330, 'xcn', 'corresponding to (05329)', 'ntsach', 'TWOT - 2870', 'nets-akh\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05329»; to become chief:--be preferred.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Ithpael) to excel, distinguish oneself</OL>'),
(5331, 'xcn', 'from (05329)', 'netsach', 'TWOT - 1402a', 'neh\'-tsakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'or netsach {nay\'-tsakh}; from «05329»; properly, a goal, i.e. the bright object at a distance travelled towards; hence (figuratively), splendor, or (subjectively) truthfulness, or (objectively) confidence; but usually (adverbially), continually (i.e. to the most distant point of view); --alway(-s), constantly, end, (+ n-)ever(more), perpetual, strength, victory.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>eminence, perpetuity, strength, victory, enduring, everlastingness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>eminence<LI>enduring of life<LI>endurance in time, perpetual, continual, unto the end<LI>everlastingness, ever</OL></OL>'),
(5332, 'xcn', 'probably identical with (05331), through the idea of brilliancy of colour', 'Netsach', 'TWOT - 1403a', 'nay\'-tsakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably identical with «05331», through the idea of brilliancy of color; juice of the grape (as blood red):--blood, strength.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>juice<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>juice of grapes<LI>blood, gore (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(5333, 'bycn', 'from (05324)', 'ntsiyb', 'TWOT - 1398b', 'nets-eeb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or ntsib {nets-eeb\'}; from «05324»; something stationary, i.e. a prefect, a military post, a statue:--garrison, officer, pillar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>set over, something placed, pillar, prefect, garrison, post<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>pillar<LI>prefect, deputy</OL></OL>'),
(5334, 'bycn', 'the same as (05333)', 'Ntsiyb', 'None', 'nets-eeb\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «05333»; station; Netsib, a place in Palestine:--Nezib.', 'Nezib = \"garrison\" or \"pillar\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in the lowlands of Judah on the border of Philistia</OL>'),
(5335, 'xycn', 'from (05329)', 'ntsiyach', 'None', 'nets-ee\'-akh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05329»; conspicuous; Netsiach, a Temple- servant:--Neziah.', 'Neziah = \"pre-eminent\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of a family of temple slaves returning from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(5336, 'rycn', 'from (05341)', 'natsiyr', 'TWOT - 1407a', 'naw-tsere\'', 'Adjective', 'from «05341»; properly, conservative; but used passively, delivered:--preserved.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>preserved</OL>'),
(5337, 'lcn', 'a primitive root', 'natsal', 'TWOT - 1404', 'naw-tsal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to snatch away, whether in a good or a bad sense:- × at all, defend, deliver (self), escape, × without fail, part, pluck, preserve, recover, rescue, rid, save, spoil, strip, × surely, take (out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to snatch away, deliver, rescue, save, strip, plunder<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tear oneself away, deliver oneself<LI>to be torn out or away, be delivered</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strip off, spoil<LI>to deliver</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to take away, snatch away<LI>to rescue, recover<LI>to deliver (from enemies or troubles or death)<LI>to deliver from sin and guilt</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be plucked out<LI>(Hithpael) to strip oneself</OL></OL>'),
(5338, 'lcn', 'corresponding to (05337)', 'ntsal', 'TWOT - 2871', 'nets-al\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05337»; to extricate:--deliver, rescue.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Aphel) to rescue, extricate, deliver</OL>'),
(5339, '!ccn', 'from (05322)', 'nitstsan', 'TWOT - 1405d', 'nits-tsawn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05322»; a blossom:--flower.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>blossom</OL>'),
(5340, '#cn', 'a primitive root', 'natsats', 'TWOT - 1405', 'naw-tsats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to glare, i.e. be bright- colored:--sparkle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to shine, sparkle</OL>'),
(5341, 'rcn', 'a primitive root', 'natsar', 'TWOT - 1407', 'naw-tsar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to guard, in a good sense (to protect, maintain, obey, etc.) or a bad one (to conceal, etc.):-- besieged, hidden thing, keep(-er, -ing), monument, observe, preserve(-r), subtil, watcher(-man).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to guard, watch, watch over, keep<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to watch, guard, keep<LI>to preserve, guard from dangers<LI>to keep, observe, guard with fidelity<LI>to guard, keep secret<LI>to be kept close, be blockaded<LI>watchman (participle)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5342, 'rcn', 'from (05341) in the sense of greenness as a striking colour', 'netser', 'TWOT - 1408a', 'nay\'-tser', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05341» in the sense of greenness as a striking color; a shoot; figuratively, a descendant:--branch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sprout, shoot, branch (always fig.)</OL>'),
(5343, 'aqn', 'from a root corresponding to (05352)', 'nqe\'', 'TWOT - 2872', 'nek-ay\'', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «05352»; clean:--pure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>clean, pure</OL>'),
(5344, 'bqn', 'a primitive root', 'naqab', 'TWOT - 1409', 'naw-kab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to puncture, literally (to perforate, with more or less violence) or figuratively (to specify, designate, libel):--appoint, blaspheme, bore, curse, express, with holes, name, pierce, strike through.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pierce, perforate, bore, appoint<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pierce, bore<LI>to prick off, designate</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be pricked off, be designated, be specified</OL><LI>(Qal) to curse, blaspheme</OL>'),
(5345, 'bqn', 'a bezel (for a gem)', 'neqeb', 'TWOT - 1409a', 'neh\'keb', 'Noun Masculine', 'a bezel (for a gem):--pipe.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>groove, socket, hole, cavity, settings<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>technical term relating to jeweller\'s work</OL></OL>'),
(5346, 'bqn', 'the same as (05345)', 'Neqeb', 'None', 'neh\'-keb', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «05345»; dell; Nekeb, a place in Palestine:--Nekeb.', 'Nekeb or Nekeb = \"cavern\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the towns on the boundary of Naphtali</OL>'),
(5347, 'hbqn', 'from (05344)', 'nqebah', 'TWOT - 1409b', 'nek-ay-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05344»; female (from the sexual form):--female.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>female<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>woman, female child<LI>female animal</OL></OL>'),
(5348, 'dqn', 'from an unused root meaning to mark (by puncturing or branding)', 'naqod', 'TWOT - 1410a', 'naw-kode\'', 'Adjective', 'from an unused root meaning to mark (by puncturing or branding); spotted:--speckled.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>speckled, marked with points<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of sheep and goats</OL></OL>'),
(5349, 'dqn', 'active participle from the same as (05348)', 'noqed', 'TWOT - 1411a', 'no-kade\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'active participle from the same as «05348»; a spotter (of sheep or cattle), i.e. the owner or tender (who thus marks them):-- herdman, sheepmaster.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sheep-raiser, sheep-dealer, sheep-tender</OL>'),
(5350, 'dqqn', 'from the same as (05348)', 'niqqud', 'TWOT - 1410b', 'nik-kood\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «05348»; a crumb (as broken to spots); also a biscuit (as pricked):--cracknel, mouldy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>crumbled thing, thing easily crumbled, crumbs<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>crumbs<LI>apparently a kind of hard biscuit or cake</OL></OL>'),
(5351, 'hddqn', 'from (05348)', 'nquddah', 'TWOT - 1410c', 'ned-ood-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «05348»; a boss:--stud.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>point, drop<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of silver</OL></OL>'),
(5352, 'hqn', 'a primitive root', 'naqah', 'TWOT - 1412', 'naw-kaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be (or make) clean (literally or figuratively); by implication (in an adverse sense) to be bare, i.e. extirpated:--acquit × at all, × altogether, be blameless, cleanse, (be) clear(-ing), cut off, be desolate, be free, be (hold) guiltless, be (hold) innocent, × by no means, be quit, be (leave) unpunished, × utterly, × wholly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be empty, be clear, be pure, be free, be innocent, be desolate, be cut off<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be empty, be clean, be pure<LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be cleaned out, be purged out<LI>to be clean, be free from guilt, be innocent<LI>to be free, be exempt from punishment<LI>to be free, be exempt from obligation</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hold innocent, acquit<LI>to leave unpunished</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5353, 'adwqn', 'from (05348) (in the fig. sense of marked)', 'Nqowda\'', 'None', 'nek-o-daw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'feminine of «05348» (in the figurative sense of marked); distinction; Nekoda, a Temple-servant:--Nekoda.', 'Nekoda = \"distinguished\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head of a family of temple slaves returning from exile to Jerusalem with Zerubbabel<LI>head of a family of exiles who were from Tel Melah, Tel Harsha, Cherub, Addan, and Immer and who could not identify their father\'s house or their genealogy being of Israel and who returned with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(5354, 'tqn', 'a primitive root', 'naqat', 'TWOT - 1996', 'naw-kat\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to loathe:--weary.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to loathe, be grieved, feel a loathing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to feel a loathing</OL></OL>'),
(5355, 'yqn', 'from (05352)', 'naqiy', 'TWOT - 1412a,1412b', 'naw-kee\'', 'Adjective', 'or naqiyi (Joel «04» : «019»; Jonah «01» : «014»), {naw-kee\'}; from «05352»; innocent:--blameless, clean, clear, exempted, free, guiltless, innocent, quit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>clean, free from, exempt, clear, innocent<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>free from guilt, clean, innocent<LI>free from punishment<LI>free or exempt from obligations</OL><LI>innocent</OL>'),
(5356, '!wyqqn', 'from (05352)', 'niqqayown', 'TWOT - 1412c', 'nik-kaw-yone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or niqqayon {nik-kaw-yone\'}; from «05352»; clearness (literally or figuratively):--cleanness, innocency.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>innocency<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>freedom from guilt, innocency<LI>freedom from punishment<LI>cleanness of teeth (physical sense)</OL></OL>'),
(5357, 'qyqn', 'from an unused root meaning to bore', 'naqiyq', 'TWOT - 1417a', 'naw-keek\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to bore; a cleft:--hole.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cleft (of a rock)</OL>'),
(5358, '~qn', 'a primitive root', 'naqam', 'TWOT - 1413', 'naw-kam\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to grudge, i.e. avenge or punish:--avenge(-r, self), punish, revenge (self), × surely, take vengeance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to avenge, take vengeance, revenge, avenge oneself, be avenged, be punished<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to avenge, take vengeance<LI>to entertain revengeful feelings</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to avenge oneself<LI>to suffer vengeance</OL><LI>(Piel) to avenge<LI>(Hophal) to be avenged, vengeance be taken (for blood)<LI>(Hithpael) to avenge oneself</OL></OL>'),
(5359, '~qn', 'from (05358)', 'naqam', 'TWOT - 1413a', 'naw-kawm\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05358»; revenge:--+ avenged, quarrel, vengeance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vengeance<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>vengeance (by God, by Samson, by enemies of Judah)</OL></OL>'),
(5360, 'hmqn', 'from (05359)', 'nqamah', 'TWOT - 1413b', 'nek-aw-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «05359»; avengement, whether the act of the passion:--+ avenge, revenge(-ing), vengeance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vengeance<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>vengeance (by God, by Israel, by enemies of Israel)</OL></OL>'),
(5361, '[qn', 'a primitive root', 'naqa`', 'TWOT - 1414', 'naw-kah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to feel aversion:--be alienated.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be estranged, be alienated<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be severed (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(5362, '@qn', 'a primitive root', 'naqaph', 'TWOT - 1415,1416', 'naw-kaf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to strike with more or less violence (beat, fell, corrode); by implication (of attack) to knock together, i.e. surround or circulate:--compass (about, -ing), cut down, destroy, go round (about), inclose, round.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strike, strike off<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to strike off skin</OL><LI>to go around, compass, round<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to go around<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go around, surround, encompass, enclose<LI>to make the round, complete the circuit<LI>to make round, round off</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5363, '@qn', 'from (05362)', 'noqeph', 'TWOT - 1415a', 'no\'-kef', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05362»; a threshing (of olives):--shaking.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>striking off</OL>'),
(5364, 'hpqn', 'from (05362)', 'niqpah', 'TWOT - 1416a', 'nik-paw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05362»; probably a rope (as encircling):--rent.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>tether, rope, encircling rope</OL>'),
(5365, 'rqn', 'a primitive root', 'naqar', 'TWOT - 1418', 'naw-kar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to bore (penetrate, quarry):--dig, pick out, pierce, put (thrust) out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bore, pick, dig, pick out<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to bore, pick, dig<LI>(Piel) to bore out<LI>(Pual) to be dug out</OL></OL>'),
(5366, 'hrqn', 'from (05365), a fissure', 'nqarah', 'TWOT - 1418a', 'nek-aw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05365», a fissure:--cleft, clift.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hole, crevice</OL>'),
(5367, 'Xqn', 'a primitive root', 'naqash', 'TWOT - 1419', 'naw-kash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to entrap (with a noose), literally or figuratively:--catch (lay a) snare.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to knock, strike, bring down<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to strike down<LI>(Niphal) to be thrust after, be impelled<LI>(Piel) to strike at, take aim at<LI>(Hithpael) to be struck</OL><LI>(CLBL) to ensnare<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to ensnare<LI>(Niphal) to be ensnared<LI>(Piel) to lay snares<LI>(Hithpael) to lay snares</OL></OL>'),
(5368, 'Xqn', 'corresponding to (05367); but used in the sense of (05362)', 'nqash', 'TWOT - 2873', 'nek-ash\'', '', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05367»; but used in the sense of «05362»; to knock:--smote.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to knock (of knees)</OL>'),
(5369, 'rn', 'the same as (05216)', 'Ner', 'TWOT - 1333a', 'nare', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «05216»; lamp; Ner, an Israelite:--Ner.', 'Ner = \"lamp\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Jehiel, father of Kish, and grandfather of king Saul<LI>father of Abner, the uncle of Saul<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps the same as 1</OL></OL>'),
(5370, 'lgrn', 'of foreign origin', 'Nergal', 'None', 'nare-gal\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign origin; Nergal, a Cuthite deity:--Nergal.', 'Nergal = \"hero\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the chief deities of Assyria and Babylon and worshipped by the men of Cuth</OL>'),
(5371, 'rcarX lgrn', 'from (05370) and (08272)', 'Nergal', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05370» and «08272»; Nergal-Sharetser, the name of two Babylonians:--Nergal-sharezer.', 'Nergal-sharezer = \"prince of fire\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chief soothsayer and a ruler in the army of Nebuchadnezzar</OL>'),
(5372, '!grn', 'from an unused root meaning to roll to pieces', 'nirgan', 'TWOT - 2115', 'neer-gawn\'', 'Verb', 'from an unused root meaning to roll to pieces; a slanderer:--talebearer, whisperer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to murmur, whisper<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>murmurers<LI>backbite, slander, talebearer, backbiter</OL></OL>'),
(5373, 'drn', 'of foreign origin', 'nerd', 'TWOT - 1420', 'nayrd', 'Noun Masculine', 'of foreign origin; nard, an aromatic:--spikenard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spikenard, nard<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>an odoriferous aromatic plant from India</OL></OL>'),
(5374, 'hyrn', 'from (05216) and (03050)', 'Neriyah', 'None', 'nay-ree-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Neriyahuw {nay-ree-yaw\'-hoo}; from «05216» and «03050»; light of Jah; Nerijah, an Israelite:--Neriah.', 'Neriah = \"lamp of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Maaseiah and father of Baruch and Seraiah</OL>'),
(5375, 'aXn', 'a primitive root', 'nasa\'', 'TWOT - 1421', 'naw-saw\'', 'Verb', 'or nacah (Psalm «04» : «06» («07»)) {naw-saw\'}; a primitive root; to lift, in a great variety of applications, literal and figurative, absol. and rel. (as follows):--accept, advance, arise, (able to, (armor), suffer to) bear(-er, up), bring (forth), burn, carry (away), cast, contain, desire, ease, exact, exalt (self), extol, fetch, forgive, furnish, further, give, go on, help, high, hold up, honorable (+ man), lade, lay, lift (self) up, lofty, marry, magnify, × needs, obtain, pardon, raise (up), receive, regard, respect, set (up), spare, stir up, + swear, take (away, up), × utterly, wear, yield.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lift, bear up, carry, take<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lift, lift up<LI>to bear, carry, support, sustain, endure<LI>to take, take away, carry off, forgive</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be lifted up, be exalted<LI>to lift oneself up, rise up<LI>to be borne, be carried<LI>to be taken away, be carried off, be swept away</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lift up, exalt, support, aid, assist<LI>to desire, long (fig.)<LI>to carry, bear continuously<LI>to take, take away</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to lift oneself up, exalt oneself<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause one to bear (iniquity)<LI>to cause to bring, have brought</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5376, 'aXn', 'corresponding to (05375)', 'nsa\'', 'TWOT - 2874', 'nes-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05375»:--carry away, make insurrection, take.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lift, bear, take, carry<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to take<LI>(Ithpael) to make a rising, make an insurrection</OL></OL>'),
(5377, 'aXn', 'a primitive root', 'nasha\'', 'TWOT - 1425', 'naw-shaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to lead astray, i.e. (mentally) to delude, or (morally) to seduce:--beguile, deceive, × greatly, ×  utterly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to beguile, deceive<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be beguiled<LI>(Hiphil) to beguile, deceive<LI>(Qal) utterly (infinitif)</OL></OL>'),
(5378, 'aXn', 'a primitive root [perhaps identical with (05377), through the idea of imposition]', 'nasha\'', 'TWOT - 1424', 'naw-shaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (perhaps identical with «05377», through the idea of imposition); to lend on interest; by implication, to dun for debt:--X debt, exact, giver of usury.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lend on interest or usury, be a creditor<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) creditor (participle)<LI>(Hiphil) to act as a creditor</OL></OL>'),
(5379, 'taXXn', 'from (05375)', 'nisse\'th', 'TWOT - 1421', 'nis-sayth\'', 'Feminine', 'passive participle feminine of «05375»; something taken, i.e. a present:--gift.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gift, portion (as something taken up)</OL>'),
(5380, 'bXn', 'a primitive root', 'nashab', 'TWOT - 1426', 'naw-shab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to blow; by implication, to disperse:--(cause to) blow, drive away.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to blow<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to blow<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to blow<LI>to disperse, to drive away</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5381, 'gXn', 'a primitive root', 'nasag', 'TWOT - 1422', 'naw-sag\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to reach (literally or figuratively):--ability, be able, attain (unto), (be able to, can) get, lay at, put, reach, remove, wax rich, × surely, (over-)take (hold of, on, upon).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to reach, overtake, take hold upon<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to overtake<LI>to reach, attain to, cause to reach<LI>to be able to secure, reach, have enough</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5382, 'hXn', 'a primitive root', 'nashah', 'TWOT - 1428', 'naw-shaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to forget; figuratively, to neglect; causatively, to remit, remove:--forget, deprive, exact.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to forget, deprive<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to forget<LI>(Niphal) to be forgotten<LI>(Piel) to cause to forget<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to forget, allow to be forgotten</OL></OL>'),
(5383, 'hXn', 'a primitive root [rather identical with (05382), in the sense of (05378)]', 'nashah', 'TWOT - 1427', 'naw-shaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (rather identical with «05382», in the sense of «05378»); to lend or (by reciprocity) borrow on security or interest:--creditor, exact, extortioner, lend, usurer, lend on (taker on) usury.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lend, be a creditor<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lend<LI>creditor (participle) (subst)</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to lend</OL></OL>'),
(5384, 'hXn', 'from (05382), in the sense of failure', 'nasheh', 'TWOT - 1429', 'naw-sheh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05382», in the sense of failure; rheumatic or crippled (from the incident to Jacob):--which shrank.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vein, nerve, tendon (in the thigh)</OL>'),
(5385, 'hawXn', 'from (05375)', 'nsuw\'ah', 'TWOT - 1421a', 'nes-oo-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or rather, nsutah {nes-oo-aw\'}; feminine. passive participle of «05375»; something borne, i.e. a load:--carriage.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>what is borne or carried about, load</OL>'),
(5386, 'yXn', 'from (05383)', 'nshiy', 'TWOT - 1427a', 'nesh-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05383»; a debt:--debt.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>debt</OL>'),
(5387, 'ayXn', 'from (05375)', 'nasiy\'', 'TWOT - 1421b,1421c', 'naw-see\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or «0nasi8» {naw-see\'}; from «05375»; properly, an exalted one, i.e. a king or sheik; also a rising mist:--captain, chief, cloud, governor, prince, ruler, vapour.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one lifted up, chief, prince, captain, leader<LI>rising mist, vapour</OL>'),
(5388, 'hyXn', 'from (05382)', 'nshiyah', 'TWOT - 1428a', 'nesh-ee-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05382»; oblivion; --forgetfulness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>forgetfulness, oblivion</OL>'),
(5389, '!yXn', 'irregular of (0606)', 'nashiyn', 'TWOT - 2875', 'naw-sheen\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) irregular plural feminine of «0606»:--women.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wives</OL>'),
(5390, 'hqyXn', 'from (05401)', 'nshiyqah', 'TWOT - 1435a', 'nesh-ee-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05401»; a kiss:--kiss.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>kiss</OL>'),
(5391, '$Xn', 'a primitive root', 'nashak', 'TWOT - 1430,1430b', 'naw-shak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to strike with a sting (as a serpent); figuratively, to oppress with interest on a loan:--bite, lend upon usury.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bite<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to bite<LI>(Piel) to bite</OL><LI>to pay, give interest, lend for interest or usury<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to give interest<LI>(Hiphil) to make to give interest</OL></OL>'),
(5392, '$Xn', 'from (05391)', 'neshek', 'TWOT - 1430a', 'neh\'-shek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05391»; interest on a debt:--usury.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>interest, usury</OL>'),
(5393, 'hkXn', 'for (03957)', 'nishkah', 'TWOT - 1431', 'nish-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'for «03957»; a cell:--chamber.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chamber, room, cell</OL>'),
(5394, 'lXn', 'a primitive root', 'nashal', 'TWOT - 1432', 'naw-shal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pluck off, i.e. divest, eject or drop:--cast (out), drive, loose, put off (out), slip.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to slip off, drop off, clear away, draw off<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to slip or drop off<LI>to draw off<LI>to clear away</OL><LI>(Piel) to clear out completely, clear entirely</OL></OL>'),
(5395, '~Xn', 'a primitive root', 'nasham', 'TWOT - 1433', 'naw-sham\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to blow away, i.e. destroy:--destroy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pant<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to pant<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of a woman in travail or labour</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5396, 'amXn', 'corresponding to (05397)', 'nishma\'', 'TWOT - 2876', 'nish-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05397»; vital breath:--breath.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>breath, spirit</OL>'),
(5397, 'hmXn', 'from (05395)', 'nshamah', 'TWOT - 1433a', 'nesh-aw-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05395»; a puff, i.e. wind, angry or vital breath, divine inspiration, intellect. or (concretely) an animal:--blast, (that) breath(-eth), inspiration, soul, spirit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>breath, spirit<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>breath (of God)<LI>breath (of man)<LI>every breathing thing<LI>spirit (of man)</OL></OL>'),
(5398, '@Xn', 'a primitive root', 'nashaph', 'TWOT - 1434', 'naw-shaf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to breeze, i.e. blow up fresh (as the wind):--blow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to blow</OL>'),
(5399, '@Xn', 'from (05398)', 'nesheph', 'TWOT - 1434a', 'neh\'-shef', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05398»; properly, a breeze, i.e. (by implication) dusk (when the evening breeze prevails):--dark, dawning of the day (morning), night, twilight.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>twilight<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>evening twilight<LI>morning twilight</OL></OL>'),
(5400, 'qXn', 'a primitive root', 'nasaq', 'TWOT - 2266', 'naw-sak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to catch fire:--burn, kindle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to kindle, burn<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be kindled<LI>(Hiphil) to make a fire, burn</OL></OL>'),
(5401, 'qXn', 'a primitive root [identical with (05400), through the idea of fastening up', 'nashaq', 'TWOT - 1435,1436', 'naw-shak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «05400», through the idea of fastening up; compare «02388», «02836»); to kiss, literally or figuratively (touch); also (as a mode of attachment), to equip with weapons:--armed (men), rule, kiss, that touched.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to put together, kiss<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to kiss<LI>(Piel) to kiss<LI>(Hiphil) to touch gently</OL><LI>to handle, be equipped with<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be equipped</OL></OL>'),
(5402, 'qXn', 'from (05401)', 'nesheq', 'TWOT - 1436a', 'neh\'-shek', 'Noun Masculine', 'or nesheq {nay\'-shek}; from «05401»; military equipment, i.e. (collectively) arms (offensive or defensive), or (concretely) an arsenal:--armed men, armour(-y), battle, harness, weapon.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>equipment, weapons, armoury<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>equipment, weapons<LI>armoury</OL></OL>'),
(5403, 'rXn', 'corresponding to (05404)', 'nshar', 'TWOT - 2877', 'nesh-ar\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05404»; an eagle:--eagle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>eagle, vulture, griffon-vulture</OL>'),
(5404, 'rXn', 'from an unused root meaning to lacerate', 'nesher', 'TWOT - 1437', 'neh\'-sher', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to lacerate; the eagle (or other large bird of prey):--eagle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>eagle, vulture, griffon-vulture</OL>'),
(5405, 'tXn', 'a primitive root', 'nashath', 'TWOT - 1438', 'naw-shath\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to eliminate, i.e. (intransitively) to dry up:--fail.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be dry, be parched<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be dry, be parched<LI>(Niphal) to be dried up</OL></OL>'),
(5406, '!wtXn', 'probably of Persian origin', 'nishtvan', 'TWOT - 1439', 'nish-tev-awn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably of Persian origin; an epistle:--letter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>letter</OL>'),
(5407, '!wtXn', 'corresponding to (05406)', 'nishtvan', 'TWOT - 2878', 'nish-tev-awn\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05406»:--letter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>letter</OL>'),
(5408, 'xtn', 'a primitive root', 'nathach', 'TWOT - 1441', 'naw-thakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to dismember:--cut (in pieces), divide, hew in pieces.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut, cut up, cut in pieces, divide<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to cut up, cut in pieces, divide by joints</OL></OL>'),
(5409, 'xtn', 'from (05408)', 'nethach', 'TWOT - 1441a', 'nay\'-thakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05408»; a fragment:--part, piece.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>piece, a piece of flesh or meat</OL>'),
(5410, 'bytn', 'from an unused root meaning to tramp', 'nathiyb', 'TWOT - 1440a,1440b', 'naw-theeb\'', 'Noun', 'or (feminine) nthiybah {neth-ee-baw\'}; or nthibah (Jeremiah 6:16) {neth-ee-baw\'}; from an unused root meaning to tramp; a (beaten) track:--path((-way)), × travel(-ler), way.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>trodden with the feet, path, pathway<LI>path, pathway, traveller</OL>'),
(5411, '!ytn', 'from (05414)', 'Nathiyn', 'TWOT - 1443a', 'naw-theen\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or Nathuwn (Ezra 8:17) {naw-thoon\'} (the proper form as passive participle), from «05414»; one given, i.e. (in the plural only) the Nethinim, or Temple-servants (as given to that duty):--Nethinims.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Nethinims<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>temple slaves assigned to the Levites and priests for service in the sanctuary</OL></OL>'),
(5412, '!ytn', 'corresponding to (05411)', 'Nthiyn', 'TWOT - 2879', 'netheen\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05411»:--Nethinims.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Nethinims<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>temple slaves assigned to the Levites and priests for service in the sanctuary</OL></OL>'),
(5413, '$tn', 'a primitive root', 'nathak', 'TWOT - 1442', 'naw-thak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to flow forth (literally or figuratively); by implication, to liquify:--drop, gather (together), melt, pour (forth, out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pour out or forth, drop (or rain), be poured, be poured out, be melted, be molten<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to pour forth<LI>(Niphal) to be poured, be poured out<LI>(Hiphil) to pour out, melt<LI>(Hophal) to be melted</OL></OL>'),
(5414, '!tn', 'a primitive root', 'nathan', 'TWOT - 1443', 'naw-than\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to give, used with greatest latitude of application (put, make, etc.):--add, apply, appoint, ascribe, assign, × avenge, × be ((healed)), bestow, bring (forth, hither), cast, cause, charge, come, commit, consider, count, + cry, deliver (up), direct, distribute, do, × doubtless, ×  without fail, fasten, frame, × get, give (forth, over, up), grant, hang (up), × have, × indeed, lay (unto charge, up), (give) leave, lend, let (out), + lie, lift up, make, + O that, occupy, offer, ordain, pay, perform, place, pour, print, ×  pull , put (forth), recompense, render, requite, restore, send (out), set (forth), shew, shoot forth (up), + sing, + slander, strike, (sub-)mit, suffer, × surely, × take, thrust, trade, turn, utter, + weep, + willingly, + withdraw, + would (to) God, yield.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give, put, set<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give, bestow, grant, permit, ascribe, employ, devote, consecrate, dedicate, pay wages, sell, exchange, lend, commit, entrust, give over, deliver up, yield produce, occasion, produce, requite to, report, mention, utter, stretch out, extend<LI>to put, set, put on, put upon, set, appoint, assign, designate<LI>to make, constitute</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be given, be bestowed, be provided, be entrusted to, be granted to, be permitted, be issued, be published, be uttered, be assigned<LI>to be set, be put, be made, be inflicted</OL><LI>(Hophal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be given, be bestowed, be given up, be delivered up<LI>to be put upon</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5415, '!tn', 'corresponding to (05414)', 'nthan', 'TWOT - 2880', 'neth-an\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05414»; give:--bestow, give pay.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give<LI>to give, allow<LI>to give, pay</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5416, '!tn', 'from (05414)', 'Nathan', 'None', 'naw-thawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05414»; given; Nathan, the name of five Israelites:--Nathan.', 'Nathan = \"giver\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of David by Bathsheba<LI>the eminent prophet in the time of David and Solomon<LI>a man of Zobah, father of one of David\'s mighty warriors<LI>father of Azariah who was over the officers of Solomon<LI>son of Attai and father of Zabad of the tribe of Judah<LI>brother of Joel of the tribe of Judah<LI>one of the head men who returned from Babylon with Ezra<LI>a man with a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>head of a family of Israel who shall mourn when they look on Him whom they pierced</OL>'),
(5417, 'lantn', 'from (05414) and (0410)', 'Nthane\'l', 'None', 'neth-an-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05414» and «0410»; given of God; Nethanel, the name of ten Israelites:--Nethaneel.', 'Nethaneel = \"given of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Zuar and a chief of the tribe of Issachar at the exodus<LI>the 4th son of Jesse and a brother of David<LI>a priest in the reign of David who blew the trumpet before the ark when it was brought from the house of Obed-edom<LI>a representative of the priestly family of Jedaiah in the time of Joiakim<LI>a priest of the family of Pashur who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>a Levite, father of Shemaiah the scribe in the reign of David<LI>a Levite, son of Obed-edom<LI>a chief of the Levites in the reign of king Josiah of Judah<LI>a prince of Judah in the reign of king Jehoshaphat of Judah who was sent by the king to teach in the cities of the kingdom<LI>a Levite of the sons of Asaph who played a musical instrument at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps the same as 5</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(5418, 'hyntn', 'from (05414) and (03050)', 'Nthanyah', 'None', 'neth-an-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Nthanyahuw {neth-an-yaw\'-hoo}; from «05414» and «03050»; given of Jah; Nethanjah, the name of four Israelites:--Nethaniah.', 'Nethaniah = \"given of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Elishama of the royal family of Judah and father of Ishmael who murdered Gedaliah<LI>father of Jehudi<LI>a Levite, one of the 4 sons of Asaph the minstrel<LI>a Levite in the reign of king Jehoshaphat of Judah</OL>'),
(5419, '$lmntn', 'from (05414) and (04428)', 'Nthan-Melek', 'None', 'neth-an\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05414» and «04428»; given of (the) king; Nethan-Melek, an Israelite:--Nathan-melech.', 'Nathan-melech = \"the gift of the king\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an official of Judah in the time of king Josiah</OL>'),
(5420, 'otn', 'a primitive root', 'nathac', 'TWOT - 1444', 'naw-thas\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to tear up:--mar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tear down, break down<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to break down</OL></OL>'),
(5421, '[tn', 'for (05422)', 'natha`', 'TWOT - 1445', 'naw-thah\'', 'Verb', 'for «05422»; to tear out:--break.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to break, break down, break out<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be broken down</OL></OL>'),
(5422, '#tn', 'a primitive root', 'nathats', 'TWOT - 1446', 'naw-thats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to tear down:--beat down, break down (out), cast down, destroy, overthrow, pull down, throw down.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pull down, break down, cast down, throw down, beat down, destroy, overthrow, break out (teeth)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pull down<LI>to break down, break off</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be pulled or broken down<LI>(Piel) to tear down<LI>(Pual) to be torn down<LI>(Hophal) to be broken, be broken down</OL></OL>'),
(5423, 'qtn', 'a primitive root', 'nathaq', 'TWOT - 1447', 'naw-thak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to tear off:--break (off), burst, draw (away), lift up, pluck (away, off), pull (out), root out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pull or tear or draw off or away or apart, draw out, pluck up, break, lift, root out<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to draw away<LI>to draw or pull off<LI>to pull or tear away</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be drawn away, be drawn out<LI>to be torn apart or in two, be snapped<LI>to be separated</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tear apart, snap<LI>to tear out, tear up, tear away</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to draw away<LI>to drag away</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be drawn away</OL></OL>'),
(5424, 'qtn', 'from (05423)', 'netheq', 'TWOT - 1447a', 'neh\'-thek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05423»; scurf:--(dry) scall.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>scab, skin eruption, scall (of leprosy)</OL>'),
(5425, 'rtn', 'a primitive root', 'nathar', 'TWOT - 1448,1449', 'naw-thar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to jump, i.e. be violently agitated; causatively, to terrify, shake off, untie:--drive asunder, leap, (let) loose, × make, move, undo.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to start up, tremble, shake, spring up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to start up<LI>(Piel) to leap<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to start up</OL><LI>to loose, let loose, undo, be free, be loose<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to unfasten, loosen<LI>to set free, unbind</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5426, 'rtn', 'corresponding to (05425)', 'nther', 'TWOT - 2881', 'neth-ar\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05425»:--shake off.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strip off<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Aphel) to strip off</OL></OL>'),
(5427, 'rtn', 'from (05425)', 'nether', 'TWOT - 1450a', 'neh\'-ther', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05425»; mineral potash (so called from effervescing with acid):--nitre.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>natron, nitre, soda, carbonate of soda</OL>'),
(5428, 'Xtn', 'a primitive root', 'nathash', 'TWOT - 1451', 'naw-thash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to tear away:--destroy, forsake, pluck (out, up, by the roots), pull up, root out (up), × utterly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pull up, expel, root out, pluck up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to pull or pluck up<LI>(Niphal) to be plucked up<LI>(Hophal) to be plucked up</OL></OL>'),
(5429, 'hao', 'from an unused root meaning to define', 'c\'ah', 'TWOT - 1452', 'seh-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning to define; a seah, or certain measure (as determinative) for grain:--measure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>seah, a measure of flour or grain<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>probably equal to 1/3 ephah</OL></OL>'),
(5430, '!wao', 'from (05431)', 'c\'own', 'TWOT - 1453a', 'seh-own\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05431»; perhaps a military boot (as a protection from mud:--battle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sandal, boot (of soldier)</OL>'),
(5431, '!ao', 'a primitive root', 'ca\'an', 'TWOT - 1453', 'saw-an\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be miry; used only as denominative from «05430»; to shoe, i.e. (active participle) a soldier shod:--warrior.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to tread, tramp</OL>'),
(5432, 'haoao', 'for (05429)', 'ca\'c\'ah', 'TWOT - 1452', 'sah-seh-aw\'', 'Verb', 'for «05429»; measurement, i.e. moderation:--measure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Pilpel) to drive away</OL>'),
(5433, 'abo', 'a primitive root', 'caba\'', 'TWOT - 1455', 'saw-baw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to quaff to satiety, i.e. become tipsy:--drunkard, fill self, Sabean, (wine-)bibber.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to drink heavily or largely, imbibe<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to imbibe<LI>wine-bibber, drunkard (participle) (subst)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5434, 'abo', 'of foreign origin', 'Cba\'', 'None', 'seb-aw\'', '', 'of foreign origin; Seba, a son of Cush, and the country settled by him:--Seba.', 'Seba = \"drink thou\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Cush n pr loc<LI>a nation south of Palestine, perhaps Ethiopia</OL>'),
(5435, 'abo', 'from (05433)', 'cobe\'', 'TWOT - 1455a', 'so\'-beh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05433»; potation, concretely (wine), or abstractly (carousal):--drink, drunken, wine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>drink, liquor, wine</OL>'),
(5436, 'yabo', 'patrial from (05434)', 'Cba\'iy', 'None', 'seb-aw-ee\'', 'Noun', 'patrial from «05434»; a Sebaite, or inhabitant of Seba:--Sabean.', 'Sabeans = \"drunkards\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the people of Seba</OL>'),
(5437, 'bbo', 'a primitive root', 'cabab', 'TWOT - 1456', 'saw-bab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to revolve, surround, or border; used in various applications, literally and figuratively (as follows):--bring, cast, fetch, lead, make, walk, × whirl, ×  round about, be about on every side, apply, avoid, beset (about), besiege, bring again, carry (about), change, cause to come about, × circuit, (fetch a) compass (about, round), drive, environ, × on every side, beset (close, come, compass, go, stand) round about, inclose, remove, return, set, sit down, turn (self) (about, aside, away, back).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to turn, turn about or around or aside or back or towards, go about or around, surround, encircle, change direction<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to turn, turn about, be brought round, change<LI>to march or walk around, go partly around, circle about, skirt, make a round, make a circuit, go about to, surround, encompass</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to turn oneself, close round, turn round<LI>to be turned over to</OL><LI>(Piel) to turn about, change, transform<LI>(Poel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to encompass, surround<LI>to come about, assemble round<LI>to march, go about<LI>to enclose, envelop</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to turn, cause to turn, turn back, reverse, bring over, turn into, bring round<LI>to cause to go around, surround, encompass</OL><LI>(Hophal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be turned<LI>to be surrounded</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5438, 'hbbo', 'from (05437)', 'cibbah', 'TWOT - 1456a', 'sib-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05437»; a (providential) turn (of affairs):--cause.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>turn of events, turn of affairs</OL>'),
(5439, 'bybo', 'from (05437)', 'cabiyb', 'TWOT - 1456b', 'saw-beeb\'', '', 'or (feminine) cbiybah {seb-ee-baw\'}; from «05437»; (as noun) a circle, neighbour, or environs; but chiefly (as adverb, with or without preposition) around:--(place, round) about, circuit, compass, on every side.', 'subst<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>places round about, circuit, round about adv<LI>in a circuit, a circuit, round about prep<LI>in the circuit, from every side</OL>'),
(5440, '$bo', 'a primitive root', 'cabak', 'TWOT - 1457', 'saw-bak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to entwine:--fold together, wrap.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to interweave<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to interweave<LI>interwoven (participle)</OL><LI>(Pual) to be interwoven</OL></OL>'),
(5441, '$bo', 'from (05440)', 'cobek', 'TWOT - 1457b', 'so\'-bek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05440»; a copse:--thicket.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thicket</OL>'),
(5442, '$bo', 'from (05440)', 'cbak', 'TWOT - 1457a', 'seb-awk\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05440», a copse:--thick(-et).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thicket</OL>'),
(5443, 'akbbo', 'from a root corresponding to (05440)', 'cabbka\'', 'TWOT - 3003', 'sab-bek-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) or sabbka: (Aramaic) {sab-bek- aw\'}; from a root corresponding to «05440»; a lyre:--sackbut.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>trigon, musical instrument<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a triangular musical instrument with four strings, similar to a lyre</OL></OL>'),
(5444, 'ykbbo', 'from (05440)', 'Cibbkay', 'None', 'sib-bek-ah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05440»; copse-like; Sibbecai, an Israelite:--Sibbecai, Sibbechai.', 'Sibbecai or Sibbechai = \"weaver\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of David\'s guard and 8th captain for the 8th month of 24,000 men of the king\'s army; a Judaite, descendant of Zerah and called the \'Hushathite\'</OL>'),
(5445, 'lbo', 'a primitive root', 'cabal', 'TWOT - 1458', 'saw-bal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to carry (literally or figuratively), or (reflexively) be burdensome; specifically, to be gravid:--bear, be a burden, carry, strong to labour.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bear, bear a load, drag oneself along<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to bear (a load)<LI>(Pual) laden (participle)<LI>(Hithpael) to make oneself a burden, drag oneself along</OL></OL>'),
(5446, 'lbo', 'corresponding to (05445)', 'cbal', 'TWOT - 2882', 'seb-al\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05445»; to erect:--strongly laid.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bear a load<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Poal) laid (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(5447, 'lbo', 'from (05445)', 'cebel', 'TWOT - 1458a', 'say\'-bel', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05445»; a load (literally or figuratively):--burden, charge.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>load, burden</OL>'),
(5448, 'lbo', 'from (05445)', 'cobel', 'TWOT - 1458a', 'so\'-bel', 'Noun Masculine', '(only in the form cubbal {soob-bawl\'}; from «05445»; a load (figuratively):--burden.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>burden, load</OL>'),
(5449, 'lbbo', 'from (05445)', 'cabbal', 'TWOT - 1458b', 'sab-bawl\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05445»; a porter:--(to bear, bearer of) burden(-s).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>burden-bearer</OL>'),
