(5478, 'hxwo', 'from the same as (05477)', 'cuwchah', 'TWOT - 1473a', 'soo-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «05477»; something swept away, i.e. filth:--torn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>offal</OL>'),
(5479, 'ytwo', 'from (07750)', 'Cowtay', 'None', 'so-tah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07750»; roving; Sotai, one of the Nethinim:--Sotai.', 'Sotai = \"changeful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ancestor of a family of Solomon\'s servants who returned from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(5480, '$wo', 'a primitive root', 'cuwk', 'TWOT - 1474', 'sook', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to smear over (with oil), i.e. anoint:--anoint (self), × at all.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to anoint, pour in anointing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to anoint<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to anoint oneself<LI>to anoint (another)<LI>to be poured</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to anoint</OL></OL>'),
(5481, 'hynwpmwo', 'of Greek origin', 'cuwmpownyah', 'TWOT - 2887', 'soom-po-neh-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) or cuwmponyah (Aramaic) {soom-po-neh-yaw\'}; or ciyphonya: (Dan. 3:10) (Aramaic) {see-fo-neh-yaw\'}; of Greek origin; a bagpipe (with a double pipe):--dulcimer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a musical instrument, wind instrument, bagpipe, double pipe, panpipes<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps dulcimer, panpipes</OL></OL>'),
(5482, 'hnwo', 'of Egyptian derivation', 'Cveneh', 'None', 'sev-ay-nay\'', 'Proper Name Location', '(rather to be written Cvenah {sev-ay\'-naw}; for Cven {sev-ane\'}; i.e to Seven); of Egyptian derivation; Seven, a place in Upper Egypt:--Syene.', 'Syene = \"her veiling (?)\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town of Egypt on the frontier of Cush or Ethiopia</OL>'),
(5483, 'owo', 'from an unused root meaning to skip (properly, for joy)', 'cuwc', 'TWOT - 1476,1477', 'soos', 'Noun Masculine', 'or cuc {soos}; from an unused root meaning to skip (properly, for joy); a horse (as leaping); also a swallow (from its rapid flight):--crane, horse((-back, -hoof)). Compare «06571».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>swallow, swift<LI>horse<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>chariot horses</OL></OL>'),
(5484, 'howo', 'from (05483)', 'cuwcah', 'TWOT - 1477', 'soo-saw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «05483»; a mare:--company of horses.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mare</OL>'),
(5485, 'yowo', 'from (05483)', 'Cuwciy', 'None', 'soo-see\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05483»; horse-like; Susi, an Israelite:--Susi.', 'Susi = \"my horse\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Gaddi, the spy for the tribe of Manasseh</OL>'),
(5486, '@wo', 'a primitive root', 'cuwph', 'TWOT - 1478', 'soof', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to snatch away, i.e. terminate:--consume, have an end, perish, × be utterly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cease, come to an end<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to come to an end<LI>(Hiphil) to make an end</OL></OL>'),
(5487, '@wo', 'corresponding to (05486)', 'cuwph', 'TWOT - 2888', 'soof', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05486»; to come to an end:-- consume, fulfill.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be fulfilled, be completed, come to an end<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to be fulfilled, be completed<LI>(Aphel) to put an end to</OL></OL>'),
(5488, '@wo', 'probably of Egyptian origin', 'cuwph', 'TWOT - 1479', 'soof', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably of Egyptian origin; a reed, especially the papyrus:--flag, Red (sea), weed. Compare «05489».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>reed, rush, water plant<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>rushes<LI>sea of rushes<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of Red Sea<LI>of arms of Red Sea<LI>of Gulf of Suez<LI>of sea from straits to Gulf of Akaba</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5489, '@wo', 'for (05488) (by ellipsis of (03220))', 'Cuwph', 'TWOT - 1479', 'soof', 'Proper Name Location', 'for «05488» (by ellipsis of «03220»); the Reed (Sea):--Red Sea.', 'Suph = \"sea weed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place opposite the site of the giving of the Deuteronomic law</OL>'),
(5490, '@wo', 'from (05486)', 'cowph', 'TWOT - 1478a', 'sofe', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05486»; a termination:--conclusion, end, hinder participle', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>end, conclusion</OL>'),
(5491, '@wo', 'corresponding to (05490)', 'cowph', 'TWOT - 2888a', 'sofe', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05490»:--end.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>end, conclusion</OL>'),
