(5927, 'hl[', 'a primitive root', '`alah', 'TWOT - 1624', 'aw-law\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to ascend, intransitively (be high) or actively (mount); used in a great variety of senses, primary and secondary, literal and figurative (as follow):--arise (up), (cause to) ascend up, at once, break (the day) (up), bring (up), (cause to) burn, carry up, cast up, + shew, climb (up), (cause to, make to) come (up), cut off, dawn, depart, exalt, excel, fall, fetch up, get up, (make to) go (away, up); grow (over) increase, lay, leap, levy, lift (self) up, light, (make) up, × mention, mount up, offer, make to pay, + perfect, prefer, put (on), raise, recover, restore, (make to) rise (up), scale, set (up), shoot forth (up), (begin to) spring (up), stir up, take away (up), work.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go up, ascend, climb<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go up, ascend<LI>to meet, visit, follow, depart, withdraw, retreat<LI>to go up, come up (of animals)<LI>to spring up, grow, shoot forth (of vegetation)<LI>to go up, go up over, rise (of natural phenomenon)<LI>to come up (before God)<LI>to go up, go up over, extend (of boundary)<LI>to excel, be superior to</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be taken up, be brought up, be taken away<LI>to take oneself away<LI>to be exalted</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bring up, cause to ascend or climb, cause to go up<LI>to bring up, bring against, take away<LI>to bring up, draw up, train<LI>to cause to ascend<LI>to rouse, stir up (mentally)<LI>to offer, bring up (of gifts)<LI>to exalt<LI>to cause to ascend, offer</OL><LI>(Hophal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be carried away, be led up<LI>to be taken up into, be inserted in<LI>to be offered</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to lift oneself</OL></OL>'),
(5928, 'hl[', 'corresponding to (05930)', '`alah', 'TWOT - 2909e', 'al-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05930»; a holocaust:--burnt offering.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>burnt offering, holocaust</OL>'),
(5929, 'hl[', 'from (05927)', '`aleh', 'TWOT - 1624a', 'aw-leh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05927»; a leaf (as coming up on a tree); collectively, foliage:--branch, leaf.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>leaf, leafage</OL>'),
(5930, 'hl[', 'f act part of (05927)', '`olah', 'TWOT - 1624c,1624d', 'o-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or mowlah {o-law\'}; feminine active participle of «05927»; a step or (collectively, stairs, as ascending); usually a holocaust (as going up in smoke):--ascent, burnt offering (sacrifice), go up to. See also «05766».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>whole burnt offering<LI>ascent, stairway, steps</OL>'),
(5931, 'hll[', 'from a root corresponding to (05927)', '`illah', 'TWOT - 2910', 'il-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) feminine from a root corresponding to «05927»; a pretext (as arising artificially):--occasion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>matter, affair, occasion</OL>'),
(5932, 'hwl[', 'for (05766)', '`alvah', 'TWOT - 1580b', 'al-vaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'for «05766»; moral perverseness:--iniquity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>injustice, unrighteousness, iniquity</OL>'),
(5933, 'hwl[', 'the same as (05932)', '`Alvah', 'None', 'al-vaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or  Alyah {al-yaw\'}; the same as «05932»; Alvah or Aljah, an Idumaean:--Aliah, Alvah.', 'Aliah or Alvah = \"evil\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a duke of Edom</OL>'),
(5934, '~wl[', 'pass part of (05956) in the denominative sense of (05958)', '`aluwm', 'TWOT - 1630c', 'aw-loom\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'passive participle of «05956» in the denominative sense of «05958»; (only in plural as abstract) adolescence; figuratively, vigor:--youth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>youth, youthful, vigour</OL>'),
(5935, '!wl[', 'from (05927)', '`Alvan', 'None', 'al-vawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or sAlyan {al-yawn\'}; from «05927»; lofty; Alvan or Aljan, an Idumaean:--Alian, Alvan.', 'Alian or Alvan = \"tall\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Horite, son of Shobal</OL>'),
(5936, 'hqwl[', 'pass part of an unused root meaning to suck', '`aluwqah', 'TWOT - 1636a', 'al-oo-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine passive participle of an unused root meaning to suck; the leech:--horse-leech.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>leech</OL>'),
(5937, 'zl[', 'a primitive root', '`alaz', 'TWOT - 1625', 'aw-laz\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to jump for joy, i.e. exult:--be joyful, rejoice, triumph.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to exult, rejoice, triumph</OL>'),
(5938, 'zl[', 'from (05937)', '`alez', 'TWOT - 1625a', 'aw-laze\'', 'Adjective', 'from «05937»; exultant:--that rejoiceth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>exultant, jubilant</OL>'),
(5939, 'htl[', 'from an unused root meaning to cover', '`alatah', 'TWOT - 1626', 'al-aw-taw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from an unused root meaning to cover; dusk:--dark, twilight.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thick darkness</OL>'),
(5940, 'yl[', 'from (05927)', '`eliy', 'TWOT - 1624b', 'el-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05927»; a pestle (as lifted):--pestle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pestle</OL>'),
(5941, 'yl[', 'from (05927)', '`Eliy', 'None', 'ay-lee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05927»; lofty; Eli, an Israelite high-priest:--Eli.', 'Eli = \"ascension\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendant of Aaron through Ithamar and high priest and judge of Israel when Samuel entered service as a child</OL>'),
(5942, 'yll[', 'from (05927)', '`illiy', 'TWOT - 1624e', 'il-lee\'', 'Adjective', 'from «05927»; high; i.e. comparative:--upper.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>upper</OL>'),
(5943, 'yll[', 'corresponding to (05942)', '`illay', 'TWOT - 2909d', 'il-lah\'-ee', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05942»; supreme (i.e. God):--(most) high.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>highest, the Most High</OL>'),
(5944, 'hyl[', 'from (05927)', '`aliyah', 'TWOT - 1624f', 'al-ee-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from «05927»; something lofty, i.e. a stair-way; also a second-story room (or even one on the roof); figuratively, the sky:--ascent, (upper) chamber, going up, loft, parlour.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>roof-room, roof chamber</OL>'),
(5945, '!wyla', 'from (05927)', '\'elyown', 'TWOT - 1624g,1624h', 'el-yone\'', '', 'from «05927»; an elevation, i.e. (adj.) lofty (compar.); as title, the Supreme:--(Most, on) high(-er, -est), upper(-most).', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>high, upper<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of Davidic king exalted above monarchs n m</OL><LI>Highest, Most High<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>name of God<LI>of rulers, either monarchs or angel-princes</OL></OL>'),
(5946, '!wyl[', 'corresponding to (05945)', '`elyown', 'TWOT - 2909c', 'el-yone\'', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05945»; the Supreme:--Most high.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the Most High<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of God</OL></OL>'),
(5947, 'zyll[', 'from (05937)', '`alliyz', 'TWOT - 1625b', 'al-leez\'', 'Adjective', 'from «05937»; exultant:--joyous, (that)  rejoice(-ing)', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>exultant, jubilant</OL>'),
(5948, 'lyl[', 'from (05953) in the sense of completing', '`aliyl', 'TWOT - 1628b', 'al-eel\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05953» in the sense of completing; probably a crucible (as working over the metal):--furnace.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>furnace, crucible</OL>'),
(5949, 'hlyl[', 'from (05953) in the sense of effecting', '`aliylah', 'TWOT - 1627c', 'al-ee-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or malilah {al-ee-law\'}; from «05953» in the sense of effecting; an exploit (of God), or a performance (of man, often in a bad sense); by implication, an opportunity:--act(-ion), deed, doing, invention, occasion, work.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wantonness, deed, doing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>wantonness<LI>deed<LI>practices, evil deeds</OL></OL>'),
(5950, 'hylyl[', 'for (05949)', '`aliyliyah', 'TWOT - 1627d', 'al-ee-lee-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'for «05949»; (miraculous) execution:--work.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>deed</OL>'),
(5951, 'twcyl[', 'from (05970)', '`aliytsuwth', 'TWOT - 1635a', 'al-ee-tsooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05970»; exultation:--rejoicing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>exultation</OL>'),
(5952, 'tyll[', 'from (05927)', '`alliyth', 'None', 'al-leeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05927»; a second-story room:--chamber. Compare «05944».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>roof-room, roof chamber</OL>'),
(5953, 'll[', 'a primitive root', '`alal', 'TWOT - 1627,1627b,1628', 'aw-lal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to effect thoroughly; specifically, to glean (also figuratively); by implication (in a bad sense) to overdo, i.e. maltreat, be saucy to, pain, impose (also literal):--abuse, affect, × child, defile, do, glean, mock, practise, thoroughly, work (wonderfully).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to act severely, deal with severely, make a fool of someone<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Poel) to act severely<LI>(Poal) to be severely dealt with<LI>(Hithpael) to busy oneself, divert oneself, deal wantonly, deal ruthlessly, abuse (by thrusting through)<LI>(Hithpoel) to practise practices, thrust forth (in wickedness)</OL><LI>(Poel) to glean<LI>(Poel) to act or play the child<LI>(Poel) to insert, thrust, thrust in, thrust upon</OL>'),
(5954, 'll[', 'corresponding to (05953) (in the sense of thrusting oneself in), to enter', '`alal', 'TWOT - 2911', 'al-al\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05953» (in the sense of thrusting oneself in), to enter; causatively, to introduce:--bring in, come in, go in.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to thrust in, go in, come in<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to go in, come in<LI>(Aphel) to bring in<LI>(Hophal) to be brought in</OL></OL>'),
(5955, 'hll[', 'act part of (05953)', '`olelah', 'TWOT - 1627a', 'o-lay-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine active participle of «05953»; only in plural gleanings; by extens. gleaning-time:--(gleaning) (of the) grapes, grapegleanings.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gleaning</OL>'),
(5956, '~l[', 'a primitive root', '`alam', 'TWOT - 1629', 'aw-lam\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to veil from sight, i.e. conceal (literally or figuratively):--X any ways, blind, dissembler, hide (self), secret (thing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to conceal, hide, be hidden, be concealed, be secret<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) secret (participle)<LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be concealed<LI>concealed, dissembler (participle)</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to conceal, hide<LI>(Hithpael) to hide oneself</OL></OL>'),
(5957, '~l[', 'corresponding to (05769)', '`alam', 'TWOT - 2912', 'aw-lam\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05769»; remote time, i.e. the future or past indefinitely; often adverb, forever:--for ((n-))ever (lasting), old.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>perpetuity, antiquity, for ever</OL>'),
(5958, '~l[', 'from (05956)', '`elem', 'TWOT - 1630a', 'eh\'-lem', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05956»; properly, something kept out of sight (compare «05959»), i.e. a lad:--young man, stripling.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>young man</OL>'),
(5959, 'hml[', 'from (05958)', '`almah', 'TWOT - 1630b', 'al-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «05958»; a lass (as veiled or private):--damsel, maid, virgin.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>virgin, young woman<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of marriageable age<LI>maid or newly married ++++ There is no instance where it can be proved that this word designates a young woman who is not a virgin. (TWOT)</OL></OL>'),
(5960, '!wml[', 'from (05956)', '`Almown', 'None', 'al-mone\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «05956»; hidden; Almon, a place in Palestine See also «05963».', 'Almon = \"concealed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Benjamin allotted to the priests</OL>'),
(5961, 'twml[', 'pl. of (05959)', '`Alamowth', 'None', 'al-aw-moth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'plural of «05959»; properly, girls, i.e. the soprano or female voice, perhaps falsetto:--Alamoth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>young women, soprano?<OL TYPE=\"b\"><LI>a term in psalm heading - Alamoth</OL></OL>'),
(5962, 'yml[', 'patrial from a name corresponding to (05867) contracted', '`Almiy', 'None', 'al-mee\'', 'Noun', '(Aramaic) patrial from a name corresponding to 5867 contracted; an Elamite or inhabitant of Elam:--Elamite.', 'Elamites = see Elam \"their heaps\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a native of Elam</OL>'),
(5963, 'hmytlbd !ml[', 'from the same as (05960) and the dual of (01690) [compare (01015)] with enclitic of direction', '`Almon', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the same as «05960» and the dual of «01690» (compare «01015») with enclitic of direction; Almon towards Diblathajim; Almon-Diblathajemah, a place in Moab:  --Almon-dilathaim.', 'Almon-diblathaim = \"concealing the two cakes\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a station of the Israelites in the wilderness of Moab</OL>'),
(5964, 'tml[', 'from (05956)', '`Alemeth', 'None', 'aw-leh\'-meth', '', 'from «05956»; a covering; Alemeth, the name of a place in Palestine and of two Israelites:--Alameth, Alemeth.', 'Alameth or Alemeth = \"covering\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, son of Jehoadah or Jerah and descended from Saul through Jonathan<LI>a town in Benjamin</OL>'),
(5965, 'ol[', 'a primitive root', '`alac', 'TWOT - 1632', 'aw-las\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to leap for joy, i.e. exult, wave joyously:--X peacock, rejoice, solace self.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rejoice<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to rejoice<LI>(Niphal) to exult<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to flap joyously (of ostrich)</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to delight oneself</OL></OL>'),
(5966, '[l[', 'a primitive root', '`ala`', 'TWOT - 1633', 'aw-lah\'', 'Verb', 'a prim root; to sip up:--suck up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to suck up (meaning uncertain)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to drink</OL></OL>'),
(5967, '[l[', 'corresponding to (06763)', '`ala`', 'TWOT - 2913', '', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06763»; a rib:--rib.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rib</OL>'),
(5968, '@l[', 'a primitive root', '`alaph', 'TWOT - 1634', 'aw-laf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to veil or cover; figuratively, to be languid:--faint, overlaid, wrap self.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cover<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pual) covered, encrusted (participle)<LI>(Hithpael) to enwrap oneself, disguise oneself, faint</OL></OL>'),
(5969, 'hpl[', 'from (05968)', '`ulpeh', 'TWOT - 1634', 'ool-peh\'', '', 'from «05968»; an envelope, i.e. (figuratively) mourning:--fainted.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wilted, fainted</OL>'),
(5970, '#l[', 'a primitive root', '`alats', 'TWOT - 1635', 'aw-lats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to jump for joy, i.e. exult:--be joyful, rejoice, triumph.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rejoice, exult<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to exult</OL></OL>'),
(5971, '~[', 'from (06004)', '`am', 'TWOT - 1640a,1640e', 'am', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06004»; a people (as a congregated unit); specifically, a tribe (as those of Israel); hence (collectively) troops or attendants; figuratively, a flock:--folk, men, nation, people.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nation, people<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>people, nation<LI>persons, members of one\'s people, compatriots, country-men</OL><LI>kinsman, kindred</OL>'),
(5972, '~[', 'corresponding to (05971)', '`am', 'TWOT - 2914', 'am', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05971»:--people.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>people</OL>'),
(5973, '~[', 'from (06004)', '`im', 'TWOT - 1640b', 'eem', 'Preposition', 'from «06004»; adverb or preposition, with (i.e. in conjunction with), in varied applications; specifically, equally with; often with prepositional prefix (and then usually unrepresented in English):--accompanying, against, and, as (X  long as), before, beside, by (reason of), for all, from (among, between), in, like, more than, of,  (un-)to, with(-al).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>with<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>with<LI>against<LI>toward<LI>as long as<LI>beside, except<LI>in spite of</OL></OL>'),
(5974, '~[', 'corresponding to (05973)', '`im', 'TWOT - 2915', 'eem', 'Preposition', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05973»:--by, from, like, to(-ward), with.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>with<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>together with, with<LI>with, during</OL></OL>'),
(5975, 'dm[', 'a primitive root', '`amad', 'TWOT - 1637', 'aw-mad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to stand, in various relations (literal and figurative, intransitive and transitive):--abide (behind), appoint, arise, cease, confirm, continue, dwell, be employed, endure, establish, leave, make, ordain, be (over), place, (be) present (self), raise up, remain, repair, + serve, set (forth, over, -tle, up), (make to, make to be at a, with-)stand (by, fast, firm, still, up), (be at a) stay (up), tarry.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to stand, remain, endure, take one\'s stand<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to stand, take one\'s stand, be in a standing attitude, stand forth, take a stand, present oneself, attend upon, be or become servant of<LI>to stand still, stop (moving or doing), cease<LI>to tarry, delay, remain, continue, abide, endure, persist, be steadfast<LI>to make a stand, hold one\'s ground<LI>to stand upright, remain standing, stand up, rise, be erect, be upright<LI>to arise, appear, come on the scene, stand forth, appear, rise up or against<LI>to stand with, take one\'s stand, be appointed, grow flat, grow insipid</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to station, set<LI>to cause to stand firm, maintain<LI>to cause to stand up, cause to set up, erect<LI>to present (one) before (king)<LI>to appoint, ordain, establish</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be presented, be caused to stand, be stood before</OL></OL>'),
(5976, 'dm[', 'for (04571)', '`amad', 'TWOT - 1637', 'aw-mad\'', 'Verb', 'for «04571»; to shake:--be at a stand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be at a stand, stand, remain, endure</OL>'),
(5977, 'dm[', 'from (5975)', '`omed', 'TWOT - 1637a', 'o\'-med', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05975»; a spot (as being fixed):--place, (+ where) stood, upright.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>standing place</OL>'),
(5978, 'dmm[', 'prol for (05973)', '`immad', 'TWOT - 1640b', 'im-mawd\'', 'Preposition', 'prol. for «05973»; along with:--against, by, from, + me, + mine, of, + that I take, unto, upon, with(-in.)', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>with</OL>'),
(5979, 'hdm[', 'from (05975)', '`emdah', 'TWOT - 1637b', 'em-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05975»; a station, i.e. domicile:--standing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>standing ground</OL>'),
(5980, 'hmm[', 'from (06004)', '`ummah', 'TWOT - 1640f', 'oom-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06004»; conjunction, i.e. society; mostly adverb or preposition (with prepositional prefix), near, beside, along with:--(over) against, at, beside, hard by, in points.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>juxtaposition<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used only as a prep<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>close by, side by side with, alongside of, parallel with<LI>agreeing with, corresponding to, exactly as, close beside<LI>correspondingly to</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5981, 'hmm[', 'the same as (05980)', '`Ummah', 'None', 'oom-maw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «05980»; association; Ummah, a place in Palestine:--Ummah.', 'Ummah = \"union\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the cities of Asher; also probably \'Acco\'</OL>'),
(5982, 'dwmm[', 'from (05975)', '`ammuwd', 'TWOT - 1637c', 'am-mood\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or  ammud {am-mood\'}; from «05975»; a column (as standing); also a stand, i.e. platform:--X apiece, pillar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pillar, column<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>pillar<LI>column, upright<LI>column (of smoke)</OL></OL>'),
(5983, '!wmm[', 'from (05971)', '`Ammown', 'TWOT - 1642', 'am-mone\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05971»; tribal, i.e. inbred; Ammon, a son of Lot; also his posterity and their country:--Ammon, Ammonites.', 'Ammon = \"tribal\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a people dwelling in Transjordan descended from Lot through Ben-ammi</OL>'),
(5984, 'ynwmm[', 'patronymically from (05983)', '`Ammowniy', 'TWOT - 1642a', 'am-mo-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from «05983»; an Ammonite or (the adjective) Ammonitish:--Ammonite(-s).', 'Ammonite = see Ammon \"tribal\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Ammon and inhabitants of Ammon</OL>'),
(5985, 'tynwmma', 'fem of (05984)', '\'Ammowniyth', 'None', 'am-mo-neeth\'', 'Adjective', 'feminine of «05984»; an Ammonitess:--Ammonite(-ss).', 'Ammonitess = see Ammon \"tribal\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a woman of Ammon</OL>'),
(5986, 'owm[', 'from (06006)', '`Amowc', 'None', 'aw-moce\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06006»; burdensome; Amos, an Israelite prophet:--Amos.', 'Amos = \"burden\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a prophet of the Lord who prophesied in the northern kingdom; native of Tekoa in Judah near Bethlehem and a shepherd by trade; author of the prophetic book by his name</OL>'),
(5987, 'qwm[', 'from (06009)', '`Amowq', 'None', 'aw-moke\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06009»; deep; Amok, an Israelite:--Amok.', 'Amok = \"to be deep\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest who returned with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(5988, 'laymm[', 'from (05971) and (0410)', '`Ammiy\'el', 'None', 'am-mee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05971» and «0410»; people of God; Ammiel, the name of three or four Israelites:--Ammiel.', 'Ammiel = \"my kinsman is God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the spy from the tribe of Dan who perished in the plague for his evil report<LI>father of Machir of Lo-debar<LI>father of Bathsheba; also \'Eliam\'<LI>the 6th son of Obed-edom and doorkeeper of the temple</OL>'),
(5989, 'dwhymm[', 'from (05971) and (01935)', '`Ammiyhuwd', 'None', 'am-mee-hood\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05971» and «01935»; people of splendor; Ammihud, the name of three Israelites:--Ammihud.', 'Ammihud = \"my kinsman is majesty\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Ephraimite, father of Elishama, the chief of the tribe at the time of the exodus<LI>a Simeonite, father of Shemuel<LI>father of Pedahel, prince of the tribe of Naphtali<LI>father of king Talmai of Geshur<LI>a descendant of Judah through his son Pharez</OL>'),
(5990, 'dbzymm[', 'from (05971) and (02064)', '`Ammiyzabad', 'None', 'am-mee-zaw-bawd\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05971» and «02064»; people of endowment; Ammizabad, an Israelite:--Ammizabad.', 'Ammizabad = \"my people have bestowed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Benaiah, who commanded the 3rd division of David\'s army</OL>'),
(5991, 'rwxymm[', 'from (05971) and (02353)', '`Ammiychuwr', 'None', 'am-mee-khoor\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05971» and «02353»; people of nobility; Ammichur, a Syrian prince:--Ammihud (from the margin).', 'Ammihud = \"people of majesty\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a ruler of Syria</OL>'),
(5992, 'bdnymm[', 'from (05971) and (05068)', '`Ammiynadab', 'None', 'am-mee-naw-dawb\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05971» and «05068»; people of liberality; Amminadab, the name of four Israelites:--Amminadab.', 'Amminadab = \"my kinsman is noble\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Ram or Aram and father of Nahshon or Naasson and an ancestor of Jesus; father-in-law of Aaron<LI>a Kohathite Levite and chief of the sons of Uzziel<LI>a Levite, son of Kohath; also \'Izhar\'</OL>'),
(5993, 'bydn ymm[', 'from (05971) and (05081)', '`Ammiy', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05971» and «05081»; my people (is) liberal; Ammi-Nadib, probably an Israelite:--Amminadib.', 'Amminadib = \"my people are willing\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an unknown person noted for the swiftness of his chariots<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>possibly not a person but should be translated \'my willing people\'</OL></OL>'),
(5994, 'qym[', 'corresponding to (06012)', '`amiyq', 'TWOT - 2916', 'am-eek\'', '', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06012»; profound, i.e. unsearchable, deep.', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>deep subst<LI>deep things, deep mysteries</OL>'),
(5995, 'rym[', 'from (06014)', '`amiyr', 'TWOT - 1645c', 'aw-meer\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06014»; a bunch of grain:--handful, sheaf.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>swath, a row of fallen grain</OL>'),
(5996, 'yddXymm[', 'from (05971) and (07706)', '`Ammiyshadday', 'None', 'am-mee-shad-dah\'ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05971» and «07706»; people of (the) Almighty; Ammishaddai, an Israelite:--Ammishaddai.', 'Ammishaddai = \"my kinsman is Almighty\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Ahiezer, prince of the tribe of Dan at the time of the exodus</OL>'),
(5997, 'tym[', 'from a primitive root meaning to associate', '`amiyth', 'TWOT - 1638a', 'aw-meeth\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from a primitive root meaning to associate; companionship; hence (concretely) a comrade or kindred man:--another, fellow, neighbour.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>relation, neighbour, associate, fellow</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(5998, 'lm[', 'a primitive root', '`amal', 'TWOT - 1639', 'aw-mal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to toil, i.e. work severely and with irksomeness:--(take) labour (in).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to labour, toil<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to labour</OL></OL>'),
(5999, 'lm[', 'from (05998)', '`amal', 'TWOT - 1639a', 'aw-mawl\'', 'Noun', 'from «05998»; toil, i.e. wearing effort; hence, worry, wheth. of body or mind:--grievance(-vousness), iniquity, labour, mischief, miserable(-sery), pain(-ful), perverseness, sorrow, toil, travail, trouble, wearisome, wickedness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>toil, trouble, labour<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>trouble<LI>trouble, mischief<LI>toil, labour</OL></OL>'),
(6000, 'lm[', 'the same as (05999)', '`Amal', 'None', 'aw-mawl\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «05999»; Amal, an Israelite:--Amal.', 'Amal = \"labour\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Asherite, son of Helem</OL>'),
(6001, 'lm[', 'from (05998)', '`amel', 'TWOT - 1639b,1639c', 'aw-male\'', '', 'from «05998»; toiling; concretely, a laborer; figuratively, sorrowful:--that laboureth, that is a misery, had taken (labour), wicked, workman.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>labourer, sufferer, wretched one<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>labourer, workman<LI>sufferer adj v</OL><LI>toiling</OL>'),
(6002, 'qlm[', 'probably of foreign origin', '`Amaleq', 'None', 'am-aw-lake\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably of foreign origin; Amalek, a descendant of Esau; also his posterity and their country:--Amalek.', 'Amalek = \"dweller in a valley\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Eliphaz by his concubine Timnah, grandson of Esau, and progenitor of a tribe of people in southern Canaan<LI>descendants of Amalek</OL>'),
(6003, 'yqlm[', 'from (06002)', '`Amaleqiy', 'None', 'am-aw-lay-kee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from «06002»; an Amalekite (or collectively the Amalekites) or descendants of Amalek:  --Amalekite(-s).', 'Amalekite = see Amalek \"people of lapping\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Amalek, the grandson of Esau</OL>'),
(6004, '~m[', 'a primitive root', '`amam', 'TWOT - 1641', 'aw-mam\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to associate; by implication, to overshadow (by huddling together):--become dim, hide.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dim, darken, grow dark<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to dim, eclipse, be held dark<LI>(Hophal) to be dimmed, grow dark</OL></OL>'),
(6005, 'lawnmm[', 'from (05973) and (0410) with a pronominal suffix inserted', '`Immanuw\'el', 'TWOT - 1640d', 'im-maw-noo-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05973» and «0410» with a pronominal suffix inserted; with us (is) God; Immanuel, a type name of Isaiah\'s son:--Immanuel.', 'Immanuel = \"God with us\" or \"with us is God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>symbolic and prophetic name of the Messiah, the Christ, prophesying that He would be born of a virgin and would be \'God with us\'</OL>'),
(6006, 'om[', 'a primitive root', '`amac', 'TWOT - 1643', 'aw-mas\'', 'Verb', 'or mamas {aw-mas\'}; a primitive root; to load, i.e. impose a burden (or figuratively, infliction):--be borne, (heavy) burden (self), lade, load, put.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to load, carry, carry a load<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to load<LI>to carry a load</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to lay a load on</OL></OL>'),
(6007, 'hyom[', 'from (06006) and (03050)', '`Amacyah', 'None', 'am-as-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06006» and «03050»; Jah has loaded; Amasjah, an Israelite:--Amasiah.', 'Amasiah = \"Jehovah is strength\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Zichri and captain of 200,000 warriors of Judah in the reign of king Jehoshaphat of Judah</OL>'),
(6008, 'd[m[', 'from (05971) and (05703)', '`Am`ad', 'None', 'am-awd\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «05971» and «05703»; people of time; Amad, a place in Palestine:--Amad.', 'Amad = \"enduring\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Asher on the border between Alammelech and Misheal</OL>'),
(6009, 'qm[', 'a primitive root', '`amaq', 'TWOT - 1644', 'aw-mak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) deep (literally or figuratively):--(be, have, make, seek) deep(-ly), depth, be profound.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be deep, be profound, make deep<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be deep<LI>(Hiphil) to make deep, make profound</OL></OL>'),
(6010, 'qm[', 'from (06009)', '`emeq', 'TWOT - 1644a', 'ay\'-mek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06009»; a vale (i.e. broad depression):--dale, vale, valley (often used as a part of proper names). See also «01025».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>valley, vale, lowland, open country</OL>'),
(6011, 'qm[', 'from (06009)', '`omeq', 'TWOT - 1644b', 'o\'-mek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06009»; depth:--depth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>depth</OL>'),
(6012, 'qm[', 'from (06009)', '`ameq', 'TWOT - 1644c', 'aw-make\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06009»; deep (literally or figuratively):--deeper, depth, strange.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>deep, unfathomable<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>unintelligible (of speech)</OL></OL>'),
(6013, 'qm[', 'from (06009)', '`amoq', 'TWOT - 1644d', 'aw-moke\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06009»; deep (literally or figuratively):--(X exceeding) deep (thing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>deep, mysterious, depths<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>deep<LI>unsearchable</OL></OL>'),
(6014, 'rm[', 'a primitive root', '`amar', 'TWOT - 1645,1646', 'aw-mar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, apparently to heap; figuratively, to chastise (as if piling blows); specifically (as denominative from «06016») to gather grain:--bind sheaves, make merchandise of.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bind sheaves<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to gather</OL><LI>to manipulate, deal tyrannically with<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hithpael) to treat as a slave</OL></OL>'),
(6015, 'rm[', 'corresponding to (06785)', '`amar', 'TWOT - 2917', 'am-ar\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06785»; wool:--wool.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wool</OL>'),
(6016, 'rm[', 'from (06014)', '`omer', 'TWOT - 1645b,1645a', 'o\'-mer', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06014»; properly, a heap, i.e. a sheaf; also an omer, as a dry measure:--omer, sheaf.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>omer<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a dry measure of 1/10 ephah (about 2 litres)</OL><LI>sheaf</OL>'),
(6017, 'hrm[', 'from (06014)', '`Amorah', 'None', 'am-o-raw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06014»; a (ruined) heap; Amorah, a place in Palestine:--Gomorrah.', 'Gomorrah = \"submersion\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the twin-city in evil with Sodom, both destroyed in judgment by God with fire from heaven<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of iniquity (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(6018, 'yrm[', 'from (06014)', '`Omriy', 'None', 'om-ree\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06014»; heaping; Omri, an Israelite:--Omri.', 'Omri = \"pupil of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>king of the northern kingdom of Israel, successor to king Elah for whom he was the captain of the army; ruled for 12 years and succeeded by his infamous son Ahab<LI>one of the sons of Becher the son of Benjamin<LI>a descendant of Pharez the son of Judah<LI>son of Michael and chief of the tribe of Issachar in the time of David</OL>'),
(6019, '~rm[', 'probably from (05971) and (07311)', '`Amram', 'None', 'am-rawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «05971» and «07311»; high people; Amram, the name of two Israelites:--Amram.', 'Amram = \"exalted people\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Kohath and Levi and father of Moses<LI>one of the sons of Bani who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(6020, 'ymrm[', 'from (06019)', '`Amramiy', 'None', 'am-raw-mee\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06019»; an Amramite or descendant of Amram:--Amramite.', 'Amramites = see Aram \"exalted\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a branch of the Kohathite family of the tribe of Levi and descendants of Amram, the father of Moses</OL>'),
(6021, 'aXm[', 'from (06006)', '`Amasa\'', 'None', 'am-aw-saw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06006»; burden; Amasa, the name of two Israelites:--Amasa.', 'Amasa = \"burden\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Ithra or Jether by Abigail the sister of David and general of the army of Absalom<LI>son of Hadlai and a prince of Ephraim in the reign of king Ahaz</OL>'),
(6022, 'yXm[', 'from (06006)', '`Amasay', 'None', 'am-aw-sah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06006»; burdensome; Amasai, the name of three Israelites:--Amasai.', 'Amasai = \"burdensome\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a warrior and chief of the captains of Judah and Benjamin who joined David at Ziklag<LI>a Kohathite Levite, father of Mahath and ancestor of Samuel<LI>a priest who blew the trumpet before the ark<LI>another Kohathite Levite in the reign of king Hezekiah of Judah</OL>'),
(6023, 'yoXm[', 'probably from (06006)', '`Amashcay', 'None', 'am-ash-sah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «06006»; burdensome; Amashsay, an Israelite:--Amashai.', 'Amashai = \"burdensome\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest, son of Azareel in the time of Nehemiah</OL>'),
(6024, 'bn[', 'from the same as (06025)', '`Anab', 'None', 'an-awb\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the same as «06025»; fruit; Anab, a place in Palestine:--Anab.', 'Anab = \"fruit\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in the mountains of southern Judah, 18 miles southwest of Hebron</OL>'),
(6025, 'bn[', 'from an unused root probably meaning to bear fruit', '`enab', 'TWOT - 1647a', 'ay-nawb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to bear fruit; a grape:--(ripe) grape, wine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>grape(s)</OL>'),
(6026, 'gn[', 'a primitive root', '`anag', 'TWOT - 1648', 'aw-nag\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be soft or pliable, i.e. (figuratively) effeminate or luxurious:--delicate(-ness), (have) delight (self), sport self.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be soft, be delicate, be dainty<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pual) to be delicate<LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be of dainty habit, be pampered<LI>to be happy about, take exquisite delight<LI>to make merry over, make sport of</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6027, 'gn[', 'from (06026)', '`oneg', 'TWOT - 1648a', 'o\'-neg', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06026»; luxury:--delight, pleasant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>exquisite delight, daintiness, delight, pleasantness</OL>'),
(6028, 'gn[', 'from (06026)', '`anog', 'TWOT - 1648b', 'aw-nogue\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06026»; luxurious:--delicate.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dainty, delicate</OL>'),
(6029, 'dn[', 'a primitive root', '`anad', 'TWOT - 1649', 'aw-nad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to lace fast:--bind, tie.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bind, tie up, bind around or upon<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to tie up</OL></OL>'),
(6030, 'hn[', 'a primitive root', '`anah', 'TWOT - 1650,1653', 'aw-naw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to eye or (generally) to heed, i.e. pay attention; by implication, to respond; by extens. to begin to speak; specifically to sing, shout, testify, announce:--give account, afflict (by mistake for «06031»), (cause to, give) answer, bring low (by mistake for «06031»), cry, hear, Leannoth, lift up, say, × scholar, (give a) shout, sing (together by course), speak, testify, utter, (bear) witness. See also «01042», «01043».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to answer, respond, testify, speak, shout<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to answer, respond to<LI>to testify, respond as a witness</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make answer<LI>to be answered, receive answer</OL></OL><LI>(Qal) to sing, utter tunefully<LI>(Qal) to dwell</OL>'),
(6031, 'hn[', 'a primitive root [possibly rather ident. with (06030) through the idea of looking down or browbeating]', '`anah', 'TWOT - 1651,1652', 'aw-naw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (possibly rather ident. with «06030» through the idea of looking down or browbeating); to depress literally or figuratively, transitive or intransitive (in various applications, as follows):--abase self, afflict(-ion, self), answer (by mistake for «06030»), chasten self, deal hardly with, defile, exercise, force, gentleness, humble (self), hurt, ravish, sing (by mistake for «06030»), speak (by mistake for «06030»), submit self, weaken, × in any wise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be occupied, be busied with<LI>to afflict, oppress, humble, be afflicted, be bowed down<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be put down, become low<LI>to be depressed, be downcast<LI>to be afflicted<LI>to stoop</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to humble oneself, bow down<LI>to be afflicted, be humbled</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to humble, mishandle, afflict<LI>to humble, be humiliated<LI>to afflict<LI>to humble, weaken oneself</OL><LI>(Pual)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be afflicted<LI>to be humbled</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to afflict<LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to humble oneself<LI>to be afflicted</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6032, 'hn[', 'corresponding to (06030)', '`anah', 'TWOT - 2918', 'an-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06030»:--answer, speak.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to answer, respond<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to answer, make reply<LI>to respond</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6033, 'hn[', 'corresponding to (06031)', '`anah', 'TWOT - 2919a', 'an-aw\'', '', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06031»:--poor.', 'v<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to be humble, be low adj<LI>poor, needy</OL>'),
(6034, 'hn[', 'probably from (06030)', '`Anah', 'None', 'an-aw\'', '', 'probably from «06030»; an answer; Anah, the name of two Edomites and one Edomitess:--Anah.', 'Anah = \"answer\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Zibeon and father of Aholibamah, a wife of Esau<LI>a Horite chief n pr f<LI>daughter of Zibeon</OL>'),
(6035, 'wn[', 'from (06031)', '`anav', 'TWOT - 1652a', 'aw-nawv\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (by intermixture with «06041») Aanayv {aw-nawv\'}; from «06031»; depressed (figuratively), in mind (gentle) or circumstances (needy, especially saintly):--humble, lowly, meek, poor. Compare «06041».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>poor, humble, afflicted, meek<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>poor, needy<LI>poor and weak<LI>poor, weak and afflicted<LI>humble, lowly, meek</OL></OL>'),
(6036, 'bwn[', 'pass. part. from the same as (06025)', '`Anuwb', 'None', 'aw-noob\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'passive participle from the same as «06025»; borne (as fruit); Anub, an Israelite:--Anub.', 'Anub = \"confederate\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Coz, descendant of Judah and Caleb through Ashur, the father of Tekoa</OL>'),
(6037, 'hwn[', 'from (06035)', '`anvah', 'TWOT - 1652b', 'an-vaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «06035»; mildness (royal); also (concretely) oppressed:--gentleness, meekness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>humility, meekness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>humility, meekness<LI>condescension</OL></OL>'),
(6038, 'hwn[', 'from (06035)', '`anavah', 'TWOT - 1652b', 'an-aw-vaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06035»; condescension, human and subjective (modesty), or divine and objective (clemency):--gentleness, humility, meekness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>humility, meekness</OL>'),
(6039, 'twn[', 'from (06031)', '`enuwth', 'TWOT - 1652c', 'en-ooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06031»; affliction:--affliction.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>affliction</OL>'),
(6040, 'yn[', 'from (06031)', '`oniy', 'TWOT - 1652e', 'on-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06031»; depression, i.e. misery:  --afflicted(-ion), trouble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>affliction, poverty, misery<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>affliction<LI>poverty</OL></OL>'),
(6041, 'yn[', 'from (06031)', '`aniy', 'TWOT - 1652d', 'aw-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06031»; depressed, in mind or circumstances (practically the same as «06035», although the margin constantly disputes this, making «06035» subjective and «06041» objective):--afflicted, humble, lowly, needy, poor.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>poor, afflicted, humble, wretched<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>poor, needy<LI>poor and weak<LI>poor, weak, afflicted, wretched<LI>humble, lowly</OL></OL>'),
(6042, 'ynn[', 'from (06031)', '`Unniy', 'None', 'oon-nee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06031»; afflicted; Unni, the name of two Israelites:--Unni.', 'Unni = \"afflicted\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite doorkeeper in the time of David<LI>a Levite concerned in the sacred office after the return from exile in Babylon</OL>'),
(6043, 'hyn[', 'from (06030)', '`Anayah', 'None', 'an-aw-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06030»; Jah has answered; Anajah, the name of two Israelites:--Anaiah.', 'Anaiah = \"Jehovah has answered\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest who helped Ezra and signed the covenant with Nehemiah</OL>'),
(6044, '~yn[', 'for pl. of (05869)', '`Aniym', 'None', 'aw-neem\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'for plural of «05869»; fountains; Anim, a place in Palestine:--Anim.', 'Anim = \"fountains\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in the mountains of southern Judah</OL>'),
(6045, '!yn[', 'from (06031)', '`inyan', 'TWOT - 1651a', 'in-yawn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06031»; ado, i.e. (generally) employment or (specifically) an affair:--business, travail.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>occupation, task, job</OL>'),
(6046, '~n[', 'from the dual of (05869)', '`Anem', 'None', 'aw-name\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the dual of «05869»; two fountains; Anem, a place in Palestine: Anem.', 'Anem = \"fountains\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levitical city in Issachar allotted to the Gershonites</OL>'),
(6047, '~mn[', 'as if pl. of some Egyptian word', '`Anamim', 'None', 'an-aw-meem\'', 'Noun', 'as if plural of some Egyptian word; Anamim, a son of Mizraim and his descendants, with their country:--Anamim.', 'Anamim = \"affliction of the waters\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a tribe of Egyptians</OL>'),
(6048, '$lmmn[', 'of foreign origin', '`Anammelek', 'None', 'an-am-meh\'-lek', 'Proper Name', 'of foreign origin; Anammelek, an Assyrian deity:--Anammelech.', 'Anammelech = \"image of the king\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Assyrian false god introduced to Israel during the monarchy; worshipped with rites resembling those of Molech; companion god of \'Adrammelech\'</OL>'),
(6049, '!n[', 'a primitive root', '`anan', 'TWOT - 1655,1656', 'aw-nan\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to cover; used only as a denominative from «06051», to cloud over; figuratively, to act covertly, i.e. practise magic:--X bring, enchanter, Meonemin, observe(-r of) times, soothsayer, sorcerer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to make appear, produce, bring (clouds)<LI>(Poel) to practise soothsaying, conjure<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to observe times, practice soothsaying or spiritism or magic or augury or witchcraft<LI>soothsayer, enchanter, sorceress, diviner, fortuneteller, barbarian, Meonenim (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(6050, '!n[', 'corresponding to (06051)', '`anan', 'TWOT - 2921', 'an-an\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06051»:--cloud.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cloud</OL>'),
