(6116, 'hrc[', 'from (06113)', '`atsarah', 'TWOT - 1675c', 'ats-aw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or matsereth {ats-eh\'-reth}; from «06113»; an assembly, especially on a festival or holiday:--(solemn) assembly (meeting).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>assembly, solemn assembly<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>assembly (sacred or festive meeting)<LI>assemblage, company, group</OL></OL>'),
(6117, 'bq[', 'a primitive root', '`aqab', 'TWOT - 1676', 'aw-kab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to swell out or up; used only as denominative from «06119», to seize by the heel; figuratively, to circumvent (as if tripping up the heels); also to restrain (as if holding by the heel):--take by the heel, stay, supplant, ×  utterly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to supplant, circumvent, take by the heel, follow at the heel, assail insidiously, overreach<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to supplant, overreach, attack at the heel<LI>(Piel) to hold back</OL></OL>'),
(6118, 'bq[', 'from (06117) in the sense of (6119)', '`eqeb', 'TWOT - 1676e', 'ay\'-keb', '', 'from «06117» in the sense of «06119»; a heel, i.e. (figuratively) the last of anything (used adverbially, for ever); also result, i.e. compensation; and so (adverb with preposition or relatively) on account of:--X because, by, end, for, if, reward.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>consequence<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>consequence<LI>consequence, gain, reward<LI>end adv</OL><LI>as a consequence, because, consequently conj<LI>as a consequence of, that, because</OL>'),
(6119, 'bq[', 'from (06117)', '`aqeb', 'TWOT - 1676a', 'aw-kabe\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (feminine) hiqqbah {ik-keb-aw\'}; from «06117»; a heel (as protuberant); hence, a track; figuratively, the rear (of an army):--heel, (horse-)hoof, last, lier in wait (by mistake for «06120»), (foot- )step.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>heel, rear, footprint, hinder part, hoof, rear of a troop, footstep<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>heel<LI>mark of heel, footprint<LI>hinder part, rear</OL></OL>'),
(6120, 'bq[', 'from (06117) in its denominative sense', '`aqeb', 'TWOT - 1676b', 'aw-kabe\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06117» in its denominative sense; a lier in wait:--heel (by mistake for «06119»).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>overreacher, supplanter</OL>'),
(6121, 'bq[', 'from (06117)', '`aqob', 'TWOT - 1676c', 'aw-kobe\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06117»; in the original sense, a knoll (as swelling up); in the denominative sense (transitive) fraudulent or (intransitive) tracked:--crooked, deceitful, polluted.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>deceitful, sly, insidious<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>deceitful, sly, insidious, slippery<LI>foot-tracked</OL><LI>steep, hilly</OL>'),
(6122, 'hbq[', 'from an unused form from (06117) meaning a trick', '`oqbah', 'TWOT - 1676d', 'ok-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of an unused form from «06117» meaning a trick; trickery:--subtilty.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>subtlety, insidiousness, craftiness</OL>'),
(6123, 'dq[', 'a primitive root', '`aqad', 'TWOT - 1677', 'aw-kad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to tie with thongs:--bind.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to bind, tie</OL>'),
(6124, 'dq[', 'from (06123)', '`aqod', 'TWOT - 1678a', 'aw-kode\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06123»; striped (with bands):--ring straked.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>streaked, striped</OL>'),
(6125, 'hq[', 'from (05781)', '`aqah', 'TWOT - 1585a', 'aw-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05781»; constraint:--oppression.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>oppression, pressure</OL>'),
(6126, 'bwqq[', 'from (06117)', '`Aqquwb', 'None', 'ak-koob\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06117»; insidious; Akkub, the name of five Israelites:--Akkub.', 'Akkub = \"insidious\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Elioenai and descendant of David through Zerubbabel<LI>a head of a family returning from exile<LI>head of a family of temple slaves returning from exile<LI>a Levite gatekeeper<LI>a Levite who helped Ezra expound the law to the people<LI>a Levite gatekeeper after the return from exile</OL>'),
(6127, 'lq[', 'a primitive root', '`aqal', 'TWOT - 1680', 'aw-kal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to wrest:--wrong.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bend, twist<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pual) to be bent out of shape, be distorted, be crooked</OL></OL>'),
(6128, 'lqlq[', 'from (06127)', '`aqalqal', 'TWOT - 1680a', 'ak-al-kal\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06127»; winding:--by(-way), crooked way.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>winding, devious, crooked</OL>'),
(6129, '!wtllq[', 'from (06127)', '`aqallathown', 'TWOT - 1680b', 'ak-al-law-thone\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06127»; tortuous:--crooked.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>crooked</OL>'),
(6130, '!q[', 'from an unused root meaning to twist', '`Aqan', 'None', 'aw-kawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to twist; tortuous; Akan, an Idummaean:--Akan. Compare «03292».', 'Akan = \"sharp-sighted\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Ezer, descendant of Seir, and one of the chiefs of the Horites of Edom</OL>'),
(6131, 'rq[', 'a primitive root', '`aqar', 'TWOT - 1681,1682', 'aw-kar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pluck up (especially by the roots); specifically, to hamstring; figuratively, to exterminate:--dig down, hough, pluck up, root up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pluck up, root up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to pluck up, root up<LI>(Niphal) to be plucked up</OL><LI>to cut, hamstring<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to cut, hamstring</OL></OL>'),
(6132, 'rq[', 'corresponding to (06131)', '`aqar', 'TWOT - 2926', 'ak-ar\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06131»:--pluck up by the roots.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pluck, be rooted up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Ithp\'al) to be rooted up</OL></OL>'),
(6133, 'rq[', 'from (06131) fig., a transplanted person, i.e. naturalised citizen', '`eqer', 'TWOT - 1681a', 'ay\'-ker', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06131». figuratively, a transplanted person, i.e. naturalized citizen:--stock.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>member, offspring, offshoot</OL>'),
(6134, 'rq[', 'the same as (06133)', '`Eqer', 'None', 'ay\'-ker', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «06133»; Eker, an Israelite:--Eker.', 'Eker = \"offspring\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Judah</OL>'),
(6135, 'rq[', 'from (06131)', '`aqar', 'TWOT - 1682a', 'aw-kawr\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06131»; sterile (as if extirpated in the generative organs):--(X male or female) barren (woman).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>barren, sterile</OL>'),
(6136, 'rqq[', 'from (06132)', '`iqqar', 'TWOT - 2926a', 'ik-kar\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «06132»; a stock:--stump.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>root, stock</OL>'),
(6137, 'brq[', 'of uncertain derivation', '`aqrab', 'TWOT - 1683', 'ak-rawb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; a scorpion; figuratively, a scourge or knotted whip:--scorpion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>scorpion</OL>'),
(6138, '!wrq[', 'from (06131)', '`Eqrown', 'None', 'ek-rone\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06131»; eradication; Ekron, a place in Palestine:--Ekron.', 'Ekron = \"emigration\" or \"torn up by the roots\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the most northerly of the 5 principal cities of the Philistines; located in the lowlands of Judah and later given to Dan</OL>'),
(6139, 'ynwrq[', 'from (06138)', '`Eqrowniy', 'None', 'ek-ro-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'or mEqroniy {ek-ro-nee\'; patrial from «06138»; an Ekronite or inhabitant of Ekron:--Ekronite.', 'Ekronites = see Ekron \"emigration\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Ekron</OL>'),
(6140, 'Xq[', 'a primitive root', '`aqash', 'TWOT - 1684', 'aw-kash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to knot or distort; figuratively, to pervert (act or declare perverse):--make crooked, (prove, that is) perverse(-rt).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be perverse, twist, pervert, make crooked, prove perverse, declare perverse<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be crooked<LI>(Piel) to twist, distort, pervert, make crooked<LI>(Hiphil) to declare crooked<LI>(Qal) perverse</OL></OL>'),
(6141, 'Xqq[', 'from (06140)', '`iqqesh', 'TWOT - 1684a', 'ik-kashe\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06140»; distorted; hence, false:--crooked, froward, perverse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>twisted, distorted, crooked, perverse, perverted</OL>'),
(6142, 'Xqq[', 'the same as (06141)', '`Iqqesh', 'None', 'ik-kashe\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «06141»; perverse; Ikkesh, an Israelite:--Ikkesh.', 'Ikkesh = \"twisted\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Ira, the Tekoite, and one of David\'s mighty warriors</OL>'),
(6143, 'twXqq[', 'from (06141)', '`iqqshuwth', 'TWOT - 1684b', 'ik-kesh-ooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06141»; perversity:--X froward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>distortion, crookedness</OL>'),
(6144, 'r[', 'the same as (05892)', '`Ar', 'None', 'awr', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «05892»; a city; Ar, a place in Moab:--Ar.', 'Ar = \"a city\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city of Moab located south of the Arnon river; perhaps the capital</OL>'),
(6145, 'r[', 'from (05782)', '`ar', 'TWOT - 1684+', 'awr', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05782»; a foe (as watchful for mischief):--enemy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>enemy, adversary, foe</OL>'),
(6146, 'r[', 'corresponding to (06145)', '`ar', 'TWOT - 2930a', 'awr', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06145»:--enemy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>enemy, adversary, foe</OL>'),
(6147, 'r[', 'from (05782)', '`Er', 'None', 'ayr', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05782»; watchful; Er, the name of two Israelites:--Er.', 'Er = \"awake\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the eldest son of Judah<LI>son of Shelah and grandson of Judah</OL>'),
(6148, 'br[', 'a primitive root', '`arab', 'TWOT - 1686', 'aw-rab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to braid, i.e. intermix; technically, to traffic (as if by barter); also or give to be security (as a kind of exchange):--engage, (inter-)meddle (with), mingle (self), mortgage, occupy, give pledges, be(-come, put in) surety, undertake.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pledge, exchange, mortgage, engage, occupy, undertake for, give pledges, be or become surety, take on pledge, give in pledge<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to take on pledge, go surety for<LI>to give in pledge<LI>to exchange<LI>to pledge</OL><LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to exchange pledges<LI>to have fellowship with, share</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6149, 'br[', 'a primitive root [identical with (0614) idea of close association]; to be agreeable', '`areb', 'TWOT - 1687a', 'aw-rabe\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «06148» through the idea of close association); to be agreeable:--be pleasant(-ing), take pleasure in, be sweet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be pleasant, be sweet, be pleasing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(TWOT) sweet, pleasant</OL></OL>'),
(6150, 'br[', 'a primitive root [identical with (06148) through the idea of covering with a texture]', '`arab', 'TWOT - 1689', 'aw-rab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «06148» through the idea of covering with a texture); to grow dusky at sundown:--be darkened, (toward) evening.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to become evening, grow dark<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to become evening, grow dark<LI>(Hiphil) to spend the evening, do at evening</OL></OL>'),
(6151, 'br[', 'corresponding to (06148)', '`arab', 'TWOT - 2927', 'ar-ab\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06148»; to commingle:--mingle (self), mix.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to mix, join together<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pael) mixed (participle)<LI>(Ithpael) mixed (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(6152, 'br[', 'from (06150) in the fig. sense of sterility', '`', 'TWOT - 1688a,1688c', '', 'Proper Name', 'or mArab {ar-ab\'}; from «06150» in the figurative sense of sterility; Arab (i.e. Arabia), a country East of Palestine:--Arabia.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>steppe-dwellers<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the people inhabiting the country east and south of Canaan, the nomadic desert Bedouins<LI>Arabians, Arabs</OL></OL>'),
(6153, 'br[', 'from (06150)', '`ereb', 'TWOT - 1689a', 'eh\'-reb', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06150»; dusk:--+ day, even(-ing, tide), night.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>evening, night, sunset<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>evening, sunset<LI>night</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(6154, 'br[', 'from (06148)', '`ereb', 'TWOT - 1685a,1685b', 'ay\'-reb', 'Noun Masculine', 'or mereb (1 Kings 10:15), (with the article prefix), {eh\'-reb}; from «06148»; the web (or transverse threads of cloth); also a mixture, (or mongrel race):--Arabia, mingled people, mixed (multitude), woof.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>woof<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>as mixed, interwoven<LI>knitted material</OL><LI>mixture, mixed people, mixed company</OL>'),
(6155, 'br[', 'from (06148)', '`arab', 'TWOT - 1690b', 'aw-rawb\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06148»; a willow (from the use of osiers as wattles):--willow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>poplar, willow<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a tree characterised by dark wood</OL></OL>'),
(6156, 'br[', 'from (06149)', '`areb', 'TWOT - 1687a', 'aw-rabe\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06149»; pleasant:--sweet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sweet, pleasant</OL>'),
(6157, 'br[', 'from (06148)', '`arob', 'TWOT - 1685c', 'aw-robe\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06148»; a mosquito (from its swarming):--divers sorts of flies, swarm.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>swarm<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>probable meaning from \'mixture\' and \'incessant or involved motion\'</OL></OL>'),
(6158, 'br[', 'from (06150)', '`oreb', 'TWOT - 1690a', 'o-rabe\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or mowreb {o-rabe\'}; from «06150»; a raven (from its dusky hue):--raven.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>raven</OL>'),
(6159, 'br[', 'the same as (06158)', '`Oreb', 'None', 'o-rabe\'', '', 'or mOwreb {o-rabe\'}; the same as «06158»; Oreb, the name of a Midianite and of the cliff near the Jordan:--Oreb.', 'Oreb = \"raven\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the chieftains of the Midianite army defeated by Gideon n pr loc<LI>a rock east of the Jordan where Oreb and part of his army fell to the Ephraimites</OL>'),
(6160, 'hbr[', 'from (06150) (in the sense of sterility)', '`arabah', 'TWOT - 1688d', 'ar-aw-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06150» (in the sense of sterility); a desert; especially (with the article prefix) the (generally) sterile valley of the Jordan and its continuation to the Red Sea:--Arabah, champaign, desert, evening, heaven, plain, wilderness. See also «01026».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>desert plain, steppe, desert, wilderness</OL>'),
(6161, 'hbbr[', 'fem. pass. part. of (06048) in the sense of a bargain or exchange', '`arubbah', 'TWOT - 1686a', 'ar-oob-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine passive participle of «06048» in the sense of a bargain or exchange; something given as security, i.e. (literally) a token (of safety) or (metaphorically) a bondsman:--pledge, surety.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pledge, token, bond, surety, thing exchanged</OL>'),
(6162, '!wbr[', 'from (06148) (in the sense of exchange)', '`arabown', 'TWOT - 1686b', 'ar-aw-bone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06148» (in the sense of exchange); a pawn (given as security):--pledge.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pledge, security</OL>'),
(6163, 'ybr[', 'from (06152)', '`Arabiy', 'None', 'ar-aw-bee\'', 'Adjective', 'or mArbiy {ar-bee\'}; patrial from «06152»; an Arabian or inhabitant of Arab (i.e. Arabia):--Arabian.', 'Arabian = see Arabia \"mixed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Arabia<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>steppe-dweller</OL></OL>'),
(6164, 'ytbr[', 'from (01026)', '`Arbathiy', 'None', 'ar-baw-thee\'', 'Adjective', 'patrial from «01026»; an Arbathite or inhabitant of (Beth-)Arabah:--Arbahite.', 'Arbathite = see Betharabah \"desert house\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Beth-arabah</OL>'),
(6165, 'gr[', 'a primitive root', '`arag', 'TWOT - 1691', 'aw-rag\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to long for:--cry, pant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to long for, pant after</OL>'),
(6166, 'dr[', 'from an unused root meaning to sequester itself', '`Arad', 'None', 'ar-awd\'', '', 'from an unused root meaning to sequester itself; fugitive; Arad, the name of a place near Palestine, also of a Canaanite and an Israelite:--Arad.', 'Arad = \"a wild ass\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, son of Beriah, who drove out the inhabitants of Gath n pr loc<LI>a royal city of the Canaanites north of the wilderness of Judah</OL>'),
(6167, 'dr[', 'corresponding to (06171)', '`arad', 'TWOT - 2928', 'ar-awd\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06171»; an onager:--wild ass.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wild ass</OL>'),
(6168, 'hr[', 'a primitive root', '`arah', 'TWOT - 1692', 'aw-raw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) bare; hence, to empty, pour out, demolish:--leave destitute, discover, empty, make naked, pour (out), rase, spread self, uncover.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be bare, be nude, uncover, leave destitute, discover, empty, raze, pour out<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bare, lay bare<LI>to lay bare by emptying, empty<LI>to pour out</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make naked, strip bare (of sexual offences)<LI>to pour out</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be poured out, be exposed<LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to expose oneself, make oneself naked<LI>pouring oneself, spreading oneself (participle)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6169, 'hr[', 'from (06168)', '`arah', 'TWOT - 1692a', 'aw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from «06168»; a naked (i.e. level) plot:--paper reed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bare place</OL>'),
(6170, 'hgwr[', 'pass. part. of (06165)', '`aruwgah', 'TWOT - 1691a', 'ar-oo-gaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or iarugah {ar-oo-gaw\'}; feminine passive participle of «06165»; something piled up (as if (figuratively) raised by mental aspiration), i.e. a paterre:--bed, furrow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>garden terrace or bed</OL>'),
(6171, 'dwr[', 'from the same as (06166)', '`arowd', 'TWOT - 1693', 'aw-rode\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «06166»; an onager (from his lonesome habits):--wild ass.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wild ass</OL>'),
(6172, 'hwr[', 'from (06168)', '`ervah', 'TWOT - 1692b', 'er-vaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06168»; nudity, literally (especially the pudenda) or figuratively (disgrace, blemish):--nakedness, shame, unclean(-ness).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nakedness, nudity, shame, pudenda<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>pudenda (implying shameful exposure)<LI>nakedness of a thing, indecency, improper behaviour<LI>exposed, undefended (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(6173, 'hwr[', 'corresponding to (06172)', '`arvah', 'TWOT - 2929', 'ar-vaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06172»; nakedness, i.e. (figuratively) impoverishment:--dishonor.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dishonour, nakedness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>dishonour (metaphor of nakedness)</OL></OL>'),
(6174, '~wr[', 'from (06191) (in its original sense)', '`arowm', 'TWOT - 1588c', 'aw-rome\'', 'Adjective', 'or marom {aw-rome\'}; from «06191» (in its original sense); nude, either partially or totally:--naked.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>naked, bare</OL>'),
(6175, '~wr[', 'pass. part. of (06191)', '`aruwm', 'TWOT - 1698c', 'aw-room\'', 'Adjective', 'passive participle of «06191»; cunning (usually in a bad sense):--crafty, prudent, subtil.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>subtle, shrewd, crafty, sly, sensible<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>crafty<LI>shrewd, sensible, prudent</OL></OL>'),
(6176, 'r[wr[', 'from (06209) reduplicated', '`arow`er', 'TWOT - 1705b,1705c', 'ar-o-ayr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or sarear {ar-awr\'}; from «06209» reduplicated; a juniper (from its nudity of situation):--health.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>naked, stripped, destitute<LI>tree or bush<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>probably juniper or cypress</OL></OL>'),
(6177, 'r[wr[', 'the same as (06176)', '`Arow`er', 'None', 'ar-o-ayr\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or `Aro`er {ar-o-ayr\'}; or `Ar`owr {ar-ore\'}; the same as «06176»; nudity of situation; Aroer, the name of three places in or near Palestine:--Aroer.', 'Aroer = \"ruins\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city on the north bank of the river Arnon, the southern point of the territory of Sihon the king of the Amorites and later of Reuben; modern \'Arair\'<LI>a city in Ammon near the Jabbok belonging to Gad<LI>a town in southern Judah</OL>'),
(6178, '#wr[', 'pass. part. of (06206)', '`aruwts', 'TWOT - 1702a', 'aw-roots\'', 'Adjective', 'passive participle of «06206»; feared, i.e. (concretely) a horrible place or chasm:--cliffs.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dreadful<LI>(CLBL) chasm, ravine, steep slope</OL>'),
(6179, 'yr[', 'from (05782)', '`Eriy', 'None', 'ay-ree\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05782»; watchful; Eri, an Israelite:--Eri.', 'Eri = \"watchful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Gad and progenitor of the family of Erites</OL>'),
(6180, 'yr[', 'patronymically of (06179)', '`Eriy', 'None', 'ay-ree\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically of «06179»; a Erite (collectively) or descendants of Eri:--Erites.', 'Erites = see Erites \"watchful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Eri, the son of Gad</OL>'),
(6181, 'hyr[', 'from (06172)', '`eryah', 'TWOT - 1692c', 'er-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'for «06172»; nudity:--bare, naked, × quite.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nudity, nakedness</OL>'),
(6182, 'hoyr[', 'from an unused root meaning to comminute', '`ariycah', 'TWOT - 1699a', 'ar-ee-saw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning to comminute; meal:--dough.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dough, meal, coarse meal, kneading trough<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(6183, '@yr[', 'from (06201)', '`ariyph', 'TWOT - 1701a', 'aw-reef\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06201»; the sky (as dropping at the horizon):--heaven.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cloud, mist</OL>'),
(6184, '#yr[', 'from (06206)', '`ariyts', 'TWOT - 1702b', 'aw-reets\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06206»; fearful, i.e. powerful or tyrannical:--mighty, oppressor, in great power, strong, terrible, violent.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>awe-inspiring, terror-striking, awesome, terrifying, ruthless, mighty</OL>'),
(6185, 'yryr[', 'from (06209)', '`ariyriy', 'TWOT - 1705a', 'ar-e-ree\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06209»; bare, i.e. destitute (of children):--childless.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stripped, childless, bare of children</OL>'),
(6186, '$r[', 'a primitive root', '`arak', 'TWOT - 1694', 'aw-rak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to set in a row, i.e. arrange, put in order (in a very wide variety of applications):--put (set) (the battle, self) in array, compare, direct, equal, esteem, estimate, expert (in war), furnish, handle, join (battle), ordain, (lay, put, reckon up, set) (in) order, prepare, tax, value.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to arrange, set or put or lay in order, set in array, prepare, order, ordain, handle, furnish, esteem, equal, direct, compare<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to arrange or set or lay in order, arrange, state in order, set forth (a legal case), set in place<LI>to compare, be comparable</OL></OL><LI>(Hiphil) to value, tax</OL>'),
(6187, '$r[', 'from (06186)', '`erek', 'TWOT - 1694a', 'eh\'rek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06186»; a pile, equipment, estimate:--equal, estimation, (things that are set in) order, price, proportion, × set at, suit, taxation, × valuest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>order, row, estimate, things that are set in order, layer, pile<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>order, row<LI>estimate, valuation</OL></OL>'),
(6188, 'lr[', 'a primitive root', '`arel', 'TWOT - 1695', 'aw-rale\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to strip; but used as denominative from «06189»; to expose or remove the prepuce, whether literal (to go naked) or figurative (to refrain from using):--count uncircumcised, foreskin to be uncovered.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to remain uncircumcised, count uncircumcised, count as foreskin<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to regard as uncircumcised<LI>to remain unharvested (fig.)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be counted as uncircumcised</OL></OL>'),
(6189, 'lr[', 'from (06188)', '`arel', 'TWOT - 1695b', 'aw-rale\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'rom «06188»; properly, exposed, i.e. projecting loose (as to the prepuce); used only technically, uncircumcised (i.e. still having the prepuce uncurtailed):--uncircumcised (person).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>uncircumcised, having foreskin</OL>'),
(6190, 'hlr[', 'from (06189)', '`orlah', 'TWOT - 1695a', 'or-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «06189»; the prepuce:--foreskin, + uncircumcised.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>foreskin, uncircumcised</OL>'),
(6191, '~r[', 'a primitive root', '`aram', 'TWOT - 1698', 'aw-ram\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to be (or make) bare; but used only in the derivative sense (through the idea perhaps of smoothness) to be cunning (usually in a bad sense):--X very, beware, take crafty (counsel), be prudent, deal subtilly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be subtle, be shrewd, be crafty, beware, take crafty counsel, be prudent<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be crafty, be subtle<LI>(Hiphil) to be crafty, be or become shrewd</OL></OL>'),
(6192, '~r[', 'a primitive root; to pile up', '`aram', 'TWOT - 1696', 'aw-ram\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pile up:--gather together.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Niphal) to heap up, pile, be heaped up</OL>'),
(6193, '~r[', 'from (06191)', '`orem', 'TWOT - 1698a', 'o\'-rem', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06191»; a stratagem:--craftiness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>subtlety, shrewdness, craftiness</OL>'),
(6194, '~r[', 'from (06192)', '`arem', 'TWOT - 1696a', 'aw-rame\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Jer. 50:26  or (feminine)  aremah {ar-ay-maw\'}; from «06192»; a heap; specifically, a sheaf:--heap (of corn), sheaf.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>heap, pile</OL>'),
(6195, 'hmr[', 'from (06193)', '`ormah', 'TWOT - 1698b', 'or-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «06193»; trickery; or (in a good sense) discretion:--guile, prudence, subtilty, wilily, wisdom.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shrewdness, craftiness, prudence</OL>'),
(6196, '!wmr[', 'probably from (06191)', '`armown', 'TWOT - 1697a', 'ar-mone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from «06191»; the plane tree (from its smooth and shed bark):--chestnut tree.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>plane-tree<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>as stripped of bark</OL></OL>'),
(6197, '!r[', 'probably from (05782)', '`Eran', 'None', 'ay-rawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «05782»; watchful; Eran, an Israelite:--Eran.', 'Eran = \"watcher\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the eldest son of Ephraim</OL>'),
(6198, 'ynr[', 'patronymically from (06197)', '`Eraniy', 'None', 'ay-raw-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from «06197»; an Eranite or descendant (collectively) of Eran:--Eranites.', 'Eranites = see Eran \"watcher\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the descendants of Eran, the son of Ephraim</OL>'),
(6199, 'r[r[', 'from (06209)', '`ar`ar', 'TWOT - 1705b', 'ar-awr\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06209»; naked, i.e. (figuratively) poor:--destitute. See also «06176».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stripped, destitute</OL>'),
(6200, 'yr[r[', 'patronymically from (06177)', '`Aro`eriy', 'None', 'ar-o-ay-ree\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from «06177»; an Aroerite or inhabitant of Aroer:--Aroerite.', 'Aroerite = see Aroer \"destitute\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Aroer</OL>'),
(6201, '@r[', 'a primitive root', '`araph', 'TWOT - 1701', 'aw-raf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to droop; hence, to drip:--drop (down).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to drop, drip<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to drop, trickle</OL></OL>'),
(6202, '@r[', 'a primitive root [identical with (06201) through the idea of sloping]', '`araph', 'TWOT - 1700', 'aw-raf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «06201» through the idea of sloping); properly, to bend downward; but used only as a denominative from «06203», to break the neck; hence (figuratively) to destroy:--that is beheaded, break down, break (cut off, strike off) neck.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to break the neck (of an animal)</OL>'),
(6203, '@r[', 'from (06202)', '`oreph', 'TWOT - 1700a', 'o-ref\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06202»; the nape or back of the neck (as declining); hence, the back generally (whether literal or figurative):-- back ((stiff-)neck((-ed).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>neck, back of the neck, back<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>back of the neck<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of fleeing foe<LI>of apostasy (fig.)</OL><LI>stiff of neck, obstinate (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(6204, 'hpr[', 'from (06203)', '`Orpah', 'None', 'or-paw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'feminine of «06203»; mane; Orpah, a Moabites:--Orpah.', 'Orpah = \"gazelle\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Moabite woman, wife of Chilion, the son of Naomi, and sister-in- law of Ruth</OL>'),
(6205, 'lpr[', 'probably from (06201)', '`araphel', 'TWOT - 1701b', 'ar-aw-fel\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from «06201»; gloom (as of a lowering sky):--(gross, thick) dark (cloud, -ness).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cloud, heavy or dark cloud, darkness, gross darkness, thick darkness</OL>'),
(6206, '#r[', 'a primitive root', '`arats', 'TWOT - 1702', 'aw-rats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to awe or (intransitive) to dread; hence, to harass:--be affrighted (afraid, dread, feared, terrified), break, dread, fear, oppress, prevail, shake terribly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tremble, dread, fear, oppress, prevail, break, be terrified, cause to tremble<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to tremble, terrify<LI>to tremble, feel dread</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be awesome, be terrible<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to regard or treat with awe, regard or treat as awful<LI>to inspire with awe, terrify</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6207, 'qr[', 'a primitive root', '\'araq', 'TWOT - 1703', 'aw-rak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to gnaw, i.e. (figuratively) eat (by hyberbole); also (participle) a pain:--fleeing, sinew.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to gnaw, chew</OL>'),
(6208, 'yqr[', 'from an unused name meaning a tush', '`Arqiy', 'None', 'ar-kee\'', 'Adjective', 'patrial from an unused name meaning a tush; an Arkite or inhabitant of Erek:--Arkite.', 'Arkite = see Arki \"gnawing\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Arki or Arka</OL>'),
(6209, 'rr[', 'a primitive root', '`arar', 'TWOT - 1705', 'aw-rar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to bare; figuratively, to demolish:--make bare, break, raise up (perhaps by clerical error for raze), ×  utterly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strip, make bare, strip oneself<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to strip, strip oneself<LI>(Poel) to lay bare<LI>(Hithpalpel) to be utterly stripped, be utterly laid bare<LI>(Pilpel) break</OL></OL>'),
(6210, 'Xr[', 'from an unused root meaning perhaps to arch', '`eres', 'TWOT - 1706a', 'eh\'res', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning perhaps to arch; a couch (properly, with a canopy):--bed(-stead), couch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>couch, divan, bed</OL>'),
(6211, 'X[', 'from (06244)', '`ash', 'TWOT - 1715a,1617,2931', 'awsh', 'Noun', 'from «06244»; a moth:--moth. See also «05906».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>moth<LI>herbage, grass</OL>'),
(6212, 'bX[', 'from an unused root meaning to glisten (or be green)', '`eseb', 'TWOT - 1707a', 'eh\'seb', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to glisten (or be green); grass (or any tender shoot):--grass, herb.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>herb, herbage, grass, green plants</OL>'),
(6213, 'hX[', 'a primitive root', '`asah', 'TWOT - 1708,1709', 'aw-saw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to do or make, in the broadest sense and widest application (as follows):--accomplish, advance, appoint, apt, be at, become, bear, bestow, bring forth, bruise, be busy, × certainly, have the charge of, commit, deal (with), deck, + displease, do, (ready) dress(-ed), (put in) execute(-ion), exercise, fashion, + feast, (fight-)ing man, + finish, fit, fly, follow, fulfill, furnish, gather, get, go about, govern, grant, great, + hinder, hold ((a feast)), ×  indeed, + be industrious, + journey, keep, labour, maintain, make, be meet, observe, be occupied, offer, + officer, pare, bring (come) to pass, perform, pracise, prepare, procure, provide, put, requite, × sacrifice, serve, set, shew, × sin, spend, × surely, take, × thoroughly, trim, × very, + vex, be (warr-)ior, work(-man), yield, use.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to do, fashion, accomplish, make<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to do, work, make, produce 1a</OL><LI>to do 1a<LI>to work 1a<LI>to deal (with) 1a<LI>to act, act with effect, effect<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to make 1a</OL><LI>to make 1a<LI>to produce 1a<LI>to prepare 1a<LI>to make (an offering) 1a<LI>to attend to, put in order 1a<LI>to observe, celebrate 1a<LI>to acquire (property) 1a<LI>to appoint, ordain, institute 1a<LI>to bring about 1a<LI>to use 1a<LI>to spend, pass<LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be done<LI>to be made<LI>to be produced<LI>to be offered<LI>to be observed<LI>to be used</OL><LI>(Pual) to be made</OL><LI>(Piel) to press, squeeze</OL>'),
(6214, 'lahX[', 'from (06213) and (0410)', '`Asah\'el', 'None', 'as-aw-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06213» and «0410»; God has made; Asahel, the name of four Israelites:--Asahel.', 'Asahel = \"God-made\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nephew of David, son of David\'s sister Zeruiah, and brother of Joab and Abishai; swift of foot he was killed by Abner when he pursued him in battle and caught him<LI>a Levite in the reign of king Jehoshaphat of Judah who went through the kingdom giving instruction in the law<LI>a Levite in the reign of king Hezekiah of Judah in charge of the tithes and dedicated things in the temple<LI>a priest, father of Jonathan, in the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(6215, 'wX[', 'apparently a form of the pass. part. of (06213) in the original sense of handling', '`Esav', 'None', 'ay-sawv\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'apparently a form of the passive participle of «06213» in the original sense of handling; rough (i.e. sensibly felt); Esav, a son of Isaac, including his posterity:--Esau.', 'Esau = \"hairy\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>eldest son of Isaac and Rebecca and twin brother of Jacob; sold the birthright for food when he was hungry and the divine blessing went to Jacob; progenitor of the Arab peoples</OL>'),
(6216, 'qwX[', 'from (06231)', '`ashowq', 'TWOT - 1713c', 'aw-shoke\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06231»; oppressive (as noun, a tyrant):--oppressor.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>oppressor, extortioner</OL>'),
(6217, 'qwX[', 'passive participle of (06231)', '`ashuwq', 'TWOT - 1713d', 'aw-shook\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or mashuq {aw-shook\'}; passive participle of «06231»; used in plural masculine as abstractly, tyranny:--oppressed(-ion). (Doubtful.)', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>oppression, extortion</OL>'),
(6218, 'rwX[', 'from (06235)', '`asowr', 'TWOT - 1711d', 'aw-sore\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or masor {aw-sore\'}; from «06235»; ten; by abbrev. ten strings, and so a decachord:--(instrument of) ten (strings, -th).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ten, decade<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>ten, tenth<LI>ten-stringed, harp</OL></OL>'),
(6219, 'twX[', 'from (06245)', '`ashowth', 'TWOT - 1716b', 'aw-shoth\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06245»; shining, i.e. polished:--bright.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>smooth, shiny</OL>'),
(6220, 'twX[', 'for (06219)', '`Ashvath', 'None', 'ash-vawth\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'for «06219»; bright; Ashvath, an Israelite:--Ashvath.', 'Ashvath = \"sleek\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the sons of Japhlet of the tribe of Asher</OL>'),
(6221, 'layX[', 'from (06213) and (0410)', '`Asiy\'el,', 'None', 'as-ee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06213» and «0410»; made of God; Asiel, an Israelite:--Asiel.', 'Asiel = \"made by God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Simeonite and ancestor of Jehu</OL>'),
(6222, 'hyX[', 'from (06213) and (03050)', '`Asayah', 'None', 'aw-saw-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06213» and «03050»; Jah has made; Asajah, the name of three or four Israelites:--Asaiah.', 'Asaiah = \"made by Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a prince of the tribe of Simeon in the time of king Hezekiah of Judah<LI>a servant of king Josiah of Judah<LI>a Merarite Levite, chief of his family, in the time of David</OL>'),
(6223, 'ryX[', 'from (06238)', '`ashiyr', 'TWOT - 1714b', 'aw-sheer\'', '', 'from «06238»; rich, whether literal or figurative (noble):--rich (man).', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rich, wealthy n<LI>the rich, the wealthy, rich man</OL>'),
(6224, 'yryX[', 'from (06235)', '`asiyriy', 'TWOT - 1711f', 'as-ee-ree\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06235»; tenth; by abbreviation, tenth month or (feminine) part:--tenth (part).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ordinal number<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a tenth</OL></OL>'),
(6225, '!X[', 'a primitive root', '`ashan', 'TWOT - 1712', 'aw-shan\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to smoke, whether literal or figurative:--be angry (be on a) smoke.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to smoke, be angry, be wroth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to smoke<LI>to fume, be wroth, be furious</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6226, '!X[', 'from (06225)', '`ashen', 'TWOT - 1712b', 'aw-shane\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06225»; smoky:--smoking.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>smoking</OL>'),
(6227, '!X[', 'from (06225)', '`ashan', 'TWOT - 1712a', 'aw-shawn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06225»; smoke, literally or figuratively (vapor, dust, anger):--smoke(-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>smoke<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>smoke<LI>in metaphor, simile<LI>smoke (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(6228, '!X[', 'the same as (06227)', '`Ashan', 'None', 'aw-shawn\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «06227»; Ashan, a place in Palestine:--Ashan.', 'Ashan = \"smoke\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in the lowland of Judah later mentioned as belonging to Simeon</OL>'),
(6229, 'qX[', 'a primitive root (identical with (06231))', '`asaq', 'TWOT - 1710', 'aw-sak', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «06231»); to press upon, i.e. quarrel; --strive with.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hithpael) to strive, contend, quarrel</OL>'),
(6230, 'qX[', 'from (06229)', '`eseq', 'None', 'ay\'sek', 'Noun', 'from «06229»; strife:--Esek.', 'Esek = \"contention\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a well which the herdsmen of Isaac dug in the valley of Gerar</OL>'),
(6231, 'qX[', 'a primitive root (comp. (06229))', '`ashaq', 'TWOT - 1713', 'aw-shak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (compare «06229»); to press upon, i.e. oppress, defraud, violate, overflow:--get deceitfully, deceive, defraud, drink up, (use) oppress((-ion)), -or), do violence (wrong).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to press upon, oppress, violate, defraud, do violence, get deceitfully, wrong, extort<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to oppress, wrong, extort<LI>to oppress</OL><LI>(Pual) to be exploited, be crushed</OL></OL>'),
(6232, 'qX[', 'from (06231)', '`Esheq', 'None', 'ay-shek\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06231»; oppression; Eshek, an Israelite:--Eshek.', 'Eshek = \"oppressor\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, late descendant of Saul</OL>'),
(6233, 'qX[', 'from (06231)', '`osheq', 'TWOT - 1713a', 'o\'-shek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06231»; injury, fraud, (subjectively) distress, (concretely) unjust gain:--cruelly, extortion, oppression, thing (deceitfully gotten).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>oppression, extortion, injury<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>oppression<LI>extortion<LI>gain by extortion</OL></OL>'),
(6234, 'hqX[', 'from (06233)', '`oshqah', 'TWOT - 1713b', 'osh-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «06233»; anguish:--oppressed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>oppression, abuse, distress</OL>'),
(6235, 'rX[', 'from (06237)', '`eser', 'TWOT - 1711a', 'eh\'ser', 'Noun', 'masculine of term aasarah {as-aw-raw\'}; from «06237»; ten (as an accumulation to the extent of the digits):--ten, (fif-, seven-)teen.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ten<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>ten<LI>with other numbers</OL></OL>'),
(6236, 'rX[', 'corresponding to (06235)', '`asar', 'TWOT - 2932', '', 'Noun', '(Aramaic) masculine aasrah (Aramaic). {as-raw\'}; corresponding to «06235»; ten:--ten, + twelve.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ten</OL>'),
(6237, 'rX[', 'a primitive root (ident. with (06238))', '`asar', 'TWOT - 1711c', 'aw-sar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (ident. with «06238»); to accumulate; but used only as denominative from «06235»; to tithe, i.e. to take or give a tenth:--X surely, give (take) the tenth, (have, take) tithe(-ing, -s), × truly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tithe, take the tenth part of, give a tithe, take a tithe<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to tithe<LI>(Piel) to give a tithe<LI>(Hiphil) to take a tithe</OL></OL>'),
(6238, 'rX[', 'a primitive root', '`ashar', 'TWOT - 1714', 'aw-shar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to accumulate; chiefly (specifically) to grow (causatively, make) rich:--be(-come, en-, make, make self, wax) rich, make (1 Kings 22:48 marg). See «06240».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or become rich or wealthy, enrich, pretend to be rich<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be or become rich<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make rich<LI>to gain riches</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to enrich oneself, pretend to be rich</OL></OL>'),
(6239, 'rX[', 'from (06238)', '`osher', 'TWOT - 1714a', 'o\'-sher', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06238»; wealth:--X far (richer), riches.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wealth, riches</OL>'),
(6240, 'rX[', 'from (06235)', '`asar', 'TWOT - 1711b', 'aw-sawr\'', 'Noun', 'for «06235»; ten (only in combination), i.e. -teen; also (ordinal) -teenth:--(eigh-, fif-, four-, nine-, seven-, six-,  thir-)teen(-th), + eleven(-th), + sixscore thousand, + twelve(-th).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ten, -teen (in combination with other numbers)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used only in combination to make the numbers 11-19</OL></OL>'),
(6241, '!wrXX[', 'from (06235)', '`issarown', 'TWOT - 1711h', 'is-saw-rone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or oissaron {is-saw-rone\'}; from «06235»; (fractional) a tenth part:--tenth deal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>tenth part, tithe</OL>'),
(6242, '~yrX[', 'from (06235)', '`esriym', 'TWOT - 1711e', 'es-reem\'', 'Noun', 'from «06235»; twenty; also (ordinal) twentieth:--(six-)score, twenty(-ieth).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>twenty, twentieth</OL>'),
