(6248, 'twtX[', 'from (06245)', '`ashtuwth', 'TWOT - 1717a', 'ash-tooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06245»; cogitation:--thought.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thought, idea</OL>'),
(6249, 'ytX[', 'apparently masc. pl. construction of (06247) in the sense of an afterthought (used only in connection with (06240) in lieu of (259)) eleven or (ordinal) eleventh', '`ashtey', 'TWOT - 1717c', 'ash-tay\'', 'Noun', 'apparently masculine plural construction of «06247» in the sense of an afterthought (used only in connection with «06240» in lieu of «0259») eleven or (ordinal) eleventh:--+ eleven(-th).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one, eleven, eleventh<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>one as combined with ten (06240)</OL></OL>'),
(6250, 'hntX[', 'from (06245)', '`eshtonah', 'TWOT - 1717b', 'esh-to-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06245»; thinking:--thought.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thought</OL>'),
(6251, 'hrtX[', 'probably from (06238)', '`ashtrah', 'TWOT - 1718a', 'ash-ter-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'probably from «06238»; increase:--flock.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ewe, flock, increase, young</OL>'),
(6252, 'twrtX[', 'pl. of (06251)', '`Ashtarowth', 'TWOT - 1718b', 'ash-taw-roth\'', '', 'or bAshtaroth {ash-taw-roth\'}; plural of «06251»; Ashtaroth, the name of a Sidonian deity, and of a place East of the Jordan:--Asharoth, Astaroth. See also «01045», «06253», «06255».', 'Ashtaroth or Astaroth = \"star\" n pr f deity<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>false goddesses in the Canaanite religion, usually related to fertility cult n pr loc<LI>a city in Bashan east of the Jordan given to Manasseh<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>same as 06255</OL></OL>'),
(6253, 'trtX[', 'probably for (06251)', '`Ashtoreth', 'TWOT - 1718', 'ash-to\'reth', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'probably for «06251»; Ashtoreth, the Phoenician goddess of love (and increase):--Ashtoreth.', 'Ashtoreth = \"star\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the principal female deity of the Phoenicians worshipped in war and fertility<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Ishtar\' of Assyria and \'Astarte\' by the Greeks and Romans</OL></OL>'),
(6254, 'ytrtX[', 'from (06252)', '`Ashtrathiy', 'None', 'ash-ter-aw-thee\'', 'Adjective', 'patrial from «06252»; an Ashterathite or inhabitant of Ashtaroth:--Ashterathite.', 'Ashterathite = see Astaroth \"star\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of the city of Ashtaroth</OL>'),
(6255, '~ynrq trtX[', 'from (06252) and the dual of (07161)', '`Ashtroth', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06252» and the dual of «07161»; Ashtaroth of (the) double horns (a symbol of the deity); Ashteroth-Karnaim, a place East of the Jordan:--Ashtoreth Karnaim.', 'Ashtoreth-karnaim = \"Ashtoreth of the two horns or peaks\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in Bashan east of the Jordan given to Manasseh<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>same as 06252</OL></OL>'),
(6256, 't[', 'from (05703)', '`eth', 'TWOT - 1650b', 'ayth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05703»; time, especially (adverb with preposition) now, when, etc.:--+ after, (al-)ways, × certain, + continually, + evening, long, (due) season, so (long) as, (even-, evening-, noon-)tide, ((meal-)), what) time, when.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>time<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>time (of an event)<LI>time (usual)<LI>experiences, fortunes<LI>occurrence, occasion</OL></OL>'),
(6257, 'dt[', 'a primitive root', '`athad', 'TWOT - 1719', 'aw-thad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to prepare:--make fit, be ready to become.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be ready, make ready, prepare<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to make ready<LI>(Hithpael) to be prepared</OL></OL>'),
(6258, 'htt[', 'from (06256)', '`attah', 'TWOT - 1650c', 'at-taw\'', 'Adverb', 'from «06256»; at this time, whether adverb, conjunction or expletive:--henceforth, now, straightway, this time, whereas.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>now<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>now<LI>in phrases</OL></OL>'),
(6259, 'dwt[', 'pass. part. of (06257)', '`athuwd', 'TWOT - 1719a', 'aw-thood\'', 'Adjective', 'passive participle of «06257»; prepared:--ready.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ready, prepared</OL>'),
(6260, 'dwtt[', 'from (06257)', '`attuwd', 'TWOT - 1719b', 'at-tood\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or sattud {at-tood\'}; from «06257»; prepared, i.e. full grown; spoken only (in plural) of he-goats, or (figuratively) leaders of the people:--chief one, (he) goat, ram.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ram, he-goat, chief one</OL>'),
(6261, 'ytt[', 'from (06256)', '`ittiy', 'TWOT - 1650d', 'it-tee\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06256»; timely:--fit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>timely, ready</OL>'),
(6262, 'ytt[', 'for (06261)', '`Attay', 'None', 'at-tah\'ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'for «06261»; Attai, the name of three Israelites:--Attai.', 'Attai = \"opportune\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Judaite, grandson of Sheshan the Jerahmeelite by daughter Ahlai whom he gave in marriage to Jarha, his Egyptian slave; his grandson Zabad was one of David\'s mighty warriors<LI>one of the lion-faced warriors of Gad, captains of the host, who joined David in the wilderness<LI>the 2nd son of king Rehoboam of Judah by Maachah, the daughter of Absalom</OL>'),
(6263, 'dyt[', 'corresponding to (06264)', '`athiyd', 'TWOT - 2934', 'ath-eed\'', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06264»; prepared:--ready.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ready, prepared</OL>'),
(6264, 'dyt[', 'from (06257)', '`athiyd', 'TWOT - 1719a', 'aw-theed\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06257»; prepared; by implication, skilful; feminine plural the future; also treasure:--things that shall come, ready, treasures.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ready, prepared<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>ready<LI>ready, skilled<LI>prepared, impending<LI>prepared, stored up, treasure</OL></OL>'),
(6265, 'hyt[', 'from (05790) and (03050)', '`Athayah', 'None', 'ath-aw-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05790» and «03050»; Jah has helped; Athajah, an Israelite:--Athaiah.', 'Athaiah = \"Jehovah has helped\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Judah through Perez; dwelt at Jerusalem after the return from exile in Babylon</OL>'),
(6266, 'qyt[', 'from (06275)', '`athiyq', 'TWOT - 1721c', 'aw-theek\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06275»; properly, antique, i.e. venerable or splendid:--durable.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>eminent, surpassing, choice, splendid<LI>(TWOT) durable</OL>'),
(6267, 'qytt', 'from (06275)', 'attiyq', 'TWOT - 1721d', 'at-teek\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06275»; removed, i.e. weaned; also antique:--ancient, drawn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>removed, weaned, old, ancient, taken away<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>removed, weaned<LI>old, ancient</OL></OL>'),
(6268, 'qytt[', 'corresponding to (06267)', '`attiyq', 'TWOT - 2935', 'at-teek\'', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06267»; venerable:--ancient.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ancient, advanced, aged, old, taken away</OL>'),
(6269, '$t[', 'from an unused root meaning to sojourn', '`Athak', 'None', 'ath-awk\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from an unused root meaning to sojourn; lodging; Athak, a place in Palestine:--Athach.', 'Athach = \"lodging place\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Judah</OL>'),
(6270, 'ylt[', 'from an unused root meaning to compress', '`Athlay', 'None', 'ath-lah\'ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to compress; constringent; Athlai, an Israelite:--Athlai.', 'Athlai = \"whom Jehovah afflicts\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the sons of Bebai and one who put away his foreign wife in the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(6271, 'hylt[', 'from the same as (06270) and (03050)', '`Athalyah', 'None', 'ath-al-yaw\'', '', 'or mAthalyahuw {ath-al-yaw\'-hoo}; from the same as «06270» and «03050»; Jah has constrained; Athaljah, the name of an Israelitess and two Israelites:--Athaliah.', 'Athaliah = \"afflicted of the Lord\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Jeroham of the tribe of Benjamin<LI>father of Jeshaiah of the sons of Elam who was one of the heads of a family who returned with Ezra from exile n pr f<LI>the daughter of Ahab and Jezebel and the wife of king Jehoram of Judah; killer of all the members of the royal family of Judah with the exception of one baby named Joash who was hidden by the high priest Jehoiada until 6 years had passed and Jehoiada led the revolution to put him on the throne, overthrowing Athaliah and putting her to death</OL>'),
(6272, '~t[', 'a primitive root', '`atham', 'TWOT - 1720', 'aw-tham', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; probably to glow, i.e. (figuratively) be desolated:--be darkened.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Niphal) to be burned up, be scorched<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(6273, 'ynnt[', 'from an unused root meaning to force', '`Otnniy', 'None', 'oth-nee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to force; forcible; Othni, an Israelite:--Othni.', 'Othni = \"lion of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite, son of Shemaiah, the first-born of Obed-edom</OL>'),
(6274, 'laynt[', 'from the same as (06273) and (0410)', '`Othniy\'el', 'None', 'oth-nee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «06273» and «0410»; force of God; Othniel, an Israelite:--Othniel.', 'Othniel = \"lion of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Kenaz, younger brother of Caleb, and husband of Achsah the daughter of Caleb and his own niece; first judge of Israel, who after the death of Joshua, delivered the Israelites from the oppression of Chushanrishathaim</OL>'),
(6275, 'qt[', 'a primitive root', '`athaq', 'TWOT - 1721', 'aw-thak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to remove (intransitive or transitive) figuratively, to grow old; specifically, to transcribe:--copy out, leave off, become (wax) old, remove.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to move, proceed, advance, move on, become old, be removed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to move<LI>to advance (in years), grow old and weak</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to move forward, proceed, move on<LI>to remove<LI>to transcribe</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6276, 'qt[', 'from (06275)', '`atheq', 'TWOT - 1721b', 'aw-thake\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06275»; antique, i.e. valued:--durable.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>handed forward, advanced, enduring, durable, valuable, eminent, surpassing</OL>'),
(6277, 'qt[', 'from (06275) in the sense of license', '`athaq', 'TWOT - 1721a', 'aw-thawk\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06275» in the sense of license; impudent:--arrogancy, grievous (hard) things, stiff.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>forward, bold, arrogant<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of speech</OL></OL>'),
(6278, '!ycq t[', 'from (06256) and (07011)', '`Eth', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06256» and «07011»; time of a judge; Eth-Katsin, a place in Palestine:--Ittah-kazin (by including directive enclitic).', 'Ittah-kazin = \"time of the judge\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the landmarks of the boundary of Zebulun; site unknown</OL>'),
(6279, 'rt[', 'a primitive root [rather denominative from (06281)]', '`athar', 'TWOT - 1722', 'aw-thar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (rather denominative from «06281»); to burn incense in worship, i.e. intercede (reciprocally, listen to prayer):--intreat, (make) pray(-er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pray, entreat, supplicate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to pray, entreat<LI>(Niphal) to be supplicated, be entreated<LI>(Hiphil) to make supplication, plead</OL></OL>'),
(6280, 'rt[', 'a primitive root', '`athar', 'TWOT - 1723', 'aw-thar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) abundant:--deceitful, multiply.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be abundant<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be plentiful<LI>(Hiphil) to multiply, become abundant</OL></OL>'),
(6281, 'rt[', 'from (06280)', '`Ether', 'None', 'eh\'ther', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06280»; abundance; Ether, a place in Palestine:--Ether.', 'Ether = \"abundant\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in the lowlands of Judah allotted to Simeon</OL>'),
(6282, 'rt[', 'from (06280)', '`athar', 'TWOT - 1722a,1724a', 'aw-thawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06280»; incense (as increasing to a volume of smoke); hence (from «06279») a worshipper:--suppliant, thick.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>suppliant, worshipper<LI>odour, incense (odoriferous smoke)</OL>'),
(6283, 'trt[', 'from (06280)', '`athereth', 'TWOT - 1723a', 'ath-eh\'-reth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06280»; copiousness:--abundance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>abundance, excess, copiousness</OL>'),
(6284, 'hap', 'a primitive root', 'pa\'ah', 'TWOT - 1725', 'paw-aw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to puff, i.e. blow away:--scatter into corners.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cleave in pieces, break into pieces, shatter<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil) to cleave in pieces, dash to pieces</OL></OL>'),
(6285, 'hap', 'from (06311)', 'pe\'ah', 'TWOT - 1725a', 'pay-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «06311»; properly, mouth in a figurative sense, i.e. direction, region, extremity:--corner, end, quarter, side.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>corner, edge, side, quarter, extremity<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>corner<LI>side</OL></OL>'),
(6286, 'rap', 'a primitive root', 'pa\'ar', 'TWOT - 1726,1727', 'paw-ar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to gleam, i.e. (causatively) embellish; figuratively, to boast; also to explain (i.e. make clear) oneself; denominative from «06288», to shake a tree:--beautify, boast self, go over the boughs, glorify (self), glory, vaunt self.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to glorify, beautify, adorn<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to glorify, beautify<LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to glorify oneself<LI>to get glory to oneself, be glorified</OL></OL><LI>(Piel) to go over the boughs</OL>'),
(6287, 'rap', 'from (06286)', 'p\'er', 'TWOT - 1726a', 'peh-ayr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06286»; an embellishment, i.e. fancy head-dress:--beauty, bonnet, goodly, ornament, tire.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head-dress, ornament, turban</OL>'),
(6288, 'hrap', 'from (06286)', 'p\'orah', 'TWOT - 1727a', 'peh-o-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or pora\'h {po-raw\'}; or pu\'rah {poo-raw\'}; from «06286»; properly, ornamentation, i.e. (plural) foliage (including the limbs) as bright green:--bough, branch, sprig.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bough, branch, shoot</OL>'),
(6289, 'rwrap', 'from (06286)', 'pa\'ruwr', 'TWOT - 1727b', 'paw-roor\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06286»; properly, illuminated, i.e. a glow; as noun, a flush (of anxiety):--blackness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>glow, heat<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(6290, '!rap', 'from (06286)', 'Pa\'ran', 'TWOT - 1728', 'paw-rawn\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06286»; ornamental; Paran, a desert of Arabia:--Paran.', 'Paran = \"place of caverns\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wilderness area bounded on the north by Palestine, on the west by the wilderness of Etham, on the south by the desert of Sinai, and on the east by the valley of Arabah; the exodus was through this area and probably all 18 stops were in this area</OL>'),
(6291, 'gp', 'from an unused root meaning to be torpid, i.e. crude', 'pag', 'TWOT - 1729a', 'pag', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to be torpid, i.e. crude; an unripe fig:--green fig.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>green fig, early fig</OL>'),
(6292, 'lwggp', 'from an unused root meaning to stink', 'pigguwl', 'TWOT - 1730a', 'pig-gool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or piggul {pig-gool\'}; from an unused root meaning to stink; properly, fetid, i.e. (figuratively) unclean (ceremonially):--abominable(-tion, thing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>foul thing, refuse<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>unclean sacrificial flesh (only use)</OL></OL>'),
(6293, '[gp', 'a primitive root', 'paga`', 'TWOT - 1731', 'paw-gah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to impinge, by accident or violence, or (figuratively) by importunity:--come (betwixt), cause to entreat, fall (upon), make intercession, intercessor, intreat, lay, light (upon), meet (together), pray, reach, run.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to encounter, meet, reach, entreat, make intercession<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to meet, light upon, join<LI>to meet (of kindness)<LI>to encounter, fall upon (of hostility)<LI>to encounter, entreat (of request)<LI>to strike, touch (of boundary)</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to light upon<LI>to cause to entreat<LI>to make entreaty, interpose<LI>to make attack<LI>to reach the mark</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6294, '[gp', 'from (06293)', 'pega`', 'TWOT - 1731a', 'peh\'-gah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06293»; impact (casual):--chance, occurent.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>occurrence, happening, chance</OL>'),
(6295, 'lay[gp', 'from (06294) and (0410)', 'Pag`iy\'el', 'None', 'pag-ee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06294» and «0410»; accident of God; Pagiel, an Israelite:--Pagiel.', 'Pagiel = \"event of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Ocran and chief of the tribe of Asher at the time of the exodus</OL>'),
(6296, 'rgp', 'a primitive root', 'pagar', 'TWOT - 1732', 'paw-gar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to relax, i.e. become exhausted:--be faint.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to be exhausted, be faint</OL>'),
(6297, 'rgp', 'from (06296)', 'peger', 'TWOT - 1732a', 'peh\'gher', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06296»; a carcase (as limp), whether of man or beast; figuratively, an idolatrous image:--carcase, corpse, dead body.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>corpse, carcass, monument, stela<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>corpse (of man)<LI>carcass (of animals)</OL></OL>'),
(6298, 'Xgp', 'a primitive root', 'pagash', 'TWOT - 1733', 'paw-gash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to come in contact with, whether by accident or violence; figuratively, to concur:--meet (with, together).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to meet, join, encounter<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to meet, encounter<LI>(Niphal) to meet together, meet each other<LI>(Piel) to meet, encounter</OL></OL>'),
(6299, 'hdp', 'a primitive root', 'padah', 'TWOT - 1734', 'paw-daw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to sever, i.e. ransom; gener. to release, preserve:--X at all, deliver, × by any means, ransom, (that are to be, let be) redeem(-ed), rescue, × surely.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to ransom, redeem, rescue, deliver<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to ransom<LI>(Niphal) to be ransomed<LI>(Hiphil) to allow one to be ransomed<LI>(Hophal) redeemed</OL></OL>'),
(6300, 'lahdp', 'from (06299) and (0410)', 'Pdah\'el', 'None', 'ped-ah-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06299» and «0410»; God has ransomed; Pedahel, an Israelite:--Pedahel.', 'Pedahel = \"ransomed by God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Ammihud and prince of the tribe of Naphtali</OL>'),
(6301, 'rwchdp', 'from (06299) and (06697)', 'Pdahtsuwr', 'None', 'ped-aw-tsoor\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06299» and «06697»; a rock (i.e. God) has ransomed; Pedahtsur, an Israelite:--Pedahzur.', 'Pedahzur = \"the Rock has ransomed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Gamaliel who was the chief of the tribe of Manasseh at the time of the exodus</OL>'),
(6302, 'ywdp', 'pass. part. of ((06299)) ransomed (and so occurring under 06299)', 'paduwy', 'TWOT - 1734a', 'paw-doo\'ee', 'Noun Masculine', 'passive participle of «06299». ransomed (and so occurring under «06299»); as abstractly (in plural masculine) a ransom:--(that are) to be (that were) redeemed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ransom</OL>'),
(6303, '!wdp', 'from (06299)', 'Padown', 'None', 'paw-done\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06299»; ransom; Padon, one of the Nethinim. -- Padon.', 'Padon = \"ransom\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an head or ancestor of a family of temple slaves who returned with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(6304, 'twdp', 'from (06929)', 'pduwth', 'TWOT - 1734b', 'ped-ooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or pduth {ped-ooth\'}; from «06929»; distinction; also deliverance:--division, redeem, redemption.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ransom</OL>'),
(6305, 'hydp', 'from (06299) and (03050)', 'Pdayah', 'None', 'ped-aw-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Pdayahuw {ped-aw-yaw\'-hoo}; from «06299» and «03050»; Jah has ransomed; Pedajah, the name of six Israelites:--Pedaiah.', 'Pedaiah = \"Jehovah has ransomed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Zebudah, the wife of king Josiah and the mother of king Jehoiakim both of Judah<LI>father of Zerubbabel and brother of Shealtiel who is usually called the father of Zerubbabel probably because of a lack of an heir from Shealtiel who was in the direct line of succession</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(6306, '~wydp', 'from (06299)', 'pidyowm', 'TWOT - 1734c', 'pid-yome\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or pidyom {pid-yome\'}; also pidyown {pid-yone\'}; or pidyon {pid-yone\'}; from «06299»; a ransom; --ransom, that were redeemed, redemption.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ransom, redemption</OL>'),
(6307, '!ddp', 'from an unused root meaning to extend', 'Paddan', 'TWOT - 1735', 'pad-dawn\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from an unused root meaning to extend; a plateau; or Paddan pAram {pad-dan\' ar-awm\'}; from the same and «0758»; the table-land of Aram; Paddan or Paddan-Aram, a region of Syria:--Padan, Padan-aram.', 'Padan or Padan-aram = \"field\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a plain or tableland in northern Mesopotamia in Aram, a region of Syria</OL>'),
(6308, '[dp', 'a primitive root', 'pada`', 'TWOT - 1736', 'paw-dah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to retrieve:--deliver.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to deliver<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning uncertain</OL></OL>'),
(6309, 'rdp', 'from an unused root meaning to be greasy', 'peder', 'TWOT - 1737', 'peh\'der', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to be greasy; suet:--fat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fat, suet</OL>'),
(6310, 'hp', 'from (06284)', 'peh', 'TWOT - 1738', 'peh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06284»; the mouth (as the means of blowing), whether literal or figurative (particularly speech); specifically edge, portion or side; adverbially (with preposition) according to:--accord(-ing as, -ing to), after, appointment, assent, collar, command(-ment), × eat, edge, end, entry, + file, hole, × in, mind, mouth, part, portion, × (should) say(-ing), sentence, skirt, sound, speech, × spoken, talk, tenor, × to, + two-edged, wish, word.', 'peh<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mouth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>mouth (of man)<LI>mouth (as organ of speech)<LI>mouth (of animals)<LI>mouth, opening, orifice (of a well, river, etc)<LI>extremity, end pim</OL><LI>a weight equal to one third of a shekel, occurs only in 1 Sa. 13:21</OL>'),
(6311, 'hp', 'probably from a primitive inseparable particle \"p\" (of demonstrative force) and (1931)', 'poh', 'TWOT - 1739', 'po', 'Adverb', 'or «0po6» (Job 38:11) {po}; or pow {po}; probably from a primitive inseparable particle \"p\" (of demonstrative force) and «01931»; this place (French ici), i.e. here or hence:--here, hither, the one (other, this, that) side.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>here, from here, hither<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>here<LI>hither</OL></OL>'),
(6312, 'hawp', 'from (06284)', 'Puw\'ah', 'None', 'poo-aw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Puvvah {poov-vaw\'}; from «06284»; a blast; Puah or Puvvah, the name of two Israelites:--Phuvah, Pua, Puah.', 'Puah or Pua or Phuvah = \"splendid\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Issachar<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Pua\' and \'Phuvah\'</OL><LI>man of Issachar, father of Tola, the judge of Israel after Abimelech</OL>'),
(6313, 'gwp', 'a primitive root', 'puwg', 'TWOT - 1740', 'poog', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be sluggish:--cease, be feeble, faint, be slacked.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to grow numb, be feeble, be benumbed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be feeble<LI>(Niphal) to be benumbed</OL></OL>'),
(6314, 'hgwp', 'from (06313)', 'puwgah', 'TWOT - 1740b', 'poo-gaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06313»; intermission:--rest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>benumbing, cessation, rest, relief</OL>'),
(6315, 'xwp', 'a primitive root', 'puwach', 'TWOT - 1741', 'poo\'akh', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to puff, i.e. blow with the breath or air; hence, to fan (as a breeze), to utter, to kindle (a fire), to scoff:--blow (upon), break, puff, bring into a snare, speak, utter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to breathe, blow<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to breathe<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to exhale or breathe<LI>to puff, snort<LI>to excite, inflame<LI>to puff, pant for it<LI>to breathe out, utter<LI>to blow, blast</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6316, 'twp', 'of foreign origin', 'Puwt', 'None', 'poot', 'Proper Name', 'of foreign origin; Put, a son of Ham, also the name of his descendants or their region, and of a Persian tribe:--Phut, Put.', 'Phut or Put = \"a bow\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a nation and people of northern Africa; probably Libyans</OL>'),
(6317, 'laytwp', 'from an unused root (probably meaning to disparage) and (0410)', 'Puwtiy\'el', 'None', 'poo-tee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root (probably meaning to disparage) and «0410»; contempt of God; Putiel, an Israelite:--Putiel.', 'Putiel = \"afflicted of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of the wife of Eleazar, the son of Aaron</OL>'),
(6318, 'rpytwp', 'of Egyptian derivation', 'Powtiyphar', 'None', 'po-tee-far\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of Egyptian derivation: Potiphar, an Egyptian:--Potiphar.', 'Potiphar = \"belonging to the sun\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an officer of Pharaoh, chief of the executioners, and the master to whom Joseph was sold as a slave</OL>'),
(6319, '[rp ytwp', 'of Egyptian derivation', 'Powtiy', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of Egyptian derivation; Poti-Phera, an Egyptian:--Poti-pherah.', 'Poti-pherah = \"he whom the Ra gave\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Egyptian, priest of On, father of Asenath, the wife whom Pharaoh gave to Joseph</OL>'),
(6320, '$wp', 'from an unused root meaning to paint', 'puwk', 'TWOT - 1742', 'pook', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to paint; dye (specifically, stibium for the eyes):--fair colours, glistering, paint(-ed) (-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>antimony, stibium, black paint<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>eye cosmetic</OL></OL>'),
(6321, 'lwp', 'from an unused root meaning to be thick', 'powl', 'TWOT - 1743', 'pole', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to be thick; a bean (as plump):--beans.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>beans</OL>'),
(6322, 'lwp', 'of foreign origin', 'Puwl', 'None', 'pool', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign origin; Pul, the name of an Assyrian king and of an Ethiopian tribe:--Pul.', 'Pul = \"distinguishing\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the Babylonian name for Tiglath-pileser III, king of Assyria</OL>'),
(6323, '!wp', 'a primitive root meaning to turn, i.e. be perplexed', 'puwn', 'TWOT - 1744', 'poon', 'Verb', 'a primitive root meaning to turn, i.e. be perplexed:--be distracted.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be perplexed, be distracted<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(6324, 'ynwp', 'patronymically from an unused name meaning a turn', 'Puwniy', 'None', 'poo-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from an unused name meaning a turn; a Punite (collectively) or descendants of an unknown Pun:--Punites.', 'Punites = see Puah \"scattered\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Puah, the son of Issachar</OL>'),
(6325, '!nwp', 'from (06323)', 'Puwnon', 'None', 'poo-none\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06323»; perplexity; Punon, a place in the Desert:--Punon.', 'Punon = \"darkness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a station of Israel in their wilderness wanderings</OL>'),
(6326, 'h[wp', 'from an unused root meaning to glitter', 'Puw`ah', 'None', 'poo-aw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning to glitter; brilliancy; Puah, an Israelitess:--Puah.', 'Puah = \"splendid\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 2 midwives of the Hebrews ordered by Pharaoh to kill all the male children born to Israel; time of Moses</OL>'),
(6327, '#wp', 'a primitive root', 'puwts', 'TWOT - 1745,1746,1800', 'poots', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to dash in pieces, literally or figuratively (especially to disperse):--break (dash, shake) in (to) pieces, cast (abroad), disperse (selves), drive, retire, scatter (abroad), spread abroad.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to scatter, be dispersed, be scattered<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be dispersed, be scattered<LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be scattered<LI>to be spread abroad</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to scatter<LI>Hithpael) scatter</OL><LI>(Qal) to flow, overflow<LI>to break<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Polel) to shatter<LI>(Pilpel) to dash to pieces</OL></OL>'),
(6328, 'qwp', 'a primitive root', 'puwq', 'TWOT - 1747', 'pook', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to waver:--stumble, move.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to reel, totter, stumble<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to reel<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to totter, wobble<LI>to cause tottering</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6329, 'qwp', 'a primitive root [identical with (06328) through the idea of dropping out', 'puwq', 'TWOT - 1748', 'pook', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «06328» through the idea of dropping out; compare «05312»); to issue, i.e. furnish; causatively, to secure; figuratively, to succeed:--afford, draw out, further, get, obtain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bring out, furnish, promote, go out, issue<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to produce, furnish<LI>to bring out, elicit, obtain, cause to come out from<LI>to promote<LI>to cause to go out to</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6330, 'hqwp', 'from (06328)', 'puwqah', 'TWOT - 1747a', 'poo-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06328»; a stumbling-block:--grief.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>tottering, staggering, stumbling<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of qualm of conscience (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(6331, 'rwp', 'a primitive root', 'puwr', 'TWOT - 1750', 'poor', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to crush:--break, bring to nought, ×  utterly take.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to break, crush</OL>'),
(6332, 'rwp', 'from (06331)', 'Puwr', 'TWOT - 1749', 'poor', 'Noun Masculine', 'also (plural) Puwriym {poo-reem\'}; or Puriym  {poo-reem\'}; from «06331»; a lot (as by means of a broken piece):--Pur, Purim.', 'Pur or Purim = \"lot\" or \"piece\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lot<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a special feast among the post-exilic Jews, to celebrate their deliverance from Haman\'s destruction through queen Esther\'s heroic actions</OL></OL>'),
(6333, 'hrwp', 'from (06331)', 'puwrah', 'TWOT - 1750a', 'poo-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06331»; a wine-press (as crushing the grapes):--winepress.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>winepress</OL>'),
(6334, 'atrwp', 'of Persian origin', 'Powratha\'', 'None', 'po-raw-thaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of Persian origin; Poratha, a son of Haman:--Poratha.', 'Poratha = \"fruitfulness\" or \"frustration\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the ten sons of Haman, the enemy of Mordecai and Esther</OL>'),
(6335, 'Xwp', 'a primitive root', 'puwsh', 'TWOT - 1751,1752', 'poosh', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to spread; figuratively, act proudly:--grow up, be grown fat, spread selves, be scattered.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to spring about<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to frisk, act proudly (fig.)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be scattered, be spread</OL>'),
(6336, 'ytwp', 'patronymically from an unused name meaning a hinge', 'Puwthiy', 'None', 'poo-thee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from an unused name meaning a hinge; a Puthite (collectively) or descendants of an unknown Puth:--Puhites (as if from «06312»).', 'Puhites = \"openess\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a family of Judah</OL>'),
(6337, 'zp', 'from (06338)', 'paz', 'TWOT - 1753a', 'pawz', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06338»; pure (gold); hence, gold itself (as refined):--fine (pure) gold.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>refined or pure gold</OL>'),
(6338, 'zzp', 'a primitive root', 'pazaz', 'TWOT - 1753', 'paw-zaz\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to refine (gold):--best (gold).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to refine, be refined<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hophal) to be refined</OL></OL>'),
(6339, 'zzp', 'a primitive root [identical with (06338)]', 'pazaz', 'TWOT - 1754', 'paw-zaz\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «06338»); to solidify (as if by refining); also to spring (as if separating the limbs):--leap, be made strong.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bound, be agile, be supple<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be nimble<LI>(Piel) to leap, show agility</OL></OL>'),
(6340, 'rzp', 'a primitive root', 'pazar', 'TWOT - 1755', 'paw-zar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to scatter, whether in enmity or bounty:--disperse, scatter (abroad).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to scatter, disperse<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to scatter<LI>scattered (participle)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be scattered<LI>(Piel) to scatter<LI>(Pual) to be scattered</OL></OL>'),
(6341, 'xp', 'from (06351)', 'pach', 'TWOT - 1759a,1759b', 'pakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06351»; a (metallic) sheet (as pounded thin); also a spring net (as spread out like a lamina):--gin, (thin) plate, snare.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bird trap, trap, snare<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>bird trap (literal)<LI>of calamities, plots, source or agent of calamity (fig.)</OL><LI>plate (of metal)</OL>'),
(6342, 'dxp', 'a primitive root', 'pachad', 'TWOT - 1756', 'paw-kkad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be startled (by a sudden alarm); hence, to fear in general:--be afraid, stand in awe, (be in) fear, make to shake.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fear, tremble, revere, dread, be in awe or dread<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be in dread<LI>to be in awe</OL><LI>(Piel) to be in great dread<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to dread</OL></OL>'),
(6343, 'dxp', 'from (06342)', 'pachad', 'TWOT - 1756a', 'pakh\'-ad', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06342»; a (sudden) alarm (properly, the object feared, by implication, the feeling):--dread(-ful), fear, (thing) great (fear, -ly feared), terror.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>terror, dread<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>dread<LI>object of dread</OL></OL>'),
(6344, 'dxp', 'the same as (06343)', 'pachad', 'TWOT - 1756c', 'pakh\'-ad', 'Noun Masculine', 'the same as «06343»; a testicle (as a cause of shame akin to fear):--stone.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thigh</OL>'),
