(6367, 'tryxh p', 'from (06310) and the fem. pl. of a noun (from the same root as (02356)), with the article interpolated', 'Pi', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06310» and the feminine plural of a noun (from the same root as «02356»), with the article interpolated; mouth of the gorges; Pi-ha-Chiroth, a place in Egypt:  --Pi-hahiroth. (In Numbers 14:19 without Pi-.)', 'Pi-hahiroth = \"place where sedge grows\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 3rd encampment of the Israelites after leaving Goshen in Egypt and the last one before crossing the Red Sea</OL>'),
(6368, 'xyp', 'from (06315)', 'piyach', 'TWOT - 1741a', 'pee\'-akh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06315»; a powder (as easily puffed away), i.e. ashes or dust:--ashes.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>soot, ashes</OL>'),
