(6519, 'hzrp', 'from the same as (06518)', 'prazah', 'TWOT - 1812a', 'per-aw-zaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «06518»; an open country:--(unwalled) town (without walls), unwalled village.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>open region, hamlet, unwalled village, open country</OL>'),
(6520, '!wzrp', 'from the same as (06518)', 'prazown', 'TWOT - 1812b', 'per-aw-zone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «06518»; magistracy, i.e. leadership (also concretely, chieftains):--village.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rural population, rustics, rural people, people of unwalled villages<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
