(6524, 'xrp', 'a primitive root', 'parach', 'TWOT - 1813,1814,1815', 'paw-rakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to break forth as a bud, i.e. bloom; generally, to spread; specifically, to fly (as extending the wings); figuratively, to flourish:--X abroad, × abundantly, blossom, break forth (out), bud, flourish, make fly, grow, spread, spring (up).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bud, sprout, shoot, bloom<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to bud, sprout, send out shoots, blossom<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to bud or sprout<LI>to show buds or sprouts</OL></OL><LI>(Qal) to break out (of leprosy)<LI>(Qal) to fly</OL>'),
