(6552, '!wt[rp', 'from (06546)', 'Pir`athown', 'None', 'pir-aw-thone\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06546»; chieftaincy; Pirathon, a place in Palestine:--Pirathon.', 'Pirathon = \"princely\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Ephraim in the mount of the Amalekite<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps modern \'Ferata\' located 1.5 miles (2.5 km) south from Jaffa on the road to Nablus</OL></OL>'),
(6553, '', 'patrial from (06552)', 'Pir`athowniy', '&nbsp;', 'pir-aw-tho-nee\'', 'Pirathonite = see Pirathon \"princely\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Pirathon</OL>', 'or Pirathoniy {pir-aw-tho-nee\'}; patrial from «06552»; a Pirathonite or inhabitant of Pirathon:--Pirathonite.', ''),
(6554, 'rprp', 'probably from (06565) in the sense of rushing', 'Parpar', 'None', 'par-par\'', 'Proper Name', 'probably from «06565» in the sense of rushing; rapid; Parpar, a river of Syria:--Pharpar.', 'Pharpar = \"swift\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a stream in the district of Damascus identified with the modern \'Awaj\'; rises on the southeast slopes of Mount Hermon and flows into the southernmost lake of Damascus</OL>'),
(6555, '#rp', 'a primitive root', 'parats', 'TWOT - 1826', 'paw-rats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to break out (in many applications, direct and indirect, literal and figurative):--X abroad, (make a) breach, break (away, down, -er, forth, in, up), burst out, come (spread) abroad, compel, disperse, grow, increase, open, press, scatter, urge.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to break through or down or over, burst, breach<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to break or burst out (from womb or enclosure)<LI>to break through or down, make a breach in<LI>to break into<LI>to break open<LI>to break up, break in pieces<LI>to break out (violently) upon<LI>to break over (limits), increase<LI>to use violence<LI>to burst open 1a</OL></OL><LI>to spread, distribute<OL TYPE=\"b\"><LI>(Niphal) to be broken through<LI>(Pual) to be broken down<LI>(Hithpael) to break away</OL></OL>'),
(6556, '#rp', 'from (06555)', 'perets', 'TWOT - 1826a', 'peh\'-rets', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06555»; a break (literally or figuratively):--breach, breaking forth (in), × forth, gap.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>breach, gap, bursting forth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>bursting forth, outburst<LI>breach<LI>broken wall<LI>outburst (fig. of God\'s wrath)</OL></OL>'),
(6557, '#rp', 'the same as (06556)', 'Perets', 'None', 'peh\'-rets', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «06556»; Perets, the name of two Israelites:--Perez, Pharez.', 'Perez or Pharez = \"breach\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>twin son with Zarah of Judah by Tamar and ancestor of two families of Judah, the Hezronites and Hamulites; from the Hezronites came the royal line of David and Christ</OL>'),
(6558, 'ycrp', 'patronymically from (06557)', 'Partsiy', 'None', 'par-tsee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from «06557»; a Partsite (collectively) or descendants of Perets:--Pharzites.', 'Pharzites = see Pharez \"breach\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the descendants of Pharez, the son of Judah by Tamar</OL>'),
(6559, '~ycrp', 'pl. of (06556)', 'pratsiym', 'None', 'per-aw-tseem\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'plural of «06556»; breaks; Peratsim, a mountain in Palestine:--Perazim.', 'Perazim = \"breaches\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a mountain in Palestine<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>possibly the same as \'Baal-perazim\' which was the scene of a victory of David over the Philistines located in the valley of Rephaim, south of Jerusalem, on the road to Bethlehem</OL></OL>'),
(6560, 'azz[ #rp', 'from (06556) and (05798)', 'Perets', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06556» and «05798»; break of Uzza; Perets-Uzza, a place in Palestine:--Perez-uzza.', 'Perez-uzza = \"breach of Uzza\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the place where Uzzah was slain by God for touching the Ark; located close to Jerusalem</OL>'),
(6561, 'qrp', 'a primitive root', 'paraq', 'TWOT - 1828', 'paw-rak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to break off or crunch; figuratively, to deliver:--break (off), deliver, redeem, rend (in pieces), tear in pieces.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tear apart or away, tear off, break away<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to tear away, snatch, rescue<LI>(Piel) to tear off<LI>(Hithpael) to tear off from oneself, be broken off, be broken in pieces</OL></OL>'),
