(6578, 'trp', 'from an unused root meaning to break forth', 'Prath', 'None', 'per-awth\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to break forth; rushing; Perath (i.e. Euphrates), a river of the East:--Euphrates.', 'Euphrates = \"fruitfulness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the largest and longest river of western Asia; rises from two chief sources in the Armenian mountains and flows into the Persian Gulf</OL>'),
(6579, '~trp', 'of Persian origin', 'partam', 'TWOT - 1839', 'par-tam\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Persian origin; a grandee:--(most) noble, prince.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>noble, nobleman</OL>'),
(6580, 'Xp', 'probably from an unused root meaning to disintegrate', 'pash', 'TWOT - 1843', 'pash', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from an unused root meaning to disintegrate; stupidity (as a result of grossness or of degeneracy):--extremity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>folly, weakness, stupidity</OL>'),
(6581, 'hXp', 'a primitive root', 'pasah', 'TWOT - 1840', 'paw-saw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to spread:--spread.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to spread</OL>'),
(6582, 'xXp', 'a primitive root', 'pashach', 'TWOT - 1844', 'paw-shakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to tear in pieces:--pull in pieces.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tear, rip, tear in pieces<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to tear in pieces</OL></OL>'),
(6583, 'rwxXp', 'probably from (06582)', 'Pashchuwr', 'None', 'pash-khoor\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «06582»; liberation; Pashchur, the name of four Israelites:--Pashur.', 'Pashur = \"freedom\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest, son of Malchiah and one of the chief princes in the reign of king Zedekiah of Judah<LI>a priest, son of Immer, chief governor of the temple, and the one who struck and then put the prophet Jeremiah into the stocks in the reign of king Jehoiakim of Judah<LI>son of Malchijah, father of Zechariah, and ancestor of Adaiah who did the work of the temple in the time of Nehemiah. Probably same as 1<LI>father of Gedaliah; probably the same as 1<LI>head of a family of returned exiles</OL>'),
(6584, 'tXp', 'a primitive root', 'pashat', 'TWOT - 1845', 'paw-shat\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to spread out (i.e. deploy in hostile array); by analogy, to strip (i.e. unclothe, plunder, flay, etc.):--fall upon, flay, invade, make an invasion, pull off, put off, make a road, run upon, rush, set, spoil, spread selves (abroad), strip (off, self).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strip, invade, strip off, make a dash, raid, spread out<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strip off, put off<LI>to put off (one\'s shelter), make a dash</OL><LI>(Piel) to strip<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strip of<LI>to strip off<LI>to flay</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to strip oneself of</OL></OL>'),
(6585, '[Xp', 'a primitive root', 'pasa`', 'TWOT - 1841', 'paw-sah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to stride (from spreading the legs), i.e. rush upon:--go.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to step, march, step forward</OL>'),
(6586, '[Xp', 'a primitive root [identical with (06585) through the idea of expansion]', 'pasha`', 'TWOT - 1846', 'paw-shah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «06585» through the idea of expansion); to break away (from just authority), i.e. trespass, apostatize, quarrel:--offend, rebel, revolt, transgress(-ion, -or).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rebel, transgress, revolt<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rebel, revolt<LI>to transgress</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be rebelled against</OL></OL>'),
(6587, '[Xp', 'from (06585)', 'pesa`', 'TWOT - 1841a', 'peh\'-sah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06585»; a stride:--step.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>step</OL>'),
(6588, '[Xp', 'from (06586)', 'pesha`', 'TWOT - 1846a', 'peh\'-shah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06586»; a revolt (national, moral or religious):--rebellion, sin, transgression, trespass.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>transgression, rebellion<OL TYPE=\"a\"><OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>transgression (against individuals)<LI>transgression (nation against nation)<LI>transgression (against God) 1a</OL><LI>in general 1a<LI>as recognised by sinner 1a<LI>as God deals with it 1a<LI>as God forgives<OL TYPE=\"4\"><LI>guilt of transgression<LI>punishment for transgression<LI>offering for transgression</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6589, 'qXp', 'a primitive root', 'pasaq', 'TWOT - 1842', 'paw-sak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to dispart (the feet or lips), i.e. become licentious:--open (wide).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to part, open wide<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to open wide<LI>to be talkative (of the mouth)</OL><LI>(Piel) to open wide</OL></OL>'),
(6590, 'rXp', 'corresponding to (06622)', 'pshar', 'TWOT - 2949', 'pesh-ar\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06622»; to interpret:--make (interpretations), interpreting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to interpret<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to interpret<LI>(Pael) to interpret</OL></OL>'),
(6591, 'rXp', 'from (06590)', 'pshar', 'TWOT - 2949a', 'pesh-ar\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «06590»; an interpretation:--interpretation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>interpretation (of dream)</OL>'),
(6592, 'rXp', 'corresponding to (06591)', 'pesher', 'TWOT - 1847', 'pay\'-sher', 'Noun Masculine', 'corresponding to «06591»:--interpretation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>interpretation, solution</OL>'),
(6593, 'htXp', 'from the same as (06580) as in the sense of comminuting', 'pishteh', 'TWOT - 1848', 'pish-teh\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «06580» as in the sense of comminuting; linen (i.e. the thread, as carded):--flax, linen.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flax, linen<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>fibre used as material for garments</OL></OL>'),
(6594, 'htXp', 'from (06593)', 'pishtah', 'TWOT - 1849', 'pish-taw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «06593»; flax; by implication, a wick:--flax, tow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flax<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>flax (of the plant)<LI>as wick for lamp</OL></OL>'),
(6595, 'tp', 'from (06626)', 'path', 'TWOT - 1862a', 'path', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06626»; a bit:--meat, morsel, piece.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fragment, bit, morsel (of bread), piece</OL>'),
(6596, 'tp', 'from an unused root meaning to open', 'poth', 'TWOT - 1850', 'pohth', 'Noun Feminine', 'or pothah (Ezek. 13:19) {po-thaw\'}; from an unused root meaning to open; a hole, i.e. hinge or the female pudenda:--hinge, secret participle', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sockets, hinges, secret parts (meaning dubious)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>sockets<LI>secret parts</OL></OL>'),
(6597, '~watp', 'from (06621)', 'pith\'owm', 'TWOT - 1859a', 'pith-ome\'', '', 'or pith.om {pith-ome\'}; from «06621»; instantly:--straightway, sudden(-ly).', 'adv<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>suddenly, surprisingly subst<LI>suddenness</OL>'),
(6598, 'gbtp', 'of Persian origin', 'pathbag', 'TWOT - 1851', 'pathbag\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Persian origin; a dainty:--portion (provision) of meat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>portion of food for king, delicacies</OL>'),
(6599, '~gtp', 'of Persian origin', 'pithgam', 'TWOT - 1852', 'pith-gawm\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Persian origin; a (judicial) sentence:--decree, sentence.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>edict, decree</OL>'),
(6600, '~gtp', 'corresponding to (06599)', 'pithgam', 'TWOT - 2950', 'pith-gawm\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06599»; a word, answer, letter or decree:--answer, letter, matter, word.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>command, work, affair, decree<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>word, report<LI>decree</OL></OL>'),
(6601, 'htp', 'a primitive root', 'pathah', 'TWOT - 1853', 'paw-thaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to open, i.e. be (causatively, make) roomy; usually figuratively (in a mental or moral sense) to be (causatively, make) simple or (in a sinister way) delude:--allure, deceive, enlarge, entice, flatter, persuade, silly (one).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be spacious, be open, be wide<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be spacious or open or wide<LI>(Hiphil) to make spacious, make open</OL><LI>to be simple, entice, deceive, persuade<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be open-minded, be simple, be naive<LI>to be enticed, be deceived</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be deceived, be gullible<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to persuade, seduce<LI>to deceive</OL><LI>(Pual)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be persuaded<LI>to be deceived</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6602, 'lawtp', 'from (06601) and (0410)', 'Pthuw\'el', 'None', 'peth-oo-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06601» and «0410»; enlarged of God; Pethuel, an Israelite:--Pethuel.', 'Pethuel = \"vision of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of the prophet Joel</OL>'),
(6603, 'xwttp', 'pass part of (06605)', 'pittuwach', 'TWOT - 1855a', 'pit-too\'-akh', 'Noun Masculine', 'or pittuach {pit-too\'-akh; passive participle of «06605»; sculpture (in low or high relief or even intaglio):--carved (work) (are, en-)grave(-ing, -n).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>engraving, carving</OL>'),
(6604, 'rwtp', 'of foreign origin', 'Pthowr', 'None', 'peth-ore\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'of foreign origin; Pethor, a place in Mesopotamia:--Pethor.', 'Pethor = \"soothsayer\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town of Mesopotamia and the home of Balaam; located on a river; site unknown</OL>'),
(6605, 'xtp', 'a primitive root', 'pathach', 'TWOT - 1854,1855', 'paw-thakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to open wide (literally or figuratively); specifically, to loosen, begin, plough, carve:--appear, break forth, draw (out), let go free, (en-)grave(-n), loose (self), (be, be set) open(-ing), put off, ungird, unstop, have vent.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to open<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to open<LI>(Niphal) to be opened, be let loose, be thrown open<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to free<LI>to loosen<LI>to open, open oneself</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to loose oneself</OL><LI>to carve, engrave<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to engrave<LI>(Pual) to be engraved</OL></OL>'),
(6606, 'xtp', 'corresponding to (06605)', 'pthach', 'TWOT - 2951', 'peth-akh\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06605»; to open:--open.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to open<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'il) to open</OL></OL>'),
(6607, 'xtp', 'from (06605)', 'pethach', 'TWOT - 1854a', 'peh\'-thakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06605»; an opening (literally), i.e. door (gate) or entrance way:--door, entering (in), entrance (-ry), gate, opening, place.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>opening, doorway, entrance</OL>'),
(6608, 'xtp', 'from (06605)', 'pethach', 'TWOT - 1854b', 'pay\'-thakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06605»; opening (figuratively) i.e. disclosure:--entrance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>opening, unfolding, entrance, doorway</OL>'),
(6609, 'hhktp', 'from (06605)', 'pthikhah', 'TWOT - 1854d', 'peth-ee-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06605»; something opened, i.e. a drawn sword:--drawn sword.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>drawn sword, sword</OL>'),
(6610, '!wxtp', 'from (06605)', 'pithchown', 'TWOT - 1854c', 'pith-khone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06605»; opening (the act):--open(-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>opening</OL>'),
(6611, 'hyxtp', 'from (06605) and (03050)', 'Pthachyah', 'None', 'peth-akh-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06605» and «03050»; Jah has opened; Pethachjah, the name of four Israelites:--Pethakiah.', 'Pethahiah = \"freed by Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest, in charge of the 19th course, in the time of David<LI>a Levite and returning exile who had married a foreign wife; probably the same as 3<LI>a Levite who helped lead in the confession of the people in the time of Ezra; probably the same as 2<LI>son of Meshezabeel, descendant of Zerah the son of Judah; deputy of the king in all matters concerning the people</OL>'),
(6612, 'ytp', 'from (06601)', 'pthiy', 'TWOT - 1853a', 'peth-ee\'', '', 'or pethiy {peh\'-thee}; or pthaeiy {peth-aw-ee\'}; from «06601»; silly (i.e. seducible):--foolish, simple(-icity, one).', 'n f<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>simplicity, naivete adj<LI>simple, foolish, open-minded</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(6613, 'ytp', 'from a root corresponding to (06601)', 'pthay', 'TWOT - 2952', 'peth-ah\'-ee', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «06601»; open, i.e. (as noun) width:--breadth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>width, breadth</OL>'),
(6614, 'lygytp', 'of uncertain derivation', 'pthiygiyl', 'TWOT - 1856', 'peth-eeg-eel\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; probably a figured mantle for holidays:--stomacher.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rich or expensive robe</OL>'),
(6615, 'twytp', 'from (06612)', 'pthayuwth', 'TWOT - 1853a', 'peth-ah-yooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06612»; silliness (i.e. seducibility):--simple.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>simplicity, naivete</OL>'),
(6616, 'lytp', 'from (06617)', 'pathiyl', 'TWOT - 1857a', 'paw-theel\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06617»; twine:--bound, bracelet, lace, line, ribband, thread, wire.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cord, thread (twisted)</OL>'),
(6617, 'ltp', 'a primitive root', 'pathal', 'TWOT - 1857', 'paw-thal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to twine, i.e. (literally) to struggle or (figuratively) be (morally) tortuous:--(shew self) froward, shew self unsavoury, wrestle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to twist<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be twisted<LI>to wrestle</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to be twisted</OL></OL>'),
(6618, 'ltltp', 'from (06617)', 'pthaltol', 'TWOT - 1857b', 'peth-al-tole\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06617»; tortuous (i.e. crafty):--crooked.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>twisted, tortuous</OL>'),
(6619, '~tp', 'of Egyptian derivation', 'Pithom', 'None', 'pee-thome\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'of Egyptian derivation; Pithom, a place in Egypt:--Pithom.', 'Pithom = \"the city of justice\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the store-cities which the Pharaoh made the Israelites build</OL>'),
(6620, '!tp', 'from an unused root meaning to twist', 'pethen', 'TWOT - 1858a', 'peh\'-then', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to twist; an asp (from its contortions):--adder.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a snake, venomous serpent<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps the cobra, adder, or viper</OL></OL>'),
(6621, '[tp', 'from an unused root meaning to open (the eyes)', 'petha`', 'TWOT - 1859', 'peh\'-thah', '', 'from an unused root meaning to open (the eyes); a wink, i.e. moment (compare «06597») (used only (with or without preposition) adverbially, quickly or unexpectedly):--at an instant, suddenly, × very.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>suddenness, in an instant</OL>'),
(6622, 'rtp', 'a primitive root', 'pathar', 'TWOT - 1860', 'paw-thar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to open up, i.e. (figuratively) interpret (a dream):--interpret(-ation, -er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to interpret (dreams)</OL>'),
(6623, '!wrtp', 'from (06622)', 'pithrown', 'TWOT - 1860a', 'pith-rone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or pithron {pith-rone\'}; from «06622»; interpretation (of a dream):--interpretation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>interpretation</OL>'),
(6624, 'owrtp', 'of Egyptian derivation', 'Pathrowc', 'None', 'path-roce\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'of Egyptian derivation; Pathros, a part of Egypt:--Pathros.', 'Pathros = \"region of the south\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a part of Egypt and the home country of the Pathrusim people; probably located in upper Egypt</OL>'),
(6625, 'yortp', 'patrial from (06624)', 'Pathruciy', 'None', 'path-roo-see\'', 'Adjective', 'patrial from «06624»; a Pathrusite, or inhabitant of Pathros:--Pathrusim.', 'Pathrusim = see Pathros \"region of the south\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>inhabitants of Pathros</OL>'),
(6626, 'ttp', 'a primitive root', 'pathath', 'TWOT - 1862', 'paw-thath\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to open, i.e. break:--participle', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to break up, crumble<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to crumble</OL></OL>'),
(6627, 'hac', 'from (03318)', 'tsa\'ah', 'TWOT - 1884a', 'tsaw-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03318»; issue, i.e. (human) excrement:--that (which) cometh from (out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>filth, human excrement, excrement, faeces</OL>'),
(6628, 'lac', 'from an unused root meaning to be slender', 'tse\'el', 'TWOT - 1863', 'tseh\'-el', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to be slender; the lotus tree:--shady tree.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a kind of lotus<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a thorny lotus shrub</OL></OL>'),
(6629, '!ac', 'from an unused root meaning to migrate', 'tso\'n', 'TWOT - 1864a', 'tsone', 'Noun Feminine', 'or tsaown (Psalm 144:13) {tseh-one\'}; from an unused root meaning to migrate; a collective name for a flock (of sheep or goats); also figuratively (of men):--(small) cattle, flock (+ -s), lamb (+ -s), sheep((-cote, -fold, -shearer, -herds)).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>small cattle, sheep, sheep and goats, flock, flocks<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>small cattle (usually of sheep and goats)<LI>of multitude (simile)<LI>of multitude (metaphor)</OL></OL>'),
(6630, '!nac', 'from the same as (06629) used denominatively', 'Tsa\'anan', 'None', 'tsah-an-awn\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the same as «06629» used denominatively; sheep pasture; Zaanan, a place in Palestine:--Zaanan.', 'Zaanan = \"pointed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in the low country of Judah</OL>'),
(6631, 'acac', 'from (03318)', 'tse\'etsa\'', 'TWOT - 893b', 'tseh-ets-aw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03318»; issue, i.e. produce, children:--that which cometh forth (out), offspring.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>offspring, produce, issue<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>offspring (of men)<LI>produce (of earth)<LI>descendants (metaphorical)</OL></OL>'),
(6632, 'bc', 'from an unused root meaning to establish', 'tsab', 'TWOT - 1866a,1867a', 'tsawb', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to establish; a palanquin or canopy (as a fixture); also a species of lizard (probably as clinging fast):--covered, litter, tortoise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a carrying vehicle, litter, covered wagon<LI>an unclean lizard<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps a tortoise<LI>perhaps an extinct animal, exact meaning unknown</OL></OL>'),
(6633, 'abc', 'a primitive root', 'tsaba\'', 'TWOT - 1865', 'tsaw-baw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to mass (an army or servants):--assemble, fight, perform, muster, wait upon, war.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go forth, wage war, fight, serve<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wage war, fight, go forth to war<LI>to serve (at sacred tent)</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to cause to go forth, muster</OL></OL>'),
(6634, 'abc', 'corresponding to (06623) in the fig. sense of summoning one\'s wishes', 'tsba\'', 'TWOT - 2953', 'tseb-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06623» in the figurative sense of summoning one\'s wishes; to please:--will, would.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to desire, be inclined, be willing, be pleased<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to desire<LI>to be pleased<LI>to will (without hindrance) (of God)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6635, 'abc', 'from (06633)', 'tsaba\'', 'TWOT - 1865a,1865b', 'tsaw-baw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (feminine) tsbadah {tseb-aw-aw\'}; from «06633»; a mass of persons (or figuratively, things), especially reg. organized for war (an army); by implication, a campaign, literally or figuratively (specifically, hardship, worship):--appointed time, (+) army, (+) battle, company, host, service, soldiers, waiting upon, war(-fare).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that which goes forth, army, war, warfare, host<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>army, host<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>host (of organised army)<LI>host (of angels)<LI>of sun, moon, and stars<LI>of whole creation</OL><LI>war, warfare, service, go out to war<LI>service</OL></OL>'),
(6636, '~yabc', 'pl. of (06643)', 'Tsbo\'iym', 'None', 'tseb-o-eem\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or (more correctly) Tsbiyiym  {tseb-ee-yeem\'}; or Tsbiyim {tseb-ee-yeem\'}; plural of «06643»; gazelles; Tseboim or Tsebijim, a place in Palestine:--Zeboiim, Zeboim.', 'Zeboim or Zeboiim = \"gazelles\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 5 cities in the plain which included Sodom and Gomorrah</OL>'),
(6637, 'hbbc', 'act part of the same as (06632)', 'Tsobebah', 'None', 'tso-bay-baw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'feminine active participle of the same as «06632»; the canopier (with the article); Tsobebah, an Israelitess:--Zobebah.', 'Zobebah = \"the slow\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Coz of the tribe of Judah</OL>'),
(6638, 'hbc', 'a primitive root', 'tsabah', 'TWOT - 1868', 'tsaw-baw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to amass, i.e. grow turgid; specifically, to array an army against:--fight swell.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to swell, swell up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to swell (of adulteress\' belly)<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to swell (of adulteress\' belly)</OL></OL>'),
(6639, 'hbc', 'from (06638)', 'tsabeh', 'TWOT - 1868a', 'tsaw-beh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06638»; turgid:--swell.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>swelling, swollen</OL>'),
(6640, 'wbc', 'from (06634)', 'tsbuw', 'TWOT - 2953a', 'tseb-oo\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «06634»; properly, will; concretely, an affair (as a matter of determination):--purpose.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thing, anything, matter<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>apparently thing desired<LI>as a matter of determination</OL></OL>'),
(6641, '[wbc', 'pass part of the same as (06648)', 'tsabuwa`', 'TWOT - 1872b', 'tsaw-boo\'-ah', 'Adjective', 'passive participle of the same as «06648»; dyed (in stripes), i.e. the hyena:--speckled.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>coloured, variegated, speckled</OL>'),
(6642, 'tbc', 'a primitive root', 'tsabat', 'TWOT - 1871', 'tsaw-bat\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to grasp, i.e. hand out:--reach.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to reach, hold out</OL>'),
(6643, 'ybc', 'from (06638) in the sense of prominence', 'tsbiy', 'TWOT - 1869a,1870a', 'tseb-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06638» in the sense of prominence; splendor (as conspicuous); also a gazelle (as beautiful):--beautiful(-ty), glorious  (-ry), goodly, pleasant, roe(-buck).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>beauty, glory, honour<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>beauty, decoration<LI>honour</OL><LI>roebuck, gazelle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps an extinct animal, exact meaning unknown</OL></OL>'),
(6644, 'aybc', 'for (06645)', 'Tsibya\'', 'None', 'tsib-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'for «06645»; Tsibja, an Israelite:--Zibia.', 'Zibia = \"roe\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, son of Shaharaim by wife Hodesh</OL>'),
(6645, 'hybc', 'for (06646)', 'Tsibyah', 'None', 'tsib-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'for «06646»; Tsibjah, an Israelitess:--Zibiah.', 'Zibiah = \"roe\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a native of Beersheba, wife of king Ahaziah and mother of king Joash both of Judah</OL>'),
