(6654, 'dc', 'contr from an unused root meaning to sidle off', 'tsad', 'TWOT - 1876a', 'tsad', 'Noun Masculine', 'contr. from an unused root meaning to sidle off; a side; figuratively, an adversary:--(be-)side.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>side</OL>'),
(6655, 'dc', 'corresponding to (06654)', 'tsad', 'TWOT - 2955', 'tsad', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06654»; used adverbially (with preposition) at or upon the side of:--against, concerning.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>side<LI>(CLBL) beside</OL>'),
(6656, 'adc', 'from an unused root corresponding to (06658) in the sense of intentness', 'tsda\'', 'TWOT - 2956', 'tsed-aw\'', '', '(Aramaic) from an unused root corresponding to «06658» in the sense of intentness; a (sinister) design:--true.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>purpose adj (CLBL)<LI>true</OL>'),
(6657, 'ddc', 'from the same as (06654)', 'Tsdad', 'None', 'tsed-awd\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the same as «06654»; a siding; Tsedad, a place near Palestine:--Zedad.', 'Zedad = \"mountain side\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the landmarks on the northern border of Israel as promised by Moses and restated by Ezekiel</OL>'),
(6658, 'hdc', 'a primitive root', 'tsadah', 'TWOT - 1877,1878', 'tsaw-daw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to chase; by implication, to desolate:--destroy, hunt, lie in wait.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to lie in wait<LI>to lay waste<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be laid waste</OL></OL>'),
(6659, 'qwdc', 'from (06663)', 'Tsadowq', 'None', 'tsaw-doke\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06663»; just; Tsadok, the name of eight or nine Israelites:--Zadok.', 'Zadok = \"righteous\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the high priest, son of Ahitub of the house of Eleazar the son of Aaron, and 11th in descent from Aaron; joined David after Saul\'s death and supported him against Absalom and Adonijah; anointed Solomon as king<LI>a priest, son of Meraioth, father of Meshullam of the house of Ahitub; apparently a nephew of 1<LI>father of Jerusha, the wife of king Uzziah and mother of king Jotham of Judah<LI>son of Baana and repairer of the wall of Jerusalem in the time of Nehemiah<LI>son of Immer and repairer of the wall of Jerusalem in the time of Nehemiah<LI>a leader of the people in the time of Nehemiah<LI>a scribe appointed by Nehemiah as one of the treasurers over the storehouse<LI>a valiant warrior of the tribe of Benjamin who joined David at Hebron. Same as 1?</OL>'),
(6660, 'hydc', 'from (06658)', 'tsdiyah', 'TWOT - 1877a', 'tsed-ee-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06658»; design (compare «06656»):--lying in wait.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lying in wait, ambushing</OL>'),
(6661, '~yddc', 'pl. of (06654)', 'Tsiddiym', 'None', 'tsid-deem\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'plural of «06654»; sides; Tsiddim (with the article), a place in Palestine:--Ziddim.', 'Ziddim = \"the declivities\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a fortified town in the territory of Naphtali</OL>'),
(6662, 'qyddc', 'from (06663)', 'tsaddiyq', 'TWOT - 1879c', 'tsad-deek\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06663»; just:--just, lawful, righteous (man).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>just, lawful, righteous<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>just, righteous (in government)<LI>just, right (in one\'s cause)<LI>just, righteous (in conduct and character)<LI>righteous (as justified and vindicated by God)<LI>right, correct, lawful</OL></OL>'),
(6663, 'qdc', 'a primitive root', 'tsadaq', 'TWOT - 1879', 'tsaw-dak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) right (in a moral or forensic sense):--cleanse, clear self, (be, do) just(-ice, -ify, -ify self), (be turn to) righteous(-ness).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be just, be righteous<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to have a just cause, be in the right<LI>to be justified<LI>to be just (of God)<LI>to be just, be righteous (in conduct and character)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be put or made right, be justified<LI>(Piel) justify, make to appear righteous, make someone righteous<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to do or bring justice (in administering law)<LI>to declare righteous, justify<LI>to justify, vindicate the cause of, save<LI>to make righteous, turn to righteousness</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to justify oneself</OL></OL>'),
(6664, 'qdc', 'from (06663)', 'tsedeq', 'TWOT - 1879a', 'tseh\'-dek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06663»; the right (natural, moral or legal); also (abstractly) equity or (figuratively) prosperity:--X even, (X  that which is altogether) just(-ice), ((un-))right(-eous) (cause, -ly, - ness).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>justice, rightness, righteousness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>what is right or just or normal, rightness, justness (of weights and measures)<LI>righteousness (in government)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of judges, rulers, kings<LI>of law<LI>of Davidic king, Messiah<LI>of Jerusalem as seat of just government<LI>of God\'s attribute</OL><LI>righteousness, justice (in case or cause)<LI>rightness (in speech)<LI>righteousness (as ethically right)<LI>righteousness (as vindicated), justification (in controversy), deliverance, victory, prosperity<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of God as covenant-keeping in redemption<LI>in name of Messianic king<LI>of people enjoying salvation<LI>of Cyrus</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6665, 'hqdc', 'corresponding to (06666)', 'tsidqah', 'TWOT - 2957', 'tsid-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06666»; beneficence:-- righteousness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>right doing, doing right, righteousness</OL>'),
(6666, 'hqdc', 'from (06663)', 'tsdaqah', 'TWOT - 1879b', 'tsed-aw-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06663»; rightness (abstractly), subjectively (rectitude), objectively (justice), morally (virtue) or figuratively (prosperity):--justice, moderately, right(-eous) (act, -ly,  -ness).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>justice, righteousness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>righteousness (in government)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of judge, ruler, king<LI>of law<LI>of Davidic king Messiah</OL><LI>righteousness (of God\'s attribute)<LI>righteousness (in a case or cause)<LI>righteousness, truthfulness<LI>righteousness (as ethically right)<LI>righteousness (as vindicated), justification, salvation<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of God<LI>prosperity (of people)</OL><LI>righteous acts</OL></OL>'),
(6667, 'hyqdc', 'from (06664) and (03050)', 'Tsidqiyah', 'None', 'tsid-kee-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Tsidqiyahuw {tsid-kee-yaw\'-hoo}; from «06664» and «03050»; right of Jah; Tsidkijah, the name of six Israelites:--Zedekiah, Zidkijah.', 'Zedekiah = \"Jehovah is righteous\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the last king of Judah renamed from \'Mattaniah\' by Nebuchadnezzar; son of Josiah by wife Hamutal; placed on the throne by Nebuchadnezzar when he carried his nephew Jehoiakim in captivity<LI>false prophet at the court of king Ahab of the northern kingdom of Israel<LI>son of Maaseiah, a false prophet in Babylon<LI>son of Hananiah, one of the princes of Judah in the time of Jeremiah<LI>a priest who sealed the covenant with Nehemiah<LI>son of king Jehoiakim of Judah</OL>'),
(6668, 'bhc', 'a primitive root', 'tsahab', 'TWOT - 1880', 'tsaw-hab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to glitter, i.e. be golden in color:--X  fine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to gleam, shine<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hophal) to gleam</OL></OL>'),
(6669, 'bhc', 'from (06668)', 'tsahob', 'TWOT - 1880a', 'tsaw-obe\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06668»; golden in color:--yellow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gleaming, yellow (of hair)</OL>'),
(6670, 'lhc', 'a primitive root', 'tsahal', 'TWOT - 1881,1882', 'tsaw-hal\'', 'Verb', 'a prim root; to gleam, i.e. (figuratively) be cheerful; by transf. to sound clear (of various animal or human expressions):--bellow, cry aloud (out), lift up, neigh, rejoice, make to shine, shout.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to neigh, cry shrilly<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to neigh (of men as stallions - fig.)<LI>(Piel) to cry shrilly (in distress)</OL></OL><LI>(Hiphil) to make shining</OL>'),
(6671, 'rhc', 'a primitive root', 'tsahar', 'TWOT - 1883d', 'tsaw-har\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to glisten; used only as denominative from «03323», to press out oil:--make oil.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to press oil, press out oil, glisten</OL>'),
(6672, 'rhc', 'from (06671)', 'tsohar', 'TWOT - 1883a,1883b', 'tso\'-har', '', 'from «06671»; a light (i.e. window): dual double light, i.e. noon:--midday, noon(-day, -tide), window.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>noon, midday<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>noon (as specific time of day)<LI>noon (in simile as bright of happiness, blessing) n f</OL><LI>roof<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(6673, 'wc', 'from (06680)', 'tsav', 'TWOT - 1887c', 'tsav', 'Noun Masculine', 'or tsav {tsawv}; from «06680»; an injunction:--commandment, precept.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>command, ordinance, oracle (meaning dubious)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used in mocking mimicry of Isaiah\'s words and thus not a true divine command</OL></OL>'),
(6674, 'awc', 'from an unused root meaning to issue', 'tsow\'', 'TWOT - 1884', 'tso', '', 'or tsov {tso}; from an unused root meaning to issue; soiled (as if excrementitious):--filthy.', 'adj (BDB)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>filthy n m (CLBL)<LI>filth</OL>'),
(6675, 'hawc', 'from (06674)', 'tsow\'ah', 'TWOT - 1884b', 'tso-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or tsovah {tso-aw\'}: feminine of «06674»; excrement; generally, dirt; figuratively, pollution:--dung, filth(-iness). Marg. for «02716».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>filth, excrement</OL>'),
(6676, 'rawwc', 'corresponding to (06677)', 'tsavva\'r', 'TWOT - 2958', 'tsav-var\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06677»:--neck.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>neck</OL>'),
(6677, 'rawwc', 'intensively from (06696) in the sense of binding', 'tsavva\'r', 'TWOT - 1897a', 'tsav-vawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or tsavvar (Nehemiah 3:5) {tsav-vawr\'}; or tsavvaron (Song of Solomon 4:9) {tsav-vaw-rone\'}; or (feminine) tsavva.rah (Micah 2:3) {tsav-vaw-raw\'}; intensively from «06696» in the sense of binding; the back of the neck (as that on which burdens are bound):--neck.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>neck, back of neck<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>neck, back of neck (of man)<LI>neck (of animals)</OL></OL>'),
(6678, 'abwc', 'from an unused root meaning to station', 'Tsowba\'', 'None', 'tso-baw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Tsowbah {tso-baw\'}; or Tsobah {tso-baw\'}; from an unused root meaning to station; a station; Zoba or Zobah, a region of Syria:--Zoba, Zobah.', 'Zoba or Zobah = \"station\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the name of a portion of Syria which formed a separate kingdom in the times of Saul, David, and Solomon; located northeast of Damascus</OL>'),
(6679, 'dwc', 'a primitive root', 'tsuwd', 'TWOT - 1885', 'tsood', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to lie alongside (i.e. in wait); by implication, to catch an animal (figuratively, men); (denominative from «06718») to victual (for a journey):--chase, hunt, sore, take (provision).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hunt<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to hunt<LI>(Poel) to hunt, hunt eagerly or keenly<LI>(Hithpael) take provision</OL></OL>'),
(6680, 'hwc', 'a primitive root', 'tsavah', 'TWOT - 1887', 'tsaw-vaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; (intensively) to constitute, enjoin:--appoint, (for-)bid, (give a) charge, (give a, give in, send with) command(-er, -ment), send a messenger, put, (set) in order.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to command, charge, give orders, lay charge, give charge to, order<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lay charge upon<LI>to give charge to, give command to<LI>to give charge unto<LI>to give charge over, appoint<LI>to give charge, command<LI>to charge, command<LI>to charge, commission<LI>to command, appoint, ordain (of divine act)</OL><LI>(Pual) to be commanded</OL></OL>'),
(6681, 'xwc', 'a primitive root', 'tsavach', 'TWOT - 1888', 'tsaw-vakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to screech (exultingly):--shout.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to shout, cry aloud, cry out</OL>'),
(6682, 'hxwc', 'from (06681)', 'tsvachah', 'TWOT - 1888a', 'tsev-aw-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06681»; a screech (of anguish):  --cry(-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>outcry, shout</OL>'),
(6683, 'hlwc', 'from an unused root meaning to sink', 'tsuwlah', 'TWOT - 1889a', 'tsoo-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning to sink: an abyss (of the sea):--deep.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ocean-deep, deep, ocean depth</OL>'),
(6684, '~wc', 'a primitive root', 'tsuwm', 'TWOT - 1890', 'tsoom', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to cover over (the mouth), i.e. to fast:--X at all, fast.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to abstain from food, fast</OL>'),
(6685, '~wc', 'from (06684)', 'tsowm', 'TWOT - 1890a', 'tsome', 'Noun Masculine', 'or tsom {tsome}; from from «06684»; a fast:  --fast(-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fast, fasting</OL>'),
(6686, 'r[wc', 'from (06819)', 'Tsaw`ar', 'None', 'tsoo-awr\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06819»; small; Tsuar, an Israelite:--Zuar.', 'Zuar = \"littleness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Nethaneel, the chief of the tribe of Issachar at the time of the exodus and an assistant of Moses</OL>'),
(6687, '@wc', 'a primitive root', 'tsuwph', 'TWOT - 1892', 'tsoof', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to overflow:--(make to over-)flow, swim.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to flow, overflow, flood, float<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to flood<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to flow over<LI>to cause to float</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6688, '@wc', 'from (06687)', 'tsuwph', 'TWOT - 1892a', 'tsoof', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06687»; comb of honey (from dripping):--honeycomb.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>honeycomb</OL>'),
(6689, '@wc', 'from (06688)', 'Tsuwph', 'None', 'tsoof', '', 'or Tsowphay {tso-fah\'-ee}; or Tsiyph {tseef}; from «06688»; honey-comb; Tsuph or Tsophai or Tsiph, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine:--Zophai, Zuph.', 'n pr m Zuph or Zophai = \"honeycomb\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Kohathite Levite, ancestor of Elkanah and Samuel n pr loc<LI>a district northwest of Jerusalem where Saul encountered Samuel</OL>'),
(6690, 'xpwc', 'from an unused root meaning to expand, breadth', 'Tsowphach', 'None', 'tso-fakh\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to expand, breadth; Tsophach, an Israelite:--Zophah.', 'Zophah = \"a cruse\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Asherite, son of Helem and father of Suah, Harnepher, Shual, Beri, and Imrah</OL>'),
(6691, 'rpwc', 'from (06852)', 'Tsowphar', 'None', 'tso-far\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06852»; departing; Tsophar, a friend of Job:--Zophar.', 'Zophar = \"sparrow\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 3rd friend of Job</OL>'),
(6692, '#wc', 'a primitive root', 'tsuwts', 'TWOT - 1893,1894', 'tsoots', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to twinkle, i.e. glance; by analogy, to blossom (figuratively, flourish):--bloom, blossom, flourish, shew self.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to blossom, shine, sparkle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to flourish<LI>to shine, gleam</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to blossom, put forth blossoms, produce blossoms</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to gaze, peep, glance, make the eyes sparkle</OL>'),
(6693, 'qwc', 'a primitive root', 'tsuwq', 'TWOT - 1895', 'tsook', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to compress, i.e. (figuratively) oppress, distress:--constrain, distress, lie sore, (op-)press(-or), straiten.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to constrain, press, bring into straits, straiten, oppress</OL>'),
(6694, 'qwc', 'a primitive root [identical with (06693) through the idea of narrowness (of orifice)]', 'tsuwq', 'TWOT - 1896', 'tsook', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «06693» through the idea of narrowness (of orifice)); to pour out, i.e. (figuratively) smelt, utter:--be molten, pour.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to pour out, melt</OL>'),
(6695, 'qwc', 'from (06693)', 'tsowq', 'TWOT - 1895a,1895b', 'tsoke', '', 'or (feminine) tsuwqah {tsoo-kaw\'}; from «06693»; a strait, i.e. (figuratively) distress:--anguish, × troublous.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>constraint, distress, strait<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>distress, anguish (fig.) n f</OL><LI>pressure, distress</OL>'),
(6696, 'rwc', 'a primitive root', 'tsuwr', 'TWOT - 1898,1899,1900', 'tsoor', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to cramp, i.e. confine (in many applications, literally and figuratively, formative or hostile):--adversary, assault, beset, besiege, bind (up), cast, distress, fashion, fortify, inclose, lay siege, put up in bags.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bind, besiege, confine, cramp<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to confine, secure<LI>to shut in, beseige<LI>to shut up, enclose</OL></OL><LI>(Qal) to show hostility to, be an adversary, treat as foe<LI>(Qal) to form, fashion, delineate</OL>'),
(6697, 'rwc', 'from (06696)', 'tsuwr', 'TWOT - 1901a', 'tsoor', 'Noun Masculine', 'or tsur {tsoor}; from «06696»; properly, a cliff (or sharp rock, as compressed); generally, a rock or boulder; figuratively, a refuge; also an edge (as precipitous):--edge, × (mighty) God (one), rock, × sharp, stone, × strength, × strong. See also «01049».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rock, cliff<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>rocky wall, cliff<LI>rock (with flat surface)<LI>block of stone, boulder<LI>rock (specific)<LI>rock (of God)<LI>rock (of heathen gods) n pr dei<LI>Rock</OL></OL>'),
(6698, 'rwc', 'the same as (06697)', 'Tsuwr', 'None', 'tsoor', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «06697»; rock; Tsur, the name of a Midianite and of an Israelite:--Zur.', 'Zur = \"rock\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Cozbi and one of the 5 Midianite princes who were slain when Balaam fell<LI>son of Jehiel, the father or leader of Gibeon</OL>'),
(6699, 'hrwc', 'from (06697)', 'tsuwrah', 'TWOT - 1900a', 'tsoo-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «06697»; a rock (Job 28:10); also a form (as if pressed out):--form, rock.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>form, fashion, design</OL>'),
(6700, 'layrwc', 'from (06697) and (0410)', 'Tsuwriy\'el', 'None', 'tsoo-ree-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06697» and «0410»; rock of God; Tsuriel, an Israelite:--Zuriel.', 'Zuriel = \"my rock is God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Abihail and chief of the Merarite Levites at the time of the exodus</OL>'),
(6701, 'yddXyrwc', 'from (06697) and (07706)', 'Tsuwriyshadday', 'None', 'tsoo-ree-shad-dah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06697» and «07706»; rock of (the) Almighty; Tsurishaddai, an Israelite:--Zurishaddai.', 'Zurishaddai = \"my rock is almighty\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Shelumiel, the chief of the Simeonites at the time of the exodus</OL>'),
(6702, 'twc', 'a primitive root', 'tsuwth', 'TWOT - 899', 'tsooth', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to blaze:--burn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to kindle, burn, set on fire</OL>'),
(6703, 'xc', 'from (06705)', 'tsach', 'TWOT - 1903a', 'tsakh', 'Adjective', 'from «06705»; dazzling, i.e. sunny, bright, (figuratively) evident:--clear, dry, plainly, white.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dazzling, glowing, clear, bright</OL>'),
(6704, 'hxc', 'from an unused root meaning to glow', 'tsicheh', 'TWOT - 1902a', 'tsee-kheh\'', 'Adjective', 'from an unused root meaning to glow; parched:--dried up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>parched</OL>'),
(6705, 'xxc', 'a primitive root', 'tsachach', 'TWOT - 1903', 'tsaw-khakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to glare, i.e. be dazzling white:--be whiter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be dazzling, be aglow, glow</OL>'),
(6706, 'xyxc', 'from (06705)', 'tschiyach', 'TWOT - 1903b', 'tsekh-ee\'-akh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06705»; glaring, i.e. exposed to the bright sun:--higher place, top.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shining or glaring surface, glow</OL>'),
(6707, 'hxyxc', 'from (06706)', 'tschiychah', 'TWOT - 1903c', 'tsekh-ee-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «06706»; a parched region, i.e. the desert:--dry land.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>scorched land, parched, scorched</OL>'),
(6708, 'yxyxc', 'from (06706)', 'tschiychiy', 'TWOT - 1903b', 'tsekh-ee-khee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06706»; bare spot, i.e. in the glaring sun:--higher place.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shining or glaring surface, bare places</OL>'),
(6709, 'hnxc', 'from an unused root meaning to putrefy', 'tsachanah', 'TWOT - 1904a', 'tsakh-an-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning to putrefy; stench:--ill savour.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stench, foul odour</OL>'),
(6710, 'hxcxc', 'from (06705)', 'tsachtsachah', 'TWOT - 1903d', 'tsakh-tsaw-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06705»; a dry place, i.e. desert:--drought.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>scorched region, parched land</OL>'),
(6711, 'qxc', 'a primitive root', 'tsachaq', 'TWOT - 1905', 'tsaw-khak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to laugh outright (in merriment or scorn); by implication, to sport:--laugh, mock, play, make sport.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to laugh, mock, play<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to laugh<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to jest<LI>to sport, play, make sport, toy with, make a toy of</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6712, 'qxc', 'from (06711)', 'tschoq', 'TWOT - 1905a', 'tsekh-oke\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06711»; laughter (in pleasure or derision):--laugh(-ed to scorn).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>laughter, laughing stock</OL>'),
(6713, 'rxc', 'from an unused root meaning to dazzle', 'tsachar', 'TWOT - 1906a', 'tsakh\'-ar', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to dazzle; sheen, i.e. whiteness:--white.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>reddish-gray, tawny</OL>'),
(6714, 'rxc', 'from the same as (06713)', 'Tsochar', 'None', 'tso\'-khar', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «06713»; whiteness; Tsochar, the name of a Hittite and of an Israelite:--Zohar. Compare «03328».', 'Zohar = \"tawny\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Judaite, son of Ashur by wife Helah<LI>father of Ephron the Hittite<LI>one of the sons of Simeon; also \'Zerah\'</OL>'),
(6715, 'rxc', 'from the same as (06713)', 'tsachor', 'TWOT - 1906b', 'tsaw-khore\'', 'Adjective', 'from the same as «06713»; white:--white.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>tawny</OL>'),
(6716, 'yc', 'from (06680)', 'tsiy', 'TWOT - 1907', 'tsee', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06680»; a ship (as a fixture):--ship.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ship</OL>'),
(6717, 'abyc', 'from the same as (06678)', 'Tsiyba\'', 'None', 'tsee-baw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «06678»; station; Tsiba, an Israelite:--Ziba.', 'Ziba = \"statue\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a servant of Saul whom David made steward of Jonathan\'s son Mephibosheth</OL>'),
(6718, 'dyc', 'from a form of (06679) and meaning the same', 'tsayid', 'TWOT - 1885a,1886a', 'tsah\'-yid', 'Noun Masculine', 'from a form of «06679» and meaning the same; the chase; also game (thus taken); (generally) lunch (especially for a journey):--X catcheth, food, × hunter, (that which he took in) hunting, venison, victuals.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hunting, game<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>hunting<LI>game hunted</OL><LI>provision, food<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>provision, food, food-supply</OL></OL>'),
(6719, 'dyc', 'from the same as (06718)', 'tsayad', 'TWOT - 1885b', 'tsah\'-yawd', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «06718»; a huntsman:--hunter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hunter</OL>'),
(6720, 'hdyc', 'from (06718)', 'tseydah', 'TWOT - 1886b', 'tsay-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or tsedah {tsay-daw\'}; feminine of «06718»; food:--meat, provision, venison, victuals.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>provision, food</OL>'),
(6721, '!wdyc', 'from (06679) in the sense of catching fish', 'Tsiydown', 'None', 'tsee-done\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Tsiydon {tsee-done\'}; from «06679» in the sense of catching fish; fishery; Tsidon, the name of a son of Canaan, and of a place in Palestine:--Sidon, Zidon.', 'Sidon = \"hunting\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ancient Phoenician city, on Mediterranean coast north of Tyre</OL>'),
(6722, 'yndyc', 'from (06721)', 'Tsiydoniy', 'None', 'tsee-do-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'patrial from «06721»; a Tsidonian or inhabitant of Tsidon:--Sidonian, of Sidon, Zidonian.', 'Sidonians = see hunting \"hunting\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Sidon</OL>'),
(6723, 'hyc', 'from an unused root meaning to parch', 'tsiyah', 'TWOT - 1909a', 'tsee-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning to parch; aridity; concretely, a desert:--barren, drought, dry (land, place), solitary place, wilderness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dryness, drought, desert</OL>'),
(6724, '!wyc', 'from the same as (06723)', 'tsiyown', 'TWOT - 1909b', 'tsee-yone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «06723»; a desert:--dry place.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dryness, parched land or ground</OL>'),
(6725, '!wyc', 'from the same as (06723) in the sense of conspicuousness [compare (05329)]', 'tsiyuwn', 'TWOT - 1887a', 'tsee-yoon\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «06723» in the sense of conspicuousness (compare «05329»); a monumental or guiding pillar:--sign, title, waymark.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>signpost, monument, market</OL>'),
(6726, '!wyc', 'the same (regularly) as (06725)', 'Tsiyown', 'TWOT - 1910', 'tsee-yone\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same (regularly) as «06725»; Tsijon (as a permanent capital), a mountain of Jerusalem:--Zion.', 'Zion = \"parched place\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>another name for Jerusalem especially in the prophetic books</OL>'),
(6727, 'axyc', 'as if fem. of (06704)', 'Tsiycha\'', 'None', 'tsee-khaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Tsicha( {tsee-khaw\'}; as if feminine of «06704»; drought; Tsicha, the name of two Nethinim:--Ziha.', 'Ziha = \"parched\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ancestor of a family of temple slaves who returned from exile in Babylon with Zerubbabel<LI>a chief of the temple slaves in Ophel in the time of Nehemiah</OL>'),
(6728, 'yyc', 'from the same as (06723)', 'tsiyiy', 'TWOT - 1908', 'tsee-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «06723»; a desert-dweller, i.e. nomad or wild beast:--wild beast of the desert, that dwell in (inhabiting) the wilderness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a wild beast, desert-dweller, crier, yelper<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a specific wild beast but not certainly identified</OL></OL>'),
(6729, 'qnyc', 'from an unused root meaning to confine', 'tsiynoq', 'TWOT - 1941a', 'tsee-noke\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to confine; the pillory:--stocks.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pillory, stocks</OL>'),
(6730, 'r[yc', 'from (06819)', 'Tsiy`or', 'None', 'tsee-ore\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06819»; small; Tsior, a place in Palestine:--Zior.', 'Zior = \"smallness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in the mountains of Judah belonging to the same group as Hebron</OL>'),
(6731, '#yc', 'from (06692)', 'tsiyts', 'TWOT - 1911', 'tseets', 'Noun Masculine', 'or tsits {tseets}; from «06692»; properly, glistening, i.e. a burnished plate; also a flower (as bright-colored); a wing (as gleaming in the air):--blossom, flower, plate, wing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flower, bloom<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>flower, bloom<LI>shining thing (of gold plate on high priest\'s mitre) (metaph.)</OL><LI>feather, wing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(6732, '#yc', 'the same as (06731)', 'Tsiyts', 'None', 'tseets', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «06731»; bloom; Tsits, a place in Palestine:--Ziz.', 'Ziz = \"flower\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a pass going from the shores of the Dead Sea to the wilderness of Judah near Tekoa</OL>'),
(6733, 'hcyc', 'fem. of (06731)', 'tsiytsah', 'None', 'tsee-tsaw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'feminine of «06731»; a flower:--flower.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>blossom, flower</OL>'),
(6734, 'tcyc', 'from (06731)', 'tsiytsith', 'TWOT - 1912', 'tsee-tseeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «06731»; a floral or wing-like projection, i.e. a forelock of hair, a tassel:--fringe, lock.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fringe, tassel, lock</OL>'),
(6735, 'ryc', 'from (06696)', 'tsiyr', 'TWOT - 1913a,1914a,1914b', 'tseer', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06696»; a hinge (as pressed in turning); also a throe (as a phys. or mental pressure); also a herald or errand-doer (as constrained by the principal):--ambassador, hinge, messenger, pain, pang, sorrow. Compare «06736».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>envoy, messenger<LI>pivot of door, hinge<LI>pang, distress</OL>'),
(6736, 'ryc', 'the same as (06735)', 'tsiyr', 'TWOT - 1900b', 'tseer', 'Noun Masculine', 'the same as «06735»; a form (of beauty; as if pressed out, i.e. carved); hence, an (idolatrous) image:--beauty, idol.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>image, idol</OL>'),
(6737, 'ryc', 'a denominative from (06735) in the sense of ambassador', 'tsayar', 'None', 'tsaw-yar\'', 'Verb', 'a denominative from «06735» in the sense of ambassador; to make an errand, i.e. betake oneself:--make as if...had been ambassador.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(BDB) (Hithpael) to supply oneself with provisions, take as one\'s provision<LI>(CLBL) to act as envoy</OL>'),
(6738, 'lc', 'from (06751)', 'tsel', 'TWOT - 1921a', 'tsale', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06751»; shade, whether literal or figurative:--defence, shade(-ow).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shadow, shade<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>shadow (on dial)<LI>shadow, shade (as protection)<LI>shadow (symbolic of transitoriness of life)</OL></OL>'),
(6739, 'alc', 'probably corresponding to (06760) in the sense of bowing', 'tsla\'', 'TWOT - 2959', 'tsel-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) probably corresponding to «06760» in the sense of bowing; pray:--pray.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Pael) to pray</OL>'),
(6740, 'hlc', 'a primitive root', 'tsalah', 'TWOT - 1915', 'tsaw-law\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to roast:--roast.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to roast</OL>'),
(6741, 'hllc', 'from (06738)', 'Tsillah', 'None', 'tsil-law\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'feminine of «06738»; Tsillah, an antediluvian woman:--Zillah.', 'Zillah = \"shade\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 2nd wife of Lamech and mother of Tubal-cain, an instructor of every craftsman in bronze and iron</OL>'),
(6742, 'lwlc', 'from (06749) in the sense of rolling', 'tsluwl', 'TWOT - 1922a', 'tsel-ool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06749» in the sense of rolling; a (round or flattened) cake:--cake.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cake, round loaf, round, rolling</OL>'),
(6743, 'xlc', 'a primitive root', 'tsalach', 'TWOT - 1916,1917', 'tsaw-lakh\'', 'Verb', 'or tsaleach {tsaw-lay\'-akh}; a primitive root; to push forward, in various senses (literal or figurative, transitive or intransitive):--break out, come (mightily), go over, be good, be meet, be profitable, (cause to, effect, make to, send) prosper(-ity, -ous, - ously).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to rush<LI>to advance, prosper, make progress, succeed, be profitable<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to prosper<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make prosperous, bring to successful issue, cause to prosper<LI>to show or experience prosperity, prosper</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6744, 'xlc', 'corresponding to (06743)', 'tslach', 'TWOT - 2960', 'tsel-akh\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «06743»; to advance (transitive or intransitive):--promote, prosper.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to prosper<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Aphel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to prosper<LI>show prosperity, be prosperous, have success, be successful</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6745, 'hxlc', 'from (06743)', 'tselachah', 'TWOT - 1918a', 'tsay-law-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06743»; something protracted or flattened out, i.e. a platter:--pan.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cooking pot, pot</OL>'),
(6746, 'tyxlc', 'from (06743)', 'tslochiyth', 'TWOT - 1918c', 'tsel-o-kheeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06743»; something prolonged or tall, i.e. a vial or salt-cellar:--cruse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>jar, bowl</OL>'),
(6747, 'txllc', 'from (06743)', 'tsallachath', 'TWOT - 1918b', 'tsal-lakh\'-ath', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06743»; something advanced or deep, i.e. a bowl; figuratively, the bosom:--bosom, dish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dish, bowl</OL>'),
(6748, 'ylc', 'pass part of (06740)', 'tsaliy', 'TWOT - 1915a', 'tsaw-lee\'', '', 'passive participle of «06740»; roasted:--roast.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>roasted, roast adj (CLBL)<LI>roasted</OL>'),
(6749, 'llc', 'a primitive root', 'tsalal', 'TWOT - 1920', 'tsaw-lal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to tumble down, i.e. settle by a waving motion:--sink. Compare «06750», «06751».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to sink, be submerged</OL>'),
(6750, 'llc', 'a primitive root [identical with (06749) through the idea of vibration]', 'tsalal', 'TWOT - 1919', 'tsaw-lal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «06749» through the idea of vibration); to tinkle, i.e. rattle together (as the ears in reddening with shame, or the teeth in chattering with fear):--quiver, tingle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tingle, quiver<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tingle (of ears)<LI>to quiver (of fear)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6751, 'llc', 'a primitive root [identical with (06749) through the idea of hovering over (compare (06754))]', 'tsalal', 'TWOT - 1921', 'tsaw-lal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «06749» through the idea of hovering over (compare «06754»)); to shade, as twilight or an opaque object:--begin to be dark, shadowing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or become or grow dark<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to become or grow dark<LI>(Hiphil) to shadow</OL></OL>'),
(6752, 'llc', 'from (06751)', 'tselel', 'TWOT - 1921a', 'tsay\'-lel', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06751»; shade:--shadow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shadow, shade<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>shadow (on dial)<LI>shadow, shade (as protection)<LI>shadow (symbolic of transitoriness of life)</OL></OL>'),
(6753, 'ynwpllc', 'from (06752) and the act part of (06437)', 'Tslelpowniy', 'None', 'tsel-el-po-nee\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'from «06752» and the active participle of «06437»; shade-facing; Tselelponi, an Israelitess:--Hazelelponi (including the article).', 'Hazelelponi = \"facing the shade\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sister of the sons of Etam in the genealogies of Judah</OL>'),
(6754, '~lc', 'from an unused root meaning to shade', 'tselem', 'TWOT - 1923a', 'tseh\'-lem', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to shade; a phantom, i.e. (figuratively) illusion, resemblance; hence, a representative figure, especially an idol:--image, vain shew.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>image<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>images (of tumours, mice, heathen gods)<LI>image, likeness (of resemblance)<LI>mere, empty, image, semblance (fig.)</OL></OL>'),
(6755, '~lc', 'corresponding to (06754)', 'tselem', 'TWOT - 2961', 'tseh\'-lem', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) or tslem (Aramaic) {tsel-em\'}; corresponding to «06754»; an idolatrous figure:--form, image.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>image, idol</OL>'),
(6756, '!wmlc', 'from (06754)', 'Tsalmown', 'None', 'tsal-mone\'', '', 'from «06754»; shady; Tsalmon, the name of a place in Palestine and of an Israelite:--Zalmon.', 'n pr m Zalmon = \"shady\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Ahohite, one of David\'s mighty warriors n pr loc<LI>a wooded hill in Samaria near Shechem</OL>'),
(6757, 'twmlc', 'from (06738) and (04194)', 'tsalmaveth', 'TWOT - 1921b', 'tsal-maw\'-veth', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06738» and «04194»; shade of death, i.e. the grave (figuratively, calamity):--shadow of death.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>death-shadow, deep shadow, deep darkness, shadow of death<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>death-shadow<LI>death-shadow, deep shadow, darkness<LI>death-shadow (of distress, extreme danger) (fig)<LI>death-shadow (of place of the dead) (fig)</OL></OL>'),
(6758, 'hnmlc', 'fem. of (06757)', 'Tsalmonah', 'None', 'tsal-mo-naw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'feminine of «06757»; shadiness; Tsalmonah, a place in the Desert:--Zalmonah.', 'Zalmonah = \"shady\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a station of Israel during the wilderness wanderings located on the east side of Edom</OL>'),
(6759, '[nnmlc', 'from (06738) and (04513)', 'Tsalmunna`', 'None', 'tsal-moon-naw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06738» and «04513»; shade has been denied; Tsalmunna, a Midianite:--Zalmunna.', 'Zalmunna = \"deprived of protection\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Midianite king slain by Gideon</OL>'),
(6760, '[lc', 'a primitive root: probably to curve', 'tsala`', 'TWOT - 1925', 'tsaw-lah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root: probably to curve; used only as denominative from «06763», to limp (as if one-sided):--halt.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to limp, be lame<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to limp<LI>to be lame</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6761, '[lc', 'from (06760)', 'tsela`', 'TWOT - 1925a', 'tseh\'-lah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06760»; a limping or full (figuratively):--adversity, halt(-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>limping, stumbling</OL>'),
(6762, '[lc', 'the same as (06761)', 'Tsela`', 'None', 'tseh\'-lah', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «06761»; Tsela, a place in Palestine:--Zelah.', 'Zelah = \"a rib\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in Benjamin containing the family burial place of Saul</OL>'),
(6763, '[lc', 'from (06760)', 'tsela`', 'TWOT - 1924a', 'tsay-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or (feminine) tsalTah {tsal-aw\'}; from «06760»; a rib (as curved), literally (of the body) or figuratively (of a door, i.e. leaf); hence, a side, literally (of a person) or figuratively (of an object or the sky, i.e. quarter); architecturally, a (especially floor or ceiling) timber or plank (single or collective, i.e. a flooring):--beam, board, chamber, corner, leaf, plank, rib, side (chamber).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>side, rib, beam<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>rib (of man)<LI>rib (of hill, ridge, etc)<LI>side-chambers or cells (of temple structure)<LI>rib, plank, board (of cedar or fir)<LI>leaves (of door)<LI>side (of ark)</OL></OL>'),
(6764, '@lc', 'from an unused root of unknown meaning', 'Tsalaph', 'None', 'tsaw-lawf\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root of unknown meaning; Tsalaph, an Israelite:--Zalaph.', 'Zalaph = \"wound\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Hanun who assisted in rebuilding the city wall of Jerusalem after the return from exile</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(6765, 'dxplc', 'from the same as (06764) and (0259)', 'Tslophchad', 'None', 'tsel-of-chawd\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «06764» and «0259»; Tselophchad, an Israelite:--Zelophehad.', 'Zelophehad = \"first-born\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Manassite, son of Hepher and grandson of Gilead; came out of Egypt with Moses and died in the wilderness leaving only five daughters as heirs; their right to the inheritance was confirmed by divine direction</OL>'),
(6766, 'xclc', 'from (06738) and (06703)', 'Tseltsach', 'None', 'tsel-tsakh\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06738» and «06703»; clear shade; Tseltsach, a place in Palestine:--Zelzah.', 'Zelzah = \"shadow\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place on the boundary of Benjamin, close to Rachel\'s tomb, 5 miles (8 km) southwest of Jerusalem</OL>'),
(6767, 'lclc', 'from (06750) reduplicated', 'tslatsal', 'TWOT - 1919a,1919b,1919c', 'tsel-aw-tsal\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06750» reduplicated; a clatter, i.e. (abstractly) whirring (of wings); (concretely) a cricket; also a harpoon (as rattling), a cymbal (as clanging):--cymbal, locust, shadowing, spear.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>whirring, buzzing<LI>spear<LI>whirring locust</OL>'),
(6768, 'qlc', 'from an unused root meaning to split', 'Tseleq', 'None', 'tseh\'-lek', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to split; fissure; Tselek, an Israelite:--Zelek.', 'Zelek = \"fissure\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Ammonite and a warrior for David</OL>'),
(6769, 'ytllc', 'from the fem. of (06738)', 'Tsillthay', 'None', 'tsil-leth-ah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the feminine of «06738»; shady; Tsillethai, the name of two Israelites:--Zilthai.', 'Zilthai = \"dark\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite of the sons of Shimhi<LI>a Manassite and commander of thousands who came to David at Ziklag</OL>'),
(6770, 'amc', 'a primitive root', 'tsame\'', 'TWOT - 1926', 'tsaw-may\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to thirst (literally or figuratively):--(be a-, suffer) thirst(-y).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be thirsty</OL>'),
(6771, 'amc', 'from (06770)', 'tsame\'', 'TWOT - 1926b', 'tsaw-may\'', 'Adjective', 'from «06770»; thirsty (literally or figuratively):--(that) thirst(-eth, -y).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thirsty</OL>'),
(6772, 'amc', 'from (06770)', 'tsama\'', 'TWOT - 1926a', 'tsaw-maw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06770»; thirst (literally or figuratively):--thirst(-y).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thirst</OL>'),
(6773, 'hamc', 'from (06772)', 'tsim\'ah', 'TWOT - 1926c', 'tsim-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «06772»; thirst (figuratively, of libidinousnes):--thirst.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>parched condition, thirst, dehydration</OL>'),
(6774, '!wammc', 'from (06771)', 'tsimma\'own', 'TWOT - 1926d', 'tsim-maw-one\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «06771»; a thirsty place, i.e. desert:--drought, dry ground, thirsty land.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thirsty ground</OL>'),
(6775, 'dmc', 'a primitive root', 'tsamad', 'TWOT - 1927', 'tsaw-mad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to link, i.e. gird; figuratively, to serve, (mentally) contrive:--fasten, frame, join (self).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bind, join, fasten<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to join, join or attach oneself to<LI>(Pual) to be fastened, be bound<LI>(Hiphil) to combine, fit together, hitch up</OL></OL>'),
(6776, 'dmc', 'a yoke or team (ie pair)', 'tsemed', 'TWOT - 1927a', 'tseh\'-med', 'Noun Masculine', 'a yoke or team (i.e. pair); hence, an acre (i.e. day\'s task for a yoke of cattle to plough):--acre, couple, × together, two (donkeys), yoke (of oxen).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>couple, pair, team, yoke<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>couple, pair, span (usually of animals)<LI>acre<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the amount of land a span of oxen could plow in one day</OL></OL></OL>'),
(6777, 'hmmc', 'from an unused root meaning to fasten on', 'tsammah', 'TWOT - 1929a', 'tsam-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root meaning to fasten on; a veil:--locks.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>veil, woman\'s veil</OL>'),
