(6868, 'hdrc', 'apparently from an unused root meaning to pierce', 'Tsredah', 'None', 'tser-ay-daw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Tsredathah {tser-ay-daw\'-thaw}; apparently from an unused root meaning to pierce; puncture; Tseredah, a place in Palestine:--Zereda, Zeredathah.', 'Zereda or Zeredathah = \"fortress\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town or territory in Manasseh and the home of Jeroboam</OL>'),
