(7038, 'tlq', 'a primitive root', 'qalat', 'TWOT - 2027', 'kaw-lat\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to maim:--lacking in his parts.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be stunted, be handicapped, be deformed (of a sacrificial animal lacking body parts)</OL>'),
(7039, 'ylq', 'from (07033)', 'qaliy', 'TWOT - 2023a', 'kaw-lee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or qaliyi {kaw-lee\'}; from «07033»; roasted ears of grain:--parched corn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>parched grain, roasted grain<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a common food</OL></OL>'),
(7040, 'yllq', 'from (07043)', 'Qallay', 'None', 'kal-lah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07043»; frivolous; Kallai, an Israelite:--Kallai.', 'Kallai = \"swift\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest of the family of Sallai in the time of Nehemiah</OL>'),
(7041, 'hylq', 'from (07034)', 'Qelayah', 'None', 'kay-law-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07034»; insignificance; Kelajah, an Israelite:--Kelaiah.', 'Kelaiah = \"Jehovah has dishonoured\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Kelita\'</OL></OL>'),
(7042, 'atylq', 'from (07038)', 'Qliyta\'', 'None', 'kel-ee-taw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07038»; maiming; Kelita, the name of three Israelites:--Kelita.', 'Kelita = \"crippled\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Kelaiah\'</OL></OL>'),
(7043, 'llq', 'a primitive root', 'qalal', 'TWOT - 2028', 'kaw-lal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) light, literally (swift, small, sharp, etc.) or figuratively (easy, trifling, vile, etc.):--abate, make bright, bring into contempt, (ac-)curse, despise, (be) ease(-y, -ier), (be a, make, make somewhat, move, seem a, set) light(-en, -er, -ly, -ly afflict, -ly esteem, thing), × slight(-ly), be swift(-er), (be, be more, make, re-)vile, whet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be slight, be swift, be trifling, be of little account, be light<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be slight, be abated (of water)<LI>to be swift<LI>to be trifling, be of little account</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be swift, show oneself swift<LI>to appear trifling, be too trifling, be insignificant<LI>to be lightly esteemed</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make despicable<LI>to curse</OL><LI>(Pual) to be cursed<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make light, lighten<LI>to treat with contempt, bring contempt or dishonour</OL><LI>(Pilpel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shake<LI>to whet</OL><LI>(Hithpalpel) to shake oneself, be moved to and fro</OL></OL>'),
(7044, 'llq', 'from (07043)', 'qalal', 'TWOT - 2028c', 'kaw-lawl\'', 'Adjective', 'from «07043»; brightened (as if sharpened):--burnished, polished.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>burnished, polished</OL>'),
(7045, 'hllq', 'from (07043)', 'qlalah', 'TWOT - 2028d', 'kel-aw-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07043»; vilification:--(ac-)curse(-d, - ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>curse, vilification, execration</OL>'),
(7046, 'olq', 'a primitive root', 'qalac', 'TWOT - 2029', 'kaw-las\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to disparage, i.e. ridicule:--mock, scoff, scorn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to mock, scoff<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to scoff at<LI>(Hithpael) to mock, deride, make fun of</OL></OL>'),
(7047, 'olq', 'from (07046)', 'qelec', 'TWOT - 2029a', 'keh\'-les', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07046»; a laughing-stock:--derision.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>derision, ridicule</OL>'),
(7048, 'hollq', 'intensive from (07046)', 'qallacah', 'TWOT - 2029b', 'kal-law-saw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'intensive from «07046»; ridicule:--mocking.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mocking, derision</OL>'),
(7049, '[lq', 'a primitive root', 'qala`', 'TWOT - 2030,2031', 'kaw-lah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root: to sling: also to carve (as if a circular motion, or into light forms):--carve, sling (out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sling, hurl forth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sling<LI>slinger (participle)</OL><LI>(Piel) to sling</OL><LI>(Qal) to carve</OL>'),
(7050, '[lq', 'from (07049)', 'qela`', 'TWOT - 2030a,2030c', 'keh\'-lah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07049»; a sling; also a (door) screen (as if slung across), or the valve (of the door) itself:--hanging, leaf, sling.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sling, slingstones<LI>curtain, drape, hanging</OL>'),
(7051, '[llq', 'intensive from (07049)', 'qalla`', 'TWOT - 2030b', 'kal-law\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'intensive from «07049»; a slinger:--slinger.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>slinger</OL>'),
(7052, 'lqlq', 'from (07043)', 'qloqel', 'TWOT - 2028e', 'kel-o-kale\'', 'Adjective', 'from «07043»; insubstantial:--light.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>contemptible, worthless</OL>'),
(7053, '!wXllq', 'from an unused root meaning to prick', 'qillshown', 'TWOT - 2032', 'kil-lesh-one\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to prick; a prong, i.e. hay-fork:--fork.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>forks, three-pronged pitchfork, goad<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(7054, 'hmq', 'act part of (06965)', 'qamah', 'TWOT - 1999b', 'kuw-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of active participle of «06965»; something that rises, i.e. a stalk of grain:--(standing) corn, grown up, stalk.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>standing grain</OL>'),
(7055, 'lawmq', 'from (06965) and (0410)', 'Qmuw\'el', 'None', 'kem-oo-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «06965» and «0410»; raised of God; Kemuel, the name of a relative of Abraham, and of two Israelites:--Kemuel.', 'Kemuel = \"raised of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Nahor by Milcah and father of Aram<LI>son of Shiphtan, prince of the tribe of Ephraim, and one of the 12 men selected to apportion the promised land between the tribes<LI>Levite, father of Hashabiah, prince of the tribe in the time of David</OL>'),
(7056, '!wmq', 'from (06965)', 'Qamown', 'None', 'kaw-mone\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06965»; an elevation; Kamon, a place East of the Jordan:--Camon.', 'Camon = \"raised\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the place in Gilead where the judge Jair was buried</OL>'),
(7057, 'Xwmmq', 'from an unused root meaning to sting', 'qimmowsh', 'TWOT - 2037a', 'kim-moshe\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or qiymowsh {kee-moshe\'}; from an unused root meaning to sting; a prickly plant:--nettle. Compare «07063».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thistles or nettles, a thorny or useless plant</OL>'),
(7058, 'xmq', 'from an unused root probably meaning to grind', 'qemach', 'TWOT - 2033a', 'keh\'-makh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to grind; flour:--flour, meal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flour, meal, meal flour</OL>'),
(7059, 'tmq', 'a primitive root', 'qamat', 'TWOT - 2034', 'kaw-mat\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pluck, i.e. destroy:--cut down, fill with wrinkles.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to seize<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to seize<LI>(Pual) to be snatched away prematurely</OL></OL>'),
(7060, 'lmq', 'a primitive root', 'qamal', 'TWOT - 2035', 'kaw-mal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to wither:--hew down, wither.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be decayed, be withered<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to moulder, be withered</OL></OL>'),
(7061, '#mq', 'a primitive root', 'qamats', 'TWOT - 2036', 'kaw-mats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to grasp with the hand:--take an handful.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to grasp, enclose with the hand, take a handful</OL>'),
(7062, '#mq', 'from (07061)', 'qomets', 'TWOT - 2036a', 'ko\'mets', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07061»; a grasp, i.e. handful:--handful.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>closed hand, fist, handful</OL>'),
(7063, '!wXmmq', 'from the same as (07057)', 'qimmashown', 'TWOT - 2037a', 'kim-maw-shone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «07057»; a prickly plant:--thorn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thistles or nettles, a thorny or useless plant</OL>'),
(7064, '!q', 'contracted from (07077)', 'qen', 'TWOT - 2042a', 'kane', 'Noun Masculine', 'contracted from «07077»; a nest (as fixed), sometimes including the nestlings; figuratively, a chamber or dwelling:--nest, room.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nest<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>nest (of bird)<LI>cells (like nests in Noah\'s ark)</OL></OL>'),
(7065, 'anq', 'a primitive root', 'qana\'', 'TWOT - 2038', 'kaw-naw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) zealous, i.e. (in a bad sense) jealous or envious:--(be) envy(-ious), be (move to, provoke to) jealous(-y), × very, (be) zeal(-ous).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to envy, be jealous, be envious, be zealous<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be jealous of<LI>to be envious of<LI>to be zealous for<LI>to excite to jealous anger</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to provoke to jealous anger, cause jealousy</OL></OL>'),
(7066, 'anq', 'corresponding to (07069)', 'qna\'', 'TWOT - 2974', 'ken-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07069»; to purchase:--buy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to acquire, buy, purchase</OL>'),
(7067, 'annq', 'from (07065)', 'qanna\'', 'TWOT - 2038b', 'kan-naw\'', 'Adjective', 'from «07065»; jealous:--jealous. Compare «07072».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>jealous (only of God)</OL>'),
(7068, 'hanq', 'from (07065)', 'qin\'ah', 'TWOT - 2038a', 'kin-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07065»; jealousy or envy:--envy(-ied), jealousy, × sake, zeal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ardour, zeal, jealousy<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>ardour, jealousy, jealous disposition (of husband)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sexual passion</OL><LI>ardour of zeal (of religious zeal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of men for God<LI>of men for the house of God<LI>of God for his people</OL><LI>ardour of anger<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of men against adversaries<LI>of God against men</OL><LI>envy (of man)<LI>jealousy (resulting in the wrath of God)</OL></OL>'),
(7069, 'hnq', 'a primitive root', 'qanah', 'TWOT - 2039', 'kaw-naw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to erect, i.e. create; by extension, to procure, especially by purchase (causatively, sell); by implication to own:--attain, buy(-er), teach to keep cattle, get, provoke to jealousy, possess(-or), purchase, recover, redeem, × surely, × verily.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to get, acquire, create, buy, possess<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to get, acquire, obtain 1a</OL><LI>of God originating, creating, redeeming His people 1a<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>possessor 1a</OL><LI>of Eve acquiring 1a<LI>of acquiring knowledge, wisdom<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to buy</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be bought<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to possess</OL></OL>'),
(7070, 'hnq', 'from (07069)', 'qaneh', 'TWOT - 2040a', 'kaw-neh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07069»; a reed (as erect); by resemblance a rod (especially for measuring), shaft, tube, stem, the radius (of the arm), beam (of a steelyard):--balance, bone, branch, calamus, cane, reed, × spearman, stalk.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>reed, stalk, bone, balances<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>stalk<LI>water-plant, reed<LI>calamus (aromatic reed)<LI>derived meanings<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>measuring-rod<LI>reed (as unit of measure - 6 cubits)<LI>beam (of scales - for scales themselves)<LI>shaft (of lampstand)<LI>branches (of lampstand)<LI>shoulder-joint</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7071, 'hnq', 'fem. of (07070)', 'Qanah', 'None', 'kaw-naw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'feminine of «07070»; reediness; Kanah, the name of a stream and of a place in Palestine:--Kanah.', 'Kanah = \"reed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a stream flowing into the Mediterranean Sea that marked the boundary between Ephraim on the south and Manasseh on the north<LI>a town marking the boundary of Asher</OL>'),
(7072, 'awnnq', 'for (07067)', 'qannow\'', 'TWOT - 2038c', 'kan-no\'', 'Adjective', 'for «07067»; jealous or angry:--jealous.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>jealous</OL>'),
(7073, 'znq', 'probably from an unused root meaning to hunt', 'Qnaz', 'None', 'ken-az\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from an unused root meaning to hunt; hunter; Kenaz, the name of an Edomite and of two Israelites:--Kenaz.', 'Kenaz = \"hunter\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Eliphaz and grandson of Esau; one of the dukes of Edom<LI>a brother of Caleb and father of Othniel</OL>'),
(7074, 'yzznq', 'patronymic from (07073)', 'Qnizziy', 'None', 'ken-iz-zee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'patronymic from «07073», a Kenizzite or descendant of Kenaz:--Kenezite, Kenizzites.', 'Kenezite or Kenizzites = \"descendant of Kenaz\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Kenaz</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(7075, '!ynq', 'from (07069)', 'qinyan', 'TWOT - 2039a', 'kin-yawn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07069»; creation, i.e. (concretely) creatures; also acquisition, purchase, wealth:--getting, goods, × with money, riches, substance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thing acquired, acquisition, possession, purchased property, wealth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>thing acquired (by purchase)<LI>creatures (more general)</OL></OL>'),
(7076, '!wmnnq', 'from an unused root (meaning to erect)', 'qinnamown', 'TWOT - 2041', 'kin-naw-mone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root (meaning to erect); cinnamon bark (as in upright rolls):--cinnamon.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cinnamon<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>fragrant bark used as spice</OL></OL>'),
(7077, '!nq', 'a primitive root', 'qanan', 'TWOT - 2042', 'kaw-nan\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to erect; but used only as denominative from «07064»; to nestle, i.e. build or occupy as a nest:-- make...nest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make a nest<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to make a nest<LI>(Pual) to be nested</OL></OL>'),
(7078, '#nq', 'from an unused root probably meaning to wrench', 'qenets', 'TWOT - 2043a', 'keh\'-nets', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to wrench; perversion:--end.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>snare, net<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(7079, 'tnq', 'from (07069)', 'Qnath', 'None', 'ken-awth\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «07069»; possession; Kenath, a place East of the Jordan:--Kenath.', 'Kenath = \"possession\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in Gilead east of the Jordan taken possession of by a certain Nobah and renamed in his own honour</OL>'),
(7080, '~oq', 'a primitive root', 'qacam', 'TWOT - 2044', 'kaw-sam\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to distribute, i.e. determine by lot or magical scroll; by implication, to divine:--divine(-r, -ation), prudent, soothsayer, use (divination).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to practice divination, divine<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of diviners of the nations, Balaam<LI>of false prophets of Israel<LI>prohibited</OL></OL>'),
(7081, '~oq', 'from (07080)', 'qecem', 'TWOT - 2044a', 'keh\'-sem', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07080»; a lot: also divination (including its fee), oracle:--(reward of) divination, divine sentence, witchcraft.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>divination, witchcraft<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the nations, Balaam<LI>of false prophets<LI>in a good sense (king\'s lips as oracles)</OL></OL>'),
(7082, 'ooq', 'a primitive root', 'qacac', 'TWOT - 2045', 'kaw-sas\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to lop off:--cut off.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Poel) to strip off, cut off</OL>'),
(7083, 'toq', 'from the same as (03563) (or as (07185))', 'qeceth', 'TWOT - 2080b', 'keh\'-seth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «03563» (or as «07185»); properly, a cup, i.e. an ink-stand:--inkhorn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pot (for ink), inkhorn, inkwell</OL>'),
(7084, 'hly[q', 'perhaps from (07049) in the sense of inclosing', 'Q`iylah', 'None', 'keh-ee-law\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'perhaps from «07049» in the sense of inclosing; citadel; Keilah, a place in Palestine:--Keilah.', 'Keilah = \"fortress\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in the lowlands of Judah northwest of Hebron</OL>'),
(7085, '[q[q', 'from the same as (06970)', 'qa`aqa`', 'TWOT - 2046a', 'kah-ak-ah\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «06970»; an incision or gash:--+ mark.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>incision, imprintment, tattoo, mark</OL>'),
(7086, 'hr[q', 'probably from (07167)', 'q`arah', 'TWOT - 2047a', 'keh-aw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'probably from «07167»; a bowl (as cut out hollow):--charger, dish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dish, platter</OL>'),
(7087, 'apq', 'a primitive root', 'qapha\'', 'TWOT - 2048,2048a', 'kaw-faw\'', '', 'a primitive root; to shrink, i.e. thicken (as unracked wine, curdled milk, clouded sky, frozen water):--congeal, curdle, dark, settle.', 'v<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to thicken, condense, congeal, settle, become dense<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be condensed<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thickening (participle)</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to cause to curdle n m</OL><LI>congelation</OL>'),
(7088, 'dpq', 'a primitive root', 'qaphad', 'TWOT - 2049', 'kaw-fad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to contract, i.e. roll together:--cut off.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to gather together, roll up, harvest</OL>'),
(7089, 'hdpq', 'from (07088)', 'qphadah', 'TWOT - 2049b', 'kef-aw-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07088»; shrinking, i.e., terror:--destruction.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shuddering, anguish</OL>'),
(7090, 'dwppq', 'from (07088)', 'qippowd', 'TWOT - 2049a', 'kip-pode\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or qippod {kip-pode\'}; from «07088»; a species of bird, perhaps the bittern (from its contracted form):--bittern.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>porcupine, hedgehog<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a shrinking animal</OL></OL>'),
(7091, 'zwppq', 'from an unused root meaning to contract, i.e. spring forward', 'qippowz', 'TWOT - 2050a', 'kip-poze\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to contract, i.e. spring forward; an arrow-snake (as darting on its prey):--great owl.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>arrow snake, owl<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(7092, '#pq', 'a primitive root', 'qaphats', 'TWOT - 2051', 'kaw-fats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to draw together, i.e. close; by implication, to leap (by contracting the limbs); specifically, to die (from gathering up the feet):--shut (up), skip, stop, take out of the way.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to draw together, close, shut, shut up, stop up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to shut<LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to draw oneself together (of death)<LI>to be shut up to death</OL><LI>(Piel) springing, skipping (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(7093, '#q', 'contracted from (07112), an extremity', 'qets', 'TWOT - 2060a', 'kates', 'Noun Masculine', 'contracted from «07112»; an extremity; adverbially (with prepositional prefix) after:--+ after, (utmost) border, end, (in-)finite, × process.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>end<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>end, at the end of (of time)<LI>end (of space)</OL></OL>'),
(7094, 'bcq', 'a primitive root', 'qatsab', 'TWOT - 2052', 'kaw-tsab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to clip, or (generally) chop:--cut down, shorn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to cut off, shear</OL>'),
(7095, 'bcq', 'from (07094)', 'qetseb', 'TWOT - 2052a', 'keh\'-tseb', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07094»; shape (as if cut out); base (as if there cut off):--bottom, size.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cut, shape, extremity, form, base<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>cut, shape<LI>extremity</OL></OL>'),
(7096, 'hcq', 'a primitive root', 'qatsah', 'TWOT - 2053', 'kaw-tsaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to cut off; (figuratively) to destroy; (partially) to scrape off:--cut off, cut short, scrape (off).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut off<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to cut off<LI>(Piel) to cut off<LI>(Hiphil) to scrape, scrape off</OL></OL>'),
(7097, 'hcq', 'from (07096)', 'qatseh', 'TWOT - 2053a,2053c', 'kaw-tseh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (negative only) qetseh {kay\'-tseh}; from «07096»; an extremity (used in a great variety of applications and idioms; compare «07093»):--X after, border, brim, brink, edge, end, (in-)finite, frontier, outmost coast, quarter, shore, (out-)side, × some, ut(-ter-)most (part).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>end, extremity<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>end, mouth, extremity<LI>border, outskirts<LI>the whole (condensed term for what is included within extremities)<LI>at the end of (a certain time)</OL></OL>'),
(7098, 'hcq', 'fem. of (07097)', 'qatsah', 'TWOT - 2053b', 'kaw-tsaw\'', 'Noun', 'feminine of «07097»; a termination (used like «07097»):--coast, corner, (selv-)edge, lowest, (uttermost) participle', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>end, extremity<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>end<LI>from the whole of, from among (of what is included between extremities)</OL></OL>'),
(7099, 'wcq', 'from (07096)', 'qetsev', 'TWOT - 2053d', 'keh\'-tsev', 'Noun Masculine', 'and (feminine) qitsvah {kits-vaw\'}; from «07096»; a limit (used like «07097», but with less variety):--end, edge, uttermost participle', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>end, border, boundary</OL>'),
(7100, 'xcq', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to incise', 'qetsach', 'TWOT - 2055a', 'keh\'-tsakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to incise; fennelflower (from its pungency):--fitches.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>black cummin<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a plant with small black acrid seeds used as a condiment</OL></OL>'),
(7101, '!ycq', 'from (07096) in the sense of determining', 'qatsiyn', 'TWOT - 2054a', 'kaw-tseen\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07096» in the sense of determining; a magistrate (as deciding) or other leader:--captain, guide, prince, ruler. Compare «06278».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chief, ruler, commander<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>chief, commander (in war)<LI>dictator<LI>ruler (of one in authority)</OL></OL>'),
(7102, 'h[ycq', 'from (07106)', 'qtsiy`ah', 'TWOT - 2056a', 'kets-ee-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07106»; cassia (as peeled; plural the bark):--cassia.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cassia<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a spice; a powdered bark like cinnamon</OL></OL>'),
(7103, 'h[ycq', 'the same as (07102)', 'Qtsiy`ah', 'None', 'kets-ee-aw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «07102»; Ketsiah, a daughter of Job:--Kezia.', 'Kezia = \"cassia\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 2nd of the daughters born to Job after his trial</OL>'),
(7104, '#ycq', 'from (07112)', 'Qtsiyts', 'None', 'kets-eets\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «07112»; abrupt; Keziz, a valley in Palestine:--Keziz.', 'Keziz = \"cut off\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town on Benjamin and the eastern border of the tribe</OL>'),
(7105, 'rycq', 'from (07114)', 'qatsiyr', 'TWOT - 2062a,2062b', 'kaw-tseer\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07114»; severed, i.e. harvest (as reaped), the crop, the time, the reaper, or figuratively; also a limb (of a tree, or simply foliage):--bough, branch, harvest (man).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>harvest, harvesting<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>process of harvesting<LI>crop, what is harvested or reaped<LI>time of harvest</OL><LI>boughs, branches</OL>'),
(7106, '[cq', 'a primitive root', 'qatsa`', 'TWOT - 2056,2057', 'kaw-tsah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to strip off, i.e. (partially) scrape; by implication, to segregate (as an angle):--cause to scrape, corner.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to scrape, scrape off, cut off<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil) to scrape</OL><LI>to be cornered, be set in corners<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hophal) to cut off places, make corners</OL></OL>'),
(7107, '@cq', 'a primitive root', 'qatsaph', 'TWOT - 2058', 'kaw-tsaf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to crack off, i.e. (figuratively) burst out in rage:--(be) anger(-ry), displease, fret self, (provoke to) wrath (come), be wroth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be displeased, be angry, fret oneself, be wroth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be wroth, to be full of wrath, to be furious<LI>(Hiphil) to provoke to wrath or anger<LI>(Hithpael) to put oneself in a rage, anger oneself</OL></OL>'),
(7108, '@cq', 'corresponding to (07107)', 'qtsaph', 'TWOT - 2975', 'kets-af\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07107»; to become enraged:--be furious.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to be or become angry, be wroth</OL>'),
(7109, '@cq', 'from (07108)', 'qtsaph', 'TWOT - 2975a', 'kets-af\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «07108»; rage:--wrath.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wrath (of God), anger</OL>'),
(7110, '@cq', 'from (07107)', 'qetseph', 'TWOT - 2058a,2059b', 'keh\'-tsef', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07107»; a splinter (as chipped off); figuratively, rage or strife:--foam, indignation, × sore, wrath.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wrath, anger<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of God<LI>of man</OL><LI>splinter, twig, broken twig<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(7111, 'hpcq', 'from (07107)', 'qtsaphah', 'TWOT - 2059a', 'kets-aw-faw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07107»; a fragment:--bark(-ed).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>snapping or splintering, something fragmented or splintered</OL>'),
(7112, '#cq', 'a primitive root', 'qatsats', 'TWOT - 2060', 'kaw-tsats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to chop off (literally or figuratively):--cut (asunder, in pieces, in sunder, off), ×  utmost.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut off<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to cut off<LI>(Piel) to cut or hew off, cut in two, cut in pieces<LI>(Pual) to be cut or hewn off</OL></OL>'),
(7113, '#cq', 'corresponding to (07112)', 'qtsats', 'None', 'kets-ats\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07112»:--cut off.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Pael) to cut off</OL>'),
(7114, 'rcq', 'a primitive root', 'qatsar', 'TWOT - 2061,2062', 'kaw-tsar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to dock off, i.e. curtail (transitive or intransitive, literal or figurative); especially to harvest (grass or grain):--X at all, cut down, much discouraged, grieve, harvestman, lothe, mourn, reap(-er), (be, wax) short(-en, -er), straiten, trouble, vex.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be short, be impatient, be vexed, be grieved<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be short<LI>(Piel) to shorten<LI>(Hiphil) to shorten</OL><LI>to reap, harvest<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to reap, harvest<LI>(Hiphil) to reap, harvest</OL></OL>'),
(7115, 'rcq', 'from (07114)', 'qotser', 'TWOT - 2061b', 'ko\'-tser', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07114»; shortness (of spirit), i.e. impatience:--anguish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shortness, impatience, anguish</OL>'),
(7116, 'rcq', 'from (07114)', 'qatser', 'TWOT - 2061a', 'kaw-tsare\'', 'Adjective', 'from «07114»; short (whether in size, number, life, strength or temper):--few, hasty, small, soon.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>short, impatient<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>in size, number, life, strength, etc</OL></OL>'),
(7117, 'tcq', 'from (07096)', 'qtsath', 'TWOT - 2053e', 'kets-awth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07096»; a termination (literally or figuratively); also (by implication) a portion; adverbially (with prepositional prefix) after:--end, part, × some.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>end, part<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>end<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of corners, of earth</OL><LI>from the end of<LI>at the end of</OL></OL>'),
(7118, 'tcq', 'corresponding to (07117)', 'qtsath', 'TWOT - 2976', 'kets-awth\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07117»:--end, partly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>end, part</OL>'),
(7119, 'rq', 'contracted from an unused root meaning to chill', 'qar', 'TWOT - 2077a', 'kar', 'Adjective', 'contracted from an unused root meaning to chill; cool; figuratively, quiet:--cold, excellent (from the margin).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cool<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>cool, calm, self-possessed (of spirit)</OL></OL>'),
(7120, 'rq', 'from the same as (07119)', 'qor', 'TWOT - 2077b', 'kore', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «07119»; cold:--cold.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cold</OL>'),
(7121, 'arq', 'a primitive root [rather identical with (07122) through the idea of accosting a person met]', 'qara\'', 'TWOT - 2063', 'kaw-raw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (rather identical with «07122» through the idea of accosting a person met); to call out to (i.e. properly, address by name, but used in a wide variety of applications):--bewray (self), that are bidden, call (for, forth, self, upon), cry (unto), (be) famous, guest, invite, mention, (give) name, preach, (make) proclaim(- ation), pronounce, publish, read, renowned, say.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to call, call out, recite, read, cry out, proclaim<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to call, cry, utter a loud sound<LI>to call unto, cry (for help), call (with name of God)<LI>to proclaim<LI>to read aloud, read (to oneself), read<LI>to summon, invite, call for, call and commission, appoint, call and endow<LI>to call, name, give name to, call by</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to call oneself<LI>to be called, be proclaimed, be read aloud, be summoned, be named</OL><LI>(Pual) to be called, be named, be called out, be chosen</OL></OL>'),
(7122, 'arq', 'a primitive root, to encounter, whether accidentally or in a hostile manner', 'qara\'', 'TWOT - 2064', 'kaw-raw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root: to encounter, whether accidentally or in a hostile manner:--befall, (by) chance, (cause to) come (upon), fall out, happen, meet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to encounter, befall, meet<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to meet, encounter<LI>to befall (fig)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to meet, meet unexpectedly<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to meet</OL></OL>'),
(7123, 'arq', 'corresponding to (07121)', 'qra\'', 'TWOT - 2977', 'ker-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07121»:--call, cry, read.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to call, read aloud, read out, shout<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to call, proclaim<LI>to read aloud, read out</OL><LI>(Ithp\'el) to be summoned, be called</OL></OL>'),
(7124, 'arq', 'properly, act part of (07121)', 'qore\'', 'TWOT - 2063a', 'ko-ray\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'properly, active participle of «07121»; a caller, i.e. partridge (from its cry):--partridge. See also «06981».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>partridge</OL>'),
(7125, 'harq', 'from (07122)', 'qir\'ah', 'TWOT - 2064', 'keer-aw\'', '', 'from «07122»; an encountering, accidental, friendly or hostile (also adverbially, opposite):--X against (he come), help, meet, seek, × to, × in the way.', 'n m (BDB)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to encounter, befall, meet<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to meet, encounter<LI>to befall (fig)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7126, 'brq', 'a primitive root', 'qarab', 'TWOT - 2065', 'kaw-rab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to approach (causatively, bring near) for whatever purpose:--(cause to) approach, (cause to) bring (forth, near), (cause to) come (near, nigh), (cause to) draw near (nigh), go (near), be at hand, join, be near, offer, present, produce, make ready, stand, take.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to come near, approach, enter into, draw near<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to approach, draw near<LI>(Niphal) to be brought near<LI>(Piel) to cause to approach, bring near, cause to draw near<LI>(Hiphil) to bring near, bring, present</OL></OL>'),
(7127, 'brq', 'corresponding to (07126)', 'qreb', 'TWOT - 2978', 'ker-abe\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07126»:--approach, come (near, nigh), draw near.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to approach, come near<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to approach<LI>(Pael) to offer, draw near<LI>(Aphel) to be summoned</OL></OL>'),
(7128, 'brq', 'from (07126)', 'qrab', 'TWOT - 2063b', 'ker-awb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07126»; hostile encounter:--battle, war.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>battle, war</OL>'),
(7129, 'brq', 'corresponding to (07128)', 'qrab', 'TWOT - 2978a', 'ker-awb\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07128»:--war.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>war</OL>'),
(7130, 'brq', 'from (07126)', 'qereb', 'TWOT - 2066a', 'keh\'-reb', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07126»; properly, the nearest part, i.e. the center, whether literal, figurative or adverbial (especially with preposition):--X among, × before, bowels, × unto charge, + eat (up), × heart, × him, × in, inward (X -ly, part, -s, thought), midst, + out of, purtenance, × therein, × through, ×  within self.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>midst, among, inner part, middle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>inward part<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>physical sense<LI>as seat of thought and emotion<LI>as faculty of thought and emotion</OL><LI>in the midst, among, from among (of a number of persons)<LI>entrails (of sacrificial animals)</OL></OL>'),
(7131, 'brq', 'from (07126)', 'qareb', 'TWOT - 2065a', 'kaw-rabe\'', 'Adjective', 'from «07126»; near:--approach, come (near, nigh), draw near.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>near, approaching</OL>'),
(7132, 'hbrq', 'from (07126)', 'qrabah', 'TWOT - 2065c', 'ker-aw-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07126»; approach:--approaching, draw near.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an approach, a drawing near</OL>'),
(7133, '!brq', 'from (07126)', 'qorban', 'TWOT - 2065e', 'kor-bawn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or qurban {koor-bawn\'}; from «07126»; something brought near the altar, i.e. a sacrificial present:--oblation, that is offered, offering.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>offering, oblation</OL>'),
(7134, '~drq', 'perhaps from (06923) in the sense of striking upon', 'qardom', 'TWOT - 2067', 'kar-dome\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'perhaps from «06923» in the sense of striking upon; an axe:--ax.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>axe</OL>'),
