(7152, 'twyrq', 'pl. of (07151)', 'Qriyowth', 'None', 'ker-ee-yoth\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'plural of «07151»; buildings; Kerioth, the name of two places in Palestine:--Kerioth, Kirioth.', 'Kerioth = \"cities\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in the southern district of Judah<LI>a city in Moab</OL>'),
(7153, '[br[ tyrq', 'from (07151) and (0704) or (0702)', 'Qiryath', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'or (with the article interposed) Qiryath ha- Arbaw (Neh. 11:25) {keer-yath\' haw-ar-bah\'}; from «07151» and «0704» or «0702»; city of Arba, or city of the four (giants); Kirjath-Arba or Kirjath-ha-Arba, a place in Palestine:--Kirjath-arba.', 'Kirjath-arba = \"city of Arba\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>early name of the city which after the conquest was called \'Hebron\'</OL>'),
(7154, 'l[b tyrq', 'from (07151) and (01168)', 'Qiryath', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «07151» and «01168»; city of Baal; Kirjath-Baal, a place in Palestine:--Kirjath-baal.', 'Kirjath-baal = \"city of Baal\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city on the northern boundary of Judah and on the western and southern boundaries of Benjamin<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Kirjath-jearim\' and \'Baalah\'</OL></OL>'),
(7155, 'twcx tyrq', 'from (07151) and the fem. pl. of (02351)', 'Qiryath', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «07151» and the feminine plural of «02351»; city of streets; Kirjath-Chutsoth, a place in Moab:--Kirjath-huzoth.', 'Kirjath-huzoth = \"city of streets\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in Moab</OL>'),
(7156, '~ytyrq', 'dual of (07151)', 'Qiryathayim', 'None', 'keer-yaw-thah\'-yim', 'Proper Name Location', 'dual of «07151»; double city; Kirjathaim, the name of two placed in Palestine:--Kiriathaim, Kirjathaim.', 'Kiriathaim = \"two cities\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city east of the Jordan in Moab<LI>a town in Naphtali allotted to the Gershonite Levites</OL>'),
(7157, '~yr[y tyrq', 'from (07151) and the pl. of (03293) or (05892)', 'Qiryath', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'or (Jer. 26:20) with the article interposed; or (Josh. 18:28) simply the former part of the word; or Qiryath tAriym {keer-yath\' aw-reem\'}; from «07151» and the plural of «03293» or «05892»; city of forests, or city of towns; Kirjath-Jearim or Kirjath-Arim, a place in Palestine:--Kirjath, Kirjath-jearim, Kirjath-arim.', 'Kirjath-jearim = \"city of forests\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city on the northern boundary of Judah and on the western and southern boundaries of Benjamin<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Kirjath-baal\' and \'Baalah\'</OL></OL>'),
(7158, 'hnno tyrq', 'from (07151) and a simpler fem. from the same as (05577), or (for the latter name) (05612)', 'Qiryath', 'None', '', 'Neuter', 'or Qiryath Cepher {keer-yath\' say-fer}; from «07151» and a simpler feminine from the same as «05577», or (for the latter name) «05612»; city of branches, or of a book; Kirjath-Sannah or Kirjath-Sepher, a place in Palestine:--Kirjath-sannah, Kirjath-sepher.', 'Kirjath-sepher or Kirjath-sannah = \"city of the book\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in the mountains of Judah to the west of Hebron</OL>'),
(7159, '~rq', 'a primitive root', 'qaram', 'TWOT - 2071', 'kaw-ram\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to cover:--cover.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to spread or lay something over, cover, spread over<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be spread over</OL></OL>'),
(7160, '!rq', 'a primitive root', 'qaran', 'TWOT - 2072', 'kaw-ran\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to push or gore; used only as denominative from «07161», to shoot out horns; figuratively, rays:--have horns, shine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shine<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to send out rays<LI>(Hiphil) to display or grow horns, be horned</OL></OL>'),
(7161, '!rq', 'from (07160)', 'qeren', 'TWOT - 2072a', 'keh\'-ren', '', 'from «07160»; a horn (as projecting); by implication, a flask, cornet; by resembl. an elephant\'s tooth (i.e. ivory), a corner (of the altar), a peak (of a mountain), a ray (of light); figuratively, power:--X hill, horn.', 'n f<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>horn<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>horn<LI>of strength (fig)<LI>flask (container for oil)<LI>horn (as musical instrument)<LI>horn (of horn-like projections on the altar)<LI>of rays of light<LI>hill n pr loc (BDB)</OL><LI>a place conquered by Israel probably in Bashan</OL>'),
(7162, '!rq', 'corresponding to (07161)', 'qeren', 'TWOT - 2980', 'keh\'-ren', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07161»; a horn (literally or for sound):--horn, cornet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>horn<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>as musical instrument<LI>symbolic (in visions)<LI>of an animal</OL></OL>'),
(7163, '$wpph !rq', 'from (07161) and (06320)', 'qeren', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'from «07161» and «06320»; horn of cosmetic; Keren-hap-Puk, one of Job\'s daughters:--Keren-happuch.', 'Keren-happuch = \"horn of antimony\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the daughters of Job born after his trial</OL>'),
(7164, 'orq', 'a primitive root', 'qarac', 'TWOT - 2073', 'kaw-ras\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to protrude; used only as denominative from «07165» (for alliteration with «07167»), to hunch, i.e. be hump-backed:--stoop.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to bend down, stoop, crouch</OL>'),
(7165, 'orq', 'from (07164)', 'qerec', 'TWOT - 2073a', 'keh\'-res', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07164»; a knob or belaying-pin (from its swelling form):--tache.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hook</OL>'),
(7166, 'lorq', 'from (07164)', 'qarcol', 'TWOT - 2073b', 'kar-sole\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07164»; an ankle (as a protuberance or joint):--foot.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ankle</OL>'),
(7167, '[rq', 'a primitive root', 'qara`', 'TWOT - 2074', 'kaw-rah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to rend, literally or figuratively (revile, paint the eyes, as if enlarging them):--cut out, rend, ×  surely, tear.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tear, tear in pieces<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tear, rend<LI>to tear away or out<LI>to tear, rend asunder 1a</OL><LI>to make wide or large (of eyes) 1a<LI>to rend open (of heavens)<OL TYPE=\"4\"><LI>to tear, rend (of wild beasts)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be rent, be split asunder</OL></OL>'),
(7168, '[rq', 'from (07167)', 'qera`', 'TWOT - 2074a', 'keh\'-rah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07167»; a rag:--piece, rag.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rag, torn pieces of garment or fabric</OL>'),
(7169, '#rq', 'a primitive root', 'qarats', 'TWOT - 2075', 'kaw-rats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pinch, i.e. (partially) to bite the lips, blink the eyes (as a gesture of malice), or (fully) to squeeze off (a piece of clay in order to mould a vessel from it):--form, move, wink.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to narrow, form, nip, pinch, squeeze, wink, purse<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to pinch<LI>(Pual) to be nipped or pinched off, be formed</OL></OL>'),
(7170, '#rq', 'corresponding to (07171) in the sense of a bit (to \"eat the morsels of\" any one, i.e. chew him up [fig] by slander)', 'qrats', 'TWOT - 2981', 'ker-ats\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07171» in the sense of a bit (to \"eat the morsels of\" any one, i.e. chew him up (figuratively) by slander):--+ accuse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>piece<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>denounce, slander, accuse maliciously, chew on (idiom)</OL></OL>'),
(7171, '#rq', 'from (07169)', 'qerets', 'TWOT - 2075a', 'keh\'-rets', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07169»; extirpation (as if by constriction):--destruction.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nipping, nipper, stinger<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>nipping or stinging insect, gadfly</OL></OL>'),
(7172, '[qrq', 'from (07167)', 'qarqa`', 'TWOT - 2076', 'kar-kah\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07167»; floor (as if a pavement of pieces or tesseroe), of a building or the sea:--bottom, (X one side of the) floor.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>floor, bottom</OL>'),
(7173, '[qrq', 'the same as (07172)', 'Qarqa`', 'None', 'kar-kah\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «07172»; ground-floor; Karka (with the article prefix), a place in Palestine:--Karkaa.', 'Karkaa = \"floor\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a landmark on the southern boundary of Judah<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>site unknown</OL></OL>'),
(7174, 'rqrq', 'from (06979)', 'Qarqor', 'None', 'kar-kore\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06979»; foundation; Karkor, a place East of the Jordan:--Karkor.', 'Karkor = \"foundation\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place east of the Jordan in Gilead where Zebah and Zalmunna were again routed by Gideon</OL>'),
(7175, 'Xrq', 'from an unused root meaning to split off', 'qeresh', 'TWOT - 2079a', 'keh\'-resh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to split off; a slab or plank; by implication, a deck of a ship:--bench, board.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>board, boards, plank<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>board<LI>boards</OL></OL>'),
(7176, 'trq', 'from (07136) in the sense of building', 'qereth', 'TWOT - 2068h', 'keh\'-reth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07136» in the sense of building; a city:--city.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>city, town</OL>'),
(7177, 'htrq', 'from (07176)', 'Qartah', 'None', 'kar-taw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «07176»; city; Kartah, a place in Palestine:--Kartah.', 'Kartah = \"city\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Zebulun allotted to the Merarite Levites</OL>'),
(7178, '!trq', 'from (07176)', 'Qartan', 'None', 'kar-tawn\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «07176»; city-plot; Kartan, a place in Palestine:--Kartan.', 'Kartan = \"two cities\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Naphtali allotted to the Gershonite Levites<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Kirjathaim\'</OL></OL>'),
(7179, 'Xq', 'from (07197)', 'qash', 'TWOT - 2091a', 'kash', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07197»; straw (as dry):--stubble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stubble, chaff</OL>'),
(7180, 'aXXq', 'from an unused root (meaning to be hard)', 'qishshu\'', 'TWOT - 2083a', 'kish-shoo\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root (meaning to be hard); a cucumber (from the difficulty of digestion):--cucumber.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cucumber</OL>'),
(7181, 'bXq', 'a primitive root', 'qashab', 'TWOT - 2084', 'kaw-shab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to prick up the ears, i.e. hearken:--attend, (cause to) hear(-ken), give heed, incline, mark (well), regard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hear, be attentive, heed, incline (of ears), attend (of ears), hearken, pay attention, listen<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) incline, attend (of ears), hearken, pay attention, listen<LI>(Hiphil) to pay attention, give attention</OL></OL>'),
(7182, 'bXq', 'from (07181)', 'qesheb', 'TWOT - 2084a', 'keh\'-sheb', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07181»; a hearkening:--X diligently, hearing, much heed, that regarded.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>attentiveness, attention</OL>'),
(7183, 'bXXq', 'from (07181)', 'qashshab', 'TWOT - 2084b,2084c', 'kash-shawb\'', 'Adjective', 'or qashshub {kash-shoob\'}; from «07181»; hearkening:--attent(-ive).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>attentive</OL>'),
(7184, 'hXq', 'from an unused root meaning to be round', 'qasah', 'TWOT - 2080,2080a', 'kaw-saw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or qasvah {kas-vaw\'}; from an unused root meaning to be round; a jug (from its shape):--cover, cup.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a kind of jug, jar</OL>'),
(7185, 'hXq', 'a primitive root', 'qashah', 'TWOT - 2085', 'kaw-shaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to be dense, i.e. tough or severe (in various applications):--be cruel, be fiercer, make grievous, be ((ask a), be in, have, seem, would) hard(-en, (labour), -ly, thing), be sore, (be, make) stiff(-en, (-necked)).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be hard, be severe, be fierce, be harsh<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be hard, be difficult<LI>to be hard, be severe</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be ill-treated<LI>to be hard pressed</OL><LI>(Piel) to have severe labour (of women)<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make difficult, make difficulty<LI>to make severe, make burdensome<LI>to make hard, make stiff, make stubborn 1d</OL><LI>of obstinacy (fig)<OL TYPE=\"4\"><LI>to show stubbornness</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7186, 'hXq', 'from (07185)', 'qasheh', 'TWOT - 2085a', 'kaw-sheh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «07185»; severe (in various applications):--churlish, cruel, grievous, hard((-hearted), thing), heavy, + impudent, obstinate, prevailed, rough(-ly), sore, sorrowful, stiff((necked)), stubborn, + in trouble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hard, cruel, severe, obstinate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>hard, difficult<LI>severe<LI>fierce, intense, vehement<LI>stubborn, stiff of neck, stiff-necked<LI>rigorous (of battle)</OL></OL>'),
(7187, 'twXq', 'corresponding to (07189)', 'qshowt', 'TWOT - 2982', 'kesh-ote\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) or qshot (Aramaic) {kesh-ote\'}; corresponding to «07189»; fidelity:--truth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>truth</OL>'),
(7188, 'xXq', 'a primitive root', 'qashach', 'TWOT - 2087', 'kaw-shakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) unfeeling:--harden.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make hard, treat hardly, treat severely<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make hard, make stubborn<LI>to treat hardly, treat roughly</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7189, 'tXq', 'from an unused root meaning to balance', 'qoshet', 'TWOT - 2088,2089a', 'ko\'-shet', 'Noun Masculine', 'or qosht {kosht}; from an unused root meaning to balance; equity (as evenly weighed), i.e. reality:--truth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bow<LI>truth, balanced verity</OL>'),
(7190, 'yXq', 'from (07185)', 'qshiy', 'TWOT - 2085b', 'kesh-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07185»; obstinacy:--stubbornness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stubbornness, obstinacy</OL>'),
(7191, '!wyXq', 'from (07190)', 'Qishyown', 'None', 'kish-yone\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «07190»; hard ground; Kishjon, a place in Palestine:--Kishion, Keshon.', 'Kishion = \"hard\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town on the boundary of Issachar allotted to the Gershonite Levites</OL>'),
(7192, 'htyXq', 'from an unused root (probably meaning to weigh out)', 'qsiytah', 'TWOT - 2081a', 'kes-ee-taw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from an unused root (probably meaning to weigh out); an ingot (as definitely estimated and stamped for a coin):--piece of money (silver).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a unit of unknown value<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps weight, money</OL></OL>'),
(7193, 'tXqXq', 'by reduplication from an unused root meaning to shale off as bark', 'qasqeseth', 'TWOT - 2082a', 'kas-keh\'-seth', 'Noun Feminine', 'by reduplication from an unused root meaning to shale off as bark; a scale (of a fish); hence a coat of mail (as composed of or covered with jointed plates of metal):--mail, scale.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>scale (of fish, water animals)</OL>'),
(7194, 'rXq', 'a primitive root: to tie, physically (gird, confine, compact) or mentally (in love, league)', 'qashar', 'TWOT - 2090', 'kaw-shar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root: to tie, physically (gird, confine, compact) or mentally (in love, league):--bind (up), (make a) conspire(-acy, -ator), join together, knit, stronger, work (treason).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bind, tie, bind together, league together, conspire<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bind, confine<LI>to league together, conspire</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be bound, be bound up<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bind on<LI>to bind fast<LI>to bind, tie<LI>to bind to oneself</OL><LI>(Pual) robust, vigorous (participle)<LI>(Hithpael) to conspire</OL></OL>'),
(7195, 'rXq', 'from (07194)', 'qesher', 'TWOT - 2090a', 'keh\'-sher', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07194»; an (unlawful) alliance:--confederacy, conspiracy, treason.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>conspiracy, treason, (unlawful) alliance</OL>'),
(7196, 'rXXq', 'from (07194)', 'qishshur', 'TWOT - 2090b', 'kish-shoor\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07194»; an (ornamental) girdle (for women):--attire, headband.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bands, sashes, headbands<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>ornaments that are bound on</OL></OL>'),
(7197, 'XXq', 'a primitive root', 'qashash', 'TWOT - 2091,2092', 'kaw-shash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to become sapless through drought; used only as denominative from «07179»; to forage for straw, stubble or wood; figuratively, to assemble:--gather (selves) (together).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to gather, assemble, collect, gather stubble or sticks<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to gather together<LI>(Poel) to gather stubble<LI>(Hithpoel) to gather oneself together</OL></OL>'),
(7198, 'tXq', 'from (07185) in the original sense of (06983) of bending', 'qesheth', 'TWOT - 2093', 'keh\'-sheth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07185» in the original sense (of «06983») of bending: a bow, for shooting (hence, figuratively, strength) or the iris:--X  arch(-er), + arrow, bow((-man, -shot)).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bow<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>bow (for hunting, battle)<LI>bowmen, archers<LI>bow (fig. of might)<LI>rainbow</OL></OL>'),
(7199, 'tXXq', 'intensive (as denominative) from (07198)', 'qashshath', 'TWOT - 2094', 'kash-shawth\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'intensive (as denominative) from «07198»; a bowman:--X archer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bowman, archer</OL>'),
(7200, 'har', 'a primitive root', 'ra\'ah', 'TWOT - 2095', 'raw-aw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to see, literally or figuratively (in numerous applications, direct and implied, transitive, intransitive and causative):--advise self, appear, approve, behold, × certainly, consider, discern, (make to) enjoy, have experience, gaze, take heed, × indeed, × joyfully, lo, look (on, one another, one on another, one upon another, out, up, upon), mark, meet, × be near, perceive, present, provide, regard, (have) respect, (fore-, cause to, let) see(-r, -m, one another), shew (self), × sight of others, (e-)spy, stare, ×  surely, × think, view, visions.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to see, look at, inspect, perceive, consider<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to see<LI>to see, perceive<LI>to see, have vision<LI>to look at, see, regard, look after, see after, learn about, observe, watch, look upon, look out, find out<LI>to see, observe, consider, look at, give attention to, discern, distinguish<LI>to look at, gaze at</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to appear, present oneself<LI>to be seen<LI>to be visible</OL><LI>(Pual) to be seen<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to see, show<LI>to cause to look intently at, behold, cause to gaze at</OL><LI>(Hophal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be caused to see, be shown<LI>to be exhibited to</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to look at each other, face</OL></OL>'),
(7201, 'har', 'from (07200)', 'ra\'ah', 'TWOT - 394a', 'raw-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07200»; a bird of prey (probably the vulture, from its sharp sight):--glede. Compare «01676».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bird of prey<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps kite or hawk</OL></OL>'),
(7202, 'har', 'from (07200)', 'ra\'eh', 'TWOT - 2095a', 'raw-eh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «07200»; seeing, i.e. experiencing:--see.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) seeing</OL>'),
(7203, 'har', 'act part of (07200)', 'ro\'eh', 'TWOT - 2095b,2095c', 'ro-eh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'active participle of «07200»; a seer (as often rendered); but also (abstractly) a vision:--vision.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>seer, prophet<LI>(prophetic) vision</OL>'),
(7204, 'har', 'for (07203)', 'Ro\'eh', 'None', 'ro-ay\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'for «07203»; prophet; Roeh, an Israelite:--Haroeh (including the article).', 'Haroeh = \"vision\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a man of Judah</OL>'),
(7205, '!bwar', 'from the imperative of (07200) and (01121)', 'R\'uwben', 'None', 'reh-oo-bane\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the imperative of «07200» and «01121»; see ye a son; Reuben, a son of Jacob:--Reuben.', 'Reuben = \"behold a son\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the eldest son of Jacob by Leah<LI>the tribe descended from Reuben<LI>the territory inhabited by the tribe of Reuben</OL>'),
(7206, 'ynbwar', 'patronymic from (07205)', 'R\'uwbeniy', 'None', 'reh-oob-ay-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymic from «07205»; a Reubenite or descendant of Reuben:--children of Reuben, Reubenites.', 'Reubenite = see Reuben \"behold a son\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Reuben the son of Jacob</OL>'),
(7207, 'hwar', 'from (07200)', 'ra\'avah', 'TWOT - 2095', 'rah-av-aw\'', 'Verb', 'from «07200»; sight, i.e. satisfaction:--behold.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to behold</OL>'),
(7208, 'hmwar', 'pass part of (07213)', 'R\'uwmah', 'None', 'reh-oo-maw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'feminine passive participle of «07213»; raised; Reumah, a Syrian woman:--Reumah.', 'Reumah = \"elevated\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the concubine of Nahor, the brother of Abraham</OL>'),
(7209, 'yar', 'from (07200)', 'r\'iy', 'TWOT - 2095e', 'reh-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07200»; a mirror (as seen):--looking glass.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mirror</OL>'),
(7210, 'yar', 'from (07200)', 'ro\'iy', 'TWOT - 2095f', 'ro-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07200»; sight, whether abstractly (vision) or concretely (a spectacle):--gazingstock, look to, (that) see(-th).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>looking, appearance, seeing, sight<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>seeing<LI>appearance<LI>sight, spectacle</OL></OL>'),
(7211, 'hyar', 'from (07200) and (03050)', 'R\'ayah', 'None', 'reh-aw-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07200» and «03050»; Jah has seen; Reajah, the name of three Israelites:--Reaia, Reaiah.', 'Reaia or Reaiah = \"Jehovah has seen\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Shobal the son of Judah<LI>a Reubenite, son of Micah and father of Baal<LI>a progenitor of a family of temple slaves who returned from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(7212, 'tyar', 'from (07200)', 'r\'iyth', 'TWOT - 2095d', 'reh-eeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07200»; sight:--beholding.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) look</OL>'),
(7213, '~ar', 'a primitive root', 'ra\'am', 'TWOT - 2096', 'raw-am\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to rise:--be lifted up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to rise</OL>'),
(7214, '~ar', 'from (07213)', 'r\'em', 'TWOT - 2096a', 'reh-ame\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or rieym {reh-ame\'}; or reym {rame}; or rem {rame}; from «07213»; a wild bull (from its conspicuousness):--unicorn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>probably the great aurochs or wild bulls which are now extinct. The exact meaning is not known.</OL>'),
(7215, 'hmar', 'from (07213)', 'ra\'mah', 'TWOT - 2096b', 'raw-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07213»; something high in value, i.e. perhaps coral:--coral.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>corals</OL>'),
(7216, 'twmar', 'pl. of (07215)', 'Ra\'mowth', 'None', 'raw-moth\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Ramoth {raw-moth\'}; plural of «07215»; heights; Ramoth, the name of two places in Palestine:--Ramoth.', 'Ramoth = \"heights\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in Gilead; site dubious<LI>a Levitical city in Issachar</OL>'),
(7217, 'Xar', 'corresponding to (07218)', 're\'sh', 'TWOT - 2983', 'raysh', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07218»; the head; figuratively, the sum:--chief, head, sum.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chief, head<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>head (of man)<LI>head (as seat of visions)<LI>chief<LI>sum (essential content)</OL></OL>'),
(7218, 'Xar', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to shake', 'ro\'sh', 'TWOT - 2097', 'roshe', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to shake; the head (as most easily shaken), whether literal or figurative (in many applications, of place, time, rank, itc.):--band, beginning, captain, chapiter, chief(-est place, man, things), company, end, × every (man), excellent, first, forefront, ((be-))head, height, (on) high(-est part, (priest)), × lead, × poor, principal, ruler, sum, top.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head, top, summit, upper part, chief, total, sum, height, front, beginning<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>head (of man, animals)<LI>top, tip (of mountain)<LI>height (of stars)<LI>chief, head (of man, city, nation, place, family, priest)<LI>head, front, beginning<LI>chief, choicest, best<LI>head, division, company, band<LI>sum</OL></OL>'),
(7219, 'Xar', 'apparently the same as (07218)', 'ro\'sh', 'TWOT - 2098', 'roshe', 'Noun Masculine', 'or rowsh (Deut. 32:32) {roshe}; apparently the same as «07218»; a poisonous plant, probably the poppy (from its conspicuous head); generally poison (even of serpents):--gall, hemlock, poison, venom.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gall, venom, bitter, poisonous</OL>'),
(7220, 'Xar', 'probably the same as (07218)', 'Ro\'sh', 'None', 'roshe', '', 'probably the same as «07218»; Rosh, the name of an Israelite and of a foreign nation:--Rosh.', 'Rosh = \"head\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Benjamin</OL>'),
(7221, 'hXar', 'from the same as (07218)', 'ri\'shah', 'TWOT - 2097a', 'ree-shaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «07218»; a beginning:--beginning.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>beginning time, early time</OL>'),
(7222, 'hXar', 'from (07218)', 'ro\'shah', 'TWOT - 2097b', 'ro-shaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «07218»; the head:--head(-stone).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>top, topmost</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(7223, '!wXar', 'from (07221)', 'ri\'shown', 'TWOT - 2097c', 'ree-shone\'', '', 'or riishon {ree-shone\'}; from «07221»; first, in place, time or rank (as adjective or noun):--ancestor, (that were) before(-time), beginning, eldest, first, fore(-father) (-most), former (thing), of old time, past.', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>first, primary, former<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>former (of time)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ancestors<LI>former things</OL><LI>foremost (of location)<LI>first (in time)<LI>first, chief (in degree) adv</OL><LI>first, before, formerly, at first</OL>'),
(7224, 'ynXar', 'from (07223)', 'ri\'shoniy', 'TWOT - 2097d', 'ree-sho-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'from «07223»; first:--first.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>first</OL>'),
(7225, 'tyXar', 'from the same as (07218)', 're\'shiyth', 'TWOT - 2097e', 'ray-sheeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «07218»; the first, in place, time, order or rank (specifically, a firstfruit):--beginning, chief(-est), first(-fruits, part, time), principal thing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>first, beginning, best, chief<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>beginning<LI>first<LI>chief<LI>choice part</OL></OL>'),
(7226, 'tXar', 'from (07218)', 'ra\'ashoth', 'TWOT - 2097f', 'rah-ash-oth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07218»; a pillow (being for the head):--bolster.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>head place, place at the head</OL>'),
(7227, 'br', 'contracted from (07231)', 'rab', 'TWOT - 2099a,2099b', 'rab', '', 'by contracted from «07231»; abundant (in quantity, size, age, number, rank, quality):--(in) abound(-undance, -ant, -antly), captain, elder, enough, exceedingly, full, great(-ly, man, one), increase, long (enough, (time)), (do, have) many(-ifold, things, a time), ((ship-))master, mighty, more, (too, very) much, multiply(-tude), officer, often(-times), plenteous, populous, prince, process (of time), suffice(-lent).', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>much, many, great<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>much<LI>many<LI>abounding in<LI>more numerous than<LI>abundant, enough<LI>great<LI>strong<LI>greater than adv<LI>much, exceedingly n m</OL><LI>captain, chief</OL>'),
(7228, 'br', 'by contraction from (07232)', 'rab', 'TWOT - 2100a', 'rab', 'Noun Masculine', 'by contraction from «07232»; an archer (or perhaps the same as «07227»):--archer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>archer</OL>'),
(7229, 'br', 'corresponding to (07227)', 'rab', 'TWOT - 2984a', 'rab', '', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07227»:--captain, chief, great, lord, master, stout.', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>great<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>great<LI>great (fig of power) n</OL><LI>captain, chief</OL>'),
