(7270, 'lgr', 'a primitive root', 'ragal', 'TWOT - 2113', 'raw-gal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to walk along; but only in specifically, applications, to reconnoiter, to be a tale-bearer (i.e. slander); also (as denominative from «07272») to lead about:--backbite, search, slander, (e-)spy (out), teach to go, view.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go on foot, spy out, foot it, go about, walk along, move the feet<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be a tale-bearer, slander, go about<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to slander<LI>to go about as explorer, spy</OL><LI>(Tiphel) to teach to walk</OL></OL>'),
