(7292, 'bhr', 'a primitive root', 'rahab', 'TWOT - 2125', 'raw-hab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to urge severely, i.e. (figuratively) importune, embolden, capture, act insolently:--overcome, behave self proudly, make sure, strengthen.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to behave proudly, act stormily or boisterously or arrogantly<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to act insolently, storm against, beset, importune<LI>(Hiphil) to disturb, alarm, awe, confuse, make bold or proud</OL></OL>'),
