(7298, 'thr', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to hollow out', 'rahat', 'TWOT - 2127a,2128a', 'rah\'-hat', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to hollow out; a channel or watering-box; by resemblance a ringlet of hair (as forming parallel lines):--gallery, gutter, trough.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>trough, hollow<LI>lock of hair<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(7299, 'wr', 'from a root corresponding to (07200)', 'rev', 'TWOT - 2990', 'rave', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «07200»; aspect:--form.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>appearance</OL>'),
(7300, 'dwr', 'a primitive root', 'ruwd', 'TWOT - 2129', 'rood', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to tramp about, i.e. ramble (free or disconsolate):--have the dominion, be lord, mourn, rule.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wander restlessly, roam<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to roam<LI>(Hiphil) to be restless, show restlessness</OL></OL>'),
(7301, 'hwr', 'a primitive root', 'ravah', 'TWOT - 2130', 'raw-vaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to slake the thirst (occasionally of other appetites):--bathe, make drunk, (take the) fill, satiate, (abundantly) satisfy, soak, water (abundantly).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be satiated or saturated, have or drink one\'s fill<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to take one\'s fill<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be drunk, be intoxicated<LI>to drench, water abundantly, saturate</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to saturate, water, cause to drink</OL></OL>'),
(7302, 'hwr', 'from (07301)', 'raveh', 'TWOT - 2130b', 'raw-veh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «07301»; sated (with drink):--drunkenness, watered.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>watered, saturated</OL>'),
(7303, 'hghwr', 'from an unused root probably meaning to cry out', 'Rowhagah', 'None', 'ro-hag-aw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to cry out; outcry; Rohagah, an Israelite:--Rohgah.', 'Rohgah = \"clamour\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Asherite of the sons of Shamer</OL>'),
(7304, 'xwr', 'a primitive root [identical with (07306)]', 'ravach', 'TWOT - 2132', 'raw-vakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «07306»); properly, to breathe freely, i.e. revive; by implication, to have ample room:--be refreshed, large.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be wide, be spacious, breathe<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to breathe easily, be relieved<LI>(Pual) spacious (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(7305, 'xwr', 'from (07304)', 'revach', 'TWOT - 2132a', 'reh\'-vakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07304»; room, literally (an interval) or figuratively (deliverance):--enlargement, space.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>space<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>space, interval<LI>respite, relief</OL></OL>'),
(7306, 'xwr', 'a primitive root', 'ruwach', 'TWOT - 2131', 'roo\'-akh', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to blow, i.e. breathe; only (literally) to smell or (by implication, perceive (figuratively, to anticipate, enjoy):--accept, smell, ×  touch, make of quick understanding.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to smell, scent, perceive odour, accept<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of horse<LI>of delight (metaph)</OL></OL>'),
(7307, 'xwr', 'from (07306)', 'ruwach', 'TWOT - 2131a', 'roo\'-akh', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07306»; wind; by resemblance breath, i.e. a sensible (or even violent) exhalation; figuratively, life, anger, unsubstantiality; by extension, a region of the sky; by resemblance spirit, but only of a rational being (including its expression and functions):--air, anger, blast, breath, ×  cool, courage, mind, × quarter, × side, spirit((-ual)), tempest, × vain, ((whirl-))wind(-y).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wind, breath, mind, spirit<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>breath<LI>wind<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of heaven<LI>quarter (of wind), side<LI>breath of air<LI>air, gas<LI>vain, empty thing</OL><LI>spirit (as that which breathes quickly in animation or agitation)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spirit, animation, vivacity, vigour<LI>courage<LI>temper, anger<LI>impatience, patience<LI>spirit, disposition (as troubled, bitter, discontented)<LI>disposition (of various kinds), unaccountable or uncontrollable impulse<LI>prophetic spirit</OL><LI>spirit (of the living, breathing being in man and animals)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>as gift, preserved by God, God\'s spirit, departing at death, disembodied being</OL><LI>spirit (as seat of emotion)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>desire<LI>sorrow, trouble</OL><LI>spirit<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>as seat or organ of mental acts<LI>rarely of the will<LI>as seat especially of moral character</OL><LI>Spirit of God, the third person of the triune God, the Holy Spirit, coequal, coeternal with the Father and the Son<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>as inspiring ecstatic state of prophecy<LI>as impelling prophet to utter instruction or warning<LI>imparting warlike energy and executive and administrative power<LI>as endowing men with various gifts<LI>as energy of life<LI>as manifest in the Shekinah glory<LI>never referred to as a depersonalised force</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7308, 'xwr', 'corresponding to (07307)', 'ruwach', 'TWOT - 2991a', 'roo\'-akh', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07307»:--mind, spirit, wind.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spirit, wind<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>wind<LI>spirit<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of man<LI>seat of the mind</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7309, 'hxwr', 'from (07305)', 'rvachah', 'TWOT - 2132b', 'rev-aw-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «07305»; relief:--breathing, respite.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>respite, relief</OL>'),
(7310, 'hywr', 'from (07301)', 'rvayah', 'TWOT - 2130c', 'rev-aw-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07301»; satisfaction:--runneth over, wealthy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>saturation</OL>'),
(7311, '~wr', 'a primitive root', 'ruwm', 'TWOT - 2133', 'room', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be high actively, to rise or raise (in various applications, literally or figuratively):--bring up, exalt (self), extol, give, go up, haughty, heave (up), (be, lift up on, make on, set up on, too) high(-er, one), hold up, levy, lift(-er) up, (be) lofty, (X a-)loud, mount up, offer (up), + presumptuously, (be) promote(-ion), proud, set up, tall(-er), take (away, off, up), breed worms.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rise, rise up, be high, be lofty, be exalted<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be high, be set on high<LI>to be raised, be uplifted, be exalted<LI>to be lifted, rise</OL><LI>(Polel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to raise or rear (children), cause to grow up<LI>to lift up, raise, exalt<LI>to exalt, extol</OL><LI>(Polal) to be lifted up<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to raise, lift, lift up, take up, set up, erect, exalt, set on high<LI>to lift up (and take away), remove<LI>to lift off and present, contribute, offer, contribute</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be taken off, be abolished<LI>(Hithpolel) to exalt oneself, magnify oneself</OL><LI>(Qal) to be rotten, be wormy</OL>'),
(7312, '~wr', 'from (07311)', 'ruwm', 'TWOT - 2133a', 'room', 'Noun Masculine', 'or rum {room}; from «07311»; (literally) elevation or (figuratively) elation:--haughtiness, height, × high.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>haughtiness, height, elevation<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>height, loftiness<LI>haughtiness</OL></OL>'),
(7313, '~wr', 'corresponding to (07311)', 'ruwm', 'TWOT - 2992', 'room', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07311»; (figuratively only):-- extol, lift up (self), set up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rise<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to be lifted up<LI>(Aphel) to exalt<LI>(Hithpolel) to lift oneself up</OL></OL>'),
(7314, '~wr', 'from (07313)', 'ruwm', 'TWOT - 2992a', 'room', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «07313»; (literally) altitude:--height.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>height</OL>'),
(7315, '~wr', 'from (07311)', 'rowm', 'TWOT - 2133b', 'rome', 'Adverb', 'from «07311»; elevation, i.e. (adverbially) aloft:--on high.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>on high, upwards</OL>'),
(7316, 'hmwr', 'from (07311)', 'Ruwmah', 'None', 'roo-maw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «07311»; height; Rumah, a place in Palestine:--Rumah.', 'Rumah = \"height\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>home of the grandfather of king Jehoiakim of Judah</OL>'),
(7317, 'hmwr', 'fem. of (07315)', 'rowmah', 'TWOT - 2133c', 'ro-maw\'', 'Adjective', 'feminine of «07315»; elation, i.e. (adverbially) proudly:--haughtily.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>proudly, haughtily</OL>'),
(7318, '~mwr', 'from (07426)', 'rowmam', 'TWOT - 2133f', 'ro-mawm\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07426»; exaltation, i.e. (figuratively and specifically) praise:--be extolled.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Polal) praise, exaltation, extolling</OL>'),
(7319, 'hmmwr', 'act part of (07426)', 'rowmmah', 'TWOT - 2133f?', 'ro-mem-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine active participle of «07426»; exaltation, i.e. praise:--high.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>uplifting, arising</OL>'),
(7320, 'rz[ ytmmwr', 'from (07311) and (05828)', 'Rowmamtiy', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Masculine', '(or Romam from «07311» and «05828»; I have raised up a help; Romamti-Ezer, an Israelite:--Romamti- ezer.', 'Romamti-ezer = \"I have exalted the Helper\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 14 sons of Heman</OL>'),
(7321, '[wr', 'a primitive root', 'ruwa`', 'TWOT - 2135', 'roo-ah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to mar (especially by breaking); figuratively, to split the ears (with sound), i.e. shout (for alarm or joy):--blow an alarm, cry (alarm, aloud, out), destroy, make a joyful noise, smart, shout (for joy), sound an alarm, triumph.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shout, raise a sound, cry out, give a blast<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shout a war-cry or alarm of battle<LI>to sound a signal for war or march<LI>to shout in triumph (over enemies)<LI>to shout in applause<LI>to shout (with religious impulse)<LI>to cry out in distress</OL><LI>(Polal) to utter a shout<LI>(Hithpolel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shout in triumph<LI>to shout for joy</OL></OL><LI>(Niphal) destroyed</OL>'),
(7322, '@wr', 'a primitive root', 'ruwph', 'TWOT - 2201', 'roof', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to triturate (in a mortar), i.e. (figuratively) to agitate (by concussion):--tremble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Polel) to shake, rock</OL>'),
(7323, '#wr', 'a primitive root', 'ruwts', 'TWOT - 2137', 'roots', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to run (for whatever reason, especially to rush):--break down, divide speedily, footman, guard, bring hastily, (make) run (away, through), post.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to run<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to run<LI>runners (participle as subst)</OL><LI>(Polel) to run swiftly, dart<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bring or move quickly, hurry<LI>to drive away from, cause to run away</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7324, 'qwr', 'a primitive root', 'ruwq', 'TWOT - 2161', 'rook', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pour out (literally or figuratively), i.e. empty:--X arm, cast out, draw (out), (make) empty, pour forth (out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make empty, empty out<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to empty, keep empty or hungry<LI>to pour out or down<LI>to empty out</OL><LI>(Hophal) to be emptied out</OL></OL>'),
(7325, 'rwr', 'a primitive root', 'ruwr', 'TWOT - 2162', 'roor', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to slaver (with spittle), i.e. (by analogy) to emit a fluid (ulcerous or natural):--run.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to flow</OL>'),
(7326, 'Xwr', 'a primitive root', 'ruwsh', 'TWOT - 2138', 'roosh', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be destitute:--lack, needy, (make self) poor (man).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be poor, be in want, lack<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be poor<LI>to be in want or hunger<LI>poor man (subst)</OL><LI>(Hithpolel) one impoverishing himself (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(7327, 'twr', 'probably for (07468)', 'Ruwth', 'None', 'rooth', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'probably for «07468»; friend; Ruth, a Moabitess:--Ruth.', 'Ruth = \"friendship\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>daughter-in-law of Naomi, wife of Boaz, and grandmother of David</OL>'),
