(7486, 'oom[r', 'of Egyptian origin', 'Ra`mcec', 'None', 'rah-mes-ace\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Raamcec {rah-am-sace\'}; of Egyptian origin; Rameses or Raamses, a place in Egypt:--Raamses, Rameses.', 'Raamses or Rameses = \"child of the sun\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in lower Egypt built by Hebrew slaves; probably in Goshen</OL>'),
(7487, '!n[r', 'corresponding to (07488)', 'ra`anan', 'TWOT - 2999', 'rah-aw-nan\'', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07488»; green, i.e. (figuratively) prosperous; --flourishing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flourishing</OL>'),
(7488, '!n[r', 'from an unused root meaning to be green', 'ra`anan', 'TWOT - 2190a', 'rah-an-awn\'', '', 'from an unused root meaning to be green; verdant; by analogy, new; figuratively, prosperous:--green, flourishing.', 'v<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Palel) to be or grow luxuriant or fresh or green adj<LI>luxuriant, fresh</OL>'),
(7489, '[[r', 'a primitive root', 'ra`a`', 'TWOT - 2191,2192', 'raw-ah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to spoil (literally, by breaking to pieces); figuratively, to make (or be) good for nothing, i.e. bad (physically, socially or morally):--afflict, associate selves (by mistake for «07462»), break (down, in pieces), + displease, (be, bring, do) evil (doer, entreat, man), show self  friendly (by mistake for «07462»), do harm, (do) hurt, (behave self, deal) ill, × indeed, do mischief, punish, still, vex, (do) wicked (doer, -ly), be (deal, do) worse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be bad, be evil<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be displeasing<LI>to be sad<LI>to be injurious, be evil<LI>to be wicked, be evil (ethically)</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to do an injury or hurt<LI>to do evil or wickedly<LI>mischief (participle)</OL></OL><LI>to break, shatter<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to break<LI>broken (participle)<LI>to be broken</OL><LI>(Hithpolel) to be broken, be broken in pieces, be broken asunder</OL></OL>'),
(7490, '[[r', 'corresponding to (07489)', 'r`a`', 'TWOT - 3000', 'reh-ah\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07489»:--break, bruise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to crush, break, shatter</OL>'),
(7491, '@[r', 'a primitive root', 'ra`aph', 'TWOT - 2193', 'raw-af\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to drip:--distil, drop (down).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to trickle, drip<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to trickle, drip<LI>(Hiphil) to trickle</OL></OL>'),
(7492, '#[r', 'a primitive root', 'ra`ats', 'TWOT - 2194', 'raw-ats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to break in pieces; figuratively, harass:--dash in pieces, vex.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to shatter</OL>'),
(7493, 'X[r', 'a primitive root', 'ra`ash', 'TWOT - 2195', 'raw-ash', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to undulate (as the earth, the sky, etc.; also a field of grain), partic. through fear; specifically, to spring (as a locust):--make afraid, (re-)move, quake, (make to) shake, (make to) tremble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to quake, shake<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to quake, shake<LI>(Niphal) to be made to quake<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to quake<LI>to cause to spring or leap (of horse)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7494, 'X[r', 'from (07493)', 'ra`ash', 'TWOT - 2195a', 'rah\'-ash', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07493»; vibration, bounding, uproar:--commotion, confused noise, earthquake, fierceness, quaking, rattling, rushing, shaking.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>quaking, rattling, shaking<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>earthquake<LI>quaking, trembling (of person)<LI>shaking, quivering (of dart)</OL></OL>'),
(7495, 'apr', 'a primitive root', 'rapha\'', 'TWOT - 2196', 'raw-faw\'', 'Verb', 'or raphah {raw-faw\'}; a primitive root; properly, to mend (by stitching), i.e. (figuratively) to cure:--cure, (cause to) heal, physician, repair, × thoroughly, make whole.  See «07503».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to heal, make healthful<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to heal<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of God<LI>healer, physician (of men)<LI>of hurts of nations involving restored favour (fig)<LI>of individual distresses (fig)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be healed<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>literal (of persons)<LI>of water, pottery<LI>of national hurts (fig)<LI>of personal distress (fig)</OL><LI>(Piel) to heal<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>literal<LI>of national defects or hurts (fig)</OL><LI>(Hithpael) in order to get healed (infinitive)</OL></OL>'),
(7496, 'apr', 'from (07495) in the sense of (07503)', 'rapha\'', 'TWOT - 2198c', 'raw-faw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07495» in the sense of «07503»; properly, lax, i.e. (figuratively) a ghost (as dead; in plural only):--dead, deceased.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ghosts of the dead, shades, spirits</OL>'),
(7497, 'apr', 'from (07495) in the sense of invigorating', 'rapha\'', 'TWOT - 2198d', 'raw-faw\'', 'Proper Name', 'or raphah {raw-faw\'}; from «07495» in the sense of invigorating; a giant:--giant, Rapha, Rephaim(-s). See also «01051».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>giants, Rephaim<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>old tribe of giants</OL></OL>'),
(7498, 'apr', 'probably the same as (07497)', 'Rapha\'', 'None', 'raw-faw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Raphah {raw-faw\'}; probably the same as «07497»; giant; Rapha or Raphah, the name of two Israelites:--Rapha.', 'Rapha = \"tall\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Binea and a descendant of Saul<LI>son of Benjamin</OL>'),
(7499, 'hapr', 'pass part of (07495)', 'rphu\'ah', 'TWOT - 2196a', 'ref-oo-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine passive participle of «07495»; a medicament:--heal(-ed), medicine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>remedy, medicine</OL>'),
(7500, 'twapr', 'from (07495)', 'riph\'uwth', 'TWOT - 2196b', 'rif-ooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07495»; a cure:--health.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>healing</OL>'),
(7501, 'lapr', 'from (07495) and (0410)', 'Rpha\'el', 'None', 'ref-aw-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07495» and «0410»; God has cured; Rephael, an Israelite:--Rephael.', 'Rephael = \"healed of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Shemaiah and grandson of Obed-edom</OL>'),
(7502, 'dpr', 'a primitive root', 'raphad', 'TWOT - 2197', 'raw-fad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to spread (a bed); by implication, to refresh:--comfort, make (a bed), spread.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to spread<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to spread<LI>(Piel) to spread out, support</OL></OL>'),
(7503, 'hpr', 'a primitive root', 'raphah', 'TWOT - 2198', 'raw-faw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to slacken (in many applications, literal or figurative):--abate, cease, consume, draw (toward evening), fail, (be) faint, be (wax) feeble, forsake, idle, leave, let alone (go, down), (be) slack, stay, be still, be slothful, (be) weak(-en). See «07495».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sink, relax, sink down, let drop, be disheartened<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sink down<LI>to sink, drop<LI>to sink, relax, abate<LI>to relax, withdraw</OL><LI>(Niphal) idle (participle)<LI>(Piel) to let drop<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to let drop, abandon, relax, refrain, forsake<LI>to let go<LI>to refrain, let alone<LI>to be quiet</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to show oneself slack</OL></OL>'),
(7504, 'hpr', 'from (07503)', 'rapheh', 'TWOT - 2198a', 'raw-feh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «07503»; slack (in body or mind):--weak. raphah, Raphah. See «07497», «07498». riphah. See «07383».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>slack</OL>'),
(7505, 'awpr', 'pass part of (07495)', 'Raphuw\'', 'None', 'raw-foo\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'passive participle of «07495»; cured; Raphu, an Israelite:--Raphu.', 'Raphu = \"healed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Palti, the spy from the tribe of Benjamin</OL>'),
(7506, 'xpr', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to sustain', 'Rephach', 'None', 'reh\'-fakh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to sustain; support; Rephach, an Israelite:--Rephah.', 'Rephah = \"healing of the breath\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Ephraim and a ancestor of Joshua</OL>'),
(7507, 'hdypr', 'from (07502)', 'rphiydah', 'TWOT - 2197a', 'ref-ee-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07502»; a railing (as spread along):--bottom.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>support</OL>'),
(7508, '~ydypr', 'from the same as (07507)', 'Rphiydiym', 'None', 'ref-ee-deem\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'plural of the masculine of the same as «07507»; ballusters; Rephidim, a place in the Desert:--Rephidim.', 'Rephidim = \"rests\" or \"stays\" or \"resting places\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a station of Israel in the wilderness between Egypt and Sinai</OL>'),
(7509, 'hypr', 'from (07495) and (03050)', 'Rphayah', 'None', 'ref-aw-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07495» and «03050»; Jah has cured; Rephajah, the name of five Israelites:--Rephaiah.', 'Rephaiah = \"healed of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Zerubbabel and David<LI>a Simeonite chief in the reign of Hezekiah<LI>son of Tola and grandson of Issachar<LI>son of Binea and a descendant of Saul<LI>son of Hur and a ruler of Jerusalem in the time of Nehemiah</OL>'),
(7510, '!wypr', 'from (07503)', 'riphyown', 'TWOT - 2198b', 'rif-yone\'', '', 'from «07503»; slackness:--feebleness.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sinking</OL>'),
(7511, 'opr', 'a primitive root', 'raphac', 'TWOT - 2199', 'raw-fas\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to trample, i.e. prostrate:--humble self, submit self.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"c\"><OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to stamp oneself down, humble oneself<LI>stamping or tramping down (participle)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7512, 'opr', 'corresponding to (07511)', 'rphac', 'TWOT - 3001', 'ref-as\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07511»:--stamp.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tread, trample<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) treading, trampling (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(7513, 'hdopr', 'from (07511)', 'raphcodah', 'TWOT - 2200', 'raf-so-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07511»; a raft (as flat on the water):--flote.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>raft</OL>'),
(7514, 'qpr', 'a primitive root', 'raphaq', 'TWOT - 2202', 'raw-fak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to recline:--lean.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to support<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hithpael) to support oneself, lean</OL></OL>'),
(7515, 'Xpr', 'a primitive root', 'raphas', 'TWOT - 2199', 'raw-fas\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to trample, i.e. roil water:--foul, trouble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to stamp, tread, foul by stamping or treading<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to tread down, foul by treading, foul with the feet<LI>(Niphal) to be fouled</OL></OL>'),
(7516, 'Xpr', 'from (07515)', 'rephesh', 'TWOT - 2203a', 'reh\'-fesh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07515»; mud (as roiled):--mire.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mire, mud</OL>'),
(7517, 'tpr', 'probably from (07503)', 'repheth', 'TWOT - 2204', 'reh\'-feth', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from «07503»; a stall for cattle (from their resting there):--stall.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stable, stall</OL>'),
(7518, '#r', 'contracted from (07533)', 'rats', 'TWOT - 2212a', 'rats', 'Noun Masculine', 'contracted from «07533»; a fragment:--piece.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>piece, bar<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(7519, 'acr', 'a primitive root', 'ratsa\'', 'TWOT - 2205', 'raw-tsaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to run; also to delight in:--accept, run.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to run</OL>'),
(7520, 'dcr', 'a primitive root', 'ratsad', 'TWOT - 2206', 'raw-tsad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; probably to look askant, i.e. (figuratively) be jealous:--leap.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to watch stealthily or with envious hostility, watch with enmity, watch with envy</OL>'),
(7521, 'hcr', 'a primitive root', 'ratsah', 'TWOT - 2207', 'raw-tsaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be pleased with; specifically, to satisfy a debt:--(be) accept(-able), accomplish, set affection, approve, consent with, delight (self), enjoy, (be, have a) favour(-able), like, observe, pardon, (be, have, take) please(-ure), reconcile self.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be pleased with, be favourable to, accept favourably<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be pleased with, be favourable to<LI>to accept<LI>to be pleased, be determined<LI>to make acceptable, satisfy<LI>to please</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be accepted, be pleased with<LI>(Piel) to seek favour of<LI>(Hiphil) to please, pay off<LI>(Hithpael) to make oneself acceptable or pleasing</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(7522, '!wcr', 'from (07521)', 'ratsown', 'TWOT - 2207a', 'raw-tsone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or ratson {raw-tsone\'}; from «07521»; delight (especially as shown):--(be) acceptable(-ance, -ed), delight, desire, favour, (good) pleasure, (own, self, voluntary) will, as...(what) would.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pleasure, delight, favour, goodwill, acceptance, will<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>goodwill, favour<LI>acceptance<LI>will, desire, pleasure, self-will</OL></OL>'),
(7523, 'xcr', 'a primitive root', 'ratsach', 'TWOT - 2208', 'raw-tsakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to dash in pieces, i.e. kill (a human being), especially to murder:--put to death, kill, (man-)slay(-er), murder(-er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to murder, slay, kill<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to murder, slay<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>premeditated<LI>accidental<LI>as avenger<LI>slayer (intentional) (participle)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be slain<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to murder, assassinate<LI>murderer, assassin (participle)(subst)</OL><LI>(Pual) to be killed</OL></OL>'),
(7524, 'xcr', 'from (07523)', 'retsach', 'TWOT - 2208a', 'reh-tsakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07523»; a crushing; specifically, a murder-cry:--slaughter, sword.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shattering</OL>'),
(7525, 'aycr', 'from (07521)', 'Ritsya\'', 'None', 'rits-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07521»; delight; Ritsjah, an Israelite:--Rezia.', 'Rezia = \"delight\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Asherite of the sons of Ulla</OL>'),
(7526, '!ycr', 'probably for (07522)', 'Rtsiyn', 'None', 'rets-een\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably for «07522»; Retsin, the name of a Syrian and of an Israelite:--Rezin.', 'Rezin = \"firm\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>king of Damascus during the reigns of kings Jotham and Ahaz of Judah<LI>the progenitor of a family of temple slaves who returned from captivity with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(7527, '[cr', 'a primitive root', 'ratsa`', 'TWOT - 2209', 'raw-tsah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pierce:--bore.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to bore, pierce<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the ear</OL></OL>'),
(7528, '@cr', 'a denominative from (07529)', 'ratsaph', 'TWOT - 2210', 'raw-tsaf\'', 'Verb', 'a denominative from «07529»; to tessellate, i.e. embroider (as if with bright stones):--pave.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fit together, fit out, pattern<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be fitted out, design</OL></OL>'),
(7529, '@cr', 'for (07565)', 'retseph', 'TWOT - 2223a', 'reh\'-tsef', 'Noun Masculine', 'for «07565»; a red-hot stone (for baking):--coal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hot stone, glowing stone or coal, flame, firebolt, spark</OL>'),
(7530, '@cr', 'the same as (07529)', 'Retseph', 'None', 'reh\'-tsef', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «07529»; Retseph, a place in Assyrian:--Rezeph.', 'Rezeph = \"a hot stone\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place conquered by Assyria</OL>'),
(7531, 'hpcr', 'from (07529)', 'ritspah', 'TWOT - 2210a,2211a', 'rits-paw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «07529»; a hot stone; also a tessellated pavement:--live coal, pavement.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pavement<LI>glowing stone or coal, live coal</OL>'),
(7532, 'hpcr', 'the same as (07531)', 'Ritspah', 'None', 'rits-paw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'the same as «07531»; Ritspah, an Israelitess:--Rizpah.', 'Rizpah = \"pavement\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a concubine of king Saul and mother of Armoni and Mephibosheth</OL>'),
(7533, '#cr', 'a primitive root', 'ratsats', 'TWOT - 2212', 'raw-tsats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to crack in pieces, literally or figuratively:--break, bruise, crush, discourage, oppress, struggle together.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to crush, oppress<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to crush, get crushed, be crushed<LI>to crush, oppress (fig)<LI>crushed (participle passive)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be crushed, be broken<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to crush in pieces<LI>to grievously oppress (fig)</OL><LI>(Poel) to oppress (fig)<LI>(Hiphil) to crush<LI>(Hithpoel) to crush each other</OL></OL>'),
(7534, 'qr', 'from (07556) in its original sense', 'raq', 'TWOT - 2218a', 'rak', '', 'from «07556» in its original sense; emaciated (as if flattened out):--lean((-fleshed)), thin.', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thin, lean</OL>'),
(7535, 'qr', 'the same as (07534) as a noun', 'raq', 'TWOT - 2218a', 'rak', 'Adverb', 'the same as «07534» as a noun; properly, leanness, i.e. (figuratively) limitation; only adverbial, merely, or conjunctional, although:--but, even, except, howbeit howsoever, at the least, nevertheless, nothing but, notwithstanding, only, save, so (that), surely, yet (so), in any wise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>only, altogether, surely<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>only<LI>only, nought but, altogether (in limitation)<LI>save, except (after a negative)<LI>only, altogether, surely (with an affirmative)<LI>if only, provided only (prefixed for emphasis)<LI>only, exclusively (for emphasis)</OL></OL>'),
(7536, 'qr', 'from (07556)', 'roq', 'TWOT - 2219a', 'roke', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07556»; spittle:--spit(-ting, -tle).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spittle</OL>'),
(7537, 'bqr', 'a primitive root', 'raqab', 'TWOT - 2213', 'raw-kab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to decay (as by worm-eating):--rot.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to rot</OL>'),
(7538, 'bqr', 'from (07537)', 'raqab', 'TWOT - 2213a', 'raw-kawb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07537»; decay (by caries):--rottenness (thing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rottenness, decay (always fig)</OL>'),
(7539, '!wbqqr', 'from (07538)', 'riqqabown', 'TWOT - 2213b', 'rik-kaw-bone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07538»; decay (by caries):--rotten.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rottenness, decay, decayed</OL>'),
(7540, 'dqr', 'a primitive root', 'raqad', 'TWOT - 2214', 'raw-kad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to stamp, i.e. to spring about (wildly or for joy):--dance, jump, leap, skip.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to skip about<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to skip about<LI>(Piel) to dance, leap<LI>(Hiphil) to make to skip</OL></OL>'),
(7541, 'hqqr', 'from (07534)', 'raqqah', 'TWOT - 2218c', 'rak-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «07534»; properly, thinness, i.e. the side of the head:--temple.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>temple, the temple (of the head)</OL>'),
(7542, '!wqqr', 'from (07534)', 'Raqqown', 'None', 'rak-kone\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «07534»; thinness; Rakkon, a place in Palestine:--Rakkon.', 'Rakkon = \"the temple\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a well-watered place in Dan near Joppa</OL>'),
(7543, 'xqr', 'a primitive root', 'raqach', 'TWOT - 2215', 'raw-kakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to perfume:--apothecary, compound, make (ointment), prepare, spice.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to mix, compound<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to mix, compound<LI>compounder, mixer, perfumer (participle) (subst)</OL><LI>(Pual) mixed (participle)<LI>(Hiphil) to mix</OL></OL>'),
(7544, 'xqr', 'from (07543)', 'reqach', 'TWOT - 2215a', 'reh\'-kakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07543»; properly, perfumery, i.e. (by implication) spicery (for flavor):--spiced.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spice, spicery</OL>'),
(7545, 'xqr', 'from (07542)', 'roqach', 'TWOT - 2215b', 'ro\'-kakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07542»; an aromatic:--confection, ointment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spice-mixture, perfume, ointment</OL>'),
(7546, 'xqqr', 'from (07543)', 'raqqach', 'TWOT - 2215c', 'rak-kawkh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07543»; a male perfumer:--apothecary.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ointment-maker, perfumer</OL>'),
(7547, 'xqqr', 'from (07543)', 'raqquach', 'TWOT - 2215e', 'rak-koo\'-akh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07543»; a scented substance:--perfume.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>perfumery, perfume, unguent</OL>'),
(7548, 'hxqqr', 'from (07547)', 'raqqachah', 'TWOT - 2215d', 'rak-kaw-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «07547»; a female perfumer:--confectioner.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ointment-maker (female), perfumer (female)</OL>'),
(7549, '[yqr', 'from (07554)', 'raqiya`', 'TWOT - 2217a', 'raw-kee\'-ah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07554»; properly, an expanse, i.e. the firmament or (apparently) visible arch of the sky:--firmament.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>extended surface (solid), expanse, firmament<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>expanse (flat as base, support)<LI>firmament (of vault of heaven supporting waters above)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>considered by Hebrews as solid and supporting \'waters\' above</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7550, 'qyqr', 'from (07556) in its original sense', 'raqiyq', 'TWOT - 2218b', 'raw-keek\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from, «07556» in its original sense; a thin cake; -- cake, wafer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thin cake, wafer</OL>'),
(7551, '~qr', 'a primitive root', 'raqam', 'TWOT - 2216', 'raw-kam\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to variegate color, i.e. embroider; by implication, to fabricate:--embroiderer, needlework, curiously work.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to variegate, mix colours<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) variegator (worker in colours) (participle)<LI>(Pual) to be skilfully wrought or woven</OL></OL>'),
(7552, '~qr', 'from (07551)', 'Reqem', 'None', 'reh\'-kem', '', 'from «07551»; versi-color; Rekem, the name of a place in Palestine, also of a Midianite and an Israelite:--Rekem.', 'Rekem = \"variegation\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 5 kings of Midian killed by the Israelites<LI>one of the 4 sons of Hebron and the father of Shammai<LI>a Manassite, son of Machir by Maachah his wife n pr loc<LI>a town in Benjamin; site unknown</OL>'),
(7553, 'hmqr', 'from (07551)', 'riqmah', 'TWOT - 2216a', 'rik-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07551»; variegation of color; specifically, embroidery:--broidered (work), divers colours, (raiment of) needlework (on both sides).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>variegated stuff, embroidered</OL>'),
