(7681, 'agX', 'probably from (07686)', 'Shage\'', 'None', 'shaw-gay\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «07686»; erring; Shage, an Israelite:--Shage.', 'Shage = \"erring\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Hannathon the Hararite, one of David\'s mighty warriors</OL>'),
(7682, 'bgX', 'a primitive root', 'sagab', 'TWOT - 2234', 'saw-gab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) lofty, especially inaccessible; by implication, safe, strong; used literally and figuratively --defend, exalt, be excellent, (be, set on) high, lofty, be safe, set up (on high), be too strong.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be high, be inaccessibly high<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be (too) high (for capture)<LI>to be high (of prosperity)</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be high<LI>to be set on high, be (safely) set on high<LI>to be exalted (of God)</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to set on high, set (securely) on high<LI>to exalt, exalt (in effective hostility)</OL><LI>(Pual) to be set (securely) on high<LI>(Hiphil) to act exaltedly</OL></OL>'),
(7683, 'ggX', 'a primitive root', 'shagag', 'TWOT - 2324', 'shaw-gag\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to stray, i.e. (figuratively) sin (with more or less apology):--X also for that, deceived, err, go astray, sin ignorantly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go astray, err, commit sin or error<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to err (mentally)<LI>to sin (ignorantly or inadvertently)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7684, 'hggX', 'from (07683)', 'shgagah', 'TWOT - 2324a', 'sheg-aw-gaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07683»; a mistake or inadvertent transgression:--error, ignorance, at unawares; unwittingly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sin, sin of error or inadvertence, inadvertent sin<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>error</OL></OL>'),
(7685, 'hgX', 'a primitive root', 'sagah', 'TWOT - 2233b', 'saw-gaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to enlarge (especially upward, also figuratively):--grow (up), increase.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to grow, increase<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to grow (great)<LI>(Hiphil) to increase</OL></OL>'),
(7686, 'hgX', 'a primitive root', 'shagah', 'TWOT - 2325', 'shaw-gaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to stray (causatively, mislead), usually (figuratively) to mistake, especially (morally) to transgress; by extension (through the idea of intoxication) to reel, (figuratively) be enraptured:--(cause to) go astray, deceive, err, be ravished, sin through ignorance, (let, make to) wander.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go astray, stray, err<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to err, stray<LI>to swerve, meander, reel, roll, be intoxicated, err (in drunkenness)<LI>to go astray (morally)<LI>to commit sin of ignorance or inadvertence, err (ignorantly)</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lead astray<LI>to lead astray, mislead (mentally)<LI>to lead astray (morally)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7687, 'bwgX', 'from (07682)', 'Sguwb', 'None', 'seg-oob\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07682»; aloft; Segub, the name of two Israelites:--Segub.', 'Segub = \"exalted\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the youngest son of Hiel the Bethelite who rebuilt Jericho<LI>a Judaite, son of Hezron</OL>'),
(7688, 'xgX', 'a primitive root', 'shagach', 'TWOT - 2326', 'shaw-gakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to peep, i.e. glance sharply at:--look (narrowly).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to gaze, stare</OL>'),
