(7757, 'lwX', 'from an unused root meaning to hang down', 'shuwl', 'TWOT - 2346a', 'shool', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to hang down; a skirt; by implication, a bottom edge:--hem, skirt, train.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>skirt (of robe)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of high priest\'s robe<LI>of God\'s train, city as woman, ignominy, defilement (fig)</OL></OL>'),
(7758, 'llwX', 'from (07997)', 'showlal', 'TWOT - 2399a', 'sho-lawl\'', 'Adjective', 'or sheylal (Micah 1:8) {shay-lawl\'}; from «07997»; nude (especially bare-foot); by implication, captive:--spoiled, stripped.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>barefoot</OL>'),
(7759, 'tymmlwX', 'from (07999)', 'Shuwlammiyth', 'None', 'shoo-lam-meeth\'', 'Adjective', 'from «07999»; peaceful (with the article always prefixed, making it a pet name); the Shulammith, an epithet of Solomon\'s queen:--Shulamite.', 'Shulamite = \"the perfect\" or \"the peaceful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the heroine lover of the Song of Songs (of Solomon)</OL>'),
(7760, '~wX', 'a primitive root', 'suwm', 'TWOT - 2243', 'soom', 'Verb', 'or siym {seem}; a primitive root; to put (used in a great variety of applications, literal, figurative, inferentially, and elliptically):--X any wise, appoint, bring, call (a name), care, cast in, change, charge, commit, consider, convey, determine, + disguise, dispose, do, get, give, heap up, hold, impute, lay (down, up), leave, look, make (out), mark, + name, × on, ordain, order, + paint, place, preserve, purpose, put (on), + regard, rehearse, reward, (cause to) set (on, up), shew, + stedfastly, take, × tell, + tread down, ((over-))turn, × wholly, work.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to put, place, set, appoint, make<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to put, set, lay, put or lay upon, lay (violent) hands on<LI>to set, direct, direct toward 1a</OL><LI>to extend (compassion) (fig)<OL TYPE=\"3\"><LI>to set, ordain, establish, found, appoint, constitute, make, determine, fix<LI>to set, station, put, set in place, plant, fix<LI>to make, make for, transform into, constitute, fashion, work, bring to pass, appoint, give</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to set or make for a sign<LI>(Hophal) to be set</OL></OL>'),
(7761, '', 'corresponding to (07760)', 'suwm', '&nbsp;', 'soom', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to set, make, appoint<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make, make decree, set out (decree)<LI>to make, appoint<LI>to set, fix</OL><LI>(Ithp\'al) to be made, be set, be laid</OL></OL>', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07760»:--+ command, give, lay, make, + name, + regard, set.', ''),
(7762, '~wX', 'from an unused root meaning to exhale', 'shuwm', 'TWOT - 2347', 'shoom', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to exhale; garlic (from its rank odor):--garlic.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>garlic</OL>'),
