(7796, 'qrwX', 'the same as (08321)', 'Sowreq', 'None', 'so-rake\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «08321»; a vine; Sorek, a valley in Palestine:--Sorek.', 'Sorek = \"choice vines\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a wadi in Palestine in which Delilah lived</OL>'),
(7797, 'XwX', 'a primitive root', 'suws', 'TWOT - 2246', 'soos', 'Verb', 'or siys {sece}; a primitive root; to be bright, i.e. cheerful:--be glad, × greatly, joy, make mirth, rejoice.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to exult, rejoice<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to exult, display joy</OL></OL>'),
(7798, 'aXwX', 'from (07797)', 'Shavsha\'', 'None', 'shav-shaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07797»; joyful; Shavsha, an Israelite:--Shavsha.', 'Shavsha = \"nobility\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the royal scribe or secretary for David</OL>'),
(7799, '!XwX', 'from (07797)', 'shuwshan', 'TWOT - 2356', 'shoo-shan\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or showshan {sho-shawn\'}; or shoshan {sho- shawn\'}; and (feminine) showshannah {sho-shan-naw\'}; from «07797»; a lily (from its whiteness), as a flower of arch. ornament; also a (straight) trumpet (from the tubular shape): lily, Shoshannim.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lily<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>probably any lily-like flower<LI>Shoshannim, in title of Ps. 45</OL></OL>'),
