(7801, 'yknXwX', 'of foreign origin', 'Shuwshankiy', 'None', 'shoo-shan-kee\'', 'Proper Name', '(Aramaic) of foreign origin; a Shushankite (collectively) or inhabitants of some unknown place in Assyrian:--Susanchites.', 'Susanchites = see Shushan \"lily\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the inhabitants of the city of Shushan or Susa</OL>'),
(7802, 'twd[ !XwX', 'from (07799) and (05715)', 'Shuwshan', 'None', '', 'Noun Masculine', 'or (plural of former) Showshanniym aEduwth {sho-shan-neem\' ay-dooth\'}; from «07799» and «05715»; lily (or trumpet) of assemblage; Shushan-Eduth or Shoshannim-Eduth, the title of a popular song:--Shoshannim-Eduth, Shushan-eduth.', 'Shoshannim-eduth or Shushan-eduth = \"lilies\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>instruction in the title of Psalm 60 and Psalm 80<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning uncertain</OL></OL>'),
(7803, 'xltwX', 'probably from (07582) and the same as (08520)', 'Shuwthelach', 'None', 'shoo-theh\'-lakh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «07582» and the same as «08520»; crash of breakage; Shuthelach, the name of two Israelites:--Shuthelah.', 'Shuthelah = \"noise of breaking\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Ephraim, ancestor of Joshua, and progenitor of family of Ephraim</OL>'),
(7804, 'bzX', 'corresponding to (05800)', 'shzab', 'TWOT - 3027', 'shez-ab\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «05800»; to leave, i.e. (causatively) free:--deliver.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Peel or Peil) to deliver</OL>'),
(7805, '@zX', 'a primitive root', 'shazaph', 'TWOT - 2357', 'shaw-zaf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to tan (by sun-burning); figuratively (as if by a piercing ray) to scan:--look up, see.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to catch sight of, look on</OL>'),
(7806, 'rzX', 'a primitive root', 'shazar', 'TWOT - 2358', 'shaw-zar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to twist (a thread of straw):--twine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to twist, be twisted<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hophal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be twisted<LI>twisted (participle)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7807, 'xX', 'from (07817)', 'shach', 'TWOT - 2361a', 'shakh', 'Adjective', 'from «07817»; sunk, i.e. downcast:--+ humble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>low, lowly</OL>'),
(7808, 'xX', 'for (07879)', 'seach', 'TWOT - 2255c', 'say\'-akh', 'Noun Masculine', 'for «07879»; communion, i.e. (reflexively) meditation:--thought.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thought</OL>'),
(7809, 'dxX', 'a primitive root', 'shachad', 'TWOT - 2359', 'shaw-khad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to donate, i.e. bribe:--hire, give a reward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to give a present, bribe, ransom, offer gifts</OL>'),
(7810, 'dxX', 'from (07809)', 'shachad', 'TWOT - 2359a', 'shakh\'-ad', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07809»; a donation (venal or redemptive):--bribe(-ry), gift, present, reward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>present, bribe</OL>'),
(7811, 'hxX', 'a primitive root', 'sachah', 'TWOT - 2247', 'saw-khaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to swim; causatively, to inundate:--(make to) swim.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to swim<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) swim (participle)<LI>(Hiphil) to make to swim</OL></OL>'),
(7812, 'hxX', 'a primitive root', 'shachah', 'TWOT - 2360', 'shaw-khaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to depress, i.e. prostrate (especially reflexive, in homage to royalty or God):--bow (self) down, crouch, fall down (flat), humbly beseech, do (make) obeisance, do reverence, make to stoop, worship.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bow down<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to bow down<LI>(Hiphil) to depress (fig)<LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bow down, prostrate oneself 1c</OL><LI>before superior in homage 1c<LI>before God in worship 1c<LI>before false gods 1c<LI>before angel</OL></OL>'),
(7813, 'wxX', 'from (07811)', 'sachuw', 'TWOT - 2247a', 'saw\'-khoo', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07811»; a pond (for swimming):--to swim in.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>swimming</OL>'),
(7814, 'qwxX', 'from (07832)', 'schowq', 'TWOT - 1905d', 'sekh-oke\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or schoq {sekh-oke\'}; from «07832»; laughter (in merriment or defiance):--derision, laughter(-ed to scorn, -ing), mocked, sport.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>laughter, laughing stock, mocking, derision<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>laughter<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>joyful<LI>hollow</OL><LI>derision (of object)<LI>sport</OL></OL>'),
(7815, 'rwxX', 'from (07835)', 'shchowr', 'TWOT - 2368a', 'shekh-ore\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07835»; dinginess, i.e. perhaps soot:--coal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>blackness<LI>(CLBL) pit</OL>'),
(7816, 'twxX', 'from (07812)', 'shchuwth', 'TWOT - 2360a', 'shekh-ooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07812»; pit:--pit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pit</OL>'),
(7817, 'xxX', 'a primitive root', 'shachach', 'TWOT - 2361', 'shaw-khakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to sink or depress (reflexive or causative):--bend, bow (down), bring (cast) down, couch, humble self, be (bring) low, stoop.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bow, crouch, bow down, be bowed down<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be bowed down, be prostrated, be humbled<LI>to bow (in homage)<LI>to bow (of mourner)<LI>to crouch (of wild beast in lair)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be prostrated, be humbled, be reduced, be weakened, proceed humbly, be bowed down<LI>(Hiphil) to prostrate, lay low, bow down<LI>(Hithpolel) to be cast down, be despairing</OL></OL>'),
(7818, 'txX', 'a primitive root', 'sachat', 'TWOT - 2248', 'saw-khat\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to tread out, i.e. squeeze (grapes):--press.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to squeeze, press out</OL>'),
(7819, 'txX', 'a primitive root', 'shachat', 'TWOT - 2362', 'shaw-khat\'', '', 'a primitive root; to slaughter (in sacrifice or massacre):--kill, offer, shoot out, slay, slaughter.', 'v<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to kill, slaughter, beat<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to slaughter 1a</OL><LI>beast for food 1a<LI>sacrifice 1a<LI>person in human sacrifice 1a<LI>beaten, hammered (of shekels)<LI>(Niphal) to be slaughtered, be slain (of food or sacrifice) n f</OL><LI>(BDB) slaughtering<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>word doubtful</OL></OL>'),
(7820, 'txX', 'a primitive root [identical with (07819) through the idea of striking]', 'shachat', 'TWOT - 2362', 'shaw-khat\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «07819» through the idea of striking); to hammer out:--beat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to beat, hammer<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) beaten (participle)</OL><LI>(TWOT) to kill, slaughter</OL>'),
(7821, 'htyxX', 'from (07819)', 'shchiytah', 'TWOT - 2362a', 'shekh-ee-taw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07819»; slaughter:--killing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>slaughtering, killing, slaying (of act)</OL>'),
(7822, '!yxX', 'from an unused root probably meaning to burn', 'shchiyn', 'TWOT - 2364a', 'shekh-een\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to burn; inflammation, i.e. an ulcer; --boil, botch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>boil, inflamed spot, inflammation, eruption<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of man, leprosy, of man and beast</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(7823, 'oyxX', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to sprout', 'shachiyc', 'TWOT - 1484', 'shaw-khece\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or cachiysh {saw-kheesh\'}; from an unused root apparently meaning to sprout; after-growth:--(that) which springeth of the same.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>volunteer grain<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>grain that shoots up of itself the second year, without replanting</OL></OL>'),
(7824, '@yxX', 'from the same as (07828)', 'shachiyph', 'TWOT - 2249', 'shaw-kheef\'', '', 'from the same as «07828»; a board (as chipped thin):--cieled with.', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>panelled or wainscotted with wood<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning doubtful n</OL><LI>a wainscot of wood<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning doubtful</OL></OL>'),
(7825, 'tyxX', 'from (07812)', 'shchiyth', 'TWOT - 2360b', 'shekh-eeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07812»; a pit-fall (literally or figuratively):--destruction, pit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pit</OL>'),
(7826, 'lxX', 'from an unused root probably meaning to roar', 'shachal', 'TWOT - 2363a', 'shakh\'-al', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to roar; a lion (from his characteristic roar):--(fierce) lion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lion<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of Jehovah, wicked men (fig)</OL></OL>'),
(7827, 'tlxX', 'apparently from the same as (07826) through some obscure idea, perhaps that of peeling off by concussion of sound', 'shcheleth', 'TWOT - 2363b', 'shekh-ay\'-leth', 'Noun Feminine', 'apparently from the same as «07826» through some obscure idea, perhaps that of peeling off by concussion of sound; a scale or shell, i.e. the aromatic mussel.:--onycha.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>onycha<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>an ingredient used in the holy incense</OL></OL>'),
(7828, '@xX', 'from an unused root meaning to peel, i.e. emaciate', 'shachaph', 'TWOT - 2365a', 'shakh\'-af', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to peel, i.e. emaciate; the gull (as thin):--cuckoo.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a ceremonially unclean bird<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>cuckow, gull, seagull, sea-mew<LI>maybe an extinct bird, exact meaning unknown</OL></OL>'),
(7829, 'tpxX', 'from the same as (07828)', 'shachepheth', 'TWOT - 2365b', 'shakh-eh\'-feth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «07828»; emaciation:--consumption.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>consumption, wasting disease<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a wasting disease of the lungs</OL></OL>'),
(7830, '#xX', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to strut', 'shachats', 'TWOT - 2366a', 'shakh\'-ats', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root apparently meaning to strut; haughtiness (as evinced by the attitude):--X lion, pride.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dignity, pride<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>majestic wild beasts</OL></OL>'),
(7831, '~wcxX', 'from the same as (07830)', 'Shachatsowm', 'None', 'shakh-ats-ome\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the same as «07830»; proudly; Shachatsom, a place in Palestine:--Shahazimah (from the margin).', 'Shahazimah = \"toward the heights\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Issachar</OL>'),
(7832, 'qxX', 'a primitive root', 'sachaq', 'TWOT - 1905c', 'saw-khak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to laugh (in pleasure or detraction); by implication, to play:--deride, have in derision, laugh, make merry, mock(-er), play, rejoice, (laugh to) scorn, be in (make) sport.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to laugh, play, mock<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to laugh (usually in contempt or derision)<LI>to sport, play</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make sport<LI>to jest<LI>to play (including instrumental music, singing, dancing)</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to laugh mockingly</OL></OL>'),
(7833, 'qxX', 'a primitive root', 'shachaq', 'TWOT - 2367', 'shaw-khak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to comminate (by trituration or attrition):--beat, wear.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rub away, beat fine, pulverise<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rub away 1a</OL><LI>of incense, stones 1a<LI>of enemies (fig)</OL></OL>'),
(7834, 'qxX', 'from (07833)', 'shachaq', 'TWOT - 2367a', 'shakh\'-ak', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07833»; a powder (as beaten small): by analogy, a thin vapor; by extension, the firmament:--cloud, small dust, heaven, sky.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dust, cloud<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>fine dust<LI>(thin) cloud</OL></OL>'),
(7835, 'rxX', 'a primitive root [identical with (07836) through the idea of the duskiness of early dawn]', 'shachar', 'TWOT - 2368', 'shaw-khar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «07836» through the idea of the duskiness of early dawn); to be dim or dark (in color):--be black.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be black<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be black (of skin)</OL></OL>'),
(7836, 'rxX', 'a primitive root', 'shachar', 'TWOT - 2369', 'shaw-khar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to dawn, i.e. (figuratively) be (up) early at any task (with the implication of earnestness); by extension, to search for (with painstaking):--(do something) betimes, enquire early, rise (seek) betimes, seek diligently) early, in the morning).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to seek, seek early or earnestly, look early or diligently for<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to look for diligently, seek<LI>(Piel) to seek, seek early</OL></OL>'),
(7837, 'rxX', 'from (07836)', 'shachar', 'TWOT - 2369a', 'shakh\'-ar', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07836»; dawn (literal, figurative or adverbial):--day(-spring), early, light, morning, whence riseth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dawn<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>dawn<LI>at dawn (as adverb)</OL></OL>'),
(7838, 'rxX', 'from (07835)', 'shachor', 'TWOT - 2368b', 'shaw-khore\'', 'Adjective', 'or shachowr {shaw-khore\'}; from «07835»; properly, dusky, but also (absol.) jetty:--black.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>black</OL>'),
(7839, 'twrxX', 'from (07836)', 'shacharuwth', 'TWOT - 2368c', 'shakh-ar-ooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07836»; a dawning, i.e. (figuratively) juvenescence:--youth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>blackness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>blackness (of hair indicating youth)</OL></OL>'),
(7840, 'trxrxX', 'from (07835)', 'shcharchoreth', 'TWOT - 2368d', 'shekh-ar-kho\'-reth', 'Adjective', 'from «07835»; swarthy:--black.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>blackish</OL>'),
(7841, 'hyrxX', 'from (07836) and (03050)', 'Shcharyah', 'None', 'shekh-ar-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07836» and «03050»; Jah has sought; Shecharjah, an Israelite:--Shehariah.', 'Shehariah = \"dawning of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, son of Jehoram</OL>'),
(7842, '~yrxX', 'dual of (07837)', 'Shacharayim', 'None', 'shakh-ar-ah\'-yim', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'dual of «07837»; double dawn; Shacharajim, an Israelite:--Shaharaim.', 'Shaharaim = \"double dawn\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, father of Jobab, Zibia, Mesha, Malcham, Jeuz, Shachia, Mirma, Abitub, and Elpaal</OL>'),
(7843, 'txX', 'a primitive root', 'shachath', 'TWOT - 2370', 'shaw-khath\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to decay, i.e. (causatively) ruin (literally or figuratively):--batter, cast off, corrupt(-er, thing), destroy(-er, -uction), lose, mar, perish, spill, spoiler, × utterly, waste(-r).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to destroy, corrupt, go to ruin, decay<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be marred, be spoiled, be corrupted, be corrupt, be injured, be ruined, be rotted<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to spoil, ruin<LI>to pervert, corrupt, deal corruptly (morally)</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to spoil, ruin, destroy<LI>to pervert, corrupt (morally)<LI>destroyer (participle)</OL><LI>(Hophal) spoiled, ruined (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(7844, 'txX', 'corresponding to (07843)', 'shchath', 'TWOT - 3026', 'shekh-ath\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07843»:--corrupt, fault.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to corrupt<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>corrupt (participle)<LI>fault (subst)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7845, 'txX', 'from (07743)', 'shachath', 'TWOT - 2343.1c,2370d', 'shakh\'-ath', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07743»; a pit (especially as a trap); figuratively, destruction:--corruption, destruction, ditch, grave, pit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pit, destruction, grave<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>pit (for catching lions)<LI>pit (of Hell)</OL></OL>'),
(7846, 'tX', 'from (07750)', 'set', 'TWOT - 2240a', 'sayte', 'Noun Masculine', 'or cet {sayt}; from «07750»; a departure from right, i.e. sin:--revolter, that turn aside.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>swerver, revolter, rebel, deeds that swerve</OL>'),
(7847, 'htX', 'a primitive root', 'satah', 'TWOT - 2250', 'saw-taw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to deviate from duty:--decline, go aside, turn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to turn aside, go aside, turn, decline<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to turn aside</OL></OL>'),
(7848, 'httX', 'meaning the sticks of wood [from the same as (07850)]', 'shittah', 'TWOT - 2371', 'shit-taw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of a derivative (only in the plural shittiym {shit-teem\'}; meaning the sticks of wood) from the same as «07850»; the acacia (from its scourging thorns):--shittah, shittim. See also «01029».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>acacia tree, acacia wood</OL>'),
(7849, 'xtX', 'a primitive root', 'shatach', 'TWOT - 2372', 'shaw-takh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to expand:--all abroad, enlarge, spread, stretch out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to spread, spread abroad, stretch out<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to spread<LI>spreading, expanding (participle)</OL><LI>(Piel) to spread out</OL></OL>'),
(7850, 'ttX', 'act part of an otherwise unused root meaning (properly, to pierce', 'shotet', 'TWOT - 2344b', 'sho-tate\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'active participle of an otherwise unused root meaning (properly, to pierce; but only as a denominative from «07752») to flog; a goad:--scourge.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>scourge</OL>'),
(7851, '~yttX', 'the same as the pl. of (07848)', 'Shittiym', 'None', 'shit-teem\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as the plural of «07848»; acacia trees; Shittim, a place East of the Jordan:--Shittim.', 'Shittim = \"the acacias\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>place of Israel\'s encampment between the conquest of the transjordanic region and crossing the Jordan into Canaan<LI>a place west of Jerusalem</OL>'),
(7852, '~tX', 'a primitive root', 'satam', 'TWOT - 2251', 'saw-tam\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to lurk for, i.e. persecute:--hate, oppose self against.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hate, oppose oneself to, bear a grudge, retain animosity against, cherish animosity against<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to cherish animosity against</OL></OL>'),
(7853, '!tX', 'a primitive root', 'satan', 'TWOT - 2252', 'saw-tan\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to attack, (figuratively) accuse:--(be an) adversary, resist.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be or act as an adversary, resist, oppose</OL>'),
(7854, '!tX', 'from (07853)', 'satan', 'TWOT - 2252a', 'saw-tawn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07853»; an opponent; especially (with the article prefixed) Satan, the arch-enemy of good:--adversary, Satan, withstand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>adversary, one who withstands<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>adversary (in general - personal or national)</OL><LI>superhuman adversary<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>Satan (as noun pr)</OL></OL>'),
(7855, 'hntX', 'from (07853)', 'sitnah', 'TWOT - 2252b', 'sit-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07853»; opposition (by letter):--accusation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>accusation, enmity</OL>'),
(7856, 'hntX', 'the same as (07855)', 'Sitnan', 'None', 'sit-naw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «07855»; Sitnah, the name of a well in Pal:--Sitnah.', 'Sitnah = \"strife\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 2nd of the 2 wells dug by Isaac in the valley of Gerar</OL>'),
(7857, '@tX', 'a primitive root', 'shataph', 'TWOT - 2373', 'shaw-taf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to gush; by implication, to inundate, cleanse; by analogy, to gallop, conquer:--drown, (over-)flow(- whelm, rinse, run, rush, (throughly) wash (away).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wash, rinse, overflow, engulf, rinse or wash off<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to overflow<LI>to flow, run<LI>to rinse or wash off</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be swept away, be rinsed out<LI>(Pual) to be rinsed, be scoured and rinsed</OL></OL>'),
(7858, '@tX', 'from (07857)', 'sheteph', 'TWOT - 2373a', 'sheh\'-tef', 'Noun Masculine', 'or sheteph {shay\'-tef}; from «07857»; a deluge (literally or figuratively):--flood, outrageous, overflowing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flood, downpour</OL>'),
(7859, 'rtX', 'of uncertain derivation', 'shtar', 'TWOT - 3007', 'shet-ar\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; a side:--side.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>side (Dan. 7:<LI></OL>'),
(7860, 'rtX', 'act part of an otherwise unused root probably meaning to write', 'shoter', 'TWOT - 2374a', 'sho-tare\'', 'Masculine', 'active participle of an otherwise unused root probably meaning to write; properly, a scribe, i.e. (by analogy or implication) an official superintendent or magistrate:--officer, overseer, ruler.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) official, officer</OL>'),
(7861, 'yrtX', 'from the same as (07860)', 'Shitray', 'None', 'shit-rah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the same as «07860»; magisterial; Shitrai, an Israelite:--Shitrai.', 'Shitrai = \"my officers\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an official of David</OL>'),
(7862, 'yX', 'probably from (07737)', 'shay', 'TWOT - 2375', 'shah\'-ee', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from «07737»; a gift (as available):--present.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gift, present, gift offered as homage</OL>'),
(7863, 'ayX', 'from the same as (07721) by permutation', 'siy\'', 'TWOT - 1421i', 'see', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «07721» by permutation; elevation:-- excellency.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>loftiness (of pride)</OL>'),
(7864, 'ayX', 'for (07724)', 'Shya\'', 'None', 'sheh-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'for «07724»; Sheja, an Israelite:--Sheva (from the margin).', 'Sheva = \"Jehovah contends\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the scribe of David<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Seraiah\', \'Shisha\', and \'Shavsha\'</OL></OL>'),
(7865, '!ayX', 'from (07863)', 'Siy\'on', 'None', 'see-ohn\'', 'Proper Name', 'from «07863»; peak; Sion, the summit of Mt. Hermon:--Sion.', 'Sion = \"lofty\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>another name for Mount Hermon</OL>'),
(7866, '!wyaX', 'from the same as (07722)', 'Shi\'yown', 'None', 'shee-ohn\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the same as «07722»; ruin; Shijon, a place in Palestine --Shihon.', 'Shion = \"ruin\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town of Issachar located near Mount Tabor</OL>'),
(7867, 'byX', 'a primitive root', 'siyb', 'TWOT - 2253', 'seeb', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to become aged, i.e. (by implication) to grow gray:--(be) grayheaded.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be hoary, be gray</OL>'),
(7868, 'byX', 'corresponding to (07867)', 'siyb', 'TWOT - 3008', 'seeb', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07867»:--elder.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be gray, be hoary, be hoary-headed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) elders (subst)</OL></OL>'),
(7869, 'byX', 'from (07867)', 'seyb', 'TWOT - 2253a', 'sabe', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07867»; old age:--age.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hoary age, gray-headed age</OL>'),
(7870, 'hbyX', 'by permutation from (07725)', 'shiybah', 'TWOT - 2340b', 'shee-baw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'by permutation from «07725»; a return (of property):--captivity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>restoration</OL>'),
(7871, 'hbyX', 'from (03427)', 'shiybah', 'TWOT - 922b', 'shee-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03427»; residence:--while...lay.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sojourn</OL>'),
