(7933, '!kX', 'from (07931)', 'sheken', 'TWOT - 2387a', 'sheh\'-ken', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07931»; a residence:--habitation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dwelling</OL>'),
(7934, '!kX', 'from (07931)', 'shaken', 'TWOT - 2387b', 'shaw-kane\'', 'Adjective', 'from «07931»; a resident; by extension,  a fellow-citizen:--inhabitant, neighbour, nigh.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>inhabitant, neighbour<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>inhabitant<LI>neighbour</OL></OL>'),
(7935, 'hynkX', 'from (07931) and (03050)', 'Shkanyah', 'None', 'shek-an-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or (prol.) Shkanyahuw {shek-an-yaw\'-hoo}; from «07931» and «03050»; Jah has dwelt; Shekanjah, the name of nine Israelites:--Shecaniah, Shechaniah.', 'Shecaniah or Shechaniah = \"dweller with Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Zerubbabel whose descendants returned from exile with Ezra<LI>son of Jehiel of the sons of Elam and one who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>father of Shemaiah who repaired part of the wall of Jerusalem in the time of Nehemiah<LI>son of Arah, father-in-law of Tobiah who opposed Nehemiah<LI>a priest who returned from exile with Zerubbabel<LI>a priest in the time of king Hezekiah of Judah</OL>'),
(7936, 'rkX', 'a primitive root [apparently akin (by prosthesis) to (03739) through the idea of temporary purchase]', 'sakar', 'TWOT - 2264.1', 'saw-kar\'', 'Verb', 'or (by permutation) cakar (Ezra 4:5) {saw-kar\'}; a primitive root (apparently akin (by prosthesis) to «03739» through the idea of temporary purchase; compare «07937»); to hire:--earn wages, hire (out self), reward, × surely.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hire<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to hire<LI>(Niphal) to hire oneself out<LI>(Hithpael) to earn wages</OL></OL>'),
(7937, 'rkX', 'a primitive root', 'shakar', 'TWOT - 2388', 'shaw-kar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to become tipsy; in a qualified sense, to satiate with a stimulating drink or (figuratively) influence:--(be filled with) drink (abundantly), (be, make) drunk(-en), be merry. (Superlative of «08248».)', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or become drunk or drunken, be intoxicated<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to become drunken<LI>(Piel) to make drunken, cause to be drunk<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to be drunk<LI>(Hithpael) to make oneself drunk</OL></OL>'),
(7938, 'rkX', 'from (07936)', 'seker', 'TWOT - 2264.1a', 'seh\'-ker', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07936»; wages:--reward, sluices.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hire, wages</OL>'),
(7939, 'rkX', 'from (07936)', 'sakar', 'TWOT - 2264.1b', 'saw-kawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07936»; payment of contract; concretely, salary, fare, maintenance; by implication, compensation, benefit:--hire, price, reward(-ed), wages, worth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hire, wages<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>wages<LI>reward, pay<LI>fare, fee, passage-money</OL></OL>'),
(7940, 'rkX', 'the same as (07939)', 'Sakar', 'None', 'saw-kar\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «07939»; recompense; Sakar, the name of two Israelites:--Sacar.', 'Sacar = \"wages\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Ahiam, one of David\'s mighty warriors<LI>a Korahite Levite gatekeeper, the 4th son of Obed-edom in the time of David</OL>'),
(7941, 'rkX', 'from (07937)', 'shekar', 'TWOT - 2388a', 'shay-kawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07937»; an intoxicant, i.e. intensely alcoholic liquor:--strong drink, + drunkard, strong wine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>strong drink, intoxicating drink, fermented or intoxicating liquor</OL>'),
(7942, '!wrkkX', 'for (07943)', 'Shikkrown', 'None', 'shik-ker-one\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'for «07943»; drunkenness, Shikkeron, a place in Palestine:--Shicron.', 'Shicron = \"drunkenness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a landmark on the northwestern boundary of Judah lying between Ekron and Jabneel</OL>'),
(7943, '!wrkkX', 'from (07937)', 'shikkarown', 'TWOT - 2388c', 'shik-kaw-rone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07937»; intoxication:--(be) drunken(-ness).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>drunkenness</OL>'),
(7944, 'lX', 'from (07952) abbrev', 'shal', 'TWOT - 2389.1', 'shal', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07952» abbrev.; a fault:--error.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>error, fault<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning uncertain</OL></OL>'),
(7945, 'lX', 'for the rel (0834)', 'shel', 'TWOT - 184', 'shel', '', 'for the rel. «0834»; used with prepositional prefix, and often followed by some pronominal affix; on account of, whatsoever, whichsoever:--cause, sake.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>who, which</OL>'),
(7946, '!nalX', 'for (07600)', 'shal\'anan', 'TWOT - 2304a', 'shal-an-awn\'', 'Adjective', 'for «07600»; tranquil:--being at ease.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>at ease, quiet, secure</OL>'),
(7947, 'blX', 'a primitive root', 'shalab', 'TWOT - 2390', 'shaw-lab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to space off; intensive (evenly) to make equidistant:--equally distant, set in order.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Pual) to be bound, be joined, be joined together</OL>'),
(7948, 'blX', 'from (07947)', 'shalab', 'TWOT - 2390a', 'shaw-lawb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07947»; a spacer or raised interval, i.e. the stile in a frame or panel:--ledge.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>joinings (of bases)</OL>'),
(7949, 'glX', 'a primitive root', 'shalag', 'TWOT - 2391', 'shaw-lag\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, meaning to be white; used only as denominative from «07950»; to be snow-white (with the linen clothing of the slain):--be as snow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to snow, be as snow</OL>'),
(7950, 'glX', 'from (07949)', 'sheleg', 'TWOT - 2391a', 'sheh\'-leg', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07949»; snow (probably from its whiteness):--snow(-y).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>snow</OL>'),
(7951, 'hlX', 'a primitive root', 'shalah', 'TWOT - 2392', 'shaw-law\'', 'Verb', 'or shalav (Job 3:26) {shaw-lav\'}; a primitive root; to be tranquil, i.e. secure or successful:--be happy, prosper, be in safety.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be at rest, prosper, be quiet, be at ease<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or have quiet<LI>to be at ease, prosper</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7952, 'hlX', 'a primitive root [probably identical with (07953) through the idea of educing]', 'shalah', 'None', 'shaw-law\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (probably identical with «07953» through the idea of educing); to mislead:--deceive, be negligent.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Niphal) to be negligent<LI>(Hiphil) to mislead</OL>'),
(7953, 'hlX', 'a primitive root [rather cognate (by contraction) to the base of (05394), (07997) and their congeners through the idea of extracting]', 'shalah', 'TWOT - 2393', 'shaw-law\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (rather cognate (by contraction) to the base of «05394», «07997» and their congeners through the idea of extracting); to draw out or off, i.e. remove (the soul by death):--take away.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to draw out, extract</OL>'),
(7954, 'hlX', 'corresponding to (07951)', 'shlah', 'TWOT - 3032', 'shel-aw\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07951»; to be secure:--at rest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) at ease</OL>'),
(7955, 'hlX', 'from a root corresponding to (07952)', 'shalah', 'None', 'shaw-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «07952»; a wrong:--thing amiss.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>neglect, remissness</OL>'),
(7956, 'hlX', 'the same as (07596) (shortened)', 'Shelah', 'None', 'shay-law\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «07596» (shortened); request; Shelah, the name of a postdiluvian patriarch and of an Israelite:--Shelah.', 'Shelah = \"a petition\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the youngest son of Judah</OL>'),
(7957, 'tbhlX', 'from the same as (03851) with sibilant prefix', 'shalhebeth', 'TWOT - 1077c', 'shal-heh\'-beth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «03851» with sibilant prefix; a flare of fire:--(flaming) flame.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flame</OL>'),
(7958, 'wlX', 'by orthographical variation from (07951) through the idea of sluggishness', 'slav', 'TWOT - 2265', 'sel-awv\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or slayv {sel-awv\'}; by orthographical variation from 7951 through the idea of sluggishness; the quail collectively (as slow in flight from its weight):--quails.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>quail</OL>'),
(7959, 'wlX', 'from (07951)', 'shelev', 'TWOT - 2392a', 'sheh\'-lev', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07951»; security:--prosperity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ease, prosperity</OL>'),
(7960, 'wlX', 'from the same as (07955)', 'shaluw', 'None', 'shaw-loo\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) or shaluwth (Aramaic) {shaw-looth\'}; from the same as «07955»; a fault:--error, × fail, thing amiss.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>neglect, remissness</OL>'),
(7961, 'wlX', 'from (07951)', 'shalev', 'TWOT - 2392c', 'shaw-lave\'', 'Adjective', 'or shaleyv {shaw-lave\'}; feminine shlevah {shel-ay-vaw\'}; from «07951»; tranquil; (in a bad sense) careless; abstractly, security:--(being) at ease, peaceable, (in) prosper(-ity), quiet(-ness), wealthy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>quiet, at ease, prosperous<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>at ease (of persons)<LI>quiet (of land)<LI>quiet, ease<LI>ease (subst)</OL></OL>'),
(7962, 'hwlX', 'from (07951)', 'shalvah', 'TWOT - 2392d', 'shal-vaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07951»; security (genuine or false):--abundance, peace(-ably), prosperity, quietness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>quietness, ease, prosperity</OL>'),
(7963, 'hwlX', 'corresponding to (07962)', 'shlevah', 'TWOT - 3032b', 'shel-ay-vaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07962»; safety:--tranquillity. See also «07961».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ease, prosperity</OL>'),
(7964, 'xwllX', 'from (07971)', 'shilluwach', 'TWOT - 2394b', 'shil-loo\'-akh', 'Noun Masculine', 'or shilluach {shil-loo\'-akh}; from «07971»; (only in plural) a dismissal, i.e. (of a wife) divorce (especially the document); also (of a daughter) dower:--presents, have sent back.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sending away, parting gift<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>sending away<LI>parting gift</OL></OL>'),
(7965, '~wlX', 'from (07999)', 'shalowm', 'TWOT - 2401a', 'shaw-lome\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or shalom {shaw-lome\'}; from «07999»; safe, i.e. (figuratively) well, happy, friendly; also (abstractly) welfare, i.e. health, prosperity, peace:--X do, familiar, × fare, favour, + friend, × great, (good) health, (X perfect, such as be at) peace(-able, -ably), prosper(-ity, -ous), rest, safe(-ty), salute, welfare, (X all is, be) well, × wholly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>completeness, soundness, welfare, peace<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>completeness (in number)<LI>safety, soundness (in body)<LI>welfare, health, prosperity<LI>peace, quiet, tranquillity, contentment<LI>peace, friendship<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of human relationships<LI>with God especially in covenant relationship</OL><LI>peace (from war)<LI>peace (as adjective)</OL></OL>'),
(7966, '~wllX', 'from (07999)', 'shilluwm', 'TWOT - 2401h', 'shil-loom\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or shillum {shil-loom\'}; from «07999»; a requital, i.e. (secure) retribution, (venal) a fee:--recompense, reward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>requital, reward<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>requital, retribution<LI>reward, bribe</OL></OL>'),
(7967, '~wllX', 'the same as (07966)', 'Shalluwm', 'None', 'shal-loom\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or (shorter) Shallum {shal-loom\'}; the same as «07966»; Shallum, the name of fourteen Israelites:--Shallum.', 'Shallum = \"retribution\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Jabesh, conspirator and slayer of king Zachariah of the northern kingdom of Israel ending the dynasty of Jehu; assumed the throne and became the 15th king of the northern kingdom; reigned for one month and was killed by Menahem<LI>the 3rd son of king Josiah of Judah and subsequent king of Judah; reigned for 3 months before he was taken captive to Egypt where he was placed in chains and later died<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Jehoahaz\'</OL><LI>husband of Huldah the prophetess in the reign of king Josiah of Judah. Maybe the same as 4<LI>uncle of Jeremiah the prophet. Maybe the same as 3<LI>a Simeonite, son of Shaul and grandson of Simeon<LI>a Judaite, son of Sisamai and father of Jekamiah in the family of Jerahmeel<LI>an Ephraimite, father of Jehizkiah<LI>a son of Naphtali<LI>a Korahite Levite, chief of a family of gatekeepers for the east gate of the temple<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>maybe same as 13</OL><LI>son of Halohesh and ruler of a district of Jerusalem; also repairer of the wall of Jerusalem in the time of Nehemiah<LI>a priest, of the family of Eleazar, son of Zadok and father of Hilkiah in the family line of Ezra<LI>a Korahite Levite, son of Kore, father of Maaseiah, and in charge of the work of the service. Maybe same as 9<LI>a Levite gatekeeper who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>a Levite and descendant of Bani who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(7968, '!wllX', 'probably for (07967)', 'Shalluwn', 'None', 'shal-loon\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably for «07967»; Shallun, an Israelite:--Shallum.', 'Shallun = \"retribution\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Colhozeh and ruler of a district of the Mizpah</OL>'),
(7969, 'XwlX', 'a primitive number', 'shalowsh', 'TWOT - 2403a', 'shaw-loshe\'', 'Noun', 'or shalosh {shaw-loshe\'}; masculine shlowshah {shel-o-shaw\'}; or shloshah {shel-o-shaw\'}; a primitive number; three; occasionally (ordinal) third, or (multipl.) thrice:--+ fork, + often(-times), third, thir(-teen, -teenth), three, + thrice. Compare «07991».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>three, triad<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>3, 300, third</OL></OL>'),
(7970, '~yXwlX', 'multiple of (07969)', 'shlowshiym', 'TWOT - 2403d', 'shel-o-sheem\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or shloshiym {shel-o-sheem\'}; multiple of «07969»; thirty; or (ordinal) thirtieth:--thirty, thirtieth. Compare «07991».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thirty, thirtieth</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(7971, 'xlX', 'a primitive root', 'shalach', 'TWOT - 2394', 'shaw-lakh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to send away, for, or out (in a great variety of applications):--X any wise, appoint, bring (on the way), cast (away, out), conduct, × earnestly, forsake, give (up), grow long, lay, leave, let depart (down, go, loose), push away, put (away, forth, in, out), reach forth, send (away, forth, out), set, shoot (forth, out), sow, spread, stretch forth (out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to send, send away, let go, stretch out<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to send<LI>to stretch out, extend, direct<LI>to send away<LI>to let loose</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be sent<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to send off or away or out or forth, dismiss, give over, cast out<LI>to let go, set free<LI>to shoot forth (of branches)<LI>to let down<LI>to shoot</OL><LI>(Pual) to be sent off, be put away, be divorced, be impelled<LI>(Hiphil) to send</OL></OL>'),
(7972, 'xlX', 'corresponding to (07971)', 'shlach', 'TWOT - 3033', 'shel-akh\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07971»:--put, send.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to send<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to send, send out<LI>to be sent</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7973, 'xlX', 'from (07971)', 'shelach', 'TWOT - 2394a', 'sheh\'-lakh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07971»; a missile of attack, i.e. spear; also (figuratively) a shoot of growth; i.e. branch:--dart, plant, × put off, sword, weapon.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>weapon, missile, sprout<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>missile, weapon<LI>sprout, shoot</OL></OL>'),
(7974, 'xlX', 'the same as (07973)', 'Shelach', 'None', 'sheh\'-lakh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «07973»; Shelach, a postdiluvian patriarch:--Salah, Shelah. Compare «07975».', 'Salah or Shelah = \"sprout\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Arphaxad and father of Eber</OL>'),
(7975, 'xlX', 'from (07971)', 'Shiloach', 'None', 'shee-lo\'-akh', 'Proper Name Location', 'or (in imitation of «07974») Shelach (Neh. 3:15) {sheh\'-lakh}; from «07971»; rill; Shiloach, a fountain of Jerusalem:-- Shiloah, Siloah.', 'Shiloah or Siloah = \"sent\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a fountain just southeast of Jerusalem</OL>'),
(7976, 'hxllX', 'from (07964)', 'shilluchah', 'TWOT - 2394c', 'shil-loo-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «07964»; a shoot:--branch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shoot, branch</OL>'),
(7977, 'yxlX', 'from (07973)', 'Shilchiy', 'None', 'shil-khee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07973»; missive, i.e. armed; Shilchi, an Israelite:--Shilhi.', 'Shilhi = \"armed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Azubah, the mother of Jehoshaphat</OL>'),
(7978, '~yxlX', 'pl. of (07973)', 'Shilchiym', 'None', 'shil-kheem\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'plural of «07973»; javelins or sprouts; Shilchim, a place in Palestine:--Shilhim.', 'Shilhim = \"fountains\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in the southern portion of Judah</OL>'),
(7979, '!xlX', 'from (07971)', 'shulchan', 'TWOT - 2395a', 'shool-khawn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07971»; a table (as spread out); by implication, a meal:--table.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>table<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>table<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of king\'s table, private use, sacred uses</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7980, 'tlX', 'a primitive root', 'shalat', 'TWOT - 2396', 'shaw-lat\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to dominate, i.e. govern; by implication, to permit:--(bear, have) rule, have dominion, give (have) power.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to domineer, exercise power over, dominate, have mastery, be master, lord it over<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to domineer, lord it over, become master<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give power of<LI>to get mastery of</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7981, 'tlX', 'corresponding to (07980)', 'shlet', 'TWOT - 3034', 'shel-ate\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07980»:--have the mastery, have power, bear rule, be (make) ruler.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to have power, rule, domineer, rule over<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) have power upon or over, rule, fall upon, assault, be ruler<LI>(Aphel) make ruler</OL></OL>'),
(7982, 'tlX', 'from (07980)', 'shelet', 'TWOT - 2397a', 'sheh\'-let', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07980»; probably a shield (as controlling, i.e. protecting the person):--shield.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shield</OL>'),
(7983, '!wtlX', 'from (07980)', 'shiltown', 'TWOT - 2396b', 'shil-tone\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «07980»; a potentate; --power.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mastery</OL>'),
(7984, '!wtlX', 'corresponding to (07983)', 'shiltown', 'TWOT - 3034c', 'shil-tone\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) or shilton {shil-tone\'}; corresponding to «07983»:--ruler.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>governor, ruler, official</OL>'),
(7985, '!tlX', 'from (07981)', 'sholtan', 'TWOT - 3034a', 'shol-tawn\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «07981»; empire (abstractly or concretely):--dominion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dominion, sovereignty<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>dominion, sovereignty<LI>realm</OL></OL>'),
(7986, 'ttllX', 'fem. from (07980)', 'shalleteth', 'TWOT - 2396c', 'shal-leh\'-teth', 'Adjective', 'feminine from «07980»; a vixen:--imperious.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>imperious, domineering</OL>'),
(7987, 'ylX', 'from (07951)', 'shliy', 'TWOT - 2392b', 'shel-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07951»; privacy:--+ quietly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>quiet, private, quietness</OL>'),
(7988, 'hylX', 'from (07953)', 'shilyah', 'TWOT - 2393a', 'shil-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from «07953»; a fetus or babe (as extruded in birth):--young one.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>afterbirth</OL>'),
(7989, 'tyllX', 'from (07980)', 'shalliyt', 'TWOT - 2396a', 'shal-leet\'', 'Adjective', 'from «07980»; potent; concretely, a prince or warrior:--governor, mighty, that hath power, ruler.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>having mastery, domineering, master<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>having mastery<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ruler (subst)</OL><LI>domineering, imperious</OL></OL>'),
(7990, 'tyllX', 'corresponding to (07989)', 'shalliyt', 'TWOT - 3034b', 'shal-leet\'', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07989»; mighty; abstractly, permission; concretely, a premier:--captain, be lawful, rule(- r).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>having mastery, having authority, ruling<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>having or exercising mastery, ruling<LI>ruler (subst)<LI>having authority<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>it is authorised</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7991, 'XylX', 'from (07969)', 'shaliysh', 'TWOT - 2403e,2403f,2403g', 'shaw-leesh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or shalowsh ( 1 Chron. 11:11; 12:18) {shaw- loshe\'}; or shalosh (2 Sam. 23:13) {shaw-loshe\'}; from «07969»; a triple, i.e. (as a musical instrument) a triangle (or perhaps rather three-stringed lute); also (as an indefinite, great quantity) a three-fold measure (perhaps a treble ephah); also (as an officer) a general of the third rank (upward, i.e. the highest):--captain, instrument of musick, (great) lord, (great) measure, prince, three (from the margin).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>third part<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>name of a measure</OL><LI>a musical instrument<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>maybe three-stringed, triangular shape, or three-barred<LI>perhaps a sistrum or triangle</OL><LI>shield carrier, adjutant, officer, captain</OL>'),
(7992, 'yXylX', 'ordinal from (07969)', 'shliyshiy', 'TWOT - 2403b', 'shel-ee-shee\'', 'Adjective', 'ordinal from «07969»; third; feminine a third (part); by extension, a third (day, year or time); specifically, a third-story cell):--third (part, rank, time), three (years old).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>third, one third, third part, third time<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>ordinal number</OL></OL>'),
(7993, '$lX', 'a primitive root', 'shalak', 'TWOT - 2398', 'shaw-lak', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to throw out, down or away (literally or figuratively):--adventure, cast (away, down, forth, off, out), hurl, pluck, throw.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to throw, cast, hurl, fling<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to throw, cast, throw away, cast off, shed, cast down<LI>to cast (lots) (fig)</OL><LI>(Hophal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be thrown, be cast<LI>to be cast forth or out<LI>to be cast down<LI>to be cast (metaph)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(7994, '$lX', 'from (07993)', 'shalak', 'TWOT - 2398a', 'shaw-lawk\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07993»; bird of prey, usually thought to be the pelican (from casting itself into the sea):--cormorant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bird of prey<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>probably the cormorant</OL></OL>'),
(7995, 'tkllX', 'from (07993)', 'shalleketh', 'TWOT - 2398b', 'shal-leh\'-keth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «07993»; a felling (of trees):--when cast.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>felling (of tree)</OL>'),
(7996, 'tkllX', 'the same as (07995)', 'Shalleketh', 'None', 'shal-leh\'-keth', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «07995»; Shalleketh, a gate in Jerusalem:--Shalleketh.', 'Shallecheth = \"overthrow\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the temple gates on the west side</OL>'),
(7997, 'llX', 'a primitive root', 'shalal', 'TWOT - 2399,2400', 'shaw-lal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to drop or strip; by implication, to plunder:--let fall, make self a prey, × of purpose, (make a, (take)) spoil.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to draw out<LI>to spoil, plunder, take spoil<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to spoil, plunder<LI>(Hithpolel) to be spoiled, be plundered</OL></OL>'),
(7998, 'llX', 'from (07997)', 'shalal', 'TWOT - 2400a', 'shaw-lawl\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07997»; booty:--prey, spoil.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>prey, plunder, spoil, booty<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>prey<LI>booty, spoil, plunder (of war)<LI>plunder (private)<LI>gain (meaning dubious)</OL></OL>'),
(7999, '~lX', 'a primitive root', 'shalam', 'TWOT - 2401c', 'shaw-lam\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be safe (in mind, body or estate); figuratively, to be (causatively, make) completed; by implication, to be friendly; by extension, to reciprocate (in various applications):--make amends, (make an) end, finish, full, give again, make good, (re-)pay (again), (make) (to) (be at) peace(-able), that is perfect, perform, (make) prosper(-ous), recompense, render, requite, make restitution, restore, reward, × surely.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be in a covenant of peace, be at peace<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be at peace<LI>peaceful one (participle)</OL><LI>(Pual) one in covenant of peace (participle)<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make peace with<LI>to cause to be at peace</OL><LI>(Hophal) to live in peace</OL><LI>to be complete, be sound<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be complete, be finished, be ended<LI>to be sound, be uninjured</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to complete, finish<LI>to make safe<LI>to make whole or good, restore, make compensation<LI>to make good, pay<LI>to requite, recompense, reward</OL><LI>(Pual)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be performed<LI>to be repaid, be requited</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to complete, perform<LI>to make an end of</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8000, '~lX', 'corresponding to (07999)', 'shlam', 'TWOT - 3035', 'shel-am\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07999»; to complete, to restore:--deliver, finish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be complete, be finished, be sound<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) finished (participle)<LI>(Aphel) to finish, bring to an end, render in full</OL></OL>'),
(8001, '~lX', 'corresponding to (07965)', 'shlam', 'TWOT - 3035a', 'shel-awm\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07965»; prosperity:--peace.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>welfare, prosperity, peace, well-being</OL>'),
(8002, '~lX', 'from (07999)', 'shelem', 'TWOT - 2401b', 'sheh\'-lem', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07999»; properly, requital, i.e. a (voluntary) sacrifice in thanks:--peace offering.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>peace offering, requital, sacrifice for alliance or friendship<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>voluntary sacrifice of thanks</OL></OL>'),
(8003, '~lX', 'from (07999)', 'shalem', 'TWOT - 2401d', 'shaw-lame\'', 'Adjective', 'from «07999»; complete (literally or figuratively); especially friendly:--full, just, made ready, peaceable, perfect(-ed), quiet, Shalem (by mistake for a name), whole.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>complete, safe, peaceful, perfect, whole, full, at peace<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>complete<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>full, perfect<LI>finished</OL><LI>safe, unharmed<LI>peace (of covenant of peace, mind)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>perfect, complete (of keeping covenant relation)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8004, '~lX', 'the same as (08003)', 'Shalem', 'None', 'shaw-lame\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «08003»; peaceful; Shalem, an early name of Jerusalem:--Salem.', 'Salem = \"peace\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the place of which Melchizedek was king<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>most Jewish commentators affirm that it is the same as Jerusalem</OL></OL>'),
(8005, '~llX', 'from (07999)', 'shillem', 'TWOT - 2401e', 'shil-lame\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07999»; requital:--recompense.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>recompense, requital</OL>'),
(8006, '~llX', 'the same as (08005)', 'Shillem', 'None', 'shil-lame\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «08005»; Shillem, an Israelite:--Shillem.', 'Shillem = \"repaid\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Naphtali</OL>'),
(8007, 'amlX', 'probably for (08008)', 'Salma\'', 'None', 'sal-maw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably for «08008»; clothing; Salma, the name of two Israelites:--Salma.', 'Salma = \"garment\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Boaz, father-in-law of Ruth, and grandfather of David<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Salmon\', \'Salmah\'</OL></OL>'),
(8008, 'hmlX', 'transp for (08071)', 'salmah', 'TWOT - 2270b', 'sal-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'transp. for «08071»; a dress:--clothes, garment, raiment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>garment, outer garment, wrapper, mantle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>garment, outer garment</OL></OL>'),
(8009, 'hmlX', 'the same as (08008)', 'Salmah', 'None', 'sal-maw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «08008»; clothing; Salmah, an Israelite:--Salmon. Compare «08012».', 'Salmon = \"garment\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Boaz, father-in-law of Ruth, and grandfather of David<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Salmah\', \'Salma\'</OL></OL>'),
(8010, 'hmlX', 'from (07965)', 'Shlomoh', 'TWOT - 2401i', 'shel-o-mo\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07965»; peaceful; Shelomah, David\'s successor:--Solomon.', 'Solomon = \"peace\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of David by Bathsheba and 3rd king of Israel; author of Proverbs and Song of Songs</OL>'),
(8011, 'hmllX', 'from (07966)', 'shillumah', 'TWOT - 2401h', 'shil-loo-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «07966»; retribution:--recompense.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>reward, requital, retribution</OL>'),
(8012, '!wmlX', 'from (08008)', 'Salmown', 'None', 'sal-mone\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08008»; investiture; Salmon, an Israelite:--Salmon. Compare «08009».', 'Salmon = \"garment\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Boaz, father-in-law of Ruth, and grandfather of David<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Salmah\', \'Salma\'</OL></OL>'),
(8013, 'twmlX', 'f. pl. of (07965)', 'Shlomowth', 'None', 'shel-o-moth\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'feminine plural of «07965»; pacifications; Shelomoth, the name of two Israelites:--Shelomith (from the margin), Shelomoth. Compare «08019».', 'Shelomoth or Shelomith = \"peaceful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Gershonite Levite, son of Shimei in the time of David<LI>a Kohathite Levite of the sons of Izhar in the time of David<LI>a Gershonite Levite, son of Zichri in the time of David</OL>'),
(8014, 'ymlX', 'from (08008)', 'Salmay', 'None', 'sal-mah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08008»; clothed; Salmai, an Israelite:--Shalmai.', 'Shalmai or Salmai or Shamlai = \"my thanks\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ancestor of a family of temple slaves who returned from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(8015, 'ymlX', 'from (07965)', 'Shlomiy', 'None', 'shel-o-mee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07965»; peaceable; Shelomi, an Israelite:--Shelomi.', 'Shelomi = \"peaceful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Asherite, father of Ahihud, the leader of the tribe of Asher at the time of the division of the land of Canaan</OL>'),
(8016, 'ymllX', 'patronymically from (08006)', 'Shillemiy', 'None', 'shil-lay-mee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'patronymically from «08006»; a Shilemite (collectively) or descendants of Shillem:--Shillemites.', 'Shillemites = see Shillem \"recompense\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Shillem, a son of Naphtali</OL>'),
(8017, 'laymlX', 'from (07965) and (0410)', 'Shlumiy\'el', 'None', 'shel-oo-mee-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07965» and «0410»; peace of God; Shelumiel, an Israelite:--Shelumiel.', 'Shelumiel = \"friend of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Zurishaddai and prince of the tribe of Simeon at the time of the exodus</OL>'),
(8018, 'hymlX', 'from (08002) and (03050)', 'Shelemyah', 'None', 'shel-em-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Shelemyahuw {shel-em-yaw\'-hoo}; from «08002» and «03050»; thank-offering of Jah; Shelemjah, the name of nine Israelites:--Shelemiah.', 'Shelemiah = \"repaid by Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Bani who put away his foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>another son of Bani who put away his foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>father of Hananiah who repaired part of the wall of Jerusalem in the time of Nehemiah<LI>a priest in the time of Nehemiah in charge of the treasury<LI>father of Jehucal or Jucal in the time of Zedekiah<LI>Levite upon whom the lot for the East Gate fell; in the time of David<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Meshelemiah\' and \'Shallum\'</OL><LI>father of Nethaniah and grandfather of Jehudi, who was the messenger sent to Baruch the scribe of Jeremiah<LI>son of Abdeel and one the men commanded by king Jehoiakim of Judah to seize the prophet Jeremiah and his scribe Baruch<LI>father of Irijah, the captain of the guard who arrested Jeremiah</OL>'),
(8019, 'tymlX', 'from (07965)', 'Shlomiyth', 'None', 'shel-o-meeth\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Shlowmiyth (Ezra 8:10) {shel-o- meeth\'}; from «07965»; peaceableness; Shelomith, the name of five Israelites and three Israelitesses:--Shelomith.', 'Shelomith = \"peaceful\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Gershonite Levite, son of Zichri in the time of David<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Shelomoth\'; same as 08013</OL><LI>son of king Rehoboam of Judah by Maacah the granddaughter of Absalom<LI>head of a family of exiles who returned with Ezra n pr f<LI>a woman of Dan, daughter of Dibri, and mother of a son who blasphemed God and was stoned to death in the time of Moses<LI>daughter of Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(8020, '!mlX', 'of foreign derivation', 'Shalman', 'None', 'shal-man\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign derivation; Shalman, a king apparently of Assyria:--Shalman. Compare «08022».', 'Shalman = \"fire-worshipper\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a contraction for Shalmaneser king of Assyria<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>maybe an obscure Assyrian king, predecessor of Pul</OL></OL>'),
(8021, '!mlX', 'from (07999)', 'shalmon', 'TWOT - 2401f', 'shal-mone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07999»; a bribe:--reward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>reward, bribe</OL>'),
(8022, 'roanmlX', 'of foreign derivation', 'Shalman\'ecer', 'None', 'shal-man-eh\'-ser', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign derivation; Shalmaneser, an Assyrian king:--Shalmaneser. Comp «08020».', 'Shalmaneser = \"fire-worshipper\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Assyrian king who probably reigned between Tiglath-pileser and Sargon; invaded the northern kingdom of Israel when the last king Hoshea was on the throne; forced Hoshea to pay tribute but had to reinvade when Hoshea reneged; it is uncertain whether Shalmaneser or Sargon concluded the siege which finally ended the northern kingdom<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>maybe a common name for Assyrian kings in the 8th century BC</OL></OL>'),
(8023, 'ynlX', 'the same as (07888)', 'Shiloniy', 'None', 'shee-lo-nee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «07888»; Shiloni, an Israelite:--Shiloni.', 'Shiloni = see Shiloh \"peace bringer\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Shiloh</OL>'),
(8024, 'ynlX', 'from (07956)', 'Shelaniy', 'None', 'shay-law-nee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «07956»; a Shelanite (collectively), or descendants of Shelah:--Shelanites.', 'Shelanites = see Shelah \"quietness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a descendant of Shelah</OL>'),
(8025, '@lX', 'a primitive root', 'shalaph', 'TWOT - 2402', 'saw-laf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to pull out, up or off:--draw (off), grow up, pluck off.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to draw out or off, take off<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to draw out<LI>to draw off<LI>to shoot up, draw out (of blade of grass on roof)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8026, '@lX', 'from (08025)', 'shelaph', 'None', 'sheh\'-lef', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08025»; extract; Sheleph, a son of Jokthan:--Sheleph.', 'Sheleph = \"a drawing forth\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 2nd son of Joktan and a descendant of Shem</OL>'),
(8027, 'XlX', 'a primitive root perhaps originally to intensify, i.e. treble', 'shalash', 'TWOT - 2403', 'shaw-lash\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root perhaps originally to intensify, i.e. treble; but apparently used only as denominative from «07969», to be (causatively, make) triplicate (by restoration, in portions, strands, days or years):--do the third time, (divide into, stay) three (days, - fold, parts, years old).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to do a third time, do three times, divide in three parts<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to do a third time, divide into three parts<LI>(Pual) to be three years of age, be threefold</OL></OL>'),
(8028, 'XlX', 'from (08027)', 'Shelesh', 'None', 'sheh\'-lesh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08027»; triplet; Shelesh, an Israelite:--Shelesh.', 'Shelesh = \"might\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Asherite, son of Helem</OL>'),
(8029, 'XllX', 'from (08027)', 'shillesh', 'TWOT - 2403h', 'shil-laysh\'', 'Adjective', 'from «08027»; a descendant of the third degree, i.e. great grandchild:--third (generation).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pertaining to the third, third (generation)</OL>'),
(8030, 'hXlX', 'fem. from the same as (08028)', 'Shilshah', 'None', 'shil-shaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'feminine from the same as «08028»; triplication; Shilshah, an Israelite:--Shilshah.', 'Shilshah = \"strong\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Asherite, son of Zophah</OL>'),
(8031, 'hXlX', 'from (08027)', 'Shalishah', 'None', 'shaw-lee-shaw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'feminine from «08027»; trebled land; Shalishah, a place in Palestine:--Shalisha.', 'Shalisha = \"thirs\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a district near Mount Ephraim through which Saul passed as he searched for the asses</OL>'),
(8032, '~wXlX', 'from the same as (08028)', 'shilshowm', 'TWOT - 2403c', 'shil-shome\'', 'Adverb', 'or shilshom {shil-shome\'}; from the same as «08028»; trebly, i.e. (in time) day before yesterday:--+ before (that time, - time), excellent things (from the margin), + heretofore, three days, + time past.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>day before yesterday, three days ago<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>an idiom for \'heretofore in times past\'</OL></OL>'),
(8033, '~X', 'a primitive particle [rather from the relative pronoun, (0834)]; there (transferring to time) then', 'sham', 'TWOT - 2404', 'shawm', 'Adverb', 'a primitive particle (rather from the relative pronoun, «0834»); there (transferring to time) then; often thither, or thence:--in it, + thence, there (-in, + of, + out), + thither, + whither.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>there, thither<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>there<LI>thither (after verbs of motion)<LI>from there, thence<LI>then (as an adverb of time)</OL></OL>'),
(8034, '~X', 'a primitive word [perhaps rather from (07760) through the idea of definite and conspicuous position', 'shem', 'TWOT - 2405', 'shame', 'Noun Masculine', 'a primitive word (perhaps rather from «07760» through the idea of definite and conspicuous position; compare «08064»); an appellation, as a mark or memorial of individuality; by implication honor, authority, character:--+ base, (in-)fame(-ous), named(-d), renown, report.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>name<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>name<LI>reputation, fame, glory<LI>the Name (as designation of God)<LI>memorial, monument</OL></OL>'),
(8035, '~X', 'the same as (08034)', 'Shem', 'None', 'shame', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «08034»; name; Shem, a son of Noah (often includ. his posterity):--Sem, Shem.', 'Shem = \"name\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the eldest son of Noah and progenitor of the Semitic tribes</OL>'),
(8036, '~X', 'corresponding to (08034)', 'shum', 'TWOT - 3036', 'shoom', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «08034»:--name.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>name</OL>'),
(8037, 'ammX', 'from (08074)', 'Shamma\'', 'None', 'sham-maw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08074»; desolation; Shamma, an Israelite:--Shamma.', 'Shamma = \"desert\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Asherite, son of Zophar</OL>'),
(8038, 'rbamX', 'apparently from (08034) and (083)', 'Shem\'eber', 'None', 'shem-ay\'-ber', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'apparently from «08034» and «083»; name of pinion, i.e. illustrious; Shemeber, a king of Zeboim:--Shemeber.', 'Shemeber = \"lofty flight\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>king of Zeboim and an ally of the king of Sodom</OL>'),
(8039, 'hamX', 'perhaps for (08093)', 'Shim\'ah', 'None', 'shim-aw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'perhaps for «08093»; Shimah, an Israelite:--Shimah. Compare «08043».', 'Shimeah = \"report\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, son of Mikloth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Shimeam\'</OL></OL>'),
(8040, 'lwamX', 'a primitive word [rather perhaps from the same as (08071) (by insertion of the aleph) through the idea of wrapping up]', 'smo\'wl', 'TWOT - 2267a', 'sem-ole\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or smosl {sem-ole\'}; a primitive word (rather perhaps from the same as «08071» (by insertion of the aleph) through the idea of wrapping up); properly, dark (as enveloped), i.e. the north; hence (by orientation), the left hand:--left (hand, side).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the left, the left hand, the left side<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>left<LI>left hand<LI>north (as one faces east)</OL></OL>'),
(8041, 'lamX', 'a primitive root [denom from (08040)]', 'sama\'l', 'TWOT - 2267', 'saw-mal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (denominative from «08040»); to use the left hand or pass in that direction):--(go, turn) (on the, to the) left.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to take the left, go to the left<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go to the left<LI>to turn (aside) to the left (fig)<LI>to use the left hand</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8042, 'ylamX', 'from (08040)', 'sma\'liy', 'TWOT - 2267b', 'sem-aw-lee\'', 'Adjective', 'from «08040»; situated on the left side:--left.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>left, left side, on the left</OL>'),
(8043, '~amX', 'for (08039) [compare (038)]', 'Shim\'am', 'None', 'shim-awm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'for «08039» (compare «038»); Shimam, an Israelite:--Shimeam.', 'Shimeam = \"their fame\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, son of Mikloth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Shimeah\'</OL></OL>'),
(8044, 'rgmX', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Shamgar', 'None', 'sham-gar\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; Shamgar, an Israelite judge:--Shamgar.', 'Shamgar = \"sword\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Anath and a judge of Israel; with an ox-goad he slew 600 Philistines and delivered Israel</OL>'),
(8045, 'dmX', 'a primitive root', 'shamad', 'TWOT - 2406', 'shaw-mad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to desolate:--destory(- uction), bring to nought, overthrow, perish, pluck down, × utterly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to destroy, exterminate, be destroyed, be exterminated<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be annihilated, be exterminated<LI>to be destroyed, be devastated</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to annihilate, exterminate<LI>to destroy</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8046, 'dmX', 'corresponding to (08045)', 'shmad', 'TWOT - 3037', 'shem-ad\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «08045»:--consume.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Aphel) to destroy</OL>'),
(8047, 'hmmX', 'from (08074)', 'shammah', 'TWOT - 2409d', 'sham-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08074»; ruin; by implication, consternation:--astonishment, desolate(-ion), waste, wonderful thing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>waste, horror, appalment<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a waste (of land, city, etc)<LI>appalment, horror</OL></OL>'),
(8048, 'hmmX', 'the same as (08047)', 'Shammah', 'None', 'sham-maw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «08047»; Shammah, the name of an Edomite and four Israelites:--Shammah.', 'Shammah = \"astonishment\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Reuel, grandson of Esau, and a chief of Edom<LI>the 3rd son of Jesse and a brother of David<LI>son of Agee the Hararite and one of the 30 of David\'s mighty warriors<LI>the Harodite, one of the 30 of David\'s mighty warriors<LI>another Hararite, one of the 30 of David\'s mighty warriors</OL>'),
(8049, 'twhmX', 'for (08048)', 'Shamhuwth', 'None', 'sham-hooth\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'for «08048»; desolation; Shamhuth, an Israelite:--Shamhuth.', 'Shamhuth = \"desolation\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 5th captain (of the military divisions) for the 5th month in the time of David<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Shammoth\' (08054) and \'Shammah\' (08048)</OL></OL>'),
(8050, 'lawmX', 'from the pass part of (08085) and (0410)', 'Shmuw\'el', 'None', 'sehm-oo-ale\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from the passive participle of «08085» and «0410»; heard of God; Shemuel, the name of three Israelites:--Samuel, Shemuel.', 'Samuel = \"his name is El\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Elkanah by his wife Hannah and judge or prophet of Israel during the days of Saul and David<LI>son Ammihud and the prince of the tribe of Simeon who was chosen to divide the land of Canaan between the tribes. Spelled \'Shemuel\'<LI>son of Tola and grandson of Issachar. Spelled \'Shemuel\'</OL>'),
(8051, '[wmmX', 'from (08074)', 'Shammuwa`', 'None', 'sham-moo\'-ah', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08074»; renowned; Shammua, the name of four Israelites:--Shammua, Shammuah.', 'Shammua = \"renowned\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Zaccur and the spy from the tribe of Reuben<LI>son of David by his wife Bathsheba<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Shammuah\' and \'Shimea\'</OL><LI>a Levite, son of Galal and father of Abda who lived in Jerusalem after the return from exile in the time of Nehemiah<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Shemaiah\'</OL><LI>a priest, head of the family of Bilgah in the time of Joiakim after the return from exile</OL>'),
(8052, 'h[wmX', 'pass part of (08074)', 'shmuw`ah', 'TWOT - 2412d', 'sehm-oo-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine passive participle of «08074»; something heard, i.e. an announcement:--bruit, doctrine, fame, mentioned, news, report, rumor, tidings.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>report, news, rumour<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>report, news, tidings<LI>mention</OL></OL>'),
(8053, 'rwmX', 'pass part of (08103)', 'Shamuwr', 'None', 'shaw-moor\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'passive participle of «08103»; observed; Shamur, an Israelite:--Shamir (from the margin).', 'Shamer or Shamir = \"guardian\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite of the sons of Michah in the time of David</OL>'),
(8054, 'twmmX', 'pl. of (08047)', 'Shammowth', 'None', 'sham-moth\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'plural of «08047»; ruins; Shammoth, an Israelite:--Shamoth.', 'Shammoth = \"desolations\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the Harodite, one of the 30 of David\'s mighty warriors</OL>'),
(8055, 'xmX', 'a primitive root', 'samach', 'TWOT - 2268', 'saw-makh\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; probably to brighten up, i.e. (figuratively) be (causatively, make) blithe or gleesome:--cheer up, be (make) glad, (have, make) joy(-ful), be (make) merry, (cause to, make to) rejoice, × very.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rejoice, be glad<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rejoice<LI>to rejoice (arrogantly), exult (at)<LI>to rejoice (religiously)</OL><LI>(Piel) to cause to rejoice, gladden, make glad<LI>(Hiphil) to cause to rejoice, gladden, make glad</OL></OL>'),
(8056, 'xmX', 'from (08055)', 'sameach', 'TWOT - 2268a', 'saw-may\'-akh', 'Adjective', 'from «08055»; blithe or gleeful:--(be) glad, joyful, (making) merry((-hearted), -ily), rejoice(-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>joyful, merry, glad<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>joyful, showing joy<LI>you who rejoice (subst)</OL></OL>'),
(8057, 'hxmX', 'from (08056)', 'simchah', 'TWOT - 2268b', 'sim-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08056»; blithesomeness or glee, (religious or festival):--X exceeding(-ly), gladness, joy(-fulness), mirth, pleasure, rejoice(-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>joy, mirth, gladness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>mirth, gladness, joy, gaiety, pleasure<LI>joy (of God)<LI>glad result, happy issue</OL></OL>'),
(8058, 'tmX', 'a primitive root', 'shamat', 'TWOT - 2408', 'shaw-mat\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to fling down; incipiently to jostle; figuratively, to let alone, desist, remit:--discontinue, overthrow, release, let rest, shake, stumble, throw down.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to release, let drop or loose or rest or fall<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to let drop or fall<LI>(Niphal) to be made to fall down, be thrown down<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to let drop<LI>to release, let drop</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8059, 'httmX', 'from (08058)', 'shmittah', 'TWOT - 2408a', 'shem-it-taw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08058»; remission (of debt) or suspension of labor):--release.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>letting drop of exactions, (temporary) remitting, release (from debt)</OL>'),
(8060, 'ymmX', 'from (08073)', 'Shammay', 'None', 'sham-mah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08073»; destructive; Shammai, the name of three Israelites:--Shammai.', 'Shammai = \"desolate\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Judaite, son of Onam and descendant of Jerahmeel<LI>a Judaite, son of Rekem, father of Maon, and descendant of Jerahmeel\'s brother, Caleb<LI>a Judaite, son of Mered and brother of Miriam and Ishbah</OL>'),
(8061, '[dymX', 'apparently from (08034) and (03045)', 'Shmiyda`', 'None', 'shem-ee-daw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'apparently from «08034» and «03045»; name of knowing; Shemida, an Israelite:--Shemida, Shemidah.', 'Shemida = \"wise\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Gilead, grandson of Manasseh, and progenitor of a family in Manasseh</OL>'),
(8062, 'y[dymX', 'patronymically from (08061)', 'Shmiyda`iy', 'None', 'shem-ee-daw-ee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'patronymically from «08061»; a Shemidaite (collectively) or descendants of Shemida:--Shemidaites.', 'Shemidaites = see Shemida \"wise\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Shemida, the son of Gilead and grandson of Manasseh</OL>'),
(8063, 'hkymX', 'from (05564)', 'smiykah', 'TWOT - 2269a', 'sem-ee-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05564»; a run (as sustaining the Oriental sitter):--mantle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rug, coverlet, thick coverlet</OL>'),
(8064, '~ymX', 'from an unused root meaning to be lofty', 'shamayim', 'TWOT - 2407a', 'shaw-mah\'-yim', 'Noun Masculine', 'dual of an unused singular shameh {shaw-meh\'}; from an unused root meaning to be lofty; the sky (as aloft; the dual perhaps alluding to the visible arch in which the clouds move, as well as to the higher ether where the celestial bodies revolve):--air, × astrologer, heaven(-s).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>heaven, heavens, sky<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>visible heavens, sky<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>as abode of the stars<LI>as the visible universe, the sky, atmosphere, etc</OL><LI>Heaven (as the abode of God)</OL></OL>'),
(8065, '!ymX', 'corresponding to (08064)', 'shamayin', 'TWOT - 3038', 'shaw-mah\'-yin', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «08064»:--heaven.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>heaven, heavens, sky<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>visible sky<LI>Heaven (as abode of God)</OL></OL>'),
(8066, 'ynymX', 'from (08083)', 'shmiyniy', 'TWOT - 2411c', 'shem-ee-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'from «08083»; eight:--eight.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>eighth (ordinal number)</OL>'),
(8067, 'tynymX', 'from (08066)', 'shmiyniyth', 'TWOT - 2411c', 'shem-ee-neeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «08066»; probably an eight-stringed lyre:--Sheminith.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Sheminith<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps an eight-stringed musical instrument<LI>perhaps a musical notation, i.e. an octave</OL></OL>'),
(8068, 'rymX', 'from (08104) in the original sense of pricking', 'shamiyr', 'TWOT - 2416a', 'shaw-meer\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08104» in the original sense of pricking; a thorn; also (from its keenness for scratching) a gem, probably the diamond:--adamant (stone), brier, diamond.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thorn(s), adamant, flint<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>thorns, thorn-bushes<LI>adamant (as sharp)<LI>a sharp stone, flint<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>perhaps a diamond</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8069, 'rymX', 'the same as (08068)', 'Shamiyr', 'pr n loc', 'shaw-meer\'', '', 'the same as «08068»; Shamir, the name of two places in Palestine:--Shamir. Compare «08053».', 'Shamir = \"a point\" or \"thorn\" n pr loc<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in the mountain district of Judah<LI>a town in Ephraim where the judge Tola lived and was buried</OL>'),
(8070, 'twmrymX', 'probably from (08034) and plural of (07413)', 'Shmiyramowth', 'None', 'shem-ee-raw-moth\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Shmariymowth {shem-aw-ree- moth\'}; probably from «08034» and plural of «07413»; name of heights; Shemiramoth, the name of two Israelites:--Shemiramoth.', 'Shemiramoth = \"name of heights\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Merarite Levite in the second rank in the choir of David<LI>a Levite in the time of king Jehoshaphat of Judah</OL>'),
(8071, 'hlmX', 'perhaps by permutation for the fem. of (05566) (through the idea of a cover assuming the shape of the object beneath)', 'simlah', 'TWOT - 2270a', 'sim-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'perhaps by permutation for the feminine of «05566» (through the idea of a cover assuming the shape of the object beneath); a dress, especially a mantle:--apparel, cloth(-es, -ing), garment, raiment. Compare «08008».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wrapper, mantle, covering garment, garments, clothes, raiment, a cloth</OL>'),
(8072, 'hlmX', 'probably for the same as (08071)', 'Samlah', 'None', 'sam-law\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably for the same as «08071»; Samlah, an Edomite:--Samlah.', 'Samlah = \"garment\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a king of Moab and successor of Hadad or Hadar</OL>'),
(8073, 'ylmX', 'for (08014)', 'Shamlay', 'None', 'sham-lah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'for «08014»; Shamlai, one of the Nethinim:--Shalmai (from the margin).', 'Shalmai = \"my garments\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a family, descendants of Shamlai, of temple slaves who returned from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(8074, '~mX', 'a primitive root', 'shamem', 'TWOT - 2409', 'shaw-mame\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to stun (or intransitively, grow numb), i.e. devastate or (figuratively) stupefy (both usually in a passive sense):--make amazed, be astonied, (be an) astonish(-ment), (be, bring into, unto, lay, lie, make) desolate(-ion, places), be destitute, destroy (self), (lay, lie, make) waste, wonder.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be desolate, be appalled, stun, stupefy<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be desolated, be deflowered, be deserted, be appalled<LI>to be appalled, be awestruck</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be desolated, be made desolate<LI>to be appalled</OL><LI>(Polel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be stunned<LI>appalling, causing horror (participle) 1c</OL><LI>horror-causer, appaller (subst)<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to devastate, ravage, make desolated<LI>to appal, show horror</OL><LI>(Hophal) to lay desolate, be desolated<LI>(Hithpolel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to be desolate<LI>to be appalled, be astounded<LI>to cause oneself desolation, cause oneself ruin</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8075, '~mX', 'corresponding to (08074)', 'shmam', 'TWOT - 3039', 'shem-am\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «08074»:--be astonied.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Ithpolel) [CLBL] to be appalled, be stunned</OL>'),
(8076, '~mX', 'from (08074)', 'shamem', 'TWOT - 2409a', 'shaw-mame\'', 'Adjective', 'from «08074»; ruined:--desolate.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>devastated, deserted, desolate</OL>'),
(8077, 'hmmX', 'from (08076)', 'shmamah', 'TWOT - 2409b,2409c', 'shem-aw-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or shimamah {shee-mam-aw\'}; feminine of «08076»; devastation; figuratively, astonishment:--(laid, × most) desolate(- ion), waste.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>devastation, waste, desolation</OL>'),
(8078, '!wmmmX', 'from (08074)', 'shimmamown', 'TWOT - 2409e', 'shim-maw-mone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08074»; stupefaction:--astonishment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>horror, dismay, appalment</OL>'),
(8079, 'tymmX', 'probably from (08074) (in the sense of poisoning)', 'smamiyth', 'TWOT - 2271', 'sem-aw-meeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'probably from «08074» (in the sense of poisoning); a lizard (from the superstition of its noxiousness):--spider.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a kind of lizard</OL>'),
(8080, '!mX', 'a primitive root', 'shaman', 'TWOT - 2410', 'shaw-man\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to shine, i.e. (by analogy) be (causatively, make) oily or gross:--become (make, wax) fat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or become fat, grow fat<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) fat (subst)<LI>(Hiphil) to make fat, show fatness</OL></OL>'),
(8081, '!mX', 'from (08080)', 'shemen', 'TWOT - 2410c', 'sheh\'-men', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08080»; grease, especially liquid (as from the olive, often perfumed); figuratively, richness:--anointing, × fat (things), × fruitful, oil((-ed)), ointment, olive, + pine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fat, oil<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>fat, fatness<LI>oil, olive oil<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>as staple, medicament or unguent<LI>for anointing</OL><LI>fat (of fruitful land, valleys) (metaph)</OL></OL>'),
(8082, '!mX', 'from (08080)', 'shamen', 'TWOT - 2410a', 'shaw-mane\'', 'Adjective', 'from «08080»; greasy, i.e. gross; figuratively, rich:--fat, lusty, plenteous.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fat, rich, robust<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>fat, rich (of food)<LI>stout, robust (of men)</OL></OL>'),
(8083, 'hnmX', 'apparently from (08082) through the idea of plumpness', 'shmoneh', 'TWOT - 2411a', 'shem-o-neh\'', 'Noun', 'or shmowneh {shem-o-neh\'}; feminine shmonah {shem-o-naw\'}; or shmownah {shem-o-naw\'}; apparently from «08082» through the idea of plumpness; a cardinal number, eight (as if a surplus above the \"perfect\" seven); also (as ordinal) eighth:--eight((-een, -eenth)), eighth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>eight, eighth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>eight (as cardinal number)<LI>eighth (as ordinal number)<LI>in combination with other numbers</OL></OL>'),
(8084, '~ynmX', 'mult from (08083)', 'shmoniym', 'TWOT - 2411b', 'shem-o-neem\'', 'Adjective', 'or shmowniym {shem-o-neem\'}; mult. from «08083»; eighty, also eightieth:--eighty(-ieth), fourscore.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>eighty, fourscore<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>eighty (as cardinal number)<LI>eightieth (as ordinal number)<LI>in combination with other numbers</OL></OL>'),
(8085, '[mX', 'a primitive root', 'shama`', 'TWOT - 2412, 2412a', 'shaw-mah\'', '', 'a primitive root; to hear intelligently (often with implication of attention, obedience, etc.; causatively, to tell, etc.):--X attentively, call (gather) together, ×  carefully, × certainly, consent, consider, be content, declare, × diligently, discern, give ear, (cause to, let, make to) hear(-ken, tell), × indeed, listen, make (a) noise, (be) obedient, obey, perceive, (make a) proclaim(-ation), publish, regard, report, shew (forth), (make a) sound, × surely, tell, understand, whosoever (heareth), witness.', 'v<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hear, listen to, obey<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hear (perceive by ear)<LI>to hear of or concerning<LI>to hear (have power to hear)<LI>to hear with attention or interest, listen to<LI>to understand (language)<LI>to hear (of judicial cases)<LI>to listen, give heed 1a</OL><LI>to consent, agree 1a<LI>to grant request<OL TYPE=\"8\"><LI>to listen to, yield to<LI>to obey, be obedient</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be heard (of voice or sound)<LI>to be heard of<LI>to be regarded, be obeyed</OL><LI>(Piel) to cause to hear, call to hear, summon<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to hear, tell, proclaim, utter a sound<LI>to sound aloud (musical term)<LI>to make proclamation, summon<LI>to cause to be heard n m</OL></OL><LI>sound</OL>'),
(8086, '[mX', 'corresponding to (08085)', 'shma`', 'TWOT - 3040', 'shem-ah\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «08085»:--hear, obey.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hear<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to hear, have a sense of hearing<LI>(Ithpael) to show oneself obedient</OL></OL>'),
(8087, '[mX', 'for the same as (08088)', 'Shema`', 'None', 'sheh\'-mah', '', 'for the same as «08088»; Shema, the name of a place in Palestine and of four Israelites:--Shema.', 'Shema = \"hear\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Reubenite, son of Joel, father of Azaz, and grandfather of Bela<LI>a Judaite, son of Hebron and father of Raham<LI>a Benjamite, son of Elpaal who along with his brother Beriah were heads of their fathers houses in Aijalon and who drove out the inhabitants of Gath. Probably the same as \'Shimhi\'<LI>an Israelite who stood on the right hand of Ezra as he read the Law to the people</OL>'),
(8088, '[mX', 'from (08085)', 'shema`', 'TWOT - 2412b', 'shay\'-mah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08085»; something heard, i.e. a sound, rumor, announcement; abstractly, audience:--bruit, fame, hear(-ing), loud, report, speech, tidings.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>report, a hearing</OL>'),
(8089, '[mX', 'from (08085)', 'shoma`', 'TWOT - 2412c', 'sho\'-mah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08085»; a report:--fame.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>report, rumour, news, fame</OL>'),
(8090, '[mX', 'for (08087)', 'Shma`', 'None', 'shem-aw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'for «08087»; Shema, a place in Palestine:--Shema.', 'Shema = \"hear\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Judah at the limits of the tribe toward Edom in the south<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>same as 08088; this word 08090 not found in the Hebrew text</OL></OL>'),
(8091, '[mX', 'from (08085)', 'Shama`', 'None', 'shaw-maw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08085»; obedient; Shama, an Israelite:--Shama.', 'Shama = \"obedient\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Hotham the Aroerite, brother of Jeiel, both listed as mighty warriors of David</OL>'),
(8092, 'a[mX', 'for (08093)', 'Shim`a\'', 'None', 'shim-aw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'for «08093»; Shima, the name of four Israelites:--Shimea, Shimei, Shamma.', 'Shimea = \"fame\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of David by Bathsheba<LI>brother of David, the 3rd son of Jesse<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Shammah\', \'Shimma\', and \'Shimeah\'</OL><LI>a Gershonite Levite, father of Berachiah, and grandfather of Asaph<LI>a Merarite Levite, son of Uzzah, and father of Haggiah</OL>'),
(8093, 'h[mX', 'fem. of (08088)', 'Shim`ah', 'None', 'shim-aw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'feminine of «08088»; annunciation; Shimah, an Israelite:--Shimeah.', 'Shimeah = \"fame\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>brother of David, the 3rd son of Jesse<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>also \'Shammah\', and \'Shimma\'</OL></OL>'),
(8094, 'h[mX', 'for (08093)', 'Shma`ah', 'None', 'shem-aw-aw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'for «08093»; Shemaah, an Israelite:--Shemaah.', 'Shemaah = \"the rumour\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, the Gibeathite, father of Ahiezer and Joash, both mighty warriors of David who joined him at Ziklag</OL>'),
(8095, '!w[mX', 'from (08085)', 'Shim`own', 'None', 'shim-one\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08085»; hearing; Shimon, one of Jacob\'s sons, also the tribe descended from him:--Simeon.', 'Simeon or Shimeon = \"heard\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the 2nd son of Jacob by his wife Leah and progenitor of the tribe of Simeon<LI>an Israelite of the sons of Bani who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(8096, 'y[mX', 'from (08088)', 'Shim`iy', 'None', 'shim-ee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08088»; famous; Shimi, the name of twenty Israelites:--Shimeah (from the margin), Shimei, Shimhi, Shimi.', 'Shimei or Shimhi or Shimi or Shimea = \"renowned\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, son of Gera of the house of Saul in the time of David<LI>a Benjamite, son of Elah and commissariat officer in the time of Solomon<LI>the Ramathite in charge of the vineyards of David<LI>son of Gershon and grandson of Levi<LI>a Levite, son of Jeduthun and chief of the 10th division of singers in the time of David<LI>a Levite of the sons of Heman who took part in the purification of the temple in the time of king Hezekiah of Judah<LI>a Levite, brother of Cononiah in charge of receiving the tithes and offerings in the reign of king Hezekiah of Judah<LI>a Levite who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>a Judaite, son of Pedaiah and brother of Zerubbabel<LI>a Simeonite, son of Zacchur<LI>a Reubenite, son of Gog and father of Micah<LI>one of the sons of Hashum who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>one of the sons of Bani who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>a Benjamite, son of Kish, father of Jair, and grandfather of Mordecai in the time of Esther<LI>a Levite, son of Jahath, grandson of Gershon, and great grandson of Levi<LI>Benjamite, father of Adaiah, Beraiah, and Shimrath. Spelled \'Shimhi\'</OL>'),
(8097, 'y[mX', 'patronymically from (08096)', 'Shim`iy', 'None', 'shim-ee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'patronymically from «08096»; a Shimite (collectively) or descendants of Shimi:--of Shimi, Shimites.', 'Shimites = see Shimei \"renowned\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Shimei or Shimi</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(8098, 'hy[mX', 'from (08085) and (03050)', 'Shma`yah', 'None', 'shem-aw-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Shmamyahuw {shem-aw-yaw\'-hoo}; from «08085» and «03050»; Jah has heard; Shemajah, the name of twenty-five Israelites:--Shemaiah.', 'Shemaiah = \"heard by Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a prophet of the Lord in the reign of king Rehoboam of Judah<LI>the Nehelamite, a false prophet in the time of the prophet Jeremiah<LI>father of Delaiah, one of the princes of Judah in the time of the prophet Jeremiah<LI>an inhabitant of Kirjathjearim and father of Urijah, a prophet of the Lord in the time of the prophet Jeremiah<LI>a Judaite, son of Shechaniah, father of Hattush, and descendant of Zerubbabel<LI>a Simeonite, father of Shimri<LI>a Reubenite, son of Joel and father of Gog<LI>a Merarite Levite, son of Hasshub in the time of Nehemiah<LI>a Levite, son of Galal and father of Obadiah<LI>a Levite and head of the family of the sons of Elizaphan who were commissioned to bring the ark to Jerusalem in the time of David<LI>a Levite and scribe, son of Nethaneel in the time of David<LI>a Levite, 1st son of Obed-Edom in the time of David<LI>a Levite, descendant of Jeduthun the singer in the time of king Hezekiah of Judah<LI>a Levite, one of the messengers of Ezra to Iddo<LI>a Levite in the time of king Jehoshaphat of Judah<LI>a Levite, one of several in charge of distributing the free will offerings brought to God to their Levite brethren in the time of king Hezekiah of Judah<LI>a Levite in the time of king Josiah of Judah<LI>head of a family of exiles who returned with Ezra<LI>a priest, of the sons of Harim who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>an Israelite of the sons of Harim who had a foreign wife in the time of Ezra<LI>son of Delaiah, grandson of Mehetabeel, and a false prophet hired by Tobiah and Sanballat to give false guidance to Nehemiah<LI>a priest who sealed the covenant with Nehemiah and participated in the dedication of the wall<LI>a priest who returned from exile with Zerubbabel<LI>a leader of the people at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem in the time of Nehemiah<LI>grandfather of the priest Zechariah who participated in the dedication of the wall in the time of Nehemiah<LI>another of the priests who along with 25 took part in the dedication of the wall in the time of Nehemiah</OL>'),
(8099, 'yn[mX', 'patronymically from (08095)', 'Shim`oniy', 'None', 'shim-o-nee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'patronymically from «08095»; a Shimonite (collectively) or descendants of Shimon:--tribe of Simeon, Simeonites.', 'Simeonites = see Simeon \"harkening\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Simeon</OL>'),
(8100, 't[mX', 'from (08088)', 'Shim`ath', 'None', 'shim-awth\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'feminine of «08088»; annunciation; Shimath, an Ammonitess:--Shimath.', 'Shimeath = \"report\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Ammonitess, mother of Jozachar or Zabad, one of the assassins of king Joash of Judah</OL>'),
(8101, 'yt[mX', 'patronymically from (08093)', 'Shim`athiy', 'None', 'shim-aw-thee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'patronymically from «08093»; a Shimathite (collectively) or descendants of Shimah:--Shimeathites.', 'Shimeathites =see Shimeath \"report\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a family of scribes</OL>'),
(8102, '#mX', 'from an unused root meaning to emit a sound', 'shemets', 'TWOT - 2413a', 'sheh\'-mets', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to emit a sound; an inkling:--a little.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>whisper, little</OL>'),
(8103, 'hcmX', 'from (08102)', 'shimtsah', 'TWOT - 2413b', 'shim-tsaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «08102»; scornful whispering (of hostile spectators):--shame.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>whisper, derision, whispering</OL>'),
(8104, 'rmX', 'a primitive root', 'shamar', 'TWOT - 2414', 'shaw-mar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to hedge about (as with thorns), i.e. guard; generally, to protect, attend to, etc.:--beward, be circumspect, take heed (to self), keep(-er, self), mark, look narrowly, observe, preserve, regard, reserve, save (self), sure, (that lay) wait (for), watch(-man).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to keep, guard, observe, give heed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to keep, have charge of<LI>to keep, guard, keep watch and ward, protect, save life 1a</OL><LI>watch, watchman (participle)<OL TYPE=\"3\"><LI>to watch for, wait for<LI>to watch, observe<LI>to keep, retain, treasure up (in memory)<LI>to keep (within bounds), restrain<LI>to observe, celebrate, keep (sabbath or covenant or commands), perform (vow)<LI>to keep, preserve, protect<LI>to keep, reserve</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be on one\'s guard, take heed, take care, beware<LI>to keep oneself, refrain, abstain<LI>to be kept, be guarded</OL><LI>(Piel) to keep, pay heed<LI>(Hithpael) to keep oneself from</OL></OL>'),
