(8138, 'hnX', 'a primitive root', 'shanah', 'TWOT - 2421', 'shaw-naw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to fold, i.e. duplicate (literally or figuratively); by implication, to transmute (transitive or intransitive):--do (speak, strike) again, alter, double, (be given to) change, disguise, (be) diverse, pervert, prefer, repeat, return, do the second time.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to repeat, do again, change, alter<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to change<LI>(Niphal) to be repeated<LI>(Piel) to change, alter<LI>(Hithpael) to disguise oneself</OL></OL>'),
