(8165, 'ry[X', 'formed like (08163)', 'Se`iyr', 'TWOT - 2274h,2274g', 'say-eer\'', '', 'formed like «08163»; rough; Seir, a mountain of Idumaea and its aboriginal occupants, also one in Palestine:--Seir.', 'Seir = \"hairy\" or \"shaggy\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>patriarch of the Horites, the inhabitants of Edom before the descendants of Esau, the Edomites n pr terr<LI>the land of Edom, south of the Dead Sea n pr mont<LI>a mountain range in Edom extending from the Dead Sea to the Elanitic Gulf<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>apparently also called \'Mount Seir\' and extending most of the distance of the mountain range itself</OL><LI>a mountain in northern Judah lying westward from Kirjath-jearim</OL>'),
(8166, 'hry[X', 'from (08163)', 's`iyrah', 'None', 'seh-ee-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «08163»; a she-goat:--kid.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>she-goat</OL>'),
(8167, 'hry[X', 'formed as (08166)', 'S`iyrah', 'None', 'seh-ee-raw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'formed as «08166»; roughness; Seirah, a place in Palestine:--Seirath.', 'Seirath = \"the shaggy\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place probably in southeast Ephraim</OL>'),
(8168, 'l[X', 'from an unused root meaning to hollow out', 'sho`al', 'TWOT - 2432a', 'sho\'-al', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to hollow out; the palm; by extension, a handful:--handful, hollow of the hand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hollow hand, hollow of hand, handful<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>hollow hand, hollow of hand<LI>handful</OL></OL>'),
(8169, '~ybl[X', 'pl. from (07776)', 'Sha`albiym', 'None', 'shah-al-beem\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Sha.alabbiyn {shah-al-ab-been\'}; plural from «07776»; fox-holes; Shaalbim or Shaalabbin, a place in Palestine:--Shaalabbin, Shaalbim.', 'Shaalbim or Shaalabbin = \"place of foxes\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Dan occupied by the Amorites</OL>'),
(8170, 'ynbl[X', 'patrial from (08169)', 'Sha`alboniy', 'None', 'shah-al-bo-nee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'patrial from «08169»; a Shaalbonite or inhabitant of Shaalbin:--Shaalbonite.', 'Shaalbonite = see Shaalbim \"place of foxes\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Shaalbim or Shaalabbin</OL>'),
(8171, '~yl[X', 'pl. of (07776)', 'Sha`aliym', 'None', 'shah-al-eem\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'plural of «07776»; foxes; Shaalim, a place in Palestine:--Shalim.', 'Shalim = \"foxes\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a district in Israel</OL>'),
(8172, '![X', 'a primitive root', 'sha`an', 'TWOT - 2434', 'shaw-an\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to support one\'s self:--lean, lie, rely, rest (on, self), stay.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lean on, trust in, support<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to lean, lean upon, support oneself<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of trust in God (fig)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8173, '[[X', 'a primitive root', 'sha`a`', 'TWOT - 2435,2436', 'shaw-ah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; (in a good acceptation) to look upon (with complacency), i.e. fondle, please or amuse (self); (in a bad one) to look about (in dismay), i.e. stare:--cry (out) (by confusion with «07768»), dandle, delight (self), play, shut.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to stroke, be smeared over, be blinded<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be smeared over, be blinded<LI>to smear eyes shut</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to besmear (of eyes), smear over eyes<LI>(Hithpalpel) to blind oneself, be blinded</OL><LI>to sport, take delight in<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pilpel) to sport, delight in, take delight in, delight oneself<LI>(Palpal) to be fondled<LI>(Hithpalpel) to delight oneself</OL></OL>'),
(8174, '@[X', 'from (05586)', 'Sha`aph', 'None', 'shah\'-af', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «05586»; fluctuation; Shaaph, the name of two Israelites:--Shaaph.', 'Shaaph = \"division\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Jahdai of the family of Caleb, the brother of Jerahmeel<LI>son of Caleb, the brother of Jerahmeel, by his concubine Maachah and father of Madmannah</OL>'),
(8175, 'r[X', 'a primitive root', 'sa`ar', 'TWOT - 2274d,2275,2276', 'saw-ar\'', '', 'a primitive root; to storm; by implication, to shiver, i.e. fear:--be (horribly) afraid, fear, hurl as a storm, be tempestuous, come like (take away as with) a whirlwind.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to storm, shiver, dread, bristle (with horror), be very afraid<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bristle (with horror)<LI>to dread</OL></OL><LI>to storm away, sweep away, whirl away<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sweep away<LI>to storm away (of God\'s action against the wicked) (fig)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be stormy, be tempestuous (exceedingly)<LI>(Piel) to whirl away, be stormed away<LI>(Hithpael) to storm against, come as a storm</OL></OL>'),
(8176, 'r[X', 'primitive root', 'sha`ar', 'TWOT - 2438', 'shaw-ar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to split or open, i.e. (literally, but only as denominative from «08179») to act as gate-keeper (see «07778»): (figuratively) to estimate:--think.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to split open, reason out, calculate, reckon, estimate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to calculate Pr 23:7</OL></OL>'),
(8177, 'r[X', 'corresponding to (08181)', 's`ar', 'TWOT - 3011', 'seh-ar\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «08181»; hair:--hair.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hair (of head)</OL>'),
(8178, 'r[X', 'from (08175)', 'sa`ar', 'TWOT - 2275a', 'sah\'-ar', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08175»; a tempest; also a terror:--affrighted, ×  horribly, × sore, storm. See «08181».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>storm, tempest, terror, horror</OL>'),
(8179, 'r[X', 'from (08176) in its original sense', 'sha`ar', 'TWOT - 2437a', 'shah\'-ar', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08176» in its original sense; an opening, i.e. door or gate:--city, door, gate, port (X -er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>gate (of entrance)<LI>gate (of space inside gate, i.e. marketplace, public meeting place)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>city, town</OL><LI>gate (of palace, royal castle, temple, court of tabernacle)<LI>heaven</OL></OL>'),
(8180, 'r[X', 'from (08176)', 'sha`ar', 'TWOT - 2438a', 'shah\'-ar', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08176»; a measure (as a section):--(hundred-)fold.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a unit of measure<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>100 measures = 100 for 1 = 100 fold</OL></OL>'),
(8181, 'r[X', 'from (08175) in the sense of dishevelling', 'se`ar', 'TWOT - 2274a', 'say-awr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or sa.ar (Isaiah 7:20) {sah\'-ar}; from «08175» in the sense of dishevelling; hair (as if tossed or bristling):--hair(-y), ×  rough.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hair<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>hair (of animals, man)<LI>hair (of garment made of hair)</OL></OL>'),
(8182, 'r[X', 'from (08176)', 'sho`ar', 'TWOT - 2439a', 'sho-awr\'', 'Adjective', 'from «08176»; harsh or horrid, i.e. offensive:--vile.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>horrid, disgusting, vile, offensive</OL>'),
(8183, 'hr[X', 'from (08178)', 's`arah', 'TWOT - 2275b', 'seh-aw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «08178»; a hurricane:--storm, tempest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>storm</OL>'),
(8184, 'hr[X', 'from (08175) in the sense of roughness', 's`orah', 'TWOT - 2274f', 'seh-o-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or snowrah {seh-o-raw\'} (feminine meaning the plant); and (masculine meaning the grain); also s or {seh-ore\'}; or s-owr {seh-ore\'}; from «08175» in the sense of roughness; barley (as villose):--barley.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>barley<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>barley (of the plant)<LI>barley (of the meal or grain)</OL></OL>'),
(8185, 'hr[X', 'from (08181)', 'sa`arah', 'TWOT - 2274b', 'sah-ar-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «08181»; hairiness:--hair.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a single hair</OL>'),
(8186, 'hrwr[X', 'from (08176) in the sense of (08175)', 'sha`aruwrah', 'TWOT - 2439b', 'shah-ar-oo-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or shanariyriyah {shah-ar-ee-ree-yaw\'}; or shaparurith {shah-ar-oo-reeth\'}; feminine from «08176» in the sense of «08175»; something fearful:--horrible thing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>horrible thing</OL>'),
(8187, 'hyr[X', 'from (08176) and (03050)', 'Sh`aryah', 'None', 'sheh-ar-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08176» and «03050»; Jah has stormed; Shearjah, an Israelite:--Sheariah.', 'Sheariah = \"valued by Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite of the family of Saul, one of the 6 sons of Azel</OL>'),
(8188, '~yr[X', 'pl. of (08184)', 'S`oriym', 'None', 'seh-o-reem\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'masculine plural of «08184»; barley grains; Seorim, an Israelite:--Seorim.', 'Seorim = \"barley\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest in the time of David in charge of the 4th course of service</OL>'),
(8189, '~yr[X', 'dual of (08179)', 'Sha`arayim', 'None', 'shah-ar-ah\'-yim', 'Proper Name Location', 'dual of «08179»; double gates; Shaarajim, a place in Palestine:--Shaaraim.', 'Shaaraim = \"double gate\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Judah<LI>a town in Simeon</OL>'),
(8190, 'zgX[X', 'of Persian derivation', 'Sha`ashgaz', 'None', 'shah-ash-gaz\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of Persian derivation; Shaashgaz, a eunuch of Xerxes:--Shaashgaz.', 'Shaashgaz = \"servant of the beautiful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the eunuch in the palace of Xerxes who was in charge of the women in the 2nd house</OL>'),
(8191, '[X[X', 'from (08173)', 'sha`shua`', 'TWOT - 2436a', 'shah-shoo\'-ah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08173»; enjoyment:--delight, pleasure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>delight, enjoyment<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>delight<LI>object of delight</OL></OL>'),
(8192, 'hpX', 'a primitive root', 'shaphah', 'TWOT - 2440', 'shaw-faw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to abrade, i.e. bare:--high, stick out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sweep bare, scrape<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be wind-swept, be bare, be scraped barren (by wind)<LI>(Pual) to be bare, be laid bare</OL></OL>'),
(8193, 'hpX', 'probably from (05595) or (08192) through the idea of termination (compare (05490))', 'saphah', 'TWOT - 2278a', 'saw-faw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or (in dual and plural) sepheth {sef-eth\'}; probably from «05595» or «08192» through the idea of termination (compare «05490»); the lip (as a natural boundary); by implication, language; by analogy, a margin (of a vessel, water, cloth, etc.):--band, bank, binding, border, brim, brink, edge, language, lip, prating, ((sea-))shore, side, speech, talk, (vain) words.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lip, language, speech, shore, bank, brink, brim, side, edge, border, binding<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>lip (as body part)<LI>language<LI>edge, shore, bank (of cup, sea, river, etc)</OL></OL>'),
(8194, 'hpX', 'from (08192) in the sense of clarifying', 'shaphah', 'TWOT - 2440a', 'shaw-faw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08192» in the sense of clarifying; a cheese (as strained from the whey):--cheese.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cream, cheese<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(8195, 'wpX', 'from (08192)', 'Shphow', 'None', 'shef-o\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Shphiy {shef-ee\'}; from «08192»; baldness (compare «08205»); Shepho or Shephi, an Idumaean:--Shephi, Shepho.', 'Shepho or Shephi = \"bold\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Edomite, son of Shobal of the sons of Seir</OL>'),
(8196, 'twpX', 'from (08199)', 'shphowt', 'TWOT - 2443b', 'shef-ote\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or shphuwt {shef-oot\'}; from «08199»; a judicial sentence, i.e. punishment:--judgment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>judgment, act of judgment</OL>'),
(8197, '~pwpX', 'from the same as (08207)', 'Shphuwpham', 'None', 'shef-oo-fawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Shphuwphan {shef-oo-fawn\'}; from the same as «08207»; serpent-like; Shephupham or Shephuphan, an Israelite:-- Shephuphan, Shupham.', 'Shephuphan or Shupham = \"serpent\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Bela and grandson of Benjamin</OL>'),
(8198, 'hxpX', 'from the same as (8207)\">(08207))', 'shiphchah', 'None', 'shif-khaw\'', '', 'feminine from an unused root meaning to spread out (as a family; see «04940»); a female slave (as a member of the household):--(bond-, hand-)maid(-en, -servant), wench, bondwoman, womanservant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>maid, maid-servant, slavegirl<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>maid, maid-servant (as belonging to a mistress)<LI>of address, speaker, humility (fig)</OL></OL>'),
(8199, 'tpX', 'a primitive root', 'shaphat', 'TWOT - 2443', 'shaw-fat\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to judge, i.e. pronounce sentence (for or against); by implication, to vindicate or punish; by extenssion, to govern; passively, to litigate (literally or figuratively):--+ avenge, × that condemn, contend, defend, execute (judgment), (be a) judge(-ment), × needs, plead, reason, rule.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to judge, govern, vindicate, punish<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to act as law-giver or judge or governor (of God, man) 1a</OL><LI>to rule, govern, judge<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to decide controversy (of God, man)<LI>to execute judgment 1a</OL><LI>discriminating (of man) 1a<LI>vindicating 1a<LI>condemning and punishing 1a<LI>at theophanic advent for final judgment<LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to enter into controversy, plead, have controversy together<LI>to be judged</OL><LI>(Poel) judge, opponent-at-law (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(8200, 'tpX', 'corresponding to (08199)', 'shphat', 'TWOT - 2045', 'shef-at\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «08199»; to judge:--magistrate.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to judge<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) judge (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(8201, 'tpX', 'from (08199)', 'shephet', 'TWOT - 2443a', 'sheh\'-fet', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08199»; a sentence, i.e. infliction:--judgment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>judgment, act of judgment</OL>'),
(8202, 'tpX', 'from (08199)', 'Shaphat', 'None', 'shaw-fawt\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08199»; judge; Shaphat, the name of four Israelites:--Shaphat.', 'Shaphat = \"judged\" or \"he hath judged\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Hori and the prince of Simeon chosen to spy out the promised land<LI>father of the prophet Elisha<LI>a Judaite, son of Shemaiah and descendant of Zerubbabel in the royal line of Judah<LI>a chief of the tribe of Gad<LI>son of Adlai and chief herdsman for David over the herds in the valleys</OL>'),
(8203, 'hytpX', 'from (08199) and (03050)', 'Shphatyah', 'None', 'shef-at-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Shphatyahuw {shef-at-yaw\'-hoo}; from «08199» and «03050»; Jah has judged; Shephatjah, the name of ten Israelites:-- Shephatiah.', 'Shephatiah = \"Jehovah has judged\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of David by Abital; David\'s 5th son<LI>head of a family of exiles returning from Babylon with Zerubbabel<LI>another head of a family of exiles returning from Babylon with Zerubbabel<LI>a Judaite, son of Mahalaleel and father of Amariah<LI>a prince of Judah, son of Mattan and one of the counsellors who advised king Zedekiah of Judah to kill the prophet Jeremiah<LI>the Haruphite, one of David\'s mighty warriors who joined him at Ziklag<LI>son of Maachah and prince of the tribe of Simeon in the time of David<LI>son of king Jehoshaphat of Judah and brother to his successor Jehoram</OL>'),
(8204, '!tpX', 'from (08199)', 'Shiphtan', 'None', 'shif-tawn\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08199»; judge-like; Shiphtan, an Israelite:--Shiphtan.', 'Shiphtan = \"judicial\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Ephraimite, father of Kemuel, the leader of the tribe selected to divide the promised land between the tribes</OL>'),
(8205, 'ypX', 'from (08192)', 'shphiy', 'TWOT - 2440b', 'shef-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08192»; bareness; concretely, a bare hill or plain:--high place, stick out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bareness, smooth or bare height, bare place, high places, barren height<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>bareness<LI>bare place, bare height</OL></OL>'),
(8206, '~yppX', 'pl. of an unused noun from the same as (08207) and meaning the same', 'Shuppiym', 'None', 'shoop-peem\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'plural of an unused noun from the same as «08207» and meaning the same; serpents; Shuppim, an Israelite:--Shuppim.', 'Shuppim = \"serpents\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Iri or Ir, grandson of Bela, and great grandson of Benjamin<LI>a Merarite Levite, son of Hosah, and in charge of the West Gate of the temple in the time of David</OL>'),
(8207, '!pypX', 'from an unused root meaning the same as (07779)', 'shphiyphon', 'TWOT - 2448a', 'shef-ee-fone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning the same as «07779»; a kind of serpent (as snapping), probably the cerastes or horned adder:--adder.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>horned snake<LI>(CLBL) a serpent, perhaps an adder or horned snake</OL>'),
(8208, 'rypX', 'from (08231)', 'Shaphiyr', 'None', 'shaf-eer\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «08231»; beautiful; Shaphir, a place in Palestine:--Saphir.', 'Saphir = \"fair\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in Judah; site unknown</OL>'),
(8209, 'ryppX', 'intensive of a form corresponding to (08208)', 'sappiyr', 'TWOT - 3046a', 'shap-peer\'', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) intensive of a form corresponding to «08208»; beautiful:--fair.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fair, beautiful (of foliage)</OL>'),
(8210, '$pX', 'a primitive root', 'shaphak', 'TWOT - 2444', 'shaw-fak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to spill forth (blood, a libation, liquid metal; or even a solid, i.e. to mound up); also (figuratively) to expend (life, soul, complaint, money, etc.); intensively, to sprawl out:--cast (up), gush out, pour (out), shed(-der, out), slip.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pour, pour out, spill<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pour, pour out<LI>to shed (blood)<LI>to pour out (anger or heart) (fig)</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be poured out, be shed<LI>(Pual) to be poured out, be shed<LI>(Hithpael)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be poured out<LI>to pour out oneself</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8211, '$pX', 'from (08210)', 'shephek', 'TWOT - 2444a', 'sheh\'-fek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08210»; an emptying place, e.g. an ash-heap:--are poured out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>place of pouring</OL>'),
(8212, 'hkpX', 'a derivative from (08210)', 'shophkah', 'TWOT - 2444b', 'shof-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of a derivative from «08210»; a pipe (for pouring forth, e.g. wine), i.e. the penis:--privy member.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>penis, urethra, male organ<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>as fluid duct</OL></OL>'),
(8213, 'lpX', 'a primitive root', 'shaphel', 'TWOT - 2445', 'shaw-fale\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to depress or sink (expec. figuratively, to humiliate, intransitive or transitive):--abase, bring (cast, put) down, debase, humble (self), be (bring, lay, make, put) low(-er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or become low, sink, be humbled, be abased<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be or become low<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lay or bring low, humiliate<LI>to set in a lower place, show abasement<LI>to make low, sit down</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8214, 'lpX', 'corresponding to (08213)', 'shphal', 'None', 'shef-al\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «08213»:--abase, humble, put down, subdue.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be or bring low, humble<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Aphel) to bring low, humble</OL></OL>'),
(8215, 'lpX', 'from (08214)', 'shphal', 'None', 'shef-al\'', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) from «08214»; low:--basest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>low, lowliest (of station)</OL>'),
(8216, 'lpX', 'from (08213)', 'shephel', 'TWOT - 2445a', 'shay\'-fel', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08213»; an humble rank:--low estate (place).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lowliness, low estate or condition</OL>'),
(8217, 'lpX', 'from (08213)', 'shaphal', 'TWOT - 2445c', 'shaw-fawl\'', 'Adjective', 'from «08213»; depressed, literally or figuratively:--base(-st), humble, low(-er, -ly).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>low, humble<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>low (in height)<LI>low (in station), humble (of condition or spirit)<LI>humiliated<LI>lowly (as subst)</OL></OL>'),
(8218, 'hlpX', 'from (08216)', 'shiphlah', 'TWOT - 2445b', 'shif-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «08216»; depression:--low place.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lowliness, humiliation, a low place</OL>'),
(8219, 'hlpX', 'from (08213)', 'shphelah', 'TWOT - 2445d', 'shef-ay-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08213»; Lowland, i.e. (with the article) the maritime slope of Palestine:--low country, (low) plain, vale(-ley).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lowland, valley<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>lowland<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>strip west of Judean mountains (technical term) 1a</OL><LI>the Shephelah<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>strip near coast north of Carmel</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8220, 'twlpX', 'from (08213)', 'shiphluwth', 'TWOT - 2445e', 'shif-looth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08213»; remissness:--idleness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sinking, idleness, inactivity</OL>'),
(8221, '~pX', 'probably from (08192)', 'Shpham', 'None', 'shef-awm\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'probably from «08192»; bare spot; Shepham, a place in or near Palestine:--Shepham.', 'Shepham = \"bald\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place or region in northeastern Canaan on the eastern border</OL>'),
(8222, '~pX', 'from (08193)', 'sapham', 'TWOT - 2279', 'saw-fawm\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08193»; the beard (as a lip-piece):--beard, (upper) lip.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>moustache</OL>'),
(8223, '~pX', 'formed like (08221)', 'Shapham', 'None', 'shaw-fawm\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'formed like «08221»; baldly; Shapham, an Israelite:--Shapham.', 'Shapham = \"bold\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a subchief of the tribe of Gad in the land of Bashan</OL>'),
(8224, 'twmpX', 'fem. pl. of (08221)', 'Siphmowth', 'None', 'sif-moth\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'feminine plural of «08221»; Siphmoth, a place in Palestine:--Siphmoth.', 'Siphmoth = \"fruitful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in the Nekeb in southern Judah</OL>'),
(8225, 'ympX', 'patrial from (08221)', 'Shiphmiy', 'None', 'shif-mee\'', 'Adjective', 'patrial from «08221»; a Shiphmite or inhabitant of Shepham:--Shiphmite.', 'Shiphmite = see Siphmoth \"fruitful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Shepham or Siphmoth</OL>'),
(8226, '!pX', 'a primitive root', 'saphan', 'TWOT - 1537', 'saw-fan\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to conceal (as a valuable):--treasure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cover, cover in, panel, hide, treasure up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>covered, panelled, treasures (participle)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8227, '!pX', 'from (08226)', 'shaphan', 'TWOT - 2446a', 'shaw-fawn\'', '', 'from «08226»; a species of rock-rabbit (from its hiding), i.e. probably the hyrax:--coney.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rock badger, coney, the hyrax n pr m<LI>secretary or scribe of king Josiah of Judah<LI>father of Ahikam in the time of king Josiah of Judah<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>improbably the same as 2</OL><LI>father of Elasah in the time of the prophet Jeremiah<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps the same as 3</OL><LI>a scribe and father of Gemariah<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps the same as 2</OL><LI>father of Jaazaniah in the time of Ezekiel<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps the same as 2</OL></OL>'),
(8228, '[pX', 'from an unused root meaning to abound', 'shepha`', 'TWOT - 2447a', 'sheh\'-fah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to abound; resources:--abundance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>abundance</OL>'),
(8229, 'h[pX', 'from (08228)', 'shiph`ah', 'TWOT - 2447b', 'shif-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «08228»; copiousness:--abundance, company, multitude.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>abundance, quantity, multitude</OL>'),
(8230, 'y[pX', 'from (08228)', 'Shiph`iy', 'None', 'shif-ee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08228»; copious; Shiphi, an Israelite:--Shiphi.', 'Shiphi = \"abundant\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Simeonite, son of Allon and father of Ziza in the time of king Hezekiah of Judah</OL>'),
(8231, 'rpX', 'a primitive root', 'shaphar', 'TWOT - 2449', 'shaw-far\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to glisten, i.e. (figuratively) be (causatively, make) fair:--X goodly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be pleasing, be beautiful, be fair, be comely, be bright, glisten<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be beautiful</OL></OL>'),
(8232, 'rpX', 'corresponding to (08231)', 'shphar', 'TWOT - 3046', 'shef-ar\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «08231»; to be beautiful:--be acceptable, please, + think good.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be fair, be seemly, seem good, seem pleasing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to seem good, be acceptable</OL></OL>'),
(8233, 'rpX', 'from (08231)', 'shepher', 'TWOT - 2449a', 'sheh\'-fer', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08231»; beauty:--X goodly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>beauty, goodness, goodliness</OL>'),
(8234, 'rpX', 'the same as (08233)', 'Shepher', 'None', 'sheh\'-fer', 'Proper Name', 'the same as «08233»; Shepher, a place in the Desert:--Shapper.', 'Shapher = \"beauty\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a station of Israel in the wilderness</OL>'),
(8235, 'hrpX', 'from (08231)', 'shiphrah', 'TWOT - 2449b', 'shif-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08231»; brightness:--garnish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) fairness, clearness</OL>'),
(8236, 'hrpX', 'the same as (08235)', 'Shiphrah', 'None', 'shif-raw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'the same as «08235»; Shiphrah, an Israelitess:--Shiphrah.', 'Shiphrah = \"fair\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the two Hebrew midwives who were ordered by Pharaoh to kill all the male children born to the Hebrews but who disobeyed</OL>'),
(8237, 'rwrpX', 'from (08231)', 'shaphruwr', 'TWOT - 2449d', 'shaf-roor\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08231»; splendid, i.e. a tapestry or canopy:--royal pavilion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>canopy, royal pavilion<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning doubtful</OL></OL>'),
(8238, 'rprpX', 'from (08231)', 'shpharphar', 'TWOT - 3046b', 'shef-ar-far\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «08231»; the dawn (as brilliant with aurora):--X  very early in the morning.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dawn, early morning</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(8239, 'tpX', 'a primitive root', 'shaphath', 'TWOT - 2441a', 'shaw-fath\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to locate, i.e. (generally) hang on or (figuratively) establish, reduce:--bring, ordain, set on.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to set, place, put, ordain<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to set<LI>to ordain, establish</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8240, 'tpX', 'from (08239)', 'shaphath', 'TWOT - 2450', 'shaw-fawth\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08239»; a (double) stall (for cattle); also a (two-pronged) hook (for flaying animals on):--hook, pot.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hook-shaped pegs, hooks, pots, fold<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning doubtful</OL></OL>'),
(8241, '@cX', 'from (07857) (for alliteration with (07110))', 'shetseph', 'TWOT - 2373a', 'sheh\'-tsef', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «07857» (for alliteration with «07110»); an outburst (of anger):--little.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flood, downpour, overflowing</OL>'),
(8242, 'qX', 'from (08264)', 'saq', 'TWOT - 2282a', 'sak', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08264»; properly, a mesh (as allowing a liquid to run through), i.e. coarse loose cloth or sacking (used in mourning and for bagging); hence, a bag (for grain, etc.):--sack(-cloth, -clothes).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mesh, sackcloth, sack, sacking<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>sack (for grain)<LI>sackcloth<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>worn in mourning or humiliation<LI>same material spread out to lie on</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8243, 'qX', 'corresponding to (07785)', 'shaq', 'TWOT - 3047', 'shawk', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07785»; the leg:--leg.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>leg (lower)</OL>'),
(8244, 'dqX', 'a primitive root', 'saqad', 'TWOT - 2281', 'saw-kad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to fasten:--bind.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bind, bind on, be kept on (meaning doubtful)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be kept on</OL></OL>'),
(8245, 'dqX', 'a primitive root', 'shaqad', 'TWOT - 2451', 'shaw-kad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be alert, i.e. sleepless; hence to be on the lookout (whether for good or ill):--hasten, remain, wake, watch (for).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wake, watch, awake, be alert<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to keep watch of, be wakeful over<LI>to be wakeful, wake (as mourner or sufferer)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8246, 'dqX', 'a denominative from (08247)', 'shaqad', 'TWOT - 2451b', 'shaw-kad\'', 'Verb', 'a denominative from «08247»; to be (intensively, make) almond-shaped:--make like (unto, after the fashion of) almonds.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Pual) cups shaped like almond blossoms (participle)</OL>'),
(8247, 'dqX', 'from (08245)', 'shaqed', 'TWOT - 2451a', 'shaw-kade\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08245»; the almond (tree or nut; as being the earliest in bloom):--almond (tree).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>almond tree, almonds<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>almond (the nut)<LI>almond-tree</OL></OL>'),
(8248, 'hqX', 'a primitive root', 'shaqah', 'TWOT - 2452', 'shaw-kaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to quaff, i.e. (causatively) to irrigate or furnish a potion to:--cause to (give, give to, let, make to) drink, drown, moisten, water. See «07937», «08354».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give to drink, irrigate, drink, water, cause to drink water<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to water, irrigate<LI>to water, give drink to</OL><LI>(Pual) to be watered<LI>(Niphal) variant</OL></OL>'),
(8249, 'wqqX', 'from (08248)', 'shiqquv', 'TWOT - 2452a', 'shif-koov\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08248»; (plural collective) a draught:--drink.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>drink, refreshment</OL>'),
(8250, 'ywqqX', 'from (08248)', 'shiqquwy', 'TWOT - 2452a', 'shik-koo\'-ee', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08248»; a beverage; moisture, i.e. (figuratively) refreshment:--drink, marrow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>drink, refreshment</OL>'),
(8251, '#wqqX', 'from (08262)', 'shiqquwts', 'TWOT - 2459b', 'shik-koots\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or shiqquts {shik-koots\'}; from «08262»; disgusting, i.e. filthy; especially idolatrous or (concretely) an idol:-- abominable filth (idol, -ation), detestable (thing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>detestable thing or idol, abominable thing, abomination, idol, detested thing</OL>'),
(8252, 'tqX', 'a primitive root', 'shaqat', 'TWOT - 2453', 'shaw-kat\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to repose (usually figurative):--appease, idleness, (at, be at, be in, give) quiet(-ness), (be at, be in, give, have, take) rest, settle, be still.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be quiet, be tranquil, be at peace, be quiet, rest, lie still, be undisturbed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be quiet, be undisturbed 1a</OL><LI>to be at peace (of land)<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to be quiet, be inactive</OL><LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to show quietness 1b</OL><LI>quietness, display of quietness (subst)<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to quiet, be quiet<LI>to cause quietness, pacify, allay</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8253, 'tqX', 'from (08252)', 'sheqet', 'TWOT - 2453a', 'sheh\'-ket', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08252»; tranquillity:--quietness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>quiet, tranquillity, quietness</OL>'),
(8254, 'lqX', 'a primitive root', 'shaqal', 'TWOT - 2454', 'shaw-kal\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to suspend or poise (especially in trade):--pay, receive(-r), spend, × throughly, weigh.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to weigh, weigh out, pay out<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to weigh<LI>to weigh out (a price)<LI>of grief (fig)</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be weighed<LI>to be weighed out</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8255, 'lqX', 'from (08254)', 'sheqel', 'TWOT - 2454a', 'sheh\'-kel', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08254»; probably a weight; used as a commercial standard:--shekel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shekel<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the chief unit of weight or measure<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gold - 1/10000 of a talent and equal to 220 grains<LI>silver - 1/3000 of a talent and equal to 132 grains<LI>copper - 1/1500 of a talent and equal to 528 grains</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8256, '~qX', 'of uncertain derivation', 'shaqam', 'TWOT - 2455', 'shaw-kawm\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or (feminine) shiqmah {shik-maw\'}; of uncertain derivation; a sycamore (usually the tree):--sycamore (fruit, tree).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sycamore tree (bearing figs)</OL>'),
(8257, '[qX', 'a primitive root', 'shaqa`', 'TWOT - 2456', 'shaw-kah\'', 'Verb', '(abbreviated Am. 8:8); a primitive root; to subside; by implication, to be overflowed, cease; causatively, to abate, subdue:--make deep, let down, drown, quench, sink.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sink, sink down, subside<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to sink<LI>(Niphal) to sink, collapse<LI>(Hiphil) to sink down, cause to settle</OL></OL>'),
(8258, 'hrwr[qX', 'from (08257)', 'shqa`ruwrah', 'TWOT - 2047b', 'shek-ah-roo-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08257»; a depression:--hollow strake.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>depression, hollow</OL>'),
(8259, '@qX', 'a primitive root', 'shaqaph', 'TWOT - 2457', 'shaw-kaf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to lean out (of a window), i.e. (by implication) peep or gaze (passively, be a spectacle):-- appear, look (down, forth, out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to overlook, look down or out, overhang, look out and down<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to lean over (and look), look down<LI>(Hiphil) to look down, look down upon</OL></OL>'),
(8260, '@qX', 'from (08259)', 'sheqeph', 'TWOT - 2458a', 'sheh\'-kef', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08259»; a loophole (for looking out), to admit light and air:--window.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>framework, casing (of doors), door, lintel</OL>'),
(8261, '@qX', 'pass part of (08259)', 'shaquph', 'TWOT - 2458b', 'shaw-koof\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'passive participle of «08259»; an embrasure or opening (compare «08260») with bevelled jam:--light, window.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>frame, casing (of windows), beams laid over, window frames</OL>'),
(8262, '#qX', 'a primitive root', 'shaqats', 'TWOT - 2459', 'shaw-kats\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be filthy, i.e. (intensively) to loathe, pollute:--abhor, make abominable, have in abomination, detest, × utterly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to detest, make abominable, count filthy, make detestable<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to detest<LI>to make detestable</OL></OL>'),
(8263, '#qX', 'from (08262)', 'sheqets', 'TWOT - 2459a,2459b', 'sheh\'-kets', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08262»; filth, i.e. (figuratively and specifically) an idolatrous object:--abominable(-tion).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>detestable thing or idol, an unclean thing, an abomination, detestation</OL>'),
(8264, 'qqX', 'a primitive root', 'shaqaq', 'TWOT - 2460', 'shaw-kak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to course (like a beast of prey); by implication, to seek greedily:--have appetite, justle one against another, long, range, run (to and fro).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to run, run about, rush, run to and fro, be eager or greedy or thirsty<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) roving, ranging, longing, rush out upon (participle)<LI>(Hithpalpel) to rush to and fro, rush back and forth</OL></OL>'),
(8265, 'rqX', 'a primitive root', 'saqar', 'TWOT - 2283', 'saw-kar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to ogle, i.e. blink coquettishly:--wanton.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to ogle, be wanton<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>ogling (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(8266, 'rqX', 'a primitive root', 'shaqar', 'TWOT - 2461', 'shaw-kar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to cheat, i.e. be untrue (usually in words):--fail, deal falsely, lie.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to do or deal falsely, be false, trick, cheat<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to deal falsely<LI>(Qal) to deal falsely</OL></OL>'),
(8267, 'rqX', 'from (08266)', 'sheqer', 'TWOT - 2461a', 'sheh\'-ker', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08266»; an untruth; by implication, a sham (often adverbial):--without a cause, deceit(-ful), false(-hood, -ly), feignedly, liar, + lie, lying, vain (thing), wrongfully.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lie, deception, disappointment, falsehood<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>deception (what deceives or disappoints or betrays one)<LI>deceit, fraud, wrong<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fraudulently, wrongfully (as adverb)</OL><LI>falsehood (injurious in testimony)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>testify falsehood, false oath, swear falsely</OL><LI>falsity (of false or self-deceived prophets)<LI>lie, falsehood (in general)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>false tongue</OL><LI>in vain</OL></OL>'),
(8268, 'tqX', 'from (08248)', 'shoqeth', 'TWOT - 2452b', 'sho\'-keth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08248»; a trough (for watering):--trough.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>watering trough</OL>'),
(8269, 'rX', 'from (08323)', 'sar', 'TWOT - 2295a', 'sar', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08323»; a head person (of any rank or class):--captain (that had rule), chief (captain), general, governor, keeper, lord, ((-task- ))master, prince(-ipal), ruler, steward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>prince, ruler, leader, chief, chieftain, official, captain<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>chieftain, leader<LI>vassal, noble, official (under king)<LI>captain, general, commander (military)<LI>chief, head, overseer (of other official classes)<LI>heads, princes (of religious office)<LI>elders (of representative leaders of people)<LI>merchant-princes (of rank and dignity)<LI>patron-angel<LI>Ruler of rulers (of God)<LI>warden</OL></OL>'),
(8270, 'rX', 'from (08324)', 'shor', 'TWOT - 2469a', 'shore', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08324»; a string (as twisted (compare «08306»)), i.e. (specifically) the umbilical cord (also figuratively, as the centre of strength):--navel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>umbilical cord, navel, navel-string</OL>'),
(8271, 'arX', 'a root corresponding to that of (08293)', 'shre\'', 'TWOT - 3048', 'sher-ay\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) a root corresponding to that of «08293»; to free, separate; figuratively, to unravel, commence; by implication (of unloading beasts) to reside:--begin, dissolve, dwell, loose.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to loosen, abide, begin<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to loosen<LI>to abide (from loosing girths for camp)</OL><LI>(Pael) to begin, open<LI>(Ithpael) to be loosened</OL></OL>'),
(8272, 'rcarX', 'of foreign derivation', 'Shar\'etser', 'None', 'shar-eh\'-tser', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign derivation; Sharetser, the name of an Assyrian and an Israelite:--Sharezer.', 'Sharezer or Sherezer = \"prince of fire\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of king Sennacherib of Assyria and murderer of his father<LI>an Israelite whom the people sent to the house of God to pray in the time of the prophet Zechariah and king Darius</OL>'),
(8273, 'brX', 'from an unused root meaning to glare', 'sharab', 'TWOT - 2462a', 'shaw-rawb\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to glare; quivering glow (of the air), expec. the mirage:--heat, parched ground.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>burning or scorching heat, parched ground</OL>'),
(8274, 'hybrX', 'from (08273) and (03050)', 'Sherebyah', 'None', 'shay-rayb-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08273» and «03050»; Jah has brought heat; Sherebjah, the name of two Israelites:--Sherebiah.', 'Sherebiah = \"Jehovah has scorched\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Levite who assisted Ezra at the reading of the Law and who sealed the covenant with Nehemiah</OL>'),
(8275, 'tybrX', 'for (07626)', 'sharbiyt', 'TWOT - 2314b', 'shar-beet\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'for «07626»; a rod of empire:--sceptre.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sceptre<LI>(TWOT) dart, spear</OL>'),
(8276, 'grX', 'a primitive root', 'sarag', 'TWOT - 2284', 'saw-rag\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to intwine:--wrap together, wreath.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be intertwined<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pual) to be intertwined<LI>(Hithpael) to intertwine oneself</OL></OL>'),
(8277, 'drX', 'a primitive root', 'sarad', 'TWOT - 2285', 'saw-rad\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; properly, to puncture (compare «08279»), i.e. (figuratively through the idea of slipping out) to escape or survive:--remain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to escape, survive</OL>'),
(8278, 'drX', 'from (08277)', 'srad', 'TWOT - 2286a', 'ser-awd\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08277»; stitching (as pierced with a needle):--service.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>plaited or braided work</OL>'),
(8279, 'drX', 'from (08277)', 'sered', 'TWOT - 2286b', 'seh\'-red', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08277»; a (carpenter\'s) scribing-awl (for pricking or scratching measurements):--line.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stylus, a line, marker<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a marking tool for wood</OL></OL>'),
(8280, 'hrX', 'a primitive root', 'sarah', 'TWOT - 2287', 'saw-raw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to prevail:--have power (as a prince).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>contend, have power, contend with, persist, exert oneself, persevere<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to persevere, contend with</OL></OL>'),
(8281, 'hrX', 'a primitive root', 'sharah', 'TWOT - 2463', 'shaw-raw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to free:--direct.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to let loose, free<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to let loose<LI>(Piel) to set free</OL></OL>'),
(8282, 'hrX', 'from (08269)', 'sarah', 'TWOT - 2295b', 'saw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «08269»; a mistress, i.e. female noble:--lady, princess, queen.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>princess, noblewoman, noble lady</OL>'),
(8283, 'hrX', 'the same as (08282)', 'Sarah', 'None', 'saw-raw\'', 'Proper Name Feminine', 'the same as «08282»; Sarah, Abraham\'s wife:--Sarah.', 'Sarah = \"noblewoman\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wife of Abraham and mother of Isaac</OL>'),
(8284, 'hrX', 'probably from (07791)', 'sharah', 'TWOT - 2355b', 'shaw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'probably feminine of «07791»; a fortification (literally or figuratively):--sing (by mistake for «07891»), wall.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wall<LI>(CLBL) vine-row</OL>'),
(8285, 'hrX', 'from (08324) in its original sense of pressing', 'sherah', 'TWOT - 2469b', 'shay-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08324» in its original sense of pressing; a wrist-band (as compact or clasping):--bracelet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bracelet</OL>'),
(8286, 'gwrX', 'from (08276)', 'Sruwg', 'None', 'ser-oog\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08276»; tendril; Serug, a postdiluvian patriarch:--Serug.', 'Serug = \"branch\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Reu and great grandfather of Abraham</OL>'),
(8287, '!xwrX', 'probably from (08281) (in the sense of dwelling [compare (08271)] and (02580)', 'Sharuwchen', 'None', 'shaw-roo-khen\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'probably from «08281» (in the sense of dwelling (compare «08271») and «02580»; abode of pleasure; Sharuchen, a place in Palestine:--Sharuhen.', 'Sharuhen = \"refuge of grace\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in Judah allotted to Simeon</OL>'),
(8288, '$wrX', 'from (08308)', 'srowk', 'TWOT - 2290a', 'ser-oke\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08308»; a thong (as laced or tied):--((shoe-)) latchet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sandal thong</OL>'),
(8289, '!wrX', 'probably abridged from (03474)', 'Sharown', 'None', 'shaw-rone\'', '', 'probably abridged from «03474»; plain, Sharon, the name of a place in Palestine:--Lasharon, Sharon.', 'n m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>plain, level n pr loc Sharon = \"a plain\"<LI>the district lying between the mountains of central Palestine and the Mediterranean Sea and north of Joppa<LI>a district on the east of the Jordan around Gilead and Bashan</OL>'),
(8290, 'ynwrX', 'patrial from (08289)', 'Sharowniy', 'None', 'shaw-ro-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'patrial from «08289»; a Sharonite or inhabitant of Sharon:--Sharonite.', 'Sharonite = see Sharon \"a plain\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>inhabitant of the district of Sharon</OL>'),
(8291, 'qwrX', 'pass part from the same as (08321)', 'saruwq', 'TWOT - 2294b', 'sar-ook\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'passive participle from the same as «08321»; a grapevine:--principal plant. See «08320», «08321».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vine-tendrils or clusters</OL>'),
(8292, 'hqwrX', 'pass part of (08319)', 'shruwqah', 'TWOT - 2468b', 'sher-oo-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or (by permutation) shriyqah {sher-ee- kaw\'}; feminine passive participle of «08319»; a whistling (in scorn); by analogy, a piping:--bleating, hissing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>piping, whistling, hissing</OL>'),
(8293, 'twrX', 'from (08281) abbreviated', 'sheruwth', 'TWOT - 2463', 'shay-rooth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08281» abbreviated; freedom:--remnant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>remnant</OL>'),
