(8363, 'lytX', 'from (08362)', 'shthiyl', 'TWOT - 2480a', 'sheth-eel\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08362»; a sprig (as if transplanted), i.e. sucker:--plant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>plant, cutting, transplanted shoot, slip</OL>'),
(8364, 'yxltX', 'patronymically from (07803)', 'Shuthalchiy', 'None', 'shoo-thal-kee\'', 'Adjective', 'patronymically from «07803»; a Shuthalchite (collectively) or descendants of Shuthelach:--Shuthalhites.', 'Shuthalhites = see Shuthelah \"freshly appointed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descendants of Shuthelah, son of Ephraim, and of his son of the same name</OL>'),
(8365, '~tX', 'a primitive root', 'shatham', 'TWOT - 2481', 'shaw-tham\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to unveil (figuratively):--be open.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to open<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(8366, '!tX', 'a primitive root', 'shathan', 'TWOT - 2377', 'shaw-than\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; (causatively) to make water, i.e. urinate:--piss.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to urinate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>one who urinates (used as a designation of a male)</OL></OL>'),
(8367, 'qtX', 'a primitive root', 'shathaq', 'TWOT - 2482', 'shaw-thak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to subside:--be calm, cease, be quiet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be quiet, be silent</OL>'),
(8368, 'rtX', 'a primitive root', 'sathar', 'TWOT - 2297', 'saw-thar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to break out (as an eruption):--have in (one\'s) secret parts.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Niphal) to burst out, break out</OL>'),
(8369, 'rtX', 'of foreign derivation', 'Shethar', 'None', 'shay-thawr\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign derivation; Shethar, a Persian satrap:--Shethar.', 'Shethar = \"a star\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 7 princes of Media or Persian empire</OL>'),
(8370, 'ynzwb rtX', 'of foreign derivation', 'Shthar', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of foreign derivation; Shethar-Bozenai, a Persian officer:--Shethar-boznai.', 'Shethar-boznai = \"star of splendour\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Persian officer in the reign of Darius</OL>'),
(8371, 'ttX', 'a primitive root', 'shathath', 'TWOT - 2483', 'shaw-thath\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to place, i.e. array; reflex. to lie:--be laid, set.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to set, appoint</OL>'),
(8372, 'at', 'from (the base of) (08376)', 'ta\'', 'TWOT - 2484', 'taw', 'Noun Masculine', 'and (feminine) ta ah (Ezek. 40:12) {taw-aw\'}; from (the base of) «08376»; a room (as circumscribed):--(little) chamber.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chamber, guardroom</OL>'),
(8373, 'bat', 'a primitive root', 'ta\'ab', 'TWOT - 2485', 'taw-ab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to desire:--long.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to long for</OL>'),
(8374, 'bat', 'a primitive root [probably identical with (08373) through the idea of puffing disdainfully at', 'ta\'ab', 'TWOT - 2486', 'taw-ab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (probably identical with «08373» through the idea of puffing disdainfully at; compare «0340»); to loathe (morally):--abhor.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to loathe, abhor</OL>'),
(8375, 'hbat', 'from (08374) [compare (015)]', 'ta\'abah', 'TWOT - 2485a', 'tah-ab-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08374» (compare «015»); desire:--longing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>longing</OL>'),
(8376, 'hat', 'a primitive root', 'ta\'ah', 'TWOT - 2487', 'taw-aw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to mark off, i.e. (intensively) designate:--point out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to mark out, point out</OL>'),
(8377, 'wat', 'from (08376)', 't\'ow', 'TWOT - 2488', 'teh-o\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'and towt (the original form) {toh}; from «08376»; a species of antelope (probably from the white stripe on the cheek):--wild bull (ox).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wild ox, antelope, oryx<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps an extinct animal, exact meaning unknown</OL></OL>'),
(8378, 'hwat', 'from (0183) (abbrev)', 'ta\'avah', 'TWOT - 40d', 'tah-av-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «0183» (abbreviated); a longing; by implication, a delight (subjectively, satisfaction, objectively, a charm):--dainty, desire, × exceedingly, × greedily, lust(ing), pleasant. See also «06914».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>desire<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>desire, wish, longings of one\'s heart<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lust, appetite, covetousness (bad sense)</OL><LI>thing desired, object of desire</OL></OL>'),
(8379, 'hwat', 'from (08376)', 'ta\'avah', 'TWOT - 2496b', 'tah-av-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08376»; a limit, i.e. full extent:--utmost bound.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>boundary, limit<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning uncertain</OL></OL>'),
(8380, '~wat', 'from (08382)', 'ta\'owm', 'TWOT - 2489a', 'taw-ome\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or taom {taw-ome\'}; from «08382»; a twin (in plural only), literally or figuratively:--twins.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>twin</OL>'),
(8381, 'hlat', 'from (0422)', 'ta\'alah', 'TWOT - 94b', 'tah-al-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «0422»; an imprecation:--curse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>curse</OL>'),
(8382, '~at', 'a primitive root', 'ta\'am', 'TWOT - 2489', 'taw-am\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be complete; but used only as denominative from «08380», to be (causatively, make) twinned, i.e. (figuratively) duplicate or (arch.) jointed:--coupled (together), bear twins.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be double, be joined<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be double<LI>(Hiphil) to bear twins</OL></OL>'),
(8383, '!at', 'from (0205)', 't\'un', 'TWOT - 48b', 'teh-oon\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «0205»; naughtiness, i.e. toil:--lie.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>toil</OL>'),
(8384, '!at', 'perhaps of foreign derivation', 't\'en', 'TWOT - 2490', 'teh-ane\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or (in the singular, feminine) t:enah {teh-ay- naw\'}; perhaps of foreign derivation; the fig (tree or fruit):--fig (tree).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fig, fig tree</OL>'),
(8385, 'hnat', 'from (0579)', 'ta\'anah', 'TWOT - 126a,126b', 'tah-an-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or tonanah {to-an-aw\'}; from «0579»; an opportunity or (subjectively) purpose:--occasion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>occasion, time of heat or oestrous or copulation, sexual drive (of animal)<LI>occasion, opportunity (for a quarrel)</OL>'),
(8386, 'hynat', 'from (0578)', 'ta\'aniyah', 'TWOT - 124b', 'tah-an-ee-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «0578»; lamentation:--heaviness, mourning.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mourning, grieving</OL>'),
(8387, 'hlX tnat', 'from (08385) and (07887)', 'Ta\'anath', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «08385» and «07887»; approach of Shiloh; Taanath-Shiloh, a place in Palestine:--Taanath-shiloh.', 'Taanath-shiloh = \"approach to Shiloh\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a landmark on the boundary of Ephraim</OL>'),
(8388, 'rat', 'a primitive root', 'ta\'ar', 'TWOT - 2491,2491b', 'taw-ar\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to delineate; reflex. to extend:--be drawn, mark out, (Rimmon-)methoar (by union with «07417»).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to be drawn, incline, delineate, extend<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL><LI>(Piel) to draw in outline, trace out</OL>'),
(8389, 'rat', 'from (08388)', 'to\'ar', 'TWOT - 2491a', 'to\'-ar', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08388»; outline, i.e. figure or appearance:--+ beautiful, × comely, countenance, + fair, × favoured, form, × goodly, ×  resemble, visage.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shape, form, outline, figure, appearance</OL>'),
(8390, '[rat', 'perhaps from (0772)', 'Ta\'area`', 'None', 'tah-ar-ay\'-ah', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'perhaps from «0772»; Taarea, an Israelite:--Tarea. See «08475».', 'Tarea = \"chamber of a neighbour\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Benjamite, son of Micah of the family of Saul</OL>'),
(8391, 'rwXXat', 'from (0833)', 't\'ashshuwr', 'TWOT - 183g', 'teh-ash-shoor\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «0833»; a species of cedar (from its erectness):--box (tree).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a species of tree<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>box tree - a small evergreen tree<LI>perhaps cypress or cedar</OL></OL>'),
(8392, 'hbt', 'perhaps of foreign derivation', 'tebah', 'TWOT - 2492', 'tay-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'perhaps of foreign derivation; a box:--ark.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ark<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>vessel which Noah built<LI>basket vessel in which Moses was placed</OL></OL>'),
(8393, 'hawbt', 'from (0935)', 'tbuw\'ah', 'TWOT - 212c', 'teb-oo-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «0935»; income, i.e. produce (literally or figuratively):--fruit, gain, increase, revenue.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>produce, product, revenue<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>product, yield, crops (of the earth usually)<LI>income, revenue<LI>gain (of wisdom) (fig)<LI>product of lips (fig)</OL></OL>'),
(8394, '!wbt', 'from (0995)', 'tabuwn', 'TWOT - 239c', 'taw-boon\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'and (feminine) tbuwnah {teb-oo-naw\'}; or towbunah {to-boo-naw\'}; from «0995»; intelligence; by implication, an argument; by extension, caprice:--discretion, reason, skilfulness, understanding, wisdom.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>understanding, intelligence<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the act of understanding<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>skill</OL><LI>the faculty of understanding<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>intelligence, understanding, insight</OL><LI>the object of knowledge<LI>teacher (personification)</OL></OL>'),
(8395, 'howbt', 'from (0947)', 'tbuwcah', 'TWOT - 216c', 'teb-oo-saw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «0947»; a treading down, i.e. ruin:--destruction.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a treading down, downtreading, ruin, downfall, destruction</OL>'),
(8396, 'rwbt', 'from a root corresponding to (08406)', 'Tabowr', 'None', 'taw-bore\'', '', 'from a root corresponding to «08406»; broken region; Tabor, a mountain in Palestine, also a city adjacent:--Tabor.', 'Tabor = \"mound\" n pr mont<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a mountain in the plain of Esdraelon rising abruptly and insulated except for a narrow ridge on the west connecting it to the hills of Nazareth n pr loc<LI>a town around the summit of Mount Tabor (<LI><LI>a city of the Merarite Levites located in the territory of Zebulun n pr arbour<LI>the place of an oak tree which was on the homeward journey of Saul after he had been anointed by Samuel</OL>'),
(8397, 'lbt', 'apparently from (01101)', 'tebel', 'TWOT - 248d', 'teh\'-bel', 'Noun Masculine', 'apparently from «01101»; mixture, i.e. unnatural bestiality:--confusion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>confusion (violation of nature or divine order)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perversion (in sexual sin)</OL></OL>'),
(8398, 'lbt', 'from (02986)', 'tebel', 'TWOT - 835h', 'tay-bale\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02986»; the earth (as moist and therefore inhabited); by extension, the globe; by implication, its inhabitants; specifically, a partic. land, as Babylonia, Palestine:--habitable part, world.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>world</OL>'),
(8399, 'tylbt', 'from (01086)', 'tabliyth', 'TWOT - 246c', 'tab-leeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01086»; consumption:--destruction.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>destruction</OL>'),
(8400, 'lllbt', 'from (01101) in the original sense of flowing', 'tballul', 'TWOT - 248e', 'teb-al-lool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01101» in the original sense of flowing: a cataract (in the eye):--blemish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>obscurity, defect (in vision), confusion</OL>'),
(8401, '!bt', 'probably from (01129)', 'teben', 'TWOT - 2493', 'teh\'-ben', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from «01129»; properly, material, i.e. (specifically) refuse haum or stalks of grain (as chopped in threshing and used for fodder):--chaff, straw, stubble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>straw, stubble<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>as building material<LI>as fodder for livestock</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(8402, '!bt', 'from (08401)', 'Tibni', 'None', 'tib-nee\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08401»; strawy; Tibni, an Israelite:--Tibni.', 'Tibni = \"intelligent\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>contender for the throne of the northern kingdom of Israel after the death of Zimri; fought for 4 years with the rival faction whose leader was Omri; died after 4 years leaving the throne to Omri</OL>'),
(8403, 'tynbt', 'from (01129)', 'tabniyth', 'TWOT - 255d', 'tab-neeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01129»; structure; by implication, a model, resemblance:--figure, form, likeness, pattern, similitude.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pattern, plan, form, construction, figure<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>construction, structure<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL><LI>pattern<LI>figure, image (of idols)</OL></OL>'),
(8404, 'hr[bt', 'from (01197)', 'Tab`erah', 'None', 'tab-ay-raw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «01197»; burning; Taberah, a place in the Desert:--Taberah.', 'Taberah = \"burning\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in the wilderness of Paran</OL>'),
(8405, '#bt', 'from the same as (0948)', 'Tebets', 'None', 'tay-bates\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the same as «0948»; whiteness; Tebets, a place in Palestine:--Thebez.', 'Thebez = \"conspicuous\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town near Shechem</OL>'),
(8406, 'rbt', 'corresponding to (07665)', 'tbar', 'TWOT - 3052', 'teb-ar\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07665»; to be fragile (figuratively):--broken.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to break (P\'al) broken in pieces (participle)</OL>'),
(8407, 'roalp tlgt', 'of foreign derivation', 'Tiglath', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Tiglath Plecer {tig- lath pel-eh-ser}; or Tilgath Pilnlecer {til-gath\' pil-neh-eh\'-ser} or Tilgath Pilnecer {til-gath\' pil-neh\'-ser}; of foreign derivation; Tiglath- Pileser or Tilgath-pilneser, an Assyr. king:--Tiglath-pileser, Tilgath- pilneser.', 'Tiglath-pileser or Tilgath-pilneser = \"thou will uncover the wonderful bond\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Assyrian king who attacked Samaria or northern kingdom of Israel in the reign of Pekah</OL>'),
(8408, 'lwmgt', 'from (01580)', 'tagmuwl', 'TWOT - 360c', 'tag-mool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «01580»; a bestowment:--benefit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>benefit, act of grace</OL>'),
(8409, 'hrgt', 'from (01624)', 'tigrah', 'TWOT - 378b', 'tig-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01624»; strife, i.e. infliction:--blow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>contention, strife, conflict, hostility</OL>'),
(8410, 'rhdt', 'apparently from (01725)', 'tidhar', 'TWOT - 408b', 'tid-hawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'apparently from «01725»; enduring; a species of hard-wood or lasting tree (perhaps oak):--pine (tree).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a species of hardwood tree<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps boxwood, elm</OL></OL>'),
(8411, 'arydt', 'from (01753) in the original sense of enduring', 'tdiyra\'', 'TWOT - 2669d', 'ted-ee-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(Aramaic) from «01753» in the original sense of enduring; permanence, i.e. (adverb) constantly:--continually.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>continuance, continuity, perpetuity<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>constantly (as adverb)</OL></OL>'),
(8412, 'rmdt', 'apparently from (08558)', 'Tadmor', 'None', 'tad-more\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Tammor (1 Kings 9:18) {tam-more\'}; apparently from «08558»; palm-city; Tadmor, a place near Palestine:--Tadmor.', 'Tadmor = \"palm tree\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city built by Solomon after his conquest of Hamath-zobah</OL>'),
(8413, 'l[dt', 'perhaps from (01763)', 'Tid`al', 'None', 'tid-awl\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'perhaps from «01763»; fearfulness; Tidal, a Canaanite:--Tidal.', 'Tidal = \"great son\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chief of various nomadic tribes and an ally of Chedorlaomer</OL>'),
(8414, 'wht', 'from an unused root meaning to lie waste', 'tohuw', 'TWOT - 2494a', 'to\'-hoo', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to lie waste; a desolation (of surface), i.e. desert; figuratively, a worthless thing; adverbially, in vain:--confusion, empty place, without form, nothing, (thing of) nought, vain, vanity, waste, wilderness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>formlessness, confusion, unreality, emptiness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>formlessness (of primeval earth)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nothingness, empty space</OL><LI>that which is empty or unreal (of idols) (fig)<LI>wasteland, wilderness (of solitary places)<LI>place of chaos<LI>vanity</OL></OL>'),
(8415, '~wht', 'from (01949)', 'thowm', 'TWOT - 2495a', 'teh-home\'', 'Noun', 'or thom {teh-home\'}; (usually feminine) from «01949»; an abyss (as a surging mass of water), especially the deep (the main sea or the subterranean water-supply):--deep (place), depth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>deep, depths, deep places, abyss, the deep, sea<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>deep (of subterranean waters)<LI>deep, sea, abysses (of sea)<LI>primeval ocean, deep<LI>deep, depth (of river)<LI>abyss, the grave</OL></OL>'),
(8416, 'hllht', 'from (01984)', 'thillah', 'TWOT - 500c', 'teh-hil-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01984»; laudation; specifically (concretely) a hymn:--praise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>praise, song or hymn of praise<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>praise, adoration, thanksgiving (paid to God)<LI>act of general or public praise<LI>praise-song (as title)<LI>praise (demanded by qualities or deeds or attributes of God)<LI>renown, fame, glory<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of Damascus, God<LI>object of praise, possessor of renown (fig)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8417, 'hlht', 'from an unused noun (apparently from (01984)) meaning bluster', 'toholah', 'TWOT - 2494b', 'to-hol-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of an unused noun (apparently from «01984») meaning bluster; braggadocio, i.e. (by implication) fatuity:--folly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>error</OL>'),
(8418, 'hklht', 'from (01980)', 'tahalukah', 'TWOT - 498e', 'tah-hal-oo-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «01980»; a procession:--X went.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>procession</OL>'),
(8419, 'hkpht', 'from (02015)', 'tahpukah', 'TWOT - 512f', 'tah-poo-kaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «02015»; a perversity or fraud:--(very) froward(-ness, thing), perverse thing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>perversity, perverse thing</OL>'),
(8420, 'wt', 'from (08427)', 'tav', 'TWOT - 2496a', 'tawv', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08427»; a mark; by implication, a signature:--desire, mark.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>desire, mark<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>mark (as a sign of exemption from judgment)</OL></OL>'),
(8421, 'bwt', 'corresponding to (07725), to come back', 'tuwb', 'TWOT - 3053', 'toob', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07725», to come back; specifically (transitive and ellip.) to reply:--answer, restore, return (an answer).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to return, come back<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(P\'al) to return, come back<LI>(Aphel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to restore, give back, answer<LI>to return</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8422, 'lbwt', 'probably of foreign derivation', 'Tuwbal', 'None', 'too-bal\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Tubal {too-bal\'}; probably of foreign derivation; Tubal, a postdiluvian patriarch and his posterity:--Tubal.', 'Tubal = \"thou shall be brought\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Japheth and grandson of Noah n pr terr<LI>a region in east Asia Minor<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>perhaps nearly equal to Cappadocia</OL></OL>'),
(8423, '!yq lbwt', 'apparently from (02986) (compare (02981)) and (07014)', 'Tuwbal', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'apparently from «02986» (compare «02981») and «07014»; offspring of Cain; Tubal-Kajin, an antidiluvian patriarch:--Tubal-cain.', 'Tubal-cain = \"thou will be brought of Cain\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Lamech by his wife Zillah and the first worker in metal</OL>'),
(8424, 'hgwt', 'from (03013)', 'tuwgah', 'TWOT - 839b', 'too-gaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03013»; depression (of spirits); concretely a grief:--heaviness, sorrow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>grief, heaviness, sorrow</OL>'),
(8425, 'hmrgwt', 'probably of foreign derivation', 'Towgarmah', 'None', 'to-gar-maw\'', '', 'or Togarmah {to-gar-maw\'}; probably of foreign derivation; Togarmah, a son of Gomer and his posterity:--Togarmah.', 'Togarmah = \"thou wilt break her\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Gomer, grandson of Japheth, and great grandson of Noah n pr terr<LI>territory settled by the descendants of Togarmah<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>probably the area known as Armenia</OL></OL>'),
(8426, 'hdwt', 'from (03034)', 'towdah', 'TWOT - 847b', 'to-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03034»; properly, an extension of the hand, i.e. (by implication) avowal, or (usually) adoration; specifically, a choir of worshippers:--confession, (sacrifice of) praise, thanks(-giving, offering).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>confession, praise, thanksgiving<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>give praise to God<LI>thanksgiving in songs of liturgical worship, hymn of praise<LI>thanksgiving choir or procession or line or company<LI>thank-offering, sacrifice of thanksgiving<LI>confession</OL></OL>'),
(8427, 'hwt', 'a primitive root', 'tavah', 'TWOT - 2496', 'taw-vaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to mark out, i.e. (primitive) scratch or (definite) imprint:--scrabble, set (a mark).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to scrabble, limit, mark, make or set a mark<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Piel) to mark<LI>(Hiphil) to set a mark</OL></OL>'),
(8428, 'hwt', 'a primitive root [or perhaps ident with (08427) through a similar idea from scraping to pieces]', 'tavah', 'TWOT - 2497', 'taw-vaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (or perhaps ident. with «08427» through a similar idea from scraping to pieces); to grieve:--limit (by confusion with «08427»).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hiphil) to pain, wound, trouble, cause pain<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning probable</OL></OL>'),
(8429, 'hhwt', 'corresponding to (08539) or perhaps to (07582) through the idea of sweeping to ruin [compare (08428)]', 'tvahh', 'TWOT - 3054', 'tev-ah\'', 'Verb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «08539» or perhaps to «07582» through the idea of sweeping to ruin (compare «08428»); to amaze, i.e. (reflex. by implication) take alarm:--be astonied.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(P\'al) to be startled, be alarmed</OL>'),
(8430, 'xwt', 'from an unused root meaning to depress', 'Towach', 'None', 'to\'-akh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to depress; humble; Toach, an Israelite:--Toah.', 'Toah = \"lowly\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Zuph, father of Eliel, and ancestor of Samuel and Heman</OL>'),
(8431, 'tlxwt', 'from (03176)', 'towcheleth', 'TWOT - 859b', 'to-kheh\'-leth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from  «03176»; expectation:--hope.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hope</OL>'),
(8432, '$wt', 'from an unused root meaning to sever', 'tavek', 'TWOT - 2498', 'taw\'-vek', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to sever; a bisection, i.e. (by implication) the centre:--among(-st), × between, half, ×  (there- ,where-), in(-to), middle, mid(-night), midst (among), × out (of), × through, × with(-in).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>midst, middle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>midst, middle<LI>into, through (after verbs of motion)<LI>among (of a number of persons)<LI>between (of things arranged by twos)<LI>from among (as to take or separate etc)</OL></OL>'),
(8433, 'hxkwt', 'from (03198)', 'towkechah', 'TWOT - 865a,865b', 'to-kay-khaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'and towkachath {to-kakh\'-ath}; from «03198»; chastisement; figuratively (by words) correction, refutation, proof (even in defence):--argument, × chastened, correction, reasoning, rebuke, reproof, × be (often) reproved.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rebuke, correction, reproof, punishment, chastisement<LI>argument, reproof<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>argument, impeachment<LI>reproof, chiding<LI>correction, rebuke</OL></OL>'),
