(8446, 'rwt', 'a primitive root', 'tuwr', 'TWOT - 2500', 'toor', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to meander (causatively, guide) about, especially for trade or reconnoitring:--chap(-man), sent to descry, be excellent, merchant(-man), search (out), seek, (e-)spy (out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to seek, search out, spy out, explore<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to seek out, select, find out how to do something<LI>to spy out, explore 1a</OL><LI>explorers, spies (participle)<OL TYPE=\"3\"><LI>to go about 1a</OL><LI>merchant, trader (participle)<LI>(Hiphil) to make a search, make a reconnaissance</OL></OL>'),
