(8471, 'oxnpxt', 'of Egyptian derivation', 'Tachpanchec', 'None', 'takh-pan-khace\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Tchaphnchec (Ezek. 30:18) {tekh- af-nekh-ace\'}; or Tachpnec (Jeremiah 2:16) {takh-pen-ace\'}; of Egyptian derivation; Tachpanches, Techaphneches or Tachpenes, a place in Egypt:--Tahapanes, Tahpanhes, Tehaphnehes.', 'Tahpanhes or Tahapanes or Tehaphnehes = \"thou will fill hands with pity\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in Egypt; modern \'Tel Defenneh\' or \'Tel Defneh\' located approx 18 miles (29 km) east southeast from Tanis</OL>'),
