(8490, 'hrmyt', 'from the same as (08558)', 'tiymarah', 'TWOT - 2523d', 'tee-maw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or timarah {tee-maw-raw\'}; from the same as «08558»; a column, i.e. cloud:--pillar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pillar, column<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>palm-like spreading at top</OL></OL>'),
(8491, 'ycyt', 'patrial or patronymically from an unused noun of uncertain meaning', 'Tiytsiy', 'None', 'tee-tsee\'', 'Neuter', 'patrial or patronymically from an unused noun of uncertain meaning; a Titsite or descendant or inhabitant of an unknown Tits:--Tizite.', 'Tizite = \"thou shall go forth\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Tiz</OL>'),
(8492, 'Xwryt', 'from (03423) in the sense of expulsion', 'tiyrowsh', 'TWOT - 2505', 'tee-roshe\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or tiyrosh {tee-roshe\'}; from «03423» in the sense of expulsion; must or fresh grape-juice (as just squeezed out); by implication (rarely) fermented wine:--(new, sweet) wine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wine, fresh or new wine, must, freshly pressed wine</OL>'),
(8493, 'ayryt', 'probably from (03372)', 'Tiyrya\'', 'None', 'tee-reh-yaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from «03372»; fearful, Tirja, an Israelite:--Tiria.', 'Tiria = \"fear\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Judaite, son of Jehaleleel</OL>'),
(8494, 'oryt', 'probably of foreign derivation', 'Tiyrac', 'None', 'tee-rawce\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably of foreign derivation; Tiras, a son of Japheth:--Tiras.', 'Tiras = \"desire\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Japheth and grandson of Noah</OL>'),
(8495, 'Xyt', 'from an unused root meaning to butt', 'tayish', 'TWOT - 2506', 'tah\'-yeesh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to butt; a buck or he-goat (as given to butting):--he goat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>he-goat</OL>'),
(8496, '$t', 'from the same base as (08432) (in the sense of cutting to pieces)', 'tok', 'TWOT - 2509a', 'toke', 'Noun Masculine', 'or towk (Psa. 72:14) {toke}; from the same base as «08432» (in the sense of cutting to pieces); oppression:--deceit, fraud.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>injury, oppression, oppressor<LI>(TWOT) fraud, deceit, deceitful</OL>'),
(8497, 'hkt', 'a primitive root', 'takah', 'TWOT - 2507', 'taw-kaw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to strew, i.e. encamp:--sit down.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Pual) to be led, be assembled<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning wholly dubious</OL><LI>(CLBL) (Pu) to lay down, recline</OL>'),
(8498, 'hnwkt', 'pass part of (08505)', 'tkuwnah', 'TWOT - 964e', 'tek-oo-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine passive participle of «08505»; adjustment, i.e. structure; by implication, equipage:--fashion, store.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>arrangement, preparation, fixed place<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>arrangement, disposition<LI>preparation<LI>fixed place</OL></OL>'),
(8499, 'hnwkt', 'T@kuwnah', 'tkuwnah', 'tek-oo-naw\'', 'tek-oo-naw\'', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>arrangement, preparation, fixed place, seat, place<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>arrangement, disposition<LI>preparation<LI>fixed place, seat, place</OL></OL>', 'from «03559»; or probably ident. with «08498»; something arranged or fixed, i.e. a place:--seat.', ''),
(8500, 'ykkt', 'probably of foreign derivation', 'tukkiy', 'TWOT - 2508', 'took-kee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or tuwkkiy {took-kee\'}; probably of foreign derivation; some imported creature, probably a peacock:--peacock.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>peacock, baboon, ape<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>peacock<LI>(TWOT) baboon, ape</OL></OL>'),
(8501, '$kt', 'from an unused root meaning to dissever, i.e. crush', 'takak', 'TWOT - 2509?', 'taw-kawk\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to dissever, i.e. crush:--deceitful.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>injury, oppression, oppressor</OL>'),
(8502, 'hlkt', 'from (03615)', 'tiklah', 'TWOT - 982e', 'tik-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03615»; completeness:--perfection.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>perfection, completion, completeness</OL>'),
(8503, 'tylkt', 'from (03615)', 'takliyth', 'TWOT - 982f', 'tak-leeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03615»; completion; by implication, an extremity:--end, perfect(-ion).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>end, perfection, consummation, completion, completeness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>end<LI>completeness</OL></OL>'),
(8504, 'tlkt', 'probably for (07827)', 'tkeleth', 'TWOT - 2510', 'tek-ay\'-leth', 'Noun Feminine', 'probably for «07827»; the cerulean mussel, i.e. the color (violet) obtained therefrom or stuff dyed therewith:--blue.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>violet, violet stuff<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>violet thread<LI>violet stuff or fabric</OL><LI>(TWOT) blue (covering spectrum from brilliant red through deep purple)</OL>'),
(8505, '!kt', 'a primitive root', 'takan', 'TWOT - 2511', 'taw-kan\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to balance, i.e. measure out (by weight or dimension); figuratively, arrange, equalize, through the idea of levelling (ment. estimate, test):--bear up, direct, be ((un-))equal, mete, ponder, tell, weigh.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to regulate, measure, estimate, ponder, balance, make even, level, weigh, be equal, be weighed out, test, prove<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) estimate (participle)<LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be estimated<LI>to be made even or right, be adjusted to the standard</OL><LI>(Piel) to weigh out, mete out<LI>(Pual)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be weighed out, be measured out<LI>measured out (participle)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8506, '!kt', 'from (08505)', 'token', 'TWOT - 2511a', 'to\'-ken', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08505»; a fixed quantity:--measure, tale.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>measurement, a measured amount</OL>'),
(8507, '!kt', 'the same as (08506)', 'Token', 'None', 'to\'-ken', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «08506»; Token, a place in Palestine:--Tochen.', 'Tochen = \"measurement\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Simeon until the time of David</OL>'),
(8508, 'tynkt', 'from (08506)', 'tokniyth', 'TWOT - 2511b', 'tok-neeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «08506»; admeasurement, i.e. consummation:--pattern, sum.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>measurement, pattern, proportion</OL>'),
(8509, '$yrkt', 'apparently from an unused root meaning to encompass', 'takriyk', 'TWOT - 1037a', 'tak-reek\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'apparently from an unused root meaning to encompass; a wrapper or robe:--garment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>robe</OL>'),
(8510, 'lt', 'by contraction from (08524)', 'tel', 'TWOT - 2513a', 'tale', 'Noun Masculine', 'by contraction from «08524»; a mound:--heap, × strength.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mound, heap, heap of ruins<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>mound (of ruin-heap of city)<LI>mound, hill (of elevation on which city stood)</OL></OL>'),
(8511, 'alt', 'a primitive root', 'tala\'', 'None', 'taw-law\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to suspend; figuratively (through hesitation) to be uncertain; by implication (of mental dependence) to habituate:--be bent, hang (in doubt).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Qal) to hang, hang to, cling to</OL>'),
(8512, 'byba lt', 'from (08510) and (024)', 'Tel', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «08510» and «024»; mound of green growth; Tel-Abib, a place in Chaldaea:--Tel-abib.', 'Tel-abib = \"mound of the flood\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in Babylon, the home of the prophet Ezekiel, located on the river Chebar which was probably a branch of the Euphrates</OL>'),
(8513, 'halt', 'from (03811)', 'tla\'ah', 'TWOT - 1066a', 'tel-aw-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03811»; distress:--travail, travel, trouble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>toil, hardship, distress, weariness</OL>'),
(8514, 'hbwalt', 'from (03851)', 'tal\'uwbah', 'TWOT - 1065a', 'tal-oo-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03851»; desiccation:--great drought.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>drought</OL>'),
(8515, 'rXXalt', 'of foreign derivation', 'Tla\'ssar', 'None', 'tel-as-sar\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Tlassar {tel-as-sar\'}; of foreign derivation; Telassar, a region of Assyria:--Telassar.', 'Telassar or Thelasar = \"Assyrian hill\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city conquered and held by the Assyrians located apparently in Mesopotamia</OL>'),
(8516, 'tXblt', 'from (03847)', 'talbosheth', 'TWOT - 1075c', 'tal-bo\'-sheth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «03847»; a garment:--clothing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>garment, clothing, raiment</OL>'),
(8517, 'glt', 'corresponding to (07950)', 'tlag', 'TWOT - 3057', 'tel-ag\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «07950»; snow:--snow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>snow</OL>'),
(8518, 'hlt', 'a primitive root', 'talah', 'TWOT - 2512', 'taw-law\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to suspend (especially to gibbet):--hang (up).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hang<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hang 1a</OL><LI>to hang up (any object) 1a<LI>to put to death by hanging<LI>(Niphal) to be hanged<LI>(Piel) to hang, hang up (for display)</OL></OL>'),
(8519, 'hnwlt', 'from (03885) in the sense of obstinacy', 'tluwnah', 'TWOT - 1097a', 'tel-oo-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or tlunnah {tel-oon-naw\'}; from «03885» in the sense of obstinacy; a grumbling:--murmuring.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>murmuring</OL>'),
(8520, 'xlt', 'probably from an unused root meaning to dissever', 'Telach', 'None', 'teh\'-lakh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'probably from an unused root meaning to dissever; breach; Telach, an Israelite:--Telah.', 'Telah = \"vigour\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a son of Ephraim</OL>'),
(8521, 'aXrx lt', 'from (08510) and the fem. of (02798)', 'Tel', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «08510» and the feminine of «02798»; mound of workmanship; Tel-Charsha, a place in Babylonia:--Tel-haresha, Tel-harsa.', 'Tel-harsa or Tel-haresha = \"mound of the deaf mute\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town of Babylon<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>probably located in the low country near the sea</OL></OL>'),
(8522, 'ylt', 'probably from (08518)', 'tliy', 'TWOT - 2512a', 'tel-ee\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from «08518»; a quiver (as slung):--quiver.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>quiver<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>quiver (with its arrows)<LI>quiver (as hanging from shoulder)</OL></OL>'),
(8523, 'ytylt', 'ordinal from (08532)', 'tliythay', 'TWOT - 3058c', 'tel-ee-thah\'-ee', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) or taltiy (Aramaic) {tal-tee\'}; ordinal from «08532»; third:--third.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>third<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>third (the ordinal number)</OL></OL>'),
(8524, 'llt', 'a primitive root', 'talal', 'TWOT - 2513', 'taw-lal\'', '', 'a primitive root; to pile up, i.e. elevate:--eminent. Compare «02048».', 'v (CLBL)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to exalt<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) eminent, exalted (participle) adj (BDB)</OL><LI>exalted, lofty</OL>'),
(8525, '~lt', 'from an unused root meaning to accumulate', 'telem', 'TWOT - 2515a', 'teh\'-lem', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to accumulate; a bank or terrace:--furrow, ridge.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>furrow</OL>'),
(8526, 'ymlt', 'from (08525)', 'Talmay', 'None', 'tal-mah\'-ee', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'from «08525»; ridged; Talmai, the name of a Canaanite and a Syrian:--Talmai.', 'Talmai = \"furrowed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the 3 sons of the giant Anak who were slain by the men of Judah<LI>son of Ammihud, king of Geshur, later king of Geshur himself, and father of Maacah, the mother of Absalom and wife of David</OL>'),
(8527, 'dymlt', 'from (03925)', 'talmiyd', 'TWOT - 1116c', 'tal-meed\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «03925»; a pupil:--scholar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>scholar</OL>'),
(8528, 'xlm lt', 'from (08510) and (04417)', 'Tel', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «08510» and «04417»; mound of salt; Tel-Melach, a place in Babylonia:--Tel-melah.', 'Tel-melah = \"mound of salt\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in Babylon from which some exiles of unknown parentage came; returned to Jerusalem with Zerubbabel</OL>'),
(8529, '[lt', 'a denominative from (08438)', 'tala`', 'TWOT - 2516c', 'taw-law\'', 'Verb', 'a denominative from «08438»; to crimson, i.e. dye that color:--X scarlet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Pual) to clad in scarlet, be wearing scarlet</OL>'),
(8530, 'hyplt', 'from an unused root meaning to tower', 'talpiyah', 'TWOT - 2517', 'tal-pee-yaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from an unused root meaning to tower; something tall, i.e. (plural collective) slenderness:--armoury.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>weapons, armoury, armaments<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning doubtful</OL></OL>'),
(8531, 'tlt', 'from (08532)', 'tlath', 'TWOT - 3058b', 'tel-ath\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from «08532»; a tertiary rank:--third.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>third, one of three, a third part</OL>'),
(8532, 'tlt', 'corresponding to (07969)', 'tlath', 'TWOT - 3058a', 'tel-awth\'', 'Noun', '(Aramaic) masculine tlathah (Aramaic) {tel-aw-thaw\'}; or tlatha  (Aramaic) {tel-aw-thaw\'}; corresponding to «07969»; three or third:--third, three.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>three<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>three (cardinal number)<LI>third (ordinal number)</OL></OL>'),
(8533, '!ytlt', 'mult of (08532)', 'tlathiyn', 'TWOT - 3058d', 'tel-aw-theen\'', 'Noun', '(Aramaic) mult. of «08532»; ten times three:--thirty.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thirty</OL>'),
(8534, 'ltlt', 'by reduplication, from (08524) through the idea of vibration', 'taltal', 'TWOT - 2513c', 'tal-tal\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'by reduplication, from «08524» through the idea of vibration; a trailing bough (as pendulous):--bushy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wavy, branchy (used of woman\'s hair - fig)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning uncertain</OL></OL>'),
(8535, '~t', 'from (08552)', 'tam', 'TWOT - 2522c', 'tawm', 'Adjective', 'from «08552»; complete; usually (morally) pious; specifically, gentle, dear:--coupled together, perfect, plain, undefiled, upright.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>perfect, complete<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>complete, perfect<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one who lacks nothing in physical strength, beauty, etc</OL><LI>sound, wholesome<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an ordinary, quiet sort of person</OL><LI>complete, morally innocent, having integrity<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one who is morally and ethically pure</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8536, '~t', 'corresponding to (08033)', 'tam', 'TWOT - 3059', 'tawm', 'Adverb', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «08033»; there:--X thence, there, ×  where.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>there</OL>'),
(8537, '~t', 'from (08552)', 'tom', 'TWOT - 2522a', 'tome', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08552»; completeness; figuratively, prosperity; usually (morally) innocence:--full, integrity, perfect(-ion), simplicity, upright(-ly, -ness), at a venture. See «08550».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>integrity, completeness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>completeness, fulness<LI>innocence, simplicity<LI>integrity</OL></OL>'),
(8538, 'hmmt', 'from (08537)', 'tummah', 'TWOT - 2522b', 'toom-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «08537»; innocence:--integrity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>integrity</OL>'),
(8539, 'hhmt', 'a primitive root', 'tamahh', 'TWOT - 2518', 'taw-mah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to be in consternation:--be amazed, be astonished, marvel(-lously), wonder.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be astounded, be stunned, be amazed, be dumbfounded<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to be astounded<LI>(Hithpael) to astonish yourself, be astounded, be astonished at one another</OL></OL>'),
(8540, 'hhmt', 'from a root corresponding to (08539)', 'tmahh', 'TWOT - 3060', 'tem-ah\'', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to «08539»; a miracle:--wonder.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wonder, miracle</OL>'),
(8541, '!whmmt', 'from (08539)', 'timmahown', 'TWOT - 2518a', 'tim-maw-hone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08539»; consternation:--astonishment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>astonishment, bewilderment, stupefaction</OL>'),
(8542, 'zwmmt', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Tammuwz', 'TWOT - 2519', 'tam-mooz\'', 'Proper Name', 'of uncertain derivation; Tammuz, a Phoenician deity:--Tammuz.', 'Tammuz = \"sprout of life\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Sumerian deity of food or vegetation</OL>'),
(8543, 'lwmt', 'probably for (0865)', 'tmowl', 'TWOT - 2521', 'tem-ole\'', 'Adverb', 'or tmol {tem-ole\'}; probably for «0865»; properly, ago, i.e. a (short or long) time since; especially yesterday, or (with «08032») day before yesterday:--+ before (-time), + these (three) days, + heretofore, + time past, yesterday.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>before, before that time, beforetime, heretofore, of late, of old, these days, time(s) past, yesterday, day before yesterday, recently, formerly<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>yesterday<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>recently, formerly (usual usage) (fig)</OL><LI>as formerly, so more recently<LI>from yesterday, already</OL></OL>'),
(8544, 'hnwmt', 'from (04327)', 'tmuwnah', 'TWOT - 1191b', 'tem-oo-naw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or tmunah {tem-oo-naw\'}; from «04327»; something portioned (i.e. fashioned) out, as a shape, i.e. (indefinitely) phantom, or (specifically) embodiment, or (figuratively) manifestation (of favor):--image, likeness, similitude.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>form, image, likeness, representation, semblance</OL>'),
(8545, 'hrwmt', 'from (04171)', 'tmuwrah', 'TWOT - 1164a', 'tem-oo-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04171»; barter, compensation:--(ex-)change(-ing), recompense, restitution.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that which is exchanged, exchange, substitute, recompense</OL>'),
(8546, 'htwmt', 'from (04191)', 'tmuwthah', 'TWOT - 1169c', 'tem-oo-thaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «04191»; execution (as a doom):--death, die.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>death</OL>'),
(8547, 'xmt', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Temach', 'None', 'teh\'-makh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; Temach, one of the Nethinim:--Tamah, Thamah.', 'Tamah or Thamah = \"laughter\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a head of a family of temple slaves who returned from exile with Zerubbabel</OL>');
INSERT INTO `hebrew_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(8548, 'dymt', 'from an unused root meaning to stretch', 'tamiyd', 'TWOT - 1157a', 'taw-meed\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to stretch; properly, continuance (as indefinite extension); but used only (attributively as adjective) constant (or adverbially, constantly); ellipt. the regular (daily) sacrifice:--alway(-s), continual (employment, -ly), daily, ((n-))ever(-more), perpetual.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>continuity, perpetuity, to stretch<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>continually, continuously (as adverb)<LI>continuity (subst)</OL></OL>'),
(8549, '~ymt', 'from (08552)', 'tamiym', 'TWOT - 2522d', 'taw-meem\'', 'Adjective', 'from «08552»; entire (literally, figuratively or morally); also (as noun) integrity, truth:--without blemish, complete, full, perfect, sincerely (-ity), sound, without spot, undefiled, upright(-ly), whole.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>complete, whole, entire, sound<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>complete, whole, entire<LI>whole, sound, healthful<LI>complete, entire (of time)<LI>sound, wholesome, unimpaired, innocent, having integrity<LI>what is complete or entirely in accord with truth and fact (neuter adj/subst)</OL></OL>'),
(8550, '~ymmt', 'pl. of (08537)', 'Tummiym', 'None', 'toom-meem\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'plural of «08537»; perfections, i.e. (techn.) one of the epithets of the objects in the high-priest\'s breastplate as an emblem of complete Truth:--Thummim.', 'Thummim = \"perfection\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>stones provided for the means of achieving a sacred lot<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used with the Urim, the will of God was revealed</OL></OL>'),
(8551, '$mt', 'a primitive root', 'tamak', 'TWOT - 2520', 'taw-mak\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to sustain; by implication, to obtain, keep fast; figuratively, to help, follow close:--(take, up-)hold (up), maintain, retain, stay (up).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to grasp, hold, support, attain, lay hold of, hold fast<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to grasp, lay hold of, attain<LI>to hold up, support<LI>to hold, keep<LI>to take hold of each other</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be seized, be held</OL></OL>'),
(8552, '~mt', 'a primitive root', 'tamam', 'TWOT - 2522', 'taw-mam\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to complete, in a good or a bad sense, literal, or figurative, transitive or intransitive (as follows):--accomplish, cease, be clean (pass-)ed, consume, have done, (come to an, have an, make an) end, fail, come to the full, be all gone, × be all here, be (make) perfect, be spent, sum, be (shew self) upright, be wasted, whole.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be complete, be finished, be at an end<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be finished, be completed 1a</OL><LI>completely, wholly, entirely (as auxiliary with verb)<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to be finished, come to an end, cease<LI>to be complete (of number)<LI>to be consumed, be exhausted, be spent<LI>to be finished, be consumed, be destroyed<LI>to be complete, be sound, be unimpaired, be upright (ethically)<LI>to complete, finish<LI>to be completely crossed over</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be consumed<LI>(Hiphil)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to finish, complete, perfect<LI>to finish, cease doing, leave off doing<LI>to complete, sum up, make whole<LI>to destroy (uncleanness)<LI>to make sound</OL><LI>(Hithpael) to deal in integrity, act uprightly</OL></OL>'),
(8553, 'hnmt', 'from (04487)', 'Timnah', 'None', 'tim-naw\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «04487»; a portion assigned; Timnah, the name of two places in Palestine:--Timnah, Timnath, Thimnathah.', 'Timnath or Timnah or Thimnathah = \"portion\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town on the northern boundary of Judah later assigned to Dan<LI>a town in the hill country of Judah</OL>'),
(8554, 'ynmt', 'patrial from (08553)', 'Timniy', 'None', 'tim-nee\'', 'Adjective', 'patrial from «08553»; a Timnite or inhabitant of Timnah:--Timnite.', 'Timnite = \"thou wilt number: a portion\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inhabitant of Timnath or Timnah or Thimnathah</OL>'),
(8555, '[nmt', 'from (04513)', 'Timna`', 'None', 'tim-naw\'', '', 'from «04513»; restraint; Timna, the name of two Edomites:--Timna, Timnah.', 'Timna or Timnah = \"restrained\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a chief or duke of Esau and of Edom n pr f<LI>the concubine of Eliphaz, the son of Esau<LI>daughter of Seir the Horite and sister of Lotan</OL>'),
(8556, 'orx tnmt', 'from (08553) and (02775)', 'Timnath', 'None', '', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Timnath Cerach {tim-nath seh\'-rakh}; from «08553» and «02775»; portion of (the) sun; Timnath-Cheres, a place in Palestine:--Timnath-heres, Timnath-serah.', 'Timnath-heres or Timnath-serah = \"portion of the sun\" or \"abundant portion\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city given to Joshua as a inheritance in the mountains of Ephraim on the north of the hill of Gaash where he was buried</OL>'),
(8557, 'omt', 'from (04529)', 'temec', 'TWOT - 1223c', 'teh\'-mes', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04529»; liquefaction, i.e. disappearance:--melt.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dissolving, melting, melting (away)</OL>'),
(8558, 'rmt', 'from an unused root meaning to be erect', 'tamar', 'TWOT - 2523', 'taw-mawr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root meaning to be erect; a palm tree:--palm (tree).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>palm tree, date palm</OL>'),
(8559, 'rmt', 'the same as (08558)', 'Tamar', 'None', 'taw-mawr\'', '', 'the same as «08558»; Tamar, the name of three women and a place:--Tamar.', 'Tamar = \"palm-tree\" n pr f<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>widow of Er, the son of Judah; fiancee of Shelah, another son of Judah; wife of Judah and mother of Pharez and Zerah<LI>daughter of David by Maacah, sister of Absalom, and rape victim of Amnon her half brother, another son of David<LI>daughter of Absalom n pr loc<LI>a place on the southern border of Gad</OL>'),
(8560, 'rmt', 'from the same root as (08558)', 'tomer', 'TWOT - 2523a', 'to\'-mer', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same root as «08558»; a palm trunk:--palm tree.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>palm tree, post, column</OL>'),
(8561, 'rmmt', 'from the same root as (08558)', 'timmor', 'TWOT - 2523c', 'tim-more\'', 'Noun Feminine', '(plural o or (feminine) timmorah (singular and plural) {tim-mo-raw\'}; from the same root as «08558»; (arch.) a palm-like pilaster (i.e. umbellate):--palm tree.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>palm tree figure (as ornament)</OL>'),
(8562, 'qwrmt', 'from (04838)', 'tamruwq', 'TWOT - 1246b', 'tam-rook\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or tamruq {tam-rook\'}; or tamriyq {tam-reek\'}; from «04838»; properly, a scouring, i.e. soap or perfumery for the bath; figuratively, a detergent:--X cleanse, (thing for) purification(-fying).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a scraping, rubbing<LI>(CLBL) remedy (for an injury)</OL>'),
(8563, 'rwrmt', 'from (04843)', 'tamruwr', 'TWOT - 1248L', 'tam-roor\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «04843»; bitterness (plural as collective):--X most bitter(-ly).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bitterness</OL>'),
(8564, 'rwrmt', 'from the same root as (08558)', 'tamruwr', 'TWOT - 2523e', 'tam-roor\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same root as «08558»; an erection, i.e. pillar (probably for a guide-board):--high heap.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>guideposts, markers, signposts, high heap<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning doubtful</OL></OL>'),
(8565, '!t', 'from an unused root probably meaning to elongate', 'tan', 'TWOT - 2528a', 'tan', 'Noun Masculine', 'from an unused root probably meaning to elongate; a monster (as preternaturally formed), i.e. a sea-serpent (or other huge marine animal); also a jackal (or other hideous land animal):--dragon, whale. Compare «08577».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dragon, maybe the extinct dinosaur the plesiosaurus, whale</OL>'),
(8566, 'hnt', 'a primitive root', 'tanah', 'TWOT - 2524', 'taw-naw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to present (a mercenary inducement), i.e. bargain with (a harlot):--hire.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hire<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to hire<LI>(Hiphil) to hire (a prostitute), give amorous favours</OL></OL>'),
(8567, 'hnt', 'a primitive root [identical with (08566) through the idea of attributing honour]', 'tanah', 'TWOT - 2525', 'taw-naw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root (identical with «08566» through the idea of attributing honor); to ascribe (praise), i.e. celebrate, commemorate:--lament, rehearse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Piel) to recount, rehearse, tell again</OL>'),
(8568, 'hnnt', 'probably fem. of (08565)', 'tannah', 'TWOT - 2528b', 'tan-naw\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably feminine of «08565»; a female jackal:--dragon.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>habitations, jackals, (TWOT) dragon, (TWOT) sea monster<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning uncertain</OL></OL>'),
(8569, 'hawnt', 'from (05106)', 'tnuw\'ah', 'TWOT - 1317a', 'ten-oo-aw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05106»; alienation; by implication, enmity:--breach of promise, occasion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>opposition, alienation, enmity</OL>'),
(8570, 'hbwnt', 'from (05107)', 'tnuwbah', 'TWOT - 1318c', 'ten-oo-baw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05107»; produce:--fruit, increase.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fruit, produce</OL>'),
(8571, '$wnt', 'perhaps from the same as (0594) through the idea of protraction', 'tnuwk', 'TWOT - 2527a', 'ten-ook\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'perhaps from the same as «0594» through the idea of protraction; a pinnacle, i.e. extremity:--tip.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>tip, lobe (of ear)</OL>'),
(8572, 'hmwnt', 'from (05123)', 'tnuwmah', 'TWOT - 1325b', 'ten-oo-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05123»; drowsiness, i.e. sleep:--slumber(-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>slumber, slumberings, sleep</OL>'),
(8573, 'hpwnt', 'from (05130)', 'tnuwphah', 'TWOT - 1330b', 'ten-oo-faw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05130»; a brandishing (in threat); by implication, tumult; specifically, the official undulation of sacrificial offerings:--offering, shaking, wave (offering).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>swinging, waving, wave offering, offering<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a swinging, brandishing<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of God\'s hand, weapons</OL><LI>waving, wave-offering (technical term of sacrifice)<LI>offering (of gold or brass)</OL></OL>'),
(8574, 'rwnnt', 'from (05216)', 'tannuwr', 'TWOT - 2526', 'tan-noor\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05216»; a fire-pot:--furnace, oven.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>furnace, oven, fire-pot, (portable) stove<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>for cooking<LI>of God\'s wrath, His furnace (fig)<LI>of hunger, desire for evil<LI>fire-pot</OL></OL>'),
(8575, '~wxnt', 'from (05162)', 'tanchuwm', 'TWOT - 1344d', 'tan-khoom\'', 'Noun', 'or tanchum {tan-khoom\'}; and (feminine) tanchuwmah {tan-khoo-maw\'}; from «05162»; compassion, solace:--comfort, consolation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>consolation(s)</OL>'),
(8576, 'tmxnt', 'for (08575) (fem.)', 'Tanchumeth', 'None', 'tan-khoo\'-meth', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'for «08575» (feminine); Tanchumeth, an Israelite:--Tanhumeth.', 'Tanhumeth = \"consolation\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Seraiah, a leader who joined Gedaliah after Jerusalem\'s fall</OL>'),
(8577, '!ynnt', 'intensive from the same as (08565)', 'tanniyn', 'TWOT - 2528b', 'tan-neen\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or tanniym (Ezek. 29:3) {tan-neem\'}; intensive from the same as «08565»; a marine or land monster, i.e. sea-serpent or jackal:--dragon, sea-monster, serpent, whale.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dragon, serpent, sea monster<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>dragon or dinosaur<LI>sea or river monster<LI>serpent, venomous snake</OL></OL>'),
(8578, '!ynt', 'corresponding to (08147)', 'tinyan', 'TWOT - 3061a', 'tin-yawn\'', 'Adjective', '(Aramaic) corresponding to «08147»; second:--second.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>second</OL>'),
(8579, 'twnynt', 'from (08578)', 'tinyanuwth', 'TWOT - 3061b', 'tin-yaw-nooth\'', 'Adverb', '(Aramaic) from «08578»; a second time:--again.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the second time, again</OL>'),
(8580, 'tmXnt', 'from (05395)', 'tanshemeth', 'TWOT - 1433b', 'tan-sheh\'-meth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05395»; properly, a hard breather, i.e. the name of two unclean creatures, a lizard and a bird (both perhaps from changing color through their irascibility), probably the tree-toad and the water-hen:--mole, swan.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an unclean animal of some kind<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>an unclean bird<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>perhaps the ibis, water-hen, species of owl, barn owl</OL><LI>an unclean lizard<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>perhaps the chameleon</OL><LI>perhaps an extinct lizard or bird, exact meaning unknown</OL></OL>'),
(8581, 'b[t', 'a primitive root', 'ta`ab', 'TWOT - 2530', 'taw-ab\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to loathe, i.e. (morally) detest:--(make to be) abhor(-red), (be, commit more, do) abominable(-y), ×  utterly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to abhor, be abominable, do abominably<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Niphal) to be abhorred, be detested<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in the ritual sense<LI>in the ethical sense</OL><LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to loathe, abhor, regard as an abomination 1b</OL><LI>in the ritual sense 1b<LI>in the ethical sense<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>to cause to be an abomination</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to make abominable, do abominably<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in the ritual sense<LI>in the ethical sense</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8582, 'h[t', 'a primitive root', 'ta`ah', 'TWOT - 2531', 'taw-aw\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to vacillate, i.e. reel or stray (literally or figuratively); also causative of both:--(cause to) go astray, deceive, dissemble, (cause to, make to) err, pant, seduce, (make to) stagger, (cause to) wander, be out of the way.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to err, wander, go astray, stagger<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to err<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wander about (physically)<LI>of intoxication<LI>of sin (ethically)<LI>wandering (of the mind)</OL><LI>(Niphal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be made to wander about, be made to stagger (drunkard)<LI>to be led astray (ethically)</OL><LI>(Hiphil) to cause to wander<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to wander about (physically)<LI>to cause to wander (of intoxication)<LI>to cause to err, mislead (mentally and morally)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8583, 'w[t', 'from (08582)', 'To`uw', 'None', 'to\'-oo', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'or Tomiy {to\'-ee}; from «08582»; error, Tou or Toi, a Syrian king:--Toi, Tou.', 'Toi or Tou = \"wander\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>king of Hamath in the time of David</OL>'),
(8584, 'hdw[t', 'from (05749)', 't`uwdah', 'TWOT - 1576g', 'teh-oo-daw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05749»; attestation, i.e. a precept, usage:--testimony.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>testimony, attestation, confirmation<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>testimony, (prophetic) injunction<LI>attestation</OL></OL>'),
(8585, 'hl[t', 'from (05927)', 't`alah', 'TWOT - 1624n,1624o', 'teh-aw-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05927»; a channel (into which water is raised for irrigation); also a bandage or plaster (as placed upon a wound):--conduit, cured, healing, little river, trench, watercourse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>conduit, water course, trench<LI>healing (of new flesh and skin forming over wound)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(CLBL) bandage, plaister (for healing of wound)</OL></OL>'),
(8586, 'lwl[t', 'from (05953)', 'ta`aluwl', 'TWOT - 1627f', 'tah-al-ool\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05953»; caprice (as a fit coming on), i.e. vexation; concretely a tyrant:--babe, delusion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wantonness, caprice, vexation</OL>'),
(8587, 'hmml[t', 'from (05956)', 'ta`alummah', 'TWOT - 1629a', 'tah-al-oom-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «05956»; a secret:--thing that is hid, secret.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hidden thing, secret, that which is hidden</OL>'),
(8588, 'gwn[t', 'from (06026)', 'ta`anuwg', 'TWOT - 1648c', 'tah-an-oog\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'or taanug {tah-an-oog\'}; and (feminine) taeanugah {tah-ah-oog-aw\'}; from «06026»; luxury:--delicate, delight, pleasant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>daintiness, luxury, exquisite delight, pleasantness, delight, comfort<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>luxury<LI>dainty<LI>delight</OL></OL>'),
(8589, 'tyn[t', 'from (06031)', 'ta`aniyth', 'TWOT - 1652f', 'tah-an-eeth\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06031»; affliction (of self), i.e. fasting:--heaviness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>humiliation (by fasting), ascetic practice of fasting</OL>'),
(8590, '$n[t', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Ta`anak', 'None', 'tah-an-awk\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'or Tanak {tah-nawk\'}; of uncertain derivation; Taanak or Tanak, a place in Palestine:--Taanach, Tanach.', 'Taanach or Tanach = \"sandy\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an ancient Canaanite city conquered by Joshua and allotted to the half tribe of Manasseh although in the territory of Issachar; given to the Kohathite Levites; located on the west of the Jordan and near the waters of Megiddo</OL>'),
(8591, '[[t', 'a primitive root', 'ta`a`', 'TWOT - 2532', 'taw-ah\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to cheat; by analogy, to maltreat:--deceive, misuse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to deceive, misuse<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Pilpel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be a mocker, mock<LI>mocker (subst)</OL><LI>(Hithpalpel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to ridicule<LI>mocking (participle)</OL></OL></OL>'),
