(8597, 'hrapt', 'from (06286)', 'tiph\'arah', 'TWOT - 1726b', 'tif-aw-raw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'or tiphereth {tif-eh\'-reth}; from «06286»; ornament (abstractly or concretely, literally or figuratively):--beauty(- iful), bravery, comely, fair, glory(-ious), hono; ornament (abstractly or concretely, literally or figuratively):--beauty(-iful), bravery, comely, fair, glory(-ious), honour, majesty.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>beauty, splendour, glory<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>beauty, finery (of garments, jewels)<LI>glory<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of rank, renown<LI>as attribute of God</OL><LI>honour (or nation Israel)<LI>glorying, boasting (of individual)</OL></OL>'),
(8598, 'xwppt', 'from (05301)', 'tappuwach', 'TWOT - 1390c', 'tap-poo\'-akh', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «05301»; an apple (from its fragrance), i.e. the fruit or the tree (probably includ. others of the pome order, as the quince, the orange, etc.):--apple (tree). See also «01054».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>apple, apple tree<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>apple tree<LI>apples</OL></OL>'),
(8599, 'xwppt', 'the same as (08598)', 'Tappuwach', 'None', 'tap-poo\'-akh', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «08598»; Tappuach, the name of two places in Palestine, also of an Israelite:--Tappuah.', 'Tappuah = \"the apple city\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Judaite of the family of Caleb, son of Hebron n pr loc<LI>a town in the lowland of Judah<LI>a town on the border in Ephraim<LI>a territory within the boundaries of Manasseh</OL>'),
(8600, 'hcwpt', 'from (06327)', 'tphowtsah', 'TWOT - 1745b', 'tef-o-tsaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06327»; a dispersal:--dispersion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dispersion</OL>'),
(8601, '!ypt', 'from (0644)', 'tuphiyn', 'TWOT - 2533', 'too-feen\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «0644»; cookery, i.e. (concretely) a cake:--baked piece.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>broken piece, baked pieces, pieces cooked<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning dubious</OL></OL>'),
(8602, 'lpt', 'from an unused root meaning to smear', 'taphel', 'TWOT - 2534a,2535a', 'taw-fale\'', '', 'from an unused root meaning to smear; plaster (as gummy) or slime; (figuratively) frivolity:--foolish things, unsavoury, untempered.', 'adj<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>foolish, insipid<LI>(BDB) tasteless, unseasoned n m<LI>whitewash<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>meaning uncertain</OL></OL>'),
(8603, 'lpt', 'from the same as (08602)', 'Tophel', 'None', 'to\'-fel', 'Proper Name Location', 'from the same as «08602»; quagmire; Tophel, a place near the Desert:--Tophel.', 'Tophel = \"white\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place southeast of the Dead Sea and in or near the \'Arabah\'</OL>'),
