(8605, 'hllpt', 'from (06419)', 'tphillah', 'TWOT - 1776a', 'tef-il-law\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06419»; intercession, supplication; by implication, a hymn:--prayer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>prayer<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>prayer<LI>pray a prayer<LI>house of prayer<LI>hear prayer<LI>in Ps titles (of poetic or liturgical prayer)</OL></OL>'),
(8606, 'tclpt', 'from (06426)', 'tiphletseth', 'TWOT - 1778c', 'tif-leh\'-tseth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06426»; fearfulness:--terrible.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shuddering, horror</OL>'),
(8607, 'xopt', 'from (06452)', 'Tiphcach', 'None', 'tif-sakh\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'from «06452»; ford; Tiphsach, a place in Mesopotamia:--Tipsah.', 'Tiphsah = \"cross over\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place at the northeast limit of Solomon\'s empire; located on the Euphrates river<LI>a place in the northern kingdom of Israel which king Menahem attacked and where he ripped open all the pregnant women<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>might be the same as 1</OL></OL>'),
(8608, '@pt', 'a primitive root', 'taphaph', 'TWOT - 2536', 'taw-faf\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to drum, i.e. play (as) on the tambourine:--taber, play with timbrels.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to play or sound the timbrel, beat, play upon, drum (on a timbrel or other object)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) playing (participle)<LI>(Poel) beating (participle)</OL></OL>'),
(8609, 'rpt', 'a primitive root', 'taphar', 'TWOT - 2537', 'taw-far\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to sew:--(women that) sew (together).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sew together<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal) to sew, sew together<LI>(Piel)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sew<LI>sewing (participle)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(8610, 'Xpt', 'a primitive root', 'taphas', 'TWOT - 2538', 'taw-fas\'', 'Verb', 'a primitive root; to manipulate, i.e. seize; chiefly to capture, wield, specifically, to overlay; figuratively, to use unwarrantably:--catch, handle, (lay, take) hold (on, over), stop, × surely, surprise, take.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to catch, handle, lay hold, take hold of, seize, wield<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(Qal)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lay hold of, seize, arrest, catch<LI>to grasp (in order to) wield, wield, use skilfully</OL><LI>(Niphal) to be seized, be arrested, be caught, be taken, captured<LI>(Piel) to catch, grasp (with the hands)</OL></OL>'),
(8611, 'tpt', 'from the base of (08608)', 'topheth', 'TWOT - 2499a', 'to\'-feth', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the base of «08608»; a smiting, i.e. (figuratively) contempt:--tabret.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>act of spitting, spit</OL>'),
(8612, 'tpt', 'the same as (08611)', 'Topheth', 'TWOT - 2539', 'to\'-feth', 'Proper Name Location', 'the same as «08611»; Topheth, a place near Jerusalem:--Tophet, Topheth.', 'Tophet or Topheth = \"place of fire\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in the southeast end of the valley of the son of Hinnom south of Jerusalem. Same as 08613</OL>'),
(8613, 'htpt', 'probably a form of (08612)', 'Tophteh', 'None', 'tof-teh\'', 'Proper Name Location', 'probably a form of «08612»; Tophteh, a place of cremation:--Tophet.', 'Tophet = \"place of fire\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place in the southeast end of the valley of the son of Hinnom south of Jerusalem<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>same as 8612</OL></OL>'),
(8614, 'ytpt', 'perhaps from (08199)', 'tiphtay', 'TWOT - 3062', 'tif-tah\'-ee', 'Noun Masculine', '(Aramaic) perhaps from «08199»; judicial, i.e. a lawyer:--sheriff.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>magistrate<LI>(BDB) name of a magistrate</OL>'),
(8615, 'hwqt', 'from (06960)', 'tiqvah', 'TWOT - 1994d,1994e', 'tik-vaw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06960»; literally, a cord (as an attachment (compare «06961»)); figuratively, expectancy:--expectation ((-ted)), hope, live, thing that I long for.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cord<LI>hope, expectation<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>hope<LI>ground of hope<LI>things hoped for, outcome</OL></OL>'),
(8616, 'hwqt', 'the same as (08615)', 'Tiqvah', 'None', 'tik-vaw\'', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'the same as «08615»; Tikvah, the name of two Israelites:--Tikvah.', 'Tikvath or Tikvah = \"hope\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>father of Shallum, the husband of the prophetess Huldah in the time of king Josiah of Judah<LI>father of Tikvah in the time of Ezra</OL>'),
(8617, 'hmwqt', 'from (06965)', 'tquwmah', 'TWOT - 1999g', 'tek-oo-maw\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «06965»; resistfulness:--power to stand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>standing, ability or power to stand</OL>'),
(8618, '~mwqt', 'from (06965)', 'tqowmem', 'TWOT - 1999?', 'tek-o-mame\'', 'Verb Neuter', 'from «06965»; an opponent:--rise up against.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(Hithpol) a rising against (participle)</OL>'),
(8619, '[wqt', 'from (08628) (in the musical sense)', 'taqowa`', 'TWOT - 2541b', 'taw-ko\'-ah', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «08628» (in the musical sense); a trumpet:--trumpet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a blast-(wind)-instrument, trumpet</OL>'),
(8620, '[wqt', 'a form of (08619)', 'Tqowa`', 'None', 'tek-o\'-ah', 'Proper Name Masculine', 'a form of «08619»; Tekoa, a place in Palestine:--Tekoa, Tekoah.', 'Tekoa or Tekoah = \"a stockade\" n pr m<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Judaite, son of Ashur and grandson of Hezron n pr loc<LI>a town in the hill country of Judah near Hebron built by king Rehoboam of Judah; birthplace of Amos<LI>a wilderness area where king Jehoshaphat of Judah defeated the people of Moab, Ammon, and Mount Seir</OL>'),
